 using reusable Razor components.\n* *Healthcare Security & Compliance:* Leverage data access layers and authentication protocols that adhere to strict healthcare compliance requirements (e.g., HIPAA) and data security standards.\n* *System Integration:* Connect our custom Blazor applications with third-party systems (as needed) and SQL databases to create a unified flow of data. Leverage CI/CD pipelines to ensure optimal performance.\n* *Cross-Functional Collaboration:* Work closely with the product manager and operational stakeholders to translate complex healthcare business needs into elegant technical solutions.\n\n*Requirements*\n\n* *Experience:* 5+ years of professional software development experience using the Microsoft .NET ecosystem.\n* *Blazor Expertise:* Proven, hands-on experience building production applications with Blazor and migrating older architectures to modern, component-based frameworks.\n* *Backend Mastery:* Strong proficiency in C#, ASP.NET Core Web API, Entity Framework Core, and modern SQL database design.\n* *Web Technologies:* Fluency in HTML5, CSS3/Bootstrap, and an understanding of JavaScript interoperability within Blazor applications.\n* *Startup Mentality:* Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, ambiguous environment, taking ownership of projects from conception to deployment.\n\n*The Impact You Will Make*\n\nBy modernizing our platform, you are doing more than just writing code; you are building the technological foundation that allows our startup to scale its mission. Your innovations will directly reduce friction in healthcare operations, allowing our users to focus on what matters most: delivering exceptional care and improving patient outcomes.\n\nMust be able to pass a criminal background check as well as a drug test.\n\nJob Types: Full-time, Contract\n\nPay: $40.00 - $55.00 per hour\n\nBenefits:\n* 401(k)\n\n\n\nApplication Question(s):\n* I confirm that I do not require sponsorship now, or EVER, to work legally in the United States. Please answer Yes if this is true. \n\nLocation:\n* Florida (Required)\n\nWork Location: Remote','2026-05-07 01:36:56','open',0,'Mango Chamba, LLC','https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5e01c590308e5452','scraped','Just posted'),(2284,NULL,'job','Front End Software Engineer','Full-time','Annapolis Junction, MD 20701',NULL,'',162000.00,'$142,000 - $182,000 a year','Software Engineer, AI-Assisted CNO Development\n\nMake an Impact Where It Matters Most\n\nAt Intelliforce, we build mission technology that helps operators move faster and make better decisions in complex environments. In this role, you will support CNO development across multiple teams by designing, developing, and integrating tools that improve how mission software gets built and used. You will work closely with stakeholders and engineers to create AI and ML-assisted workflows that solve real reverse engineering and development challenges in the field.\n\nWhat Makes This Opportunity Stand Out\n\nThis role gives you the chance to shape how CNO developers work across the mission. You will lead projects from concept through deployment, build AI-assisted workflows, and help teams turn difficult operational problems into practical technical solutions. The work blends software engineering, stakeholder engagement, workflow design, and applied AI, so you stay close to both the mission and the engineers doing the work.\n\nAt Intelliforce, your work is visible and your ideas matter. Because we support prime programs, our teams stay close to meaningful mission work with real momentum. Because we are a small business, leadership is accessible, communication is direct, and strong engineering gets noticed. Add in long-term stability, strong benefits, and a people-first culture, and this becomes more than another software role. It is a chance to improve how mission tools are built, tested, and delivered across the CNO space.\n\nHere’s What Your Day-to-Day Could Include\n\n• Lead projects from inception to delivery in the CNO domain, including problem decomposition, design, development, deployment, and maintenance\n• Work with mission stakeholders to gather requirements and turn them into practical solutions\n• Collaborate with software engineers to test workflows, identify issues, and recommend fixes\n• Partner with stakeholders to understand and solve real-world reverse engineering challenges\n• Build and integrate tools that improve development workflows across multiple mission teams\n• Apply AI and ML technologies to support smarter, faster engineering outcomes\n• Navigate obstacles, adapt quickly, and keep solutions moving forward\n\nMinimum Qualifications\n\n• Clearance: Top Secret Clearance with Full Scope Polygraph, must be active. We do not have the ability to sponsor clearances\n• Citizenship: Must be a U.S. Citizen. We cannot sponsor visas\n• 12 years of relevant experience with a Bachelor’s degree in a technical discipline\n• Four additional years of relevant experience may be substituted in place of a Bachelor’s degree\n\nRequired Skills\n\n• Production-grade software development experience in Python\n• Experience in the CNO developer domain building tools for operational use\n• Experience with development of AI systems and customization of AI models\n• Practical experience with platforms for processing Agency data sets\n• Experience with software source control, including Git\n• Experience with Atlassian tools including Jira and Confluence\n• Experience interacting with stakeholders to gather requirements\n• Knowledge of Python or similar scripting languages\n\nDesired Skills\n\n• Experience working as a lead for a development team\n• Practical experience in one or more artificial intelligence domains such as intelligent systems, autonomy, planning, LLMs, or LLM training\n• Knowledge of end-to-end SIGINT collection and analysis systems\n• Experience with production CNO capabilities and operations\n• Familiarity with cloud computing technologies such as AWS, Docker, 