n impact early.\n\nHere’s What Your Day-to-Day Could Include\n\n• Turn vague or high-level requirements into actionable software by working directly with customers and stakeholders\n• Build prototypes, gather feedback, and iterate quickly based on what users actually need\n• Work with senior developers to review code, understand architectural decisions, and grow your technical judgment\n• Use AI-assisted development tools to speed up learning, prototyping, and delivery\n• Build full-stack solutions that combine scripts, user interfaces, backend logic, and integrated data sources\n• Support mission awareness and workflow automation through practical, user-focused tools\n\nMinimum Qualifications\n\n• Clearance: Top Secret Clearance with Full Scope Polygraph, must be active. We do not have the ability to sponsor clearances\n• Citizenship: Must be a U.S. Citizen. We cannot sponsor visas\n• 3 years of relevant experience with a Bachelor’s degree in a technical discipline\n• Four additional years of relevant experience may be substituted in place of a Bachelor’s degree\n\nRequired Skills\n\n• Development experience with Python and JavaScript\n• Comfort working through ambiguity and adapting to changing requirements\n• Strong communication skills and the ability to ask good questions and work directly with users\n• Comfort navigating Linux environments\n• Experience using Git for day-to-day development workflows\n\nDesired Skills\n\n• Hands-on experience with agentic AI frameworks or building tools using LLMs\n• Familiarity with containerization tools such as Docker\n• Exposure to or interest in SIGINT or CNO mission spaces\n\nCompensation Range: $203,000.00 - $249,000.00\n*The salary range provided reflects an estimate based on current market trends and may be adjusted based on factors such as the candidate\'s experience, skills, and qualifications. The final offer will be tailored after a thorough evaluation of the candidate’s background and suitability for the role. Ple