* Des Weiteren hast du gute Kenntnisse im Konfigurationsmanagement (Visual Studio, TFS, Git, Visual Studio Code, Azure DevOps) und in objektorientierter Analyse und Design (Design Patterns)\n* Idealerweise kennst du Frameworks wie z.B. CUDA, Google Test, TensorFlow\n* Sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse runden dein Profil ab\n\n*Deine Benefits*\n\n* Durch flexible Arbeitszeiten, Möglichkeiten für Homeoffice und Teilzeitmodelle unterstützen wir Deine Work-Life-Balance und die Vereinbarkeit von Familie und Beruf\n* Mit dem Schulungsangebot unserer sepp.med Akademie und individueller Weiterbildung bringen wir Dich und Dein fachliches Know-How weiter, denn aktive Personalentwicklung ist uns wichtig\n* Dein Wohlbefinden und Deine Fitness unterstützen wir durch Aktionen zur Gesundheitsförderung, Sportprogramme und eine kostenlose Mitgliedschaft im Fitnessstudio\n* Lerne Deine Kollegen ganz persönlich kennen und erlebe das Wir-Gefühl von sepp.med bei unseren Teamevents, Feiern und firmenweiten Aktivitäten\n* Wir zahlen attraktive Gehälter, Urlaubs- und Weihnachtsgeld, Prämien und wir honorieren langjährige Firmenzugehörigkeit\n* Mit unseren betrieblichen Sozialleistungen unterstützen wir Deine persönliche Vorsorge und soziale Absicherung\n* Offene Kommunikation und persönlicher Dialog auf allen Ebenen sind uns wichtig, denn Deine Anliegen und Deine Beteiligung an unserer Strategieentwicklung liegen uns am Herzen\n* Du kannst Dich spielerisch mit Kollegen messen und Spaß haben oder ernsthaft austauschen – dafür veranstalten wir Engineering Camps, Hackathons und Expertenrunden\n\nWir freuen uns sehr über deine Bewerbung. Bei Fragen erreichst du unsere Ansprechpartner Frau Baigger & Herrn Alef per Telefon unter der 09195-931-186/-261.\n\nsepp.med gmbh - Gewerbering 9 - 91341 Röttenbach\n\nArt der Stelle: Festanstellung\n\nLeistungen:\n* Betriebliche Altersvorsorge\n* Betriebliche Weiterbildung\n* Firmenevents\n* Firmenhandy\n* Firmenwagen\n* Flexible Arbeitszeiten\n* Homeoffice-Möglichkeit\n* Kostenlose Getränke\n\n\n\nBewerbungsfrage(n):\n* Sind Sie reisebereit oder bereit umzuziehen?\n* Was ist Ihre Gehaltsvorstellung?\n* Was ist Ihr frühestmögliches Eintrittsdatum?\n* Was ist Ihre bevorzugte Arbeitsform? (remote/hybrid/vor-ort)\n\nSprache:\n* Deutsch (Erforderlich)\n\nArbeitsort: Vor Ort','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'sepp.med GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=42cfd03d8fd53f36','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2342,NULL,'job','Senior Softwareentwickler C# m/w/d','Festanstellung','91522 Ansbach',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Software-Entwicklung\n\nForchheim\n\nVollzeit\n\nUnbefristet\n\n*Zeit für deinen nächsten Karriereschritt bei sepp.med *\n\nWir entwickeln in enger Zusammenarbeit mit unseren Kunden weltweit führende Lösungen zur Bildgebung und Diagnose. Als Key Supplier treiben wir die Digitalisierung durch moderne Produkt-, Web- und Cloud-Lösungen voran. Dabei setzen wir auf AI, Machine Learning, Agilität und ein innovatives Tech-Stack. Sei Teil dieses wegweisenden Projektes und gestalte die Medizintechnik der Zukunft aktiv mit!\n\n*Deine Aufgaben - C#-Entwicklung mit Weitblick *\n\n* *Pflege und Erweiterung* – mit deiner Entwicklungserfahrung arbeitest du an der großen Codebasis einer robusten medizinischen Software in modernen DevOps-Umgebungen.\n* *Modernisierung und Migration* – zusammen mit deinem agilen Team bist du verantwortlich für die Analyse und Weiterentwicklung bestehender medizinischer Anwendungen unter C# und .NET.\n* *Konzepte & Architektur gestalten* – du erarbeitest aktiv einen fachlichen Zugang zur bestehenden Software und ihrer Architektur, um neue Designs zu erarbeiten, vorzuschlagen, zu prüfen und zu implementieren.\n* *Dein Know-how erweitern* – du hältst dein Wissen stets aktuell – unser Team unterstützt dich dabei.\n\n*Das bringst du mit - Dein Erfolgsprofil *\n\n* *Abgeschlossenes Studium im Bereich Informatik* – du hast einen Bachelor, Master oder ein Diplom in Informatik oder eine vergleichbare Qualifikation, z. B. Berufsausbildung oder verwandter Studiengang.\n* *C#/.NET Know-how* – in der Softwareentwicklung mit dem .NET Framework bzw. .NET 8 hast du mehrjährige Erfahrung und beherrschst Testautomatisierung auf mehreren Abstraktionsebenen.\n* *Clean Code & Design* – du arbeitest objektorientiert, nutzt Clean Code-Prinzipien und folgst SOLID.\n* *Tool-Kompetenz & Frameworks* – idealerweise hast du Erfahrung mit Azure DevOps, TFS, git, Visual Studio (Code) und GitHub Copilot\n* *Teamgeist & Initiative* – du bringst dich gerne ein und möchtest gemeinsam mit deinem Team wachsen.\n* *Sprachlich fit* – du verfügst über gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse.\n\n*Be you with us! – Deine Vorteile bei sepp.med*\n\n* Flexible Arbeitsmodelle & Work-Life-Balance – mit Homeoffice, Teilzeitoptionen und flexiblen Zeiten gestaltest du deinen Alltag passend zu deinem Leben.\n* Weiterbildung & Entwicklung – über unsere sepp.med Akademie oder individuell – wir fördern dich gezielt.\n* Gesundheit & Fitness – mit Sportangeboten, Gesundheitsaktionen und kostenloser Fitnessstudio-Mitgliedschaft bleibst du fit.\n* Sichere Zukunft & Wertschätzung – mit attraktiver Vergütung, Sonderzahlungen und Jubiläumsboni bist du rundum gut versorgt.\n* Starke Gemeinschaft & Kommunikation – Teamevents, transparente Kommunikation und echter Zusammenhalt sind bei uns gelebter Alltag.\n* Innovation & Austausch – Engineering Camps, Hackathons oder Expertenrunden – bei uns kannst du dich fachlich und kreativ einbringen.\n* Corporate Benefits – mit exklusiven Mitarbeiterrabatten in vielen Bereichen.\n\nArt der Stelle: Festanstellung\n\nLeistungen:\n* Betriebliche Altersvorsorge\n* Betriebliche Weiterbildung\n* Firmenevents\n* Flexible Arbeitszeiten\n* Homeoffice-Möglichkeit\n* Kostenlose Getränke\n* Kostenloser Parkplatz\n* Mitarbeiter-Rabatt\n\n\n\nBewerbungsfrage(n):\n* Was ist Ihre Gehaltsvorstellung?\n* Sind Sie reise- oder umzugsbereit?\n* Was ist Ihr frühestmögliches Eintrittsdatum?\n* Was ist Ihre bevorzugte Arbeitsform? (remote/hybrid/vor-ort)\n\nSprache:\n* Deutsch (Erforderlich)\n\nArbeitsort: Vor Ort','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'sepp.med GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=4acfa56ce74f9cd5','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2343,NULL,'job','Internship in Motion Generation for Agricultural Robotics (f/m/x)','Vollzeit','Karlsruhe',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'ZEISS is seeking a motivated intern to join our newly established AgTech department and work on mobile robots operating within high-end greenhouses. This is your chance to actively contribute to a large strategic initiative aiming to revolutionize labor automation in agriculture with innovative robotic systems.\n\nAs an intern, you will become part of a dynamic, start-up minded team of scientists and research engineers. Your primary role will be to develop and evaluate motion generation algorithms for a robot manipulator. You will gain hands-on experience in a real-world research environment, tackle exciting technical challenges, and help us shape the future of agricultural automation.\n\nYour Role\n\nWith us, you have the opportunity to perfectly combine your studies with practical experience while actively contributing to exciting projects. This allows you to gain valuable skills, expand your network, and grow both professionally and personally.\n\nAlgorithmic Development: Implement and evaluate state-of-the-art motion planning and control approaches for highly unstructured environments\n\nSoftware Engineering: Develop, refactor and maintain motion generation pipelines building blocks in a large robotics codebase\n\nReal-world evaluation: Test approaches on real hardware in greenhouses\n\nYour Profile\n\nPursuing a Master’s degree in robotics, computer science, electrical, mechanical engineering or related field\n\nGood foundation in robotics, kinematics, dynamics, motion planning, control theory, optimization, or machine learning\n\nGood coding skills with C++ and Python\n\nHands-on experience with tools like ROS 2, Pinocchio, Drake, MoveIt, Tesseract, ros2_control or LeRobot is a plus\n\nHigh motivation and openness to learn new skills\n\nAbility to work well in an interdisciplinary, international team\n\nExcellent command of English; German skills are an asset but not required\n\nSounds exciting? Then become part of #teamZEISS and help us shape the future! Please provide your complete application documents (CV, transcript of records, etc.).\n\nYour ZEISS Recruiting Team:\n\nSelina Safradin','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'ZEISS Group','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e734c851001dc930','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2344,NULL,'job','Developer & Administrator for Computer Vision projects (m/f/d)','Vollzeit','Manching',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job Description:\n\nIn order to support Air Power Engineering , Airbus Defence and Space is looking for a\n\nDeveloper & Administrator for Computer Vision projects (d/f/m)\n\nYour location\n\nLocated about an hour’s drive north of Munich, Manching is an up-and-coming market town that offers a wide range of leisure and cultural activities. Here, you can enjoy the quality of life in the countryside while the pleasures of near-by cities are still within easy reach.\n\nOur Benefits for You\n\nFair Compensation & Extras: Attractive remuneration and individual additional benefits, such as company pension schemes, mobility offers (e.g., bike leasing), or corporate discounts with partner companies in accordance with our current guidelines.\n\nTime for You (and Your Loved Ones): 30 days of annual leave based on our collective agreement (35-hour week); work-life balance through flexible working hours (flextime), mobile working, part-time options, job sharing, and sabbatical opportunities.\n\nGrowth Made Easy: Excellent professional development opportunities and international, group-wide career perspectives.\n\nFeel Good at Work: On-site company doctor; comprehensive health programs (sports courses, preventive care, etc.), canteen and cafeteria, and local childcare facilities at selected locations.\n\nDiversity Connects: Work in a diverse environment with more than 140 nationalities, where exchange, mutual support, and inclusion are part of our DNA.\n\nYour tasks and responsibilities\n\nThe candidate will have the following main responsibilities:\n\nDevelopment & integration of computer vision systems\n\nAdministration of project network & tools\n\nThis will encompass the following activities:\n\nDefinition of concepts, implementation and system integration of vision solutions\n\nPresentation of work results to co-workers & management\n\nTraining and evaluation of machine learning algorithms\n\nIntegration of vision models in different use cases\n\nAnalysis of complex technical problems & derivation of optimal solutions\n\nIdentification of new trends & technologies in computer vision and implementation in our solutions\n\nDesired skills and qualifications\n\nBachelor degree in the area of engineering, software development, physics or an equivalent field of study.\n\nProgramming skills in Python and C/C++\n\nEmbedded systems development\n\nInterest in Neural Networks and AI\n\nAbility to clearly present & communicate\n\nStrong team player\n\nReadyness for occasional business trips\n\nFluent English, German would be an advantage\n\nNot a 100% match? No worries! Airbus supports your personal growth with customized development solutions.\n\nTake your career to a new level and apply online now!\n\n#MYCYM\n\n#LI-LD1\n\nThis job requires an awareness of any potential compliance risks and a commitment to act with integrity, as the foundation for the Company’s success, reputation and sustainable growth.\n\nCompany:\n\nAirbus Defence and Space GmbH\n\nEmployment Type:\n\nPermanent\n\n-\n\nExperience Level:\n\nEntry Level\n\nJob Family:\n\nSub-system development <JF-EN-EQ>\n\nBy submitting your CV or application you are consenting to Airbus using and storing information about you for monitoring purposes relating to your application or future employment. This information will only be used by Airbus.\nAirbus is committed to achieving workforce diversity and creating an inclusive working environment. We welcome all applications irrespective of social and cultural background, age, gender, disability, sexual orientation or religious belief.\n\nAirbus is, and always has been, committed to equal opportunities for all. As such, we will never ask for any type of monetary exchange in the frame of a recruitment process. Any impersonation of Airbus to do so should be reported to emsom@airbus.com .\n\nAt Airbus, we support you to work, connect and collaborate more easily and flexibly. Wherever possible, we foster flexible working arrangements to stimulate innovative thinking.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Airbus Defence and Space GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6f17d04a23e32d82','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2345,NULL,'job','Software-/Algorithmenentwickler C++ m/w/d','Festanstellung','96052 Bamberg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'*Unser Unternehmen*\n\nDie sepp.med gmbh ist seit über 40 Jahren erfolgreicher Partner in der Softwareentwicklung verschiedener Branchen. Unsere Erfahrung im Projektmanagement, der sicherheitskritischen Softwareentwicklung sowie in Qualitätssicherung und Test von komplexen Systemen ermöglichen es uns mit unseren Kunden an den Innovationen von morgen zu arbeiten.\n\n*Das Projektumfeld*\n\nFür unsere Kunden befassen wir uns mit der Medizintechnik von morgen. Unsere Kunden entwickeln weltweit führende Lösungen zur Bildgebung und Diagnose. Als Key Supplier entwickeln wir in enger Zusammenarbeit mit unseren Kunden moderne Produkt‑, Web- und Cloud-Lösungen, um die Digitalisierung der Produkte voranzutreiben. Dabei setzen wir auf die Themen AI, Machine Learning und Agilität, sowie einen innovativen Tech Stack. Für ein neues Projekt zusammen mit unserem Kunden suchen wir Dich (m/w/d) als weltoffenen Softwareentwickler im Bereich der C#-Umgebungen, der Spaß hat am Einsatz neuer Tools, am Entdecken innovativer Ansätze und dem Arbeiten im Team.\n\n*Deine Aufgaben*\n\n* Du unterstützt die C++ (C++/CLI, C#) Entwicklung, Integration und Betreuung von medizinischen bildgebenden Algorithmen in der Produkterstellung/-Pflege, inklusive Qualitätssicherung mittels automatisierter Tests (Unit- und Integrationstests)\n* Im gesamten Lebenszyklus der Software verbesserst du die Produktqualität und arbeitest in agilen Software-Teams\n* Du bist verantwortlich für die Konzeption und Entwicklung von Algorithmen, Schnittstellen, Integration und Test\n* Des Weiteren fällt die Softwarespezifikation in Zusammenarbeit mit dem Produktmanagement im Kundenumfeld in deinen Aufgabenbereich\n* Du hältst dein Wissen up to date, unser Team unterstützt dich dabei\n\n*Das bringst Du mit*\n\n* Du hast eine Ausbildung zum Fachinformatiker oder ein Fach- oder Hochschulstudium, in den Fachrichtungen Medizinische Informatik, Informatik, Mathematik, Physik, Elektrotechnik oder vergleichbar, erfolgreich abgeschlossen\n* Du bist ein Teamplayer und hast großen Spaß am Arbeiten in einem agilen Team\n* Du zeichnest dich durch dein souveränes Auftreten, deine Lösungsorientierung und deine selbstorganisierte Arbeitsweise aus\n* Idealerweise hast Du Dich schon mit Aufgaben aus der Medizin beschäftigt\n* Du bist begeistert von agilen Entwicklungsmethoden und besitzt sehr gute Windows‑, Linux- und Netzwerk-Kenntnisse\n* Du hast bereits Erfahrungen in der Softwareentwicklung gesammelt und möchtest Deine Kenntnisse in Modern C++, C#, Python, … kontinuierlich erweitern.\n* Des Weiteren hast du gute Kenntnisse im Konfigurationsmanagement (Visual Studio, TFS, Git, Visual Studio Code, Azure DevOps) und in objektorientierter Analyse und Design (Design Patterns)\n* Idealerweise kennst du Frameworks wie z.B. CUDA, Google Test, TensorFlow\n* Sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse runden dein Profil ab\n\n*Deine Benefits*\n\n* Durch flexible Arbeitszeiten, Möglichkeiten für Homeoffice und Teilzeitmodelle unterstützen wir Deine Work-Life-Balance und die Vereinbarkeit von Familie und Beruf\n* Mit dem Schulungsangebot unserer sepp.med Akademie und individueller Weiterbildung bringen wir Dich und Dein fachliches Know-How weiter, denn aktive Personalentwicklung ist uns wichtig\n* Dein Wohlbefinden und Deine Fitness unterstützen wir durch Aktionen zur Gesundheitsförderung, Sportprogramme und eine kostenlose Mitgliedschaft im Fitnessstudio\n* Lerne Deine Kollegen ganz persönlich kennen und erlebe das Wir-Gefühl von sepp.med bei unseren Teamevents, Feiern und firmenweiten Aktivitäten\n* Wir zahlen attraktive Gehälter, Urlaubs- und Weihnachtsgeld, Prämien und wir honorieren langjährige Firmenzugehörigkeit\n* Mit unseren betrieblichen Sozialleistungen unterstützen wir Deine persönliche Vorsorge und soziale Absicherung\n* Offene Kommunikation und persönlicher Dialog auf allen Ebenen sind uns wichtig, denn Deine Anliegen und Deine Beteiligung an unserer Strategieentwicklung liegen uns am Herzen\n* Du kannst Dich spielerisch mit Kollegen messen und Spaß haben oder ernsthaft austauschen – dafür veranstalten wir Engineering Camps, Hackathons und Expertenrunden\n\nWir freuen uns sehr über deine Bewerbung. Bei Fragen erreichst du unsere Ansprechpartner Frau Baigger & Herrn Alef per Telefon unter der 09195-931-186/-261.\n\nsepp.med gmbh - Gewerbering 9 - 91341 Röttenbach\n\nArt der Stelle: Festanstellung\n\nLeistungen:\n* Betriebliche Altersvorsorge\n* Betriebliche Weiterbildung\n* Firmenevents\n* Firmenhandy\n* Firmenwagen\n* Flexible Arbeitszeiten\n* Homeoffice-Möglichkeit\n* Kostenlose Getränke\n\n\n\nBewerbungsfrage(n):\n* Sind Sie reisebereit oder bereit umzuziehen?\n* Was ist Ihre Gehaltsvorstellung?\n* Was ist Ihr frühestmögliches Eintrittsdatum?\n* Was ist Ihre bevorzugte Arbeitsform? (remote/hybrid/vor-ort)\n\nSprache:\n* Deutsch (Erforderlich)\n\nArbeitsort: Vor Ort','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'sepp.med GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a5f58b11ac32f742','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2346,NULL,'job','Internship - Agentic AI for Computational Biology (all genders)','Praktikum','Darmstadt',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Work Your Magic with us!\n\nReady to explore, break barriers, and discover more? We know you’ve got big plans – so do we! Our colleagues across the globe love innovating with science and technology to enrich people’s lives with our solutions in Healthcare, Life Science, and Electronics. Together, we dream big and are passionate about caring for our rich mix of people, customers, patients, and planet. That\'s why we are always looking for curious minds that see themselves imagining the unimaginable with us.\n\nUnited As One for Patients, our purpose in Healthcare is to help create, improve and prolong lives. We develop medicines, intelligent devices and innovative technologies in therapeutic areas such as Oncology, Neurology and Fertility. Our teams work together across 6 continents with passion and relentless curiosity in order to help patients at every stage of life. Joining our Healthcare team is becoming part of a diverse, inclusive and flexible working culture, presenting great opportunities for personal development and career advancement across the globe.\n\nYour Role\n\nAre you passionate about artificial intelligence and eager to make a real impact in cancer research? As an Intern in Computational Oncology, you will collaborate with a dynamic team to explore and implement cutting-edge agentic AI approaches that accelerate our biological research workflows. You will work alongside our team to advance our understanding of cancer biology and contribute to the discovery of new therapeutic strategies. The purpose of this role is to solve the challenge of applying agentic AI technologies, including automated knowledge collection, retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), vector databases and agentic workflows, to support target prioritisation and early research programs.\n\nThe position is based in Darmstadt, Germany, and we offer a hybrid work model.\n\nWho You Are\n\nYou are currently pursuing a master\'s degree in computational biology, computer science, bioinformatics, data science, or a related field with a strong interest in life sciences.\nYou have a solid understanding of AI and machine learning concepts, with hands-on experience with large language models (LLMs) and a good understanding of agentic AI frameworks.\nYou are comfortable working with modern software development concepts, including APIs, data integration, and connecting heterogeneous tools and data sources into coherent workflows.\nYou are proficient in Python; knowledge of R is a welcome addition.\nYou are familiar with concepts such as retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), MCP, vector databases, and tool-use in agentic systems, or you are highly motivated to learn these rapidly.\nYou have a basic understanding of biology or molecular life sciences, sufficient to contextualise your work within an oncology research environment.\nYou are an enthusiastic, creative, goal-oriented, proactive and out-of-the-box thinker with a strong ability to work both independently and collaboratively, this matters especially as our team is on a learning journey alongside you.\nYou have excellent English communication skills, both written and spoken.\nYou are eager to share your knowledge and enable others to build on what you create.\n\nDuration, Location & Additional Information\n\nDuration:\n\n6 months, starting as soon as possible\n\nLocation: Darmstadt, Germany\n\nAdditional Information: A valid work permit is required for the internship.\n\nWhat we offer: We are curious minds that come from a broad range of backgrounds, perspectives, and life experiences. We believe that this variety drives excellence and innovation, strengthening our ability to lead in science and technology. We are committed to creating access and opportunities for all to develop and grow at your own pace. Join us in building a culture of inclusion and belonging that impacts millions and empowers everyone to work their magic and champion human progress!\n\nApply now and become a part of a team that is dedicated to Sparking Discovery and Elevating Humanity!','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Merck KGaA','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b1101a8a2926357a','scraped','vor 2 Tagen'),(2347,NULL,'job','Data & AI Education Consultant (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','60314 Frankfurt am Main',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Über uns\n\nstatworx ist ein führendes Beratungs- und Entwicklungsunternehmen für Daten und KI mit Sitz in Frankfurt am Main. Wir bieten strategische Beratung für mittelständische Unternehmen und globale Konzerne. Wir entwickeln innovative Daten- & KI-Lösungen für alle Unternehmensbereiche und Tätigkeitsfelder. Wir befähigen Menschen auf allen Kompetenzniveaus mit unseren Daten- & KI-Bildungsformaten. Kurz gesagt: Wir unterstützen Unternehmen bei allen Aspekten der digitalen Transformation – seit mehr als 10 Jahren, in über 1000 Daten- & KI-Projekten und für über 100 Kunden aus fast allen Industrien.\n\nSeit 2011 haben wir in unserer statworx AI Academy weltweit bereits über 15.000 Personen in den Themengebieten Data Science, künstliche Intelligenz und Machine Learning weitergebildet. Von kleinen Trainingseinheiten & Einstiegsprogrammen bis zu langfristigen und globalen Schulungskonzepten und Data Culture Initiativen für unsere Kunden im DAX-Umfeld, bieten wir ein vielfältiges und maßgeschneidertes Portfolio an. Unser Anspruch ist es, stetig am Puls der Zeit zu sein (aktuell u.A. Generative KI, Large Language Models und Data Culture) und unsere Trainingsmethoden konstant weiterzuentwickeln. Zum weiteren Aufbau unseres Teams und Schulungsangebotes suchen wir derzeit nach Verstärkung.\n\nDeine Aufgaben\n\nDu entwickelst und realisierst eigenverantwortlich Schulungs- und Trainingsprojekte für Enterprisekunden, z. B. zu Data Literacy, Data Culture, Generativer KI, Machine Learning, Agentic AI, LLMs und verwandten Themen\nDu führst Trainings und Trainingsreihen im Corporate-Learning-Umfeld durch – überwiegend virtuell, sowie punktuell in Präsenz (ca. 20 %)\nDu konzipierst und erstellst theoretische und praxisnahe Trainingseinheiten, inklusive interaktiver Übungen und Anwendungsbeispiele mit Python, Shell sowie No-Code- und Low-Code-Umgebungen\nDu berätst Kunden im Rahmen von Data-Culture-Initiativen und betreust Communities of Practice sowie Lerncommunities\nDu reviewst bestehende Schulungsmaterialien und entwickelst diese sowohl inhaltlich als auch technisch kontinuierlich weiter\nDu arbeitest aktiv an internen Initiativen mit, z. B. Hackathons, Blogbeiträgen und Formaten zum internen Wissensaustausch und Kompetenzaufbau\n\nDein Profil\n\nDu hast ein erfolgreich abgeschlossenes Masterstudium z. B. in BWL, Statistik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Sozial- oder Politikwissenschaften oder einem vergleichbaren Studiengang.\nDu konntest bereits praktische Erfahrung in Data-Science-Projekten sammeln – idealerweise im Konzern- oder Beratungsumfeld.\nDu hast ein ausgeprägtes Talent dafür, komplexe technische Inhalte verständlich, anschaulich und interaktiv aufzubereiten und zu vermitteln.\nDu bringst sehr gute Kenntnisse in Data-Science-Methoden sowie praktische Erfahrung in mindestens einer relevanten Programmiersprache (z. B. Python oder R) mit.\nIdealerweise hast du bereits Erfahrung mit agilen Arbeitsmethoden (insbesondere Scrum) und Digitalisierungsprojekten gesammelt.\nDu kommunizierst sicher und überzeugend und verfügst über sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift (C2)\nDu arbeitest zuverlässig, strukturiert und sorgfältig und verstehst dich als Teamplayer:in\nDu hast Freude daran, gelegentlich zu Kunden im europäischen Raum zu reisen\n\nDas bieten wir Dir\n\nData & AI im Kern: Dich erwarten vielfältige und anspruchsvolle Projekte mit namhaften Kund:innen aus unterschiedlichen Branchen – von datengetriebenen Lösungen bis hin zu innovativen KI-Anwendungen\nFachliche Vielfalt & Entwicklung: Du arbeitest an komplexen, abwechslungsreichen Fragestellungen und baust dabei kontinuierlich deine Expertise in deinem Fachgebiet sowie im Umfeld von Data & AI aus\nProfessionelle Weiterentwicklung: Wir fördern deine methodische, fachliche und persönliche Entwicklung – durch regelmäßiges Feedback, individuelle Förderung, Weiterbildungsangebote und unser Mentoring-Programm\nKultur & Zusammenarbeit: Dich erwartet ein offenes, diverses und wertschätzendes Arbeitsumfeld mit flachen Hierarchien, kurzen Entscheidungswegen und einem starken Teamgefühl\nModerne Arbeitsweise: Wir leben eine iterative, moderne Arbeitskultur mit klarer Kommunikation, Eigenverantwortung und Raum für neue Ideen und Gestaltungsmöglichkeiten\nTransparente Vergütung: Wir bieten faire, strukturierte und nachvollziehbare Gehaltsstufen, die regelmäßig an Markt- und Leistungsentwicklungen angepasst werden\nFlexibles Arbeiten: Unser modernes Office in Frankfurt ist dein zentraler Arbeitsort – gleichzeitig hast du die Möglichkeit, regelmäßig remote zu arbeiten und bis zu vier Wochen pro Jahr aus dem EU-Ausland zu arbeiten\nMobilität & Gesundheit: Profitiere von einem ermäßigten Deutschlandticket und vergünstigtem Zugang zu Sport- und Wellnessangeboten über Wellpass\nAusstattung & Extras: Hochwertiges IT-Equipment (z. B. MacBook Pro), regelmäßige Team-Events sowie zusätzliche Leistungen wie Kinderbetreuungszuschüsse und attraktive Mitarbeiterrabatte runden dein Gesamtpaket ab\n\nDeine Bewerbung\n\nBewirb Dich einfach über das Bewerbungsformular und hänge Deinen aktuellen Lebenslauf samt Darstellung deiner Methodenkenntnisse an. Wir werden uns anschließend umgehend bei Dir melden. Bei Fragen rund um Deine Bewerbung erreichst Du uns unter jobs@statworx.com.\n\nWas für uns besonders wichtig ist: Wir schätzen die Einzigartigkeit jedes Menschen und begegnen einander stets auf Augenhöhe. Unterschiedliche Hintergründe, Einstellungen und Ideen bereichern uns und bilden die Grundlage unseres Erfolgs. Daher freuen wir uns über jede Bewerbung – unabhängig von Geschlecht, Nationalität, ethnischer und sozialer Herkunft, Religion, Weltanschauung, Behinderung, Alter sowie sexueller Orientierung und Identität.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'statworx','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5e44ce60cc1ea048','scraped','vor 2 Tagen'),(2348,NULL,'job','Data & AI Product Engineer (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','Home Office',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Beschreibung\n\nWir suchen einen Data & AI Product Engineer (m/w/d) zur Weiterentwicklung der daten- und KI-basierten Produktfeatures unserer SaaS-Lösungen. Unsere Plattform verbindet Gäste, Betriebe und Caterer in der digitalen Betriebsgastronomie und im Corporate Catering - von der Menüplanung bis zur Auswertung.\n\nDu verbindest technisches Produktdenken mit einem starken Verständnis für Daten und künstliche Intelligenz. Gemeinsam mit anderen Teams entwickelst du Lösungen, die komplexe Informationen aus Menüs, Verkäufen, Feedback, Trends und externen Einflussfaktoren in klare, nutzbare Handlungsempfehlungen übersetzen.\n\nOb Verbrauchsprognosen, smarte Menüoptimierung oder personalisierte Gästekommunikation – deine Arbeit hilft unseren Kund:innen, schneller bessere Entscheidungen zu treffen, Lebensmittelverschwendung zu reduzieren und wirtschaftliche Ergebnisse nachhaltig zu verbessern. Wir freuen uns auf deine Ideen und deine Bewerbung!\n\nDeine Aufgaben\n\nEnd-to-End Feature Development: Verantwortung für Data- & AI-Features von der Idee über Prototyping bis zur produktiven Integration in unsere SaaS-Plattform\nDatenaufbereitung und Feature Engineering: Aufbereitung und Transformation von Daten aus User Events, POS-, Menü-, IoT- und CRM-Systemen\nGenerative AI & LLMs: Implementierung und Integration von LLM-APIs (z. B. OpenAI, Anthropic, Mistral) für Chatbots, Textanalyse und automatisierte Content-Erstellung\nAPI Design und Integration: Konzeption und Anbindung von APIs und MCPs\nRecommendation Systems: Entwicklung intelligenter Empfehlungssysteme für personalisierte Menüs, Aktionen und Bestellprognosen\nForecasting und Time Series: Aufbau von Zeitreihenanalysen und Prognosemodellen zur Vorhersage von Nachfrage, Besuchsfrequenzen und Absatzentwicklungen\nRapid Prototyping: Schnelles Testen und Iterieren neuer Ideen in enger Zusammenarbeit mit Product, Design und Backend\nData Infrastructure: Mitarbeit an skalierbarer Dateninfrastruktur – von Pipelines und Feature Stores bis zu Model Deployment und Monitoring\nProduct Collaboration: Enge Zusammenarbeit mit dem Product-Team, um datengetriebene Insights und KI-Modelle in echte Kundenerlebnisse zu überführen\n\nDanach suchen wir\n\nAbgeschlossenes Studium im Bereich (Wirtschafts-)Informatik, Data Science, Machine Learning oder ein vergleichbarer Hintergrund\nErfahrung in der Entwicklung datenbasierter oder KI-gestützter Anwendungen, idealerweise im SaaS- oder Produktumfeld\nSehr gutes Verständnis von Datenmodellierung, Analytics und Machine Learning\nErfahrung im Aufbau und Betrieb moderner Datenarchitekturen und Pipelines, idealerweise mit Microsoft Fabric und AI Foundry\nPraxis in Cloud-basierten Datenplattformen und produktionsnahen Data-Workflows\nSehr gute Kenntnisse in Python und SQL\nErfahrung mit API-Integrationen und grundlegender Backend-Entwicklung\nKenntnisse in Feature Engineering, Zeitreihen-Forecasting und Recommender-Systemen von Vorteil\nIdealerweise Erfahrung mit LLM-APIs und modernen AI-Toolchains inkl. MCP\nFähigkeit, technische Lösungen aus Produkt- und Nutzerperspektive zu denken\nStrukturierte, selbstständige Arbeitsweise sowie hohe Motivation und Flexibilität\nFreude daran, neue Ideen schnell zu testen, iterativ weiterzuentwickeln und in Produkte zu überführen\nSehr gute Englischkenntnisse und gute Deutschkenntnisse von Vorteil\n\nDas bieten wir dir\n\nFlexibilität: flexible Arbeitszeiten & Remote Work sind selbstverständlich\nTeilzeit oder Vollzeit: Wir finden für dich das richtige Arbeitsmodell\nMehr Urlaub: 28 Urlaubstage pro Jahr plus je einen weiteren Tag nach zwei und nach vier Jahren\nWorkation: 30 Tage pro Jahr mobiles Arbeiten im europäischen Ausland\nKostenloses Mittagessen: dreimal pro Woche kostenloses und frisch gekochtes Mittagessen\nTeamspirit: Offene Arbeitskultur, kurze Entscheidungswege & agile Arbeitsmethoden\nRaum für Ideen: Viel Gestaltungsspielraum mit 20 % Slack-Time\nWorkplace: Zentral gelegenes Office mit moderner Ausstattung, einer Dachterrasse und Grill für entspannte Feierabende.\nKaffee-Liebe: Frisches Obst, hervorragender Siebträger-Kaffee und vermutlich die beste Getränkeauswahl in einem Bürokühlschrank\nGemeinsame Events: Regelmäßige Teamevents und Ausflüge\nFitness & Mobilität: Arbeitgeberzuschuss zum Deutschlandticket, kostenloser E-Scooter Verleih, Fitness-Zuschüsse (urbansportclub, Jobrad etc.)\nZukunftssicherheit: Angebot und Bezuschussung zur betrieblichen Altersvorsorge – damit du langfristig gut aufgestellt bist.\nEntwicklungsmöglichkeiten: zahlreiche Entwicklungs- & Fortbildungsmöglichkeiten sowie internationale Konferenzbesuche\nTop-Team: Gut gelaunte & ambitionierte Kolleg:innen, die stolz auf das gemeinsame Werk sind\n\nHast du weitere Fragen?\n\nDann melde dich unter jobs@menio.com bei uns. Myriam Harrendorf beantwortet dir deine Fragen gerne. Bitte sende uns deine Bewerbungsunterlagen zusammengefügt in einem PDF, einschließlich Anschreiben, Lebenslauf und Zeugnisse, zu.\n\nÜber uns\n\nDas ist menio\n\nWir sind ein innovatives und engagiertes Team aus über 75 Entwickler:innen, Projektmanager:innen und Kreativen, die Herausforderungen lieben.\n\nmenio ist ein aufstrebendes Unternehmen mit einer modularen Softwarelösung für die Betriebsgastronomie auf dem europäischen und internationalen Markt. Wir sind dort, wo unsere Kund:innen uns brauchen – und entwickeln gemeinsam lösungsorientierte Konzepte. Wir suchen nach Menschen, die Herausforderungen lieben und genauso viel Freude an Innovation und lebenslangem Lernen haben wie wir. Bei uns findest du Raum für deine Ideen, Anregungen und Fähigkeiten. Wir nutzen stets eine breite Basis neuester Softwaretechnologie, haben Spaß an Innovationen und \"lebenslanges Lernen\" ist bei uns nicht bloß eine Worthülse, sondern wird gelebt. Durch unseren gemeinsamen Ehrgeiz und den Respekt füreinander erreichen wir Großes - sowohl im Team als auch mit unseren Kund:innen & Partner:innen.\n\nWir schätzen eine Kommunikation, in der Integrität und Transparenz unser Handeln leiten. Unser modernes Office im Herzen der City schafft eine angenehme Arbeitsatmosphäre und unser Dachgeschoss mit Dachterrasse lädt zum Luftholen, Nachdenken, Auftanken & gemeinsamen Verweilen ein.\n\nMöchtest Du mehr über menio erfahren? Dann schau doch mal bei LinkedIn und Instagram vorbei!','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'menio GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=01a40e382d979269','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2349,NULL,'job','Senior Operations Research Scientist','Vollzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Hungry for a challenge?\n\nThat’s good, because at Just Eat Takeaway.com (JET) we believe everything is possible, or, as we say, everything is on the table. We are a leading global online food delivery marketplace. Our tech ecosystem connects millions of active customers with hundreds of thousands of connected partners in countries across the globe.\n\nOur mission? To empower every food moment around the world, whether it’s through customer service, coding or couriers.\n\nThe Opportunity\n\nAs a Senior Operations Research (OR) Scientist, you will play a pivotal role in designing an optimization system that balances the supply/demand capacity of the logistics network. You will dive deep into large-scale geospatial and real-time data to design automated decision-making systems that operate in a dynamic, real-world environment. You will develop high-performance robust optimization models, utilizing techniques like mixed-integer programming (MIP), constraint programming, stochastic programming, metaheuristics, etc. and launch them into production to control operational decisions at scale.\n\nYou will collaborate with Data Scientists to create hybrid systems where Machine Learning guides optimization constraints and objective functions. You will help bridge the gap between prediction and control, working with engineers to define the simulation and experimental environments needed to validate these systems. In this senior role, you’ll work closely with fellow scientists to establish and implement best practices, share constructive feedback, and mentor junior team members. Staying at the forefront of OR advancements, you’ll explore new algorithms, architectures, and methodologies to enhance the performance of our products and algorithms.\n\nThese are some of the key ingredients to the role:\n\nAdvanced proficiency in designing large scale, real-time optimization systems for time critical decisions, with extensive experience applying these techniques in production environments.\nDeep expertise in exact optimization techniques (mixed-integer programming/decomposition), robust optimization (Stochastic/Worst case/Scenario based programming) and meta-heuristic methods.\nExtensive hands-on experience with commercial solvers (CPLEX/Gurobi) and open-source alternatives (HIGHS/SCIP/Google OR-Tools)\nProficiency in Python object oriented programming, and experience with libraries such as Pyomo, PuLP, or GurobiPy.\nHands-on experience in setting up simulations for model validation and data generation.\nProven experience in getting models to production, scaling, and maintaining them for long-term success.\nStrong understanding of software development best practices, including testing, git, code reviews, and model lifecycle management.\nWorking with Docker containers to support reproducible and scalable environments.\nExperience with real time systems and stream processing is desirable.\nBasic understanding of machine learning is required.\nFamiliarity with Control Theory concepts (feedback loops, PID, or MPC) to manage dynamic supply/demand signals is beneficial.\nExperience in the logistics domain is also beneficial.\n\nWhat will you bring to the table?\n\nSystems Thinking: You intuitively understand feedback loops and second-order effects in complex networks.\nLeadership and mentorship skills, with the ability to guide and develop junior data scientists and foster team collaboration.\nA holistic project approach, from generating business cases to managing the full lifecycle of models.\nAbility to generate innovative ideas, test hypotheses rigorously, and pitch business cases to stakeholders.\nCritical analysis of approaches, assumptions, and business impact, with the ability to challenge and refine strategies for optimal results.\nPreference for simple, scalable, and effective solutions, particularly in complex projects.\nExpertise in agile environments with strong collaborative skills, particularly in cross-functional teams.\nExcellent communication skills, including the ability to present complex data insights and OR concepts to a wide range of stakeholders, both technical and non-technical.\n\nAt JET, this is on the menu:\n\nOur teams forge connections internally and work with some of the best-known brands on the planet, giving us truly international impact in a dynamic environment.\n\nFun, fast-paced and supportive, the JET culture is about movement, growth and about celebrating every aspect of our JETers. Thanks to them we stay one step ahead of the competition.\n\nInclusion, Diversity & Belonging\n\nNo matter who you are, what you look like, who you love, or where you are from, you can find your place at Just Eat Takeaway.com. We’re committed to creating an inclusive culture, encouraging diversity of people and thinking, in which all employees feel they truly belong and can bring their most colourful selves to work every day.\n\nWhat else is cooking?\n\nWant to know more about our JETers, culture or company? Have a look at our career site where you can find people\'s stories, blogs, podcasts and more JET morsels.\n\nAre you ready to take your seat? Apply now!\n\n#LI-CB2','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Lieferando','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=61a36a416fe814e6','scraped','vor 2 Tagen'),(2350,NULL,'job','Data Scientist:in – AI & Analytics (d/m/w)','Vollzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Das Business-Insights-Team beim Tagesspiegel unterstützt den Verlag und die Redaktion mit aussagekräftigen Reports, präzisen Analysen sowie daten- und KI-gestützten Lösungen - mit dem Ziel, informierte Entscheidungen zu ermöglichen und das Leitmedium aus der Hauptstadt auf seinem Weg in die digitale Zukunft zu begleiten.\n\nMit unserem Team decken wir die gesamte Datenwertschöpfungskette ab - vom Tracking in Web und App über die Datenverarbeitung bis hin zur Verwendung der Daten für Reports, Ad-hoc-Analysen, CRM, Data-Science-Anwendungen und KI-Produkte.\n\nAls Data Scientist:in – AI & Analytics bist Du wesentlicher Bestandteil unseres Teams und entwickelst Lösungen, die im Alltag von Redaktion, Produkt, Vertrieb und Tech funktionieren - vom analytischen Report bis zum produktiven RAG-System.\n\nDas sind Deine Aufgaben:\nData Science und Advanced Analytics: Du unterstützt bei der Entwicklung datenbasierter Modelle, fortgeschrittener Analysen und Metriken. Dabei kannst Du einschätzen, wann Ergebnisse belastbar sind, und kommunizierst Unsicherheiten klar und nachvollziehbar.\nKI-Produkte entwickeln: Du setzt Gen-AI-Use-Cases um - darunter Copilots, RAG-Systeme und agentische Workflows - und integrierst LLMs in bestehende Arbeitsabläufe und Datenlandschaften. Bei Bedarf kannst Du auch ML-Modelle entwickeln.\nAnalysen und Dashboards: Du beantwortest konkrete Fragestellungen aus Redaktion, Produkt und Vertrieb mithilfe von Daten. Du planst, erstellst und pflegst Reports und Dashboards, die verständlich, reproduzierbar und für unsere Stakeholder:innen tatsächlich nutzbar sind.\nEntwicklung und Betrieb: Du bringst Data-Science- und AI-Komponenten in produktive Umgebungen: sauber entwickelt, evaluiert, dokumentiert und überwacht. Dabei nutzt Du Cloud-Infrastruktur wie GCP, insbesondere BigQuery, Cloud Run und Vertex AI, und arbeitest eng mit dem Engineering-Team zusammen.\nStakeholder:innen‑Management: Du nimmst Anforderungen aus den Fachbereichen auf, stimmst diese ab und kommunizierst Fortschritte, Herausforderungen und Ergebnisse.\nDas bringst Du mit:\nRelevanter Hintergrund: Du hast ein abgeschlossenes relevantes Studium, eine relevante Ausbildung oder vergleichbare praktische Erfahrung im Bereich Data Science, Data Analytics, Software Engineering oder KI.\nPython- und SQL-Kenntnisse: Du bist sicher im Umgang mit Python, SQL und Git und hast bereits Lösungen entwickelt, die über explorative Notebooks hinausgehen.\nErfahrung mit Cloud- und Dateninfrastruktur: Du hast praktische Erfahrung mit GCP, insbesondere BigQuery, Cloud Run oder Vertex AI, oder mit vergleichbarer Cloud-Infrastruktur.\nHands-on-Erfahrung mit LLMs: Du hast bereits mit LLMs gearbeitet - etwa in den Bereichen Prompting, Embeddings, RAG oder Evaluation - und idealerweise Anwendungen gebaut, die produktiv genutzt werden.\nKenntnisse in Machine Learning und Statistik: Du verfügst über ein gutes Grundverständnis klassischer ML-Verfahren und statistischer Konzepte und kennst den Unterschied zwischen korrelativen und kausalen Zusammenhängen.\nInteresse an agentischen Workflows: Idealerweise hast Du Interesse an agentischen Workflows, MCP oder vergleichbaren Ansätzen - oder Lust, Dich in diese Themen einzuarbeiten.\nKommunikationsfähigkeit: Du kannst komplexe technische Zusammenhänge verständlich erklären, Anforderungen mit Stakeholder:innen besprechen und Deine Lösungen schriftlich wie mündlich nachvollziehbar darstellen. Für die erfolgreiche Zusammenarbeit in unserem überwiegend deutschsprachigen Umfeld setzen wir Deutschkenntnisse auf mindestens B2‑Niveau voraus (C1 wünschenswert).\n\nDu erfüllst nicht alle Anforderungen, hast aber Lust, mit uns daten- und KI-gestützte Lösungen für den Tagesspiegel zu entwickeln? Dann freuen wir uns trotzdem auf Deine Bewerbung!\n\nDas bieten wir Dir:\nKreativer Freiraum in einem Team, in dem Ideen geschätzt werden und Du Deine Visionen in einem innovativen Medienunternehmen im Herzen Berlins umsetzen kannst\nFlache Hierarchien mit kurzen Entscheidungswegen und direkter Kommunikation\nBezuschusstes BVG-Firmenticket und Zuschuss zur betrieblichen Altersvorsorge\nKostenloses Digital-Abonnement von Tagesspiegel & Tagesspiegel Plus, Handelsblatt und die Zeit\nMöglichkeiten zur beruflichen Weiterentwicklung durch die Online-Plattform Masterplan, um Deine Karriere voranzutreiben\nFlexible Arbeitszeiten und mobiles Arbeiten bis zu 50%\n\nJede Nachricht erzählt eine eigene Geschichte – und so ist es auch mit den Menschen, die bei uns arbeiten. Beim Tagesspiegel schätzen wir die Vielfalt unserer Mitarbeiterinnen und Mitarbeiter und sind fest davon überzeugt, dass unterschiedliche Perspektiven unsere Arbeit bereichern.\n\nWir setzen uns für Chancengleichheit ein und fördern einen respektvollen Umgang miteinander. Unabhängig von Herkunft, Geschlecht, Religion, Alter oder sexueller Identität – bei uns bist Du willkommen. Lass uns gemeinsam ein inspirierendes Arbeitsumfeld schaffen, in dem jeder seine Einzigartigkeit einbringen kann!\n\nDu denkst, wir sollten uns kennenlernen?\n\nWenn Du bereit bist, Deine Fähigkeiten in einem inspirierenden Team einzusetzen und einen echten Unterschied zu machen, dann bewirb Dich jetzt über unser Bewerbungsportal https://verlagsjobs.tagesspiegel.de/ und sende uns Deine Bewerbungsunterlagen. Gemeinsam erzählen wir Geschichten, die bewegen!\n\nWir freuen uns darauf, Dich kennenzulernen!','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Verlag Der Tagesspiegel GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=26d75b4196fc48ea','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2351,NULL,'job','KI Specialist (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','63150 Heusenstamm',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Werde Teil des INDUSTRA Teams!\n\nWir sind ein zukunftsorientiertes Unternehmen mit dem klaren Ziel unsere Prozesse durch den intelligenten Einsatz von künstlicher Intelligenz nachhaltig zu optimieren. Dafür suchen wir einen KI Specialist (m/w/d) in Vollzeit, der technisches Know-how mit strategischem Denken verbindet und KI-Lösungen von der Idee bis zur Umsetzung begleitet.\n\nDeine Hauptaufgaben:\nEntwicklung und Umsetzung einer KI-Strategie zur Optimierung und Automatisierung von Unternehmensprozessen\nAnalyse bestehender Abläufe und Identifikation von KI-Potenzialen\nEinführung, Training und Weiterentwicklung von KI-Systemen (z. B. LLMs, RPA, Predictive Analytics, Chatbots)\nAutomatisierung von Workflows und datengetriebenen Entscheidungsprozessen\nZusammenarbeit mit Fachabteilungen zur Integration von KI-Lösungen in bestehende Systeme\nBewertung neuer KI-Technologien und Tools hinsichtlich Nutzen, Skalierbarkeit und Wirtschaftlichkeit\nSicherstellung von Datenschutz, IT-Sicherheit und ethischem KI-Einsatz\nSchulung und Beratung von Mitarbeitenden im Umgang mit KI\nUnsere Anforderungen:\nabgeschlossenes Studium in Informatik, Data Science, KI, Wirtschaftsingenieurwesen oder vergleichbare Qualifikation\nfundierte Kenntnisse in Künstlicher Intelligenz, Machine Learning oder Automatisierung\nErfahrung mit KI-Tools, APIs, LLMs (z. B. OpenAI, Azure, AWS), RPA oder vergleichbaren Technologien\nVerständnis für Geschäftsprozesse und deren Optimierung\nanalytische, strukturierte und lösungsorientierte Arbeitsweise\nsehr gute Deutsch- und gute Englischkenntnisse\nEigeninitiative, Innovationsgeist und Freude daran, Neues aufzubauen\nWir bieten:\neine Schlüsselrolle beim Aufbau und der Weiterentwicklung unserer KI-Landschaft\ngroße Gestaltungsfreiheit und direkter Einfluss auf Unternehmensprozesse\nspannende Projekte mit modernsten KI-Technologien\nflache Hierarchien und kurze Entscheidungswege\nattraktive Vergütung und Entwicklungsmöglichkeiten\nflexible Arbeitszeiten und hybride Arbeitsmodelle\n\nWir wertschätzen diverse Teams und freuen uns auf deine Bewerbung, unabhängig von deiner Nationalität, ethnischen Herkunft, Geschlecht, sexuellen Orientierung, Religion, Behinderung oder Alter.\n\nDu fühlst dich angesprochen? Dann sende deinen Lebenslauf an die Personalabteilung der INDUSTRA GmbH. Wir freuen uns darauf, dich kennenzulernen.\nVollzeit\nHeusenstamm','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'INDUSTRA GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2e19f642b33f48d7','scraped','vor 2 Tagen'),(2352,NULL,'job','Working Student Data (m/w/d)','Teilzeit','80331 München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About Us\n\nDeepImmo is an innovative PropTech company that’s revolutionizing the real estate market! Our big goal is to create more transparency around buying and renting properties. To achieve this, we offer a data-driven Real Estate OS, a software solution that delivers deep analysis into location, market dynamics, and demand — providing our customers with actionable insights and thereby giving them a decisive competitive advantage. Together, we are shaping the future of the real estate industry by developing smart, innovative solutions, free from old conventions and plenty of courage to embrace the new.\n\nThe DeepImmo Data & Analytics team contributes the quantitative edge into our product by building the data groundwork and bringing the data alive. We integrate a wide range of data sources, create robust pipelines, and build the machine learning models and analytical methods that power our Real Estate OS.\n\nTo strengthen our team, we’re looking for a Working Student Data (m/w/d) who is excited to get hands-on across the full data spectrum — with a slight focus on Data Engineering and DataOps. If you enjoy building reliable pipelines, improving data quality, and making systems run smoothly (while also getting exposure to AI projects), this role is for you.\n\nYour Role\n\nIn this role, you will:\n\nImplement data pipelines in PySpark on Databricks to transform raw data into structured, analytics-ready datasets.\nMaintain, improve, and extend existing pipelines — ensuring reliability, performance, and clarity as our data landscape grows.\nRefine raw data into “gold data” by developing well-constructed data models, setting up quality assurance measures, and helping orchestrate the end-to-end flow.\nKeep the data flowing (DataOps): help us monitor pipelines, spot issues early, troubleshoot when things go wrong, and contribute to making our operations more stable and observable by improving our infrastructure and workflows\nParticipate in machine learning / AI projects:\nWe’re continuously experimenting and releasing AI features for our Real Estate OS. You’ll support model improvement, explore ideas with real-world applications to real estate, and help move promising prototypes towards deployment.\n\nYour Profile\n\nYou are currently studying in a Master’s program in Computer Science, Data Engineering, Applied Statistics, or a related field.\nYou have a strong interest in working in a data-focused role — ideally with curiosity for DataOps and how data products run in production.\nYou bring a high degree of self-organisation and individual responsibility and enjoy taking ownership of tasks end-to-end.\nYou’re well familiar with SQL, Python and interested in Big Data processing with Apache Spark / PySpark as well as DataOps\nAdditionally, you’re ideally interested in working with AirFlow, AWS and Databricks\nFluency in English is a must-have, good German skills are beneficial\n\nWhy grow with us?\n\nBe the data-driven force behind a product that is redefining how real estate professionals work.\nBecome part of a small, ambitious team where your contributions are visible and valued.\nHelp us shape the future of the real estate industry.\n\nYour benefits at deepImmo:\n\nEGYM Wellpass: Work out at over 6,000 sports and wellness facilities throughout Germany—from gyms to yoga studios to thermal baths. deepImmo covers half the cost for you.\nDrinks & snacks: Coffee, soft drinks, water, energy drinks, or a quick snack between meals—with us, you don\'t have to worry about the basics. Your focus belongs to your ideas.\nTop location & top equipment: We work in a modern office in the heart of Munich and provide you with everything you need to work productively and efficiently, whether in our office or remotely.\nFlexible working: We believe in trust and personal responsibility. With us, you can work in a hybrid model that works best for you and your team.\nStart-up spirit & real impact: With us, you\'re not just one of many—you play an active role in shaping the company. We celebrate ideas, initiative, and impact.\nTeam events & offsites: Whether it\'s after-work get-togethers, offsites in Mallorca, or spontaneous lunches, we make a point of taking time to foster real team spirit','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'DeepImmo GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d112a3cb3f6f709b','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2353,NULL,'job','Thesis Student (m/f/d) - AI for Automotive MCET','Vollzeit','85386 Eching',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nDENSO, the world\'s second largest mobility supplier, is leading in developing and providing components and systems for automotive components such as heating, air conditioning, motor cooling, exhaust gas aftertreatment, automotive electrics and electronics and instrumentation.\n\nJob Description\n\nTrajectory prediction models aim to forecast how agents such as pedestrians or vehicles will move in the future. Many models have been proposed, but they are often evaluated under different settings. This makes it difficult to understand which approaches work best and why.\n\nThis master’s thesis focuses on systematically benchmarking major trajectory prediction models in a consistent and structured way, following their development over time. The goal is to build a clear understanding of how different modeling choices affect performance, robustness, and generalization.\n\nBased on this analysis, the project will explore simple and effective improvements or a unified modeling approach that combines the strengths of existing methods.\n\nKey Research Areas and Tasks\n\nBenchmarking major trajectory prediction models under a unified and reproducible setup\nAnalysis of failure cases in trajectory prediction (e.g., collisions, unrealistic trajectories, lack of diversity)\nDevelopment of a clean benchmarking pipeline for fair comparison\nInvestigation of modeling improvements or a unified architecture\nEvaluation using common metrics (e.g., ADE, FDE)\n\nQualifications\n\nYou are interested in autonomous driving, machine learning, or robotics.\nBasic knowledge of deep learning and sequence modeling.\nHands-on experience with reading and adapting research codebases.\nStrong Python skills.\nExperience with experiments and data analysis is a plus.\n\nAdditional Information\n\nEmployee benefits: Urban Sports Club, etc.\nAttractive work environment: Modern offices, on-site cafeteria, free parking\nInternational company: Career opportunities in a global setting\nOpen corporate culture: Diverse, multicultural team\nEvents: Regular company and team events\n\nIt has come to our attention that various individuals have contacted people offering false employment opportunities with DENSO. Such scams are fraudulent and intended to steal from the victims.\n\nBy making you aware of this, we hope to avoid and ultimately stop victims from falling for this scam. Please do not provide any personal or financial information and do not send any money to anyone you suspect of recruitment fraud.\n\nIf you are contacted by someone whom you suspect may not be appropriately representing DENSO, please email: EU_DIEU_TALENTACQUISITION@eu.denso.com. Please forward the original email that you received that includes the original subject line and complete header information.\n\nDo not send CVs or vacancy applications to that email address as it will not be reviewed or considered. If you wish to apply for a job, please submit your application for an open position to https://careers.smartrecruiters.com/DENSOINTERNATIONALEUROPE','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'DENSO AUTOMOTIVE Deutschland GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=84f7ffe8f0bf5b91','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2354,NULL,'job','(Senior) Consultant Technology Transformation - Data & AI (Financial Services) (w/m/d)','','50667 Köln',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Are you ready to shape your future with confidence?\nGemeinsam die Welt jeden Tag ein bisschen besser machen. Für diesen Anspruch setzen wir bei EY alles in Bewegung und gehen als Team „all in“. Schließlich haben wir ein klares Ziel vor Augen: nachhaltigen Wert und Wachstum zu schaffen – für unsere Mandant:innen, Mitarbeitenden und die gesamte Gesellschaft. Unser globales Netzwerk aus rund 400.000 Mitarbeitenden weltweit bietet dir alle Möglichkeiten zu wachsen, dich zu entwickeln, dich zu spezialisieren sowie deine Stärken und Interessen beruflich zu verfolgen. Wir glauben daran, dass der richtige Karriereweg so individuell ist wie du.\n\nUnser Bereich Financial Services fokussiert sich auf Finanzdienstleistungen und unterstützt Banken, Versicherungen und Asset Manager dabei, in einer sich stets verändernden und schnelllebigen Welt erfolgreich zu sein.\n\nDeine Aufgaben\nAls Teil unseres auf den Finanzdienstleistungssektor spezialisierten Data & AI Teams in München, Frankfurt/Main, Düsseldorf, Köln, Stuttgart, Hamburg oder Berlin berätst du unsere Kund:innen zu Themen rund um die Konzeption und den Aufbau modernster Datenplattformen, sowie bei der Umsetzung von innovativen Advanced Analytics, Machine Learning und AI-Anwendungen und bei der Operationalisierung dieser Anwendungen. Du begleitest Automatisierungs- und Transformationsvorhaben für international agierende Konzerne der Finanzbranche. Dabei übernimmst du vielfältige Aufgaben:\n\nBeratung unserer Kund:innen bei der Entwicklung von Lösungen für herausfordernde Problemstellungen mit Hilfe von Advanced Analytics und AI, von der Konzeption über die Strategie bis hin zur Umsetzung\nKonzeption und Aufbau modernster Datenplattformen und eines entsprechenden Datenmanagements, sowie die Umsetzung geschäftsrelevanter Anwendungen\nAktive Einbindung in die Durchführung und die Planung sämtlicher Phasen innerhalb großer IT-Transformationsprojekte\nDurchführung von Datenanalysen und die Aufbereitung von strukturierten und unstrukturierten Daten, plus Mitwirken bei der Auswahl geeigneter Datenquellen und Aufbau der dazugehörigen Datenströme und -architekturen\nEigenverantwortliche Übernahme von Teilaufgaben in der Weiterentwicklung unseres Service Portfolios als Teil unserer Data & AI Community\n\nDein Skillset\n\nAbgeschlossenes Studium der (Wirtschafts-) Informatik, (Wirtschafts-) Mathematik, Physik, Statistik, des Ingenieurwesens oder einer anderen Studienrichtung mit technologisch-analytischem Hintergrund\nErste Erfahrungen im Finanzsektor (Versicherungen, Banken oder ähnlichen Bereichen), Datenmanagement, Data Engineering oder Data Science mit IT-Orientierung, zudem idealerweise Kenntnisse im Bereich Cloud-Technologien\nSehr gute Kommunikationsfähigkeiten in Deutsch (mindestens C1-Niveau) und Englisch\n\nDein Mindset\n\nAgil: Du bist der Meinung, dass eine flexible Denkweise genauso wichtig für den Erfolg ist wie Wissen und Fähigkeiten.\nNeugierig: Du bist ambitioniert und engagiert. Wir suchen Menschen, die in Chancen und nicht in Herausforderungen denken und durch gezielte Fragen bessere Lösungen finden.\nTeamorientiert: Du schätzt vielfältige Perspektiven und arbeitest gerne im Team. Wir suchen Menschen, die gemeinsam mit uns etwas erreichen und ein vertrauensvolles Arbeitsumfeld schaffen wollen.\n\nDeine Benefits\n\nBei EY arbeitest du in leistungsstarken, interdisziplinären Teams mit innovativen Technologien. In einem flexiblen und inklusiven Arbeitsumfeld unterstützen wir dich in deinen unterschiedlichen Lebenssituationen. Inspirierende Kolleg:innen sowie Trainings- und Entwicklungsmöglichkeiten on- und off-the-Job helfen dir dabei, über dich hinauszuwachsen und die Fähigkeiten weiterzuentwickeln, die du zukünftig brauchst. Eine steile Lernkurve ist dir garantiert. Mehr über unsere Benefits.\n\nBewirb dich noch heute!\nMehr Informationen zum Bewerbungsprozess bei EY findest du auf unserer Karriereseite.\n\nWeitere Informationen zu Financial Services findest du hier.\nWas andere über uns sagen, findest du auf kununu und Glassdoor.\n\nBei EY leben wir Vielfalt und begrüßen alle Bewerbungen. Sag uns gerne frühzeitig Bescheid, wenn wir dich hinsichtlich eines barrierefreien Bewerbungsprozesses unterstützen können.\n\nDu hast noch Fragen? Unser Recruitment Center beantwortet diese gerne unter +49 6196 996 10005.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'EY','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f1b0ca460594de7b','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2355,NULL,'job','Data Scientist (m/f/x)','Vollzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'At Enpal, we are not just a company; we are a movement. As a recognized greentech unicorn and one of Europe’s fastest-growing energy companies, we’re dedicated to making solar energy accessible and effortless for homeowners across the continent. Our innovative business model for solar panels, heat pumps, home energy storage systems, and EV charging stations is redefining the residential energy market. With our mission to empower homeowners to embrace clean energy, we are paving the way for a sustainable, decentralized energy future.\n\nAs the leading player in residential solar, Enpal is expanding its next frontier: Enpal Energy, our platform for managing, optimizing, and orchestrating millions of distributed energy assets. This includes building Europe’s largest Virtual Power Plant (VPP), connecting solar systems, batteries, heat pumps, and EV chargers to actively stabilize the grid and unlock new revenue streams for our customers.\n\nOur vision is bold: to become the driving force in Europe’s transition to distributed, intelligent, and clean energy generation.\n\nWe are looking for a Data Scientist to join our growing Energy Data Science team. Our forecasting models directly support energy trading decisions across one of Europe\'s largest residential energy communities, and your work will have measurable impact on how we participate in the energy market. This role is ideal for a hands-on data scientist with strong software engineering skills and experience contributing across the full data and ML stack.\n\nWhat you\'ll do\n\nResearch, develop, and productionize time series forecasting models for energy markets (e.g. load, generation, and weather forecasting), owning the full lifecycle from data exploration and feature engineering through model training, evaluation, deployment, monitoring, and retraining.\n\nContribute to our MLOps infrastructure: experiment tracking, model versioning, automated retraining pipelines, and production observability.\n\nCommunicate forecasting performance and model insights to trading and product stakeholders, connecting technical results to business impact.\n\nCollaborate closely with Data Engineers, Software Engineers, and Product to deliver well-engineered, reliable data science products.\n\nHelp shape our data science roadmap and contribute to the direction of next-generation forecasting approaches.\n\nMentor and support junior data scientists, fostering a culture of continuous learning and technical growth.\n\nWhat you\'ll bring\n\nUniversity degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, or a related quantitative field.\n\n3+ years of industry experience in machine learning with a focus on time series forecasting, or in data science applied to the energy sector or complex distributed systems.\n\nProficiency in Python and SQL, with strong software engineering fundamentals: testing, code quality, version control, and CI/CD.\n\nProven experience deploying and monitoring machine learning models in production.\n\nPractical experience with data engineering tasks: pipeline development, data quality management, and feature engineering at scale, with the ability to build, debug, and maintain these independently.\n\nExperience with cloud infrastructure (Azure, AWS, or GCP).\n\nHands-on experience with MLOps practices and tooling: experiment tracking, model registries, automated retraining workflows, and CI/CD for ML.\n\nExperience with Snowflake or similar cloud data warehouses.\n\nExperience with distributed data processing frameworks (PySpark, Dask, or similar).\n\nEnd-to-end ownership mindset: comfortable independently driving a project from research through production.\n\nFluent in English.\n\nNice to have...\n\nExperience in the energy industry, particularly in energy trading, energy market structures (day-ahead, intraday, balancing), or virtual power plants.\n\nDeep experience with time series forecasting methods.\n\nExperience working with weather data or numerical weather prediction models.\n\nExperience scaling ML systems, managing many models in parallel, or high-throughput inference.\n\nExperience with probabilistic forecasting or uncertainty quantification.\n\nWhat we offer\n\nWork at Germany\'s first green unicorn - Play an active role in shaping the solar energy transition.\n\nThe sun shines all over the world - At Enpal, you\'ll work with a highly motivated, diverse team of over 65 nationalities.\n\nThe ideal setup for your focus - We are convinced that excellent results are achieved when the conditions are right. That\'s why we rely on a hybrid working concept that gives you the freedom to always work in the way that best suits your tasks. Do you need new inspiration on an international level? With Workflex, we offer you the opportunity to relocate abroad for up to 30 days a year, depending on your responsibilities.\n\nGrown-up business & startup spirit - In our modern office in Berlin-Friedrichshain, you\'ll find everything your heart desires, from height-adjustable desks and table tennis to stocked beverage fridges and barista coffee.\n\nYour kick-start at Enpal - Onboarding day with a welcome bag, buddy program, and a team that really supports you.\n\nStay up to date & help shape the future - Transparent all-hands meetings, short decision-making processes, and an open feedback culture - without mistakes, there is no progress.\n\nThe energy transition can only be achieved together - At Enpal, you can expect legendary team spirit and unforgettable team events.\n\nYour extra boost - 29 + 2 vacation days, discounted membership at Wellhub, and corporate benefits. Everything you need to help you achieve a good work-life balance.\n\nAt Enpal, we are proud of the diversity of our team. No decisions are made on the basis of skin colour, religion or religious belief, ethnic or national origin, nationality, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability or age, either during recruitment or employment. Enpal stands for a safe workplace and takes action against discrimination and harassment of any kind.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Enpal','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e36cafcb942f2e04','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2356,NULL,'job','Machine Learning Engineer – Retail & Buying (m/f/d))','','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Our Mission\nLimango is a unique online destination created with families in mind, delighting customers daily with an outstanding selection of brands at attractive prices. Headquartered in the heart of Munich, our centrally located office is home to 300 passionate employees who share a deep commitment to understanding and fulfilling the needs of families.\n\nAt limango, you’ll find everything a family could need: fashion for babies, kids, women, and men, as well as homeware, toys, cosmetics, and family holiday offers. We proudly feature a mix of classic, well-established brands alongside emerging, innovative European labels.\nFounded in 2007 and a proud member of the Otto Group since 2009, limango now serves over 22 million members across Germany, Austria, the Netherlands, and Poland. We sell over 40,000 products daily to German customers alone.\n\nOur ambition is to keep growing and earn the trust of families, especially moms, throughout Europe. To help us achieve this goal, we are looking for motivated, talented individuals eager to join us and be part of something big.\n\nWe foster a culture built around hybrid work in Munich (2 days in the office), while staying open to remote talent who value collaboration and real impact.\nJoin the limango IT!\n\nAs a Machine Learning Engineer in our Retail ML team, you will take end‑to‑end ownership of designing, developing and maintaining advanced machine learning solutions that directly influence our commercial performance. Your work will span dynamic pricing, demand forecasting and data‑driven buying decisions, where you will build, optimize and productionize models operating at scale.\n\nYou will explore and implement LLM‑based methods and agentic AI approaches to enhance automation, decision support and model interpretability in real retail scenarios. A key part of your role will be building reliable, scalable data pipelines and ensuring high‑quality data flows across our ML ecosystem.\n\nYou will collaborate closely with business stakeholders, product teams and data specialists to translate complex retail challenges into measurable ML outcomes, ensuring that models deliver tangible business value. You will join a focused team of three Machine Learning Engineers and report directly to the ML Retail Team Lead.\n\nYour Profile\n\nTechnical expertise\n\nProven experience as a Machine Learning Engineer (mid–senior), working with end‑to‑end ML systems in production.\nStrong command of Python (data processing, model development, performance optimization) and SQL (analytical queries, data modelling)\nPractical experience with ML frameworks such as TensorFlow, scikit‑learn, XGBoost and/or LightGBM, including model training, tuning and deployment\nHands‑on experience with Google Cloud Platform (GCP) services used in ML workloads (e.g., Cloud Storage, BigQuery, Vertex AI, Cloud Functions)\nFamiliarity with Apache Airflow for orchestrating data pipelines and ML workflows\nFluency in English for technical documentation and cross‑team collaboration\n\nNice to have\n\nDomain knowledge in retail, e‑commerce or supply chain, especially data patterns and operational constraints.\nExperience building and maintaining pricing, demand forecasting or other time‑series models in production environments.\nUnderstanding of ETL/ELT pipelines, MLOps practices, CI/CD for ML, feature stores and model monitoring.\nHands‑on experience with Large Language Models, prompt engineering, fine‑tuning or integrating LLMs into production systems.\n\nPersonal qualities\n\nStrong analytical reasoning and a structured approach to designing ML solutions.\nCuriosity and willingness to experiment with emerging technologies, architectures and modelling techniques.\nAbility to explain complex ML concepts, trade‑offs and model behaviour to non‑technical stakeholders.\nProactive, ownership‑driven mindset with focus on delivering reliable production systems.\nComfort working with incomplete information, evolving requirements and iterative discovery.\nTeam‑oriented attitude, openness to code reviews, architectural discussions and collaborative problem‑solving.\nOur Offer\nHybrid working model for people from Munich, remote working for people from other locations.\nA Culture That Feels Like Home, open, team-oriented atmosphere.\nRoom to Grow, take ownership of your work with creative freedom in a fast-moving company.\nWork in the Heart of Munich, our office is centrally located.\nContinuous Learning, access to language courses and tailored development programs.\nPerks That Matter, we subsidize your MVG ticket, EGYM Wellpass or JobBike to support your mobility and well-being.\nCompany Events, regular company events that our culture and bring the team together.\nWe look forward to your application!\nWe look forward to receiving your complete application, including a letter of motivation, references/ certificates, salary expectations and your earliest possible start date. We can\'t wait to get to know you. Apply now!\n\nJoanna Wójtowicz\nRecruiting Manager','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'limango GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=687f7f41ae4433e5','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2357,NULL,'job','Praktikant:in (m/w/d) in der Softwareentwicklung, ab 09/2026','Vollzeit','10245 Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Wenn aus Theorie Praxis wird\n\nSoftware und Programmieren, neue Technik und Technologien sind genau deins? Im Studium hast du schon vieles gelernt, das du jetzt in der Praxis in echten Projekten anwenden möchtest? Du arbeitest eigenständig und gleichzeitig gern im Team?\nDann bist du bei uns mehr als richtig. In deinem Praktikum bei uns lernst und vertiefst du das, was dich ohnehin schon interessiert. Und das nicht nur durch Zugucken, sondern durch Machen. Dabei unterstützen und begleiten dich unsere Entwickler:innen ab dem ersten Tag.\n\nBei BettercallPaul herrscht eine echte Leidenschaft für Softwarelösungen, Machine Learning und Data Science. Wir sind Expert:innen für komplexe und geschäftskritische Software, die wir individuell für unsere Kunden konzipieren und entwickeln. Unser Team besteht aus hochqualifizierten und motivierten Kolleg:innen und zur Unterstützung in spannenden Projekten suchen wir – dich!\n\nDu wirst:\n\nSoftware gemeinsam mit erfahrenen Entwickler:innen für Kundenprojekte entwickeln\nim Team agile Software erdenken und mitprogrammieren\nvon Frontend bis Backend überall dabei sein\neigenverantwortlich technisch Lösungsbausteine entwickeln\nfür Anwendungen mithelfen, die höchste Qualität zu sichern\nVorschläge und Ideen einbringen, die Beitrag zum gemeinsamen Projekterfolg sind\n\nDu hast:\n\naktuell einen Studienplatz in Informatik oder einem vergleichbaren Studiengang mit IT-Affinität\ngroßes Interesse an der Softwareentwicklung\nerste Erfahrung in einer objektorientierten Programmiersprache gesammelt, idealerweise\nJava\nLust darauf, Neues zu lernen und auszuprobieren\nSpaß daran, eigenverantwortlich Aufgaben zu übernehmen\neine strukturierte, analytische und lösungsorientierte Arbeitsweise\ngute Deutschkenntnisse\n\nDu triffst auf:\n\neine steile Lernkurve durch abwechslungsreiche Aufgaben mit hoher Eigenverantwortung\neine ausführliche Einarbeitung und eine optimale Betreuung in einem tollen Team\nflexible Arbeitszeiten und mobiles Arbeiten\neine teamorientierte Unternehmenskultur mit Events auch nach getaner Arbeit\n\nKontakt\n\nInteressant? Dann bewirb dich jetzt!\nDu hast Fragen zur Stelle, zum Unternehmen oder zum Bewerbungsprozess? Dann melde dich gern bei unserem Recruiter Marvin!\n\nMarvin:\n+49 151 40 22 97 89\nmarvin.streich@bcxp.de\n\nBitte füge deiner Bewerbung deinen aktuellen Lebenslauf, eine aktuelle Notenübersicht und ein kurzes Anschreiben bei.\n\nBettercallPaul GmbH | Boxhagener Straße 78 | 10245 Berlin\n\nÜber uns\n\nErfolgreiche Softwarelösungen brauchen ein Team aus einzigartigen Menschen. Wir halten zusammen und wir unterstützen uns – wir sind ein Team, ohne Wenn und Aber! Und gleichzeitig darfst du bei uns der Mensch sein, der du bist. Und du darfst dich zu dem Menschen entwickeln, der du sein möchtest.\n\nDu willst komplexe Aufgaben, für die es bislang keine Lösung gibt? Einen Job, bei dem du gemeinsam mit deinen Kolleg:innen Software mit Substanz entwickelst? Du suchst eine Aufgabe, bei der du eine gute Balance zwischen deinem Privat- und Berufsleben hast? Dann entdecke unsere Möglichkeiten für dich.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'BettercallPaul gmbh','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1ced3f8843b9b694','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2358,NULL,'job','Senior Consultant Analytics (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','44263 Dortmund',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Senior Consultant Analytics (m/w/d)\nDie Apps Associates GmbH…\n\n…ist ein weltweit tätiges IT-Beratungsunternehmen, das seine Kunden im Rahmen von Software-Projekten unterstützt. Unsere Leistungen umfassen Beratung, Entwicklung, Service und Implementierung im Bereich der Oracle Software Produkte. Nach Gründung des Unternehmens im Jahre 2002 in den USA folgte die Eröffnung des Global Development Center in Indien sowie 2006 der Europazentrale in Dortmund. Derzeit unterstützen über 1400 Mitarbeiter unsere Kunden dabei, die optimalen Lösungen zu finden und tragen somit zum Erfolg des Unternehmens bei.\n\nWas dich bei uns erwartet:\n\nDu berätst interne und externe Stakeholder zu analytischen Fragestellungen und datenbasierten Lösungsansätzen.\n\nDu analysierst komplexe Datenbestände und identifizierst Trends, Muster sowie konkrete Handlungsempfehlungen.\n\nDu konzipierst, entwickelst und implementierst Analytics ‑ , Reporting ‑ und Business ‑ Intelligence ‑ Lösungen.\n\nDu baust Dashboards, KPIs und datengetriebene Steuerungsmodelle auf und entwickelst diese kontinuierlich weiter.\n\nDu entwickelst und betreibst Data ‑ Warehouse ‑ Lösungen nach gängigen Modellierungsansätzen (z. B. Data Vault, Star ‑ Schema).\n\nDu konzipierst und entwickelst ETL ‑ Strecken zur Datenintegration aus verschiedenen Quellsystemen.\n\nDu übersetzt fachliche Anforderungen in technische Konzepte und tragfähige Datenmodelle.\n\nDu stellst Datenqualität, Datenkonsistenz und Data ‑ Governance sicher.\n\nDu präsentierst Analyseergebnisse auf Management ‑ Ebene und leitest konkrete Empfehlungen ab.\n\nDu unterstützt Junior Consultants fachlich und übernimmst Mentoring ‑ Aufgaben.\n\nOptional wirkst du bei Angebots ‑ und Projektakquise mit.\n\nWas wir uns von dir Wünschen:\n\nDu verfügst über ein abgeschlossenes Studium der (Wirtschafts) Informatik, Data Science, Statistik, Mathematik, Wirtschaftswissenschaften oder eine vergleichbare Qualifikation.\n\nDu bringst mindestens 5 Jahre relevante Berufserfahrung im Bereich Analytics, Business Intelligence oder Data Consulting mit.\n\nDu hast fundierte Kenntnisse in mindestens einem der folgenden Bereiche:\n\nDatenanalyse & Statistik\n\nBusiness Intelligence / Reporting\n\nAdvanced Analytics / Predictive Analytics\n\nFundierte Erfahrung mit folgenden Tools & Technologien (Fokus Oracle):\n\nOracle Data Integrator (ODI)\n\nOracle Database & Data‑Warehouse‑Implementierungen\n\nOracle Business Intelligence (OBIEE) / Oracle Analytics Server\n\nPL/SQL‑Entwicklung\n\nGute Kenntnisse in Datenmodellierung, ETL‑Prozessen und Datenarchitekturen.\n\nWünschenswert: Erfahrung mit PostgreSQL.\n\nInteresse an KI‑ und Machine‑Learning‑Themen sowie datengetriebenen Innovationen.\n\nVerständnis für betriebswirtschaftliche Zusammenhänge und Geschäftsprozesse.\n\nStrukturierte, eigenverantwortliche und lösungsorientierte Arbeitsweise.\n\nSehr gute Deutsch‑ und gute Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift für den Einsatz im internationalen Umfeld.\n\nWas wir bieten:\n\nFörderung Deiner betrieblichen Altersvorsorge\n\nEine offene Unternehmenskultur, per „Du\" und ohne Dresscode\n\nEine familiäre Arbeitsatmosphäre und flexible Arbeitszeiten für eine gesunde Work-Life-Balance\n\nDeine Entscheidung: Arbeiten im Homeoffice oder in unserem modernen Büro mit Blick auf den Phönixsee\n\nVier Zertifizierungen im Jahr werden von uns bezahlt und monetär belohnt\n\nKostenlose Getränke (Kaffee, Tee, Softdrinks, Wasser) und Süßigkeiten aus unserer Candy Bar\n\nEine professionelle Einarbeitung und Einblicke in internationale Projekte von weltbekannten Kunden\n\nMöglichkeit auf ein Jobrad und einen Dienstwagen\n\nFirmenhandy zur privaten Nutzung\n\nHaben wir Dein Interesse geweckt?\n\nDann lass uns doch ganz unkompliziert sprechen: Schick mir einfach eine Nachricht – ein Anschreiben brauchst Du nicht. Wir vereinbaren direkt einen kurzen Teamscall.\n\nDeine Ansprechpartnerin:\n\nSybille Kutscher\n\nDirector HR & Recruiting\n\n+49 151 21714547\n\nsybille.kutscher@appsassociates.com\n\nwww.appsassociates.com','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Apps Associates','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=56fddadd2ead8ef2','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2359,NULL,'job','Data & AI Engineer (w/m/d), remote in DE','Vollzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Location\n\nGermany; Berlin; Darmstadt; Frankfurt; Hamburg; Köln; Magstadt; München\n\nEmployment Type\n\nFull time\n\nLocation Type\n\nRemote\n\nDepartment\n\nPCG x Data & AI\n„Cloud ist deine Welt – egal ob AWS, Microsoft, Google oder SAP? Dann passt du zu uns! Bei Public Cloud Group (PCG) begleiten wir Unternehmen dabei, ihre IT-Landschaften in der Cloud modern, sicher und zukunftsfähig zu gestalten.\n\nFast 500 Cloud-Expert:innen an 21 Standorten innerhalb Europas sind schon Teil unseres Teams – und wir wachsen weiter. Hast du Lust, dein Know-how bei uns in PCG DACH einzubringen, in einem Team, das genau so Cloud-verrückt ist wie du?“\n\nMehr darüber, wie die Arbeit bei uns aussieht, kannst du auf unserer Karriereseite erfahren.\n\nWorum geht´s?\n\nAls (Senior) Data & AI Engineer (w/m/d) in unserer Hyperscaler-agnostischen Data & AI Area bist du die gestaltende Kraft, um State-of-the-Art Machine Learning und Generative AI in die echte Anwendung bei unseren Kunden zu bringen. Du arbeitest als Teil unseres internen Delivery-Teams (bei uns gibt es kein Bodyleasing) und begleitest zukunftsweisende AI-Initiativen von der ersten kreativen Idee bis hin zur stabilen, skalierbaren Architektur.\n\nIn dieser Rolle nutzt du deine Souveränität in modernen Cloud-Strukturen (AWS, Google Cloud oder Microsoft Azure), um Managed AI-Dienste wie Vertex AI, AWS Bedrock oder Azure AI Foundry geschickt zu orchestrieren. Du entwickelst intelligente Agentic Workflows, integrierst Sprachmodelle (LLMs) und baust durchdachte RAG-Architekturen auf.\n\nDein Ziel ist es, technologische Innovationen mit Handwerkskunst und Engineering-Exzellenz zu verbinden, um messbare Mehrwerte zu schaffen und die Visionen unserer Kunden Wirklichkeit werden zu lassen.\n\nDas wirst Du tun:\n\nMitgestaltung zukunftsweisender AI-Lösungen: Du verantwortest das Design und die Entwicklung moderner Machine-Learning-Lösungen, um komplexe Herausforderungen unserer Kunden nachhaltig zu lösen.\n\nAufbau intelligenter GenAI-Strukturen: Du gestaltest und integrierst innovative Generative AI Lösungen sowie RAG-Architekturen und begleitest den Aufbau moderner Agentic Tools.\n\nOrchestrierung moderner Cloud-AI-Dienste: Souverän nutzt und vernetzt du die AI-Services führender Hyperscaler wie Google Vertex AI und Azure AI Foundry, um technologische Potenziale voll auszuschöpfen.\n\nBrückenschlag zur Produktion (MLOps): Du entwickelst ML-Modelle nicht nur, sondern sicherst durch professionelles Engineering und Operationalisierung (MLOps) deren reibungslose Einbindung in echte Produktivsysteme.\n\nGanzheitliche Begleitung & Beratung: Als fachliche Vertrauensperson begleitest du unsere Kunden von der ersten kreativen Ideation (PoC) bis zum erfolgreichen produktiven Rollout ihrer AI-Anwendungsfälle.\n\nImpulsgeberin für technologische Trends: Du hast den AI-Markt im Blick, evaluierst neue Technologien mit Neugier und entwickelst unsere \"Data & AI Area\" durch deine Impulse aktiv weiter.\n\nDas wünschen wir uns vor dir:\n\nFundierte Projekterfahrung: Du blickst auf einige Jahre Erfahrung im IT-Projektgeschäft zurück, in denen du dich intensiv mit Machine Learning, AI und moderner Datenverarbeitung auseinandergesetzt hast.\n\nSicherheit in Cloud-Umgebungen: Du fühlst dich in mindestens einem der drei großen Hyperscaler (AWS, Google Cloud oder Microsoft Azure) zu Hause und weißt, wie man deren Potenziale nutzt.\n\nRoutine in Python & Frameworks: Du beherrschst Python sicher und bringst praktische Erfahrung mit gängigen ML/AI-Frameworks in unsere Projekte ein.\n\nPraxis mit AI-Ecosystemen: Du hast bereits aktiv mit Plattformen wie Vertex AI, AWS Bedrock oder Azure AI Foundry gearbeitet und Lösungen darin umgesetzt.\n\nBegeisterung für GenAI: Du bringst Hands-on-Erfahrung mit LLMs und Prompt Engineering mit und hast bereits erste Agentic Workflows (z. B. via LangChain oder LlamaIndex) gestaltet.\n\nGanzheitliches Architekturverständnis: Du verstehst die Grundlagen der API-Entwicklung und Cloud-Architekturen, um AI-Modelle nahtlos und stabil in bestehende Systeme zu integrieren.\n\nKommunikationsstärke: Es bereitet dir Freude, komplexe AI-Konzepte verständlich zu vermitteln und unsere Kunden bei ihren strategischen Entscheidungen zu begleiten.\n\nData Engineering Grundlagen: Idealerweise hast du ein solides Fundament in SQL oder modernen Data Warehouses (z. B. BigQuery, Snowflake), um die Datenaufbereitung für deine Modelle selbstständig voranzutreiben.\n\nWissen über Vector-Datenbanken: Du hast bereits erste Berührungspunkte mit Vector-Datenbanken (z. B. Vertex AI Vector Search, Azure AI Search oder pgvector) gesammelt.\n\nFachspezifische Zertifizierungen: Du hast Zertifizierungen im Bereich Machine Learning / AI in Google und Azure absolviert oder hast Lust, diese bei uns mit unserer Unterstützung zu erwerben. Bestenfalls bringst Du Kenntnisse in AWS Bedrock mit.\n\nTeamfähigkeit und Drive: Du überzeugst mit Ergebnisorientierung und der Freude an der Zusammenarbeit mit unserem diversen Team, bestehend aus Experten mit Leidenschaft.\n\nWas hast Du davon:\n\nFlexibilität pur: Arbeite so, wie es zu deinem Leben passt. Remote oder im Office, Arbeitsgebiete bundesweit oder in einem unserer Offices in Deutschland (Magstadt, Darmstadt, Berlin, München, Hamburg, Köln, Ulm, Heidelberg, Frankfurt).\n\nWorkation: Arbeiten & neue Orte entdecken? Nutze bis zu 30 Tage Workation im Jahr und verbinde Job & Abenteuer.\n\nAuszeiten: Mit 30 Tagen Urlaub tankst du Energie, wann immer du sie brauchst.\n\nDeine Hardware, deine Wahl: Mac, Windows oder Linux – du entscheidest, womit du am liebsten arbeitest.\n\nWeiterkommen: Schulungen, Labs und Zertifizierungen bei AWS, Azure, Google & SAP – wir pushen dein Cloud-Know-how.\n\nFeedback, das zählt: Regelmäßige Entwicklungs- und Gehaltsgespräche, damit du genau weißt, wo du stehst.\n\nMehr als Basics: wähle zwischen Spendit Card, oder Wellpass oder Deutschlandticket. On top Kita-Zuschuss und Bikeleasing als weitere Extras für dein Leben abseits des Laptops.\n\nTeamspirit: Ob Teamevents (altern. Hackathons), Sommerfest oder Weihnachtsfeier – wir feiern Erfolge zusammen.\n\nKlingt das gut?\n\nSuper, dann schicke uns jetzt deine Bewerbung über das Bewerberportal - Keine Sorge, es dauert keine 60 Sekunden.\n\nWir freuen uns auf Dich!\n\nBei uns zählt das Talent, nicht das Etikett – wir heißen Bewerber:innen jeglicher Herkunft und Identität herzlich willkommen, unabhängig von Geschlecht, Nationalität, ethnischer und sozialer Herkunft, Weltanschauung, Behinderung, Alter sowie sexueller Orientierung und Identität.\n\n_______\n\nRecruitment Agencies:\n\nWe at PCG have an in-house recruitment team, which focuses on sourcing great candidates directly. PCG does not accept unsolicited resumes from agency or search firm recruiters. Fees will not be paid in the event a candidate submitted by a recruiter without an agreement in place is hired. When we do use agencies, we have a PSL in place, so please do not contact managers directly.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Public Cloud Group Holding GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ea16fd044027738d','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2360,NULL,'job','Wissenschaftliche*r Mitarbeiter*in (w/m/d) Künstliche Intelligenz / Machine Learning – Projekt iTAS-PLMS','Teilzeit','Ulm',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Im Institut für Medizintechnik und Mechatronik der THU ist zum frühestmöglichen Zeitpunkt die Teilzeitstelle (80%) mit der Möglichkeit zur Promotion zu besetzen:\n\nWissenschaftliche*r Mitarbeiter*in (w/m/d) Künstliche Intelligenz / Machine Learning – Projekt iTAS-PLMS\niTAS-PLMS (interactive Therapy Assistance System for patients with Periodic Limb Movement during Sleep) ist ein vom Bundesministerium für Bildung und Forschung gefördertes Projekt. Das Ziel dieses Projekts ist die Erforschung eines Sensorsystems, das die Therapie und Diagnostik des Restleg Legs Syndroms in häuslicher Umgebung verbessern soll.\n\nIhre Aufgaben an der THU:\n\nEntwicklung von technischen Prototypen (Hard- und Software), um Messungen mit Probanden durchzuführen zu können.\nUnterstützung bei der Durchführung von Messungen im Rahmen von Messkampagnen in klinischer sowie häuslicher Umgebung.\nErforschung von robusten Maschine Learning Algorithmen zur Auswertung der erhobenen Daten.\nErstellung wissenschaftlicher Publikationen, Berichte und Präsentationen, Teilnahme an Fachveranstaltungen und Konferenzen.\n\nDas bringen Sie mit:\n\nEinen wissenschaftlichen Hochschulabschluss (Master / Uni-Diplom) mit sehr gutem Abschluss in einem Studiengang im Bereich Mechatronik, Medizintechnik, Informatik, Elektrotechnik, Computational Science & Engineering o.ä.\nSehr gute Programmierkenntnisse, idealerweise in Python\nSehr gute Kenntnisse in Elektronikentwicklung und künstlicher Intelligenz ist gewünscht\nBefähigung und Bereitschaft zur Teilnahme an einem Promotionsprogramm\nAusgeprägte Flexibilität, Lernbereitschaft, Bereitschaft zu interdisziplinärer Kooperation und Teamfähigkeit\nSehr gute Kommunikationsfähigkeit, in Wort und Schrift, in deutscher und englischer Sprache\n\nDas erwartet Sie bei uns:\n\nEine promotionsgeeignete Stelle in einem zukunftsweisenden KI-Forschungsprojekt\nMitarbeit an einem hochrelevanten Forschungsvorhaben mit direkter industrieller Anwendung\nEnge Zusammenarbeit mit einem interdisziplinären Team aus Hochschule und Medizin\nEnge wissenschaftliche Betreuung und regelmäßige Team Events\nDie Möglichkeit, Forschungsergebnisse in Publikationen, Demonstratoren und industrielle Anwendungen zu überführen\nAls zertifizierte familienbewusste Hochschule ermöglichen wir Ihnen flexible und mobile Arbeitsmöglichkeiten, die sich mit Ihrem Familienleben verbinden lassen\nWir unterstützen Ihre Entwicklung durch vielfältige, auch individuelle Fort- und Weiterbildungsangebote\nWir bieten Ihnen zahlreiche Angebote in den Bereichen Sport und Gesundheit und bezuschussen Ihr Deutschlandticket\nEin motiviertes Team begleitet Sie bei Ihrem Einstieg\nWir fördern Diversität und Inklusion und schaffen ein Arbeitsumfeld, das die Vielfalt unserer Mitarbeitenden wertschätzt\nDurch die hohe Lebensqualität in der attraktiven Region Ulm können Sie die perfekte Balance zwischen Beruf und Freizeit genießen\n\nFür inhaltliche Fragen zur Stelle steht Ihnen der Teilprojektleiter Prof. Dr. Michael Munz unter michael.munz@thu.de gerne zur Verfügung.\n\nWeitere Informationen und Kontaktmöglichkeiten:\n\nDie Entgeltzahlung erfolgt entsprechend Ihrer Qualifikation in EG 13.\n\nDas Arbeitsverhältnis ist befristet bis 31.01.2028. Die Stelle ist grundsätzlich teilbar.\n\nFalls Sie Ihren Hochschulabschluss im Ausland erlangt haben, fügen Sie Ihren Unterlagen bitte zusätzlich eine Zeugnisbewertung der Zentralstelle für ausländisches Bildungswesen (ZAB) bei.\n\nDie Technische Hochschule Ulm fördert aktiv die Gleichstellung aller Mitarbeitenden. Schwerbehinderte Menschen werden bei entsprechender Eignung bevorzugt eingestellt.\n\nHaben wir Ihr Interesse geweckt? Dann freuen wir uns auf Ihre Bewerbung bis zum 01.06.2026 ausschließlich über unser Bewerbungsportal (Kenn-Nr.: 11-2026).','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Technischen Hochschule Ulm','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=557980efebbcbc16','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2361,NULL,'job','SENIOR CONSULTANT DATA PLATFORMS & AI (M/W/D)','Vollzeit','Hannover',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Cratos GmbH\nHannover\nPräsenz / Mobil\nBerufserfahrung\nVollzeit\nPubliziert: 30.04.2026\nSENIOR CONSULTANT DATA PLATFORMS & AI (M/W/D)\nDie Cratos GmbH ist ein inhabergeführtes Beratungsunternehmen mit Sitz in Hannover. Als international agierender Beratungspartner konzentrieren wir uns auf die Themen Strategie, Change-Management, IT-Unterstützung, sowie auf Technologie- und Innovationsmanagement. Unser Kundenkreis besteht aus deutschen, sowie auch anderen europäischen Unternehmen vorrangig aus den Branchen Energie, Banken, Versicherung, IT und Industrie. CRATOS GmbH ist mehr als eine Unternehmensberatung. Wir tragen Verantwortung für Mensch, Wirtschaft, Gesellschaft und Umwelt und entwickeln Produkte für eine erfolgreiche Energiewende. Nachhaltiges, partnerschaftliches und verantwortliches Denken leitet unser Handeln.\n\nAb sofort suchen wir eine*n Senior Consultant Data Platforms and AI (m/w/d)\n\nDeine Aufgaben:\n\nData & AI Architekturberatung\n\nKonzeption moderner Data-, Analytics- und AI-Architekturen für Kundenprojekte\nBewertung bestehender Systemlandschaften und Ableitung zukunftsfähiger Zielbilder\nEntwicklung skalierbarer Lösungen für Data Platforms, Reporting, Advanced Analytics und AI Use Cases\nSicherstellung von Architekturprinzipien hinsichtlich Performance, Sicherheit, Governance und Skalierbarkeit\nTechnische Beratung auf Management-, Fachbereichs- und IT-Ebene\n\nKundenprojekte & Delivery Excellence\n\nFachliche Verantwortung in anspruchsvollen Data- und Transformationsprojekten\nÜbersetzung fachlicher Anforderungen in umsetzbare technische Lösungsansätze\nSteuerung komplexer Workstreams an der Schnittstelle zwischen Business und IT\nQualitätssicherung von Konzepten, Lösungsdesigns und Umsetzungsergebnissen\nSparring für Projektleitungen, Consultants und Kundenteams\n\nData Strategy & Plattformen\n\nBeratung beim Aufbau moderner Datenplattformen und datengetriebener Operating Models\nEntwicklung von Roadmaps für Data Modernization, Cloud Transformation und Governance\nIdentifikation relevanter Use Cases mit messbarem Business Value\nUnterstützung bei Tool-, Plattform- und Technologieentscheidungen\nBegleitung von Migrations- und Transformationsvorhaben\n\nAI & Innovation\n\nIdentifikation, Bewertung und Priorisierung sinnvoller AI-Anwendungsfälle\nKonzeption von AI-fähigen Datenarchitekturen und Datenbereitstellung\nBeratung zu Themen wie GenAI, Machine Learning, Automatisierung und Data Products\nBeobachtung relevanter Markt- und Technologietrends\nEntwicklung innovativer Lösungsansätze für Kundenherausforderungen\n\nMarkt, Kunde & Business Development\n\nAktive Mitwirkung in Angebotsprozessen, Pitches und Kundenterminen\nFachliche Unterstützung bei der Positionierung von Data-&-AI-Leistungen\nÜbersetzung technischer Themen in klaren Business-Mehrwert\nAufbau vertrauensvoller Kundenbeziehungen auf Fach- und Managementebene\nMitwirkung bei der Weiterentwicklung des Beratungsportfolios\n\nStandards & Enablement\n\nWeiterentwicklung interner Methoden, Frameworks und Best Practices\nMentoring von Consultants und fachliche Unterstützung im Team\nWissensaufbau zu neuen Technologien, Plattformen und AI-Themen\nDurchführung interner Enablement-Formate, Workshops und Trainings\nBeitrag zum Aufbau von Thought Leadership im Bereich Data & AI\nDas bringst du mit:\nMehrjährige Erfahrung in der Konzeption, Umsetzung und Weiterentwicklung von Data-, Analytics- oder AI-Lösungen im Consulting- oder IT-Umfeld\nFundierte Erfahrung in modernen Data Architectures, Data Platforms und Cloud-basierten Ökosystemen (z. B. Azure, AWS, Google Cloud)\nSehr gutes Verständnis von Themen wie Data Warehousing, BI, Datenintegration, Governance und skalierbaren Plattformarchitekturen\nErfahrung in der technischen und fachlichen Steuerung komplexer Data-Projekte von der Strategie bis zur Umsetzung\nFähigkeit, Business-Anforderungen in tragfähige technische Lösungsansätze zu übersetzen\nErfahrung in der Bewertung und Konzeption von AI-Use-Cases, idealerweise in Bereichen wie GenAI, Machine Learning oder Automatisierung\nVerständnis der Anforderungen an Datenverfügbarkeit, Qualität und Governance als Grundlage erfolgreicher AI-Lösungen Erfahrung in der aktiven Mitarbeit bei Angebotsprozessen, Pitches und Kundenpräsentationen\nSouveränes Auftreten gegenüber Fachbereichen, IT-Leitungen sowie Management- und C-Level-Stakeholdern\nHervorragende Kommunikations-, Moderations- und Präsentationsfähigkeiten\nHohe Kundenorientierung sowie die Fähigkeit, Vertrauen und langfristige Beziehungen aufzubauen\nStrukturierte, lösungsorientierte und eigenverantwortliche Arbeitsweise\nUnternehmerisches Denken sowie Interesse an der Weiterentwicklung von Angeboten und Geschäftspotenzialen\nFreude daran, Wissen zu teilen, Kolleg:innen zu entwickeln und fachlich Orientierung zu geben\nMindestens 7–10 Jahre Berufserfahrung, davon idealerweise mehrere Jahre im Beratungsumfeld\nHochschulabschluss in Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Mathematik, Wirtschaft oder eine vergleichbare Qualifikation\nSehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\nReisebereitschaft, auch international\n\nVon Vorteil:\n\nErfahrung mit Microsoft Fabric, Databricks, Snowflake oder vergleichbaren Plattformen\nErfahrung in regulierten Branchen wie Finance, Healthcare, Public Sector oder Industrie\nZertifizierungen in Cloud-, Architektur- oder Data-Technologien\nNetzwerk im Markt zu potenziellen Kunden, Partnern oder Talenten\n\nDu erfüllst nicht alle Kriterien, bist aber trotzdem interessiert? Bewirb dich gerne!\n\nDas bieten wir dir:\n\nVerantwortungsvolle Tätigkeit\n\nDu übernimmst Verantwortung und gestaltest Projekte mit echtem Impact.\n\nZusammenarbeit mit renommierten Kunden\n\nSpannende Projekte mit führenden Unternehmen aus Energie, Industrie und IT warten auf dich.\n\nFlache Hierarchien\n\nKurze Wege, direkte Kommunikation, bei uns zählt dein Beitrag.\n\nModerne Arbeitsplatzausstattung\n\nWähle dein Notebook innerhalb unserer Standards selbst aus. Dazu erhältst du Smartphone und Monitor.\n\nFaires Gehalt\n\nEine Vergütung, die deine Leistung anerkennt.\n\nWeiterbildungen\n\nInterne und externe Trainings bringen dich fachlich und persönlich weiter.\n\nPersönliche Weiterentwicklung\n\nIndividuelle Entwicklungspläne und Feedback fördern dein Wachstum.\n\nHomeoffice & Flexibilität\n\nArbeite flexibel, im Büro oder von zuhause.\n\nBist du neugierig geworden und möchtest mit uns gemeinsam unsere Kunden zu mehr Erfolg verhelfen?\nDann freuen wir uns auf deine aussagekräftigen Bewerbungsunterlagen - ganz schnell und bequem direkt über unser Bewerbungsformular.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'CRATOS GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=554afea2f8c0d7db','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2362,NULL,'job','Praktikum Digitalisierung für Machine Learning (all genders)','Praktikum','14974 Ludwigsfelde',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Wir sind über 13.000. An 19 Standorten weltweit. Jedes dritte Flugzeug fliegt mit unserer Technologie.\nImmer effizienter, leiser, nachhaltiger. Wir gestalten die Zukunft der Luftfahrt. Was wir noch brauchen? Dich.\n\nUnser Team in Ludwigsfelde bei Berlin sucht Dich:\n\nPraktikum Digitalisierung für Machine Learning (all genders)\n\nSTARKE AUFGABEN\nEntwicklung, Implementierung und Optimierung von Machine-Learning-Modellen auf PoC Level\nSkalierung von Machine-Learning-Modellen für den Einsatz in produktiven Systemen, unter Berücksichtigung von Performance, Skalierbarkeit und Sicherheit\nAufbau, Testing und Verwaltung von Datenpipelines für Trainings- und Produktionssysteme\nDatenaufnahme, Qualitätssicherung und Feature Engineering\nEnge und eigenständige Zusammenarbeit mit Data Scientists, Softwareentwicklern und anderen Teams zur Integration von Modellen in bestehende Arbeitsabläufe\nRecherche, Evaluierung und Auswahl geeigneter Machine-Learning-Algorithmen und -Technologien, basierend auf aktuellen Forschungsergebnissen\nAdressatengerechte Dokumentation und Präsentation der entwickelten Modelle und deren Ergebnisse\nBESTE VORAUSSETZUNGEN\nStudium in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Mathematik, Statistik, Ingenieurwesen oder einer vergleichbaren Studienrichtung\nEinschlägige Erfahrung in der Entwicklung und Implementierung von Machine-Learning-Modellen vorzugsweise in Computer Vision Projekten und fundierte Kenntnisse in Python\nErfahrung mit Machine-Learning-Tools wie z.B. PyTorch und Scikit-learn\nKenntnisse in der Arbeit mit großen Datensätzen und Datenbanktechnologien\nErste Erfahrung in der Entwicklung von APIs und der Integration von ML-Modellen in produktive Umgebungen sowie Erfahrung mit Produktivierungstechnologien und Tools (Docker, Kubernetes, GitHub, VSCode, Linux) wünschenswert\nSehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse\nStarke analytische Fähigkeiten und die Fähigkeit, komplexe Zusammenhänge verständlich zu kommunizieren\nTeamfähigkeit und eine proaktive, selbstständige Arbeitsweise\nAUSGEZEICHNETES UMFELD\nEinblicke in die Luftfahrtbranche und Jobs mit Verantwortung\nTeamspirit u.a. durch Studi-Netzwerk & Events\nMentoring und individuelle Betreuung\nFlexible Arbeitszeitmodelle mit mobilem Arbeiten\nKantine und Snackautomaten\nMöglichkeit zur Teilnahme an örtlichen Laufevents\nKostenfreie Parkplätze\n\nSTARTKLAR?\n\nDann gib Deiner Bewerbung Schub und schick uns Deine Unterlagen (Lebenslauf, Notenübersicht der Hochschule, Schulabschlusszeugnis sowie eine aktuelle Immatrikulation) online. Gleich jetzt, gleich hier.\n\nWir freuen uns auf Dich!\n\nIhr:e Ansprechpartner:in im Personalbereich:\n\nDominik Pögl','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'MTU Maintenance Berlin-Brandenburg GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1f44e205657689bc','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2363,NULL,'job','IT Admin Working Student (all gender)- Hybrid, Berlin','Teilzeit','10827 Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Your mission\n\ndida is one of the leading machine learning agencies, working on assignments and projects in science, industry, and the public sector. Our Team, which mainly consists of machine learning scientists, contributes to new insights and innovations in AI research.\nWe aim to foster the responsible development and integration of machine learning across all areas of society and see ourselves as a bridge between research and industry applications. Become part of our team and support us!\n\nYour Tasks:\n\nLinux Administration: Patch management, monitoring, user management, as well as analysis and troubleshooting of our Linux systems.\n\nService Operations: Planning, provisioning, and configuration of internal services, including clean technical documentation.\n\nHardware Support: Assistance with the physical maintenance of server and client hardware, including component replacement.\n\nCI/CD & Automation: Contributing to the setup and maintenance of CI/CD pipelines as well as the automation of recurring operations tasks.\n\nFrontend for Internal Tools: Selective further development of small frontend applications for internal process tools.\n\nYour Profile\n\nEnrolled Student: You are studying Computer Science, Maths, or a similar field.\n\nLinux Skills: You have solid knowledge of Linux (Shell, package management, basic system administration).\n\nFrontend Basics: You have initial experience in frontend development (HTML, CSS, JavaScript).\n\nNetwork Knowledge: You possess a basic understanding of networks and common protocols.\n\nProblem Solver: You are eager to dive into new topics and solve problems independently.\n\nLocation & Duration: You live in Berlin and have at least 1.5 years of study remaining.\n\nWhy us?\n\nBecome part of a highly qualified team developing machine learning models for AI research and applications:\n\nTogether with GFZ (Helmholtz Centre for Geosciences) and ESA (European Space Agency), we developed a model to analyze satellite data in support of modern agriculture\n\nWe automated the detection of specific cloud structures for the German Weather Service (DWD)\n\nWe support Deutsche Bahn in detecting unusual objects on railway tracks\n\nAnd we won the “AI for Earth Award” for one of our solutions that detects illegal mining in satellite images of the rainforest\n\nWhat Else Awaits You:\n\nDeep Dive in ML: Immerse yourself in the world of machine learning and explore its full potential with us\n\nFast Learning: Take on responsibility early in a young company and develop quickly\n\nImpact: Apply the knowledge you gain during your studies and shape dida\n\nTeam Culture: Work in an open, diverse, and international team\n\nFlexible Working: We offer hybrid work models with remote options – tailored to your studies\n\nGreat Location: Our office is centrally located in Berlin-Kreuzberg, with excellent public transport connections and all the benefits of a city office\n\nAbout us\n\ndida is a machine learning software company with exciting problems for instance in computer vision and natural language processing. Our team tackles applied problems for different customers by using latest scientific advancements (especially in deep learning) and therefore believes that research oriented thinking can help solving real-world problems more efficiently.\n\nAt dida, we stand for equal opportunities, regardless of gender, nationality, ethnic background or disability. We encourage everyone, especially women, people of color, and people with disabilities to apply at dida.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'dida Datenschmiede GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f96007c424b26c68','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2364,NULL,'job','Data Scientist (f/m/d)','Teilzeit','Neudorf',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Your mission\nWork on challenging research and development problems in battery diagnostics, specifically:\n\nPerform statistical analyses on EV and high-voltage battery data\nDevelop and refine machine learning methods for battery systems\nSupport the design, implementation, and testing of new diagnostic procedures\nBuild and validate models for assessing EV high-voltage batteries\nCollaborate closely with our Battery Analytics and Data Engineering teams\nContribute to improving and automating our testing processes\nYour profile\nWe welcome both experienced data scientists and recent graduates — what matters most is strong analytical thinking and a solid academic foundation. You should have:\n\nA completed degree in statistics, mathematics, physics, computer science, or a comparable quantitative field (excellent academic record valued, especially for early-career applicants)\nSolid knowledge of statistics and data analysis\nGenuine interest in developing test and measurement procedures\nInterest in electric vehicles and energy storage systems (lithium-ion batteries)\nThe ability to bridge theory and practice meaningfully\nProgramming skills, ideally in Python\nExcellent English or German skills\nAn independent, structured, and precise way of working\nStrong willingness to learn and enthusiasm for new challenges\nPrior industry experience is a plus but not required — if you\'ve graduated with strong results and a quantitative mindset, we\'d like to hear from you.\nWhy us?\nWork at the frontier of battery diagnostics development\nAccess to AVILOO\'s globally unique EV battery database\nA central role at the heart of our Research and Data Science team\nA dynamic team that\'s genuinely breaking new ground\nThe chance to drive worldwide innovation leadership in an exponentially growing market\nFlexible working arrangements\nFull-time or part-time (minimum 30 hours/week) — we\'re open to either\nCompetitive salary in an environment where performance is rewarded\nAbout us\nSince its foundation in 2018, AVILOO has quickly become the global market leader in the field of battery diagnostics for electric vehicles.\n\nWith more than 90 employees, we already dominate the global “remarketing” & “after-sales” market for electric vehicles. Our customers already include the most renowned vehicle manufacturers, testing companies, leasing companies, vehicle dealers and automobile clubs.\n\nYou will be at the forefront and make a significant contribution to the company\'s success by independently leveraging the enormous potential of your business area.\n\nWe want you to join our dynamic and performance-oriented team and enjoy the success of AVILOO together. Your satisfaction is our CEO\'s business:\n\n“We take care of our people. While performance is important to us, we also ensure a good work-life balance. As a father of five children, I know that parents in particular need to be flexible. I guarantee you this flexibility!” Dr. Marcus Berger - CEO\n\nIf you want to continue your career with us, then this is your chance!\n\nIf you want to be part of a dynamic and successful team where the entrepreneurial spirit is still alive, then this is your chance!\n\nIf you\'ve had enough of narrow framework conditions and slow decisions, then this is your chance!\n\nIf you finally want to create something yourself, implement your own ideas and concepts, then this is your chance!\n\nDo you want to be in the thick of it? Do you want to be part of a team that really deserves the name, where we treat each other with respect without exception and celebrate this together time and time again? Do you want to work in a company where everyone is allowed to say what they think? Then give us a call at any time or send us your application documents! We will get back to you reliably! We look forward to getting to know you!\n\nAVILOO GmbH, IZ NÖ Süd, Straße 16, Objekt 69, 2355 Wiener Neudorf, Austria\nTel: +43676 772 5495, Web: www.aviloo.com/en/jobs-company','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'AVILOO GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=548f0953d5f050b2','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2365,NULL,'job','Werkstudent (m/w/d) AI-Produkte – Kreditvergleich','Studentenjob','80339 München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Unternehmensbeschreibung\n\nDu willst schon im Studium nicht nur zuschauen, sondern echten Impact schaffen? In unserem CHECK24 KAI-Team (Kredite Artificial Intelligence) baust Du die Brücke zwischen modernster Data Science und Millionen von Kunden, die täglich mit uns den passenden Kredit finden.\n\nUnsere Modelle ersetzen regelbasierte Logiken, durchdringen den gesamten Kreditvergleich und bilden das Rückgrat unserer smarten Kundenfeatures. Wir kombinieren etabliertes Machine Learning, LLMs und generative AI – um den Kreditvergleich kontinuierlich intelligenter zu gestalten.\n\nDu musst kein Finanzexperte sein – wir suchen neugierige Köpfe, die komplexe Technologie einfach und erlebbar machen wollen.\n\nAls Werkstudent (m/w/d) für AI-Produkte, unterstützt Du den Product-Owner und ein agiles, interdisziplinäres Feature-Team (Data Scientists, Data Engineers, Backend-Entwickler) bei einer Vielzahl an Frontier-Produkten, beispielsweise im Bereich Conversational AI. Du wirst Teil des Teams, das aus Modellergebnissen Produkte macht, die Kunden lieben!\n\nDu hast Lust, neben dem Studium an AI-Produkten mitzuwirken, die Millionen Menschen erreichen? Dann bewirb Dich jetzt bei der CHECK24 Vergleichsportal Finanzen GmbH.\n\nStellenbeschreibung\n\nMitarbeit an AI-Features: Du wirkst an der Konzeption und Weiterentwicklung von ML- und LLM-basierten Features mit – von der ersten Recherche über das Experiment bis zum erfolgreichen Rollout\nA/B-Testing & datengetriebene Entscheidungen: Du gestaltest Experimente aktiv mit, begleitest Tests von Anfang bis Ende, analysierst die Ergebnisse und lernst, daraus fundierte Go-/No-Go-Entscheidungen auf unserer hauseigenen Experimentierplattform abzuleiten\nStakeholder-Kommunikation: Du übersetzt komplexe ML-Konzepte – etwa Modellperformance oder Feature Importance – in verständliche Business-Sprache und bereitest Inhalte zielgruppengerecht auf\nCross-funktionale Zusammenarbeit: Du arbeitest eng mit Data Scientists und ML-Engineers zusammen, um Modellergebnisse in echte, kundenwirksame Produkte zu überführen\nInnovation & GenAI: Du recherchierst und evaluierst neue Technologien – darunter LLMs und Agentic Workflows – und entwickelst konkrete Ideen, wie generative AI den Kreditvergleich weiter verbessern kann\n\nQualifikationen\n\nWas Du mitbringst\n\nLaufendes Studium in Wirtschaftsinformatik, Data Science, Informatik, Wirtschaftswissenschaften oder einem vergleichbaren Studiengang – mit sehr guten Studienleistungen\nInteresse an Produktmanagement und digitalen Produkten – idealerweise erste Erfahrungen mit Data Science, ML oder KI\nNeugier für technische Zusammenhänge und ein Grundverständnis dafür, wie datengetriebene Produkte funktionieren\nAnalytisches Denkvermögen und sicherer Umgang mit Daten – ob SQL, Python oder Excel\nKommunikationsstärke und die Fähigkeit, komplexe Sachverhalte verständlich aufzubereiten\nSehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse (mind. C1) in Wort und Schrift\n\nNice-to-haves\n\nAktive Nutzung von AI-Tools (z. B. ChatGPT, Claude) sowie Interesse an Prompt Engineering oder GenAI-Produkten\nErste Erfahrung mit agilen Methoden oder der Entwicklung von Prototypen mit generativen AI-Tools\nKenntnisse in Python, Jupyter-Notebooks oder Cloud-Plattformen (AWS, GCP)\nGrundverständnis für FinTech oder das Verbraucherkreditgeschäft\n\nZusätzliche Informationen\n\nImpact ab Tag 1: Deine Arbeit fließt direkt in Produkte ein, die täglich von tausenden Kunden genutzt werden – kein Kaffeekochen, sondern echte Verantwortung von Anfang an\nPräsenz als Wettbewerbsvorteil: Wir arbeiten eng zusammen – Deine Arbeitszeiten passen wir an Deinen Vorlesungsplan an. Das gemeinsame Arbeiten vor Ort erzeugt unseren CHECKito-Spirit\nCutting-Edge Tech: Du arbeitest mit einem Team, das produktionsreife ML-Modelle und LLM-Anwendungen baut – kein Prototyping-Friedhof, sondern echte AI auf der Plattform für unsere Kunden\nStabilität & Startup-Spirit: Gründergeführtes Unternehmen mit über 25 Jahren Erfolgsgeschichte, aber kleine, autonome Teams, die wie Startups agieren – ohne unnötige Bürokratie\nWir bringen Dich voran: Steile Lernkurve durch direktes Mentoring von erfahrenen Produktmanagern und Data Scientists. Regelmäßiges Feedback und die Chance, nach dem Studium bei uns einzusteigen\nWir schätzen Deinen Einsatz: Attraktive Vergütung, flexible Arbeitszeiten passend zu Deinem Vorlesungsplan und Sonderkonditionen für Fitness-Studios und Öffi-Ticket\nFood & Drinks: Kostenlose Mahlzeiten (Frühstück & Lunch), frisches Obst, Getränke-Flatrate und CHECK24-Gutscheine\nCheckito-Spirit: Wir wissen, dass nur exzellente Teams exzellente Online-Produkte entwickeln. Deshalb gehören Events zum Feiern und Netzwerken sowie unsere legendären Sommer- und Weihnachtsfeiern immer dazu','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'CHECK24','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8e5d73915b1461ab','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2366,NULL,'job','Senior Data Scientist','Vollzeit','Home Office',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'NEW CAREER OPPORTUNITY\n\nBuild your career with Kraken Robotics. Make a difference to others. If innovation drives you, and you want a career that makes a difference to the world, helping humanity overcome the challenges in our oceans – safely, efficiently, and sustainably – then come join us at Kraken Robotics.\n\nKraken Robotics is currently seeking a Senior Data Scientist to join our team. This position can be Remote or working out of any of our Global Offices.\n\nKraken’s Sensor Research Group (SRG) is dedicated to accelerating innovation in sensor technology through agile prototyping and hands-on experimentation. By rapidly exploring new concepts and technical pathways, the team aims to uncover opportunities and address potential limitations early in development—well before significant resources are committed to scaling or commercialization.\n\nThe SRG also addresses urgent technology challenges, defects, and operational issues by leveraging in-house Subject Matter Experts to develop fast, field-testable solutions. This quick feedback loop helps refine or redirect development efforts efficiently.\n\nWe are currently seeking a Senior Data Scientist with expertise in marine data processing. Experience with AI/ML techniques applied to sensor data is a strong asset.\n\nKraken fosters a culture of collaboration, experimentation, and calculated risk-taking. Within the SRG, this translates to rapid prototyping, frequent iteration, and close engagement with operators to ensure solutions are grounded in real-world performance. The group values agility over perfection - quickly developing and testing ideas to learn what works, what doesn\'t, and where to go next.\n\nRoles and Responsibilities:\n\nDevelop, maintain, and execute strategic research initiatives within the Sensor Research Group.\nConduct hands-on R&D and prototyping across Kraken’s portfolio of underwater sensor systems, sonar processing, and machine learning-based analytics.\nIdentify innovation opportunities and assess emerging technologies in sensor processing and data analytics.\nEnhance and expand Kraken’s data processing pipelines, workflows, and infrastructure.\nImprove access to existing datasets and apply them to model training, validation, and broader team use in research and development efforts.\nContribute to the scientific community through collaborative research, conference participation, academic publications, and partnerships with universities.\nSupport business development through technical discussions with customers and contributions to proposal writing.\nParticipate in knowledge-sharing events, technical workshops, and cross-functional innovation discussions.\n\nQualifications and Experience:\n\nEducation: Master’s / PhD degree in Computer Science, Applied Mathematics, or a related field, with a focus on data processing, machine learning, or sensor analytics.\nExperience:\n8+ years experience in research and development or industry\nExperience with marine data processing\nTechnical Expertise:\nExperience in cloud infrastructure and scaling\nKnowledge of marine geospatial data and related formats\nBackground in machine learning and large data processing\nProficiency in Python and C++\nFamiliarity with GPU-accelerated computing and distributed data architectures\nKnowledge of sensor fusion, sonar processing, sensor processing and data analysis, or other relevant technologies.\nFamiliarity with underwater environment dynamics and applications of underwater sensor systems.\n\nPreferred Skills:\n\nStrong problem-solving and analytical abilities with a focus on innovation and practical application.\nProven ability to self-organize research efforts, including defining and pursuing ambitious technical objectives.\nComfortable working in a fast-paced, multidisciplinary, and highly collaborative environment.\nFamiliarity with agile development methodologies and rapid prototyping approaches.\nExcellent communication skills for presenting technical findings and collaborating with both technical and non-technical stakeholders.\nEffective at managing time and resources in support of evolving research priorities.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Kraken Robotics','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=52906b18027d7f46','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2367,NULL,'job','SAP BTP Spezialist (m/w/d)','Teilzeit','80331 München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'SWAN Consultancy GmbH\n\nWer wir sind?\n\nSicherheit & Freiheit vereint - Wir haben uns 2019 mit der Gründung der SWAN Consultancy zur Aufgabe gemacht Menschen – die auf der Suche nach einem selbstbestimmten aber abgesicherten Berufsweg sind - zu unterstützen.\n\nWir kombinieren die Vorteile eines Freiberuflers mit denen eines Angestellten. Das bedeutet wir ermöglichen maximale Flexibilität von Arbeits- und Urlaubszeiten und gleichzeitig Sicherheiten durch Festgehalt, Sozialversicherung und einem hohen Gesamt-Einkommen.\n\nWir bieten DIR eine Festanstellung mit den Vorzügen einer freiberuflichen Tätigkeit. Arbeite flexibel, selbstständig sowie selbstbestimmt und genieße gleichzeitig ein krisensicheres Einkommen.\n\nDeine Benefits bei uns\nÜberdurchschnittliches Einkommen\nmaximale Urlaubstage\nUmsatzbeteiligung von 60-70%\n100 % REMOTE - egal ob Zuhause, Unterwegs, Strand oder Berge\nAnstellung im Homeoffice (europaweit)\nEquipment & Notebook nach Wahl\nPersönliches Mentoring\nSpannende Projekte\nBahncard 100 per Entgeltumwandlung und landesspezifische Benefits\nFlexibilität, Work-Life-Balance, Sicherheit!\n\nDeine Aufgaben\nWir suchen in den Bereichen Beratung, Entwicklung und/oder Architektur für SAP Business Technology Platform:\nBeratung und Implementierung von SAP (BTP)-Lösungen für Kundenprojekte\nIntegration von Daten, Prozessen und Anwendungen über die SAP BTP Plattform\nEntwicklung und Anpassung von Anwendungen auf der SAP BTP-Plattform (inkl. SAP Fiori, SAP HANA Cloud und SAP Integration Suite)\nDesign und Implementierung von Cloud-nativen Anwendungen und Microservices\nNutzung von KI-, Machine Learning- und Analytics-Funktionen der SAP BTP zur Optimierung von Geschäftsprozessen\nSicherstellung der nahtlosen Integration von SAP S/4HANA und anderen Systemen mit SAP BTP\nEnge Zusammenarbeit mit Fachabteilungen und Stakeholdern zur Umsetzung maßgeschneiderter Lösungen\nSchulung und Support für Endanwender sowie technische Dokumentation der entwickelten Lösungen\n\nMögliche Projekteinsätze:\nSAP BTP-Berater / Consulant\nSAP BTP-Entwickler\nSAP BTP-Architekten\nSAP BTP-Integrationsexperten\n\nEgal welche SAP Business Technology Platform Expertise du mibringst, wir freuen uns auf deine Bewerbung!\n\nDeine Erfahrungen & Skills\nFundierte Erfahrung in der Implementierung und Nutzung von SAP BTP\nTiefgehende Kenntnisse in SAP Cloud Plattform, SAP Integration Suite, SAP HANA Cloud und SAP Fiori\nODER Erfahrung in der Entwicklung mit SAP BTP (ABAP, Java, Node.js) und Cloud-native Technologien\nODER Erfahrung in der Integration von SAP-Systemen (z. B. SAP S/4HANA, SAP SuccessFactors, SAP Ariba)\nODER Kenntnisse in der Implementierung von KI- und Machine Learning-Funktionen auf der SAP BTP\nErfahrung mit Agilen Methoden (Scrum, Kanban) und DevOps-Praktiken\nSehr gute Deutsch- & Englischkenntnisse','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'SWAN Consultancy GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9b49c05603fa6679','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2368,NULL,'job','Deep Learning Engineer for Omics Data (f/m/x)','Vollzeit','Köln',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Faculty of Mathematics and Natural Sciences\nDeep Learning Engineer for Omics Data (f/m/x)\nInstitute for Genetics and the Cluster of Excellence for Aging Research (CECAD)\n\nWe are one of the largest and oldest universities in Europe and one of the most important employers in our region. Our broad range of subjects, the dynamic development of our main research areas and our central location in Cologne make us attractive for students and researchers from around the world. We offer a wide range of career opportunities in science, technology, and administration.\n\nThe Poetsch group is looking for a Deep Learning Engineer (f/m/x) to support the team in the study of genomes and how they change with aging and in cancer development. This is a core-funded position with a strong collaborative focus and the goal to build up deep learning infrastructures on Omics data for the lab and beyond.\n\nYOUR TASKS\nWorking closely with other lab members to convert theoretical concepts into practical code\nProviding technical guidance to junior members and interns\nImplementing and evaluating state-of-the-art machine learning and deep learning techniques and algorithms, with a strong focus on omics data\nDevising and testing new algorithms, often moving from academic papers to working code\nCreating internal tools to speed up research, such as automated evaluation frameworks, data annotation tools, or specialized libraries\n\nYOUR PROFILE\nPhD in Computer Science, Bioinformatics, Artificial Intelligence or a related field or equivalent experience level\nSolid understanding of machine learning fundamentals, including common algorithms, model training and evaluation techniques\nExperience with Python programming and at least one AI/ML framework(e.g. TensorFlow, PyTorch)\nExposure to data science concepts such as data pre- processing, feature extraction, and exploratory analysis\nExposure to biomedical data science\nCuriosity and willingness to explore emerging AI domains in the biomedical domain\nVery good interpersonal and communication skills; in particular, the ability to effectively work in a diverse, collaborative and interdisciplinary research environment\nFluency in English - written and oral (German is not required)\n\nWE OFFER\nOpportunity to receive training in cutting-edge methods in using deep learning on genomics data and their integration\nA diverse working environment with equal opportunities\nSupport in balancing work and family life\nExtensive advanced training opportunities\nOccupational health management offers\nFlexible working time models\n\nThe University of Cologne promotes equal opportunities and diversity. Women will be considered preferentially in accordance with the Equal Opportunities Act of North Rhine-Westphalia (Landesgleichstellungsgesetz – LGG NRW). We also expressly welcome applications from all suitable candidates regardless of their gender, nationality, ethnic and social origin, religion, disability, age, sexual orientation and identity.\n\nThe position is available from 01.07.2026 on a full-time basis (39,83 hours per week). The position is to be filled for a fixed term until 30.06.2028 with the possibility of an extension. If the applicant meets the relevant wage requirements and personal qualifications, the salary is based on remuneration group 13 TV-L of the pay scale for the German public sector.\n\nPlease apply online with proof of the required qualifications and a motivation letter (without a photo) under: https://jobportal.uni-koeln.d e. The reference number is\nWiss2604-09. The application deadline is 20.05.2026.\n\nFor further inquiries, please contact Professor Dr Anna Poetsch ( apoetsch@uni-koeln.de ) and take a look at our FAQs .','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Universität zu Köln','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ca908eb44290e209','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2369,NULL,'job','Inhouse (Senior) AI Engineer (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','69115 Heidelberg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Wir sind die Berater der Weltmarktführer: Hochmotivierte Experten, die sich miteinander vernetzen, um als erfolgreiches Team digitale End-to-End-Geschäftsprozesslösungen voranzutreiben. Gemeinsam stärken wir die Zukunft der beeindruckendsten Unternehmen der Welt aus Maschinen- und Anlagenbau, Automotive, Life Science, Pharma und Chemie, mit denen wir viel gemeinsam haben.\n\nUnser ausgezeichneter Ruf bei Hidden Champions öffnet dir die Türen zu anspruchsvollen Digitalisierungsprojekten mit echtem Gestaltungsspielraum. Bei cbs arbeitest du in einem starken Team, übernimmst schnell Verantwortung und entwickelst dich fachlich wie persönlich weiter, gemeinsam mit Kollegen, die den Anspruch haben, wirklich etwas zu bewegen.\n\nAls (Senior) AI Engineer wirst Du Teil unseres internen AI Teams und arbeitest an der Entwicklung, dem sicheren Betrieb und der kontinuierlichen Weiterentwicklung unserer AI‑Lösungen. Unser Team deckt dabei verschiedene Perspektiven rund um moderne AI-Systeme ab – von der Entwicklung intelligenter Anwendungen über Plattform‑ und Infrastrukturthemen bis hin zu Data Science und AI Security.\n\nIn dieser Rolle arbeitest Du an der Schnittstelle von AI, Software Engineering, Daten und IT‑Security. Je nach Deinem Profil und Deinen Interessen kannst Du dabei unterschiedliche Schwerpunkte setzen – beispielsweise bei der Entwicklung von AI‑Anwendungen, beim Aufbau von Plattformen und Infrastruktur, bei datengetriebenen Modellen oder bei der Absicherung von AI-Systemen.\n\nWas Dich erwartet\n·Du entwickelst und integrierst AI‑gestützte Anwendungen und Services für unterschiedliche interne Anwendungsfälle.\nDu arbeitest mit modernen AI-Technologien wie Large Language Models und evaluierst neue Ansätze für praktische Einsatzszenarien.\nDu führst Prototypen AI‑basierter Systeme in produktionsreife Lösungen über.\nDu arbeitest mit Daten, entwickelst Modelle oder analysierst Daten, um neue Erkenntnisse und Funktionen zu ermöglichen.\nDu entwickelst oder betreibst Plattformkomponenten, die die Entwicklung und den Betrieb von AI-Anwendungen erleichtern.\nDu unterstützt dabei, unsere AI-Systeme sicher und verantwortungsvoll zu gestalten, z. B. beim Umgang mit Daten oder möglichen Risiken moderner AI-Technologien.\nDu arbeitest eng mit Kolleginnen und Kollegen aus Engineering, Plattform, Security und Data Science zusammen.\nDu verfolgst neue Entwicklungen im AI‑Ökosystem und bringst diese sinnvoll in unsere Lösungen ein.\n\nWas wir uns wünschen\nErfahrung in Softwareentwicklung oder Software Engineering (z. B. mit Python, TypeScript oder ähnlichen Technologien).\nInteresse oder Erfahrung mit AI-Technologien, z. B. Machine Learning, Large Language Models oder AI‑basierte Anwendungen.\nErfahrung in einem oder mehreren der folgenden Bereiche:o Entwicklung von AI‑ oder datengetriebenen Anwendungeno Data Science oder Machine Learningo Plattform‑, Cloud‑ oder Infrastrukturentwicklungo IT‑Security oder Security Engineering\nVerständnis moderner Softwarearchitekturen und cloudbasierter Systeme.\nInteresse daran, neue Technologien pragmatisch in reale Anwendungen zu überführen.\nStrukturierte Arbeitsweise, Eigeninitiative und Freude am Arbeiten in interdisziplinären Teams.\nUnsere Benefits:\n\nAus- und Weiterbildung\n\nSAP- und Salesforce-Zertifizierungen, Competence Center-Tage, Fachspezifische Schulungen\n\nBetriebliche Gesundheitsförderung\n\nZuschuss zur betrieblichen Altersvorsorge, Zusatzversicherungen, diverse Sportangebote wie Urban Sports Club, Yoga etc.\n\nEvents\n\nBeratertage, Weihnachtsfeier, Sommerfest, Teamevents, Alumni-Treffen, Jubiläumsfeiern und -reisen\n\nPrämien\n\nUmsatzbeteiligungen, Prämienzahlungen für erfolgreich abgeschlossene Projekte, Attraktive Gehaltsmodelle, Mitarbeiterempfehlungsprämien\n\nArbeitszeiten\n\nFlexible Arbeitszeitmodelle, mobiles Arbeiten, 30 Tage Urlaub, Workation\n\nAusstattung\n\nFirmenhandy (iPhone), Notebook / Macbook, Mitarbeiter PC Programm, Ergonomische Arbeitsplätze, Kostenlose Getränke, Gemeinschaftsräume mit Wohlfühlcharakter\n\nFirmenwagen\n\nFirmenwagen inkl. Tankkarte/ Mobilitätspauschale, Bahncard, Jobrad\n\nZuwendungen\n\nZuschüsse für Kindergarten/Kita und außerordentliche Zuwendungen je Lebenssituation und Betriebszugehörigkeit\n\nDein Ansprechpartner\n\nChristina Argyriadou\n\nSenior Recruiterin\n\n+49 15165577154\n\nchristina.argyriadou@cbs-consulting.de\n\nBereich: Corporate Functions\n\nAnsprechpartner: Christina Argyriadou\n\nPractice: Intern\n\nFilter: Berufserfahrung: Professionals\n\nBenefits: Interne','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'cbs Corporate Business Solutions GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2e98ba10096428e9','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2370,NULL,'job','Software Engineer C++','Vollzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We are looking for a Software Engineer (C++) to join our team in Berlin, Germany. We offer flexible working hours and the option for partial remote work.\n\nYou will join the agile engineering team behind PIX4Dmatic, our next-generation desktop application designed for large-scale photogrammetry and professional mapping. We are a collaborative group that values transparency and iterative growth. We operate in 3-week sprints, balancing rapid feature development with high-quality releases.\n\nYou’ll be part of the entire lifecycle - from the initial estimation of new features to the final release at the end of the sprint. Our team bridges the gap between complex R&D research and a seamless user experience, ensuring that specialized algorithms are effectively integrated into a high-performance, cross-platform environment.\n\nYou are a good match for this position if you are a curious learner and a proactive communicator. You don\'t just want to write code; you want to understand the \"why\" behind the features and participate in the estimation process.\n\nResponsibilities\nFeature Development: Designing and implementing new features that span the entire stack, from QML-based UI components to backend logic.\nAgile Collaboration: Actively participating in technical estimations and sprint planning to help the team commit to realistic and impactful goals.\nCode Quality: Writing clean, maintainable C++ code and performing code reviews to ensure the stability of our application.\nAlgorithm Integration: Implement and optimize the backend logic required to support new photogrammetry and image processing capabilities developed by our R&D teams.\nMaintenance & Troubleshooting: Investigate and resolve software defects and performance bottlenecks, ensuring a smooth user experience while gaining a deep understanding of our architecture\nSpecialized Projects: Depending on your interests and team needs, you’ll have the opportunity to dive into specialized areas such as coordinate reference systems (CRS), 3D visualization, etc.\n\nRequirements\nSolid foundation in C++ .\nFamiliarity with, or a desire to learn, Qt/QML for desktop UI development.\nAn \"Agile mindset\" - you enjoy collaborating, estimating work together, and improving the product through continuous iteration.\nExperience or interest in 3D graphics, Windows development or geospatial data is a significant plus.\nProficient English language skills, written and spoken.\nThe ability to work effectively as part of a team is essential, to communicate and collaborate with colleagues to achieve common goals.\nYou have a passionate, positive, collaborative and respectful attitude\nWhat we offer\nExciting work with cutting-edge technology in an international company.\nConveniently located office near Alexanderplatz and Hackescher Markt.\nFlexible working hours and the option for hybrid work.\n30 days of paid vacation.\nEmployee Assistance Program with Lyra providing Mental, Legal and Financial assistance.\nCorporate discounts on retail and travel.\nChoose one of two benefit options: Deutschlandticket or a voucher.\nCompany Social Events.\nErgonomic desks and chairs.\nOpportunities for learning and professional development.\n\nWorking environment\n\nPIX4D is a unique, fun, and intellectually stimulating company where you can grow and excel in your field. Our environment is authentic and multicultural, a place where we respect and learn from each other in the pursuit of being the best at what we do. Get more information here.\n\nRecruitment\n\nPIX4D promotes diversity and offers opportunities across all levels and career paths in all of its offices regardless of gender, race, or religion. We use standardized and structured interviews to ensure all candidates are treated equally and avoid any discrimination.\n\nCompany\nWhen you work at PIX4D, you empower professionals worldwide to digitize reality through survey-grade georeferenced 2D maps and 3D models. These outputs can be measured, analyzed, and shared, all based on data from images taken by plane, drone, or mobile phone.\n\nWe build solutions that take advantage of technology including reality capture, computer vision, digital twins, and machine learning to help solve our customers\' most complex challenges.\n\nFounded in 2011, PIX4D has its headquarters in Lausanne, Switzerland and commercial and R&D offices in Denver, Berlin, Bucharest, Tokyo and Madrid.\n\nAdditional information\n\nAll our candidate applications are screened by humans and not an AI recruiter.\n\n#LI-EMI\n\n#Hybrid','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Pix4D','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d060a3270fd29fcc','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2371,NULL,'job','On-Site IT Support','Vollzeit','Ulm',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Teoresi is an international engineering services company founded in 1987 in Turin, Italy. At Teoresi, we specialize in supporting companies in creating projects using cutting-edge technologies such as self-driving cars and nanotechnology for the medical field. Our innovative approach involves close collaboration with the R&D departments of major industrial brands. We provide turnkey solutions to help our clients bring their products to market faster. We have been selected by Amazon as one of only 10 companies to work on developing new products using Alexa voice technology.\n\nWe are always looking for talented individuals to join our team. At Teoresi, we value innovation in each project challenge, teamwork, diversity, and we think beyond borders, both geographically and in terms of our approach. We are committed to staying up-to-date with technological advancements while also prioritizing people and environmental sustainability. Our team is diverse and located around the world, which allows us to offer international career opportunities and meet the needs of a constantly evolving market. We believe in the importance of proactivity and learning in a team environment and are dedicated to generating innovation in everything we do.\nIf you share our values and are interested in joining a forward-thinking company, keep reading and apply!\n\nDescription\nProvide on-site IT support on the production floor\nEnsure production machines and systems are properly connected and synchronized\nCheck network connectivity between machines, production systems, and IT infrastructure\nSupport the operation and availability of production-related IT systems\nIdentify, document, and troubleshoot technical issues directly in the plant\nCoordinate with production, maintenance, IT, and external support teams\nSupport incident resolution and follow-up of corrective actions\nAssist with basic hardware, software, and network-related topics in the production environment\nCompany Teoresi Group -> Teoresi GmbH | Germany\nJob requirements\n\nExperience in IT support, production IT, plant support, maintenance, or a similar technical role\nBasic understanding of networks, IT infrastructure, hardware, and system connectivity\nInterest in working directly in a production / plant environment\nHands-on mentality and willingness to support issues on site\nStructured, reliable, and solution-oriented working style\nGood communication skills with production and technical teams\nGerman language skills required; English is an advantage\nExperience in automotive production or industrial manufacturing\nKnowledge of production systems, machine connectivity, MES, shopfloor IT, or industrial networks\nBasic understanding of OT / IT interface\n\nWhat We Offer:\nTake a closer look at Teoresi\'s benefits here: https://www.teoresigroup.com/career/benefit-germany/\nWork-life balance with Flex & Remote working options\nWork from Anywhere: flexibility to work for a certain period outside of Germany\nUp to 33 days of vacation\nJob Ticket\nAttractive Employees-Referral Campaign\nHealth And Fitness program with Egym Wellpass\nEdenred City Card\nExclusive employee discounts - Corporate Benefits\nInternational working atmosphere\nFlat organizational structure\nIndividual training options\nCorporate and Team events\n * Teoresi Group is committed to workforce inclusion and providing an environment where equal employment opportunities are available to all applicants and employees without regard to disabilities, race, color, religion, national origin, age, marital status, sexual orientation, gender identity and expression or veteran status. * Candidates are hereby informed that, by submitting their application, all data will be processed in accordance with the provisions of our privacy policy, which can be read at the following link: https://www.teoresigroup.com/privacy-notice-recruitment/\n\nEducation\n\nBachelor\'s Degree\n\nCareer level\n\nEntry Level (0 - 1 year)\nJob reference\n\nTeoDe_OnsiteIT_20260429\n\nJob Category\n\nEngineering\n\nDate added\n\n29 April 2026\n\nLocation\n\nGermany - Ulm\n\nJob Type\n\nFull-time','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Teoresi Group','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=50e1705c0fa2927a','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2372,NULL,'job','Praktikum Business Intelligence (w/m/d)','Vollzeit','Hamburg',NULL,'',13002266.00,'1.300 € – 2.266 € pro Monat','Praktikum Business Intelligence | Advanced Analytics (w/m/d)\nUnsere Work Group „Advanced Analytics“ besteht aus zwei Data Scientists und einem Senior Expert Business Analytics und ist Teil eines größeren Teams, das OTTO-Mitarbeitende agil unterstützt, Analytics im Self Service zu betreiben. Gemeinsam gewinnen wir tiefere datengestützte Erkenntnisse mit Data Science-Methoden und Machine Learning-Modellen, um bessere Entscheidungen zu treffen und die Wettbewerbsfähigkeit von OTTO nachhaltig zu verbessern.\n\nViele sprechen von „Homeoffice“ – wir von „hybrid oder mobile Work“: Du kannst bis zu 50 % deiner monatlichen Arbeitszeit remote arbeiten. Unsere Teams entscheiden dabei gemeinsam mit ihrer Führungskraft, wie sie das Gleichgewicht aus Präsenzzeiten vor Ort und mobilem Arbeiten gestalten.\nDein Impact\nAls Teil des Teams befähigst du unsere Fachbereiche, wegweisende Analyseprojekte durchzuführen. Du hilfst ihnen dabei, mit Methoden aus Statistik, Machine Learning oder Generative AI eigenständig datenbasierte Entscheidungen zu treffen.\nIm Sinne des innovationstreibenden Charakters des Teams arbeitest du dich in neue Analyse-Methoden und -Tools ein und präsentierst deine Erkenntnisse in dem entsprechenden Interessentenkreis.\nDu unterstützt bei internen Marketingmaßnahmen und Akquise von User*innen für unsere Self-Service Advanced Analytics Plattform.\nDu wirkst bei der Gestaltung der OTTO internen Business Analytics Schulungsangebote und bei der Weiterentwicklung einer Self-Service Advanced Analytics Platform mit.\nDu erhältst Einblicke in die geschäftlichen Zusammenhänge und die komplexe Datenlandschaft sowie analytische Infrastruktur eines der größten E-Commerce Händler.\nDu sammelst praktische Erfahrungen in der Arbeit mit aktuellen BI Technologien im Big Data Umfeld (Google Cloud, Snowflake) in Kombination mit Analysetools (Jupyter Notebooks, Python, Big Query ML, SQL, Power BI).\n\nDu bist dir nicht sicher, ob das Praktikum zu dir passt? – Gerne stellen wir den Kontakt zu Claudia aus dem Team her.\n\nDein Profil\n\nMust-have:\n\nDu studierst in einem Studiengang mit technischem oder analytischem Schwerpunkt (z.B. Wirtschaftsinformatik, Wirtschaftswissenschaften, Informatik, Statistik, Mathematik, Data Science, Business Analytics, Psychologie, Soziologie o.ä.) oder befindest dich in deinem Gap Year zwischen Bachelor und Master.\nDu verfügst über sehr gute analytische Fähigkeiten und hast Spaß daran, dich in neue Technologien einzuarbeiten.\nDu nutzt AI-Tools selbstverständlich für Aufgaben und Prozesse in deinem Fachgebiet.\nDu kannst uns ab Anfang September 2026 für 6 Monate unterstützen.\nDein Sprachniveau: Deutsch C1 (fachkundige Sprachverwendung) und Englisch B2 (selbständige Sprachverwendung).\n\nNice-to-have:\n\nDu verfügst bereits über erste Erfahrungen mit einigen der oben genannten Analyse-Technologien und in agilen Arbeitsweisen.\n\nDu kannst auch länger als 6 Monate zur Verfügung stehen? Bei uns gibt es die Möglichkeit, je nach Bedarf und Rücksprache im Team, das Praktikum auch für 9 Monate zu absolvieren. Sprich uns hierzu gerne an!\n\nDeine Benefits\nFachliche & persönliche Entwicklung\nWeiterbildungsangebote wie z. B. die OTTO-Akademie, digitale Lernplattformen (u. a. Masterplan), Mentoring, Hospitationen, offene Feedbackkultur, Formate zur beruflichen Orientierung, Kooperation bei Abschlussarbeiten, feste*n Betreuer*in und direkte Ansprechpersonen im HR-Bereich\nKultur & Zusammenarbeit\nStudents@OTTO Community & Netzwerke, Coworking & Social Spaces, Führung auf Augenhöhe, flache Hierarchien, selbstständiges & eigenverantwortliches Arbeiten, regelmäßige Mitarbeiterbefragungen, Leading Principles, kostenfreie Heißgetränke und vielfältiges – auch veganes – Essensangebot\nVergütung & Zusatzleistungen\nAttraktive Vergütung (1300 € - 2090 €), 15 % Personalrabatt (auf OTTO-Artikel sowie zahlreiche Benefits & Mitarbeiterangebote (z. B. Events, Reisen), 30 Urlaubstage p. a., technische Grundausstattung\nStudents@OTTO Onboarding\nEinwöchiges Onboarding Programm für Studierende bestehend aus: Welcome Session, Impulsvorträgen, Get-Together & Vorstandstalk\nWork-Life-Balance\nHybrides Arbeitsmodell mit bis zu 50 % remote work im Monat, flexible Arbeitszeiten (Gleitzeit), 37,5h-Woche\nGesundheit & Wohlbefinden\nAchtsamkeits- und Stressmanagementkurse, betriebsärztliche & psychosoziale Beratung\nMobilität\nZuschuss zum Deutschlandticket, kostenfreie Parkplätze, e-Ladesäulen, StadtRAD-Stationen\n\n& viele Benefits mehr!\n\nDu hast noch offene Fragen? Dann wende dich gerne per E-Mail an nachwuchsrecruiting@otto.de. Wir melden uns so schnell wie möglich bei dir zurück. Hier findest du weitere Tipps rund um deine Onlinebewerbung.\nUnsere Work Group „Advanced Analytics“ besteht aus zwei Data Scientists und einem Senior Expert Business Analytics und ist Teil eines größeren Teams, das OTTO-Mitarbeitende agil unterstützt, Analytics im Self Service zu betreiben. Gemeinsam gewinnen wir tiefere datengestützte Erkenntnisse mit Data Science-Methoden und Machine Learning-Modellen, um bessere Entscheidungen zu treffen und die Wettbewerbsfähigkeit von OTTO nachhaltig zu verbessern.\n\nViele sprechen von „Homeoffice“ – wir von „hybrid oder mobile Work“: Du kannst bis zu 50 % deiner monatlichen Arbeitszeit remote arbeiten. Unsere Teams entscheiden dabei gemeinsam mit ihrer Führungskraft, wie sie das Gleichgewicht aus Präsenzzeiten vor Ort und mobilem Arbeiten gestalten.\nUnsere Work Group „Advanced Analytics“ besteht aus zwei Data Scientists und einem Senior Expert Business Analytics und ist Teil eines größeren Teams, das OTTO-Mitarbeitende agil unterstützt, Analytics im Self Service zu betreiben. Gemeinsam gewinnen wir tiefere datengestützte Erkenntnisse mit Data Science-Methoden und Machine Learning-Modellen, um bessere Entscheidungen zu treffen und die Wettbewerbsfähigkeit von OTTO nachhaltig zu verbessern.\n\nViele sprechen von „Homeoffice“ – wir von „hybrid oder mobile Work“: Du kannst bis zu 50 % deiner monatlichen Arbeitszeit remote arbeiten. Unsere Teams entscheiden dabei gemeinsam mit ihrer Führungskraft, wie sie das Gleichgewicht aus Präsenzzeiten vor Ort und mobilem Arbeiten gestalten.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Otto GmbH & Co. KGaA','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=130b57058afde2ba','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2373,NULL,'job','Data Engineer (mwd) – Data Platforms & Data Pipelines','Teilzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Berlin\ndeutschlandweit/remote\nDüsseldorf\nHeidelberg\nUlm\nBerufserfahrung\nVoll/Teilzeit\nSeit über 35 Jahren unterstützen wir Unternehmen dabei, aus Daten echten Mehrwert zu schaffen. Dafür entwickeln wir maßgeschneiderte Daten-, KI- und Softwarelösungen und begleiten unsere Kunden als spezialisierter Boutique-Dienstleister entlang der gesamten Data-to-Value-Journey – von der ersten Idee bis zur produktiven Anwendung. In unseren Projekten verbinden wir Data Engineering, Machine Learning, Generative AI und Software Engineering mit fundiertem Branchenverständnis sowie methodischer Klarheit. Mit über 170 Mitarbeitenden arbeiten wir an anspruchsvollen Projekten in Branchen wie Life Science, Finance und Manufacturing und entwickeln gemeinsam nachhaltige Lösungen.\n\nIn dieser Rolle unterstützt du anspruchsvolle Kundenprojekte in den Bereichen Daten, Digitalisierung und KI und entwickelst moderne Datenplattformen für Analytics und datengetriebene Anwendungen – mit direktem Einfluss auf datenbasierte Geschäftsmodelle und KI-Anwendungen.\nDas sind deine Aufgaben\nMitarbeit an Daten- und Digitalisierungsprojekten sowie aktive Mitgestaltung moderner Datenarchitekturen\nAnalyse fachlicher Anforderungen und Übersetzung in technische Spezifikationen in enger Abstimmung mit Kunden und Stakeholdern\nEntwicklung und Optimierung von Datenmodellen (z. B. Star Schema, Data Vault)\nKonzeption, Entwicklung und Betrieb von Datenpipelines (ETL/ELT, Batch und Streaming)\nIntegration, Transformation und Modellierung strukturierter und unstrukturierter Daten\nSicherstellung von Datenqualität, Datenkonsistenz sowie Monitoring von Datenflüssen\nBereitstellung von Daten für Analysen, Reporting und KI-Anwendungen (z. B. über APIs und Services)\nUmsetzung und Weiterentwicklung cloudbasierter Datenplattformen (z. B. AWS, Azure, Snowflake)\nPerformance- und Kostenoptimierung von Datenverarbeitung und –plattformen\nBeratung von Kunden zu Datenarchitekturen und datengetriebenen Lösungen\nZusammenarbeit mit Data Scientists, Softwareentwickelnden und Fachbereichen\nDas bringst du mit\nAbgeschlossenes Studium in Informatik, Mathematik, Physik oder vergleichbare praktische Erfahrung\nPraxiserfahrung im Data Engineering oder in verwandten Bereichen\nSehr gute Kenntnisse in SQL sowie in mindestens einer Programmiersprache (z. B. Python, Scala oder Java)\nErfahrung in Datenmodellierung sowie mit ETL-/ELT-Prozessen\nErfahrung im Aufbau und Betrieb von Datenpipelines\nKenntnisse in Cloud-Technologien (z. B. AWS, Azure)\nErfahrung mit Big-Data- und Streaming-Technologien (z. B. Spark, Kafka)\nIdealerweise Erfahrung mit Datenplattformen (z. B. Snowflake, Databricks, Microsoft Fabric)\nInteresse am Einsatz von AI-gestützten Tools zur Steigerung von Entwicklungseffizienz und Codequalität\nStrukturierte Arbeitsweise sowie sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse\nBereitschaft zu gelegentlichen Reisen\n\nDich erwartet ein agiles Umfeld mit kurzen Entscheidungswegen und viel Gestaltungsspielraum. Deine fachliche und persönliche Weiterentwicklung fördern wir gezielt – ob als Experte oder Expertin, in der Projektverantwortung oder perspektivisch in Richtung Architektur oder Management.\n\nDas bieten wir dir\nMensch & Kultur: Die Gemeinschaft und der Austausch im Unternehmen werden durch vielfältige Events wie Unternehmensmittagessen, Sommerfeste, Teamevents, Unternehmenskonferenzen und Weihnachtsfeiern aktiv gefördert. Ein Welcome Day sowie ein Mentoren-Programm während der Einarbeitungszeit tragen zudem dazu bei, den Zusammenhalt innerhalb der Teams zu stärken. Zusätzlich fördern wir den Teamgeist durch eine substanzielle Gewinnbeteiligung, die auf alle Mitarbeiter verteilt wird.\n\nKarriereentwicklung & Wissensaustausch: Die Vielfalt unserer (Kunden-)Projekte ermöglicht eine individuelle Karriereentwicklung. Verschiedenste Schulungsangebote und die Teilnahme an Fachkonferenzen fördern fachliches Wachstum. Ein jährliches Wissensbudget von 12 Tagen und Wissenszirkel unterstützen den kontinuierlichen Wissensaustausch.\n\nWork-Life-Balance & Flexibilität: Flexible Arbeitszeiten mit Arbeitszeitkonto, Mobile Office/hybrides Arbeiten, Workation-/Sabbatical-Optionen und die Möglichkeit Hunde mit ins Büro zu bringen, sind nur ein Teil unseres Angebots für Flexibilität und Lebensqualität. Auch in kritischen Situationen unterstützen wir mit bis zu 5 bezahlten Abwesenheitstagen, um sich um pflegebedürftige oder kranke Familienmitglieder zu kümmern.\n\nFinanzielle Vorteile: Mitarbeiter profitieren von unseren Zuschüssen für: Kinderbetreuung, Essen und Sport, betriebliche Altersvorsorge mit unverbindlicher Beratung, Deutschlandticket für nachhaltiges Reisen.\n\nGesundheit & Wohlbefinden: Verschiedene Gesundheitsmaßnahmen wie bewegte Pausen, Ergonomieberatung, Grippeimpfung und Augenarztuntersuchung fördern das Wohlbefinden und die langfristige Gesundheit der Mitarbeiter. Gesunde Snacks und Getränke gehören selbstverständlich ebenfalls zu unserem Angebot. Und um auch die soziale Interaktion zu stärken, haben wir Hobby- und Sportgruppen etabliert, welche nicht nur den lockeren Austausch, sondern auch den Zusammenhalt im Team stärken.\n\nSoziale Verantwortung & Nachhaltigkeit: Durch die HuManS-Stiftung streben wir danach, einen positiven Beitrag zur Gesellschaft zu leisten. Unsere Klimainitiative und das Umweltprogramm setzen sich engagiert für nachhaltige Unternehmenspraktiken ein.\n\nWir freuen uns auf deine Online-Bewerbung als Data Engineer (mwd) – Data Platforms & Data Pipelines!\nManuela Mayer\nPersonalreferentin\nJohannes Schluchter\nGeschäftsbereichsleiter Enterprise Analytical Systems','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'HMS Analytical Software GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=90f05435b41f297c','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2374,NULL,'job','Werkstudent (mwd) Software Development, Data & AI','Studentenjob','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Berlin\nHeidelberg\nUlm\nWerkstudent\nSeit über 35 Jahren unterstützen wir Unternehmen dabei, aus Daten echten Mehrwert zu schaffen. Dafür entwickeln wir maßgeschneiderte Daten-, KI- und Softwarelösungen und begleiten unsere Kunden als spezialisierter Boutique-Dienstleister entlang der gesamten Data-to-Value-Journey – von der ersten Idee bis zur produktiven Anwendung. In unseren Projekten verbinden wir Data Engineering, Machine Learning, Generative AI und Software Engineering mit fundiertem Branchenverständnis sowie methodischer Klarheit. Mit über 170 Mitarbeitenden arbeiten wir an anspruchsvollen Projekten in Branchen wie Life Science, Finance und Manufacturing und entwickeln gemeinsam nachhaltige Lösungen.\n\nDu möchtest neben dem Studium praktische Erfahrung sammeln und herausfinden, wie moderne Software-, Daten- und KI-Lösungen in der Praxis entstehen? In dieser Rolle unterstützt du bei der Entwicklung von Anwendungen im Bereich Software Engineering, Data Analytics und Künstliche Intelligenz und arbeitest eng mit erfahrenen Teams zusammen.\nDas sind deine Aufgaben\nMitarbeit in Softwareentwicklungs-, Data- und AI-Projekten\nUnterstützung bei der Entwicklung und Anpassung von Anwendungen zur Verarbeitung und Analyse von Daten\nMitwirkung bei der Umsetzung von einfachen Machine-Learning- oder AI-Anwendungsfällen\nÜbernahme klar abgegrenzter Teilaufgaben in Projekten im Umfeld von Cloud, Data und digitalen Technologien\nMitarbeit bei der Weiterentwicklung interner Systeme und Tools\nZusammenarbeit im Team sowie Einblick in unterschiedliche Projektbereiche\nDas bringst du mit\nLaufendes Studium im Bereich Informatik, Naturwissenschaften oder einem vergleichbaren Fachgebiet\nInteresse an Softwareentwicklung, Datenanalyse und Künstlicher Intelligenz\nErste praktische oder theoretische Kenntnisse in mindestens einer Programmiersprache (z. B. Python, Java, C# oder C++)\nGrundverständnis von Datenverarbeitung oder Interesse, sich in Machine Learning einzuarbeiten\nOffenheit für den Einsatz AI-gestützter Entwicklungswerkzeuge\nAnalytisches Denkvermögen und strukturierte Herangehensweise\nBereitschaft, Neues zu lernen und sich weiterzuentwickeln\nTeamfähigkeit sowie gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse\nDas bieten wir dir\nMensch & Kultur: Die Gemeinschaft und der Austausch im Unternehmen werden durch vielfältige Events wie Unternehmensmittagessen, Sommerfeste, Teamevents, Unternehmenskonferenzen und Weihnachtsfeiern aktiv gefördert. Ein Welcome Day sowie ein Mentoren-Programm während der Einarbeitungszeit tragen zudem dazu bei, den Zusammenhalt innerhalb der Teams zu stärken. Zusätzlich fördern wir den Teamgeist durch eine substanzielle Gewinnbeteiligung, die auf alle Mitarbeiter verteilt wird.\n\nKarriereentwicklung & Wissensaustausch: Die Vielfalt unserer (Kunden-)Projekte ermöglicht eine individuelle Karriereentwicklung. Verschiedenste Schulungsangebote und die Teilnahme an Fachkonferenzen fördern fachliches Wachstum. Ein jährliches Wissensbudget von 12 Tagen und Wissenszirkel unterstützen den kontinuierlichen Wissensaustausch.\n\nMöglichkeit zur Abschlussarbeit: Im Rahmen einer Werkstudententätigkeit wird gemeinsam geprüft, ob sich ein passendes Thema und Projekt für eine Bachelor- oder Masterarbeit realisieren lässt.\n\nWork-Life-Balance & Flexibilität: Flexible Arbeitszeiten mit Arbeitszeitkonto, Mobile Office/hybrides Arbeiten und die Möglichkeit Hunde mit ins Büro zu bringen, sind nur ein Teil unseres Angebots für Flexibilität und Lebensqualität. Auch in kritischen Situationen unterstützen wir mit bis zu 5 bezahlten Abwesenheitstagen, um sich um pflegebedürftige oder kranke Familienmitglieder zu kümmern.\n\nFinanzielle Vorteile: Mitarbeiter profitieren von unseren Zuschüssen für: Kinderbetreuung, Essen und Sport, Deutschlandticket für nachhaltiges Reisen.\n\nGesundheit & Wohlbefinden: Verschiedene Gesundheitsmaßnahmen wie bewegte Pausen, Ergonomieberatung, Grippeimpfung und Augenarztuntersuchung fördern das Wohlbefinden und die langfristige Gesundheit der Mitarbeiter. Gesunde Snacks und Getränke gehören selbstverständlich ebenfalls zu unserem Angebot. Und um auch die soziale Interaktion zu stärken, haben wir Hobby- und Sportgruppen etabliert, welche nicht nur den lockeren Austausch, sondern auch den Zusammenhalt im Team stärken.\n\nSoziale Verantwortung & Nachhaltigkeit: Durch die HuManS-Stiftung streben wir danach, einen positiven Beitrag zur Gesellschaft zu leisten. Unsere Klimainitiative und das Umweltprogramm setzen sich engagiert für nachhaltige Unternehmenspraktiken ein.\nWir freuen uns auf deine Online-Bewerbung als Werkstudent (mwd) Software Development, Data & AI!\nManuela Mayer\nPersonalreferentin\nJohannes Schluchter\nGeschäftsbereichsleiter Enterprise Analytical Systems','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'HMS Analytical Software GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ff7a1c180779871e','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2375,NULL,'job','Solution Consultant KI-Plattformen (m/w/d)','','66424 Homburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Wir sind ein dynamisches und leistungsstarkes Unternehmen der kosmetischen und pharmazeutischen Industrie. Neben der nach GMP-Richtlinien zertifizierten eigenen Produktion für unsere Gesichts-, Körper-, Haarpflegeprodukte und dekorativen Kosmetik legen wir großen Wert auf unser Qualitätsmerkmal \"Made in Germany\".\n\nJährlich werden unsere innovativen Apothekenprodukte mit Preisen wie \"Beste Neueinführung\" oder \"Top Marke\" ausgezeichnet.\n\nZur Verstärkung unseres IT-Teams suchen wir zum nächstmöglichen Zeitpunkt einen\n\nSolution Consultant KI-Plattformen (m/w/d)\n\nWas Dich erwartet:\n\nGestalte aktiv die Zukunft unserer KI-Plattformen im Unternehmen und fungiere als zentrale Schnittstelle zwischen Fachbereichen und IT.\n\nBerate zu Einsatzmöglichkeiten unserer Plattformen – von Data Science über Machine Learning bis hin zu Generative AI – von der Bedarfsanalyse bis zum produktiven Einsatz.\n\nBegleite Implementierungs- und Einführungsprojekte und unterstütze die optimale Nutzung unserer KI-Services und -Produkte in Zusammenarbeit mit internen Teams und externen Dienstleistern.\n\nBereite komplexe Plattform- und KI-Themen zielgruppengerecht auf – für Entscheidungsträger, Fachanwender und technische Teams.\n\nUnterstütze die Fachbereiche bei der Einhaltung regulatorischer Anforderungen (z. B. DSGVO, EU AI Act, NIS2).\n\nWas Sie auszeichnet:\n\nAbgeschlossenes Studium im Bereich Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Data Science oder eine vergleichbare Qualifikation – alternativ relevante Praxiserfahrung\n\nErste oder mehrjährige Erfahrung in der Begleitung von KI-, Daten- oder Plattformprojekten\n\nErfahrung oder Berührungspunkte mit der Implementierung von KI-Lösungen (z. B. LLMs, Cloud- oder On-Premise-Umgebungen)\n\nGrundlegende Kenntnisse in der Beratung und Umsetzung von KI-Anwendungen und Plattformen\n\nInteresse an aktuellen KI-Technologien, Trends und Tools sowie die Bereitschaft, dich kontinuierlich weiterzuentwickeln\n\nKommunikations- und Präsentationsstärke sowie eine strukturierte und teamorientierte Arbeitsweise\n\nNice to have:\n\nProgrammierkenntnisse (z. B. Python)\nErfahrung mit Machine Learning oder Generative AI\nWir bieten Dir:\nEinen interessanten und zukunftssicheren Arbeitsplatz mit Festvertrag\nVielseitige und fordernde Tätigkeit im Rahmen eines national/international operierenden Unternehmens\nGezielte und intensive Einarbeitung\n30 Tage Urlaub/Kalenderjahr\nVermögenswirksame Leistungen\nKostenlose betriebliche Zusatzkrankenversicherung\nDienstrad-Leasing\nGesundheitsfördernde Maßnahmen wie z. B. kostenlose Grippeschutzimpfungen\nVergünstigtes Mittagessen inkl. Softgetränken, Snacks, Obst im Betriebsrestaurant zum Sachbezugswert\nKostenloser Kaffee, Espresso, Tee, Wasser an unseren Espresso-Bars\nPersonalkauf\nHaben wir Ihr Interesse geweckt?\nDann freuen wir uns auf Ihre aussagekräftigen Bewerbungsunterlagen unter Angabe Ihrer Gehaltsvorstellung sowie des frühestmöglichen Eintrittstermins.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Dr. Theiss Naturwaren GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a6cfb077cb8cf8e9','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2376,NULL,'job','IT Consultant Software & Data Solutions (mwd)','Vollzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Berlin\ndeutschlandweit/remote\nDüsseldorf\nHeidelberg\nUlm\nBerufserfahrung\nVollzeit\nSeit über 35 Jahren unterstützen wir Unternehmen dabei, aus Daten echten Mehrwert zu schaffen. Dafür entwickeln wir maßgeschneiderte Daten-, KI- und Softwarelösungen und begleiten unsere Kunden als spezialisierter Boutique-Dienstleister entlang der gesamten Data-to-Value-Journey – von der ersten Idee bis zur produktiven Anwendung. In unseren Projekten verbinden wir Data Engineering, Machine Learning, Generative AI und Software Engineering mit fundiertem Branchenverständnis sowie methodischer Klarheit. Mit über 170 Mitarbeitenden arbeiten wir an anspruchsvollen Projekten in Branchen wie Life Science, Finance und Manufacturing und entwickeln gemeinsam nachhaltige Lösungen.\n\nDu möchtest nicht nur technische Lösungen umsetzen, sondern Kunden ganzheitlich beraten und aktiv durch ihre Projekte begleiten? Als IT‑Consultant arbeitest du eng mit unseren Kunden zusammen – von der ersten Analyse ihrer fachlichen und technischen Anforderungen über die Konzeption tragfähiger Lösungsarchitekturen bis hin zur gemeinschaftlichen Umsetzung. Dabei verstehst du dich als Sparringspartner, der technisches Know‑how, Verständnis für Geschäftsanforderungen und pragmatische Umsetzung verbindet.\nDas sind deine Aufgaben\nAnalyse komplexer fachlicher und technischer Anforderungen sowie Entwicklung tragfähiger Lösungsarchitekturen\nKonzeption moderner Software-, Cloud- und Datenlösungen (z. B. APIs, Microservices, Datenplattformen)\nUnterstützung im Presales, insbesondere durch Erarbeitung, Präsentation und Diskussion erster Lösungsansätze für konkrete Kundenanforderungen\nErstellung strukturierter Entscheidungsgrundlagen für technische und fachliche Stakeholder\nImplementierung von Software-, Cloud- und Datenkomponenten sowie Entwicklung von Prototypen und Minimum Viable Products\nEntwicklung und Betrieb von APIs, Datenpipelines und Services\nMitarbeit an Architekturentscheidungen, Code-Reviews und Delivery-Prozessen\nWeiterentwicklung von Engineering-Standards und Best Practices\nEinsatz AI-gestützter Tools zur Unterstützung von Entwicklung, Testing, Analyse und Dokumentation\nModeration von Workshops, u.a. zum Einsatz von AI- und GenAI-Lösungen sowie Mitwirkung an deren Umsetzung\nDas bringst du mit\nStudium in Informatik, Mathematik, Physik oder vergleichbare praktische Erfahrung\nErfahrung in der Softwareentwicklung, im Data Engineering oder im Cloud Engineering\nSehr gute Kenntnisse in mindestens einer Programmiersprache (z. B. Python, Java oder C#)\nErfahrung mit Cloud-Technologien (z. B. AWS, Azure) oder entsprechende Lernbereitschaft\nVerständnis für Softwarearchitekturen, Datenpipelines, APIs oder AI-gestützte Anwendungen\nFähigkeit, komplexe technische Inhalte klar und verständlich zu erklären\nAnalytische und strukturierte Arbeitsweise sowie sicherer Umgang mit komplexen Problemstellungen\nInteresse an der Verbindung von technischer Umsetzung und Beratung\nOffenheit für den Einsatz AI-gestützter Entwicklungswerkzeuge\nSehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse sowie Bereitschaft zu gelegentlichen Reisen\n\nDie Rolle bietet die Möglichkeit, technische Lösungen ganzheitlich zu gestalten und Verantwortung entlang des gesamten Projektzyklus zu übernehmen. Gleichzeitig bestehen vielfältige Entwicklungsmöglichkeiten – sowohl in Richtung Architektur und technische Spezialisierung als auch im Consulting oder in der Projektverantwortung. Eine strukturierte Weiterentwicklung und eine ausgewogene Balance zwischen Beruf und Privatleben sind fester Bestandteil der Zusammenarbeit.\n\nDas bieten wir dir\nMensch & Kultur: Die Gemeinschaft und der Austausch im Unternehmen werden durch vielfältige Events wie Unternehmensmittagessen, Sommerfeste, Teamevents, Unternehmenskonferenzen und Weihnachtsfeiern aktiv gefördert. Ein Welcome Day sowie ein Mentoren-Programm während der Einarbeitungszeit tragen zudem dazu bei, den Zusammenhalt innerhalb der Teams zu stärken. Zusätzlich fördern wir den Teamgeist durch eine substanzielle Gewinnbeteiligung, die auf alle Mitarbeiter verteilt wird.\n\nKarriereentwicklung & Wissensaustausch: Die Vielfalt unserer (Kunden-)Projekte ermöglicht eine individuelle Karriereentwicklung. Verschiedenste Schulungsangebote und die Teilnahme an Fachkonferenzen fördern fachliches Wachstum. Ein jährliches Wissensbudget von 12 Tagen und Wissenszirkel unterstützen den kontinuierlichen Wissensaustausch.\n\nWork-Life-Balance & Flexibilität: Flexible Arbeitszeiten mit Arbeitszeitkonto, Mobile Office/hybrides Arbeiten, Workation-/Sabbatical-Optionen und die Möglichkeit Hunde mit ins Büro zu bringen, sind nur ein Teil unseres Angebots für Flexibilität und Lebensqualität. Auch in kritischen Situationen unterstützen wir mit bis zu 5 bezahlten Abwesenheitstagen, um sich um pflegebedürftige oder kranke Familienmitglieder zu kümmern.\n\nFinanzielle Vorteile: Mitarbeiter profitieren von unseren Zuschüssen für: Kinderbetreuung, Essen und Sport, betriebliche Altersvorsorge mit unverbindlicher Beratung, Deutschlandticket für nachhaltiges Reisen.\n\nGesundheit & Wohlbefinden: Verschiedene Gesundheitsmaßnahmen wie bewegte Pausen, Ergonomieberatung, Grippeimpfung und Augenarztuntersuchung fördern das Wohlbefinden und die langfristige Gesundheit der Mitarbeiter. Gesunde Snacks und Getränke gehören selbstverständlich ebenfalls zu unserem Angebot. Und um auch die soziale Interaktion zu stärken, haben wir Hobby- und Sportgruppen etabliert, welche nicht nur den lockeren Austausch, sondern auch den Zusammenhalt im Team stärken.\n\nSoziale Verantwortung & Nachhaltigkeit: Durch die HuManS-Stiftung streben wir danach, einen positiven Beitrag zur Gesellschaft zu leisten. Unsere Klimainitiative und das Umweltprogramm setzen sich engagiert für nachhaltige Unternehmenspraktiken ein.\nWir freuen uns auf deine Online-Bewerbung als IT Consultant Software & Data Solutions (mwd)!\nManuela Mayer\nPersonalreferentin\nJohannes Schluchter\nGeschäftsbereichsleiter Enterprise Analytical Systems','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'HMS Analytical Software GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=897ed0d01bb8dfb9','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2377,NULL,'job','Werkstudent:in Softwareentwicklung (Java & Machine Learning)','Teilzeit','Oldenburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Oldenburg\nTeilzeit\nPraktikum/Werkstudium\n\nWarum wir reden sollten\nDu interessierst dich für Softwareentwicklung und willst verstehen, wie man komplexe Softwaresysteme gezielt modernisiert, ohne sie vollständig neu zu entwickeln? Genau das ist unser Schwerpunkt. Mit Java, KI und spezialisierten Werkzeugen analysieren wir bestehende Anwendungen. Wir erkennen Modernisierungspotenziale und entwickeln Konzepte für effiziente Migrationen – zum Beispiel von PHP zu Java. Generative KI hilft uns, Muster im Code, in Datenflüssen und in der Architektur zu finden. So können wir fundierte Entscheidungen treffen. Ob als Werkstudent:in oder im Rahmen einer Abschlussarbeit – bei uns kannst du aktiv mitgestalten.\nGemeinsam schaffen\nWir arbeiten eng zusammen, auf Augenhöhe und mit klaren Zielen. Du bringst Neugier, Ideen und eine frische Perspektive ein. Wir geben dir passende Aufgaben, unsere Erfahrung und den Freiraum, Neues auszuprobieren. Dein Beitrag kann vielfältig sein: Java-Code entwickeln, KI nutzen und einbinden oder Tools zur automatisierten Code-Analyse erweitern. Was wir tun, soll sowohl technisch als auch fachlich überzeugen – und genau daran arbeiten wir gemeinsam.\nGemeinsam lernen\nDu musst nicht alles wissen. Wichtig ist, dass du bereit bist, Neues zu lernen. Bei uns bekommst du Einblicke in reale Projekte und lernst moderne Werkzeuge kennen. Du erfährst, wie KI in der Praxis hilft, komplexe Systeme zu verstehen. Außerdem vertiefst du deine Java-Kenntnisse und arbeitest an Lösungen, die eine Modernisierung erst möglich machen. Und auch wir selbst lernen dabei noch etwas dazu.\nÜber uns\n\nSeit unserer Gründung im Jahr 2000 entwickeln wir maßgeschneiderte Softwarelösungen für führende Unternehmen in Deutschland, Österreich und der Schweiz.\n\nUnsere Teams realisieren innovative IT-Projekte unter anderem für Kunden aus den Bereichen Energie, Telekommunikation, Logistik, Industrie, Versicherungs- sowie Bankwesen.\n\nStrategisch, technologisch und methodisch sind wir branchenneutraler Partner für die digitale Transformation von Geschäftsprozessen im Mittelstand sowie im Konzern.\n\nUnsere Experten für Enterprise-, Web- und Cloud-Anwendungen analysieren bestehende IT-Strukturen, beraten bei der Auswahl zukunftssicherer Technologien, konzipieren nachhaltige Softwarearchitekturen und setzen diese in agilen Entwicklungsvorgehen um.\n\nAufgrund unseres Know-hows sind sowohl unsere Geschäftsführer als auch ein Teil unseres Teams regelmäßig als Redner auf internationalen Kongressen eingeladen und teilen darüber hinaus ihre Erfahrung in den wichtigsten Fachzeitschriften und -blogs.\n\nOPEN KNOWLEDGE impliziert unsere Firmenphilosophie. Benötigtes Wissen zur Erstellung und Wartung der Softwarelösungen werden stets offen mit den Teams auf Kundenseite geteilt, sodass diese nach Abschluss der Projektarbeit in der Lage sind, die Software selbstständig zu pflegen und weiterzuentwickeln.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'open knowledge','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5d7778982e5d4a0d','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2378,NULL,'job','Research Associate (Postdoc) in Financial Economics','Teilzeit','20146 Hamburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'InstitutionFaculty of Business, Economics and Social Sciences, Department of Economics\n\nSalary levelEGR. 13 TV-L\n\nStart date01.09.2026 or as soon as possible, fixed for a period of three years (This is a fixed-term contract in accordance with Section 2 of the academic fixed-term labor contract act [Wissenschaftszeitvertragsgesetz, WissZeitVG]).The contract provides for a maximum extension of up to three years depending on the associate’s achievements during the first stage. Providing that a position is available and that requirements have been fulfilled, the associate may apply for temporary civil servant status in accordance with Section 28 subsection 2 HmbHG.\n\nApplication deadline31.05.2026\n\nScope of workfull-time position suitable for part-time\n\nYour responsibilities\n\nDuties include teaching and research in the respective department or institute. Research associates may also pursue independent research and further academic qualifications as well as acquire teaching experience. These duties are intended to promote academic achievement. Therefore, at least one-third of set working hours will be made available for the associate’s own academic work.\n\nThe research group works at the forefront of financial economics. Current research interests include, among others, the role of disagreement in asset pricing, the effects of climate risks on financial markets, and the application of machine learning methods in asset pricing.\n\nThe postdoctoral researcher will become part of a vibrant, internationally connected research team with a strong focus on high-quality academic work. The position offers an excellent environment for developing an independent research profile, with intensive support for the candidate’s postdoctoral project and close collaboration within the group and its international network. The teaching load is 5 hours per week.\n\nYour profile\n\nA university degree in a relevant field, plus doctorate.\n\na PhD in Finance, Economics, or a related field\nstrong expertise in financial economics and asset pricing\nexcellent quantitative skills\nprogramming skills in relevant research software (Python/Matlab/R/…)\nclear research potential and independence\nstrong teamwork and communication skills\ngood command of written and spoken English\na willingness to contribute to the teaching at the undergraduate and/or graduate level of the group\nWe offer\nReliable remuneration based on wage agreements\nContinuing education opportunities\nUniversity pensions\nAttractive location\nFlexible working hours\nWork-life balance opportunities\nHealth management, EGYM Wellpass\nEducational leave\n30 days of vacation per annum\n\nUniversität Hamburg—University of Excellence is one of the strongest research educational institutions in Germany. Our work in research, teaching, educational and knowledge exchange activities is fostering the next generation of responsible global citizens ready to tackle the global challenges facing us. Our guiding principle “Innovating and Cooperating for a Sustainable Future in a digital age” drives collaboration with academic and nonacademic partner institutions in the Hamburg Metropolitan Region and around the world. We would like to invite you to be part of our community to work with us in creating sustainable and digital change for a dynamic and pluralist society.\n\nThe University of Hamburg is committed to equity. Diversity enriches our university life, whether in our studies, research, teaching, education, or workplace. We therefore welcome all applications, regardless of gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, ethnic or social background, age, religion or belief, disability, or chronic illness.\n\nThe University of Hamburg strives to increase the number of women in academia, and encourages qualified female academics to apply.\n\nSeverely disabled and disabled applicants with the same status will receive preference over equally qualified non-disabled applicants.\n\nInstructions for applying\nContact\n\nOle Wilms\n\nole.wilms@uni-hamburg.de\n\n+49 40 2395-28397\n\nReference number\n122\nLocation\n\nVon-Melle-Park 5\n20146 Hamburg\n\nApplication deadline\n31.05.2026\n\nUse only the online application form to submit your application with the following documents:\n\ncover letter\nCV\ncopies of degree certificate(s)\n\nIf you experience technical problems, send an email to bewerbungen@uni-hamburg.de.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Universität Hamburg','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c8410f3d0cccafdd','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2379,NULL,'job','KI-Projektleiter','','86405 Meitingen',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Ihr zukünftiger Aufgabenbereich\nEntwicklung einer ganzheitlichen KI-Strategie für das Unternehmen inklusive Zielbilds, Roadmap und Erfolgskennzahlen\nAufbau eines KI-Governance-Frameworks (Richtlinien, Sicherheits- und Compliance-Standards sowie Datenethik)\nEtablierung von KI-Standards, Methoden und Templates für das Unternehmen\nIdentifikation, Priorisierung und Bewertung von KI-Anwendungsfällen gemeinsam mit den Fachbereichen\nDurchführung von Machbarkeitsanalysen (technisch, wirtschaftlich, organisatorisch)\nDurchführung von Trainings, Workshops und Awareness-Maßnahmen\nDas bringen Sie mit\nErfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium in (Wirtschafts-) Informatik, Data Science, Künstliche Intelligenz, Digital Management oder vergleichbarer Fachrichtung\nErfahrung in der Umsetzung von KI- oder Digitalisierungsprojekten\nKenntnisse in Data Analysis, Statistik und Methoden des Machine Learning\nSicherer Umgang mit Programmiersprachen wie Python sowie relevanten KI-Frameworks (z. B. TensorFlow, PyTorch)\nErfahrung in der Entwicklung, Implementierung oder Betreuung von KI-Modellen sowie datengetriebenen Anwendungen.\nVerständnis für Unternehmensprozesse und Prozessoptimierung\nHervorragende kommunikative Fähigkeiten sowie die Fähigkeit, komplexe technische Sachverhalte verständlich zu vermitteln und andere zu begeistern und zu motivieren\nSpaß an Innovation und Veränderung\nWas wir bieten\nVerantwortungsvolle Tätigkeit mit langfristiger Perspektive\nEin spannendes Aufgabengebiet mit kurzen Entscheidungswegen und flachen Hierarchien\nEin ansprechendes und leistungsgerechtes Vergütungspaket bei 36 Std./Woche\nTarifliche Leistungen aus dem Tarifvertrag IG Metall, wie z.B. tarifliche Sonderzahlung mit\nUmwandlungsoption in zusätzliche freie Tage\nUmfangreiche Vorteile und Mitarbeiterangebote wie Corporate Benefits, Bikeleasing,\nBetriebliche Altersvorsorge, eigene Kantine, kostenlose Getränke\n\nStandort\nIndustriestraße 1, 86405 Meitingen','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Max Aicher GmbH & Co. KG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d7b6f98e67759ec6','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2380,NULL,'job','Senior Data Scientist (f/m/d)','Vollzeit','Hamburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'adjoe is redefining the future of mobile ads. Powered by advanced AI, first-party data and world-class engineers, we’ve perfected the offerwall experience for monetizing and scaling app publishers with solutions like Playtime – now the fastest growing rewarded advertising channel globally – driving incremental engagement, retention, and revenue. Together, this ecosystem connects app developers to over 770 million users worldwide for scalable growth. We are a profitable, high-growth company backed by a $100 million investment from Bertelsmann. Operating from offices in Hamburg, Boston, Singapore, and Tokyo, adjoe is defining the next stages of app and ad experience – right now. Join us.\n\nMeet Your Team: Playtime Data Science\n\nPlaytime is a time- and event-based ad unit that continuously rewards users with in-app currency – for the time they spend and events completed while playing mobile games. We connect advertisers to 700+ million Playtime users and serve 2bn requests per day at low latency. We ensure that all parties involved have a positive experience. Advertisers get more users for their apps. Monetizers earn revenue for users on their platforms. Users play fun games while simultaneously getting rewarded.\n\nOur data science team powers the engine that distributes our ads. They solve multiple tasks such as developing algorithms to provide the most relevant ads for users, predicting user interests and inclinations, and dynamically adjusting pricing based on these predictions. Because the user base is very diverse we are using deep learning models that we could show to be able to serve the best ads to users.\n\nWithin the Playtime team you will be responsible for services and models that we use to provide automated solutions both for our advertisers and publishers.\n\nWhat you will do:\n\nTranslate complex product requirements into actionable machine learning solutions.\n\nBuild robust models to predict user behavior, e.g. LTV and conversion prediction, optimizing retention, advertiser’s ROAS (return on advertising spend) and other dynamic values.\n\nLeverage state-of-the-art deep learning algorithms, ensuring each solution is fit-for-purpose and impact-driven.\n\nOwn the ML lifecycle from end-to-end: extracting insights from terabytes of user behavior data, developing models, validating them through A/B testing, and guiding them into production.\n\nPartner closely with Backend, Infrastructure, and Analytics teams to ensure seamless model integration and system stability.\n\nPresent your findings and solutions to product and business stakeholders, clearly communicating the impact of your work on product KPIs.\n\nWho you are:\n\nYou have 5+ years of professional experience in the Data Science field. You have a history of successfully deployed models that have made a measurable impact on business and product goals.\n\nYou have a strong knowledge of Python and main Data Science libraries: pytorch/tensorflow, pandas/polars, numpy, scikit-learn, lightGBM/catboost/xgboost.\n\nYou have experience developing deep learning models and have applied them already in a production environment with a large amount of traffic (>1 million predictions per day).\n\nYou have advanced SQL skills and experience drilling into large amounts of data using distributed query engines (e.g., AWS Athena, Trino, Spark).\n\nYou can explain complex mathematical foundations in simple, non-technical terms. You are comfortable in translating product language into ML logic and vice-versa.\n\nYou are open to relocating to Hamburg, Germany.\n\nBig Plus: Experience in the AdTech industry.\n\nPlus: Tech & Infrastructure knowledge: Airflow, hosting models, deploying models.\n\nFuel for the Journey: Benefits to Support Your Ambitions\nInvest in Your Future: Regular feedback and our development program support your growth, helping you expand your skillset and achieve your career goals.\nEasy Arrival to adjoe: From signing to settling in Hamburg, we’ve got you covered. Need a visa? No problem. Ready to build your new life and career at adjoe in Hamburg? We support every ambition—from learning German to a relocation bonus that helps you settle in and make Hamburg feel like home.\nLive Your Best Life, at Work and Beyond: We work in a hybrid setup with 3 core office days, plus flexible working hours. Enjoy 30 vacation days, 3 weeks of remote work per year, and free access to an in-house gym with lots of different fitness classes and mental health support through our Employee Assistance Program (EAP).\nThrive Where You Work: Enjoy the Alster lake view from our central office with top-notch equipment, fun open spaces, and a large variety of snacks and drinks.\nJoin the Community! Participate in regular team and company events, including hackathons and social gatherings. We work together, and we celebrate together, too.\nWe may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'AppLike GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=7e397abc88a6aefb','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2381,NULL,'job','Research Assistant (all genders) - Speech and Audio Applications','Teilzeit','91058 Erlangen',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Welcome to the Fraunhofer Institute for Integrated Circuits IIS\n\nAs the largest institute within the Fraunhofer-Gesellschaft, we have been conducting research for over 30 years in diverse fields such as artificial intelligence, microelectronics, sensor systems, data acquisition, signal processing, and signal transmission. Talented individuals from various engineering and natural science disciplines will find a wide range of exciting research topics under one roof. A few highlights that reflect our innovative strength include neuromorphic computing, 5G/6G mobile communication technologies, generative AI in speech and signal processing, and X-ray imaging for e-mobility. And that’s just the beginning! What sustainable solution will you find with us?\n\nBe part of change\n\nThe division »Audio and Media Technologies« is one of the world’s leading organizations in audio, speech, and media processing. For over 25 years, it has been shaping innovations in sound and vision – including groundbreaking technologies such as mp3 and AAC codecs. More than 200 engineers and scientists develop cutting-edge solutions that are used worldwide.\n\nBring research into real-world applications: You develop solutions for efficiently deploying and integrating machine learning models across platforms, enabling efficient real-time execution on mobile and embedded devices.\nOptimize for performance and efficiency: You adapt algorithms to meet strict constraints on memory consumption and computational complexity while maintaining high performance.\nEnsure correctness through strong fundamentals: You apply your expertise in signal processing to test, validate, and verify algorithmic behavior in practical audio processing scenarios.\nMaintain high software quality standards: You implement clean, reliable code and ensure robustness through automated testing, quality assurance practices, and solid experience with audio processing systems.\nWhat you contribute\nMaster’s, Ph.D. or equivalent in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field.\nStrong programming skills in C/C++ as well as good knowledge of Python, including experience with deep learning frameworks (e.g., PyTorch, TensorFlow).\nSolid experience with Linux environments, including shell scripting and build tools (e.g., gcc, make, cmake).\nPractical knowledge of DNN runtimes (e.g., ONNX, TensorFlow Lite) and optimization techniques such as model compression and quantization (e.g., pruning, quantization-aware training).\nExperience with audio DSPs, hardware SDK configuration, or digital signal processing for speech and audio is a plus.\nFluent English and ability to work effectively in international, multidisciplinary teams.\nStrong analytical and problem-solving skills with a structured, root-cause–oriented approach to debugging.\nWhat we offer\nAn exciting role: We offer a diverse and challenging field of work in an international environment, oriented toward state-of-the-art research and technology.\nRoom for creativity: Projects with strong practical components motivate our employees to drive innovation.\nOur colleagues enjoy our positive work culture: We are open-minded, we help and trust each other.\nTop of the line infrastructure at your workplace: With our state-of-the-art technologies, we develop solutions to meet the challenges of today and tomorrow.\nWe value personal contact: With our structured onboarding process, you will quickly become familiar with our institute and be able to extend your network successfully.\nWe take your needs seriously: We support your work-life balance by offering flexible working hours and hybrid work.\nYour goals and interests are important to us: We offer ongoing professional and personal seminars, coaching, and language classes.\nWe offer complimentary parking spaces, charging stations for electric cars, covered bicycle parking, and showers at the institute.\nIn-house health management, including sports courses, running groups, and relaxation seminars.\n\nThe position is initially limited to 2 years with the aim to extend it subsequently. The weekly working time is 39 hours. The position can also be filled on a part-time basis with a preference, however, to have it filled as close to a full-time position as possible.\n\nWe value and promote the diversity of our employees\' skills and therefore welcome all applications - regardless of age, gender, nationality, ethnic and social origin, religion, ideology, disability, sexual orientation and identity. Appointment, remuneration and social security benefits based on the public-sector collective wage agreement (TVöD).\n\nAbout Fraunhofer\n\nThe Fraunhofer-Gesellschaft currently operates 76 institutes and research institutions throughout Germany and is the world’s leading applied research organization. Around 32 000 employees work with an annual research budget of 3.4 billion euros. The Fraunhofer Institute for Integrated Circuits IIS, headquartered in Erlangen, is the largest institute of the Fraunhofer-Gesellschaft with more than 1 200 employees.\n\nWith its focus on developing key technologies that are vital for the future and enabling the commercial utilization of this work by business and industry, Fraunhofer plays a central role in the innovation process. As a pioneer and catalyst for groundbreaking developments and scientific excellence, Fraunhofer helps shape society now and in the future.\n\nFraunhofer is not only the largest organization for applied research (application-oriented research organisation) in Europe, but also a top-rated employer. But why?\n\nReady for change?\n\nPlease submit your full application (cover letter, CV and grade sheets) online.\n\nImportant: Please do not forget to click on the »Apply« button after »Save«. Otherwise, your application will not reach us.\n\nFraunhofer Institute for Integrated Circuits IIS\nwww.iis.fraunhofer.de','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Fraunhofer-Institut für Integrierte Schaltungen IIS','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c677bf71b7673f79','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2382,NULL,'job','Developer (all genders) C++ und Operations Research','','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Developer (all genders) C++ und Operations Research\nMünchen C++ Berufserfahrene\nDein Wirkungsfeld\n\nAls Developer C++ und Operations Research arbeitest du an der Weiterentwicklung unserer Supply-Chain-Produktfamilie waySuite\n\nDabei unterstützt du bei der Umsetzung von innovativen Funktionalitäten in den Bereichen Produktionsplanung, Optimierung und AI-gestützte Planung\n\nGemeinsam mit erfahrenen Kollegen entwickelst du Planungs- und Optimierungsverfahren sowie Machine-Learning-Modelle (ML, DL, GenAI)\n\nDu baust deine Erfahrung im gesamten Tech-Stack aus: von Backend- bis Frontend-Entwicklung\n\nIn agilen Teams übernimmst du Verantwortung für eigene Arbeitspakete und trägst aktiv dazu bei, Best Practices kennenzulernen und anzuwenden\n\nWas Dich auszeichnet\n\nDu hast einschlägige Berufserfahrung in der Softwareentwicklung mit C++\n\nDein Studium in Mathematik, Informatik, Operations Research, Data Science oder Ingenieurwissenschaften hast du erfolgreich abgeschlossen\n\nDu hast Kenntnisse im Umgang mit Microsoft Visual Studio und gängigen Tools für Source-Code-Management\n\nDu bringst solide Grundkenntnisse in mathematischen oder heuristischen Optimierungsverfahren sowie Interesse an ML- und AI-Technologien mit\n\nDu bist ein Teamplayer und überzeugst durch Kommunikationsstärke und Begeisterung für komplexe technische Fragestellungen\n\nDeine fließenden Deutsch- und sehr guten Englischkenntnisse runden dein Profil ab\n\nDarauf kannst Du Dich freuen\n\nEine spannende Rolle mit viel Raum, deine Kenntnisse in C++ und Operations Research zu vertiefen\n\nEnge Zusammenarbeit mit erfahrenen Senior Developern und OR-Spezialisten, die dich fachlich begleiten\n\nDie Möglichkeit, innovative Technologien wie GenAI kennenzulernen und in Projekten einzusetzen\n\nEin internationales Team und ein dynamisches, praxisnahes Arbeitsumfeld\n\nIndividuelle Weiterbildungs- und Entwicklungsmöglichkeiten, die zu deinem Weg passen\n\nDein Kontakt\nYannick Kempf\n\nvalantic','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'valantic GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=dc622650ae4b9623','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2383,NULL,'job','Werkstudent (d/w/m) KI-Management','Studentenjob','Hamburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Gestalte mit uns die Zukunft der Mobilität\n\nDu hast Entwicklungserfahrung und brennst dafür, KI-Use Cases eigenständig umzusetzen? Du studierst Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Data Science oder einen ähnlichen Studiengang und möchtest deine Programmierkenntnisse praktisch anwenden? Wenn du konkrete KI-Lösungen bauen willst, die wirklich etwas bewirken, bist du bei uns genau richtig.\n\nWir sind Marktführer für digitale Ticketing-Lösungen im ÖPNV in Deutschland und Teil von Siemens Mobility Mit über 130 klugen Köpfen entwickeln wir smarte Lösungen, die den Ticketkauf einfacher machen – für Fahrgäste wie für Verkehrsunternehmen. Unser Ziel: eine nachhaltige, vernetzte Mobilität, die das eigene Auto überflüssig macht.\n\nBringe deine Expertise ein:\n\nBei uns übernimmst du eine Schlüsselrolle bei der praktischen Umsetzung unserer identifizierten KI-Use Cases:\nKI-Implementierung: Du setzt bereits ermittelte KI-Anwendungsfälle eigenständig um und implementierst diese primär mit einem Workflow-automation Tool. Du automatisierst Prozesse und integrierst KI-Lösungen in unsere bestehenden Systeme.\nZusammenarbeit mit KI-Projektleitern & Key-Usern: Du arbeitest eng mit den KI-Key-Usern aus den einzelnen Abteilungen zusammen, verstehst ihre Anforderungen und setzt diese in technische Lösungen um. Parallel koordinierst du mit den KI-Projektleiter:innen zur Sicherstellung eines reibungslosen Ablaufs.\nEntwicklung & Optimierung: Du entwickelst, testest und optimierst KI-Lösungen iterativ. Du bringst eigene Ideen zur Verbesserung der Implementierungsprozesse ein und suchst nach innovativen Ansätzen.\nDokumentation & Knowledge Sharing: Du dokumentierst deine Implementierungen nachvollziehbar und trägst zum Wissensaufbau des Teams bei.\n\nWas brauchst du?\n\nStudium & KI-Passion: Aktuell eingeschrieben in Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Data Science oder ähnlichem. Starkes Interesse an KI und Machine Learning mit idealerweise ersten praktischen Erfahrungen.\nEntwicklungserfahrung: Erste Programmierkenntnisse (Python, JavaScript o.ä.) und nachgewiesene Entwicklungserfahrung durch Praktika oder Projekte. Idealerweise Erfahrung mit N8N oder ähnlichen Low-Code-Plattformen.\nHands-On-Mentalität: Freude daran, konkrete Lösungen zu bauen und Probleme eigenständig zu lösen. Strukturierte und ergebnisorientierte Arbeitsweise.\nZusammenarbeit: Gute Kommunikationsfähigkeiten und die Fähigkeit, mit verschiedenen Stakeholdern (technisch & fachlich) zusammenzuarbeiten.\nSprachkenntnisse: Verhandlungssichere Deutsch- und sehr gute Englischkenntnisse.\n\nWas bieten wir dir?\nFlexibles Arbeiten und Mobile Work – für deine optimale Work-Life-Balance.\nEinen Job mit Sinn, bei dem du aktiv innovative KI-Lösungen entwickelst.\nDie Möglichkeit, eigenständig zu arbeiten und dein volles Potenzial einzubringen.\nPraktische Erfahrung in der KI-Implementierung und Entwicklung mit modernen Tools.\nWeiterentwicklungsmöglichkeiten in einem agilen Software-Umfeld und die Chance, deine KI- und Entwicklungsfähigkeiten zu schärfen.\nEnge Zusammenarbeit mit erfahrenen KI-Profis und Mentoring.\nZentrale Lage unseres Hauptsitzes in Hamburg-Sternschanze.\nu.v.m. – schau mal auf unserer Karriereseite vorbei!\nDu willst zu uns?\n\nDu möchtest Teil eines engagierten Teams sein, das gemeinsam den innovativen Wandel der Mobilität gestaltet und dabei die Potenziale von Künstlicher Intelligenz voll ausschöpft? Dann bist du bei uns genau richtig!\nSchicke uns bitte deinen Lebenslauf unter Angabe deiner Verfügbarkeit und Gehaltsvorstellung über unser Bewerbungsformular zu.\n\nVielfalt macht uns stark! Wir begrüßen Bewerbungen von Menschen jeder Herkunft, Identität, Lebenssituation sowie mit und ohne Behinderung. Bei uns zählt, was du mitbringst – nicht woher du kommst.\n\nJob Details\nStandort: Hamburg\nBerufserfahrung: entry-level\nAnstellung: Teilzeit','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'eos.uptrade GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9d6a326a7d8da0d8','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2384,NULL,'job','Wiss. Mitarbeiter*in (PostDoc) (d/m/w) - 2. Qualifizierungsphase (zur erstmaligen Übernahme einer ordentlichen Professur)','Teilzeit','10623 Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Fakultät IV - Elektrotechnik und Informatik, Institut für Telekommunikationssysteme / FG Verteilte Systeme und Betriebssysteme\n\nWiss. Mitarbeiter*in (PostDoc) (d/m/w) - 2. Qualifizierungsphase (zur erstmaligen Übernahme einer ordentlichen Professur)\n\nTeilzeitbeschäftigung ist ggf. möglich\n\nIhre Aufgaben\n\nMitarbeit in Forschung und Lehre im Fachgebiet Distributed Operating Systems (DOS). Entwicklung und experimentelle Evaluation von Methoden zur Erfassung und Prognose von Energie- und Wasserverbrauch, sowie CO₂-Emissionen von KI-Systemen. Entwurf von Optimierungs- und Regelungsstrategien, die verteilte Recheninfrastrukturen anhand von Nachhaltigkeitssignalen adaptiv steuern. Weiterentwicklung unserer Co-Simulationswerkzeuge für Recheninfrastrukturen und Energiesysteme zur Analyse und Bewertung des Verhaltens sowie der Nachhaltigkeitswirkungen großer KI-Deployments. Veröffentlichung der Ergebnisse auf internationalen Konferenzen.\n\nIhr Profil\nErfolgreich abgeschlossenes wissenschaftliches Hochschulstudium (Master, Diplom oder Äquivalent) sowie Promotion in Informatik oder einem eng verwandten Fachgebiet.\nNachweisliche wissenschaftliche Publikationstätigkeit auf internationalen Konferenzen.\nFundierte Forschungserfahrung im Bereich energie- und CO₂-bewusster IT-Systeme, Nachhaltigkeitsbilanzierung oder ressourceneffizientem Betrieb großer Recheninfrastrukturen.\nSehr gute Kenntnisse im Bereich Maschinelles Lernen mit besonderem Fokus auf KI-Systeme für Training und Inferenz.\nErfahrung in der Leistungs-, Effizienz- und Ressourcenmodellierung moderner KI-Workloads.\nExpertise in datengetriebener Modellierung, Prognoseverfahren sowie Optimierungs- und Steuerungsmethoden zur Bewertung und Regelung von Systemverhalten unter Nachhaltigkeitsrestriktionen.\nSehr gute Programmierkenntnisse in Python und Erfahrung mit wissenschaftlichem Rechnen, Machine-Learning-Frameworks (z. B. PyTorch) sowie Optimierungswerkzeugen.\nErfahrung mit skalierbarer Datenanalyse, verteilten Systemen und Cloud- bzw. Rechenzentrumsinfrastrukturen.\nKenntnisse im Bereich Energiesysteme, CO₂-Bilanzierungsmethoden oder Nachhaltigkeitsmetriken sind von Vorteil.\nAusgeprägte Erfahrung in der Veröffentlichung und Präsentation wissenschaftlicher Ergebnisse sowie in der Betreuung und Lehre von Studierenden.\nDie Fähigkeit zum Unterrichten in deutscher und/oder in englischer Sprache wird vorausgesetzt; Bereitschaft, die jeweils fehlenden Sprachkenntnisse zu erwerben.\nFähigkeit zum selbstständigen wissenschaftlichen Arbeiten sowie zur erfolgreichen Zusammenarbeit mit interdisziplinären Teams und Industriepartnern von Vorteil.\nHinweise zur Bewerbung\n\nIhre schriftliche Bewerbung richten Sie bitte unter Angabe der Kennziffer mit den üblichen Unterlagen (Lebenslauf, Notenliste, ggf. Nachweise von Sprachkenntnissen) ausschließlich per E-Mail (zusammengefasst in einer PDF-Datei, max. 5 MB) an Herrn Prof. Dr. Odej Kao (odej.kao@tu-berlin.de).\n\nMit der Abgabe einer Onlinebewerbung geben Sie als Bewerber*in Ihr Einverständnis, dass Ihre Daten elektronisch verarbeitet und gespeichert werden. Wir weisen darauf hin, dass bei ungeschützter Übersendung Ihrer Bewerbung auf elektronischem Wege keine Gewähr für die Sicherheit übermittelter persönlicher Daten übernommen werden kann. Datenschutzrechtliche Hinweise zur Verarbeitung Ihrer Daten gem. DSGVO finden Sie auf der Webseite der Personalabteilung: https://www.abt2-t.tu-berlin.de/menue/themen_a_z/datenschutzerklaerung/.\n\nZur Wahrung der Chancengleichheit zwischen Frauen und Männern sind Bewerbungen von Frauen mit der jeweiligen Qualifikation ausdrücklich erwünscht. Schwerbehinderte werden bei gleicher Eignung bevorzugt berücksichtigt. Die TU Berlin schätzt die Vielfalt ihrer Mitglieder und verfolgt die Ziele der Chancengleichheit. Bewerbungen von Menschen aller Nationalitäten und mit Migrationshintergrund sind herzlich willkommen.\n\n Als PDF herunterladen\nFakten\nVeröffentlicht 30.04.2026\nAnzahl Angestellte ca. 7000\nKategorie Wissenschaftliche Mitarbeiter*in\nKategorie TU Berlin Wiss. Mitarbeiter*in mit Lehraufgaben, Wiss. Mitarbeiter*in PostDoc\nAufgabengebiet Wissenschaft & Forschung, Forschung, Lehre\nBeginn frühestmöglich\nDauer für 5 Jahre\nUmfang 100 % Arbeitszeit; Teilzeitbeschäftigung ist ggf. möglich\nVergütung Entgeltgruppe 13 TV-L Berliner Hochschulen\nAnforderungen\nAbschluss Master, Diplom oder Äquivalent und Promotion\nStudiengang Informatik\nKontakt\nKennziffer IV-163/26\nKontakt-Person Prof. Dr. Odej Kao\nBewerben\nBewerbungsfrist 15.05.2026\nKennziffer IV-163/26\nper E-Mail odej.kao@tu-berlin.de','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Technische Universität Berlin','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=7deffee2d8a70166','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2385,NULL,'job','Senior Softwareentwickler C# m/w/d','Festanstellung','97072 Würzburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Software-Entwicklung\n\nForchheim\n\nVollzeit\n\nUnbefristet\n\n*Zeit für deinen nächsten Karriereschritt bei sepp.med *\n\nWir entwickeln in enger Zusammenarbeit mit unseren Kunden weltweit führende Lösungen zur Bildgebung und Diagnose. Als Key Supplier treiben wir die Digitalisierung durch moderne Produkt-, Web- und Cloud-Lösungen voran. Dabei setzen wir auf AI, Machine Learning, Agilität und ein innovatives Tech-Stack. Sei Teil dieses wegweisenden Projektes und gestalte die Medizintechnik der Zukunft aktiv mit!\n\n*Deine Aufgaben - C#-Entwicklung mit Weitblick *\n\n* *Pflege und Erweiterung* – mit deiner Entwicklungserfahrung arbeitest du an der großen Codebasis einer robusten medizinischen Software in modernen DevOps-Umgebungen.\n* *Modernisierung und Migration* – zusammen mit deinem agilen Team bist du verantwortlich für die Analyse und Weiterentwicklung bestehender medizinischer Anwendungen unter C# und .NET.\n* *Konzepte & Architektur gestalten* – du erarbeitest aktiv einen fachlichen Zugang zur bestehenden Software und ihrer Architektur, um neue Designs zu erarbeiten, vorzuschlagen, zu prüfen und zu implementieren.\n* *Dein Know-how erweitern* – du hältst dein Wissen stets aktuell – unser Team unterstützt dich dabei.\n\n*Das bringst du mit - Dein Erfolgsprofil *\n\n* *Abgeschlossenes Studium im Bereich Informatik* – du hast einen Bachelor, Master oder ein Diplom in Informatik oder eine vergleichbare Qualifikation, z. B. Berufsausbildung oder verwandter Studiengang.\n* *C#/.NET Know-how* – in der Softwareentwicklung mit dem .NET Framework bzw. .NET 8 hast du mehrjährige Erfahrung und beherrschst Testautomatisierung auf mehreren Abstraktionsebenen.\n* *Clean Code & Design* – du arbeitest objektorientiert, nutzt Clean Code-Prinzipien und folgst SOLID.\n* *Tool-Kompetenz & Frameworks* – idealerweise hast du Erfahrung mit Azure DevOps, TFS, git, Visual Studio (Code) und GitHub Copilot\n* *Teamgeist & Initiative* – du bringst dich gerne ein und möchtest gemeinsam mit deinem Team wachsen.\n* *Sprachlich fit* – du verfügst über gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse.\n\n*Be you with us! – Deine Vorteile bei sepp.med*\n\n* Flexible Arbeitsmodelle & Work-Life-Balance – mit Homeoffice, Teilzeitoptionen und flexiblen Zeiten gestaltest du deinen Alltag passend zu deinem Leben.\n* Weiterbildung & Entwicklung – über unsere sepp.med Akademie oder individuell – wir fördern dich gezielt.\n* Gesundheit & Fitness – mit Sportangeboten, Gesundheitsaktionen und kostenloser Fitnessstudio-Mitgliedschaft bleibst du fit.\n* Sichere Zukunft & Wertschätzung – mit attraktiver Vergütung, Sonderzahlungen und Jubiläumsboni bist du rundum gut versorgt.\n* Starke Gemeinschaft & Kommunikation – Teamevents, transparente Kommunikation und echter Zusammenhalt sind bei uns gelebter Alltag.\n* Innovation & Austausch – Engineering Camps, Hackathons oder Expertenrunden – bei uns kannst du dich fachlich und kreativ einbringen.\n* Corporate Benefits – mit exklusiven Mitarbeiterrabatten in vielen Bereichen.\n\nArt der Stelle: Festanstellung\n\nLeistungen:\n* Betriebliche Altersvorsorge\n* Betriebliche Weiterbildung\n* Firmenevents\n* Flexible Arbeitszeiten\n* Homeoffice-Möglichkeit\n* Kostenlose Getränke\n* Kostenloser Parkplatz\n* Mitarbeiter-Rabatt\n\n\n\nBewerbungsfrage(n):\n* Was ist Ihre Gehaltsvorstellung?\n* Sind Sie reise- oder umzugsbereit?\n* Was ist Ihr frühestmögliches Eintrittsdatum?\n* Was ist Ihre bevorzugte Arbeitsform? (remote/hybrid/vor-ort)\n\nSprache:\n* Deutsch (Erforderlich)\n\nArbeitsort: Vor Ort','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'sepp.med GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=fcf43bf80736e642','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2386,NULL,'job','Data Engineer – Schwerpunkt Programmierung & Datenpipelines*','Vollzeit','53177 Bonn',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Was dich erwartet\n\nDu liebst es, Daten zum Fließen zu bringen, große Datenmengen performant zu verarbeiten und saubere Pipelines zu bauen? Dein Schwerpunkt liegt klar auf Entwicklung und Datenverarbeitung? Dann bist du hier richtig.\n\nDu arbeitest im Consulting-Umfeld und entwickelst für unterschiedliche Kunden immer wieder neue, abwechslungsreiche Datenlösungen.\nDu entwickelst skalierbare ETL/ELT-Datenpipelines für Batch- und Streaming-Verarbeitung und arbeitest mit Spark / PySpark, Python und SQL.\nDu implementierst Datenmodelle nach Kimball, Data Vault oder Lakehouse-Prinzipien.\nDu transformierst, normalisierst und denormalisierst Daten aus verschiedenen Quellsystemen.\nDu orchestrierst Datenpipelines mit Airflow oder vergleichbaren Tools und arbeitest mit Databricks, Snowflake oder ähnlichen Plattformen.\nDu unterstützt Datenanalyse- und Machine-Learning-Pipelines.\nDu sorgst für Qualität durch Testing, Dokumentation und CI/CD.\n\nWas du mitbringst\n\nDu bringst mehrjährige Berufserfahrung in den oben genannten Themen mit und hast sehr gute SQL-Kenntnisse sowie sehr gute Kenntnisse in Spark / PySpark.\nDu arbeitest sicher mit Python, hast Erfahrung mit dbt und Airflow oder vergleichbaren Orchestrierungstools.\nDu bist sicher im Umgang mit Snowflake und/oder Databricks und erfahren in Datenmodellierung (dimensionale Modellierung, Data Vault, Normalisierung & Denormalisierung).\nDu denkst analytisch und hast Freude daran, komplexe Datenprobleme sauber zu lösen.\nErfahrung in Datenmodellierung (dimensionale Modellierung, Data Vault, Normalisierung & Denormalisierung)\nDu denkst analytisch und hast Freude daran, komplexe Datenprobleme sauber zu lösen.\nDu arbeitest selbstorganisiert und behältst auch in mehreren Kundenprojekten den Überblick.\nDu hast Lust auf Consulting und wechselnde, spannende Projekte.\nDu kommunizierst offen und konstruktiv und schätzt offenes Feedback.\n\nWorauf du dich freuen kannst - unsere Benefits\n\nInnovative Projekte und kreatives Umfeld: Du arbeitest an spannenden Kundenprojekten in einem kreativen und dynamischen Arbeitsumfeld mit viel Raum für eigene Ideen und persönliche Weiterentwicklung.\nAgilität: Du wirst Teil eines Teams, das agil und flexibel arbeitet, um immer die besten Ergebnisse zu erzielen.\nFlexibilität: Gestalte deinen Arbeitstag nach deinen Bedürfnissen – mit der Option auf Homeoffice und flexiblen Arbeitszeiten.\nGestaltungsspielraum: Du hast die Möglichkeit, den Data-Bereich bei uns aktiv mitzugestalten und weiter auszubauen.\nWissen teilen & gemeinsam wachsen – Du profitierst von intensivem internem Know-how-Transfer und hast die Möglichkeit, Dich aktiv an der Weiterentwicklung des Teams zu beteiligen – fachlich wie menschlich.\nTeamgeist: In unserem offenen und kollegialen Umfeld wird Teamarbeit großgeschrieben – wir glauben daran, dass die besten Ideen im Austausch entstehen. Wir schätzen Vielfalt und fördern eine Kultur der Inklusion. Bei uns ist jeder herzlich willkommen!\nAttraktive Benefits: Du bekommst ein attraktives Gehalt, diverse Benefits und coole Mitarbeiterevents.\n* Wir freuen uns über Bewerbungen von allen Personen, unabhängig von Geschlecht, Alter, ethnischer Herkunft, Religion, Weltanschauung, Behinderung oder sexueller Identität. Menschen mit Behinderung werden bei gleicher Qualifikation bevorzugt berücksichtigt. Um die Lesbarkeit und Verständlichkeit zu fördern, haben wir in der gesamten Jobanzeige eine einheitliche Schreibweise gewählt. Diese dient ausschließlich der besseren Orientierung und beinhaltet keinerlei Wertung oder Ausschluss.\n\nÜber uns\n\nWir sind Haeger Consulting, ein dynamisches IT-Consulting-Unternehmen mit Standort in Bonn Bad Godesberg. Unser buntes Team von etwa 80 kreativen Köpfen und Tech-Gurus liebt es, digitale Herausforderungen zu meistern und die Zukunft aktiv mitzugestalten. Unser Team besteht aus motivierten und talentierten Profis, die mit Leidenschaft und Engagement daran arbeiten, die besten Lösungen für unsere Kunden zu entwickeln. Gemeinsam schaffen wir eine inspirierende Arbeitsatmosphäre, in der jeder sein Bestes geben kann.\n\nUnser einzigartiger Ansatz\nWir sind überzeugt davon, dass jeder Mensch einzigartig ist und Talente besitzt, die nur darauf warten, entfaltet zu werden. Bei der Auswahl neuer Mitarbeiter zählt für uns nicht nur das, was auf dem Papier steht, sondern vor allem das individuelle Potential.\n\nIndividuelle Förderung\nUnsere Mitarbeiter profitieren von kontinuierlicher Begleitung und individuellem Coaching. Wir ermutigen und unterstützen sie, ständig an sich zu arbeiten und ihr volles Potential zu entfalten. Dabei gehen wir auf persönliche Wünsche und Lebensumstände ein, um eine optimale Entwicklung und Zufriedenheit sicherzustellen.\n\nInnovation und Kreativität\nUnser Ziel ist es, die digitale Zukunft mit kreativen und maßgeschneiderten Lösungen zu gestalten. Standardlösungen sind nicht unser Ding – wir bieten innovative und agile Ansätze, die perfekt auf die Bedürfnisse und Herausforderungen unserer Kunden zugeschnitten sind.\n\nWarum Haeger Consulting?\nWeil wir anders sind. Weil wir an das Potential jedes Einzelnen glauben. Und weil wir die digitale Zukunft mit Begeisterung und Kreativität gestalten. Mach mit und werde Teil von etwas Großartigem!','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Haeger Consulting','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b6a27f36fd04826c','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2387,NULL,'job','Senior Softwareentwickler C# m/w/d','Festanstellung','96052 Bamberg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Software-Entwicklung\n\nForchheim\n\nVollzeit\n\nUnbefristet\n\n*Zeit für deinen nächsten Karriereschritt bei sepp.med *\n\nWir entwickeln in enger Zusammenarbeit mit unseren Kunden weltweit führende Lösungen zur Bildgebung und Diagnose. Als Key Supplier treiben wir die Digitalisierung durch moderne Produkt-, Web- und Cloud-Lösungen voran. Dabei setzen wir auf AI, Machine Learning, Agilität und ein innovatives Tech-Stack. Sei Teil dieses wegweisenden Projektes und gestalte die Medizintechnik der Zukunft aktiv mit!\n\n*Deine Aufgaben - C#-Entwicklung mit Weitblick *\n\n* *Pflege und Erweiterung* – mit deiner Entwicklungserfahrung arbeitest du an der großen Codebasis einer robusten medizinischen Software in modernen DevOps-Umgebungen.\n* *Modernisierung und Migration* – zusammen mit deinem agilen Team bist du verantwortlich für die Analyse und Weiterentwicklung bestehender medizinischer Anwendungen unter C# und .NET.\n* *Konzepte & Architektur gestalten* – du erarbeitest aktiv einen fachlichen Zugang zur bestehenden Software und ihrer Architektur, um neue Designs zu erarbeiten, vorzuschlagen, zu prüfen und zu implementieren.\n* *Dein Know-how erweitern* – du hältst dein Wissen stets aktuell – unser Team unterstützt dich dabei.\n\n*Das bringst du mit - Dein Erfolgsprofil *\n\n* *Abgeschlossenes Studium im Bereich Informatik* – du hast einen Bachelor, Master oder ein Diplom in Informatik oder eine vergleichbare Qualifikation, z. B. Berufsausbildung oder verwandter Studiengang.\n* *C#/.NET Know-how* – in der Softwareentwicklung mit dem .NET Framework bzw. .NET 8 hast du mehrjährige Erfahrung und beherrschst Testautomatisierung auf mehreren Abstraktionsebenen.\n* *Clean Code & Design* – du arbeitest objektorientiert, nutzt Clean Code-Prinzipien und folgst SOLID.\n* *Tool-Kompetenz & Frameworks* – idealerweise hast du Erfahrung mit Azure DevOps, TFS, git, Visual Studio (Code) und GitHub Copilot\n* *Teamgeist & Initiative* – du bringst dich gerne ein und möchtest gemeinsam mit deinem Team wachsen.\n* *Sprachlich fit* – du verfügst über gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse.\n\n*Be you with us! – Deine Vorteile bei sepp.med*\n\n* Flexible Arbeitsmodelle & Work-Life-Balance – mit Homeoffice, Teilzeitoptionen und flexiblen Zeiten gestaltest du deinen Alltag passend zu deinem Leben.\n* Weiterbildung & Entwicklung – über unsere sepp.med Akademie oder individuell – wir fördern dich gezielt.\n* Gesundheit & Fitness – mit Sportangeboten, Gesundheitsaktionen und kostenloser Fitnessstudio-Mitgliedschaft bleibst du fit.\n* Sichere Zukunft & Wertschätzung – mit attraktiver Vergütung, Sonderzahlungen und Jubiläumsboni bist du rundum gut versorgt.\n* Starke Gemeinschaft & Kommunikation – Teamevents, transparente Kommunikation und echter Zusammenhalt sind bei uns gelebter Alltag.\n* Innovation & Austausch – Engineering Camps, Hackathons oder Expertenrunden – bei uns kannst du dich fachlich und kreativ einbringen.\n* Corporate Benefits – mit exklusiven Mitarbeiterrabatten in vielen Bereichen.\n\nArt der Stelle: Festanstellung\n\nLeistungen:\n* Betriebliche Altersvorsorge\n* Betriebliche Weiterbildung\n* Firmenevents\n* Flexible Arbeitszeiten\n* Homeoffice-Möglichkeit\n* Kostenlose Getränke\n* Kostenloser Parkplatz\n* Mitarbeiter-Rabatt\n\n\n\nBewerbungsfrage(n):\n* Was ist Ihre Gehaltsvorstellung?\n* Sind Sie reise- oder umzugsbereit?\n* Was ist Ihr frühestmögliches Eintrittsdatum?\n* Was ist Ihre bevorzugte Arbeitsform? (remote/hybrid/vor-ort)\n\nSprache:\n* Deutsch (Erforderlich)\n\nArbeitsort: Vor Ort','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'sepp.med GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=46359e7bf8facfb9','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2388,NULL,'job','Lead Research Engineer (f/m/d) - Foundation and World Models on Structured Data','Vollzeit','85748 Garching bei München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We help the world run better\n\nAt SAP, we keep it simple: you bring your best to us, and we\'ll bring out the best in you. We\'re builders touching over 20 industries and 80% of global commerce, and we need your unique talents to help shape what\'s next. The work is challenging – but it matters. You\'ll find a place where you can be yourself, prioritize your wellbeing, and truly belong. What\'s in it for you? Constant learning, skill growth, great benefits, and a team that wants you to grow and succeed.\n\nWhat you`ll do:\n\nAt SAP’s Business AI Research, we are exploring the next frontier of AI methods on structured business data – graphs, tables, time series, and more. Foundation Models on Structured Data, like SAP-RPT-1, have ushered in the GenAI era for business relevant scenarios – scenarios that have so far been addressed with classical, often tree-based methods. Now, we are taking the next step. We collaborate with our existing applied research teams in creating novel benchmarks for business problems and the development of novel architectures and models, with the goal to publish benchmarks and models at scientific conferences and in the open-source community. We are working jointly with our academic partners to create ever better means of solving real business problems.\n\nThe Role:\n\nContribute to pioneering technical advances to the field of foundation models on structured data, as well as exploring world models for solving business problems.\n\nDefine the data, training, and experimentation environment to enable scalable access to data and compute.\n\nDefine and lead the creation of new training and benchmark datasets, bringing together rich semantic context with large scale business data.\n\nCollaborate on definition of evaluation frameworks and benchmark suites, driving internal and external exploration of novel tasks.\n\nMake critical design decisions regarding the selection and implementation of underlying technologies.\n\nExecute scientific experiments on internal as well as public data.\n\nDefine and drive open source model and software contributions based on research deliverables.\n\nWhat you bring:\n\nPhD or Master’s degree in computer science, artificial intelligence, physics, mathematics or other relevant disciplines.\n\n5+ years of professional experience with a deep background in Machine Learning on Structured Data, and its application in a business context.\n\nDemonstrated ownership of scalable machine learning and data environment, with deep understanding of success criteria and trade offs.\n\nKnowledge of latest research and development trends in Foundation Models on Structured Data.\n\nExperience in Data Engineering with a hands-on approach to solving data challenges.\n\nFluent in Python and the ability to convert your ideas into productive code.\n\nDeveloper experience with any SAP Application and its underlying data models is a plus.\n\nStrong communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively in cross-cultural teams.\n\nMeet your team:\n\nSAP\'s AI organization is dedicated to seamlessly infusing AI into all enterprise applications, enabling customers, partners, and developers to enhance business processes and generate remarkable business value. Join our international AI team where innovation thrives, opportunities for personal development abound, and exceptional colleagues collaborate globally.\n\n#SAPBusinessAICareers\n\nBring out your best\n\nSAP innovations help more than four hundred thousand customers worldwide work together more efficiently and use business insight more effectively. Originally known for leadership in enterprise resource planning (ERP) software, SAP has evolved to become a market leader in end-to-end business application software and related services for database, analytics, intelligent technologies, and experience management. As a cloud company with two hundred million users and more than one hundred thousand employees worldwide, we are purpose-driven and future-focused, with a highly collaborative team ethic and commitment to personal development. Whether connecting global industries, people, or platforms, we help ensure every challenge gets the solution it deserves. At SAP, you can bring out your best.\n\nWe win with inclusion\n\nSAP’s culture of inclusion, focus on health and well-being, and flexible working models help ensure that everyone – regardless of background – feels included and can run at their best. At SAP, we believe we are made stronger by the unique capabilities and qualities that each person brings to our company, and we invest in our employees to inspire confidence and help everyone realize their full potential. We ultimately believe in unleashing all talent and creating a better world.\n\nSAP is committed to the values of Equal Employment Opportunity and provides accessibility accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are interested in applying for employment with SAP and are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to Recruiting Operations Team: Careers@sap.com.\n\nFor SAP employees: Only permanent roles are eligible for the SAP Employee Referral Program, according to the eligibility rules set in the SAP Referral Policy. Specific conditions may apply for roles in Vocational Training.\n\nAI Usage in the Recruitment Process\n\nFor information on the responsible use of AI in our recruitment process, please refer to our Guidelines for Ethical Usage of AI in the Recruiting Process.\n\nPlease note that any violation of these guidelines may result in disqualification from the hiring process.\n\nRequisition ID: 448365 | Work Area: Software-Design and Development | Expected Travel: 0 - 10% | Career Status: Professional | Employment Type: Regular Full Time #LI-Hybrid','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'SAP','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=3a19d4ea55d82afd','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2389,NULL,'job','Research Engineer Neuro-Symbolic AI & Mulitmodal Assistant Systems (f/m/div.)','Festanstellung','71272 Renningen',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Aufgaben\n\nAre you passionate about building intelligent systems that truly understand and reason, especially within the complex fields of manufacturing, product development, and maintenance? Neuro-Symbolic AI is leading the next big step in AI, offering huge potential to improve production, boost automation, and enable smarter decisions, bringing us closer to human-like intelligence. We are seeking a highly motivated research engineer to strengthen our team, drive the development of Neuro-Symbolic AI approaches, and enable their practical application in concrete use cases.\n\nAs part of our advanced research team, you will conduct excellent research on Neuro-Symbolic AI methodologies to combine formal knowledge representations with machine learning techniques.\nYou will independently develop and integrate multi-modal data pipelines for Neuro-Symbolic AI.\nAdditionally, you will design and implement the architecture for advanced analysis and reasoning engines for solving complex problems.\nYou will design and implement knowledge-based AI systems with natural language interaction.\nFurthermore, you will work closely with an international team of experts to effectively transfer research solutions into business-relevant use cases such as product development, maintenance, and repair.\nLast but not least, you will proactively stay informed about the latest advances in AI and machine learning to keep Bosch at the forefront of innovation in this field.\nProfil\nEducation: PhD in Computer Science, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, or a related field\nExperience and Know-how:\nexpertise in Neuro-Symbolic AI architectures and frameworks\nproven ability to design, implement, and integrate hybrid AI systems that combine machine learning with symbolic reasoning (e.g., knowledge graphs, rule sets, logic programming, ontologies) to meet complex requirements\nadvanced knowledge in building robust data pipelines for multi-modal integration (integration, cleaning, and preprocessing of heterogeneous data sources)\npractical experience in applying state-of-the-art NLP techniques (e.g., Transformers, LLMs, information extraction) to understand user queries, extract insights from texts, and contribute to the automatic construction and expansion of dynamic knowledge bases\nPersonality and Working Practice: you succeed in translating complex research findings into practical solutions and enjoy working in an international team.\nLanguages: very good English skills written and spoken, German is a plus\nWissenswertes zum Job\n\nhttps://www.bosch-ai.com\nwww.bosch.com/research\n\nPlease submit all relevant documents (CV, certificates, and links to GitHub or kaggle account).\n\nWe offer flexible working models: from various part-time options to mobile working and job sharing. Feel free to contact us.\n\nDiversity and inclusion are not just trends for us but are firmly anchored in our corporate culture. Therefore, we welcome all applications, regardless of gender, age, disability, religion, ethnic origin or sexual identity.\n\nWork #LikeABosch starts here: Apply now!\n\nHinweise zur Bewerbung\n\nSolange diese Stelle in unserer Jobbörse ausgeschrieben ist, suchen wir nach passenden Kandidatinnen und Kandidaten.\n\nAus Datenschutzgründen ist eine Bewerbung nur über unser Bewerbungsportal möglich. Bewerbungen per Mail oder Post können wir daher leider nicht berücksichtigen.\nWillkommen in Renningen\n\nUnser Forschungscampus in Renningen bildet den internationalen Knotenpunkt unserer Bereiche Forschung und Vorausentwicklung, Cross-Domain Computing Solutions und Bosch Center for Artificial Intelligence. Mitarbeiter aus aller Welt arbeiten daran, Antworten auf die Fragen von Übermorgen zu finden. Damit sich die Ideen unserer Forscher optimal entfalten können, ist der Campus ein Netz der kurzen Wege zwischen Kommunikation und Inspiration, an dem der Kreativität keine Grenzen gesetzt sind. Wollen auch Sie die Zukunft gestalten? Wir freuen uns auf Ihre Neugier und Innovationsfreude.\n\nMehr zum Standort erfahren\nWillkommen bei Bosch\n\nBei Bosch gestalten wir Zukunft mit hochwertigen Technologien und Dienstleistungen, die Begeisterung wecken und das Leben der Menschen verbessern. Unser Versprechen an unsere Mitarbeiterinnen und Mitarbeiter steht dabei felsenfest: Wir wachsen gemeinsam, haben Freude an unserer Arbeit und inspirieren uns gegenseitig. Willkommen bei Bosch.\n\nDie Robert Bosch GmbH freut sich auf eine Bewerbung!\nNoch Fragen? Wir helfen gerne weiter!\nRund um den Bewerbungsprozess\nTechnischer Support\n\nFragen zum Bewerbungsprozess? Kathrin Stipak (Human Resources) steht bereit.\n\n+49 711 811 38015','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Bosch Group','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=50fb47b9a99c1e51','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2390,NULL,'job','Wissenschaftliche/r Mitarbeiter/in - Visual Computing (NAS)','Vollzeit','57076 Siegen',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Bereich: Fakultät IV - Naturwissenschaftlich-Technische Fakultät | Stellenumfang: Vollzeit | Beschäftigungsdauer: befristet | Ausschreibungs-ID: 7003\n\nWir sind eine interdisziplinär ausgerichtete und weltoffene Universität mit aktuell rund 14.000 Studierenden und einem Fächerspektrum von den Geistes-, Sozial- und Wirtschaftswissenschaften bis hin zu Natur-, Ingenieur- und Lebenswissenschaften. Mit über 2.000 Beschäftigten zählen wir zu den größten Arbeitgebern der Region und bieten ein einzigartiges Umfeld für Lehre, Forschung und Weiterbildung.\n\nWir suchen:\n\nIn der Fakultät IV - Naturwissenschaftlich-Technische Fakultät, ET-I / Visual Computing, suchen wir eine/n wissenschaftliche/n MItarbeiter/in zum 01.09.2026 zu folgenden Konditionen:\n\n100% = 39,83 Stunden\nEntgeltgruppe 13 TV-L\nbefristet bis 31.08.2029\nIhre Aufgaben:\nMitarbeit in einem Emmy-Noether DFG- Forschungsprojekt\nForschung im Bereich der Neuralen Architektur Suche mittels Methoden des maschinellen Lernens\nUnterstützung in Forschung und Lehre, Betreuung und Prüfung der Studierenden sowie Mitwirkung bei administrativen Aufgaben\nEigenständige Entwicklung bzw. Durchführung von entwickelten Ansätzen im Forschungsprojekt\nSchreiben von wissenschaftlichen Papern in internationalen Journalen und für internationale Konferenzen\nIhr Profil:\nWissenschaftlicher Hochschulabschluss (Master oder vergleichbar) im Fach Informatik, oder Mathematik (oder vergleichbar) mit Fokus auf Deep Learning\nStarker wissenschaftlicher Hintergrund im Bereich Automated Machine Learning, im Besonderen Neuronale Architektur Suche und Pruning-Methoden\nLehrerfahrung\nSehr gute Noten\nInteresse an interdisziplinärer Zusammenarbeit\nsehr gute Englischkenntnisse\nUnser Angebot:\nFörderung der eigenen wissenschaftlichen oder künstlerischen Qualifizierung nach dem Wissenschaftszeitvertragsgesetz (z.B. Promotion)\nVielfältige Möglichkeiten, Verantwortung zu übernehmen und einen sichtbaren Beitrag im Umfeld von Forschung und Lehre zu leisten\nEin modernes Verständnis von Führung und Zusammenarbeit\nGute Vereinbarkeit von Beruf und Privatleben, beispielsweise durch flexible Ausgestaltung von Arbeitszeit und Arbeitsort sowie Unterstützung bei der Kinderbetreuung\nUmfangreiches Personalentwicklungsprogramm\nGesundheitsmanagement mit breit gefächertem Präventions- und Beratungsangebot\n\nWir freuen uns auf Ihre Bewerbung bis zum 12.05.2026.\n\nBitte bewerben Sie sich ausschließlich über unser Jobportal (https://jobs.uni-siegen.de). Bewerbungen in Papierform oder per E-Mail können wir leider nicht berücksichtigen.\n\nIhre Ansprechperson:\n\nJun.-Prof.in Dr. Jovita Lukasik\n\n0271 740-4441\n\njovita.lukasik@uni-siegen.de\n\nChancengerechtigkeit und Diversity werden an der Universität Siegen gefördert und gelebt. Die Ausschreibung richtet sich ausdrücklich an Menschen aller Geschlechter (m/w/d); Bewerbungen von Frauen werden gemäß Landesgleichstellungsgesetz besonders berücksichtigt. Gleichermaßen wünschen wir uns Bewerbungen von Personen mit unterschiedlichstem persönlichen, sozialen und kulturellen Hintergrund, Menschen mit Schwerbehinderung und diesen Gleichgestellten.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Universität Siegen','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=294f01a0efc589e6','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2391,NULL,'job','Economists - Prices and Costs','Vollzeit','60314 Frankfurt am Main',NULL,'',5876.00,'5.876 € pro Monat','General Information\n\nType of contract Fixed-term contract, which may be extended subject to individual performance and organisational needs\n\nWho can apply? EU nationals\n\nSalary F/G (bracket 1 - step 1) full time monthly net salary: €5,876 plus benefits, for further information see what we offer.\n\nRole specialisation Economics and Monetary Policy\n\nWorking time Full time\n\nPlace of work Frankfurt am Main, Germany\n\nClosing date 19.05.2026\n\nYour team\n\nThe Prices and Costs Division in the Directorate General Economics is seeking candidates for two Economist positions.\n\nOur Directorate General monitors, analyses, models and forecasts economic developments and policies. It also prepares analytical studies, reports, and external communications. Our Division is responsible for analysing and assessing inflationary pressures in the euro area. We also provide input for internal decision-making processes and external communications on the inflation outlook and potential risks, the external and domestic environment, wage and profit developments and expectations. We work closely with briefing and forecast coordination units and with colleagues in other divisions on analysing and forecasting the different dimensions of the euro area economy. We are currently expanding our analytical work at the intersection of artificial intelligence and inflation analysis by applying advanced machine learning techniques to time series data, as well as by using large language models for the analysis of inflation dynamics.\n\nIn your role as Economist, you will be part of a team of around 20 experts in forecasting, modelling and assessing inflationary pressures and will work closely with colleagues from across the ECB’s business areas, from national central banks across the Eurosystem and their policy institutions, and from the academic community.\n\nThe ECB is an inclusive employer and we strive to reflect the diversity of the population we serve. We encourage you to apply irrespective of age, disability, ethnicity, gender, gender identity, race, religious beliefs, sexual orientation or other characteristics.\n\nYour role\n\nAs an Economist, you will:\ndevelop analytical tools (in particular using machine learning techniques) and conduct research on inflation and its determinants;\nestablish and maintain models of inflation based on macro and micro data for forecasting and analysis;\ncontribute to documents, presentations and briefing material for members of the Executive Board, the Governing Council and senior management of the ECB;\nengage and collaborate with colleagues from other divisions and business areas of the ECB, from national central banks, from other international institutions and from academia;\ncontribute to the official publications of the ECB, such as the Economic Bulletin, as well as other publications, presentations and speeches.\n\nWe actively support professional development for our staff. Besides learning opportunities such as training and mentoring, we encourage and support horizontal mobility after some years in the same position.\n\nThese positions offer you excellent opportunities to gain exposure to a large range of issues related to inflation, in terms of both subject matter and policy implications. It will enable you to use your economic and econometric modelling skills and acquire new ones. You will be part of a multicultural team that strives for continuous innovation to make a positive impact on the lives of European citizens.\n\nQualifications, experience and skills\n\nEssential:\na master\'s degree or equivalent in economics or another relevant field (see How you can join us for details on degree equivalences);\nin addition to the above, a minimum of four years\' professional experience (other than as a trainee or intern) in statistical and econometric techniques for analysing inflation;\na track record in preparing analysis using applied microeconomics or macroeconomics, leveraging machine learning techniques and/or large language models;\nvery good writing skills and the ability to draft well-structured notes to strict deadlines;\nan advanced (C1) command of English and an intermediate (B1) command of at least one other official language of the EU, according to the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages.\n\nDesired:\na PhD and a research record in economics.\n\nYou engage collaboratively with others. You pursue team goals and learn willingly from other people’s diverse perspectives. You signal any need for change by explaining it and proposing alternative solutions. You analyse complex information effectively and can evaluate different views to arrive at solutions. You know and anticipate stakeholder needs.\n\nYou are motivated to contribute to the ECB’s mission, to serve the citizens of the EU as a member of a public institution and to work with colleagues from all over Europe.\n\nYou are motivated to be part of our team and to develop and use your skills and competencies to achieve the aims of this position.\n\nWorking modalities\n\nWe would be happy to discuss part-time arrangements for these roles.\n\nFurther information\n\nThe contracts offered will be fixed-term, the appointments being until 31 December 2027.\n\nTemporary appointments may be extended or made permanent subject to organisational needs and budgetary constraints. This may result in a staff member with a non-convertible fixed-term contract being offered a convertible contract in accordance with the ECB Conditions of Employment.\n\nFor additional information on this specific vacancy, you can speak to the chair of the selection panel, Eliza Lis, on +49 (0)69 1344 6096 between 11:00 and 13:00 on Wednesday, 6 May.\n\nApplication and selection process\n\nThe recruitment process for these positions will be conducted remotely. It will include a written exercise, a presentation and an interview (tentatively scheduled for 22 and 23 June 2026).\n\nIf you are not selected for this position but are still considered suitable, you will be placed on a reserve list (see step 4 of How we hire), from which you might be considered for similar positions within the ECB.\n\nFind out how to apply for a position at the ECB.\nRead more about how you can join us.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'The European Central Bank','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e98d8ac705b819e7','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2392,NULL,'job','PhD position (f/m/d) Cross-Sensor Transfer Learning for Long-Term Forest Biomass and Structure Estimation Using Established and Next-Generation SAR Missions','Teilzeit','76344 Eggenstein-Leopoldshafen',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'part time 75%\n\nDo you have a strong interest in remote sensing, forests, and Earth observation? Are you excited about combining next-generation satellite missions with machine learning to reconstruct long-term forest dynamics? If so, we invite applications for a PhD position at the Institute of Photogrammetry and Remote Sensing (KIT-IPF), as part of the International Research Training Group C4LaND.\n\nOrganisationseinheit\n\nInstitut für Photogrammetrie und Fernerkundung (IPF)\n\nIhre Aufgaben\n\nForests play a central role in the land-use nexus by providing carbon storage, biodiversity, and renewable resources, while being increasingly affected by land-use change and climate extremes. Robust, spatially explicit and temporally consistent information on forest biomass and structure is essential for assessing long-term land-use trade-offs and informing integrated modelling and governance frameworks. Recently launched Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) satellite missions have been specifically designed to retrieve three-dimensional forest structure and above-ground biomass with high sensitivity, but their observational records are short. In contrast, established SAR missions such as Sentinel-1 offer dense and consistent time series extending back more than a decade, albeit with limited biomass sensitivity.\n\nThis PhD position is part of the International Research Training Group C4LaND and focuses on developing transfer learning approaches that link forest above-ground biomass and structure estimates from next-generation, biomass-oriented SAR missions to long-term SAR archives, thereby enabling spatially explicit reconstruction of forest dynamics at least back to the beginning of the Sentinel-1 era. The project will be hosted at KIT (Karlsruhe Institute of Technology), Institute for Photogrammetry and Remote Sensing (IPF), under the supervision of Prof. Stefan Hinz. Your Melbourne co-advisor will be Dr. Jagannath Aryal.\n\nLines of research include\n\nDeveloping cross-sensor transfer learning frameworks based on multi-level SAR observables for above-ground biomass estimation by exploiting polarimetric SAR features across sensor generations and enriching them with higher-order structural information from Polarimetric InSAR and Tomographic SAR where available.\nExploration of multi-modal and multi-model support using optical and hyperspectral data to improve robustness and generalizability of transfer learning between SAR sensors.\nSensor-aware uncertainty characterization and error transfer, with emphasis on decomposing the error budget and estimating loss of precision associated with products derived from established missions compared to new biomass missions.\nValidation across long-term forest observatories in multiple regions, including Europe (TERENO), Australia (CSIRO Permanent Rainforest Plots), and potentially Brazil, ensuring transferability across forest types, climatic zones, and land-use contexts relevant to C4LAND.\n\nEintrittstermin\n\nOctober 2026\n\nIhre Qualifikation\n\nAn above-average M.Sc. degree (or equivalent) in remote sensing, environmental sciences, computer science, forestry or a related field.\nStrong background and interest in Earth observation, remote sensing of forests and SAR data processing\nExperience with machine learning, domain adaptation, or transfer learning methods is highly desirable.\nExcellent communication skills and enthusiasm for working in an international and multidisciplinary research environment.\nFluency in English, written and spoken\nWillingness to undertake a one-year research placement at the University of Melbourne, Australia and comply with formalities at both institutions.\n\nDas bieten wir Ihnen\n\nBecome a member of staff of the only German University of Excellence that conducts large-scale research on the national level. Work under excellent working conditions in an international environment and be active in research and academic education for our future. Benefit from specific training when starting your job and from a wide range of further qualification offers. Use our flexible working time models (flexitime, work from home), our sports and leisure offers, as well as our child and holiday care services. We also pay a share of EUR 25/month in the Job Ticket Baden-Württemberg. Enjoy a large variety of dishes, snacks, and beverages at our canteens.\n\nSalary\n\nSalary category 13 TV-L, depending on the fulfillment of professional and personal requirements.\n\nContract duration\n\nlimited for 3,5 years\n\nApplication up to\n\nMay 17, 2026\n\nContact person in line-management\n\nFor further information, please contact Stefan Hinz, email: stefan.hinz@kit.edu .\n\nApplication\n\nApplications should include a letter of motivation, CV, contact details of two references, and Bachelor and Master studies transcripts.\n\nAusschreibungsnummer: 1114/2026\n\nWir streben eine möglichst gleichmäßige Besetzung der Arbeitsplätze mit Beschäftigten (w/m/d) an und würden uns daher insbesondere über Bewerbungen von Frauen freuen. Bei gleicher Eignung werden anerkannt schwerbehinderte Menschen bevorzugt berücksichtigt.\nKontakt\n\nBei allgemeinen Fragen zur Bewerbung:\nPersonalservice (PSE) - Personalbetreuung\nFrau Jung\nTelefon: +49 721 608-42098,\n\nInstitut für Photogrammetrie und Fernerkundung (IPF)','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Karlsruher Institut für Technologie','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5a329756d0cacc19','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2393,NULL,'job','Praktikant:in Softwareentwicklung & Innovation (m/w/d)','Teilzeit','89073 Ulm',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Deine Aufgaben\n\nDu willst echte Software bauen, statt Kaffee kochen? Dann lass uns reden.\n\nDu entwickelst echte Software, die Kunden später wirklich nutzen – kein „Praktikanten-Sandkasten\" mit Wegwerf-Aufgaben.\nDu arbeitest im Team, mit Pair Programming, Code Reviews und Kolleg:innen, die dir bei Fragen weiterhelfen, ohne dich zu bevormunden.\nDu bekommst Einblick in Innovation und Konzeption – wenn dich das interessiert. Workshops, Kundengespräche, Lösungsideen skizzieren – wir nehmen dich gerne mit, wenn du Lust hast.\nDu arbeitest mit modernem Tooling und KI-gestützt – Claude Code, Forgejo, saubere CI/CD. Du lernst hier nicht das, was vor zehn Jahren Stand der Technik war.\n\nIn welchem Format?\n\nDas ist bei uns offen – Hauptsache, es passt zu dir und ist planbar:\n\nPflichtpraktikum im Rahmen deines Studiums (z.B. 6 Monate)\nPraxissemester\nBachelor- oder Masterarbeit mit oder ohne Praxisphase davor\nProjektarbeit im Rahmen deines Studiums\n\nWenn dein Format hier nicht steht, frag einfach – wir sind flexibel.\n\nDein Profil\n\nDu studierst Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Software Engineering, Data Science, Künstliche Intelligenz, Machine Learning, AI Engineering oder etwas, wo Programmieren eine Rolle spielt – aber dein Studienfach ist uns weniger wichtig als deine Lust auf das Thema.\nDu hast schon mal Code geschrieben, der funktioniert hat. Mehr brauchst du nicht mitzubringen.\nDu bist neugierig – auf neue Technologien, auf KI im Entwicklungsalltag, auf das, was Kunden eigentlich umtreibt.\nDu bringst dich ein. Eigene Ideen, kritische Fragen, Vorschläge – alles willkommen. Wir lernen dabei genauso wie du.\n\nDas passt zu dir, wenn …\n\n… du das Gefühl hast, im Studium fehlt dir die Praxis – und du Lust hast, an Software zu arbeiten, die jemand wirklich benutzt. … du keinen Bock auf Praktika hast, in denen du Tabellen sortierst oder Folien kopierst. … du gerade merkst, wie KI-Tools die Entwicklung verändern – und du das mitmachen willst, statt es nur in LinkedIn-Posts zu lesen.\n\nWarum wir?\n\nWir bei Innolizer begleiten mittelständische Unternehmen in Digitalisierungspartnerschaften – und wir glauben, dass die besten Teams gemischt sind. Erfahrene Entwickler:innen brauchen Leute, die unvoreingenommen Fragen stellen, frische Ideen mitbringen und gerade frisch aus Vorlesungen Themen aufgegriffen haben, die wir noch nicht kennen.\n\nGenau dafür suchen wir dich. Egal in welchem Format – wir freuen uns über jeden, der mehr über Softwareentwicklung lernen möchte und gleichzeitig Lust hat, uns mit deinem Blick weiterzubringen.\n\nWas du bei uns bekommst:\n\nFaire Bezahlung – weil wir gemeinsam Spaß haben wollen, nicht weil du es dir leisten kannst, kostenlos zu arbeiten.\nEchte Aufgaben, echtes Vertrauen. Du bekommst Verantwortung, die zu dir passt, und wirst nicht in der Ecke geparkt.\nMentoring & Lernen. Eine erfahrene Person aus dem Team begleitet dich, du arbeitest aber von Tag eins mit allen zusammen.\nModerne Arbeitsweise. Wir arbeiten KI-augmentiert, mit sauberem Git-Workflow und Tools, die dich auch nach dem Studium weiterbringen.\nFlexible Arbeitszeiten, die zu deinem Stundenplan passen, mit unserem Büro in Ulm als Anlaufstelle.\nEin Team, das gerne zusammen Mittagessen geht – und nicht nur in Slack-Threads existiert.\n\nKontakt\n\nWir bei Innolizer begleiten mittelständische Unternehmen in Digitalisierungspartnerschaften – und wir glauben, dass die besten Teams gemischt sind. Erfahrene Entwickler:innen brauchen Leute, die unvoreingenommen Fragen stellen, frische Ideen mitbringen und gerade frisch aus Vorlesungen Themen aufgegriffen haben, die wir noch nicht kennen.\n\nGenau dafür suchen wir dich. Egal in welchem Format – wir freuen uns über jeden, der mehr über Softwareentwicklung lernen möchte und gleichzeitig Lust hat, uns mit deinem Blick weiterzubringen.\n\nWas du bei uns bekommst:\n\nFaire Bezahlung – weil wir gemeinsam Spaß haben wollen, nicht weil du es dir leisten kannst, kostenlos zu arbeiten.\nEchte Aufgaben, echtes Vertrauen. Du bekommst Verantwortung, die zu dir passt, und wirst nicht in der Ecke geparkt.\nMentoring & Lernen. Eine erfahrene Person aus dem Team begleitet dich, du arbeitest aber von Tag eins mit allen zusammen.\nModerne Arbeitsweise. Wir arbeiten KI-augmentiert, mit sauberem Git-Workflow und Tools, die dich auch nach dem Studium weiterbringen.\nFlexible Arbeitszeiten, die zu deinem Stundenplan passen, mit unserem Büro in Ulm als Anlaufstelle.\nEin Team, das gerne zusammen Mittagessen geht – und nicht nur in Slack-Threads existiert.\n\nÜber uns\n\nWir sind Innolizer. Innovationspartner für den deutschen Mittelstand – mit Liebe zum Detail und einer ehrlichen Schwäche für Dinge, die wirklich funktionieren.\n\nWir begleiten Unternehmen von der ersten Idee bis zum produktiven Betrieb. Das heißt bei uns: Wir hören zu, bevor wir bauen. Wir bauen, statt nur PowerPoints zu malen. Und wir bleiben dabei, wenn die Software das erste Mal in einer echten Halle, Werkstatt oder Fachabteilung ankommt – weil genau dort entscheidet sich, ob Innovation einen Unterschied macht oder nur in einem Pitchdeck gut aussieht.\n\nWas uns zusammenhält, ist eine Mischung aus drei Dingen: ein kleines, neugieriges Team in Ulm, das lieber Dinge baut als nur darüber zu reden. Eine eigene Software, SafetyGO, die wir täglich weiterentwickeln und in der wir lernen, was Kunden wirklich brauchen. Und Digitalisierungspartnerschaften mit Mittelständlern, die uns nahe genug an reale Probleme heranlassen, dass uns nicht langweilig wird.\n\nWir glauben, dass die nächsten Jahre fundamental anders aussehen als die letzten – weil KI Werkzeuge in unsere Hände legt, die echte Hebelwirkung entfalten, wenn man sie ernsthaft einsetzt statt nur darüber zu posten. Genau diesen Wandel wollen wir mitgestalten: mit modernem Tooling, mit digitaler Souveränität als Grundhaltung, mit Open Source, wo es passt, und mit Kolleg:innen, die zusammen Mittagessen gehen statt nur in Slack-Threads zu existieren.\n\nWenn dich das anspricht: Wir freuen uns, dich kennenzulernen.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Innolizer GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=666b96bd06a39d33','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2394,NULL,'job','Senior Data Scientist (m/f/d)','Vollzeit','80538 München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Finmatics – Your AI Accountant With Fin, the AI accountant, Finmatics makes accounting easier, faster, and smarter. Instead of manual routine tasks, our software handles them reliably—specifically designed for accountants in Germany and Austria. Our mission: To give back time, eliminate document chaos, and make workflows efficient, digital, and future-proof. At Finmatics, you get more than just innovative technology: you get an environment that promotes flexibility and gives you the space to contribute your ideas. Together, we ensure that smart technology feels like true relief—making Finmatics the favorite digital product of our customers.\n\nAs a Senior Data Scientist (m/f/d), you will work on exciting projects that deliver first-class solutions powered by modern language models. You will have full command of the technical stack necessary for development and deployment, collaborate closely with stakeholders, and play a key role in shaping the company’s data science strategy.\n\nYour Key Responsibilities\nShape and implement the company’s data science strategy and drive innovation, with a primary focus on Generative AI and Agentic workflows\nIdentify opportunities to leverage data for business value and impact\nTake ownership of the full technical stack for development and deployment\nDesign, build, and maintain scalable machine learning models and efficient data pipelines\nEnsure robust data management and engineering practices\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to gather requirements and deliver insights\nCommunicate complex technical concepts clearly to both technical and non-technical stakeholders\nRequired Qualifications\nMaster’s or Ph.D. in Data Science, Computer Science, Statistics, or related field or equivalent knowledge and experience\nHands-On experience with Generative AI and Agentic Workflows\nProven experience in taking part in complex projects\nExpertise in modern language models and machine learning frameworks\nExperience with modern LLM-Supporting Frameworks and Tools\nProficiency in modern LLM Prompting techniques and approaches\nExperience with managing feedback training pipelines and fine-tuning\nStrong command of programming languages such as Python, R or any strongly-typed computer language\nGood knowledge of cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure) and deployment processes\n\nNice to Have\n\nFamiliarity with big data technologies like Spark or Hadoop or any other commercial Data Warehouse and/or Data Lake technologies\nStrong background in data architecture and database management\nExtensive experience with data management and engineering tools\nWhat We Offer\n\nBe part of shaping the future of financial workflows using the latest technical possibilities.\n\nPossibility to work remote and flexible working hours\nOpen and honest corporate culture\nEnjoy the agility of a leading AI pioneer (Visma Group) and access a top tech-ecosystem\nMotivated, dynamic team and flat hierarchies\nAdditional benefits include Eversports credits as well as company and team events\n\nJoin us and help shape the future of data science!','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Finmatics GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=199c341f7cdda14e','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2395,NULL,'job','Internship Multimodal AI for Video Understanding (m/f/x)','Vollzeit','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Welcome to ZEISS – a company that combines innovation and responsibility! Our corporate functions are diverse and make a decisive contribution to the strategic orientation and sustainable success of ZEISS.\n\nYour role\n\nAt ZEISS Corporate Research & Technology, we are offering student positions (internship and/or master’s thesis) starting from September 2026 in the area of multimodal AI and video understanding.\n\nYou will work on research problems at the intersection of vision, language, and structured data, with a focus on developing models that can understand complex real-world scenarios such as surgical workflows\n\nThe goal is to move beyond frame-level analysis towards holistic, temporally consistent representations that integrate multiple sources of information\n\nYour tasks Contribute to research on multimodal and video-based machine learning methods, develop and evaluate models for holistic video understanding (e.g. video-language models, temporal reasoning, multimodal fusion)\n\nWork with real-world datasets and problem settings from ZEISS applications, implement and analyze state-of-the-art approaches and extend them in a research-driven setting\n\nYour profile\n\nEnrolled in a Master’s or PhD program in Computer Science, Machine Learning, or a related field in Germany\n\nStrong fundamentals in machine learning and deep learning\n\nExperience with Python and common ML frameworks (e.g. PyTorch)\n\nInterest in research and ability to work independently on open-ended problems\n\nExperience with video analysis, multimodal learning, or foundation models is a plus\n\nWhat we offer\n\nOpportunity to work on cutting-edge research with real-world impact\n\nClose collaboration with research teams at ZEISS Corporate Research and Technology\n\nPossibility to transition from internship to master’s thesis based on performance\n\nAccess to challenging datasets and modern ML infrastructure\n\nSounds exciting? Then become part of #teamZEISS and help us shape the future! Please provide your complete application documents (CV, transcript of records).\n\nYour ZEISS Recruiting Team:\n\nInes Kloda','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'ZEISS Group','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=987ebedbbd96770a','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2396,NULL,'job','Projektmanager*in (m/w/d) Digitization & Data Analytics','Festanstellung','71364 Winnenden',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Das werden Deine WOW-Momente:\n\nDu hast Lust, die Digitalisierung in einem internationalen Umfeld nicht nur zu begleiten, sondern aktiv zu steuern? Als Teil unseres globalen Qualitäts-Teams gestaltest du die Prozesse von morgen:\n\nIn dieser Position steuerst Du spannende Projekte und treibst die Umsetzung unserer weltweiten IT-Roadmap von Seiten des Qualitätsmanagements auf internationalem Parkett entscheidend voran.\n\nAls agile*r (Teil-)Projektleiter*in begleitest Du unsere Qualitätsmanagement-Prozesse sicher durch den S/4HANA-Wandel und setzt neue Maßstäbe in der Systemlandschaft.\n\nVon der ersten Idee bis zum ‘Go-live’ koordinierst Du Software-Rollouts an unseren weltweiten Standorten. So stellst Du sicher, dass wir überall nach modernen und einheitlichen Standards arbeiten.\n\nAls Brückenbauer*in zwischen Business und IT agierst du als versierte Schnittstelle, um technologische Anforderungen in operative Exzellenz für unsere globalen Business Units zu übersetzen.\n\nTransformation gelingt nur gemeinsam. Du treibst die digitale Veränderung voran mit Fokus auf Stakeholder-Management, nimmst die Kolleg:innen weltweit mit und begeisterst sie für die Vorteile neuer Technologien.\n\nDu beobachtest proaktiv Trends in den Bereichen Data Engineering, KI und Machine Learning und evaluierst wie wir diese zukunftsweisenden Lösungen sinnvoll in unsere Produktion integrieren können.\n\nEs wäre WOW, wenn Du das hier mitbringst:\n\nEin erfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium zum Beispiel in Wirtschaftsinformatik, Data Science, Business Analytics, Wirtschaftsingenieurwesen oder einer vergleichbaren Fachrichtung.\n\nMehrjährige Berufserfahrung in der Umsetzung von Digitalisierungsprojekten.\n\nKenntnisse von agilen Methoden (Scrum, Kanban) und Führen von Projekten in komplexen Matrix-Strukturen.\n\nFundierte Kenntnisse in SAP-Anwendungen sowie ein sicherer Umgang mit JIRA oder ähnlichen Tools.\n\nVerhandlungssichere Sprachkenntnisse in Deutsch und Englisch (mind. C1) für die Arbeit in unserem globalen Netzwerk sowie für Management-Präsentationen.\n\nDie Fähigkeit, komplexe Zusammenhänge schnell zu durchdringen, strukturiert aufzubereiten und in klare, umsetzbare Strategien zu überführen.\n\nKommunikationsstärke und die Gewohnheit, Dinge proaktiv anzuregen und mit hoher Eigenverantwortung zum Ziel zu führen.\n\nEine internationale Reisebereitschaft (ca. 10 %) zur Unterstützung unserer weltweiten Standorte und zur Festigung der Stakeholder-Beziehungen vor Ort.\n\nDu erfüllst noch nicht alle Anforderungen? Kein Problem! Wir freuen uns trotzdem auf Deine Bewerbung.\n\nUnser Kärcher WOW-Paket:\n\nDen Alltag flexibel gestalten: Vertrauensarbeitzeit oder Gleitzeit und die Möglichkeit, tageweise im Home-Office zu arbeiten.\n\nKleine Traum-Erfüll-Hilfen: Jubiläumszuwendungen für alle, die lang in unserem Team bleiben, Zielprämien und weitere Sonderzahlungen.\n\nWir ermöglichen bezahlte Auszeiten: Ob verlängerte Elternzeit, Pflegeauszeit, Weiterbildungszeit oder Sabbatical - im Mittelpunkt stehen Du und Deine individuelle Lebenssituation.\n\nMobilität auf Dich zugeschnitten: Fahrtkostenzuschuss für den ÖPNV von 60%, attraktive Entgeltumwandlungsmodelle zum Leasing von Fahrrad oder PKW, Prämien für Radfahrer*innen.\n\nDie richtigen Leute, zur richtigen Zeit, am richtigen Ort, mit der richtigen Perspektive: Klingt kompliziert? Nicht für uns. Wir unterstützen Dich bei Deiner individuellen Entwicklung mit unserem Talentmanagement-Prozess und einem umfangreichen Weiterbildungsangebot.\n\nAlso: Wanna WOW with us?\n\nLade einfach Deinen Lebenslauf online hoch und hinterlasse Deine Kontaktinfos. Wir freuen uns darauf, Dich von Deiner persönlichen WOW-Seite kennenzulernen! Wir begrüßen die Bewerbung von Menschen mit Behinderung, deren Integration uns ein besonderes Anliegen ist.\n\nTogether towards a clean world.\n\nElène Denk | Recruiterin\nelene.denk@karcher.com','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Alfred Kärcher SE & Co. KG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ed82fb8614fedd50','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2397,NULL,'job','Principal Researcher (f/m/d) - Foundation and World Models on Structured Business Data','Festanstellung','85748 Garching bei München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We help the world run better\n\nAt SAP, we keep it simple: you bring your best to us, and we\'ll bring out the best in you. We\'re builders touching over 20 industries and 80% of global commerce, and we need your unique talents to help shape what\'s next. The work is challenging – but it matters. You\'ll find a place where you can be yourself, prioritize your wellbeing, and truly belong. What\'s in it for you? Constant learning, skill growth, great benefits, and a team that wants you to grow and succeed.\n\nWhat you`ll do:\n\nAt SAP’s Business AI Research, we are exploring the next frontier of AI methods on structured business data – graphs, tables, time series, and more. Foundation Models on Structured Data, like SAP-RPT-1, have ushered in the GenAI era for business relevant scenarios – scenarios that have so far been addressed with classical, often tree-based methods. Now, we are taking the next step. We collaborate with our existing applied research teams in creating novel benchmarks for business problems and the development of novel architectures and models, with the goal to publish benchmarks and models at scientific conferences and in the open-source community. We are working jointly with our academic partners to create ever better means of solving real business problems.\n\nThe Role\n\nDrive pioneering technical advances to the field of foundation models on structured data, as well as exploring world models for solving business problems.\n\nExpand the horizon of what is possible by bringing together rich semantic context with large scale business data\n\nDefine the research agenda for a small squad of research scientists and engineers\n\nEnable academic research by providing Business AI relevant problem statements, frameworks and data sets.\n\nKeep the pulse with novel research, providing insights into the latest research findings and making them comparable with internal work.\n\nTranslate applied research breakthroughs into research publications at relevant top-tier conferences and contribute to thought leadership in foundation and world models on structured data.\n\nCollaborate closely with various domain specialists and data owners to understand how the data can be used for world model training.\n\nContribute to thought leadership in an entirely new field of Foundation and World Models on Structured Data.\n\nWork closely with the team developing the relational pre-trained transformer (SAP-RPT-1) to exchange information and ensure that internal initiatives and project deliverables are aligned with community best practices.\n\nCollaborate with established academic partners and define new collaborations with top tier academic researchers.\n\nSupervise PhD students during summer internships or as part of academic collaborations.\n\nWhat you bring:\n\nPhD in Computer Science, Artificial Intelligence, physics, mathematics or other relevant disciplines\n\nCandidate must have an academic background in one of the following fields: Foundation Models / Machine Learning on large scale structured data, World Models. This should be supported by a substantial record of related publications, including recent works, at top tier conferences and a well-established network in these fields.\n\nA strong research vision for foundation models on structured data, and of how world models impact the development of such foundation models\n\nExtensive research experience with machine learning on structured data\n\nIdeally, experience in Causal AI and how it relates to foundation models on structured data\n\nProven experience and deep understanding of the opportunities and challenges associated with collaboration between industrial and academic research\n\nProficiency in Python and experience with ML frameworks such as PyTorch, TensorFlow, or similar. Optionally, hands-on experience with (knowledge) graph technologies\n\nIdeally, professional experience with the combination of knowledge graphs and large language models in ERP domain\n\nProven history of leading projects with a strategic mindset complemented by superior organizational abilities\n\nMeet your team:\n\nSAP\'s AI organization is dedicated to seamlessly infusing AI into all enterprise applications, enabling customers, partners, and developers to enhance business processes and generate remarkable business value. Join our international AI team where innovation thrives, opportunities for personal development abound, and exceptional colleagues collaborate globally.\n\n#SAPBusinessAICareers\n\nBring out your best\n\nSAP innovations help more than four hundred thousand customers worldwide work together more efficiently and use business insight more effectively. Originally known for leadership in enterprise resource planning (ERP) software, SAP has evolved to become a market leader in end-to-end business application software and related services for database, analytics, intelligent technologies, and experience management. As a cloud company with two hundred million users and more than one hundred thousand employees worldwide, we are purpose-driven and future-focused, with a highly collaborative team ethic and commitment to personal development. Whether connecting global industries, people, or platforms, we help ensure every challenge gets the solution it deserves. At SAP, you can bring out your best.\n\nWe win with inclusion\n\nSAP’s culture of inclusion, focus on health and well-being, and flexible working models help ensure that everyone – regardless of background – feels included and can run at their best. At SAP, we believe we are made stronger by the unique capabilities and qualities that each person brings to our company, and we invest in our employees to inspire confidence and help everyone realize their full potential. We ultimately believe in unleashing all talent and creating a better world.\n\nSAP is committed to the values of Equal Employment Opportunity and provides accessibility accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are interested in applying for employment with SAP and are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to Recruiting Operations Team: Careers@sap.com.\n\nFor SAP employees: Only permanent roles are eligible for the SAP Employee Referral Program, according to the eligibility rules set in the SAP Referral Policy. Specific conditions may apply for roles in Vocational Training.\n\nAI Usage in the Recruitment Process\n\nFor information on the responsible use of AI in our recruitment process, please refer to our Guidelines for Ethical Usage of AI in the Recruiting Process.\n\nPlease note that any violation of these guidelines may result in disqualification from the hiring process.\n\nRequisition ID: 448468 | Work Area: Software-Research | Expected Travel: 0 - 10% | Career Status: Berufserfahren | Employment Type: Vollzeit, unbefristet | #LI-Hybrid','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'SAP','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6d25d859c43f94ea','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2398,NULL,'job','Werkstudentin / Werkstudent KI / Robotik (w/m/d)','Teilzeit','Wolfsburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Arbeitsumfeld\n\nIm ONE.Software Development Center (ONE.SDC) am Standort Dresden arbeitet der Volkswagen Konzern an softwaregetriebenen Zukunftslösungen für Produktion und Technologie. Als Werkstudentin / Werkstudent im Bereich Softwareentwicklung mit Fokus auf Robotik und Künstliche Intelligenz unterstützen Sie agile Entwicklungsteams bei der Konzeption, Entwicklung und Erprobung moderner Softwarelösungen für robotische Systeme. Der Schwerpunkt Ihrer Tätigkeit liegt auf der Softwareplattform von Robotern, deren Programmierung sowie der Integration intelligenter Funktionen. Dabei erhalten Sie Einblicke in industrielle Anwendungsfälle und arbeiten eng mit erfahrenen Softwareentwicklerinnen und Softwareentwicklern, KI-Expertinnen und KI-Experten und Robotik-Spezialistinnen und Robotik-Spezialisten zusammen. Wir freuen uns auf Ihre Bewerbung.\n\nMögliche Aufgaben dieser Rolle\nMitarbeiten an der Entwicklung und Weiterentwicklung von Softwareplattformen für robotische Systeme\nImplementieren und Programmieren von Robotersoftware, z. B. für Steuerung, Schnittstellen oder intelligente Funktionen\nUnterstützen bei der Integration von KI- und Machine-Learning-Ansätzen in robotische Anwendungen\nEntwickeln und Erproben von Prototypen sowie Evaluation neuer Technologien im Bereich Robotik und KI\nAnbinden und Integrieren von Softwaremodulen in bestehende Systemlandschaften\nMitwirken bei Tests, Verifikation und Dokumentation von Softwarekomponenten\nUnterstützen bei der Inbetriebnahme sowie beim Zusammenspiel von Software und Roboter-Hardware\n\nAnforderungen an die Qualifikation\nStudierende (Bachelor mindestens 90 CreditPoints) der Fachrichtungen Informatik, Robotik, Mechatronik, Elektrotechnik oder vergleichbarer Studienrichtungen (z.B. Maschinenbau mit software- oder simulationsnaher Vertiefung)\nGute bis sehr gute Studienleistungen\nAusgeprägtes Interesse an Softwareentwicklung, Robotik und Künstlicher Intelligenz\nProgrammierkenntnisse in Python oder C++, sowie grundlegende Erfahrung im Umgang mit Git\nErste Kenntnisse oder Interesse an KI / Machine Learning, Softwarearchitekturen, Frameworks oder Middleware (z. B. ROS), Docker und grundlegendes Verständnis von Cloud-Architekturen, Simulationsumgebungen (z. B. NVIDIA Omniverse), Numerische Simulationen sind von Vorteil\nFolgende Dokumente sind mit der Bewerbung einzureichen\nLebenslauf\nAktuelle Immatrikulationsbescheinigung\nAktueller Notenspiegel\nArbeitserlaubnis für Nicht-EU Bürgerinnen / Bürger\nKeywords\n\nSoftwarearchitektur, Industrielle Robotik, Praxisnahe Softwareentwicklung\n\nKontakt für diese Ausschreibung: Hartmut Fromm\n\nJob ID: 25226\nUnternehmen: Volkswagen AG\nStandort:\n\nWolfsburg, DE, 38436\n\nTätigkeitsfeld: IT Softwareentwicklung\nKarrierelevel: Studierende\nArbeitsmodell: Teilzeit\nVertragsart: Befristet\nMobiles Arbeiten: Bis zu 40%\nVeröffentlichungsdatum: 28.04.2026\nDarum Volkswagen\n\nWir wollen die Mobilität von morgen nachhaltig revolutionieren und gestalten. Hierfür suchen wir Talente, die bereit sind, mit uns völlig neue Wege zu gehen und dabei keine Angst haben, auch mal Fehler zu machen. Wir suchen Persönlichkeiten, die Außergewöhnliches auf die Beine stellen wollen. Und Talente, die an die Innovationskraft großer Ideen glauben. Sind Sie dabei?\n\nFragen?\n\nAlles Wichtige zur Bewerbung\nFAQ - Häufig gestellte Fragen\nMail: einstieg@volkswagen.de ✉️\nHotline: +49 5361 9 36363\n\nDie Kosten für Anrufe richten sich nach dem jeweiligen Tarif Ihres Anbieters. Bei Anrufen aus dem Ausland können Roaming-Gebühren anfallen.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Volkswagen','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8da7e873ba526097','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2399,NULL,'job','Lead Software Engineer – DevOps / Python / AWS (all genders)','Vollzeit','Frankfurt am Main',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'JOB DESCRIPTION\n\nWe have an opportunity to impact your career and provide an adventure where you can push the limits of what\'s possible.\n\nAs a Lead Software Engineer – DevOps / Python / AWS at JPMorgan Chase within the Commercial & Investment Bank, you will serve as a seasoned member of an agile team to design and deliver trusted, market-leading technology products in a secure, stable, and scalable manner. You will be responsible for implementing critical technology solutions across multiple technical areas within various business functions in support of the firm’s business objectives. Our main goal is to automate processes within the European Legal Entity JPMSE by leveraging AWS Cloud and AI solutions. You will be part of a highly qualified team that will enhance your knowledge while implementing cutting-edge solutions.\n\nJob Responsibilities:\n\nDevelop secure and high-quality production code, and review code written by others.\nDesign and implement scalable cloud-native software solutions using modern technology stacks to deliver highly available, performant, and resilient products.\nHave a solid understanding of agile methodologies such as CI/CD, Application Resiliency, and Security, Clean Coding, Object-Oriented Programming, Jira.\nCreate RESTful APIs that are scalable, secure, and efficient.\nDevelop innovative AI/ML solutions and agentic systems utilizing public cloud architecture and modern standards, specifically with AWS\nIdentify opportunities to eliminate or automate remediation of recurring issues to improve overall operational stability of software applications and systems\nLeverage AWS services for scalable deployments\nCreate and maintain Docker images\nExecute DevOps responsibilities such as container orchestration, deployments, and infrastructure management using Kubernetes\n\nRequired Qualifications, Capabilities, and Skills:\n\nFormal training or certification in software engineering concepts and 7+ years of applied experience.\nHands-on practical experience delivering system design, application development, testing, and operational stability.\nAdvanced proficiency in one or more programming languages, including Python (FastAPI)\nStrong AWS skillset: EC2, ECS, EKS, Lambda, SQS, SNS, RDS Aurora MySQL & Postgres, DynamoDB) with strong understanding of cloud architecture and best practices\nStrong Experienced with CI/CD pipelines, Docker, and Kubernetes.\nHands-on Experience in Infrastructure as Code (IAC) - Terraform.\nHands-on experience with relational databases (SQL).\n\nDemonstrated knowledge of software applications and technical processes within a technical discipline (e.g., cloud, artificial intelligence, machine learning, mobile, etc.).\n\nPreferred qualifications, capabilities, and skills\n\nGood to have LLM Experience: OpenAI, AWS Bedrock and Agentic AI.\nProficient in modern technologies like Spark\nExperience with React or Angular.\nABOUT US\n\nJ.P. Morgan is a global leader in financial services, providing strategic advice and products to the world’s most prominent corporations, governments, wealthy individuals and institutional investors. Our first-class business in a first-class way approach to serving clients drives everything we do. We strive to build trusted, long-term partnerships to help our clients achieve their business objectives.\n\nWe recognize that our people are our strength and the diverse talents they bring to our global workforce are directly linked to our success. We are an equal opportunity employer and place a high value on diversity and inclusion at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of any protected attribute, including race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, marital or veteran status, pregnancy or disability, or any other basis protected under applicable law. We also make reasonable accommodations for applicants’ and employees’ religious practices and beliefs, as well as mental health or physical disability needs. Visit our FAQs for more information about requesting an accommodation.\n\nABOUT THE TEAM\n\nJ.P. Morgan’s Commercial & Investment Bank is a global leader across banking, markets, securities services and payments. Corporations, governments and institutions throughout the world entrust us with their business in more than 100 countries. The Commercial & Investment Bank provides strategic advice, raises capital, manages risk and extends liquidity in markets around the world.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'JPMorganChase','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f90e934b8577aa51','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2400,NULL,'job','MTRA m/w/d im Softwaretest und Systemtest','Teilzeit','91052 Erlangen',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'MTRA (m/w/d) im Softwaretest und Systemtest (Teilzeit)\n\n*Deine Chance – Medizintechnik aktiv mitgestalten!*\n\nWir entwickeln in enger Zusammenarbeit mit unseren Kunden weltweit führende Lösungen zur Bildgebung und Diagnose. Als Key Supplier treiben wir die Digitalisierung durch moderne Produkt-, Web- und Cloud-Lösungen voran – mit Fokus auf AI, Machine Learning, Agilität und einem innovativen Tech-Stack. Werde Teil dieses zukunftsweisenden Projekts. Gestalte die Medizintechnik von morgen aktiv mit, in Teilzeit (25-30 Stunden pro Woche)!\n\n*Deine Aufgaben – Test mit Verantwortung und Weitblick*\n\n* Produktlinien im Bereich MRT mitentwickeln – du wirkst aktiv an der Entwicklung medizintechnischer Großsysteme in der Kernspintomographie mit.\n* Funktionale Tests planen und durchführen – du erstellst und führst Black-Box-Tests durch und sorgst so für zuverlässige Software.\n* Testspezifikationen abstimmen und dokumentieren – du arbeitest eng mit Stakeholdern wie Softwareentwicklern zusammen und übernimmst die Vorabklärung.\n* Key-Transfer übernehmen – du transferierst Leistungsmerkmale gezielt in den Softwaretest.\n* Manuelle und automatisierte Tests durchführen – du testest effektiv und effizient, sowohl händisch als auch automatisiert.\n* Testdaten erstellen und prüfen – du bereitest Daten für automatisierte Tests vor und überprüfst sie auf Qualität und Konsistenz.\n* Fehler dokumentieren und analysieren – du erfasst, analysierst und verfolgst Fehler systematisch, um kontinuierlich Verbesserungen zu erzielen.\n\n*Das bringst du mit – Dein Profil für den Testbereich*\n\n* Abgeschlossene Ausbildung als MTRA – alternativ verfügst du über eine vergleichbare Qualifikation mit Erfahrung im radiologisch-technischen Umfeld.\n* Erfahrung mit bildgebender Diagnostik und regulatorischem Umfeld – du bringst Praxiswissen aus der Radiologie mit und kennst dich mit den Anforderungen des Medizinproduktegesetzes (MPG) aus – oder möchtest dich gezielt in diesen Bereich einarbeiten.\n* Vertraut mit agilen Methoden – SCRUM und agile Arbeitsweisen sind dir ein Begriff oder du bringst Offenheit für moderne Entwicklungsprozesse mit.\n* Technisches Verständnis und Tool-Erfahrung – du hast bereits mit Tools wie MS Team Foundation Server, HP Quality Center, syngo.via oder RequirementPro gearbeitet – oder möchtest dich in diese einarbeiten.\n* Sorgfältige und strukturierte Arbeitsweise – du dokumentierst präzise und zuverlässig und nutzt SAP-Tools zur Pflege technischer Dokumentation.\n* Teamgeist und Kommunikationsfreude – du arbeitest gerne in kleinen, agilen Teams (ca. 7 Personen) und bringst dich aktiv ein.\n\n*Be you with us! – Deine Vorteile bei sepp.med*\n\n* Medizintechnik mit Zukunft – arbeite an innovativen Projekten, die die Diagnostik von morgen prägen.\n* Agile Teams und moderne Prozesse – erlebe Zusammenarbeit auf Augenhöhe, mit klarer Kommunikation und viel Eigenverantwortung.\n* Individuelle Entwicklung – nutze Weiterbildungen, Trainings und unsere sepp.med Akademie, um dein Potenzial voll zu entfalten.\n* Attraktive Rahmenbedingungen – flexible Arbeitszeiten, Homeoffice, moderne Arbeitsplätze und leistungsgerechte Vergütung inklusive.\n* Wertschätzung & Teamgeist – profitiere von einem unterstützenden Umfeld, echter Zusammenarbeit und einer offenen Unternehmenskultur.\n\nBereit, mit uns die Medizintechnik von morgen zu gestalten?\n\nDann freuen wir uns auf deine Bewerbung!\n\nArt der Stelle: Teilzeit\n\nLeistungen:\n* Betriebliche Altersvorsorge\n* Betriebliche Weiterbildung\n* Betriebsarzt/Betriebsärztin\n* Empfehlungsprogramm\n* Flexible Arbeitszeiten\n* Gleitzeit\n* Homeoffice-Möglichkeit\n* Kostenlose Getränke\n* Kostenloser Parkplatz\n* Mentoring-Programm für Mitarbeiter\n* Mitarbeiter-Rabatt\n* Zusätzliche Urlaubstage\n\n\n\nBewerbungsfrage(n):\n* Sind Sie reisebereit oder umzugsbereit?\n* Was ist Ihre Gehaltsvorstellung?\n* Was ist Ihr frühestmögliches Eintrittsdatum?\n\nSprache:\n* Deutsch (Erforderlich)\n\nArbeitsort: Zum Teil im Homeoffice in 91052 Erlangen','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'sepp.med GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=4e8ee2d2da1e6699','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2401,NULL,'job','Lead Research Engineer (f/m/d): Foundation and World Models on Structured Data','Vollzeit','85748 Garching bei München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We help the world run better\n\nAt SAP, we keep it simple: you bring your best to us, and we\'ll bring out the best in you. We\'re builders touching over 20 industries and 80% of global commerce, and we need your unique talents to help shape what\'s next. The work is challenging – but it matters. You\'ll find a place where you can be yourself, prioritize your wellbeing, and truly belong. What\'s in it for you? Constant learning, skill growth, great benefits, and a team that wants you to grow and succeed.\n\nWhat you`ll do:\n\nAt SAP’s Business AI Research, we are exploring the next frontier of AI methods on structured business data – graphs, tables, time series, and more. Foundation Models on Structured Data, like SAP-RPT-1, have ushered in the GenAI era for business relevant scenarios – scenarios that have so far been addressed with classical, often tree-based methods. Now, we are taking the next step. We collaborate with our existing applied research teams in creating novel benchmarks for business problems and the development of novel architectures and models, with the goal to publish benchmarks and models at scientific conferences and in the open-source community. We are working jointly with our academic partners to create ever better means of solving real business problems.\n\nThe Role:\n\nContribute to pioneering technical advances to the field of foundation models on structured data, as well as exploring world models for solving business problems.\n\nDefine the data, training, and experimentation environment to enable scalable access to data and compute.\n\nDefine and lead the creation of new training and benchmark datasets, bringing together rich semantic context with large scale business data.\n\nCollaborate on definition of evaluation frameworks and benchmark suites, driving internal and external exploration of novel tasks.\n\nMake critical design decisions regarding the selection and implementation of underlying technologies.\n\nExecute scientific experiments on internal as well as public data.\n\nDefine and drive open source model and software contributions based on research deliverables.\n\nWhat you bring:\n\nPhD or Master’s degree in computer science, artificial intelligence, physics, mathematics or other relevant disciplines.\n\n5+ years of professional experience with a deep background in Machine Learning on Structured Data, and its application in a business context.\n\nDemonstrated ownership of scalable machine learning and data environment, with deep understanding of success criteria and trade offs.\n\nKnowledge of latest research and development trends in Foundation Models on Structured Data.\n\nExperience in Data Engineering with a hands-on approach to solving data challenges.\n\nFluent in Python and the ability to convert your ideas into productive code.\n\nDeveloper experience with any SAP Application and its underlying data models is a plus.\n\nStrong communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively in cross-cultural teams.\n\nMeet your team:\n\nSAP\'s AI organization is dedicated to seamlessly infusing AI into all enterprise applications, enabling customers, partners, and developers to enhance business processes and generate remarkable business value. Join our international AI team where innovation thrives, opportunities for personal development abound, and exceptional colleagues collaborate globally.\n\n#SAPBusinessAICareers\n\nBring out your best\n\nSAP innovations help more than four hundred thousand customers worldwide work together more efficiently and use business insight more effectively. Originally known for leadership in enterprise resource planning (ERP) software, SAP has evolved to become a market leader in end-to-end business application software and related services for database, analytics, intelligent technologies, and experience management. As a cloud company with two hundred million users and more than one hundred thousand employees worldwide, we are purpose-driven and future-focused, with a highly collaborative team ethic and commitment to personal development. Whether connecting global industries, people, or platforms, we help ensure every challenge gets the solution it deserves. At SAP, you can bring out your best.\n\nWe win with inclusion\n\nSAP’s culture of inclusion, focus on health and well-being, and flexible working models help ensure that everyone – regardless of background – feels included and can run at their best. At SAP, we believe we are made stronger by the unique capabilities and qualities that each person brings to our company, and we invest in our employees to inspire confidence and help everyone realize their full potential. We ultimately believe in unleashing all talent and creating a better world.\n\nSAP is committed to the values of Equal Employment Opportunity and provides accessibility accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are interested in applying for employment with SAP and are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to Recruiting Operations Team: Careers@sap.com.\n\nFor SAP employees: Only permanent roles are eligible for the SAP Employee Referral Program, according to the eligibility rules set in the SAP Referral Policy. Specific conditions may apply for roles in Vocational Training.\n\nAI Usage in the Recruitment Process\n\nFor information on the responsible use of AI in our recruitment process, please refer to our Guidelines for Ethical Usage of AI in the Recruiting Process.\n\nPlease note that any violation of these guidelines may result in disqualification from the hiring process.\n\nRequisition ID: 448365 | Work Area: Software-Design and Development | Expected Travel: 0 - 10% | Career Status: Professional | Employment Type: Regular Full Time #LI-Hybrid','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'SAP','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=18c510971d34e87f','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2402,NULL,'job','Abschlussarbeit: Entwicklung eines KI-gestützten Tools zur effizienten Auswahl von Motorlagerungen','','86153 Augsburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job-ID: 13588\nTätigkeitsbeginn: ab sofort\nStandort:\n\nAugsburg, DE, 86153\n\nLand: DE\nDas sollten Sie über uns wissen\n\nEverllence ebnet den Weg in eine klimaneutrale Weltwirtschaft. Ob Industrieproduktion, Energie- oder maritime Wirtschaft: Wir denken ganzheitlich und packen schon heute die Herausforderungen von morgen an – für eine nachhaltige Wertschöpfung unserer Kunden. In unserem Technologieportfolio steckt die Erfahrung aus über 250 Jahren Ingenieurstradition. Everllence hat seinen Hauptsitz in Deutschland und beschäftigt rund 15.000 Mitarbeiter an mehr als 120 Standorten weltweit. Unsere Kunden profitieren außerdem vom globalen Service-Center-Netzwerk unserer After-Sales Marke, Everllence PrimeServ.\n\nFolgende Aufgaben können wir Ihnen anbieten\n\nWeiterentwicklung und Optimierung einer Datenbank für Motorlagerungen\nStrukturierte Aufbereitung von Datensätzen und Entwurf von Ansätzen\nBewertung verschiedener Ansätze\nEntwicklung eines Algorithmus/Models zur Klassifizierung und Auswahl von Motorlagerungen (Machine Learning)\nImplementierung des Tools in Python\nDokumentation der Entwicklung in Form eines Praxisberichts/Abschlussarbeit\nMit diesen Qualifikationen helfen Sie uns weiter\n\nStudierender in Maschinenbau, Physik, Informatik oder vergleichbar\nProgrammieraffinität (Matlab/Python und ggf. VBA)\nKenntnisse in Technischer Mechanik (Statik, Dynamik) und Interesse an numerischer Simulation\nInteresse an Methoden des maschinellen Lernens (ggf. Vorkenntnisse)\nUnsere Benefits für Sie\n\nKantine, Essenszulage, Barrierefreiheit, betriebliches Gesundheitsmanagement, Betriebsarzt, Fitnessraum, Parkplatz, gute Verkehrsanbindung, Mitarbeiterrabatte, Studentennetzwerk, Frauennetzwerk\n\nGut zu wissen\n\nBei Fragen können Sie sich gerne per E-Mail an Ihren Recruiter, Nicola Hasl, wenden. E-Mail: nicola.hasl@everllence.com.\n\n#LI-NH1 #LI-Hybrid #AUG\n\nHier sind Sie beruflich zuhause\n\nAm Hauptsitz von Everllence in Augsburg wurde einst der Dieselmotor erfunden, mit dem Rudolf Diesel der Dampfmaschine den Kampf ansagte. Heute ist die Bewältigung der Herausforderungen in den Bereichen Marine, Energie und Industrie zu unserer Hauptaufgabe geworden – nicht nur für den Erfolg unserer Kunden, sondern auch für den Erhalt unserer Umwelt. Jeden Tag arbeiten rund 5.000 Mitarbeitende an unserem Standort in der schönen Renaissancestadt Augsburg an einer besseren Zukunft: Von kleinen Effizienzsteigerungen bei einzelnen Komponenten, wie zum Beispiel Dual-Fuel- Motoren, Abgasnachbehandlungssystemen oder Softwarelösungen bis hin zu großen Innovationen auf Systemebene. Auch Sie können uns dabei unterstützen. Bei uns sind Sie richtig, wenn Sie etwas bewegen möchten.\n\nDas ist uns wichtig\n\nIntegrität und Compliance sind wesentliche Elemente unserer Unternehmenskultur. Zudem fördern wir Vielfalt und Chancengleichheit und freuen uns über vielfältige Online-Bewerbungen. Klicken Sie einfach auf „Jetzt bewerben“ und starten mit uns durch. Bewerbungen von Menschen mit Behinderung sind ausdrücklich erwünscht.\n\nHinweis: Soweit Begriffe im generischen Maskulin wie z.B. Ingenieur, Kaufmann, Techniker verwendet werden, sind alle Geschlechter (m/w/d) gleichermaßen gemeint.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Everllence SE','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=43b209ce6f6390ec','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2403,NULL,'job','Full Stack Developer mit Pipeline-Erfahrung m/w/d','Festanstellung','91301 Forchheim',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'*Deine Chance - Medizintechnik mit modernem Full-Stack-Engineering gestalten *\n\nWir entwickeln in enger Zusammenarbeit mit unseren Kunden weltweit führende Lösungen zur Bildgebung und Diagnose. Als Key Supplier treiben wir die Digitalisierung durch moderne Produkt-, Web- und Cloud-Lösungen voran. Dabei setzen wir auf AI, Machine Learning, Agilität und ein innovatives Tech-Stack.\n\nDu willst Software entwickeln, die wirklich zählt? Dann werde Teil dieses wegweisenden Projekts und gestalte die Medizintechnik der Zukunft aktiv mit!\n\n*Deine Aufgaben - Full Stack mit Innovationsgeist und Pipeline-Power *\n\n* *Komplexe Lösungen konzipieren und entwickeln* – du arbeitest agil an modernen Services mit neuesten Technologien und AI-Unterstützung und bringst deine Ideen von der Architektur bis zur Umsetzung ein.\n* *Web-Applikationen designen und realisieren* – du nutzt JavaScript/TypeScript, Angular, Svelte, HTML5, CSS3 und REST, um performante und nutzerzentrierte Anwendungen zu entwickeln.\n* *Anforderungen gemeinsam definieren* – zusammen mit dem Product Owner spezifizierst du Software zielgerichtet und übersetzt fachliche Anforderungen in technische Konzepte.\n* *Produktqualität kontinuierlich steigern* – durch automatisierte Tests und Code-Reviews sicherst du nachhaltige Qualität in einem regulierten Umfeld.\n* *Im agilen Team mitwirken* – du bringst dich aktiv ein, übernimmst Verantwortung und gestaltest innovative Softwarelösungen im engen Austausch mit Entwicklung, QA und DevOps.\n* *Produktivität durch Automatisierung erhöhen* – mit Azure DevOps Pipelines und AI-Unterstützung wie GitHub Copilot entwickelst du effiziente Build-, Test- und Deployment-Prozesse weiter.\n\n*Das bringst du mit - Dein Erfolgsprofil *\n\n* *Ausbildung oder Studium im IT-Bereich* – du hast die Ausbildung zum Fachinformatiker oder ein (Fach-)Hochschulstudium in Informatik oder einem verwandten Studiengang abgeschlossen.\n* *Praxiserfahrung mit modernen Technologien* – du kennst dich mit Angular, TypeScript, JavaScript sowie idealerweise C# und .NET bestens aus.\n* *Breites Entwicklungsverständnis* – du bringst Erfahrung in App- und Backend-Entwicklung mit und denkst ganzheitlich über Systemgrenzen hinweg.\n* *Nice to have: Erfahrung in der Cross-Plattform-Entwicklung* – idealerweise hast du bereits mit Cordova oder Xamarin gearbeitet und entwickelst Anwendungen für iOS und Android\n* *Agiles Mindset und Teamplayer-Qualitäten* – du arbeitest gern in agilen Teams, bringst deine Ideen proaktiv ein und übernimmst Ownership für deine Themen.\n* *Strukturierte und lösungsorientierte Arbeitsweise* – du gehst Aufgaben souverän, selbstorganisiert und mit Qualitätsanspruch an.\n* *Kommunikationsstärke in zwei Sprachen* – sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse runden dein Profil ab.\n\n*Deine Benefits bei sepp.med *\n\nFamilienunternehmen\n\nAls Familienunternehmen in der zweiten Generation stehen für uns kooperatives Denken und Handeln an erster Stelle!\n\nFirmen- und Teamevents\n\nDas Miteinander ist uns sehr wichtig. sepp.med stärkt das Wir-Gefühl durch gemeinsame Feste und Events: Weihnachtsfeier, Teamevents, Familiennachmittag, Expertenkonferenz.\n\nFlexibles Arbeiten\n\nUnser Gleitzeitmodell bietet dir die Möglichkeit flexibler Arbeitszeiten. Außerdem ist Homeoffice bis zu 100 % möglich, wenn es mit deinen Aufgaben – und vor allem mit unseren Kunden – vereinbar ist.\n\nVermögenswirksame Leistungen\n\nsepp.med zahlt einen attraktiven Zuschuss zu den vermögenswirksamen Leistungen.\n\nBetriebsrente\n\nWir denken an die Zukunft – auch an deine. Deshalb unterstützen wir deine Vorsorge mit einer betrieblichen Zusatzleistung.\n\nsepp.med Mitarbeiterrabatte\n\nAls Teil des sepp.med Teams bekommst du exklusive Rabatte bei vielen bekannten Marken und Unternehmen – einfach so, weil du dabei bist.\n\n*Klingt nach deinem nächsten Schritt? Dann freuen wir uns darauf, dich kennenzulernen!*\n\nWir freuen uns sehr über deine Bewerbung. Bei Fragen erreichst du unsere Ansprechpartner Dorthea Baigger & Matthias Alef per Telefon unter der 09195-931-249/-186.\n\nsepp.med gmbh - Gewerbering 9 - 91341 Röttenbach\n\nArt der Stelle: Vollzeit, Festanstellung\n\nLeistungen:\n* Betriebliche Altersvorsorge\n* Betriebliche Weiterbildung\n* Betriebsarzt/Betriebsärztin\n* Empfehlungsprogramm\n* Firmenevents\n* Firmenhandy\n* Flexible Arbeitszeiten\n* Gleitzeit\n* Homeoffice-Möglichkeit\n* Kostenlose Getränke\n* Kostenloser Parkplatz\n* Mentoring-Programm für Mitarbeiter\n* Mitarbeiter-Rabatt\n* Zusätzliche Urlaubstage\n\n\n\nBewerbungsfrage(n):\n* Welche Gehaltsvorstellung haben Sie?\n* Was ist Ihr frühestmögliche Eintrittstermin?\n* Sind Sie bereit auch vor Ort zu arbeiten?\n\nSprache:\n* Deutsch (Erforderlich)\n\nArbeitsort: Zum Teil im Homeoffice in 91301 Forchheim','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'sepp.med GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5d85d060b6a1d6b5','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2404,NULL,'job','Senior Scientist Data Science (f/m/d)','Vollzeit','51105 Köln',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Bring more to life.\n\nAre you ready to accelerate your potential and make a real difference within life sciences, diagnostics and biotechnology?\n\nAt Cytiva, one of Danaher’s 15+ operating companies, our work saves lives—and we’re all united by a shared commitment to innovate for tangible impact.\n\nYou’ll thrive in a culture of belonging where you and your unique viewpoint matter. And by harnessing Danaher’s system of continuous improvement, you help turn ideas into impact – innovating at the speed of life.\n\nWorking at Cytiva means being at the forefront of providing new solutions to transform human health. Our incredible customers undertake life-saving activities ranging from fundamental biological research to developing innovative vaccines, new medicines, and cell and gene therapies.\n\nAt Cytiva you will be able to continuously improve yourself and us – working on challenges that truly matter with people that care for each other, our customers, and their patients. Take your next step to an altogether life-changing career.\n\nLearn about the Danaher Business System which makes everything possible.\n\nAs Senior Scientist, Data Science, this role provides technical leadership to build and strategically advance data‑driven and AI‑based approaches for cell line development, upstream process development, and genetic combination analysis. The position focuses on developing and operationalizing predictive models and scalable MLOps workflows using Cytiva’s Scientific Data Platform, while working in close collaboration with a global network of Data Scientists across Cytiva and Danaher. The role also leads cross‑functional projects in partnership with R&D, IT, Quality, and Regulatory teams to enable compliant, data‑driven decision making across the cell line development workflow.\n\nWhat you will do\n\nDevelop and apply advanced ML and statistical models (e.g. regression, tree‑based, Bayesian, DoE) to support mammalian cell line and upstream process R&D.\n\nTake ownership of building and operating end‑to‑end ML workflows and a scalable data science and MLOps infrastructure, spanning data ingestion, feature engineering, model deployment, and monitoring.\n\nLeverage Cytiva’s Scientific Data Platform (Signals, TetraScience, scientific data lake) and cloud environments (AWS/Azure) for compliant analytics.\n\nDesign scalable data engineering pipelines connecting lab instruments, ELN, and analytics layers.\n\nLead and manage cross‑functional projects across R&D, IT, Quality, and Regulatory, including planning, prioritization, and stakeholder alignment.\n\nWho you are\n\nPhD or Master’s degree in Bioinformatics, Computational Biology, Data Science, Biotechnology, or a related field with several years of hands‑on experience applying machine learning and data analytics in life sciences or biopharma.\n\nStrong programming skills in Python, experience with SQL, and modern ML framework, experience in building data pipelines (Linux, Docker, CI/CD).\n\nAbility to work across disciplines and build strong working relationships with IT, scientists, and engineers.\n\nDemonstrated ability to build new teams and capabilities, including shaping ways of working and technical standards.\n\nProficient English language oral and written skills, German would be a plus.\n\nIt would be a plus if you also have experience in\n\nMammalian cell line development in an R&D or early development setting.\n\nViral vectors (AAV preferred) or advanced bioprocess development.\n\nAanalyzing NGS datasets (short and long-read sequencing).\n\nJoin our winning team today. Together, we’ll accelerate the real-life impact of tomorrow’s science and technology. We partner with customers across the globe to help them solve their most complex challenges, architecting solutions that bring the power of science to life.\n\nFor more information, visit www.danaher.com.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Cytiva','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ee6b63046bb1a981','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2405,NULL,'job','VIP Experience Specialist','Vollzeit','10783 Berlin',NULL,'',8500095000.00,'85.000 € – 95.000 € pro Jahr','This isn’t your regular job. Almedia is a place where those who want to push harder can accelerate their careers faster than anywhere else. We’re aiming to become Germany’s second bootstrapped unicorn. Almedia is already Europe’s #3 fastest-growing company in 2025 (FT1000).\n\nWe are building the future of marketing by rewarding our community of over 70 million users for engaging with our advertisers’ products. We are offering a new way to acquire users for the biggest companies in the world.\n\nAt Almedia, you’ll:\n\nOwn way more, way earlier — you’ll be trusted with responsibility fast.\n\nPush harder, get further — this isn’t a 9–5. We highly reward intensity.\n\nJoin a rare environment — you will work with ambitious high-speed, high-ownership people.\n\nFully present — we’re 5 days a week in the office to build the energising momentum we need.\n\nWe’re building the most rewarding engagement engine on the planet at Almedia. We need a VIP Experience Manager to architect the systems and product logic that drive hyper-retention for our top-tier users on Freecash. This isn\'t a support role—it’s a product-centric mission to build the engine that keeps our VIPs locked in.\n\nWhat You\'ll Do\n\nBuild the automated loyalty frameworks and backend systems that power elite user experiences.\n\nScale proactive engagement loops, shifting the department from reactive support to a systematic retention machine.\n\nDesign VIP-specific product features by dictating strategy across our Fraud, Support, and Product teams.\n\nWhat You Need\n\n3+ years of experience building and scaling VIP programs in a high-growth tech environment.\n\nTechnical Proficiency: Deep expertise in CRM automation stacks and data-driven retention modeling.\n\nBonus\n\nPrevious experience in AdTech or high-volume gaming platforms.\n\nWhat You’ll Bring\n\nA high-ownership architect who thrives on intensity and speed.\n\nA solution-driven builder who hates red tape and \"good enough.\"\n\nWired for a non-9-to-5 startup culture where results are the only currency.\n\nWhy Almedia?\n\nOwn Our Growth: We offer all Berlin-based employees equity in Almedia to truly be a part of our success.\n\nScale With Almedia: Grow alongside a startup that has been profitable from day one.\n\nCentral Berlin Office: Work from a fully-stocked modern office built for collaboration, accessible from all around Berlin.\n\nOther Benefits: Transport subsidy, breakfasts and lunches, language learning, Urban Sports Club, and more.\n\nWe believe in fostering talent, evaluating all skill levels during the hiring process, and providing a clear path for growth. Almedia is an equal opportunity employer. We embrace and celebrate diversity, and encourage individuals from all backgrounds to apply.\n\nCompensation Range: €85K - €95K','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Almedia','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5e7d25d26489f585','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2406,NULL,'job','Abschlussarbeit – Entwicklung und Embedded‑Implementierung virtueller Fahrzeugsensorik auf Basis von Machine Learning (w/m/d)','','Ingolstadt',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'To be filled:\n\n06/30/2026\n\nWork Environment\n\nDas Software‑defined‑Vehicle prägt die nächste Generation der Fahrzeugentwicklung bei der AUDI AG. In diesem Umfeld arbeitest du an innovativen Technologien für datengetriebene Fahrzeugfunktionen und gestaltest aktiv die Weiterentwicklung zukünftiger Fahrzeugsysteme mit.\nDein Einsatzbereich ist in der Entwicklung der Elektrik‑/Elektronik‑Architektur angesiedelt, einem zentralen Bestandteil moderner Fahrzeugplattformen. Hier beschäftigst du dich mit der Entwicklung virtueller Sensorik und analysierst, wie bestehende Sensorsysteme durch Machine‑Learning‑basierte Modelle ergänzt oder perspektivisch teilweise ersetzt werden können.\nZiel deiner Abschlussarbeit ist es, aus realen Fahrzeugmessdaten funktionsfähige Modelle abzuleiten und diese prototypisch umzusetzen. Du arbeitest dabei an der Schnittstelle zwischen Sensorik, Datenanalyse, Machine Learning und Embedded‑Implementierung und stehst im engen Austausch mit Fachbereichen aus der E/E‑Architektur, der Funktionsentwicklung, dem Datenmanagement sowie der Steuergeräte‑Softwareentwicklung. Die Ergebnisse werden hinsichtlich ihres funktionalen Mehrwerts sowie möglicher Potenziale zur Reduzierung von Hardwareaufwand, Kosten und Systemkomplexität bewertet.\n\nJob Purpose/Role\n\nDu analysierst die in der Fahrzeug‑Elektrik/Elektronik‑Architektur eingesetzten Sensorsysteme sowie deren Einsatzkontexte\n\nDu führst eine Wettbewerbs‑ und Vergleichsanalyse bestehender Sensor‑ und Funktionskonzepte durch\n\nDu identifizierst redundante Sensorsignale und bewertest deren Eignung für den Einsatz KI‑gestützter virtueller Sensorik\n\nDu konzipierst und entwickelst einen Prototyp eines KI‑basierten virtuellen Sensors\n\nDu trainierst, validierst und bewertest das Modell anhand realer Fahrzeugmessdaten und geeigneter Metriken\n\nDu überführst das entwickelte Modell in eine embedded‑nahe Implementierung für den Einsatz auf automobilen Steuergeräten\n\nDu bewertest die technische Leistungsfähigkeit, Robustheit sowie das wirtschaftliche Potenzial und leitest Empfehlungen für eine mögliche Serienintegration ab\n\nKey Requirements/Skills/Experience\n\nDu studierst Informatik, Informationstechnik, Elektrotechnik oder einen vergleichbaren technischen Studienrichtung\n\nDu verfügst über sehr gute Deutsch‑ und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\n\nDu bringst praktische Programmiererfahrung mit, idealerweise in Python und/oder C/C++, insbesondere für datengetriebene oder Embedded‑Anwendungen\n\nDu besitzt grundlegende Kenntnisse in Machine Learning, Signalverarbeitung oder Datenanalyse\n\nDu verfügst über Basiswissen zu automobilen Elektrik/Elektronik‑Architekturen sowie zu Fahrzeugbussystemen wie CAN, CAN FD, FlexRay oder Automotive Ethernet\n\nDu hast idealerweise erste Erfahrung im Umgang mit Fahrzeugmessdaten, Steuergeräten oder Embedded‑Implementierungen\n\nDu arbeitest eigenständig, analytisch und strukturiert an komplexen technischen Fragestellungen\n\nDu kommunizierst klar und bringst dich aktiv in die Zusammenarbeit in interdisziplinären Teams ein\n\nDen finalen Zeitraum der Abschlussarbeit vereinbarst du im Gespräch mit der Fachabteilung.\n\nAdditional information\n\nThis position is available at\n\nAUDI AG\n\n in\n\nIngolstadt\n\n.\n\nWe anchor sustainability in our business activities, products and services. We live excitement, trust, courage and responsibility, actively encourage inclusion and create an environment that fosters each employee\'s individuality in the interests of the company.\n\nReference code:\n\nI-A-111886\n\nIf you have any questions,\n\nfeel free to contact our career chat','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'AUDI AG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=721856d978198716','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2407,NULL,'job','Senior Developer (Unreal + LLM)','Festanstellung','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'München\nFull-time\nPermanent employee\nWhy us?\nwelevel is an innovative game studio based in Munich, backed by top-tier investors. We are developing Solid River, the first AAA survival game with deep city-building mechanics in the late game, set in a medieval, procedurally generated world with AI-driven NPCs.\n\nHere’s what makes us stand out:\n\nInspiring Work Environment: A central Munich location with a diverse, motivated, and international team that fosters creativity and collaboration.\nCompetitive Compensation: We believe in rewarding talent with attractive and fair packages.\nInnovative Technology: Work with the latest tools and technologies to push boundaries and make the impossible possible.\nYour Role\n\nWe are looking for a Senior Developer (Unreal + LLM) to drive the development of LLM-based NPC interactions and procedural storytelling. You will train and optimize large language models (LLMs) to create lifelike NPC conversations, intelligent world responses, and immersive AI-driven storytelling.\n\nResponsibilities\nDevelop and train LLMs for NPC interactions, procedural quests, and world lore.\nImplement AI pipelines for real-time conversational AI and decision-making.\nOptimize LLM inference for low-latency, in-game responses.\nWork with game designers and AI programmers to integrate models into gameplay.\nDevelop AI-driven dialogue systems and dynamic world events.\nResearch and implement cutting-edge machine learning techniques.\nRequirements\n3+ years of experience in AI/ML engineering, with a focus on LLM training.\nStrong experience with Python, C++, and deep learning frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch).\nExpertise in natural language processing (NLP) and AI-driven storytelling.\nExperience optimizing LLM models for real-time use in games.\nPassion for building immersive, AI-driven gameplay experiences.\nOnsite position.\nWhat we offer\nWork on a groundbreaking AAA survival city-building game.\nBe part of a passionate and highly experienced team.\nCompetitive salary and benefits package.\nOpportunity to innovate in AI-driven game development.\nA chance to grow with a rapidly expanding game studio backed by top industry veterans.\n\nAre you ready to embark on an epic journey with welevel and make SolidRiver an unforgettable gaming experience? Don\'t hesitate!\n\nApply now and let your creativity flow like a mighty river!\n\nAbout us\nwelevel is a fast-growing AI-powered game studio in the heart of Munich. We\'re creating a blockbuster title with an ambitious team, blending industry veterans with next-gen tech. As the home for bold,\ncreative minds, welevel is where innovation meets imagination. Backed by top investors, we\'re on a mission to reshape the future of gaming. We believe that great games are built by diverse teams. welevel is commited to creating an inclusive environment where people of all backgrounds identities, and experiences feel welcome and valued.','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'welevel GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=aed941560e04a612','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2408,NULL,'job','Data Scientist (w/m/d) mit Schwerpunkt Datenintegration','Teilzeit','Frankfurt am Main',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'… weil Qualität die Welt besser macht!\n\nDie DGQ ist überzeugt, dass Qualität das Herzstück allen Erfolgs ist. Leidenschaftlich arbeitet sie daran, die Bedeutung und Wirksamkeit von Qualität in Wirtschaft und Gesellschaft zu stärken. Als zentrale, deutsche Qualitätsgesellschaft ist die DGQ deshalb bundesweit erster Ansprechpartner für Qualität, Qualitätsmanagement und Qualitätssicherung.\n\nIm QualityLab der DGQ (das Team wird von aktuell drei auf fünf Spezialist:innen wachsen) verbinden wir Data Science, Domainwissen und Sozialforschung, um neues Wissen rund um Qualität zu schaffen. Als Data Scientist mit Schwerpunkt Datenintegration übernimmst du eine Schlüsselrolle: Du erschließt unsere Datenquellen, machst sie analysierbar und gewinnst daraus Erkenntnisse, die sowohl unsere Fachcommunity als auch unser eigenes Geschäft voranbringen.\n\nWir suchen dich zum nächstmöglichen Zeitpunkt in Frankfurt-Preungesheim (in Vollzeit, ggf. Teilzeit mind. 30 Stunden/Woche) als\n\nData Scientist (w/m/d) mit Schwerpunkt Datenintegration\n Deine Aufgaben:\n\nDatenquellen erschließen und integrieren:\n\nDu verbindest unsere zentralen Systeme - insbesondere Salesforce und unsere Mitgliederplattform - und machst die dort enthaltenen Daten für Analysen nutzbar.\nDu konzipierst und baust Datenpipelines (ETL-Strecken), die Rohdaten aus unterschiedlichen Quellen zusammenführen, bereinigen und in eine konsistente, analytische Datenbasis überführen.\nDu entwickelst Datenmodelle und -strukturen, die eine nachhaltige Grundlage für wiederkehrende Auswertungen und Ad-hoc-Analysen bilden.\n\nAnalyse und Erkenntnisgenerierung:\n\nDu identifizierst Thementrends und Buchungspfade unserer Mitglieder und Kund:innen, um gezielte Marketing- und Produktentscheidungen zu ermöglichen.\nDu entwickelst statistische Modelle und setzt Machine-Learning-Verfahren ein, um Muster in Research- und Geschäftsdaten aufzudecken und Prognosen abzuleiten - etwa zur Nachfrageentwicklung oder Mitgliederaktivität.\nDu erstellst aussagekräftige Dashboards und Visualisierungen, die komplexe Zusammenhänge für verschiedene Stakeholder verständlich machen.\n\nEigenverantwortung und Zusammenarbeit:\n\nDu arbeitest eng mit unserem Senior Data Scientist zusammen und übernimmst darüber hinaus eigenständige Projekte - von der Fragestellung bis zur Präsentation der Ergebnisse.\nDu gestaltest unsere Toollandschaft und technische Infrastruktur aktiv mit: Du wählst geeignete Technologien und Methoden aus und bringst eigene Ideen ein, wie wir unsere Datenarbeit weiterentwickeln können.\nDu vermittelst deine Ergebnisse verständlich an Fachkolleg:innen und Führungskräfte und trägst dazu bei, datenbasierte Entscheidungskultur in der DGQ zu stärken.\n\n Dein Profil:\n\nDu bist eine erfahrene Data-Science-Persönlichkeit, die nicht nur Modelle baut, sondern auch versteht, wie die Daten dafür zustande kommen. Du willst Dinge gestalten, nicht nur abarbeiten - und bringst die Eigeninitiative mit, in einem Team mit viel Gestaltungsfreiraum und wenig starren Vorgaben gemeinsam etwas aufzubauen.\n\nDas bringst du mit:\n\nMehrjährige Berufserfahrung im Bereich Data Science, Analytics oder einem verwandten Feld - idealerweise mit nachweisbarer Erfahrung an der Schnittstelle zur Datenintegration\nSehr gute Programmierkenntnisse in Python für Datenanalyse, Modellierung und Automatisierung (z. B. pandas, scikit-learn, SQLAlchemy, DuckDB)\nFundierte SQL-Kenntnisse und Erfahrung im Umgang mit relationalen Datenbanken - du schreibst nicht nur Abfragen, sondern denkst auch in Datenmodellen\nEine ausgeprägt eigenständige Arbeitsweise: Du identifizierst Handlungsbedarfe selbst, wählst passende Methoden und Tools und treibst Projekte proaktiv voran - auch wenn nicht alles vordefiniert ist\nErfahrung mit statistischen Methoden und Machine Learning, die du zielsicher auf reale Geschäftsfragen anwenden kannst\n\nDarüber freuen wir uns besonders:\n\nErfahrung im Aufbau von Datenpipelines und ETL-Prozessen (z. B. Anbindung von REST-APIs, Salesforce-APIs; leichtgewichtige Orchestrierung mit Python-Skripten, perspektivisch Prefect oder Dagster)\nUmfangreiche Kenntnisse in Datenmodellierung und analytischen Datenbanken bzw. Data-Warehouse-Konzepten (z. B. DuckDB als analytische Datenbank, Parquet als Austauschformat)\nPraxis in der Erstellung von Dashboards und Datenvisualisierungen (z. B. mit PowerBI oder Streamlit)\nErfahrung mit Datenbereinigung und Qualitätssicherung - du weißt, dass der Weg von Rohdaten zu belastbaren Ergebnissen selten geradlinig ist\nKommunikationsstärke: Du kannst analytische Ergebnisse so aufbereiten und präsentieren, dass auch Nicht-Techniker:innen einen klaren Mehrwert daraus ziehen\nErfahrung in einer Vereins-, Verbands- oder Bildungsorganisation ist ein Plus, aber kein Muss\n\nDu erfüllst nicht alle genannten Punkte? Bewirb dich trotzdem - uns ist wichtiger, dass du Lust hast, Dinge zu gestalten, als dass du jede Technologie bereits kennst.\n\n Was bieten wir?\n\nGeregelte Arbeitszeiten mit Gleitzeit, der Möglichkeit, an 2 Tagen pro Woche mobil zu arbeiten und 30 Tagen Urlaub für die perfekte Work-Life-Balance\nIntensive Einarbeitung: Damit du von Anfang an optimal durchstarten kannst\nZusätzliche Benefits: Arbeitgeberzuschüsse zur Betriebskantine, zur betrieblichen Altersvorsorge und zum Deutschlandticket, sowie weitere attraktive Gesundheits- und Sozialleistungen\nWertschätzung und Teamspirit: Wir fördern eine Unternehmenskultur, die auf Vertrauen, Respekt und Zusammenarbeit basiert\nWeiterentwicklung: Bei uns kannst du dich kontinuierlich weiterentwickeln – wir bieten die Möglichkeit, neue Fähigkeiten zu erlernen und dich in deinem Bereich weiterzubilden\n\nWir freuen uns auf deine Bewerbung!\n\nSende uns deine aussagekräftige Online-Bewerbung über unser Karriereportal – bitte mit deinem Wunschgehalt. Wann kannst du bei uns durchstarten?\n\nHast du Fragen zur Stelle oder möchtest du mehr über deine Möglichkeiten bei uns erfahren? Wir stehen gerne zur Verfügung und beraten dich ausführlich.\n\nSo erreichst du uns: (nur für Bewerber:innen)\nTelefon: +49 69 95424-115\nMail: recruiting@dgq.de\n\nWhatsApp: +49 151 2222 9923\n\nÜber die DGQ\nDie Deutsche Gesellschaft für Qualität (DGQ) unterstützt Unternehmen dabei, mit hochwertigen Produkten und Dienstleistungen erfolgreich am Markt zu bestehen. Das einzigartige Netzwerk der DGQ vereint über 6.000 Qualitätsexpert:innen in mehr als 4.000 Unternehmen aller Größen und Branchen. Berufseinsteiger:innen, Fachexpert:innen und Manager:innen nutzen den direkten Erfahrungsaustausch in deutschlandweit über 60 Regional- und Fachkreisen.\n\nDas DGQ-Netzwerk bietet die vielseitigste und umfassendste Plattform zum Austausch von Wissen, Praxiserfahrungen und Trends rund um qualitätsrelevante Themen. Die DGQ engagiert sich in nationalen und internationalen Initiativen, Partnerschaften, Gremien zur Gestaltung zentraler Normen sowie Innovations- und Forschungsprojekten.\n\nMit rund 200 Trainer:innen und über 1.300 praxisbezogenen Trainings stellt die DGQ ein breites Weiterbildungsangebot zur Verfügung und erteilt im Markt anerkannte Personenzertifikate. Auf Basis ihres umfassenden Engagements für Qualität gestaltet die DGQ wissensbasierte Leistungen und Lösungen für Gegenwart und Zukunft.\n\nURL dieser Seite: karriere.dgq.de/job/379/\n\nWeitere Informationen erhalten Sie unter:\n\n069 954 24-0','2026-05-07 01:37:29','open',0,'Deutsche Gesellschaft für Qualität DGQ','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=fb6b3baf61023e22','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2409,NULL,'job','AI DevOps (f/m/div)','Festanstellung','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'#WeAreIn for jobs that impact everyone\'s life. Coding the future, one algorithm at a time - ready for the challenge? As an AI DevOps in the Software & Data Science team, get ready to program the intelligence behind the chips, transform complex data into actionable insights, and create cutting-edge solutions that redefine industries and solve tomorrow\'s challenges. Are you in?\n\nYour Role\n\nKey responsibilities in your new role\n\nDevelop and maintain CI/CD pipelines for AI/ML models targeted towards chip development, ensuring smooth and efficient deployment to production environments\nDeploy and monitor AI/ML models in production environments, ensuring they meet performance, scalability, and reliability requirements and versioning and rollback capabilities\nWork closely with data scientists and engineers to understand AI/ML model requirements, develop deployment strategies, and ensure seamless integration with existing infrastructure\nDevelop and implement automated testing and validation frameworks to ensure AI/ML models meet quality and performance standards managing performance & drifts\nManage and optimize infrastructure resources (e.g., compute, storage, networking) to support AI/ML workloads, ensuring efficient use of resources and minimizing costs and drive continuous improvement\n\nYour Profile\n\nQualifications and skills to help you succeed\n\nYou are a strong team player with excellent problem-solving and communication skills, able to clearly explain ideas and collaborate with others to drive results. You naturally take initiative, help guide discussions, and inspire those around you.\n\nDegree in Computer Science, Information Technology or related fields such as Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Data Science\n1 to 3 years of experience in DevOps, software engineering or a related field\nExperience working with AI/ML models, CI/CD pipelines, containerization (e.g. Docker), cloud-based infrastructure (AWS, GCP, Azure) and container orchestration (e.g. Kubernetes)\nRelevant certifications in DevOps, Cloud Computing, or AI/ML engineering (e.g. AWS Certified DevOps Engineer, Google Cloud Certified – Professional Cloud Developer)\nStrong experience with programming (e.g. Python, Java), CI/CD tools (e.g. Jenkins, GitLab), containerization (e.g. Docker, Kubernetes), cloud platforms (e.g. AWS, GCP), and automation tools (e.g. Ansible)\nFamiliarity with AI/ML frameworks (e.g. TensorFlow, PyTorch) and monitoring/logging tools (e.g. Prometheus, Grafana)\nFluency in English (mandatory)\n\nContact:\n Magda Gomes, LinkedIn\n\n#WeAreIn for driving decarbonization and digitalization.\nAs a global leader in semiconductor solutions in power systems and IoT, Infineon enables game-changing solutions for green and efficient energy, clean and safe mobility, as well as smart and secure IoT. Together, we drive innovation and customer success, while caring for our people and empowering them to reach ambitious goals. Be a part of making life easier, safer and greener.\nAre you in?\n\nWe are on a journey to create the best Infineon for everyone.\nThis means we embrace diversity and inclusion and welcome everyone for who they are. At Infineon, we offer a working environment characterized by trust, openness, respect and tolerance and are committed to give all applicants and employees equal opportunities. We base our recruiting decisions on the applicant´s experience and skills. Learn more about our various contact channels.\nWe look forward to receiving your resume, even if you do not entirely meet all the requirements of the job posting.\nPlease let your recruiter know if they need to pay special attention to something in order to enable your participation in the interview process.\nClick here for more information about Diversity & Inclusion at Infineon.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Infineon Technologies AG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=54ee83d7496a5469','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2410,NULL,'job','PLM Engineering Data Engineer (m/w/d)','Festanstellung','Hamburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'WOFÜR WIR SIE SUCHEN\nEinführung von Methoden und Tools des Data Engineerings für unsere Produkt-Management-Datenbanken im Rahmen des entwicklungszentrierten Product-Lifecycle-Managements (PLM)\nEntwicklung von intelligenten, skalierbaren, wiederverwendbaren und zuverlässigen Lösungen und Methoden für die Datenanalyse, -integration, -bereinigung und -verarbeitung\nGenerierung von neuen Insights zusammen mit unseren Domänen- und Datenexperten (m/w/d) unserer Entwicklungsbereiche und Partner (m/w/d)\nKategorie-Entwicklung, um diese mithilfe von Clustering- und Klassifikationsalgorithmen in informativere Datenstrukturen zu überführen\nAufbau von Machine-Learning Modellen, insbesondere im Bereich Clustering, Klassifikation und Textanalyse\nDefinition und Umsetzung von Anforderungen im Rahmen der Datenhaltungs- und Verarbeitungssysteme\nUnterstützung bei der automatischen Engineering-Datenbereitstellung für die Anwendungsfelder Collaborative Engineering und digitale Verwaltung von Produkt-Entwicklungsdaten\n\nDie Stelle kann an den Standorten Kassel, Kiel, Unterlüß oder Hamburg besetzt werden.\n\nWAS SIE MITBRINGEN SOLLTEN\nErfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium, z. B. Informatik, Ingenieurwesen, Data Science oder Mathematik, oder aber eine vergleichbare Qualifikation mit den Schwerpunkten Data Science, Data Analytics\nFundierte Erfahrungen zu Methoden der semantischen Analyse (z. B. Natural Language Processing) zur strukturierten Auswertung textbasierter Daten\nGute Kenntnisse in Datenbankabfragen und Automation mit SQL (PowerShell, Skripte, PowerBI), Datenvisualisierung und Data Queries sowie objektorientierter Softwareentwicklung\nBerufserfahrung im Umgang mit PLM Datenbanken und Datenmodellen von Vorteil\nKenntnisse in NLP-Frameworks (z. B. spaCy, NLTK, transformers) sowie ML-Bibliotheken wie scikit-learn oder PyTorch / TensorFlow wünschenswert\nHohe Bereitschaft, komplexe Datenmodelle zu verstehen, semantische Beziehungen zu erfassen und domänenspezifisches Wissen analytisch aufzubereiten\nSehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\nKommunikationsstärke sowie Teamfähigkeit\n\nStärken und Erfahrungen zählen bei Rheinmetall, auch wenn vielleicht nicht alle aufgeführten Anforderungen vollständig erfüllt sind. Wir freuen uns auf Bewerber (m/w/d), die Lust haben, etwas zu bewegen und Verantwortung zu übernehmen. Wir legen Wert auf Individualität und Chancengleichheit. Schwerbehinderte Bewerber (m/w/d) werden bei gleicher Eignung besonders berücksichtigt.\n\nWAS WIR IHNEN BIETEN\n\nAn unserem Standort in Kassel bieten wir Ihnen:\n\nArbeiten an Gesamtsystemen\nBetriebliche Altersvorsorge\nMitarbeiteraktienkaufprogramm\nErgebnisbeteiligung\nFlexible Arbeitszeitmodelle, Gleitzeitmodell sowie VIVA-Familien-Service\nSubventioniertes Mittagessen und Kiosk am Standort\nFitness- und Gesundheitsangebote\nCorporate Benefits Plattform mit exklusiven Mitarbeiterrabatten für zahlreiche Shops\nVergünstigtes Jobticket\nIndividuelle und vielfältige externe sowie interne Weiterentwicklungsmöglichkeiten, u.a. in der Rheinmetall Academy\nProfessioneller Einarbeitungsprozess begleitet durch ein digitales Onboarding-Tool\n über unseren Standort und unsere Mitarbeiter (m/w/d) in Kassel erfahren Sie hier.\n\nKONTAKTDETAILS\n\nZuständige/r Ansprechpartner/in: Sherin Schümchen\n\n.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'RHEINMETALL','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d59b8db5d0e4bf95','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2411,NULL,'job','AI DevOps (m/f/div)','Festanstellung','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'#WeAreIn for jobs that impact everyone\'s life. Coding the future, one algorithm at a time - ready for the challenge? As an AI DevOps in the Software & Data Science team, get ready to program the intelligence behind the chips, transform complex data into actionable insights, and create cutting-edge solutions that redefine industries and solve tomorrow\'s challenges. Are you in?\n\nYour Role\n\nKey responsibilities in your new role\n\nDevelop and maintain CI/CD pipelines for AI/ML models targeted towards chip development, ensuring smooth and efficient deployment to production environments\nDeploy and monitor AI/ML models in production environments, ensuring they meet performance, scalability, and reliability requirements and versioning and rollback capabilities\nWork closely with data scientists and engineers to understand AI/ML model requirements, develop deployment strategies, and ensure seamless integration with existing infrastructure\nDevelop and implement automated testing and validation frameworks to ensure AI/ML models meet quality and performance standards managing performance & drifts\nManage and optimize infrastructure resources (e.g., compute, storage, networking) to support AI/ML workloads, ensuring efficient use of resources and minimizing costs and drive continuous improvement\n\nYour Profile\n\nQualifications and skills to help you succeed\n\nYou are a strong team player with excellent problem-solving and communication skills, able to clearly explain ideas and collaborate with others to drive results. You naturally take initiative, help guide discussions, and inspire those around you.\n\nDegree in Computer Science, Information Technology or related fields such as Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Data Science\n1 to 3 years of experience in DevOps, software engineering or a related field\nExperience working with AI/ML models, CI/CD pipelines, containerization (e.g. Docker), cloud-based infrastructure (AWS, GCP, Azure) and container orchestration (e.g. Kubernetes)\nRelevant certifications in DevOps, Cloud Computing, or AI/ML engineering (e.g. AWS Certified DevOps Engineer, Google Cloud Certified – Professional Cloud Developer)\nStrong experience with programming (e.g. Python, Java), CI/CD tools (e.g. Jenkins, GitLab), containerization (e.g. Docker, Kubernetes), cloud platforms (e.g. AWS, GCP), and automation tools (e.g. Ansible)\nFamiliarity with AI/ML frameworks (e.g. TensorFlow, PyTorch) and monitoring/logging tools (e.g. Prometheus, Grafana)\nFluency in English (mandatory)\n\n#WeAreIn for driving decarbonization and digitalization.\nAs a global leader in semiconductor solutions in power systems and IoT, Infineon enables game-changing solutions for green and efficient energy, clean and safe mobility, as well as smart and secure IoT. Together, we drive innovation and customer success, while caring for our people and empowering them to reach ambitious goals. Be a part of making life easier, safer and greener.\nAre you in?\n\nWe are on a journey to create the best Infineon for everyone.\nThis means we embrace diversity and inclusion and welcome everyone for who they are. At Infineon, we offer a working environment characterized by trust, openness, respect and tolerance and are committed to give all applicants and employees equal opportunities. We base our recruiting decisions on the applicant´s experience and skills. Learn more about our various contact channels.\nWe look forward to receiving your resume, even if you do not entirely meet all the requirements of the job posting.\nPlease let your recruiter know if they need to pay special attention to something in order to enable your participation in the interview process.\nClick here for more information about Diversity & Inclusion at Infineon.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Infineon Technologies AG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=df1cb0ca9f2cc68d','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2412,NULL,'job','Lead AI CoE & Delivery (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','Frankfurt am Main',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'In dieser Schlüsselrolle übernimmst Du die Leitung des Central AI Powerhouses inklusive der AI Delivery Teams und gestaltest maßgeblich den Aufbau sowie die Skalierung der globalen AI‑Fähigkeiten innerhalb der KION Group. Gemeinsam mit Business‑ und IT‑Einheiten identifizierst, entwickelst und realisierst Du nachhaltige, umsatzgenerierende AI‑Lösungen.\n\nWe offer:\n\nEin Unternehmen mit Zukunft: Schon heute beschäftigen wir als börsennotiertes M-Dax Unternehmen mehr als 42.000 MitarbeiterInnen in über 100 Ländern und treiben damit maßgeblich die Zukunft der Intralogistik voran verfolgen dabei eine klare Nachhaltigkeitsstrategie\n\nGemeinsam vorankommen : Standardisierter und dokumentierter Feedbackprozess mit internationalen Karrieremöglichkeiten und individuellen Weiterbildungsangeboten\n\nIndividuelle Benefits : Moderne IT-Ausstattung (auch für das Home Office) & Mobile Devices, Employee Assistance Program –ganzheitliches Unterstützungsprogramm für individuelle Krisensituationen, bezuschusstes Deutschlandticket, Parkplätze, Möglichkeit zum Leasen eines Dienstrads, Exklusive Vorteile / Rabatte für MitarbeiterInnen\n\nUnsere Basics: Flexible Arbeitszeiten, Teilzeitmodelle, Möglichkeit zum Mobilen Arbeiten (Hybrid Modell), Gleitzeitkonto, attraktives Vergütungspaket, betriebliche Altersvorsorge, Kantine\n\nTasks and Qualifications:\n\nDich erwarten ein hoher Gestaltungs‑ und Entscheidungsfreiraum sowie eine klare ziel‑ und bereichsübergreifende Verantwortung . Du bewegst Dich in einem Umfeld mit hohen Anforderungen , da Deine Arbeit einen unmittelbaren Beitrag zur Erreichung der finanziellen Ziele des Central AI Diamond Clusters leistet. Das Aufgabenspektrum ist breit und anspruchsvoll , geprägt von hoher Zeit Kritikalität und zugleich großer strategischer Relevanz.\n\nIn deiner Rolle agierst Du als zentrale Schnittstelle innerhalb und außerhalb der Organisation. Intern arbeitest du eng mit den IT‑AS und IT‑IS Plattform Leads, dem IT Management Team (ITMT), den globalen AI‑Powerhouses der Operating Units sowie dem KION AI Board zusammen. Extern kooperierst Du mit führenden Entwicklungs‑ und Lösungspartnern und pflegst strategische Partnerschaften mit Technologieanbietern wie Google und Microsoft .\n\nDeine Aufgaben\n\nDu verantwortest den Aufbau, die Steuerung und die Weiterentwicklung des Central AI Powerhouses sowie der AI Delivery Teams – inklusive Budget‑, Projekt‑ und Mitarbeiterverantwortung\n\nDu baust die AI‑Teams in Monterrey und Krakau auf und stellst eine effiziente Zusammenarbeit mit internen und externen Partnern sicher\n\nDu berätst die Operating Units (OUs) und AI Powerhouses bei Buy‑vs.-Build‑Entscheidungen\n\nDu führst Proofs of Concept (PoCs) durch und begleitest Solution‑ und Vendor‑Evaluierungen\n\nDu verantwortest die Central AI Powerhouse Roadmap inklusive Ressourcen‑ und Kapazitätssteuerung\n\nDu stimmst Dich eng mit IT‑AS, IT‑IS Plattformleads und dem IT Management Team (ITMT) zu Anforderungen und AI‑Capabilities ab\n\nDu unterstützt aktiv die Umsetzung zentraler AI‑Use‑Cases entlang der Unternehmensstrategie\n\nDu entwickelst und etablierst Governance‑ und Compliance‑Prozesse für AI‑Projekte unter Berücksichtigung des EU AI Acts und EU Data Acts\n\nDu bringst Dich aktiv im KION AI Board ein und gestaltest die strategische Weiterentwicklung der AI‑Initiativen mit\n\nDein Profil\n\nAbgeschlossenes Studium in Informatik, Data Science, Ingenieurwissenschaften\n\nFundierte Berufserfahrung im Bereich AI, Data Science, Machine Learning oder AI‑bezogenen Architektur‑/Technologieprojekten\n\nFundiertes Verständnis aktueller AI‑Technologien (ML‑Modelle, LLMs, Vektordatenbanken, RAG‑Methoden, moderne Frameworks)\n\nErfahrung in AI‑Projektleitung / Delivery oder technologischer Bewertung\n\nErfahrung im fachlichen Führen\n\nErfahrung in der Erstellung von Lösungen in einem kollaborativen, funktions-übergreifenden Teamumfeld\n\nFähigkeit, komplexe technische Zusammenhänge klar und adressatengerecht zu kommunizieren\n\nStark in Stakeholder‑Management, interdisziplinärer Abstimmung und zielorientiertem Arbeiten\n\nStrukturierte, selbstständige und analytische Arbeitsweise sowie hohe Lernbereitschaft\n\nDeutsch und Englisch sicher in Wort und Schrift\n\nHaben wir Dein Interesse geweckt?\n\nWenn Dich die Stelle anspricht, freuen wir uns auf Deine Onlinebewerbung! Deine Ansprechpartnerin ist Anne-Christin Fritzsche .\n\n#LI-Hybrid','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'KION Information Management Services GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=037f537a113e1acd','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2413,NULL,'job','Werkstudent Erneuerbare Energien (Last- & Lebensdauerabschätzung von Windenergieanlagen) - remote möglich','Studentenjob','20095 Hamburg',NULL,'',16.00,'Ab 16 € pro Stunde','Über das Unternehmen\n\nWir suchen Menschen, die an die positive Kraft von Energie glauben und an ihre eigene Stärke, Dinge voranzubringen. Die wissen, wie wichtig Energie und Infrastruktur sind und wie groß die Möglichkeiten, mit ihnen Zukunft für alle zu gestalten. Denn wir sind genauso: Ein großes, tatkräftiges Unternehmen, das die Tür weit aufmacht für Menschen, die mit uns gemeinsam aus Ideen echte Veränderungen machen.\n\nUnser Angebot\n\n• Spannende und anspruchsvolle Aufgaben eröffnen vielfältige Perspektiven zur persönlichen Entwicklung\n• Kollegiale Zusammenarbeit im Team und moderne Arbeitsplätze zeichnen uns aus\n• Vielfältige Events bieten Austausch- und Netzwerkoptionen für unsere Studierenden im Rahmen des Studi-Energy-Programms\n• Flexible Arbeitszeitmodelle ermöglichen die Vereinbarkeit von Job und Studium\n• Attraktive Vergütungen eröffnen Möglichkeiten: 2.289,00 € mtl. brutto bei allen Praktika und Abschlussarbeiten und ab 16,- € je Stunde brutto bei Werkstudierendentätigkeiten im Bachelorstudium bzw. ab 18,- € brutto im Masterstudium\n\nVielfältige Aufgaben\n\nDatenanalyse& Modellierung:\n\n• Zu deinem Aufgabengebiet gehören die Auswertung großer Zeitreihen- und SCADA-Datensätze aus dem Anlagenbetrieb sowie die Identifikation relevanter Last- und Betriebszustände für ausgewählte Komponenten\n• Du unterstützt bei der Entwicklung und Validierung von Modellen zur Last- und Lebensdauerabschätzung\n\nAlgorithmen& Machine Learning:\n\n• Du entwickelst und implementierst Algorithmen zur Zustandsbewertung und Prognose der Restlebensdauer\n• Der Vergleich klassischer ingenieurtechnischer Ansätze mit datengetriebenen Methoden gehört zu deinem Alltag und du leitest daraus Wartungs- und Betriebsstrategien ab\n\nDatenaufbereitung& Qualitätssicherung:\n\n• Du bereinigst, transformierst und erstellst Features aus Betriebsdaten und unterstützt beim Aufbau sowie der Dokumentation strukturierter Datenbanken\n\nVisualisierung& Prototyping:\n\n• Die Entwicklung einfacher Dashboards und Prototypen zur intuitiven Visualisierung von Lebensdauermodellen liegt in deinem Verantwortungsbereich\n\nForschung& Abschlussarbeiten:\n\n• Du bringst eigene Ideen für innovative Ansätze ein und hast die Möglichkeit zur Anbahnung einer späteren Bachelor- oder Masterarbeit im Themenfeld Condition Monitoring und Lebensdauerprognose\n\nÜberzeugendes Profil\n\n• Du bist eingeschriebene*r Student*in in Fachrichtung Informatik, Energietechnik, Maschinenbau, Elektrotechnik oder vergleichbares\n• Dein Studienabschluss liegt im Jahr 2028 oder später und du möchtest mindestens ein Jahr bei uns mitwirken\n• Du arbeitest strukturiert, eigenverantwortlich und zielorientiert\n• Neugier sowie der sichere Umgang mit unvollständigen Informationen zeichnen dich aus\n• Sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse auf mindestens C1-Niveau bringst du mit\n\nÜber den Bereich\n\nIm Team Remote Monitoring arbeiten wir täglich daran, den Betrieb unserer Windenergieanlagen intelligenter, effizienter und nachhaltiger zu gestalten. Im Betrieb unserer Anlagen entstehen große Mengen an Betriebsdaten – und genau darin liegt unser Potenzial: Diese Daten in wertvolle Informationen zu verwandeln, um Prozesse zu optimieren, Ressourcen zu schonen und die Energiewende bezahlbar zu machen.\nEin zentraler Schwerpunkt ist dabei die Last- und Lebensdauerabschätzung von Komponenten: Wir wollen besser verstehen, wie sich reale Betriebsbedingungen auf die Alterung und Ausfallwahrscheinlichkeit von Bauteilen auswirken – und wie wir diese Erkenntnisse nutzen können, um Wartungsstrategien zu verbessern, Stillstände zu reduzieren und die Lebensdauer der Anlagen zu verlängern.\nIn unserem interdisziplinären Team erwarten dich spannende Herausforderungen rund um die smarte Nutzung dieser Daten. Wir suchen kreative Köpfe und angehende Expert: innen, die mit uns neue Wege gehen und innovative Lösungen entwickeln – für die Energie von morgen.\nRemote heißt für dich: Du hast die Möglichkeit, deutschlandweit im Homeoffice zu arbeiten. In der Regel einmal monatlich triffst du deine Kolleg*innen zusätzlich vor Ort im Büro.\n\nKontakt\n\nInteressiert? Jetzt online bewerben! Ein Anschreiben ist dafür nicht erforderlich, gegebenenfalls stellen wir ein paar jobspezifische Fragen in unserem Bewerbungsformular.Unser Recruitingteam stellt neben der EnBW für weitere Konzerngesellschaften ein. Bei Fragen steht Martin, Celine | celine.martin@netze-bw.de gerne zur Verfügung.Alle Menschen sind bei uns willkommen, egal welchen Geschlechts, Alters, sexueller Identität, Herkunft, Religion, Weltanschauung, mit oder ohne Behinderung.Unsere Informationen zum Datenschutz für Bewerber (w/m/d).','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'EnBW Energie Baden-Württemberg AG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8901df9a506adc20','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2414,NULL,'job','Duales Studium 2026: Bachelor of Science - Data Science & Künstliche Intelligenz','Berufsausbildung','70178 Stuttgart',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Das sind wir:\nDer Ernst Klett Verlag\n\nBildung schafft Perspektiven. Die Ernst Klett Verlag GmbH ist eines der größten und erfolgreichsten Bildungsmedienunternehmen in Deutschland. Seit 125 Jahren steht Klett damit für professionelle Lehr- und Lernmedien – von gedrucktem Material bis zu modernsten digitalen Anwendungen für Lehrkräfte und Lernende. Wir laden Sie dazu ein, mit Ihren Kompetenzen und Qualifikationen die Bildung von heute für die Welt von morgen aktiv mitzugestalten.\n\nDas sind Sie und Ihre Fähigkeiten\nSie haben Ihr Abitur oder die allgemeine / fachgebundene Hochschulreife mit sehr guten Leistungen abgeschlossen.\nSie verfügen über Englischkenntnisse auf Niveau B2.\nSie zeichnen sich durch Ihre guten Leistungen im Fach Mathematik sowie durch Ihre Affinität / Ihr Interesse für das Programmieren aus.\nEine Leidenschaft für technologische Innovation und die Fähigkeit, sich schnell an neue Technologien anzupassen, runden Ihr Profil ab.\nIhre Aufgaben bei uns\nAls duale:r Studierende:r absolvieren Sie Ihr Studium im Rahmen der Theoriephasen an der DHBW in Mosbach und erlangen am Ende den Abschluss Bachelor of Science. Dabei tauchen Sie in die Themenwelten von Datenanalyse und künstlicher Intelligenz ein. Neben Methoden und Techniken zum Sammeln, Analysieren und Interpretieren von Daten lernen Sie beispielsweise die Anwendung von KI-Technologien wie Machine Learning, neuronalen Netzen und Sprachverarbeitung zur Lösung komplexer Probleme kennen.\nWährend Ihrer Praxisphasen in unserem Unternehmen haben Sie die Möglichkeit, praktische Erfahrungen zu sammeln und wertvolle Kontakte für die Zukunft zu knüpfen.\nSie denken Prozesse neu, treiben Veränderungen voran und übernehmen Verantwortung.\nDas Studium wird durch erfahrene Dozenten (in der DHBW) und Ausbildungsbeauftragte (im Betrieb) begleitet.\nUnsere Benefits für Ihren Alltag\n\nFlexible Arbeitszeitmodelle\n\nBetriebliche Gesundheitsförderung\n\nSubventioniertes Jobticket im Nahverkehr & weitere Vergünstigungen\n\nTarifgebundene Gehälter & Sozialleistungen\n\nSpannende Entwicklungsmöglichkeiten\n\nGeförderte Altersvorsorge\n\nOffene & respektvolle Arbeitsatmosphäre\n\nMobiles Arbeiten\n\nIhre Ansprechpartnerin\n\nAline Baßler\nGruppenleiterin Personal\n\nErnst Klett Verlag GmbH\nRotebühlstr. 77\n70178 Stuttgart\n0711 / 6672 - 1631','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Ernst Klett Verlag GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=277692de35caaa1a','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2415,NULL,'job','Postdoctoral researcher in Neuroimaging and AI (ERC project CONNECT) (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Campus Großhadern, Campus Innenstadt\n\nWorking hours\n\nFull time\n\nInstitution\n\nKlinik und Poliklinik für Radiologie\n\nDepartment\n\nFunctional Neuroimaging Group\n\nDate of entry\n\n15.07.2026\n\nApplication deadline\n\n10.05.2026\n\nReference Number\n\n2026-K-0152\n\nThe Hospital of the University of Munich, Germany, is one of the largest and most competitive university hospitals in Germany and Europe. 48 specialized hospitals, departments and institutions harbouring excellent research and education provide patient care at the highest medical level with around 11.000 employees.\n\nScope of duties\n\nThe Functional Neuroimaging research group is looking for a highly motivated PostDoc to join an ERC-funded project, combining neuroimaging and machine learning to advance our understanding of brain connectivity in neurological disorders with a focus on neuro-oncology and neurodegeneration. In your postdoctoral project you will:\n\nLead the development of scalable pipelines for preprocessing and analysis of large-scale neuroimaging datasets (structural and resting-state fMRI).\nDesign, implement, and evaluate advanced AI models for functional connectivity–based anomaly detection (e.g., graph-based models, generative approaches).\nIntegrate multimodal data (imaging, demographic, technical parameters) into robust machine learning frameworks.\nGuide methodological development, benchmarking, and validation of models using clinical outcome measures.\nSupervise PhD and MSc students and contribute to project coordination within an interdisciplinary team.\nPublish in high-impact journals and present findings at international conferences.\nOur requirements\n\nPhD in computer science, (biomedical) engineering, neuroscience, physics, or a related field.\n\nStrong expertise in machine learning/deep learning and scientific programming (Python).\nExperience working in Linux environments and high-performance computing (HPC) systems\nExperience with neuroimaging data and tools (e.g., fMRI, BIDS, FSL, FreeSurfer) is highly desirable.\nExperience with large-scale data processing and high-performance computing environments is advantageous.\nExperience working with functional MRI (fMRI) analysis is a plus.\nStrong analytical skills and ability to lead independent research projects.\nExcellent written and spoken English.\nExcellent publication track record.\n\nOur offer\n\nA dynamic and interdisciplinary research environment at LMU Klinikum, one of Europe’s leading medical institutions.\n\nAn established and structured research group with a strong publication track record, striving for high-impact publications.\nA collaborative and supportive team culture, including regular group meetings, structured supervision, and one-on-one mentoring.\nStrong research infrastructure, including dedicated support in biostatistics, clinical data science, AI algorithm development, and project management.\nOpportunities for career development, including mentorship, grant writing support, and international networking.\nFlexible and family-friendly working conditions, including options for remote work where appropriate.\nThe position is limited to three years.\nRemuneration is based on the Collective Agreement for the Public Sector of the Länder (TV-L) including all allowances customary in the public sector.\n\nOffers and services of the employer\n\nFurther education and training\n\nJob ticket\n\nCompany pension scheme\n\nDiscounts\n\nChildcare services\n\nStaff accommodation (if available)\n\nMobile work (if suitable)\n\nMrs. Dr.rer.nat. Ruat, Julia\n+49 89 4400 76624\nApplication format\nPlease use the Online-Form for your application\n\nDisabled persons will be preferentially considered in case of equal qualification. Presentation costs cannot be refunded.\n\nPlease note that we cannot reimburse travel expenses incurred through interviews.\n\nWe ask you for your understanding that postal applications will not be returned, but will be destroyed in accordance with data protection regulations. The data usage information also applies to postal applications','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'LMU Klinikum München','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ac5d022876f8a2b9','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2416,NULL,'job','Working Student (f/m/d) - Software Development for SAP Sailing Analytics','Studentenjob','69190 Walldorf',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We help the world run better\n\nAt SAP, we keep it simple: you bring your best to us, and we\'ll bring out the best in you. We\'re builders touching over 20 industries and 80% of global commerce, and we need your unique talents to help shape what\'s next. The work is challenging – but it matters. You\'ll find a place where you can be yourself, prioritize your wellbeing, and truly belong. What\'s in it for you? Constant learning, skill growth, great benefits, and a team that wants you to grow and succeed.\n\nWhat you\'ll build\n\nHelp the world\'s leading platform for portraying and analyzing sailing regattas become a successful open-source project on GitHub. You will secure the platform, keep frameworks and components up-to-date, and improve the automation of cloud processes to provide solutions for sailing events and other users. Join our team to support the open-source community in onboarding the project.\n\n1. Open-Source Launch and Security:\n\nHelp successfully publish Sailing Analytics as an open-source project on GitHub\nAddress security improvements based on Threat Modeling findings, both before and after publishing\nFocus on security, primarily through Java development\n\n2. Technology Showcases and Prototypes:\n\nUse SAP Sailing Analytics and its rich data collected in over 40,000 races to create technology showcases and prototypes, such as the AI Sailing Commentator\nFocus on data science, large language models (LLMs), and machine learning\n\n3. Maintainer Role:\n\nHelp fulfill the \"maintainer\" role for SAP post-publication of the Sailing Analytics open-source project\nWork across the full stack of the solution, including cloud infrastructure management, application logic, analytics use cases, UI, web clients, and companion apps like Sail Insight built with React Native technology\nCollaborate with the open-source community on GitHub, review pull requests and help ensure the quality and security of the solution\n\n4. Event Support (Optional):\n\nOptionally support sailing events on-site\nHelp operate the software, manage race infrastructure, and interact with users and other on-site partners, such as race management, tracking infrastructure, and wind sensor handling\n\nWhat you bring\n\nStudent (f/m/d) at a university or a university of applied sciences in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field\nComputer skills:\nSolid foundational knowledge in computer science and software engineering methodology\nSolid experience in Java\nFirst experience in building web applications\nLanguage skills: Fluent German or English\nSoft skills:\nEager to learn and find fun in working with technology\nHands-on, reliable and open-minded mentality\nStrong team working skills, fostering an inclusive and collaborative environment\nPlus: Interest or even better own experience in the sport of sailing\n\nWhere you belong\n\nAt Strategic Projects, as part of the CTO area, we are driving forward SAP’s development excellence by implementing cutting-edge and strategically relevant solutions for pressing topics. In addition, we provide expertise with tech evaluations and develop proof-of-concepts for strategic technology topics. Our team consists of about 65 colleagues who are students, young professionals, and experienced professionals in the areas of software development, design, project management and team/management assistance. We work in teams that are mainly located in Potsdam/Berlin and Walldorf and collaborate closely with other SAP teams to realize our mission.\n\nAbout Sailing Analytics:\nThe SAP Sailing Analytics is the solution that powers https://sapsailing.com. It allows regatta hosts, athletes, coaches and fans to follow live, portray and comment, analyze and understand sailing regattas in unprecedented ways. With its unparalleled high-quality sailing tracking database it serves as the foundation for various SAP technology showcases.\n\nYour set of application documents should contain a cover letter, a resume in table form, school leaving certificates, certificate of enrollment, current university transcript of records, copies of any academic degrees already earned, and if available, references from former employers (including internships). Please also describe your experience and skills in foreign languages and computer programs / programming languages.\n\nThis is a SAP global, strategic, paid working student position that provides students with opportunities to find purpose in their careers.\n\n#Workingstudent #Werkstudent #Germany #Deutschland #Student #OpenSourceOpportunity #SailingTech #StudentDeveloper #JavaProgramming #TechInnovation #CloudAutomation #CollaborativeCoding #SAPStrategicProjects #SoftwareEngineering #DynamicTechField#LIHybrid #SAPGermanStudentsCareers #SAPNextGen\n\nBring out your best\nSAP innovations help more than four hundred thousand customers worldwide work together more efficiently and use business insight more effectively. Originally known for leadership in enterprise resource planning (ERP) software, SAP has evolved to become a market leader in end-to-end business application software and related services for database, analytics, intelligent technologies, and experience management. As a cloud company with two hundred million users and more than one hundred thousand employees worldwide, we are purpose-driven and future-focused, with a highly collaborative team ethic and commitment to personal development. Whether connecting global industries, people, or platforms, we help ensure every challenge gets the solution it deserves. At SAP, you can bring out your best.\n\nWe win with inclusion\nSAP’s culture of inclusion, focus on health and well-being, and flexible working models help ensure that everyone – regardless of background – feels included and can run at their best. At SAP, we believe we are made stronger by the unique capabilities and qualities that each person brings to our company, and we invest in our employees to inspire confidence and help everyone realize their full potential. We ultimately believe in unleashing all talent and creating a better world.\n\nSAP is committed to the values of Equal Employment Opportunity and provides accessibility accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are interested in applying for employment with SAP and are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to Recruiting Operations Team: Careers@sap.com.\n\nFor SAP employees: Only permanent roles are eligible for the SAP Employee Referral Program, according to the eligibility rules set in the SAP Referral Policy. Specific conditions may apply for roles in Vocational Training.\n\nQualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to their age, race, religion, national origin, ethnicity, gender (including pregnancy, childbirth, et al), sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, protected veteran status, or disability, in compliance with applicable federal, state, and local legal requirements.\n\nSuccessful candidates might be required to undergo a background verification with an external vendor.\n\nAI Usage in the Recruitment Process\n\nFor information on the responsible use of AI in our recruitment process, please refer to our Guidelines for Ethical Usage of AI in the Recruiting Process.\n\nPlease note that any violation of these guidelines may result in disqualification from the hiring process.\n\nRequisition ID: 452326 | Work Area: Software-Design and Development | Expected Travel: 0 - 10% | Career Status: Student | Employment Type: Limited Part Time | Additional Locations: #LI-Hybrid','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'SAP','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=fef6dc33b40b237e','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2417,NULL,'job','Junior/Mid-Level Fullstack Developer (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','10178 Berlin',NULL,'',5000070000.00,'50.000 € – 70.000 € pro Jahr','Du willst nicht nur Tickets abarbeiten, sondern verstehen, wie ein Produkt wirklich funktioniert, von der Datenbank bis ins UI? Bei uns arbeitest du als Fullstack Developer mit TypeScript entlang des gesamten Stacks mit React, Nest.js und PostgreSQL und siehst direkt, welchen Impact dein Code hat.\n\nWir bauen keine überengineerten Konstrukte, sondern pragmatische, skalierbare Lösungen und suchen dafür jemanden, der Lust hat mitzudenken, sich weiterzuentwickeln und Schritt für Schritt mehr Verantwortung zu übernehmen.\n\n** Die Stelle ist mit einem hohen Onsite Fokus in Berlin auszuführen **\n\nAufgaben\nWeiterentwicklung und Gestaltung der Plattform für Energieberatung und Umsetzung energetischer Sanierungsmaßnahmen\nWeiterentwicklung der Portale für Kunden und Handwerker zur Vermittlung von Energieberatungen und Baumaßnahmen\nIntegration verschiedener Datenquellen wie CRM, Dokumentensysteme, Automatisierungstools\nQualifikation\nErste bis mehrjährige praktische Erfahrung in der Softwareentwicklung (z. B. durch Job, Praktika oder relevante Projekte)\nGrundlegende bis gute Kenntnisse in TypeScript sowie erste Erfahrung mit React und/oder Nest.js\nVerständnis von REST APIs und Webarchitekturen\nErste Berührungspunkte mit relationalen Datenbanken (idealerweise PostgreSQL)\nInteresse an sauberer Softwarearchitektur und modernen Entwicklungsprozessen\nLernbereitschaft, Eigeninitiative und Teamfähigkeit\n\nNice-to-have:\n\nErfahrung mit LLMs als Nutzer und API-Integration\nErfahrung mit Machine Learning (z.B. zur Bilderkennung, OCR, Dokumentenprüfung)\nErfahrung mit AWS (ECS, EKS, RDS, S3, SQS, Terraform), Kubernetes\nBenefits\nKleines Tech-Team: Du spielst eine zentrale Rolle innerhalb unseres Unternehmens.\nTop Büro in Berlin: zentrale Lage, moderne Ausstattung und besonderes Miteinander.\nTeam auf Augenhöhe: Bei uns zählt, was du bewegst.\nRabatte & Extras: Zugang zu attraktiven Mitarbeiterrabatten und Vorteilen.\nFeedbackkultur, die lebt: Wir sprechen ehrlich miteinander über das, was gut läuft und das, was besser werden kann.\nRegelmäßige Team-Events: Wir feiern Erfolge gemeinsam und nehmen uns Zeit fürs Miteinander.\n\nChris und Marcel sind leidenschaftliche Rennradfahrer und teilen ihre Begeisterung gern. Wenn du Lust hast, dir im Arbeitsalltag auch mal die ein oder andere Story dazu anzuhören, melde dich bei uns ;)','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'dsb Deutsche Sanierungsberatung GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=afcad51509e84fa0','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2418,NULL,'job','Werkstudent (Electronics and Machine Learning; Biotech)','Studentenjob','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Hiring a Werkstudent*in in Berlin.\n\nYou will work on a biomodulation project that involves establishing a fast feedback loop to image and modulate vasculature and training RL models on this data.\n\nThe scope of the project is understanding how to reverse vascular degeneration in humans; with a focus on reversing cognitive decline and neurodegeneration.\n\nTl;dr We’re trying to reverse aging.\n\nPay is 2k / month – work schedule is perfectly flexible, the effort is equivalent to a part time job.\n\nMainly aimed at students, but if you’re a genius NEET that got blackpilled on college and dropped out that’s also fine.\n\nYou need to know how to:\n\nSolder stuff\nRead the methodology section of a paper (or ask GPT to explain it)\nUse LLM tools to search the internet\nCode with Claude Code or Codex (knowing how to code “by hand” is a + but not required)\nSpeak English; German optional but it helps (5/5 ideal, but if you can do 3/5 that’s fine, you can apply)\n\nPerks:\n\nPerfectly flexible working hours (work whenever you want and however much you want; we only care about output – literally).\nWe cover transport, equipment, food, etc.\nConnections to a VC environment and a network of founders if you decide to work in the tech startup space afterwards.\nSmart people to advise you. If you need help, you will have a crazy old professor famous enough to have a Wikipedia page in any domain of your choice to act as advisor.\nOption to continue once you are done with your studies (or drop out) at rates much better than any DE corporation would offer (on this project, if it continues, or in one of our other companies).\n\nOur lab is in Buch (Berlin), easily accessible via the S2.\n\nIf you’re interested, email george@cerebralab.com with something about you (a list of projects, a personal website, a resume… whatever you think best represents you). The email should reflect why you meet the requirements listed above.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Cerebralab','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6f67c0829dee4ef5','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2419,NULL,'job','Wissenschaftliche/r Mitarbeiter/in im Innovations- und Kompetenzzentrum Künstliche Intelligenz (w/m/d)','Festanstellung','Amberg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Ab sofort ist an der Ostbayerischen Technischen Hochschule (OTH) Amberg-Weiden, Abt. Amberg, in der Fakultät Elektrotechnik, Medien und Informatik eine Vollzeitstelle als\n\nWissenschaftliche/r Mitarbeiter/in im Innovations- und Kompetenzzentrum Künstliche Intelligenz (w/m/d)\n\nbefristet zunächst auf 15 Monate mit Verlängerungsoption um weitere 21 Monate im Rahmen der Förderung des Projektes FORGE durch das bayerische Staatsministerium für Wissenschaft und Kultur zu besetzen. Es handelt sich bei FORGE („Foundation Models for Retrieval and Geometric Engineering“) um ein Teilprojekt des bayernweiten Initiative für ein multimodals KI-Basismodell.\n\nAufgabengebiete:\n\nErstellung eines offenen, multimodalen KI-Basismodels für das Ingenieurdesign\nKommunikation und Zusammenarbeit mit den Projektpartnern\nWissenschaftliche Publikation der Projektergebnisse\nErstellung von Proofs of Concept, Demonstratoren\nAnforderungen:\nAbgeschlossenes Hochschulstudium (Dipl.-Ing., M.Eng. oder M.Sc.) im Bereich Informatik / Künstliche Intelligenz\nGute praktische und theoretische Kenntnisse im Bereich Softwareentwicklung, Machine Learning/KI, beispielsweise mit Bildanalyse, Objekterkennung, generativen Verfahren, Large (Vision-)Language Models\nHohes Maß an Selbständigkeit, Eigenverantwortung und Leistungsbereitschaft\nProjektorientierter Arbeitsstil\nFähigkeit und Bereitschaft zum wissenschaftlichen Arbeiten\nWas wir Ihnen bieten:\nInteressante und abwechslungsreiche Tätigkeit, Mitwirkung in der Open Source-Community\nMöglichkeit zur Promotion im Rahmen des Projekts FORGE\nModerne Hardware- und Laborausstattung und Nutzung der OTH- und der bayernweiten KI-Hochleistungsrechner-Infrastruktur\nKollegiales Arbeitsklima\nBetriebliche Altersvorsorge sowie alle Sozialleistungen des öffentlichen Dienstes\n\nDas Beschäftigungsverhältnis richtet sich nach den Bestimmungen des Tarifvertrages für den öffentlichen Dienst der Länder (TV-L) und wird bei entsprechender Qualifikation max. in der Entgeltgruppe E13 vergütet und ist unbefristet.\n\nDie Hochschule fördert die berufliche Gleichstellung von Frauen und Männern und begrüßt, wenn Frauen sich bewerben. Schwerbehinderte werden bei im Wesentlichen gleicher Eignung, Befähigung und fachlicher Leistung bevorzugt eingestellt.\n\nBewerbungen mit aussagekräftigen Unterlagen (Anschreiben, Lebenslauf, Zeugnisse) sind bis spätestens 11.05.2026 über das Online-Formular einzureichen.\n\nBitte nehmen Sie in Ihrer Bewerbung Bezug auf die Bewerbungskennziffer 1992.\n\nKontakt Personalabteilung: Herr Josef Roth; E-Mail: j.roth@oth-aw.de\n\nKontakt Fachabteilung: Herr Prof. Dr. Ulrich Schäfer; E-Mail: u.schaefer@oth-aw.de\n\nDie OTH Amberg-Weiden ist eine junge Hochschule in der Mitte Europas, die ihren Studierenden in 55 Studiengängen eine zukunftsorientierte Ausbildung bietet. Über 4.300 Studierende werden in den beiden Hochschulstädten Amberg und Weiden von 118 Professorinnen und Professoren unterrichtet.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Ostbayerische Technische Hochschule Amberg-Weiden','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2a5646a416c3bd01','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2420,NULL,'job','Studienpraktikum zur Unterstützung der Weiterentwicklung von Python-Tools für die Auswertung von Signalen an elektrischen Kleinstmotoren','','Schönaich',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Entwicklungsbereich\nPraktikum\nStudierende\n\nWe create motion – Antriebssysteme von FAULHABER sind Meisterwerke der Fein- und Elektromechanik an der Grenze des technisch Machbaren. FAULHABER ist eine unabhängige, familiengeführte Unternehmensgruppe mit Stammsitz in Schönaich. Weltweit realisieren wir mit unseren über 2.300 Mitarbeitenden zukunftsweisende Lösungen für nahezu alle Märkte und Branchen, in denen Präzision und Zuverlässigkeit auf kleinstem Raum entscheidend sind, wie z. B. in der Luft- und Raumfahrt, Industrie, Robotik und der Medizin. Der Erfolg unserer Produkte beruht auf dem Einsatz unserer Mitarbeitenden - denn hinter jedem FAULHABER-Antrieb steckt der Antrieb unserer Mitarbeitenden. Bring uns mit deinem Antrieb weiter und werde Teil unseres Teams.\n\nWir bieten:\n\nBei der Entwicklung neuer Produkte, aber auch in der Produktion, werden an DC-Kleinstmotoren Signale erfasst und aufgezeichnet. Im Entwicklungsbereich werden diese Signale von Experten bewertet und helfen so den Erfolg von Entwicklungsschritten einzuschätzen. Oft ist eine vorherige Filterung oder Weiterverarbeitung hilfreich.\n\nZur besseren Auswertemöglichkeit der Signale arbeiten wir an Algorithmen und Tools, die bestimmte Eigenschaften oder Parameter in den Signalen ermitteln. Diese Tools werden in Python programmiert.\n\nZur Unterstützung bei der Entwicklung und Erprobung dieser Tools bieten wir eine Studienpraktikantenstelle an.\n\nEs besteht auch die Gelegenheit mit Hilfe von Künstlicher Intelligenz (Machine Learning) Auswertemöglichkeiten zu verbessern. Es stehen dazu bereits viele aufgezeichnete Signalkurven zur Verfügung.\n\nDu bietest:\n\nStudium mit Kenntnissen in Python-Programmierung\n\nBenefits:\nAttraktives Vergütungsangebot\nWertschätzendes Betriebsklima\nBetriebskantine\nMitarbeiterparkplatz\nBetriebsarzt\nMitarbeiterevents\nHomeoffice-Regelung\nIhr Ansprechpartner:\n\nJörg Maier\nDr. Fritz Faulhaber GmbH & Co. KG\nFaulhaberstraße 1 71101 Schönaich','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'DR. FRITZ FAULHABER GmbH & Co. KG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ca773762e52ac5de','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2421,NULL,'job','Duales Studium (B.Sc.) - Informatik mit Ausrichtung Künstliche Intelligenz (m/w/d)','Berufsausbildung','67061 Ludwigshafen am Rhein',NULL,'',1247.00,'Ab 1.247 € pro Monat','ELEMENTE DEINES DUALEN STUDIUMS\n\nDu bist von Artificial Intelligence fasziniert, hast schon selbstständig etwas programmiert und auch das Thema Programmiersprachen ist kein Neuland für dich? Zudem hast du in der Schule Spaß an Informatik und Mathematik? Du bist neugierig stets aktuelle Technologien zu erlernen und einzusetzen? Dann bist du in der Informatik mit Ausrichtung Künstliche Intelligenz richtig! Bewirb dich bei einem Unternehmen, das Zugang zu neuesten Technologien, Expertise und Inspirationen bietet und werde Teil eines kreativen Teams.\n\nDu arbeitest in einem modernen Arbeitsumfeld und bist vom ersten Tag an Teil eines dynamischen innovativen Teams. Wir geben dir die Möglichkeit, deine Ausbildung aktiv mitzugestalten: zum Beispiel bei der eigenen Auswahl der Praxisphasen wie Data Science, Mobile Apps, Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, Cyber Security, Cloud Computing und vielen mehr.\n\nDAS LERNST DU WÄHREND DEINES DUALEN STUDIUMS\nAuf dich wartet ein spannendes duales Studium in einem internationalen Unternehmen mit Fokus auf digitaler Transformation, digitalen Lösungen, Artificial Intelligence und den neuesten Technologien\nDu lernst, Computersysteme und Netzwerke, aber auch Anwendungen unter der Berücksichtigung sicherheitstechnischer und kaufmännischer Aspekte von Grund auf zu planen, zu installieren und zu betreiben\nDu erwirbst Kenntnisse in allen Bereichen der Informatik\nAuf dich warten attraktive Weiterbildungsangebote sowie einschlägige Schulungsangebote mit hoher Praxisrelevanz\nDu durchläufst individuell abgestimmte Praxisphasen und arbeitest an wertschöpfenden digitalen Projekten mit\nDAS BRINGST DU MIT\nallgemeine Hochschulreife\ngute Kenntnisse in Mathematik, Informatik\nausgeprägtes analytisches Denken und Spaß am Arbeiten mit Daten und Zahlen\nInteresse an Hard- & Software sowie Webentwicklung und Cyber Security\nBegeisterung für innovative Entwicklungen im IT-Umfeld\nhohe Zuverlässigkeit, sehr gute Kommunikationsfähigkeit, Eigeninitiative sowie Spaß an Teamarbeit\nDAS BIETEN WIR IN DEINEM DUALEN STUDIUM\nDuale Hochschule Baden-Württemberg (DHBW) in Mannheim als Kooperationspartner\nIndividuell ausgewählte Praxisphasen und Mitarbeit an aktuellen Projekten\nInnovative Schulungsangebote unserer AI Academy\nAdventure Teambuilding mit professionellen Coaches\nAttraktive Vergütung - du startest mit 1.247 Euro pro Monat im 1. Ausbildungsjahr\nZahlreiche Zusatzleistungen wie: Urlaubsgeld, freiwillige Erfolgsbeteiligung, Laptop, Büchergeld\nEssengeldzuschuss und kostenlose Getränke im Büro\n30 Tage Urlaub\n37,5 Stunden-Woche mit flexibler Arbeitszeit ab dem 1. Ausbildungsjahr\nHomeoffice ab dem 1. Ausbildungsjahr\nFreizeit- und Fitnessangebote sowie Teamevents\nAzubi WGs\nDUALES STUDIUM GESCHAFFT - WAS DANN ?\n\nAls Computerflüsterer:in und Datendenker:in startest du deine Karriere rund um das Thema IT. Du unterstützt unsere globalen Kunden bei der Entwicklung und Optimierung verschiedener Software- und Anwendungssysteme und wirst so zu einem unverzichtbaren Mitglied unseres Teams.\n\nWir haben das Netzwerk, jetzt müssen wir uns nur noch verbinden! Werde ein Teil der BASF Gruppe und kreiere mit uns IT-Lösungen für die Chemie.\n\nDEIN WEG ZU UNS: Richtig bewerben - so geht\'s!\n\nNeugierde, Offenheit und Motivation. Für uns steht deine Persönlichkeit im Vordergrund. Noten sind nicht alles. Im ersten Schritt des Auswahlverfahrens bleiben die Schulnoten daher erst einmal unberücksichtigt. Für uns ist der Gesamteindruck entscheidend.\n\nDaher LET\'S MATCH & BEWIRB DICH JETZT:\n\nBewerbungsstart: ab April 2026\n\nBewerbungsende: Es gibt keine Frist, du kannst dich bewerben solange Plätze frei sind!\n\nDIE FÜNF SCHRITTE UNSERES AUSWAHLVERFAHRENS:\n\n1. Online-Test von zu Hause aus\n\n2. Eignungstest vor Ort bei der BASF\n\n3. Vorstellungsgespräch oder Video-Interview\n\n4. ggf. werksärztliche Untersuchung\n\n5. Zusage und Vertrag\n\nDer gesamte Auswahlprozess bei BASF am Standort Ludwigshafen dauert ungefähr 50 Werktage bis zur Zusage.\n\nWir freuen uns auf deine Bewerbung!\n\nGerne kannst du uns direkt mit deiner Online - Bewerbung folgende Unterlagen hochladen:\n• Lebenslauf\n• deine letzten beiden Zeugnisse (bei ausländischen Zeugnissen inkl. amtlicher Anerkennung und beglaubigter Übersetzung)\n• das Zeugnis deines höchst erreichten Schulabschlusses\n\nKONTAKT\n\nWenn du Fragen hast, kannst du mich gern unter +49 30 200556107; yulia.haars@basf.com erreichen oder dir HIER einen Termin via MS Teams buchen.\n\nÜBER UNS\n\nWir bei BASF Digital Solutions machen die Digitalisierung der BASF möglich. Als deutsche Gruppengesellschaft der BASF mit Sitz in Ludwigshafen und Standorten wie Madrid, Schwarzheide beschäftigt die BASF Digital Solutions GmbH rund 1.700 Mitarbeiter. Digitalisierung ist einer der Schwerpunkte der neuen Unternehmensstrategie von BASF. In agilen Teams wollen wir neue digitale Lösungen einführen, die für unseren Kunden einen klaren Mehrwert darstellen.\n\nAlle relevanten Informationen zu deinem Einstieg bei uns findest du hier: https://on.basf.com/BDS\n\nVielfalt ist unsere größte Stärke!\n\nGestalte mit uns die Zukunft – in einem globalen Team, das Inklusion und Chancengleichheit unabhängig von Geschlecht, Alter, Herkunft, sexueller Orientierung, Behinderung oder Weltanschauung lebt.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'BASF Digital Solutions GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=0a7b522dfcf61d99','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2422,NULL,'job','Research Associate / Wissenschaftliche*r Mitarbeiter*in at the Institute of Circular Resource Engineering and Management','Vollzeit','21073 Hamburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Research Associate (m/f/d) -\nWissenschaftlicher Mitarbeiterin\n\nInstitute for Circular Remuneration according to guidelines of ID: 8026WV11 Start of employment: 01.09.2026 Application deadline 12.05.2026 Scope full time and fixed term until 31.08.2029\n\nThis PhD project aims to develop dynamic and multi-criteria impact assessment models for geothermal multi-resource extraction within the framework of the EU-funded MiningBrines Programme. The central objective is to evaluate the environmental, economic, and societal implications of simultaneously extracting geothermal energy, dissolved gases, and critical minerals from deep brine systems. A key goal is to move beyond conventional static life cycle assessment approaches by establishing dynamic modelling frameworks that account for evolving boundary conditions. These include climate change trajectories, energy system transitions, groundwater responses, biodiversity impacts, and regulatory developments. The project seeks to provide forward-looking, scenario-based tools that enable stakeholders to assess long-term system performance, trade-offs, and uncertainties over the lifetime of geothermal investments.\n\nThe project is expected to deliver a dynamic, scenario-based multi-criteria impact assessment framework tailored to geothermal multi-resource extraction systems. It will provide quantitative insights into long-term environmental, economic, and societal trade-offs under evolving external conditions.\n\nBy integrating machine learning, optimisation, and sustainability assessment into a decision support platform, the research will produce robust tools for responsible investment and policy-making.\n\nThe successful candidate will be part of the MiningBrines Marie Skłodowska-Curie Doctoral Network,\na European training program bringing together universities, research institutes, and industry partners.\n\nYOUR TASKS\n\nTo deliver a dynamic, scenario-based multi-criteria impact assessment framework tailored to geothermal multi-resource extraction systems\nTo provide quantitative insights into long-term environmental, economic, and societal trade-offs under evolving external conditions\nTo evaluate system performance under alternative future developments and policy contexts\nTo produce robust tools for responsible investment and policy-making\n\nYOUR PROFILE\n\nRequirements\n\nCompleted scientific university studies, in particular in the subject Environmental Engineering, Process Engineering or Chemical sciences\nEarly Stage Researcher (m/f/d) - must not obtain a doctoral degree\nDesired knowledge and personal skills\nStrong background in Life Cycle Assessment (LCA), environmental systems analysis, or sustainability assessment\nExperience with dynamic modelling approaches (e.g. time-dependent systems, scenario modelling, optimisation models)\nKnowledge of energy systems, resource recovery, carbon capture/storage or industrial process assessment\nProgramming skills (e.g. Python, MATLAB, R) for modelling, data processing and tool integration\nCapacity to work in interdisciplinary and international research environments\nOUR OFFER\nA job in an interesting, friendly and appreciative working environment\nJoining network-wide training schools and workshops\n\nELIGIBILITY CRITERIA\n\nResearchers recruited within the Doctoral Network must be Early Stage Researchers (ESRs) and must not have a doctoral degree. Additionaly, they must not have resided or carried out their main activity (work, studies, etc.) in the country of the recruiting organization (here: Germany) for more than 12 months in the 36 months immediately before recruitment date. Doctoral candidates funded by the Doctoral Networks can be of any nationality and should be enrolled in a doctoral programme leading to the award of a doctoral degree.\n\nAt the heart of TU Hamburg’s research, teaching and transfer of technology is the guiding principle of developing technology for people. The TU Hamburg sees itself in this context as a family-friendly and sustainable university with high performance and quality standards that strives for excellence in all its research fields. Interdisciplinarity, innovation, regionality and internationality are binding principles in our actions. With currently around 8.000 students, 110 professors and 1.650 employees, the TU Hamburg is characterised by short decision-making processes and close cooperation between the board, the institutes, the deans of studies, the research areas and the administration. We identify ourselves with a modern leadership culture and cultivate appreciative interaction.\nFor further information please contact Frau Dr. Ayah Alassali, Tel.-No. +49 40 30601 2438, Email: .\n\nWe value diversity, therefore all applications are welcome, regardless of gender, gender identity, ethnic origin, nationality, age, religion and belief, disability, sexual orientation and identity or social background.\n\nThe TU Hamburg stands for as well as\n\nPlease send your complete application documents (cover letter, curriculum vitae in table form, proof of completed training and/or university degree, job references or certificates of employment) via the online application system.\n\nNotice for graduates of foreign educational qualifications:\nPlease submit proof of all obtained university degrees and, if available, the recognition of your educational qualifications in Germany (e.g. anabin excerpts and/or acknowledgement of previous employers).','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Technische Universität Hamburg','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ac4328c0a36c4932','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2423,NULL,'job','Sr. Applied AI Engineer','Vollzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About The Role\n\nTaktile is redefining how financial institutions use AI to make critical decisions, and we\'re growing fast. As an Applied AI Engineer, you\'ll be at the heart of that transformation, building advanced agentic products that solve high-value problems. You will act as a product owner for the AI agents you create, turning them into reusable applications that solve concrete customer problems at scale in the financial crime or credit risk space.\n\nIf you\'re passionate about applying AI to real-world financial decisioning, stay current on advances in generative AI, and bring a solid foundation in Python, SQL, and working with APIs, you\'ll thrive here.\n\nWhat You\'ll Do as an Sr. Applied AI Engineer\n\nBuild Reusable AI Products: Act as the product owner for your application area. Design, develop, and deploy robust, repeatable Generative AI agents that serve as configurable solutions for our customers.\n\nDrive Scalable Value: Partner with Solution and Forward Deployed Engineers during critical sales and implementation projects to deeply understand customer needs. Develop standard templates and reusable components that reduce time-to-activation and solve core challenges.\n\nProduct Vision and Iteration: Synthesize customer feedback into a clear vision for your agents. Iterate on your solutions to solve concrete use cases at scale, treating every agent as a product itself.\n\nCollaborate with Core Product: Work closely with the core product team to prioritize platform features that unblock application development, and act as an expert user consultant during the development of new features.\n\nAbout You\n\nYou bring 3-6 years of data science, software engineering, consulting, or product management experience that includes customer-facing work or product ownership.\n\nYou have a strong technical or quantitative background, preferably in fields such as Computer Science, Mathematics, Software Engineering, Physics, Data Science, or Economics.\n\nYou are eager to dive into the domain of our customers, including credit underwriting, financial risk assessment, and financial crime detection.\n\nYou write clean, maintainable Python and SQL, and have a good understanding of REST APIs.\n\nYou excel at breaking down complex problems and abstracting them into scalable, reusable solutions.\n\nYou build strong relationships with both technical and business stakeholders at all levels, driven by a product-centric mindset to understand their needs and solve their challenges at scale.\n\nYou are open to a hybrid work model and can work from our London or Berlin office at least three days per week.\n\nIdeal Qualifications (but not required)\n\nYou have experience in building AI applications within financial services.\n\nYou have experience in applying and optimizing statistical and machine learning models to solve business problems.\n\nYou have experience with at least one of the major cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP).\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nWork with colleagues that lift you up, challenge you, celebrate you and help you grow. We come from many different backgrounds, but what we have in common is the desire to operate at the very top of our fields. If you are similarly capable, caring, and driven, you\'ll find yourself at home here.\n\nMake an impact and meaningfully shape an early-stage company.\n\nExperience a truly flat hierarchy and communicate directly with founding team members. Having an opinion and voicing your ideas is not only welcome but encouraged, especially when they challenge the status quo.\n\nLearn from experienced mentors and achieve tremendous personal and professional growth. Get to know and leverage our network of leading tech investors and advisors around the globe.\n\nReceive a top-of-market equity and cash compensation package.\n\nGet access to a self-development budget you can use to e.g. attend conferences, buy books or take classes.\n\nUse the equipment of your choice including meaningful home office set-up.\n\nOur Stance\n\nWe\'re eager to meet talented and driven candidates regardless of whether they tick all the boxes. We\'re looking for someone who will add to our culture, not just fit within it. We strongly encourage individuals from groups traditionally underestimated and underrepresented in tech to apply.\n\nWe seek to actively recognize and combat racism, sexism, ableism and ageism. We embrace and support all gender identities and expressions, and celebrate love in its many forms. We won\'t inquire about how you identify or if you\'ve experienced discrimination, but if you want to tell your story, we are all ears.\n\nAbout Us\n\nTaktile helps financial institutions make smarter, safer decisions with the power of AI. Our software gives teams the tools to automate complex decisions — like who to onboard, how to underwrite, or when to flag suspicious activity — with full visibility and control.\n\nBy combining AI with a rich ecosystem of financial data, Taktile enables companies to adapt their decision-making in real time as markets, customer behavior, and risks evolve.\n\nOur mission is to build the world’s leading platform for automated decision-making in financial services — setting the standard for how AI is applied responsibly and effectively in this industry.\n\nWe were founded by machine learning and data science experts with deep experience in financial services. Today, our team works across Berlin, London, and New York, bringing together engineers, entrepreneurs, and researchers from companies like Google, Amazon, and Meta, as well as fast-growing startups and enterprise leaders.\n\nBacked by top investors including Y Combinator, Index Ventures, Balderton Capital, and Tiger Global, along with the founders of Looker, GitHub, Mulesoft, Datadog, and UiPath - we’re building a world-class organization across all functions and levels to power the next generation of AI-driven decision-making in financial services.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Taktile','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=76591cfb6c0c5801','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2424,NULL,'job','Duales Studium (B.Sc.) - Data Science und Künstliche Intelligenz (m/w/d)','Berufsausbildung','67061 Ludwigshafen am Rhein',NULL,'',1247.00,'Ab 1.247 € pro Monat','ELEMENTE DEINES DUALEN STUDIUMS\n\nDu findest Artificial Intelligence spannend und möchtest an der Gestaltung neuer Prozesse und Technologien mitwirken? Wenn du in der Schule Spaß an Informatik, Mathematik und wirtschaftlichen Zusammenhängen hast dann bist du bei Data Science und Künstliche Intelligenz richtig! Bewirb dich bei einem Unternehmen, das Zugang zu neuesten Technologien, Expertise und Inspirationen bietet.\n\nDu arbeitest in einem modernen Arbeitsumfeld und bist vom ersten Tag an Teil eines dynamischen innovativen Teams. Wir geben dir die Möglichkeit, deine Ausbildung aktiv mitzugestalten: zum Beispiel bei der eigenen Auswahl der Praxisphasen wie Data Science, Mobile Apps, Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, Cyber Security, Cloud Computing und vielen mehr.\n\nDAS LERNST DU WÄHREND DEINES DUALEN STUDIUMS\nAuf dich wartet ein spannendes duales Studium in einem internationalen Unternehmen mit Fokus auf digitaler Transformation, digitalen Lösungen, Artificial Intelligence und den neuesten Technologien.\nDu durchläufst individuell abgestimmte Praxisphasen und arbeitest an wertschöpfenden digitalen Projekten mit.\nAuf dich warten attraktive Weiterbildungsangebote sowie einschlägige Schulungsangebote mit hoher Praxisrelevanz.\nDu erfährst einen spannenden Mix aus Informatik, Mathematik, Statistik und domänenspezifischen Wissen, um Daten effizient analysieren, daraus Wissen gewinnen und intelligente Anwendungen entwickeln zu können.\nDAS BRINGST DU MIT\nallgemeine Hochschulreife\nsehr gute bis gute Mathe- und Englischkenntnisse\nBegeisterung für Informatik und aktuelle IT-Themen sowie für wirtschaftliche Zusammenhänge\nHohe Zuverlässigkeit, Verantwortungsbewusstsein, sehr gute Kommunikationsfähigkeit und Eigeninitiative\nAnalytisches Denken und Interesse an Daten und Zahlen\nSpaß am Arbeiten in internationalen Projektteams und bei der Beratung in- und externer Kunden und Geschäftspartner:innen\nDAS BIETEN WIR IN DEINEM DUALEN STUDIUM\nDuale Hochschule Baden-Württemberg (DHBW) in Mannheim als Kooperationspartner\nIndividuell ausgewählte Praxisphasen und Mitarbeit an aktuellen Projekten\nInnovative Schulungsangebote unserer AI Academy\nAdventure Teambuilding mit professionellen Coaches\nAttraktive Vergütung - du startest mit 1.247 Euro pro Monat im 1. Ausbildungsjahr\nZahlreiche Zusatzleistungen wie: Urlaubsgeld, freiwillige Erfolgsbeteiligung, Laptop, Büchergeld\nEssengeldzuschuss und kostenlose Getränke im Büro\n30 Tage Urlaub\n37,5 Stunden-Woche mit flexibler Arbeitszeit ab dem 1. Ausbildungsjahr\nHomeoffice ab dem 1. Ausbildungsjahr\nFreizeit- und Fitnessangebote sowie Teamevents\nAzubi WGs\nDUALES STUDIUM GESCHAFFT - WAS DANN ?\n\nAls Computerflüsterer:in und Datendenker:in startest du deine Karriere rund um das Thema IT. Du unterstützt unsere globalen Kunden bei der Entwicklung und Optimierung verschiedener Software- und Anwendungssysteme und wirst so zu einem unverzichtbaren Mitglied unseres Teams.\n\nWir haben das Netzwerk, jetzt müssen wir uns nur noch verbinden! Werde ein Teil der BASF Gruppe und kreiere mit uns IT-Lösungen für die Chemie.\n\nDEIN WEG ZU UNS: Richtig bewerben - so geht\'s!\n\nNeugierde, Offenheit und Motivation. Für uns steht deine Persönlichkeit im Vordergrund. Noten sind nicht alles. Im ersten Schritt des Auswahlverfahrens bleiben die Schulnoten daher erst einmal unberücksichtigt. Für uns ist der Gesamteindruck entscheidend.\n\nDaher LET\'S MATCH & BEWIRB DICH JETZT:\n\nBewerbungsstart: ab Anfang April 2026\n\nBewerbungsende: Es gibt keine Frist, du kannst dich bewerben solange Plätze frei sind!\n\nDIE FÜNF SCHRITTE UNSERES AUSWAHLVERFAHRENS:\n\n1. Online-Test von zu Hause aus\n\n2. Eignungstest vor Ort bei der BASF\n\n3. Vorstellungsgespräch oder Video-Interview\n\n4. ggf. werksärztliche Untersuchung\n\n5. Zusage und Vertrag\n\nDer gesamte Auswahlprozess bei BASF am Standort Ludwigshafen dauert ungefähr 50 Werktage bis zur Zusage.\n\nWir freuen uns auf deine Bewerbung!\n\nGerne kannst du uns direkt mit deiner Online - Bewerbung folgende Unterlagen hochladen:\n• Lebenslauf\n• deine letzten beiden Zeugnisse (bei ausländischen Zeugnissen inkl. amtlicher Anerkennung und beglaubigter Übersetzung)\n• das Zeugnis deines höchst erreichten Schulabschlusses\n\nKONTAKT\n\nWenn du Fragen hast, kannst du mich gern unter +49 30 200556107; yulia.haars@basf.com erreichen oder dir HIER einen Termin via MS Teams buchen\n\nÜBER UNS\n\nWir bei BASF Digital Solutions machen die Digitalisierung der BASF möglich. Als deutsche Gruppengesellschaft der BASF mit Sitz in Ludwigshafen und Standorten wie Madrid, Schwarzheide beschäftigt die BASF Digital Solutions GmbH rund 1.700 Mitarbeiter. Digitalisierung ist einer der Schwerpunkte der neuen Unternehmensstrategie von BASF. In agilen Teams wollen wir neue digitale Lösungen einführen, die für unseren Kunden einen klaren Mehrwert darstellen.\n\nAlle relevanten Informationen zu deinem Einstieg bei uns findest du hier: https://on.basf.com/BDS\n\nVielfalt ist unsere größte Stärke!\n\nGestalte mit uns die Zukunft – in einem globalen Team, das Inklusion und Chancengleichheit unabhängig von Geschlecht, Alter, Herkunft, sexueller Orientierung, Behinderung oder Weltanschauung lebt.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'BASF Digital Solutions GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=36e851dbe7991c82','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2425,NULL,'job','Senior Product Manager - Search & Sort (all genders)','Festanstellung','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job Description\nTeam: Product Management\nJob Location: Berlin, Germany, Málaga, Spain, Munich, Germany\nPosition Type: Permanent, Full-time\nWork Flexibility: Hybrid, Onsite\n\nAt BESTSECRET, Search & Sort is evolving from a transactional tool into an intelligent, intent-driven discovery experience. As a Senior Product Manager, you will play a pivotal role in transforming how millions of customers across Europe explore and discover products—leveraging semantic search, dynamic ranking, and personalization at scale.\nThis is a high-impact opportunity to own strategy and execution end-to-end, working at the intersection of search, machine learning, and customer experience. You’ll collaborate with top-tier engineers and data scientists to build systems that directly drive business growth, contributing to a domain responsible for a significant share of company revenue.\n\nYour Responsibilities\n\nDefine and execute the product vision and roadmap for Search & Sort, covering query understanding, semantic retrieval, ranking, and result presentation\n\nLead the evolution from rule-based sorting to dynamic, context-aware ranking driven by user intent and market signals\n\nDrive technical product decisions across NLP, information retrieval, embeddings, and LLM-based approaches\n\nCollaborate cross-functionally with engineering, data science, and analytics teams to deliver scalable, high-impact solutions\n\nOwn and optimize key discovery and business KPIs (relevance, conversion, personalization, revenue impact)\n\nMentor and support other product managers, contributing to product excellence and best practices across the organization\n\nYour Qualifications\n\n5+ years of experience in product management, delivering customer-facing digital products with measurable impact\n\n2+ years working on search, ranking, or recommendation systems (e.g., semantic search, embeddings, re-ranking)\n\nStrong understanding of search architecture, NLP, and information retrieval systems; experience with LLMs is a plus\n\nSolid technical background in computer science, machine learning, data science, or software engineering\n\nProven ability to lead complex initiatives in cross-functional, matrix environments\n\nStrong communication skills with the ability to translate between technical, business, and customer perspectives\n\n#LI-MT1, #LI-HybridMalaga; #LI-HybridMunich; #LI-HybridBerlin','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Best Secret GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=cb131868a819464d','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2426,NULL,'job','Technische Projektleitung (m/w/d)','Festanstellung','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Office\nMünchen\nAbteilung\nSIRIUS (PSO)\nEmployment type\npermanent\nExperience\nGeplante Vorgänge\nfull-time\nSeniority\nexperienced\nDeine Aufgaben\nErstellung und Pflege von Architekturmodellen und -diagrammen\nDefinition von Systemarchitektur, Definition und Identifikation von Schnittstellen\nEvaluierung und Auswahl geeigneter Technologien und Frameworks\nSicherstellung der Einhaltung von Best Practices und Standards\nAktualisierung technischer Spezifikationen und Designrichtlinien\nBereitstellung von Berichten und Präsentationen für Stakeholdern\nDein Profil\nExpertise in der Konzeption und Implementierung von Microservices- Architekturen\nTiefgehende Kenntnisse in einer oder mehreren Programmiersprachen wie Java, Python, Node.js oder ähnlichen\nErfahrung mit Backend-Frameworks wie Spring Boot, Django, Flask, FastAPI, Express.js oder ähnlichen\nFundierte Kenntnisse in der Arbeit mit relationalen und NoSQL-Datenbanken\nVerständnis für Sicherheitsaspekte in der Backend- und Frontend-Entwicklung und Implementierung von Sicherheitsmaßnahmen\nErfahrung in der Entwicklung von RESTful APIs und Anwendung von API-Design-Prinzipien\nKenntnisse in der Optimierung von Webanwendungen für eine verbesserte Ladezeit und Benutzererfahrung\nTeamfähigkeit und Hands-on-Mentalität\nFließend in Deutsch oder Englisch\nBereitschaft zur Sicherheitsüberprüfung gem. §10 SÜG („Ü3“)\nWarum wir?\nUnser eigener Best-of-Breed IntraFind Technologie Stack (Java, Ansible, JavaScript, ElasticSearch, ...)\nState-of-the-Art Technologien rund um SaaS-Produkte (Docker, Kubernetes, …)\nModerne Artificial Intelligence und Machine Learning Verfahren für Content Analytics\nCutting-Edge Technologien zum Suchen und Finden von Informationen in Big Data\nEin agiles und wachsendes Team mit über 60 motivierten Kollegen\nWir sind gründergeführt und eigenfinanziert und leben ein sehr familiäres aber professionelles Miteinander\nWir sind seit über 20 Jahren auf dem Markt und marktführend im Bereich Enterprise Search und Insight Engines','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'IntraFind Software AG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=450b92879aefa93c','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2427,NULL,'job','Softwarearchitekt (m/w/d)','Festanstellung','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Office\nMünchen\nAbteilung\nSIRIUS (PSO)\nEmployment type\npermanent\nExperience\n2-5\nGeplante Vorgänge\nfull-time\nSeniority\nexperienced\nDeine Aufgaben\nEntwicklung, Anpassung und Integration von KI-basierten Softwarekomponenten\nImplementierung und Optimierung von RAG-Ansätze unter Nutzung von LLMs und Vektor-Datenbanken\nKonzeption, Entwicklung und Orchestrierung von KI-Agenten, einschließlich Tool-Anbindung und Workflow-Steuerung\nUmsetzung von Schnittstellen- und Integrationslösungen, insbesondere unter Nutzung von Model Context Protocol (MCP)\nErstellung von Dokumentationen zu Architektur, Implementierung und Nutzung von KI-Verfahren\nWissenstransfer und Unterstützung des AG bei Betrieb und Weiterentwicklung\nDein Profil\nMehrjährige Erfahrung in der Software-Entwicklung (z.B. Python)\nFundierte Kenntnisse im Umgang mit Large Language Models (LLM)\nPraxiserfahrung im Design und der Umsetzung von Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG)\nErfahrung im Einsatz und Betrieb von Vektor-Datenbanken\nErfahrung in der Anwendung und Integration von Model Context Protocol (MCP)\nErfahrung in der Konzeption und Implementierung von KI-Agenten\nFähigkeit zur Erstellung technischer Dokumentationen\nWünschenswerte Qualifikationen wie Erfahrung mit Cloud-Plattformen (AWS, Azure, GCP), in MLOps und Deployment, mit Container-Technologien (Docker, Kubernetes) und mit Datensicherheit und Compliance-Regelungen in KI-Systemen\nTeamfähigkeit und Hands-on-Mentalität\nFließend in Deutsch oder Englisch\nBereitschaft zur Sicherheitsüberprüfung gem. §10 SÜG („Ü3“)\nWarum wir?\nUnser eigener Best-of-Breed IntraFind Technologie Stack (Java, Ansible, JavaScript, ElasticSearch, ...)\nState-of-the-Art Technologien rund um SaaS-Produkte (Docker, Kubernetes, …)\nModerne Artificial Intelligence und Machine Learning Verfahren für Content Analytics\nCutting-Edge Technologien zum Suchen und Finden von Informationen in Big Data\nEin agiles und wachsendes Team mit über 60 motivierten Kollegen\nWir sind gründergeführt und eigenfinanziert und leben ein sehr familiäres aber professionelles Miteinander\nWir sind seit über 20 Jahren auf dem Markt und marktführend im Bereich Enterprise Search und Insight Engines','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'IntraFind Software AG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ba1c34c60d9dc042','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2428,NULL,'job','Ingenieur/in (w/m/d) - Analyse und Optimierung von Festkörperbatterien','Teilzeit','Ulm',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Kennziffer: 4886\nArbeitsort: Ulm\nEintrittsdatum: 01.07.2026\nKarrierestufe: Promotion\nBeschäftigungsgrad: Teilzeit, Vollzeit\nDauer der Beschäftigung: 3 Jahre\n\nVergütung: Die Vergütung erfolgt gemäß der jeweils geltenden Tarifverträge des öffentlichen Dienstes (Bund).\n\nSteige ein in die faszinierende Welt des Deutschen Zentrums für Luft- und Raumfahrt e. V. (DLR), um mit Forschung und Innovation die Zukunft mitzugestalten! Mit dem Know-how und der Neugier unserer rund 12.000 Mitarbeitenden aus 100 Nationen sowie unserer einzigartigen Infrastruktur bieten wir ein spannendes und inspirierendes Arbeitsumfeld. Gemeinsam entwickeln wir nachhaltige Technologien und tragen so zur Lösung globaler Herausforderungen bei. Möchtest du diese große Zukunftsaufgabe mit uns zusammen angehen? Dann ist dein Platz bei uns!\n\nKennziffer: 4886\nArbeitsort: Ulm\nEintrittsdatum: 01.07.2026\nKarrierestufe: Promotion\nBeschäftigungsgrad: Teilzeit; Vollzeit\nDauer der Beschäftigung: 3 Jahre\nVergütung: Die Vergütung erfolgt gemäß der jeweils geltenden Tarifverträge des öffentlichen Dienstes (Bund).\n\nKurzbeschreibung Institut/Einrichtung - Am Institut für Technische Thermodynamik entwickeln wir die Energiespeicher der Zukunft.\n\nDie Abteilung für Computergestützte Elektrochemie erforscht am Standort Helmholtz-Institut Ulm für elektrochemische Energiespeicherung (HIU) neue Theorien und Werkzeuge zur Simulation von Batteriematerialien und -zellen. Als Mitglied eines international führenden Forschungsteams im Bereich der Batteriesimulation leistest du zusammen mit unseren Partnern aus Industrie und Wissenschaft einen wichtigen Beitrag zum Verständnis und der Optimierung dieser Schlüsseltechnologien. Wir bieten damit eine attraktive Umgebung zur Durchführung internationaler Spitzenforschung mit Möglichkeit zur Promotion.\n\nDeine Aufgaben\n\nEntwicklung und Erforschung Machine Learning gestützter Workflows zur Generierung digitaler Zwilling von Elektrodenmaterialien und virtueller Analyse von Alterungsmechanismen über physikalisch-chemische Modelle\nVorhersage von Versagensmustern und Kapazitätsverlust mit Hilfe physikalisch-informierter Machine Learning Ansätze\nOptimierung von Material- und Elektrodenkonzepten für Festkörperbatterien\nMitarbeit an Projekten zur Untersuchung, Optimierung und Validierung der Ansätze in Festkörperbatterien\nVorstellung der Ergebnisse auf Konferenzen und Publikation in wissenschaftlichen Fachzeitschriften\n\nDas bringst Du mit\n\nAbgeschlossenes wissenschaftliches Hochschulstudium (Master / Diplom Uni) der der Ingenieurswissenschaften (z.B. aus den Bereichen Maschinenbau, Verfahrenstechnik, Energietechnik, Luft- und Raumfahrt), Naturwissenschaften (z. B. Fachrichtung Chemie, Physik) oder andere für die Tätigkeit relevanten Studiengänge\nFachkenntnisse im Bereich elektrochemischer Energiespeicher, Modellierung und Simulation, Machine Learning oder verwandter Wissensbereiche\nErste Erfahrungen in der Implementierung von elektrochemischen Modellen in Werkzeugen für wissenschaftliches Rechnen\nErste Erfahrungen in Machine Learning Ansätzen für Datenanalyse\n\nDas bieten wir dir\n\nDas DLR steht für Vielfalt, Wertschätzung und Gleichstellung aller Menschen. Wir fördern eigenverantwortliches Arbeiten und die individuelle Weiterentwicklung unserer Mitarbeitenden im persönlichen und beruflichen Umfeld. Dafür stehen dir unsere zahlreichen Fort- und Weiterbildungsmöglichkeiten zur Verfügung. Chancengerechtigkeit ist uns ein besonderes Anliegen, wir möchten daher insbesondere den Anteil von Frauen in der Wissenschaft und Führung erhöhen. Bewerbungen schwerbehinderter Menschen bevorzugen wir bei fachlicher Eignung.\n\nDas bieten wir dir\nDas DLR steht für Vielfalt, Wertschätzung und Gleichstellung aller Menschen. Wir fördern eigenverantwortliches Arbeiten und die individuelle Weiterentwicklung unserer Mitarbeitenden im persönlichen und beruflichen Umfeld. Dafür stehen dir unsere zahlreichen Fort- und Weiterbildungsmöglichkeiten zur Verfügung. Chancengerechtigkeit ist uns ein besonderes Anliegen, wir möchten daher insbesondere den Anteil von Frauen in der Wissenschaft und Führung erhöhen. Bewerbungen schwerbehinderter Menschen bevorzugen wir bei fachlicher Eignung.\n\nWir freuen uns darauf, dich kennenzulernen!\n\nFragen zu dieser Position ( Kennziffer 4886 ) beantwortet dir gerne:\n\nDr. Timo Danner\nTel.: +49 711 6862 8218','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Deutsches Zentrum für Luft- und Raumfahrt e. V. (DLR)','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9c8b4b8b645ebf04','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2429,NULL,'job','Data Scientist','','München',NULL,'',6000080000.00,'60.000 € – 80.000 € pro Jahr','with excellent German (C1) and English skills\n\n(all genders)\n\nLocation:\n\nGermany\n\nMunich\nFrankfurt\nHamburg\nShaping the Digital Future\n\nAt DEVnet, we are an open-minded, international team distinguished by human values, an inspiring team spirit, and a desire to grow alongside our clients. Driven by our passion for technology and our industry expertise, we develop solutions that drive innovation using data, analytics, and technology.\n\nOur 150 experts across four different locations combine technological know-how and industry knowledge with an understanding of the needs of all stakeholders. This is how we develop sustainable solutions for a data-driven world.\n\nYour impact\n\nAs a consultant, you will realize international Data Science and Data Analytics projects\nYou face exciting challenges in Advanced Analytics & Machine Learning\nYou establish and develop our data science community and the area of Data analytics\nYou develop customer relationships autonomously and proactively\nYou manage your network in the data science community\n\nNot sure whether the position is right for you? We\'re happy to connect you directly with our Data Science colleagues.\n\nYour profile\nYou have a degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Mathematics, Physics, Statistics, or similar fields\nYou are fluent in both German and English\nYou have at least 3 years of experience in Data Science\nYou have ideally professional experience in IT consulting\nYou have experience in using programming languages such as Python or R\nYou feel confident in using mathematical methods\nYou are experienced in development and operationalization of models in Statistics or Machine Learning or GenAI\nYou are familiar with containerization and cloud technologies\nYou enjoy organizing, preparing and analyzing data\nYou have strong communication skills and enjoy presenting results to stakeholders\nYou have knowledge of various data architectures and technical solution concepts\nYou are familiar with handling large and (un)structured data\nYou are flexible to work in various projects and are willing to travel\nYou are enthusiastic for new professional, technical, and industry-specific topics\nOur offer\nWe are a financially stable and independent company, offering you a secure job in a forward-thinking industry\nWe foster a culture of informality and an open, appreciative work environment with various nationalities\nYou benefit from individual guidance and professional mentoring\nYou become part of a dedicated, international team in a familiar atmosphere\nYou are part of a team that embraces teamwork, creativity, and personal responsibility\nWe provide internal and external training opportunities tailored to your individual development budget\nEvery one of us participates in training in “Nonviolent Communication“. You can also further develop your skills in this area\nWe offer you an attractive salary and profit-sharing model (Target salary: € 60,000 – € 80,000 per year, including profit share, depending on qualifications and seniority level)\nYou will work in beautiful, modern, and centrally located offices in Munich, Frankfurt, or Hamburg\nWe regularly host team and company events at our locations\nYou have the opportunity for a mix of onsite and remote work\nYou have 30 days of vacation and additional special leave options\nYou have the opportunity to participate in various internal initiatives and topic\n\nWe are committed to preventing all forms of discrimination, ensuring that everyone has equal opportunities, valuing every opinion and experience in our company, and fostering an inclusive culture where you can fully contribute at work.\n\nWe value our diversity and recognize that our success depends on different perspectives and experiences working towards common goals and a common purpose.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'DEVnet Holding','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b9b1958315f15e2e','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2430,NULL,'job','Software-Entwickler (m/w/d) mit Schwerpunkt auf KI-Technologien','Festanstellung','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Office\nMünchen\nAbteilung\nSIRIUS (PSO)\nEmployment type\npermanent\nExperience\n2-5\nGeplante Vorgänge\nfull-time\nSeniority\nentry-level\nDeine Aufgaben\nKonzeption und Umsetzung responsiver Benutzeroberflächen für Web-Applikationen\nEntwicklung von UI-Komponenten mit modernen JavaScript-Frameworks (z.B. Vue.js)\nOptimierung von Ladezeiten und Web-Performance\nSicherstellung der Skalierbarkeit und Performance der Frontend-Systeme in einer Cloud-Umgebung\nUmsetzung von Software-Tests unter Nutzung gängiger Frameworks für Unit- und Integrationstests\nErstellung und Pflege technischer Dokumentationen\nAktualisierung technischer Spezifikationen\nCode-Dokumentation zur verbesserten Wartbarkeit\nBenutzeranleitungen und Entwicklerhandbücher\nDein Profil\nExzellente Kenntnisse in HTML, CSS und JavaScript sowie praktische Erfahrungen mit modernen Frameworks (React, Angular, Vue.js)\nUmfangreiche Erfahrung in der Gestaltung von responsiven UI für unterschiedliche Endgeräte\nSicherer Umgang mit Webpack, npm bzw. Yarn\nGrundverständnis von UI/UX-Prinzipien und Zusammenarbeit mit Design-Teams; Umsetzung von Designs via CSS\nVersionskontrollsysteme wie Git\nErfahrung in Unit- und Integration-Tests\nKenntnisse zur Optimierung von Ladezeiten und zur Sicherheitsaspekten im Frontend\nTeamfähigkeit und Hands-on-Mentalität\nFließend in Deutsch oder Englisch\nBereitschaft zur Sicherheitsüberprüfung gem. §10 SÜG („Ü3“)\nWarum wir?\nUnser eigener Best-of-Breed IntraFind Technologie Stack (Java, Ansible, JavaScript, ElasticSearch, ...)\nState-of-the-Art Technologien rund um SaaS-Produkte (Docker, Kubernetes, …)\nModerne Artificial Intelligence und Machine Learning Verfahren für Content Analytics\nCutting-Edge Technologien zum Suchen und Finden von Informationen in Big Data\nEin agiles und wachsendes Team mit über 60 motivierten Kollegen\nWir sind gründergeführt und eigenfinanziert und leben ein sehr familiäres aber professionelles Miteinander\nWir sind seit über 20 Jahren auf dem Markt und marktführend im Bereich Enterprise Search und Insight Engines','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'IntraFind Software AG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a7106ea21cbc5699','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2431,NULL,'job','Frontend-Entwickler (m/w/d)','Festanstellung','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Office\nMünchen\nAbteilung\nSIRIUS (PSO)\nEmployment type\npermanent\nExperience\n2-5\nGeplante Vorgänge\nfull-time\nSeniority\nexperienced\nDeine Aufgaben\nBackend-Entwicklung unter Verwendung gängiger Technologien und Frameworks wie Java, Python oder Node.js\nDesign und Implementierung von RESTful APIs\nIntegration und Implementierung von Datenbanken (relational und NoSQL)\nEntwicklung von Microservices\nSicherstellung der Skalierbarkeit und Performance der Backend-Systeme in einer Cloud-Umgebung\nUmsetzung von Software-Tests unter Nutzung gängiger Frameworks für Unit- und Integrationstests\nDein Profil\nErfahrung im Umgang mit Programmiersprachen wie Java, Python oder Node.js\nErfahrung mit RESTful APIs und Microservices\nDatenbanken (relational und NoSQL)\nVersionskontrollsysteme wie Git\nKenntnisse in DevOps-Praktiken und Tools wie Docker und Kubernetes\nErfahrungen mit Cloud- Infrastrukturen und Skalierbarkeit\nTeamfähigkeit und Hands-on-Mentalität\nFließend in Deutsch oder Englisch\nBereitschaft zur Sicherheitsüberprüfung gem. §10 SÜG („Ü3“)\nWarum wir?\nUnser eigener Best-of-Breed IntraFind Technologie Stack (Java, Ansible, JavaScript, ElasticSearch, ...)\nState-of-the-Art Technologien rund um SaaS-Produkte (Docker, Kubernetes, …)\nModerne Artificial Intelligence und Machine Learning Verfahren für Content Analytics\nCutting-Edge Technologien zum Suchen und Finden von Informationen in Big Data\nEin agiles und wachsendes Team mit über 60 motivierten Kollegen\nWir sind gründergeführt und eigenfinanziert und leben ein sehr familiäres aber professionelles Miteinander\nWir sind seit über 20 Jahren auf dem Markt und marktführend im Bereich Enterprise Search und Insight Engines','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'IntraFind Software AG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=855833c42c113d1a','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2432,NULL,'job','Bioinformatiker','Vollzeit','Dresden',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Bioinformatiker\nJob-ID: 21174\nDKMS Life Science Lab gGmbH\n\nDresden, DE\n\nA good job can make a huge difference. With us, even a second chance at life!\nAs a leading international non-profit organization in the fight against blood cancer, our goal is to give as many blood cancer patients as possible a second chance at life and to provide access to stem cell transplants. In order to help even more patients, we need regular reinforcements from committed and highly qualified staff members with personality. In a worldwide network of around 1,600 DKMS colleagues, we would like to continue working towards this goal together with you and over 13.0 million registered donors.\nThe DKMS Life Science Lab gGmbH in Dresden carries out the molecular typing of the HLA characteristics of all DKMS donors in the fight against blood cancer and is the world\'s largest HLA tissue typing laboratory. Our laboratory, which is accredited according to international guidelines, sequences more than one million samples provided by DKMS donors every year. Our success builds on continuous research, aiming at taking advantage of the latest innovations in molecular biology and next generation sequencing and adapting those to the field of immunogenetics.\n\nThe Bioinformatics department at DKMS Life Science Lab gGmbH focuses on the analysis and integration of complex biological data, the development of computer-assisted methods for genotyping, and the design, implementation, and operation of complex software systems and analysis pipelines. We are now seeking a highly skilled and motivated individual to join our team as a Bioinformatician (m/f/d) in a full-time and permanent position.\n\nYOUR RESPONSIBILITIES:\n• Develop and implement software solutions for the processing, analysis, and interpretation of data from routine workflows and research projects\n• Create algorithms for genotyping, characterization, and quantification of relevant molecular markers\n• Design and optimize data analysis pipelines for Illumina and ONT sequencing data\n• Apply data science and machine learning techniques to optimize data-driven procedures\n• Process, systematize, and transform high-throughput biological data in containerized HPC and CI/CD environments\n• Collaborate with internal teams and external partners on scientific projects\n• Support users and other departments in solving bioinformatics problems\n• Document processes, interpret results, and create user-friendly interfaces for bioinformatics Tools\n\nOUR REQUIREMENTS:\n• Master\'s degree in Bioinformatics, Computational Biology, or a related field (Biology, Computer Science with biological focus)\n• Strong programming skills in R and/or Python\n• Experience with NGS and long-read sequence data analysis and genomic data processing\n• Knowledge of statistical methods and data visualization techniques\n• Familiarity with Linux/Unix-based operating systems and shell scripting\n• Experience with version control systems (Git) and familiarity with CI/CD pipelines\n• Understanding of containerization concepts and experience in HPC environments as well as molecular biology principles, preferably in the field of immunogenetics\n• Experience with population genomics and/or machine learning is a plus\n• Good language skills in English and German (written and spoken)\n• Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities in combination with excellent communication and teamwork skills\n\nWHAT WE OFFER\n• A meaningful job that gives people a second chance at life\n• A culture of appreciation and a collegial working environment\n• Flexible working hours with the option of partial remote work (up to 125 days per year)\n• An attractive compensation package including benefits such as employee savings plans and company pension schemes\n• 30 days of vacation per year; additional special leave for personal events\n• Sabbatical option\n• Comprehensive professional development and training opportunities\n• Free fruit, water, coffee, and tea\n• Diverse and interesting workplace health management programs (e.g., company bike scheme, health courses in cooperation with a major health insurance provider, etc.)\n• Employee benefits as part of our corporate benefits program\n\nDKMS is an ambitious organization that actively takes on challenges. Our employees are highly qualified and motivated. We look forward to receiving your online application!\n\nApply now: dkms.de/karriere\n\nDKMS Life Science Lab gGmbH\n\nSt. Petersburger Str. 2, 01069 Dresden\ndkms-lab.de','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'DKMS Group gGmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f03650a451323e20','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2433,NULL,'job','AI Engineer / Data Scientist (mwd) – Machine Learning & Generative AI','Teilzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Berlin\ndeutschlandweit/remote\nDüsseldorf\nHeidelberg\nUlm\nBerufserfahrung\nVoll/Teilzeit\nSeit über 35 Jahren unterstützen wir Unternehmen dabei, aus Daten echten Mehrwert zu schaffen. Dafür entwickeln wir maßgeschneiderte Daten-, KI- und Softwarelösungen und begleiten unsere Kunden als spezialisierter Boutique-Dienstleister entlang der gesamten Data-to-Value-Journey – von der ersten Idee bis zur produktiven Anwendung. In unseren Projekten verbinden wir Data Engineering, Machine Learning, Generative AI und Software Engineering mit fundiertem Branchenverständnis sowie methodischer Klarheit. Mit über 170 Mitarbeitenden arbeiten wir an anspruchsvollen Projekten in Branchen wie Life Science, Finance und Manufacturing und entwickeln gemeinsam nachhaltige Lösungen.\n\nAls AI Engineer / Data Scientist (mwd) arbeitest du im Team an praxisnahen GenAI-, Machine-Learning- und Data-Science-Lösungen. In Zusammenarbeit mit unseren Kunden entwickelst du Anwendungen, die Geschäfts- und Produktionsprozesse nachhaltig verbessern und echten Mehrwert schaffen.\nDas sind deine Aufgaben\nEntwicklung und Weiterentwicklung von Machine-Learning- und Generative-AI-Lösungen (z. B. mit Python, modernen AI/ML-Frameworks und LLMs) unter Einsatz moderner, AI-gestützter Entwicklungswerkzeuge\nAnalyse fachlicher und technischer Anforderungen sowie Übersetzung in umsetzbare Use Cases\nDurchführung explorativer Datenanalysen, Modellentwicklung und Prototyping inklusive Bewertung von Nutzen, Risiken und Machbarkeit\nIntegration von Data-Science-, ML- und GenAI-Komponenten in bestehende IT- und Systemlandschaften (Modelle, APIs, Services, Pipelines)\nAufbau und Weiterentwicklung von MLOps- und LLMOps-Workflows (Versionierung, CI/CD, Testing, Monitoring, Evaluation sowie Kosten- und Performance-Optimierung)\nEntwicklung und Betrieb von APIs, Microservices und Datenpipelines\nMitwirkung an der Digitalisierung von Geschäftsprozessen und Produktionsanlagen\nÜbernahme fachlicher Verantwortung in Projekten sowie Unterstützung und Mentoring im Team (bei Senior-Level)\nDas bringst du mit\nAbgeschlossenes Studium in Informatik, Mathematik, Physik oder in einem vergleichbaren Fach\nPraxiserfahrung in Data Science, (Generative) AI Engineering, Data Engineering oder Software Engineering, idealerweise im Beratungs- oder Digitalisierungskontext\nSehr gute Kenntnisse in mindestens einer Programmiersprache (z. B. Python, Java, C# oder C++)\nErfahrung mit Machine Learning und Generative AI sowie gängigen Frameworks und Tools\nErste Erfahrung und hohes Interesse an AI-assisted Development\nKenntnisse im Umgang mit Datenbanken sowie idealerweise mit modernen Datenplattformen (z. B. Databricks, Snowflake) und Big-Data-Technologien (z. B. Spark, Kafka)\nErfahrung mit Cloud-Technologien (z. B. AWS, Azure) im Kontext von ML/AI-Anwendungen\nErfahrung mit Containerisierung (z. B. Docker) und Git-basierten CI/CD-Prozessen\nVerständnis für MLOps-Prinzipien sowie erste Erfahrung mit LLM-spezifischen Themen (z. B. Evaluation, Prompting, Guardrails)\nSehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse sowie Freude an der Zusammenarbeit im Team und mit Kunden\nBereitschaft zu gelegentlichen Reisen\n\nBei uns hast du vielfältige Möglichkeiten zur fachlichen und persönlichen Weiterentwicklung. Ob als fachliche Expertin oder Experte, in der Projektleitung oder perspektivisch im Management – wir unterstützen dich dabei, deinen individuellen Weg zu gestalten und Verantwortung zu übernehmen, ohne die Balance zwischen Beruf und Privatleben aus den Augen zu verlieren.\n\nDas bieten wir dir\nMensch & Kultur: Die Gemeinschaft und der Austausch im Unternehmen werden durch vielfältige Events wie Unternehmensmittagessen, Sommerfeste, Teamevents, Unternehmenskonferenzen und Weihnachtsfeiern aktiv gefördert. Ein Welcome Day sowie ein Mentoren-Programm während der Einarbeitungszeit tragen zudem dazu bei, den Zusammenhalt innerhalb der Teams zu stärken. Zusätzlich fördern wir den Teamgeist durch eine substanzielle Gewinnbeteiligung, die auf alle Mitarbeiter verteilt wird.\n\nKarriereentwicklung & Wissensaustausch: Die Vielfalt unserer (Kunden-)Projekte ermöglicht eine individuelle Karriereentwicklung. Verschiedenste Schulungsangebote und die Teilnahme an Fachkonferenzen fördern fachliches Wachstum. Ein jährliches Wissensbudget von 12 Tagen und Wissenszirkel unterstützen den kontinuierlichen Wissensaustausch.\n\nWork-Life-Balance & Flexibilität: Flexible Arbeitszeiten mit Arbeitszeitkonto, Mobile Office/hybrides Arbeiten, Workation-/Sabbatical-Optionen und die Möglichkeit Hunde mit ins Büro zu bringen, sind nur ein Teil unseres Angebots für Flexibilität und Lebensqualität. Auch in kritischen Situationen unterstützen wir mit bis zu 5 bezahlten Abwesenheitstagen, um sich um pflegebedürftige oder kranke Familienmitglieder zu kümmern.\n\nFinanzielle Vorteile: Mitarbeiter profitieren von unseren Zuschüssen für: Kinderbetreuung, Essen und Sport, betriebliche Altersvorsorge mit unverbindlicher Beratung, Deutschlandticket für nachhaltiges Reisen.\n\nGesundheit & Wohlbefinden: Verschiedene Gesundheitsmaßnahmen wie bewegte Pausen, Ergonomieberatung, Grippeimpfung und Augenarztuntersuchung fördern das Wohlbefinden und die langfristige Gesundheit der Mitarbeiter. Gesunde Snacks und Getränke gehören selbstverständlich ebenfalls zu unserem Angebot. Und um auch die soziale Interaktion zu stärken, haben wir Hobby- und Sportgruppen etabliert, welche nicht nur den lockeren Austausch, sondern auch den Zusammenhalt im Team stärken.\n\nSoziale Verantwortung & Nachhaltigkeit: Durch die HuManS-Stiftung streben wir danach, einen positiven Beitrag zur Gesellschaft zu leisten. Unsere Klimainitiative und das Umweltprogramm setzen sich engagiert für nachhaltige Unternehmenspraktiken ein.\nWir freuen uns auf deine Online-Bewerbung als AI Engineer / Data Scientist (mwd) – Machine Learning & Generative AI!\n\nManuela Mayer\nPersonalreferentin\nKai Brodmann\nGeschäftsbereichsleiter Data Science und Business Intelligence','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'HMS Analytical Software GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=bf988e65ebd82195','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2434,NULL,'job','AI Penetration Tester / AI Security Specialist (w/m/d)','Vollzeit','Frankfurt am Main',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Über uns\n\n1&1 gehört mit über 3.100 Mitarbeitenden und fast 16 Millionen Kundenverträgen zu den führenden Telekommunikationsanbietern in Deutschland. Mit Pioniergeist, ungewöhnlichen Ideen und kreativen Teams haben wir eine führende Marktstellung im Mobilfunk und bei Breitband-Anschlüssen erobert. Durch die Kombination des über 67.000 km langen 1&1 Glasfasernetzes und regionalen Netzen schaffen wir das weitreichendste Glasfasernetz Deutschlands. Außerdem bauen wir das modernste 5G-Netz Europas, auf der Basis der neuartigen Open-RAN-Technologie. Mit offenen Schnittstellen und 5G-Funktionen in einer leistungsfähigen Cloud-Infrastruktur. Schreiben Sie die 1&1 Erfolgsgeschichte fort, indem Sie durch Einsatz und Entwicklung innovativer Technologien, die Zukunft gestalten. Werden Sie Teil von 1&1.\n\nIhre Aufgaben\n\nIn dieser Rolle übernehmen Sie eine Schlüsselposition bei der Absicherung moderner AI- und GenAI-Systeme und tragen aktiv dazu bei, Schwachstellen frühzeitig zu identifizieren und zu beheben.\n\nDurchführung von Penetrationstests auf AI-/GenAI-Systeme (z. B. LLM-Anwendungen, RAG-Systeme, AI Agents)\nSimulation realistischer Angriffsszenarien wie Prompt Injection, Jailbreaks, Data Leakage, Model Manipulation und Retrieval-Angriffe\nIdentifikation, Analyse und Dokumentation von Schwachstellen entlang des gesamten AI-Lifecycles\nEntwicklung und Implementierung von Sicherheitsmaßnahmen (z. B. Guardrails, Input-/Output-Filtering, Zugriffskontrollen)\nUnterstützung beim Aufbau sicherer AI-Architekturen im Sinne von „Secure AI by Design“\nEnge Zusammenarbeit mit AI/ML Engineers zur Integration von Security in Entwicklungsprozesse\nAufbau und Weiterentwicklung von AI-spezifischen Pentest-Methodiken, Playbooks und Testframeworks\nEntwicklung automatisierter Security-Tests (z. B. Red Teaming, Adversarial Testing)\nDurchführung von Security-Assessments, Reviews sowie Erstellung von Audit-Reports und Risikobewertungen\nBeratung von Entwicklungsteams zu AI-Security Best Practices sowie Durchführung von Trainings und Workshops\n\nDas wünschen wir uns\n\nErfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium, z. B. in Informatik, IT-Sicherheit, Cyber Security oder einem vergleichbaren Studiengang\nMehrjährige Erfahrung im Bereich IT-Security, Penetration Testing oder Offensive Security\nFundierte Kenntnisse in Web- und API-Security (z. B. OWASP Top 10)\nVerständnis moderner AI-/GenAI-Systeme (z. B. LLMs, RAG, API-basierte Architekturen)\nErfahrung in Security Testing, Schwachstellenanalyse und Exploitation sowie gute Programmierkenntnisse (z. B. Python) zur Automatisierung von Tests\nAnalytisches Denkvermögen und die Fähigkeit, sich in Angreiferperspektiven hineinzuversetzen\nErfahrung im Bereich AI Security, LLM Security oder Red Teaming\nKenntnisse relevanter Frameworks (z. B. OWASP Top 10 for LLM Applications, NIST AI RMF)\nErfahrung mit Adversarial Machine Learning\nKenntnisse in Cloud-Security (z. B. AWS, Azure)\nErfahrung in regulierten Branchen (z. B. Telekommunikation, Finanzwesen)\n\nWas wir Ihnen noch sagen möchten\n\n• Attraktives Gehalt • Starke Gemeinschaft aus Teamplayern • Vertrauensarbeitszeit mit flexibler Einteilung und der Möglichkeit, bis zu 40% mobil zu arbeiten • Zahlreiche Weiterbildungsmöglichkeiten on- und offline • Rabatte auf 1&1 Produkte und für diverse Freizeitangebote • Betriebseigenes Restaurant • Kostenlose Getränke und frisches Obst • Jobrad-Zuschuss\n\nVielfalt bereichert. Unterschiedliche Kulturen, Nationalitäten, Geschlechter, Altersgruppen, sexuelle Orientierungen und Religionen sowie Menschen mit Behinderungen – wir wünschen uns Vielfalt und fördern sie. Denn nur Teams, die alle Facetten der Gesellschaft widerspiegeln, bieten die besten Rahmenbedingungen für Kreativität und machen ein Unternehmen produktiv und unverwechselbar. Wir wertschätzen Vielfalt und begrüßen alle Bewerbungen.\n\nKontakt\n\nFragen?\n\n1&1 Telecommunication SE\nRecruting\n\njobs@1und1.de\n\nNutzen Sie für Ihre Bewerbung bitte ausschließlich unser unkompliziertes Online-Formular, sodass wir Ihnen einen möglichst transparenten Bewerbungsprozess unter Einhaltung aller datenschutzrechtlicher Vorgaben gewährleisten können. Bewerbungen per Mail können wir leider aus genannten Gründen nicht berücksichtigen.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'1&1 Telecommunication SE','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1610a2d9470363d3','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2435,NULL,'job','AI/ML Ops Engineer (w/m/d)','Vollzeit','Frankfurt am Main',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Über uns\n\n1&1 gehört mit über 3.100 Mitarbeitenden und fast 16 Millionen Kundenverträgen zu den führenden Telekommunikationsanbietern in Deutschland. Mit Pioniergeist, ungewöhnlichen Ideen und kreativen Teams haben wir eine führende Marktstellung im Mobilfunk und bei Breitband-Anschlüssen erobert. Durch die Kombination des über 67.000 km langen 1&1 Glasfasernetzes und regionalen Netzen schaffen wir das weitreichendste Glasfasernetz Deutschlands. Außerdem bauen wir das modernste 5G-Netz Europas, auf der Basis der neuartigen Open-RAN-Technologie. Mit offenen Schnittstellen und 5G-Funktionen in einer leistungsfähigen Cloud-Infrastruktur. Schreiben Sie die 1&1 Erfolgsgeschichte fort, indem Sie durch Einsatz und Entwicklung innovativer Technologien, die Zukunft gestalten. Werden Sie Teil von 1&1.\n\nIhre Aufgaben\n\nIn dieser Rolle stellen Sie den stabilen, skalierbaren Betrieb moderner ML- und GenAI-Systeme sicher und bauen eine durchgängige Delivery-Kette von der Entwicklung bis zur produktiven Nutzung auf.\n\nAufbau und Betrieb von CI/CD/CT-Pipelines für Machine-Learning-Modelle und GenAI-Anwendungen (inkl. Prompt-Workflows)\nImplementierung und Verwaltung von Model Registry, Versionierung und Deployment-Prozessen\nDeployment von AI-Services in produktiven Umgebungen mittels Docker und Kubernetes\nMonitoring und Optimierung von Modell-Performance (z. B. Drift, Latenz, Kosten, Verfügbarkeit)\nSicherstellung von Skalierbarkeit, Stabilität und Wiederholbarkeit von ML-Workflows\nErstellung auditfähiger Artefakte (z. B. Model Cards, Logs, Dokumentation)\nEnge Zusammenarbeit mit Data Scientists, AI/ML Engineers und Plattform-Teams\nWeiterentwicklung von Best Practices im Bereich MLOps und AI-Betrieb\n\nDas wünschen wir uns\n\nErfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium, z. B. in Informatik, Software Engineering oder einem vergleichbaren Studiengang\nMehrjährige Erfahrung im DevOps- oder MLOps-Umfeld\nFundierte Kenntnisse in Container-Technologien (Docker) und Orchestrierung (Kubernetes)\nErfahrung mit CI/CD-Systemen und automatisierten Deployment-Prozessen\nPraxis im Umgang mit Monitoring-, Logging- und Tracking-Tools\nGute Python-Kenntnisse zur Automatisierung von Prozessen\nErfahrung im Bereich LLMOps bzw. Betrieb von GenAI-Anwendungen\nKenntnisse relevanter Standards (z. B. ISO/IEC 42001)\nErfahrung mit hybriden Infrastrukturumgebungen (Cloud & On-Premise)\n\nWas wir Ihnen noch sagen möchten\n\n• Attraktives Gehalt • Starke Gemeinschaft aus Teamplayern • Vertrauensarbeitszeit mit flexibler Einteilung und der Möglichkeit, bis zu 40% mobil zu arbeiten • Zahlreiche Weiterbildungsmöglichkeiten on- und offline • Rabatte auf 1&1 Produkte und für diverse Freizeitangebote • Betriebseigenes Restaurant • Kostenlose Getränke und frisches Obst • Jobrad-Zuschuss\n\nVielfalt bereichert. Unterschiedliche Kulturen, Nationalitäten, Geschlechter, Altersgruppen, sexuelle Orientierungen und Religionen sowie Menschen mit Behinderungen – wir wünschen uns Vielfalt und fördern sie. Denn nur Teams, die alle Facetten der Gesellschaft widerspiegeln, bieten die besten Rahmenbedingungen für Kreativität und machen ein Unternehmen produktiv und unverwechselbar. Wir wertschätzen Vielfalt und begrüßen alle Bewerbungen.\n\nKontakt\n\nFragen?\n\n1&1 Telecommunication SE\nRecruting\n\njobs@1und1.de\n\nNutzen Sie für Ihre Bewerbung bitte ausschließlich unser unkompliziertes Online-Formular, sodass wir Ihnen einen möglichst transparenten Bewerbungsprozess unter Einhaltung aller datenschutzrechtlicher Vorgaben gewährleisten können. Bewerbungen per Mail können wir leider aus genannten Gründen nicht berücksichtigen.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'1&1 Telecommunication SE','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=bf3e45374dd50086','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2436,NULL,'job','Sensor Fusion Deep Learning Engineer (m/f/d)','','65760 Eschborn',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'To strengthen our European headquarter in Frankfurt am Main, we are currently looking for a\n\nSensor Fusion Deep Learning Engineer (m/f/d)\nAbout us\n\nMOBIS Parts Europe N.V. is the European branch of Hyundai MOBIS, a worldwide leading supplier of genuine parts and accessories in the field of automotive. Together with Hyundai Motors and Kia Motors, Hyundai MOBIS is one of the biggest companies within the Hyundai group. In addition to research and development of high-tech products for passenger cars, MOBIS Parts Europe N.V. is responsible for the whole aftersales business of genuine parts and accessories for Hyundai Motors and Kia Motors in Europe.\n\nYour profile\nMasters Degree in Computer Science, Electrical engineering, Robotics or equivalent.\n3+ years of experience in developing deep learning models for Autonomous Driving, Computer Vision or Robotics applications\nStrong programming skills in Python along with proficiency in deep learning frameworks like PyTorch or TensorFlow\nSolid foundation in mathematics relevant to Machine Learning and Robotics: Linear Algebra, Probability/Statistics and 3D Geometry\nHands-on experience in implementing training and evaluation pipelines for multi-modal perception problems like 3D object detection\nKnowledge of optimizing models for deployment (Quantization, Pruning, ONNX, TensorRT) is desired\nExperience with C/C++ for model inference and systems integration is beneficial\nComfortable working in Linux-based development environments, with tools such as Git, Docker, ROS2 and CI/CD workflows\nWillingness to learn new technologies based on project needs\nExcellent communication skills and ability to work collaboratively in a multidisciplinary engineering and research team in English\nYour tasks\nIdentify state-of-the-art Deep Neural Network architectures for sensor fusion and end-to-end learning to evaluate applicability for autonomous driving applications.\nImplement efficient DNN training pipelines and optimize DNN models for deployment on embedded platforms with hardware constraints.\nMeasure performance of neural networks and iteratively improve functional performance on use-cases.\nInvestigate issues in existing algorithm software and improve them by providing guidance for solution.\nDocument methods, experiments and results; prepare technical reports and presentations for internal and external stakeholders.\nCurate large-scale datasets to ensure high-quality training and validation.\nCollaborate on deploying trained networks into C/C++ based integration environments for on-vehicle testing.\nWhat we offer you\nYou will become an important member of an international company that is strongly focusing on the development of the latest automotive technologies.\nTake on an exciting position that will directly impact the company’s direction in the automotive industry.\nLong-term career perspective and promising growth opportunities.\nFlexible work time model that ensures an attractive work-life balance.\nModern office space with table tennis room, thinking room, and fully equipped meeting rooms.\nCafeteria area stocked daily with lunch snacks, and fresh fruits; in addition, meal vouchers are given monthly.\nFree secured underground parking lot for bikes and cars.\nGreat public transportation options.\nMany corporate benefits including discounts on nearby gym memberships.\nRegular company events, yearly sports competitions and cultural days organized by our DEI Allies team.\nCompany pension\n\nPanna Pertics\n\nTalent Acquisition Partner\n\nMobis Parts Europe N.V.\n\nZweigniederlassung Deutschland\n\nFrankfurter Strasse 60-68\n\n65760 Eschborn','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Hyundai Mobis','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5a1f10237d5a65db','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2437,NULL,'job','Wissenschaftlicher Mitarbeiter (w/ m/ d) – Neuropsychologie & Funktionelle MRT-Bildgebung','Teilzeit','Ulm',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Sie entwickeln und programmieren fMRT-Experimente und wirken an der Durchführung von MRT-Messungen mit – auch im Rahmen der Core Facility Human Experimental MRI. Ein weiterer Schwerpunkt liegt in der strukturierten Datenverwaltung sowie in der Analyse komplexer MRT-Datensätze verschiedener Modalitäten. Sie bereiten Ergebnisse auf, unterstützen deren wissenschaftliche Interpretation und wirken an der Erstellung und Publikation von Forschungsergebnissen mit.\n\nWir bieten eine vielseitige Tätigkeit in einem interdisziplinären und forschungsstarken Umfeld mit Zugang zu moderner Bildgebungstechnologie (u.a. 3T MRT im Haus; TMS; 64-Kanal EEG). Die Arbeitsatmosphäre ist offen und innovativ, mit Möglichkeiten zur Umsetzung eigener Ideen. Eine Beschäftigung in Teilzeit ist möglich (mindestens 65 %), mit weitgehend flexiblen Arbeitszeiten. Akademische Weiterentwicklung (Promotion oder Habilitation) wird gefördert.\n\nSie verfügen über einen sehr guten Masterabschluss in einem MINT-Fach mit Vorkenntnissen in Neurowissenschaften oder Psychologie, oder eine Promotion in Bildgebender Neurowissenschaft bzw. verwandten Gebieten. Eine ausgeprägte Affinität zu Data Science verbinden Sie mit starken analytischen Fähigkeiten und Fertigkeiten zur Problemlösung. Sehr gute Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift werden vorausgesetzt. Hohe Vertrautheit mit Matlab und Python sind erforderlich, sowie Kenntnisse und Erfahrungen im Bereich gängiger Machine-Learning Techniken. Auch haben Sie bereits Erfahrung in Akquise und Analyse von BOLD-fMRT-Daten (task-based und resting-state) und kennen andere MR-Bildgebungsmodalitäten und analytische Prozeduren (Volumetrie, DTI, ALS).','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Universitätsklinikum Ulm','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=7bccde7fc949223f','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2438,NULL,'job','Data Scientist','Teilzeit','Wiesbaden',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Data Scientist\n\nThe Opportunity:\n\nAs a data scientist, you’re excited at the prospect of unlocking the secrets held by a data set, and you’re fascinated by the possibilities presented by IoT, machine learning, and artificial intelligence. In an increasingly connected world, massive amounts of structured and unstructured data open new opportunities. As a data scientist at Booz Allen, you can help turn these complex data sets into useful information to solve global challenges. Across private and public sectors—from fraud detection to cancer research to national intelligence—we need you to help find the answers in the data.\n\nOn our team, you’ll use your leadership skills and data science expertise to create real-world impact. You’ll work closely with clients to understand their questions and needs, and then dig into their data-rich environments to find the pieces of their information puzzle. You’ll guide teammates and lead the development of algorithms and systems. You’ll use the right combination of tools and frameworks to turn sets of disparate data points into objective answers to advise your clients as they make informed decisions. Ultimately, you’ll provide a deep understanding of the data, what it all means, and how it can be used.\n\nWork with us as we use data science for good.\n\nJoin us. The world can’t wait.\n\nYou Have:\n\n5+ years of experience with data exploration, data cleaning, data analysis, data visualization, or data mining\n5+ years of experience with statistical and general-purpose programming languages for data analysis\n5+ years of experience analyzing structured and unstructured data sources\nExperience developing predictive data models, quantitative analyses, and visualization of targeted data sources\nExperience leading the development of solutions to complex programs\nExperience with natural language processing, text mining, or machine learning techniques\nSecret clearance\nBachelor’s degree\n\nNice If You Have:\n\nExperience with Maven Smart Systems\nExperience supporting the Department of War\nExperience in the development of algorithms leveraging R, Python, SQL, or NoSQL\nExperience with Distributed data and computing tools, including MapReduce, Hadoop, Hive, EMR, Kafka, Spark, Gurobi, or MySQL\nExperience with visualization packages, including Plotly, Seaborn, or ggplot2\nTS/SCI clearance\n\nClearance:\n\nApplicants selected will be subject to a security investigation and may need to meet eligibility requirements for access to classified information; Secret clearance is required.\n\nCompensation\n\nAt Booz Allen, we celebrate your contributions, provide you with opportunities and choices, and support your total well-being. Our offerings include health, life, disability, financial, and retirement benefits, as well as paid leave, professional development, tuition assistance, work-life programs, and dependent care. Our recognition awards program acknowledges employees for exceptional performance and superior demonstration of our values. Full-time and part-time employees working at least 20 hours a week on a regular basis are eligible to participate in Booz Allen’s benefit programs. Individuals that do not meet the threshold are only eligible for select offerings, not inclusive of health benefits. We encourage you to learn more about our total benefits by visiting the Resource page on our Careers site and reviewing Our Employee Benefits page.\n\nSalary at Booz Allen is determined by various factors, including but not limited to location, the individual’s particular combination of education, knowledge, skills, competencies, and experience, as well as contract-specific affordability and organizational requirements. The projected compensation range for this position is $99,000.00 to $225,000.00 (annualized USD). The estimate displayed represents the typical salary range for this position and is just one component of Booz Allen’s total compensation package for employees. This posting will close within 90 days from the Posting Date.\n\nIdentity Statement\n\nAs part of the hiring process, we will ask you to complete an identity verification process that leverages advanced biometrics and artificial intelligence to ensure authenticity and protect against identity fraud. You are expected to be on camera during interviews and assessments. We reserve the right to take your picture to verify your identity and prevent fraud.\n\nCandidate AI Usage Policy\n\nAI is a part of our daily work at Booz Allen, and we are committed to the responsible and ethical use of AI tools. However, we want to ensure a fair candidate process based on your own skills and knowledge. As part of this commitment, the use of artificial intelligence (AI) or other tools to assist with responses during interviews (whether in-person or virtual) is prohibited unless permission is explicitly provided.\n\nWork Model\nOur people-first culture prioritizes the benefits of collaboration, whether it occurs in person or virtually. To support engagement and effective communication, employees working virtually are generally expected to have their cameras on during meetings.\n\nRemote: If this position is listed as remote, there may still be occasions when you are required to work in person at a Booz Allen or customer facility.\n\nHybrid: If this position is listed as hybrid, you will be expected to work from a Booz Allen facility frequently, in alignment with leadership expectations and the needs of the role. You may also be required to work from or visit a customer facility.\n\nOnsite: If this position is listed as onsite, work will primarily be performed at a Booz Allen office or customer facility, where employees will collaborate directly with colleagues and customers as required by the role.\n\nCommitment to Non-Discrimination\n\nAll qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to disability, status as a protected veteran or any other status protected by applicable federal, state, local, or international law.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Booz Allen','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a41ba5d24cd9cc9e','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2439,NULL,'job','AI Product Manager','Vollzeit','München',NULL,'',5800073000.00,'58.000 € – 73.000 € pro Jahr','About Air Apps\n\nAt Air Apps, we believe in thinking bigger—and moving faster. We’re a family-founded company on a mission to create the world’s first AI-powered Personal & Entrepreneurial Resource Planner (PRP), and we need your passion and ambition to help us change how people plan, work, and live. Born in Lisbon, Portugal in 2018—and now with offices in both Lisbon and San Francisco—we’ve remained self-funded while reaching over 100 million downloads worldwide.\n\nOur long-term focus drives us to challenge the status quo every day, pushing the boundaries of AI-driven solutions that truly make a difference. Here, you’ll be a creative force, shaping products that empower people across the globe.\n\nJoin us on this journey to redefine resource management—and change lives along the way.\n\nThe Role\n\nAs an AI Product Manager at Air Apps, you will be at the forefront of shaping AI-powered applications that enhance user experiences. You will lead the product development lifecycle for AI-driven features, working closely with engineers, designers, and data scientists to develop, launch, and scale AI-driven solutions. Your role is pivotal in ensuring that AI technologies align with user needs and business objectives.\n\nThis is a fully onsite position, based at our office in Lisbon, where you will collaborate closely with cross-functional teams in person and contribute to a dynamic and fast-paced environment. We are open to support with relocation efforts.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nDefine and drive the AI product roadmap, ensuring alignment with business objectives and user needs.\n\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams, including engineering, design, and marketing, to develop and launch AI-powered features.\n\nConduct market research and analyze user feedback to identify opportunities for AI integration.\n\nWork closely with data scientists and machine learning engineers to optimize AI models for accuracy, performance, and user impact.\n\nDefine key performance indicators (KPIs) to measure success and iterate based on data-driven insights.\n\nStay up to date with AI trends, emerging technologies, and best practices to ensure our products remain competitive.\n\nEnsure ethical AI usage and compliance with data privacy regulations.\n\nRequirements\n\nAround 4+ years of experience in product management, preferably in AI, machine learning, or data-driven applications.\n\nStrong understanding of AI/ML concepts, including NLP, computer vision, and recommendation systems.\n\nExperience working with data science and engineering teams to develop AI-based features.\n\nAbility to translate complex AI concepts into user-friendly applications.\n\nStrong analytical skills and experience leveraging data to drive product decisions.\n\nWhat benefits are we offering?\n\nApple hardware ecosystem for work.\n\nAnnual Bonus\n\nTop-tier Health and Life Insurance for peace of mind.\n\nTransportation Budget to support your commute needs.\n\nCoverflex benefits package for meal allowances, well-being, and more.\n\nChildcare support.\n\nAir Conference - an opportunity to meet the team, collaborate, and grow together.\n\nPension Fund to support your long-term financial planning.\n\nUrban Sports Club membership to keep you active.\n\nMeals 100% free at the hub.\n\nDiversity & Inclusion\n\nAt Air Apps, we are committed to fostering a diverse, inclusive, and equitable workplace. We enthusiastically welcome applicants from all backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives. We celebrate diversity in all its forms and believe that varied voices and experiences make us stronger.\n\nApplication Disclaimer\n\nAt Air Apps, we value transparency and integrity in our hiring process. Applicants must submit their own work without any AI-generated assistance. Any use of AI in application materials, assessments, or interviews will result in disqualification.\n\nCompensation Range: €58K - €73K','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Air Apps','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c1318e116aabad9b','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2440,NULL,'job','Werkstudent Data Science & Analytics - Energiebranche (m/w/d)','Studentenjob','Bonn',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Klar für den Sprung vom Hörsaal in die Praxis?\n\nWir suchen dich als Werkstudenten Data Science & Analytics (m/w/d) im Team Datenmanagement, zunächst befristet für ein Jahr.\n\nHier gestaltest du aktiv unsere datengetriebene Zukunft. Du arbeitest mit echten Daten, automatisierst Prozesse und hilfst dabei fundierte Entscheidungen möglich zu machen.\nGleichzeitig bringst du Struktur in unsere Datenlandschaft und sorgst dafür, dass unsere Daten dort ankommen, wo sie gebraucht werden: zuverlässig und qualitätsgeprüft.\n\nWenn du bereit bist, Teil eines dynamischen Teams zu werden, deine Fähigkeiten weiterzuentwickeln und deine akademische Laufbahn mit praktischer Erfahrung zu ergänzen, dann bewirb dich jetzt und gestalte die digitale Transformation mit uns!\nHier bringst du dich ein\nDu gestaltest und pflegst Datenpipelines über Workflows in der KNIME Analytics Platform, um eine effiziente Datenverarbeitung und -aufbereitung zu gewährleisten.\nDabei betreust und entwickelst du unsere interne Automatisierungsplattform (KNIME Business Hub) weiter.\nDu erstellst ansprechende Visualisierungen für Endanwender:innen, wie z. B. Verbrauchsverläufe, Quoten oder Kennzahlen.\nBei der Entwicklung von Machine-Learning-Modellen für energiewirtschaftliche Fragestellungen arbeitest du mit, etwa für die Prognose von Energie- und Wasserverbräuchen oder Kundeninteraktionen.\nDu führst Datenabfragen und -analysen mit SQL (vorzugsweise MSSQL) durch.\nDu unterstützt bei der Datenmodellierung, -transformation sowie der Qualitätssicherung von Datenbeständen.\nDamit überzeugst du uns\nDu verfügst über eine abgeschlossene Ausbildung oder ein Studium im Bereich Informatik, Datenwissenschaften, (Wirtschafts-)Mathematik, Statistik oder einer vergleichbaren Qualifikation.\nZudem verfügst du über sichere SQL-Kenntnisse (vorzugsweise MSSQL) und Erfahrung in der Datenabfrage und -analyse. Programmierkenntnisse in Python, Java oder einer vergleichbaren Sprache runden dein technisches Profil ab. Idealerweise bringst du erste praktische Erfahrung im Umgang mit der KNIME Analytics Platform und/oder dem KNIME Business Hub mit.\nDeine Affinität zu Statistik/Stochastik und dein sehr gutes Zahlenverständnis ermöglichen es dir, datenbasierte Lösungen zu entwickeln. Zudem hast du ein Interesse an energiewirtschaftlichen Themen und arbeitest strukturiert und analytisch, wobei du komplexe Sachverhalte verständlich kommunizieren kannst.\nAls teamorientierte Person freust du dich auf die Zusammenarbeit mit Fachabteilungen.\nErste Erfahrungen im Umgang mit Machine-Learning-Algorithmen, deren praktische Anwendung und Erfahrungen mit mit Datenvisualisierungstools (z. B. Tableau, Power BI) sind von Vorteil.\nFreue dich auf Folgendes\nKarriere-Boost: Entwickel dich mit uns weiter! Profitiere von gezielten Weiterbildungen, die deine Fähigkeiten auf das nächste Level heben.\nArbeitsort: Bei uns hast du die Möglichkeit, flexibel und ausgewogen zu arbeiten. Mit unserem Hybrid-Arbeitsmodell kannst du deine Arbeit sowohl im Büro als auch remote innerhalb der Gleitzeit erledigen und so deine Work-Life-Balance optimal gestalten.\nMobilität: Vergünstigte Mitarbeitenden- & Familientickets, kostenlose Welo-Minuten und Top-Leasing-Angebote für Fahrräder & E-Bikes. Zudem kannst du das Deutschlandticket als günstiges Job-Ticket erhalten.\nGesundheit: Profitiere von unserem Gesundheitsprogramm sowie exklusiven Vorteilen bei Wellhub - auch für deine Familie.\nGestalte mit uns die Versorgung von morgen!\nAls Energieversorger für Bonn und die Region tragen wir, die Stadtwerke Bonn, eine besondere Verantwortung. Nachhaltigkeit, Energieeffizienz und Investitionen in die Zukunft sind dabei drei unserer Eckpfeiler, um das wichtigste Ziel der Stadt Bonn zu erreichen - Klimaneutralität bis 2035. Dafür bringen wir 140 Jahre Wissen und Erfahrung mit und gleichzeitig den Blick nach vorne mit einer Leidenschaft für Innovation.\n\nDie Eingruppierung richtet sich nach einem der besten Tarifverträge innerhalb des öffentlichen Dienstes (TV-V), entsprechend den tarifvertraglichen Bestimmungen.\n\nHaben wir dich überzeugt? Dann bewirb dich jetzt mit deinen Unterlagen unter Angabe der Kennziffer IE 26/11/11 über unser Onlineformular.\nBewerbungen von schwerbehinderten Personen sind erwünscht.\n\nDein Kontakt zu den Stadtwerken Bonn\n\nDu hast Fragen zur ausgeschriebenen Stelle oder zum Bewerbungsprozess? Dann erreichst du uns per E-Mail unter bewerbungen@swb-karriere.de. Bitte sende deine Bewerbung ausschließlich über das jeweilige Online-Formular, damit sie direkt bei der richtigen Ansprechperson landet.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Stadtwerke Bonn GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e470deee0d1c2e08','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2441,NULL,'job','Senior AI Advisory Architect (gn)','Festanstellung','Home Office',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Why SoftwareOne?\n\nSoftwareOne und Crayon haben sich zusammengeschlossen, um gemeinsam zu einem der weltweit führenden Anbieter für AI-gestützte Software- und Cloud-Lösungen zu werden. Mit mehr als 13.000 Mitarbeitenden in über 70 Ländern gestalten wir die technologische Zukunft unserer Kunden – innovativ, global vernetzt und mit klarer Vision.\n\nBei uns stehen die Menschen im Mittelpunkt. Wir fördern mutige Ideen, echte Zusammenarbeit und kontinuierliches Wachstum – unterstützt durch exzellente Lern- und Entwicklungsprogramme. Ob in unseren Technologie- und Cloud-Lösungen oder im direkten Kundenkontakt – bei uns findest du den richtigen Ort, um dein Potenzial zu entfalten.\n\nWerde Teil einer Kultur, in der deine Ideen zählen und deine Karriere keine Grenzen kennt.\nMehr Informationen findest du unter www.softwareone.com.\n\nThe role\n\nWillst du Kundenprobleme direkt angehen und daraus wirkungsvolle, skalierbare AI‑Lösungen entwickeln?\nMöchtest du Business und Technologie verbinden und dabei Architektur‑Know‑how, Hands‑on‑AI‑Expertise und starke Kommunikation vereinen?\nMotiviert dich ein globales Technologieunternehmen, das in deine fachliche Weiterentwicklung, Flexibilität und langfristige Wertschöpfung investiert?\n\nPraktische Informationen\n\nStandort: Bundesweit, Deutschland | Anstellungsart: Unbefristet | Beschäftigungsumfang: Vollzeit | Arbeitsmodell: Hybrid | Sprachkenntnisse: Fließende Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse\n\nWir suchen einen hochqualifizierten und motivierten AI Advisory Architect (gn) zur Verstärkung unseres Advisory Teams. Du arbeitest eng mit unseren Kunden rund um das Thema Künstliche Intelligenz, identifizierst fachliche und strategische Herausforderungen und entwickelst daraus sinnvolle, skalierbare AI‑Lösungen. Dabei agierst du als Bindeglied zwischen Business und Technologie und verbindest architektonisches Denken mit technischer Hands‑on‑Expertise sowie ausgeprägten Kommunikationsfähigkeiten.\n\nDeine Aufgaben\n\nAI Advisory & Solution Design: Du berätst unsere Kunden zu AI‑Strategien, identifizierst Herausforderungen, übersetzt diese in konkrete AI‑Use‑Cases und entwirfst skalierbare Lösungsarchitekturen in den Bereichen LLMs, Generative und Agentic AI, Computer Vision, Machine Learning und idealerweise MLOps.\nProjektleitung: Du leitest und koordinierst kleinere Consulting AI‑Projekte end‑to‑end, sorgst für eine strukturierte Umsetzung, hohe Ergebnisqualität und die Abstimmung mit den Erwartungen unserer Kunden.\nWorkshop‑Moderation: Du konzipierst und moderierst praxisnahe, inspirierende Workshops für Kunden und interne Teams und vermittelst ein fundiertes Verständnis für Möglichkeiten, Chancen und Grenzen von AI.\nPräsentationen: Du erstellst und hältst überzeugende Präsentationen und erklärst komplexe AI‑Konzepte, Architekturen und Empfehlungen verständlich für technische wie auch nicht‑technische Zielgruppen.\nSales Support: Du unterstützt den Vertrieb durch die Teilnahme an Kundenterminen, hilfst bei der Bedarfserhebung, gestaltest AI‑Lösungsvorschläge mit und bringst deine technische sowie architektonische Expertise ein.\n\nWhat we need to see from you\n\nDas bringst du mit\n\nErfahrung in AI‑, Lösungsarchitektur‑ oder anspruchsvollen datengetriebenen Rollen, ergänzt durch fundierte Projekterfahrung\nSehr gute Python‑Kenntnisse sowie praktische Erfahrung mit Data‑Science‑ und Analytics‑Tools\nNachweisliche Hands‑on‑Erfahrung mit AI‑ und ML‑Technologien, insbesondere LLMs, Generative AI, Agentic AI, Computer Vision und Machine Learning\nErfahrung mit MLOps und produktionsnahen AI‑Workflows ist ein klarer Vorteil\nStarke kommunikative und kundenorientierte Fähigkeiten mit der Fähigkeit, fachliche Anforderungen in klare AI‑Lösungen zu übersetzen und komplexe Themen verständlich zu erklären\nErfahrung in der Leitung kleinerer Projekte oder Workstreams, einschließlich der Durchführung von Workshops und Präsentationen\n\nDas haben wir derzeit zu bieten\n\nWir bieten dir die Möglichkeit zum Arbeiten im Homeoffice. Aber auch im Office haben wir keinen Dresscode und du kannst anziehen womit auch immer du dich wohl fühlst\nBei uns hast du die Option auf ein Sabbatical\nWir fördern Vielfalt: Mit unserer DEIB-Strategie und Women in Tech-Initiative setzen wir uns für Chancengleichheit ein\nIndividuelles Angebot an internem Coaching und psychosozialer Beratung\nProfitiere vom Unternehmenserfolg durch unser Mitarbeitendenaktien- und -empfehlungsprogramm\nAlle weiteren aktuellen Benefits findest du hier: https://www.softwareone.com/de-de/karriere/dach/benefits\n\nInteressiert?\n\nBewirb dich mit deinem Lebenslauf und wenigen Klicks über unser Online-Formular! Es ist kein Anschreiben nötig.\n\nJob Function\n\nServices\nAccommodations\n\nSoftwareOne steht für ein respektvolles, inklusives Arbeitsumfeld mit gleichen Chancen für alle – unabhängig von Herkunft, Hautfarbe, Religion, Alter, Geschlecht, Behinderung, sexueller Orientierung, Geschlechtsidentität oder anderen gesetzlich geschützten Merkmalen. Außerdem laden wir Berufsrückkehrende nach einer geplanten Auszeit ein, unser SOAR-Programm kennenzulernen.\n\nWenn du im Bewerbungsprozess Unterstützung benötigst, melde dich gern unter reasonable.accommodations@softwareone.com. Bitte nenne dabei die Stelle, auf die du dich bewirbst, sowie das Land deines Wohnsitzes. Eine vom Auswahlprozess unabhängige Kontaktperson aus unserem Team setzt sich anschließend mit dir in Verbindung, um deine Bedürfnisse zu besprechen. Wir unterstützen dich bestmöglich – und behandeln deine Angaben selbstverständlich sicher und vertraulich nach DSGVO.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'SoftwareONE','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=4598e14e9f2e8720','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2442,NULL,'job','Data Scientist (m/w/d)* Komposit-Versicherung','','Frankfurt am Main',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Data Scientist (m/w/d)* Komposit-Versicherung\n\nEine Gruppe. Viele Möglichkeiten.\n\nDie ALH Gruppe zählt zu den bedeutenden Versicherungs- und Finanzdienstleistungsunternehmen in Deutschland. Rund 3.000 Mitarbeiterinnen und Mitarbeiter bilden das Fundament für unseren Erfolg und sorgen täglich für erstklassigen Service, individuelle Beratung und die langfristige Zufriedenheit unserer Kunden.\n\nDie ALH Gruppe entwickelt sich kontinuierlich weiter und geht mit innovativen Ideen aktiv voran. Verstärken Sie unser engagiertes Team im Bereich Aktuariat & Berichtswesen am Standort Oberursel bei Frankfurt am Main und helfen Sie uns dabei, datenbasierte Anwendungen und modernste KI für die Zukunft der Komposit-Versicherung (Schaden- und Unfallversicherung) einzusetzen.\n\n Ihre Aufgaben:\n\nAufbereitung und Analyse von Daten aus verschiedenen Quellen, insbesondere aus dem Data Lake\nIdentifikation und Bewertung von Einsatzpotenzialen für Machine Learning und AI sowie Entwicklung konkreter Use Cases\nKonzeption und Umsetzung automatisierter Datenflüsse für ML-/AI-Prozesse\nAuswahl, Anpassung und Weiterentwicklung geeigneter ML-/AI-Modelle\nAbleitung des Nutzens für Geschäftsprozesse und verständliche Präsentation der Ergebnisse\nImplementierung, Betrieb und Optimierung von Modellen mit Fokus auf Stabilität und Wartbarkeit\nMitarbeit an Projekten und Weiterentwicklung von ML-/AI-Verfahren und -Systemen\n Ihre Kompetenzen:\nAmbitionierte, zahlenbegeisterte Persönlichkeit mit abgeschlossenem Studium – z. B. Data Science, (Wirtschafts-)Mathematik, Statistik, Physik – oder eine gleichwertige Qualifikation\nErfahrung in Entwicklung, Anwendung und Monitoring von ML-/AI-Modellen sowie in der Beratung von Anwendern\nSicherer Umgang mit Datenbanken, Analysetools und gängigen Programmiersprachen\nKenntnisse der Prozesse und Systeme in der Schaden-/Unfallversicherung sowie regulatorischer Rahmenbedingungen\nPräzises Ausdrucksvermögen kombiniert mit Expertise bei der Aufarbeitung und anschaulichen Kommunikation komplexer Zusammenhänge\n Unser Versprechen:\nAttraktive Vergütung: Vierzehn Monatsgehälter ab dem 2. Jahr der Betriebszugehörigkeit\nFlexible Arbeitszeit: 38-Stunden-Woche mit Gleitzeit und hybridem Arbeiten\nMehr Freizeit: 30 Urlaubstage - zusätzlich frei am 24.12. und 31.12.\nGesund & mobil: Wellhub, JobRad, Zuschuss zum Jobticket und betriebliche Krankenversicherung\nFinanzielle Extras: Betriebsrente, Vermögenswirksame Leistungen, Corporate Benefits, Haustarife auf unsere Produkte etc.\nWeiterkommen: Individuelle Fort- und Weiterbildungsmöglichkeiten\nPerfekter Einstieg: Strukturierte Einarbeitung sowie eigenverantwortliche und abwechslungsreiche Tätigkeiten\nArbeitsumfeld: Betriebsrestaurant, Sporthalle und kostenlose Parkplätze\n\nEs erwartet Sie ein Team, in dem Arbeiten Spaß macht!\n\nInteresse geweckt? Gleich über unser Online-Formular bewerben!\n\nWir freuen uns auf Ihre Bewerbung unter Angabe Ihrer Gehaltsvorstellung und Ihrer derzeitigen Kündigungsfrist!','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'ALH Gruppe','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=588f771466b88eef','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2443,NULL,'job','Lead AI Engineer (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','30177 Hannover',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Are you looking for a full-time position in a global strategic consultancy as a Lead AI Engineer to streamline patient access to life-changing treatments through expert guidance, innovative tools, and impeccable delivery?\n\nLocation: Remote, occasional travel required to Hanover (GER) or London\nSalary: Competitive, based on experience\n\nWe are Kintiga (formerly MAP Patient Access, Axtalis, and SKC), a pan-European specialist consultancy that partners with ambitious health technology developers through the complex journey to achieve successful market access across Europe,with our tailored approach, global perspective and local expertise. Our clients in healthcare and life sciences are leading innovators in pharma, biotech, medtech, digital health, and diagnostics. As part of Kintiga, we support the successful launch and reimbursement of breakthrough therapies and technologies.\n\nJoin our team and help shape the future of the cutting-edge healthcare solutions. At Kintiga, we cultivate a collaborative and entrepreneurial culture where every voice matters. We value diversity, openness, and integrity - encouraging our team members to bring their ideas and passion to work every day. Become part of a supportive, dynamic team that thrives on innovation, lifelong learning, and making a meaningful impact in healthcare and life sciences.\n\nDOWNLOAD JOB DESCRIPTION (PDF)\nHow you will create an impact:\n\nWe are looking for an experienced Lead AI Engineer to provide hands-on technical leadership across our AI-driven\nproducts and platforms. This role combines deep software engineering expertise with practical application of AI / machine learning, and the ability to manage external AI development partnership and provide technical direction to the wider delivery team and manager other developers. You will set technical direction, design and build production-grade AI solutions, and ensure high standards of security, scalability, and maintainability. You will work closely with product managers, analysts, users, and business stakeholders to turn ideas into reliable and impactful systems.\n\nDrive the development of cutting-edge AI solutions and strategies.\nBring your unique insights and experience into AI discussion. Be a major voice on buy-it vs build-it commercial decision-making and technical feasibility discussions.\nWork with AI Suite Product Owners (stream leads) and the Chief Digital Officer (CDO) to maintain and plan roadmaps for existing and new AI Suite tools.\nManage our AI solutions, lead the technical partnership with our primary AI development partner (reporting to CDO) and provide technical direction to the wider contractor and developer network\nStay up to date with latest AI technologies and contribute to in-house R&D initiatives.\nOwnership of AI services & projects, ensuring alignment with strategic goals & deadlines.\nPropose, design and deploy production-grade AI systems including LLM-powered applications, RAG pipelines, and intelligent automation workflows, - with ownership of Kintiga’s live AI Suite products (EPRI, SLR v2, PICSI) - from a hands-on technical leadership & practical coding perspective, to enhance organisational and client delivery capabilities.\nManage and take ownership of our CI/CD pipelines, automated testing, and cloud deployments.\nContribute to product roadmap planning and technical feasibility discussions.\nAbout you:\nProficiency in LLMs, agentic AI, deep learning, NLP, and predictive analytics.\nStrong background in software engineering (e.g. Python, TypeScript or similar) and hands-on experience with LLM orchestration frameworks such as LangChain, LlamaIndex, or equivalent; familiarity with model training frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch) is useful but not a primary requirement.\nExperience in AI/ML platform technologies and services such as Azure ML/Sagemaker/Vertex, OpenAI, AutoML, OCR, STT, feature stores, vector databases.\nImplementation of AI/ML architectural patterns and best practices e.g. data drift detection, experimentation tracking, RAG, deployment models\nFamiliarity with database management and basic data pipeline concepts\nProven experience leading development or engineering teams.\nExperience with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, or GCP) with a preference for Azure.\nSolid understanding of API development & microservices architecture, CI/CD pipelines and release workflows, containerisation using Docker, secure coding practices\nComfortable balancing hands-on delivery with strategic responsibilities\nWhat we offer on top:\nDynamic work environment with a highly motivated team.\nExciting career opportunities in a fast-growing international business.\nEntrepreneurial culture, openness, and integrity.\nA comprehensive onboarding and mentoring program as well as employee events\nIndividual development with extensive training and development programs.\nGenerous annual leave and a permanent position.\nHigh-end digital equipment, AI-based tools and hybrid working.\nModern, centrally located office space with a variety of healthy snacks\nAttractive croporate benefits: wellbeing support, E-Leasing, employee events and much more.\nSounds good to you? Apply now!\n\nWe look forward to receiving your application, incl.\n\nLetter of application\nCurriculum vitae\nComplete certificates incl. high school diploma\nEarliest possible start date\nSalary expectations\n\nPlease submit your application via our online application portal.\n\nGET IN TOUCH\nJanina Spottke\nExecutive Assistant to the Managing Directors\nB.B.A. Hons.\nFon: +49 511 64 68 14 – 0\nFax: +49 511 64 68 14 18','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'SKC Beratungsgesellschaft mbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e8c64094008869ef','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2444,NULL,'job','Staff Software Engineer-Greenplum','','Home Office',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'A Little About Us\n\nEDB provides a data and AI platform that enables organizations to harness the full power of Postgres for transactional, analytical, and AI workloads across any cloud, anywhere. EDB empowers enterprises to control risk, manage costs and scale efficiently for a data and AI led world. Serving more than 1,500 customers globally and as the leading contributor to the vibrant and fast-growing PostgreSQL community, EDB supports major government organizations, financial services, media and information technology companies. EDB\'s data-driven solutions enable customers to modernize legacy systems and break data silos while leveraging enterprise-grade open source technologies. EDB delivers the confidence of up to 99.999% high availability with mission critical capabilities built in such as security, compliance controls, and observability. For more information, visit www.enterprisedb.com\n\n**Candidate Note: This position is 100% remote for candidates based in certain countries within EU**\n\nWe are seeking an experienced Software Engineer to design, develop, and maintain our core analytics products including WarehousePG (WHPG), Postgres Analytics Accelerator (PGAA), as well as extensions, migration tools, monitoring systems, and performance optimizations for the PostgreSQL ecosystem.\n\nIn this role, you will be a core contributor within the team responsible for advancing our Analytics product portfolio. You will implement new features, optimize performance, and ensure the stability of our software.\n\nWhat you will be doing:\nDesign and develop PostgreSQL database features and tools.\nReview and refine code contributions from team members to ensure quality.\nWrite and maintain regression tests for bug fixes and new features.\nTroubleshoot and resolve database, network, and software-related issues.\nWork within CI/CD pipelines to ensure smooth integration and deployment.\nWhat you will bring:\n5+ years of database development experience and solid understanding of database principles.\nDeep expertise in at least one of the following: C, Rust, C++ or Go systems programming.\nCS fundamentals (algorithms, OS internals, data structures)\nProficiency in Linux-based software development and debugging.\nExperience optimizing database system performance.\nStrong problem-solving skills in database and system troubleshooting.\nExcellent verbal and written communication skills.\nWhat will give you an edge:\nExperience with distributed databases and MPP systems (e.g., Greenplum) and/or analytical libraries / databases (Spark, DataFusion, DuckDB)\nExperience with distributed query optimizers (e.g. Orca)\nSolid understanding of PostgreSQL internals.\nFamiliarity with machine learning libraries and techniques\nKnowledge of GitHub Actions workflows.\nPrior contributions to open-source database projects.\n\nEDB is committed to supporting our employees\' overall well being by offering a range of benefits and resources to promote a healthy work-life balance and wellness. We provide access to CuraLinc to aid employees in health and wellness tips and practices, as well as Wellness Fridays extending to December 2026! Check out our career site for more information on perks and benefits and reach out to our Talent Acquisition team for region specific benefits.\n\nWe know it takes a unique mix of people and skills to help us in our mission to supercharge Postgres, and we understand that not everyone will check every box. We\'d love to hear from you and we want you to apply!\n\nEDB is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. EDB was built on a commitment to trust and respect each other and to embrace an array of people and ideas. These values remain at the center of our culture and are key to our company\'s integrity.\n\nEDB does not seek or accept unsolicited resumes or CVs from recruitment agencies. EDB and its affiliates are not responsible for, and will not pay, any fees, commissions, or any other similar payment related to unsolicited resumes or CVs except as required in a written signed agreement between EDB and the recruitment agency or party requesting payment of a fee.\n\n#LI-Remote','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'EDB','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=cac3592a95dcef42','scraped','vor 11 Tagen'),(2445,NULL,'job','Werkstudent*in im Bereich Design','Studentenjob','52134 Herzogenrath',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Wen suchen wir?\n\nDu übernimmst designbezogene Aufgaben für interaktive Prototypen und Produkte\nDu gestaltest Benutzeroberflächen für digitale und physische HMI‑Lösungen\nDu führst Nutzerinterviews durch und nimmst an Workshops teil, einschließlich der Unterstützung bei der Strukturierung von Erkenntnissen und der Erstellung von Ergebnispräsentationen\nDu erstellst grafische Designs auf Basis von Wireframes\nDu arbeitest an der Entwicklung von Prototypen mit\nDu unterstützt die Teams aus Marketing, Innovation und Vertrieb bei Designfragen\n\nWer bringt uns voran?\n\nDu bist aktuell in einem Bachelor‑ oder Masterstudium eingeschrieben, z. B. in User Experience Design, Interaction Design, Human‑Machine Interaction, Industriedesign, Design Thinking oder einem vergleichbaren Studiengang\nDu verfügst über gute Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\nDu gehst sicher mit Microsoft Office um, insbesondere mit Outlook und PowerPoint\nErste Erfahrungen mit Figma oder einer vergleichbaren Anwendung sind von Vorteil\n\nWas noch wichtig ist!\n\nWir wertschätzen Vielfalt und begrüßen alle Onlinebewerbungen - unabhängig von Geschlecht, Nationalität, ethnischer und sozialer Herkunft, Religion/Weltanschauung, Behinderung, Alter sowie sexueller Orientierung und Identität. Bei uns zählt jede individuelle Geschichte!\n\nVorab Fragen? Laura Klemm (02406 822452) beantwortet diese gerne!\n\nMehr zu uns\n\nWillkommen bei Saint-Gobain\n\n\"MAKING THE WORLD A BETTER HOME\" – Das ist unser Ziel! Mit unserem vielfältigen Markenportfolio gestalten wir als Innovationsführer Materialien und Lösungen für Bau und Industrie. Unsere integrierten Lösungen für die Renovierung öffentlicher und privater Gebäude, für den Leichtbau und die Dekarbonisierung des Bausektors und der Industrie werden in einem kontinuierlichen Innovationsprozess entwickelt.\n\nAls globaler Top Employer mit rund 160.000 Mitarbeiter*innen in 75+ Ländern setzen wir auf Nachhaltigkeit und Spitzenleistung.\n\nReady to join the journey? #WeMakeTheWorldABetterHome\n\nUnsere Benefits\n\nVielseitigkeit - die Arbeit in einem internationalen Konzern, der zugleich sehr mittelständisch geprägt ist\nGesundheit und Sicherheit - Gesundheitsmaßnahmen, Fitness-Angebote, Betriebsarzt und Employee Assistance Program (EAP Assist) für mentales Wohlbefinden sowie ein Mitarbeiter-Hilfsfonds\nWeiterentwicklung und Perspektiven - passgenau für Ihre persönliche Karriere, persönliche Personalentwicklungsprogramme, eigene E-Learning Plattform, Trainingsangebote (auch international) in unserer Saint-Gobain Academy\nWir fördern Diversity - gerade auch die Förderung von Frauen in Führungspositionen ist uns ein besonderes Anliegen\nNachhaltigkeitsorientierung gemäß unseres Purpose „MAKING THE WORLD A BETTER HOME“\n\nHinweis: Unsere Benefits können je nach Position & Standort variieren\n\nMehr zum Team\n\nDas Team von Saint-Gobain lebt Vielfalt, Innovation und Zusammenarbeit. In einem Umfeld, das unterschiedliche Perspektiven schätzt, arbeiten unsere Teams an nachhaltigen Lösungen für Bauen und Wohnen – mit besonderem Fokus auf Energieeffizienz und Umweltschutz. Kontinuierliche Weiterbildung und Entwicklungsmöglichkeiten fördern dabei die persönliche und berufliche Entfaltung der Mitarbeitenden.\n\nZuhören, Austausch, Fürsorge, Solidarität, Vertrauen und Respekt vor Unterschieden bilden den Kern unserer Unternehmenskultur.\n\nUnser Rekrutierungsprozess\n\nSaint-Gobain sucht authentische Talente (m/w/d)! Nach einer ersten Sichtung der Bewerbungsunterlagen findet ein informelles Telefon- oder Onlineinterview statt. Dabei können Bewerbende ihre Skills und Teamfähigkeit zeigen. Das persönliche Gespräch vor Ort ermöglicht Einblicke ins Unternehmen. Authentizität ist dabei das A und O – wir wollen nicht nur die Fähigkeiten, sondern auch die Persönlichkeit hinter dem Lebenslauf kennenlernen. So stellen wir sicher, dass man nicht nur zum Job, sondern auch zu unserem Team und unserer Kultur passt.\n\n✨ Join us and let\'s build a brighter future together!\n\nHinweis: Unser Rekrutierungsprozess kann je nach Position & Standort variieren\n\nJob Reference: DEU01695','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Saint Gobain','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=cf89b4078a25a3e5','scraped','vor 11 Tagen'),(2446,NULL,'job','Senior/Staff Product Manager','','10827 Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'At Blacklane, we are building the future of sustainable chauffeur-driven mobility. Our Marketplace team plays a crucial role in providing chauffeur partners with the right offers to help them fill their schedules and grow their businesses. We are seeking a Senior/Staff Product Manager to take ownership of this vital area, ensuring a seamless and optimized marketplace experience that supports our partners and guarantees guests a reliable and premium ride.\n\nYOUR CHALLENGE:\n\nAs a Senior/Staff Product Manager for the Marketplace team, you will:\n\nDrive the strategy and execution of features that show tailored offers to our partners, allowing them to pick those that align with their preferences.\nOwn and optimize the end-to-end partner experience in the marketplace, from offer creation to selection.\nCollaborate cross-functionally with engineering, data, and operations teams to deliver impactful product improvements.\nDevelop data-driven insights to identify opportunities that enhance the efficiency of our partner scheduling process and ensure no guest requests go unmet.\nPrioritize the right projects that align with business goals, balancing partner needs with guest experience requirements.\nMaintain a strong understanding of partner behaviors and market dynamics to adjust the marketplace strategy and product roadmap.\nAct as the main liaison between partners, product, and the wider business to ensure the marketplace achieves its goals.\n\nABOUT YOU:\n\nWe\'re looking for someone who brings:\n\n5+ years of product management experience, at least 2 years as a Senior Product Manager.\nProven success in managing end-to-end product lifecycles and launching data-driven product improvements.\nStrong analytical skills with a data-driven mindset.\nExcellent communication and stakeholder management skills, with the ability to articulate complex concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.\nExperience working closely with engineering and design teams to deliver successful outcomes.\nYou have worked directly with Data Science or Machine Learning Teams.\nA collaborative mindset and the ability to thrive in a fast-paced, agile environment.\nBonus points if you have experience working with logistics, transportation, or B2B marketplace products.\n\nAbout Blacklane\n\nOur mission is simple but powerful: to become the world\'s leading premium, global chauffeur service. Operating in 50+ countries, we reimagine chauffeur-driven rides by prioritizing reliability, innovation, and first-class service at every step. Blacklane is also at the forefront of sustainable mobility efforts, continuously working to reduce our operational impact on the planet.\n\nOur Company Culture & Values\n\nBlacklane has grown from a two-person startup in Berlin to a global team of over 300 people representing 54+ nationalities. Our culture is powered by our commitment to three core values: Care, Drive and Excellence.\n\nCare - We are invested in each other\'s well-being and professional growth.\n\nDrive - We act with pace and determination. We are ambitious, committed to a growth mindset, and champion ownership and delivery.\n\nExcellence - We understand our customers so we can exceed expectations.\n\nWe support our people through initiatives like Employee Resource Groups (ERGs), mentorship programs that bring our values to life.\n\nWe welcome—and actively support—employees to create or join the communities that are important to them.\n\n✨ Why join Blacklane?\n\nAt Blacklane, our Compensation and Benefits strategies are designed to be fair and market-aligned. We combine base salary with variable elements and long-term incentives as part of our overall rewards framework.\n\nIn addition, we offer a benefits package tailored to each location, supporting health, wellbeing, time off, learning, and local needs. Some of the benefits for this role and country include:\n\nLocal perks – Germany (Berlin HQ)\n\n Monthly BVG / Deutschlandticket subsidy to support your commute\n Private pension plan with 20% employer contribution up to a monthly cap\n Subsidised healthy meals & snacks via our in‑office Foodji vending machine\n 28 vacation days per year, increasing with tenure\n Your Mental and Physical Health → No compromise with Nilo and Wellhub\n Hybrid setup: 3 days a week in our Berlin HQ, right in the heart of Schöneberg\n Continuous learning & certified coaching\n Fair pay and benefits tailored to local markets\n Mystery Rides: Quarterly Voucher to enjoy personal trips around the world with Blacklane and experience our service from a guest\'s perspective.\n\nDo you have any questions or want to know more about our way of working? Feel free to contact us. We\'re happy to connect!\n\nWe place great value on equal opportunities. Therefore, we welcome everyone to apply!\n\nCurious to see us in action? Let\'s go!\n\n→ Watch us on Amazon Prime\n\n→ Listen to our CEO in Startup insider episode #1643\n\n→ Blacklane is backed by investors who share our vision: Mercedes-Benz Mobility, Tasaru, Sixt, the Al Fahim Group, Alstin Capital, RI Digital Ventures, and b2venture','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'BLACKLANE','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=7b00fce08a5adf67','scraped','vor 11 Tagen'),(2447,NULL,'job','AI Acoustic Engineer (m/f/d) – UAV Localization & Signal Processing','Vollzeit','80807 München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'What we offer\n\nWork in an international, agile team creating the future of autonomous systems\nGrow your career in a expanding and ambitious engineering team\nBuild innovative products using state-of-the-art technologies in AI, robotics, and autonomy\nBenefit from a steep learning curve and continuous development\nEnjoy team events and a strong, collaborative culture\n\nYour mission\n\nDevelop and deploy AI-driven acoustic sensing systems for UAV detection, classification, localization, and tracking\nDesign, train, and extend custom neural network architectures for analyzing acoustic signatures, noise patterns, and audio anomalies\nOptimize real-time audio signal processing pipelines for UAV swarm coordination, defense systems, and stealth detection\nApply microphone array processing, acoustic beamforming, Doppler analysis, and advanced noise reduction techniques to improve UAV audio sensing performance\nLead hands-on efforts in data collection, labeling, augmentation, and training for complex, custom acoustic datasets\nIntegrate AI-powered acoustic models into multi-modal sensor fusion frameworks (Radar, RF, EO/IR, LiDAR)\nEnsure compliance with defense and aerospace standards (MIL-STD, ITAR, NATO STANAGs, IEC acoustic systems)\n\nYour profile\n\nExtensive, hands-on experience in AI-driven audio signal processing, acoustics, or acoustic sensing\nDeep knowledge of neural network models for sound applications, including detection, classification, and localization\nDemonstrated ability to design, modify, and extend network architectures, not limited to off-the-shelf models\nStrong background in microphone array processing, acoustic beamforming, sound localization, and noise reduction\nProven experience with data acquisition, labeling pipelines, augmentation strategies, and training models from scratch or adapting them to custom classes\nSolid understanding of real-time DSP and AI-enhanced signal processing systems\nHigh proficiency in Python and PyTorch, with practical experience using audio processing libraries and frameworks\n\nNice to have\n\nExperience with acoustic sensing in military or defense environments, including UAV surveillance and stealth detection\nKnowledge of psychoacoustics, bio-inspired hearing models, or advanced acoustic modeling\nFamiliarity with ROS-based systems, real-time environments, and C++\nExperience deploying, optimizing, and maintaining machine learning models in production or embedded systems\nBackground in adversarial AI for sound recognition, acoustic anomaly detection, or sonar intelligence\n\nWhat else\n\nIntrinsic motivation, attention to detail, and strong problem-solving mindset\nCreative thinker with a structured and systematic approach\nHumble and collaborative — prioritizes collective success over individual recognition\nHigh ethical standards and disciplined work ethic\nExtra-curricular leadership or achievements are a bonus\nFluent in English\nNationality of a NATO member nation or close ally is required\n\nAbout us\n\nThe world is changing. Exponential technologies are enabling new types of security threats. ATS is committed to staying ahead by building nimble, scalable, and cost-effective defences. We are looking for passionate team members who are eager to create exceptional products, safeguard our freedom, and strengthen the resilience of democracies.\n\nWho we are: Autonomous Teaming is a defence-tech start-up specializing in machine vision solutions. Driven by cutting-edge innovation, our team works on next-generation technologies designed to meet rapidly evolving security challenges.\n\nWhat we do: We develop systems that enable computers and sensors to operate as coordinated teams, collaborating in real time to counter AI-powered asymmetric threats at scale — including drone swarms and other UXVs. Our mission is to build resilient, intelligent defence capabilities that perform reliably in the most demanding environments.\n\nHow we work: We value close, in-person collaboration as the foundation for building complex, high-impact technology, while maintaining flexibility aligned to role and team needs. Our culture is built on ownership, responsibility, and trust — with a shared commitment to growing and building together.\n\nWhere we are: Based in Munich, Berlin, and Toulouse, we are expanding rapidly across Europe with plans to open additional office hubs.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'autonomous-teaming','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=537fc38ab123264d','scraped','vor 12 Tagen'),(2448,NULL,'job','ML Data Engineer (m/f/d) - Sensor Data & Pipelines','Vollzeit','80807 München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'What we offer\n\nWork in an international, agile team creating the future of autonomous systems\nGrow your career in a expanding and ambitious engineering team\nBuild innovative products using state-of-the-art technologies in AI, robotics, and autonomy\nBenefit from a steep learning curve and continuous development\nEnjoy team events and a strong, collaborative culture\n\nYour mission\n\nThis role sits at the core of our perception systems, owning the data that directly drives model performance in real-world environments. You will work closely with ML, perception, and robotics teams, focusing on building, curating, and continuously improving datasets behind object detection — turning raw sensor data into reliable, high-performing systems.\n\nYou will take end-to-end ownership of the ML data lifecycle, from data collection and ingestion to labeling, quality assurance, and continuous dataset improvement, ensuring data is representative, high-quality, and production-ready.\n\nWhat you\'ll do:\n\nDesign and maintain scalable pipelines to ingest, organize, and preprocess large volumes of time-series camera and multi-sensor data (RGB, IR, thermal, depth, IMU)\nOwn and continuously improve object detection datasets, ensuring quality, diversity, and statistical representativeness\nBuild and operate active learning loops, connecting model performance with data selection and improvement\nManage labeling workflows end-to-end, including tooling, QA validation, consistency checks, and coordination of annotation efforts\nCollaborate with ML Engineers to evaluate models and translate weaknesses, bias, and drift into actionable dataset improvements\nPlan and execute data collection campaigns (e.g. field recordings, drone/video capture) to acquire high-value real-world data\nCreate internal tools and dashboards to analyze dataset quality, distributions, and performance gaps\n\nYour profile\n\nStrong experience in Python and data processing frameworks (Pandas, NumPy, vectorized operations, multiprocessing).\nHands-on experience building ETL/ELT pipelines for ingesting, transforming, and structuring large video and sensor datasets.\nExperience with data orchestration and lifecycle management for ML and computer vision workflows, including dataset versioning and reproducibility.\nSolid understanding of object detection pipelines (Detectron2, MMDetection, COCO format, bounding-box standards).\nExperience with active learning, uncertainty sampling, or semi-supervised dataset workflows.\nFamiliarity with data annotation platforms (CVAT, Label Studio) and automated QA/consistency checks.\nStrong grasp of evaluation metrics for object detection (IoU, mAP, precision-recall curves, class-wise metrics).\nComfortable with databases (SQL/NoSQL), file systems, and the management of large-scale image, video, and sensor datasets.\nAbility to work cross-functionally with perception, deployment, robotics, and data infrastructure teams.\nFluent in English, German and/or French are a plus\n\nNice to have\n\nExperience with cloud storage and MLOps tools (AWS S3, MinIO, ClearML, MLFlow, Weights & Biases).\nFamiliarity with ROS / robotics data formats (bag files, TF trees, sensor_msgs), Docker, or embedded ML workflows.\nPrior work with robotics, drones, or multi-sensor perception systems, including IR, LiDAR, radar, or audio datasets.\n\nWhat else\n\nOutside-the-box creativity with a blend of conceptual and systematic design thinking.\nHigh intrinsic motivation, attention to detail, and strong problem-solving mindset.\nStructured, methodical, and reliable execution, even under uncertainty.\nHumble, collaborative, and mission-driven — values collective success over ego.\nHigh ethical standards and disciplined work ethic.\nExtra-curricular achievements, leadership, or unique projects are a plus.\nNATO-aligned nationality or close ally citizenship is required.\n\nWhy us?\n\nJoin us to shape the future of AI-driven defense!\n\nAbout us\n\nThe world is changing. Exponential technologies are enabling new types of security threats. ATS is committed to staying ahead by building nimble, scalable, and cost-effective defences. We are looking for passionate team members who are eager to create exceptional products, safeguard our freedom, and strengthen the resilience of democracies.\n\nWho we are: Autonomous Teaming is a defence-tech start-up specializing in machine vision solutions. Driven by cutting-edge innovation, our team works on next-generation technologies designed to meet rapidly evolving security challenges.\n\nWhat we do: We develop systems that enable computers and sensors to operate as coordinated teams, collaborating in real time to counter AI-powered asymmetric threats at scale — including drone swarms and other UXVs. Our mission is to build resilient, intelligent defence capabilities that perform reliably in the most demanding environments.\n\nHow we work: We value close, in-person collaboration as the foundation for building complex, high-impact technology, while maintaining flexibility aligned to role and team needs. Our culture is built on ownership, responsibility, and trust — with a shared commitment to growing and building together.\n\nWhere we are: Based in Munich, Berlin, and Toulouse, we are expanding rapidly across Europe with plans to open additional office hubs.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'autonomous-teaming','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=3118223c149abd81','scraped','vor 12 Tagen'),(2449,NULL,'job','Senior Data Engineer (m/f/d)','','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About the Job\n\nWe\'re looking for a motivated Senior Data Engineer (m/f/d) to join our Data & Analytics team and support its data strategies.\n\nIn your day-to-day work, you\'ll focus on building data-driven applications and get the opportunity to contribute to various projects.\n\nOur Data & Analytics team enables our clients to grow sustainably as they shift from intuitive to objective decision-making through reliable data collection, proper data infrastructure implementation, and effective data initiatives.\n\nWe firmly believe that the decade of data has begun: powerful technologies are readily accessible to turn raw data into real insights, products, features and more. We are looking for capable talents from various backgrounds to tag along on our journey to utilise data to create real impact via scalable data ML/AI infrastructure, thorough analyses and meaningful relationships to ensure proper application.\n\nIn this role, you\'ll:\nBuild high-quality data warehouses, cloud infrastructure, AI workflows, etc.\nIntegrate data from various systems into flexible and consistent representations\nExplore and evaluate the lasting impact of AI use cases and their implementation\nEnsure that all people and IT systems in the organisation have easy access to data, through various front-ends and interfaces\nWork in an agile software development process and collaborate closely with the Analytics team\nImpact the business while working in an amazing cross-functional team environment\nYour Profile\nGenuine interest in data and algorithms, and an excitement for solving difficult business problems through scalable data products\nKnowledge of version control systems, web technologies, software engineering best practices, and the inner workings of database systems\nSolid experience with SQL, Python and dbt\nExperience with machine learning and/or AI is preferred\nThe ability to turn data science into something that creates business value - is a plus\nDesire to learn new things (we know you can \"fly at least one type of plane\", and we will provide you with many types and variations of said plane)\nGood communication skills in English (native/full working proficiency)\nA degree in computer science or a comparable qualification\n\nPlease note that we are looking for support in our Berlin office.\n\nWhy Join A11:\nShape the Future of Innovation: Take the lead on game-changing projects across a diverse range of companies and geographies. You\'ll make a true impact through our strategic and hands-on working style.\nCollaborate with an International Team of Digital Natives: Unlock new opportunities to learn, contribute, and thrive in a dynamic, multicultural environment. Our Team represents over 25 nationalities and brings experience in a wide range of companies and industries.\nCareer Development: We support growth in every direction—whether you want to deepen your expertise, lead a department or explore new areas.\nEmbrace Change and New Technologies: We actively try out new tools and AI features to optimise our workflows and processes, giving you creative freedom and autonomy to reach your goals.\nExchange and Discover: From shared meals with the Team to fun offsites to frequently hosted meetups, you\'ll build lasting connections through regular events and dynamic knowledge-sharing opportunities.\n\nIf you\'re looking to accelerate growth and generate high impact, we want to hear from you!\n\nOur Commitment to Diversity and Inclusion\n\nA11 is committed to diversity and equal opportunities for all – applicants and employees alike. We value humans – with all our glorious multifaceted backgrounds, perspectives, and experiences. Our diverse team has different ethnic and cultural origins, gender identities, sexual orientations, family arrangements, religious and political affiliations, socioeconomic statuses, age groups, and abilities.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'A11','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=fab0dc66bca5a745','scraped','vor 11 Tagen'),(2450,NULL,'job','Ranking Expert / Ranking Engineer (m/w/d)','Teilzeit','80539 München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Die Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München ist eine der führenden Universitäten in Europa mit einer über 500-jährigen Tradition. Sie steht für anspruchsvolle akademische Ausbildung und herausragende Forschung.\n\nEinrichtung Hochschulleitung - Referat VIII.1 - Universitätsstruktur, strategisches Berichtswesen Vergütung TV-L Umfang Vollzeit (100%) Besetzungsdatum Zum nächstmöglichen Zeitpunkt (Die Stelle ist vorerst auf zwei Jahre befristet, eine Entfristung wird angestrebt)\n\nDas sind wir:\n\nDas Referat Universitätsstruktur, strategisches Berichtswesen ist Teil der Research and Strategy Services Division. Es berät die Hochschulleitung zu Fragen der Entwicklung der gesamten Universität und begleitet die datengestützte Qualitätsentwicklung in Forschung und Lehre; hierzu gehört auch die Betreuung von Hochschulrankings und der zugrundeliegenden datenbasierten Analyseverfahren.\n\nWir suchen Sie:\n\nRanking Expert / Ranking Engineer (m/w/d)\n\nam Standort München\n\nDas sind Ihre Aufgaben:\nMitarbeit im zentralen Ranking-Team der Universität und Weiterentwicklung bestehender Ranking-Strategien\nAnalyse nationaler und internationaler Hochschulrankings sowie deren Methodiken und Indikatoren\nAufbereitung, Validierung und Interpretation komplexer Daten (z.B. bibliometrische Daten, Drittmittel, Reputation, Internationalisierung)\nAufbau, Pflege und Weiterentwicklung von Datenmodellen zur Unterstützung von Rankingprozessen; hierbei Entwicklung von Szenarioanalysen und Simulationen zur strategischen Verbesserung von Rankingpositionen\nMitwirkung an strategischen Projekten im Bereich Datenstrategie, Performance Measurement und Hochschulentwicklung\nBeratung interner Stakeholder in den Fakultäten zu Ranking-relevanten Kennzahlen und Maßnahmen\nBeobachtung und Einordnung externer Entwicklungen durch Teilnahme an Fachnetzwerken, Konferenzen und Arbeitsgruppen im Bereich Rankings und Research Analytics; hierbei aktive Vernetzung mit nationalen und internationalen Benchmark-Universitäten sowie Austausch mit Rankingbetreibern\nBeobachtung internationaler Entwicklungen im Bereich Ranking-Methodik, Research Analytics und KI-gestützter Auswertung\nDas sind Sie:\nIhr wissenschaftliches Hochschulstudium (Master oder vergleichbar), idealerweise in Data Science, Mathematik, Informatik, Wirtschafts- oder Sozialwissenschaften haben Sie mit sehr gutem Ergebnis abgeschlossen.\nSie bringen Erfahrung im Bereich Hochschulrankings und Forschungsbewertung mit, bevorzugt an einer Universität, Forschungseinrichtung oder bei einem Ranking-Anbieter.\nSie verfügen über ausgeprägte Fähigkeiten in der Analyse verschiedener Daten sowie Erfahrung im Umgang mit großen, heterogenen Datensätzen.\nSie haben fundierte Kenntnisse in quantitativen Methoden, Statistik und/oder mathematischer Modellierung und bringen die notwendigen Erfahrungen mit Datenanalyse-Tools mit. Erfahrungen im Einsatz von KI-Methoden / Machine Learning im Analysekontext runden Ihr Profil ab.\nSie bringen komplexe Themen auf den Punkt – klar, verständlich und zielgruppengerecht, egal ob im Austausch mit Expertinnen und Experten oder in der Kommunikation mit der Hochschulleitung.\nSie denken analytisch, arbeiten strukturiert und haben den Anspruch, aus Daten und Herausforderungen konkrete, umsetzbare Lösungen zu entwickeln.\nSie arbeiten gern im Team, bringen eigene Ideen ein und schätzen den offenen Austausch in einem interdisziplinären Umfeld. Im internationalen Umfeld bewegen Sie sich sicher und kommunizieren souverän auf Englisch – mündlich wie schriftlich.\nDas ist unser Angebot:\n\nFreuen Sie sich auf verantwortungsvolle und abwechslungsreiche Aufgaben an der größten deutschen Universität. Sie arbeiten mitten in München, unweit vom Englischen Garten. Ein umfangreiches Fort- und Weiterbildungsangebot wartet auf Sie.\n\nDie Vereinbarkeit von Beruf und Familie ist uns wichtig: Sie haben bei uns die Möglichkeit zu Teilzeit, mobilem Arbeiten sowie flexible Arbeitszeiten. Die Vergütung erfolgt nach dem Tarifvertrag der Länder (). Die Stelle ist vorerst auf zwei Jahre befristet, eine Entfristung wird angestrebt.\n\nDie LMU hat die „Charta der Vielfalt“ unterzeichnet und engagiert sich für die Diversität ihrer Beschäftigten. Wir begrüßen daher alle Bewerbungen – unabhängig von Geschlecht, Nationalität, ethnischer und sozialer Herkunft, Religion/Weltanschauung, Behinderung, Alter sowie sexueller Orientierung und Identität.\n\nEine Teilzeitbeschäftigung ist grundsätzlich möglich.\n\nSchwerbehinderte Personen werden bei im Wesentlichen gleicher Qualifikation bevorzugt.\n\nKontakt:\n\nBitte reichen Sie Ihre aussagekräftige Bewerbung bis spätestens 21.05.2026 über unser Bewerbungsportal ein.\n\nFür Rückfragen steht Ihnen im Referat Universitätsstruktur, Strategisches Berichtswesen Katrin Mayer () zur Verfügung.\n\nWo Wissenschaft alles ist.\n\nAn der LMU arbeiten Wissenschaftlerinnen und Wissenschaftler auf höchstem Niveau an den Zukunftsfragen um Mensch, Gesellschaft, Kultur, Umwelt und Technologie, unterstützt durch kompetente Beschäftigte in Verwaltung, IT und Technik.\n\nIm Rahmen Ihrer Bewerbung auf eine Stelle an der LMU übermitteln Sie personenbezogene Daten. Beachten Sie bitte hierzu die für den Internetauftritt. Durch die Übermittlung Ihrer Bewerbung bestätigen Sie, dass Sie die Datenschutzinformationen zur Kenntnis genommen haben und mit der Datenverarbeitung im Rahmen des Auswahlverfahrens einverstanden sind.\n\nLudwig-Maximilians-Universität München\nGeschwister-Scholl-Platz 1\n80539 München','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=21f35eed1b72e02c','scraped','vor 11 Tagen'),(2451,NULL,'job','Data & Analytics Engineer (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','60326 Frankfurt am Main',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Wir bei Log-hub entwickeln innovative und massgeschneiderte Daten-, Analytics- und AI-Lösungen in der Nische von Supply Chain & Logistik. Dadurch befähigen wir unsere Kunden mehr aus Daten zu machen, schaffen Transparenz und bieten intelligente und moderne Entscheidungsunterstützung.\n\nWir sind ein Unternehmen mit flachen Hierarchien, kreativen Köpfen und innovativen Technologien! Jeder kann sich bei uns einbringen und zum Experten werden. Der Wissensaustausch und die gegenseitige Unterstützung sind zentrale Erfolgsfaktoren. We’re ONE Team mit dem Motto HAVE FUN!\n\nSchliesst du dein Studium in kommender Zeit erfolgreich ab, oder hast du dein Studium bereits erfolgreich abgeschlossen und suchst den perfekten Einstieg? Dann freuen wir uns auf deine Bewerbung.\n\n*Deine Challenges*\n\n* Zusammen mit dem Kunden definierst du die Bedürfnisse, die für die Daten-Projekte relevant sind\n* Du spezifizierst die technischen Aspekte und implementierst Data Pipelines mit modernen Technologien (Azure Cloud, Google Cloud, AWS, KNIME, etc.)\n* Du entwickelst individuelle Lösungen mit intelligenten Algorithmen für grosse Datensets vom Aufbau der Architektur bis hin zur Visualisierung der Ergebnisse in aussagekräftigen Dashboards\n* Du konzipierst und implementierst Simulations- und What-if-Modelle, um komplexe Supply-Chain- und Logistikentscheidungen datenbasiert zu bewerten und zu unterstützen\n* Du bist in einem mixed Team (Log-hub & Kunde) und agierst als Bindeglied und Übersetzer zwischen Fachbereich, IT und der Lösungsentwicklung\n* Es macht dir Spass, dich in taktisch und strategischen Supply Chain & Logistik Herausforderungen auszutoben - Customized Demand Forecasting, automatisierte Optimierung von Touren, Netzwerk Design Analysen, Änderung von Produktionsstandorten basierend der BOM, etc.\n\n*Das bringst du mit*\n\n* Abgeschlossenes Studium (Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Wirtschaftsingenieurwesen, Mathematik, Physik, o.ä.) mit der Leidenschaft, sich schnell in neue Themen einzuarbeiten\n* Erste Erfahrungen im Data Engineering/Analytics Bereich z.B. im Rahmen eines Praktikums oder Traineeprogramms\n* Leidenschaft für innovativen Technologien, Methoden und Themen wie Data Engineering, Analytics, Machine Learning, AI, Big Data, Simulationen, Cloud-Plattformen, sowie agilen Arbeitsweisen (z.B. Scrum)\n* Erste Erfahrungen in Daten Technologien sind von Vorteil, z.B. Microsoft Azure Synapse/Fabric, Databricks/Spark, Snowflake, Google BigLake, AWS Lake Formation, etc.\n* Teamplayer mit starken kommunikativen Fähigkeiten, der seine Expertise kundgibt\n* Professionelles Auftreten und fliessende Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse\n\n*Das sind unsere Benefits für dich*\n\n* Entwicklung + Perspektive: Individuelle Weiterbildungs- und Entwicklungsmöglichkeiten basierend auf deinen Karrierevorstellungen, sowie die Möglichkeit schnell Verantwortung zu übernehmen\n* 60-80% Home Office mit Arbeitsort im süddeutschen Raum oder der deutschsprachigen Schweiz mit flexibler Arbeitszeitgestaltung\n* BYOD-Guthaben für die Arbeitsplatzgestaltung nach deinen individuellen Bedürfnissen\n* Garantierte Abwechslung: Verschiedene Kunden, Themen, Methoden und Technologien – als Data & Analytics Engineer wird es dir bei uns nicht langweilig\n\nBist du technisch affin und hast Freude an Kundenkontakt und Beratung? Magst du es technisch hands-on zu arbeiten? Dann ist Log-hub genau das richtige Unternehmen!\n\n*Wir bitten dich, deine Bewerbung auf Englisch an careers@log-hub.com zu senden.*\n\nArt der Stelle: Vollzeit\n\n\n\nBewerbungsfrage(n):\n* Sind Sie rechtlich befugt, in diesem Land zu arbeiten: Deutschland?\n\nAusbildung:\n* Bachelor (Erforderlich)\n\nSprache:\n* Deutsch (Erforderlich)\n\nArbeitsort: Zum Teil im Homeoffice in 60326 Frankfurt am Main','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'LOG-HUB AG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=366fa351199a040e','scraped','vor 12 Tagen'),(2452,NULL,'job','Data Engineer – Drilling & Well Operations (m/f/d)','Vollzeit','76227 Karlsruhe',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We want you for...\n\nVercana GmbH is a leading company in the field of Drilling & Well Engineering, known for the high technical standards in the planning and execution of demanding drilling projects. By applying state‑of‑the‑art technologies with a strong focus on safety, environment and sustainable processes, we actively contribute to the energy transition. Our core expertise lies in well design and the operation of drilling rigs for geothermal energy and lithium mining.\n\nTo strengthen our team at our Karlsruhe office location, we are looking for a full‑time (40 hours/week), permanent Drilling & Well Data Engineer (m/f/d).\n\nYour mission\n\nDesign, development and operation of reliable data pipelines for drilling and well operations\nCollection, processing and quality assurance of real‑time rig data, including sensor and time‑series data\nImplementation and monitoring of automated data flows from rig systems to central data platforms\nDevelopment and validation of machine‑learning models,eg for drilling parameter prediction\nAnalysis of daily drilling and operational data to identify performance, safety and cost deviations\nCreation of data‑driven insights to optimize drilling performance\nDevelopment of automated operational cost‑tracking solutions\nEstablish solid data orchestration & data warehousing procedures\nDevelopment, maintenance and continuous optimization of analytics, reporting and dashboard workflows\nDocumentation of data models, pipelines and analytical outputs for operational use\n\nYour profile\n\nDegree in Computer Science, Engineering or a comparable technical field\nExperience in data engineering, ideally in industrial or energy‑related environments\nHands‑on experience in developing, training and operationalizing machine‑learning models\nExperienced in building data models for cost tracking and project controlling\nAbility to structure, process and analyze large and heterogeneous datasets\nWorking with cloud platforms (AWS)\nStrong analytical mindset and structured problem‑solving skills\nClear communication skills and the ability to work effectively in interdisciplinary teams\nBasic understanding of drilling & well operations and key drilling parameters\nSpecifically:\nSolid expertise in SQL and experience with relational as well as time‑series databases\nStrong proficiency in Python (e.g. Pandas, NumPy, Scikit‑learn),\nIntegrated LLMs into data workflows to automate the extraction of structured data from unstructured sources.\nDeveloped automated pipelines utilizing Prompt Engineering and RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) to enhance data accessibility.\nLeveraging AI tools (e.g., GitHub, Copilot, ChatGPT) to accelerate code documentation, unit testing, and SQL optimization\n\nWe offer\n\nResponsible position with creative freedom in a future-oriented company\nCollaboration on groundbreaking projects in the field of geothermal energy and lithium mining\nIndividual training and development opportunities as well as targeted mentoring by experienced colleagues\nModern working environment and a collegial, appreciative team\nLong-term prospects in an industry with great growth potential\nAttractive compensation package and benefits\n\nWe are looking forward to meeting you!\n\nInterested? Simply send us your resume using the application form and tell us why you would like to join Vercana. If you have any questions, please contact Robert Ritschel (Well Construction Manager) at jobs@v-ca.eu.\n\n*** Please note that all applications must be completed using the application form - we do not accept applications via email. ***\n\nAbout us\n\nAt Vulcan, we are united by the idea of a more sustainable and independent supply of energy and raw materials for Europe. We are pioneers in the field of CO2-neutral lithium extraction using a direct lithium extraction process and have developed an innovative and forward-looking technology for this purpose. We bring together talents and experts from over 40 nations and work passionately on the planning and construction of geothermal and lithium extraction plants, which we will operate ourselves in order to accelerate the climate-neutral mobility and energy industry. With companies such as Stellantis and Renault, we already have strong partners who are supporting us on our way to becoming a market leader.\n\nBe the first with us!','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Vulcan Energie Ressourcen GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=51733599d0ee68a6','scraped','vor 11 Tagen'),(2453,NULL,'job','Senior Data Engineer/Data Ops (m/f/d)','','Home Office',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Senior Data Engineer/Data Ops (m/f/d)\n\nRemote EMEA/ Remote India\n________________________\n\nHello I am Adriano, Machine Learning Lead at Kayzen, and I am now looking for a Senior Data Engineer who will be a part of the machine learning engineering team bridging the gap between data science and ad systems engineering team\n\nBut wait, you have not heard of Kayzen before?\n\nKayzen is a mobile demand-side platform (DSP) dedicated to democratizing programmatic advertising. We enable leading apps, agencies, media buyers, and brands to run programmatic customer acquisition, retargeting, and brand performance campaigns through our self-serve and managed service options. Built on the three core pillars of performance, transparency, and control, Kayzen powers the world\'s best mobile marketing teams with bespoke solutions that fuel business growth and deliver a competitive advantage. With an unprecedented scale of 300B+ daily ad requests from 1.6B+ unique users worldwide, we serve up to 1B+ ads per day in 180 countries. Kayzen is accessible through our APIs and user interface.\n\nThe role\n\nAre you excited about data? Will you take on the challenge to help us make Kayzen a ML first organization leading the AdTech space? Do you want to change the way we as an organization manage our data and do business? Are you interested in how billions of data points flow through various systems & data pipelines and how it is governed to generate knowledge and value? If your answer is \"yes\" to all these questions, if you are a problem solver and a team player, we would love to meet you!\n\nDay to day\n\nAs a Data Engineer/Data Ops, you will work to create innovative solutions for handling peta-bytes of data with billions of rows & joins. Your work can vary from creating real time and offline features generation pipelines to managing our data infrastructure to be reliable and fast!\nYou\'ll be responsible for:\n\nProgram and maintain our data pipelines that fuels our on-premise/cloud data warehouse used to generate and serve our models\nMaintain and improve our fleet of data servers (the software), making sure they are reliable and able to process our billions of logs and data points\nDevelop and productionize data pipelines for our ML models in both bare-metal and the cloud environment.\nMake suggestions and lead projects to improve our data processing capabilities\nContribute to the team enabling us to be always better\n\nSounds like you?\n\nWe are looking for a candidate with a minimum 5+ yrs of professional experience in creating and maintaining big data pipelines, identifying data related process improvements, maintaining Kubernetes, Hadoop and Spark infrastructure.\n\nBachelor\'s/Master\'s degree in a quantitative field of Mathematics, Physics, Computer Science, Machine learning Engineering, Business Analytics, Information Management or related field.\nYou know relevant programming languages (Python, Java, etc)\nExpert in SQL & NoSQL and big data processing pipelines (we use Python, Spark, Airflow)\nHave proven experience managing data infrastructure that can store and process Petabytes of data (we use Hadoop, Spark)\nKubernetes wizard. LLM symbiotic.\nYou have proven affinity with data\nYou have strong analytical and problem-solving skills\nYou can translate business requirements into data solutions\nYou have excellent stakeholder management skills.\nPrevious experience with Clickhouse is a plus\nPrevious experience with ad-tech is a plus\nExperience with Real time big data processing is a plus\nGeneral understanding of Machine Learning techniques (Neural Networks, Random Forest, etc.) and ML frameworks (Mlflow, PyTorch, Tensorflow, etc.) is a plus\n\nWhat do we offer?\n\nExceptional career growth and learning opportunity\nA unique opportunity to be part of an experienced team of industry experts and entrepreneurs who bring massive change to the Adtech market\nDirect, day-to-day work experience with the management\nA fun, driven, and multinational team located across Germany, India, Argentina, Ukraine, Turkey, the UK and soon more countries\nA flexible work-from-home arrangement\nA 500-dollar home-office setup budget\nA 1000-dollar annual learning and development budget','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Kayzen','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c562e4f0646b89aa','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2454,NULL,'job','Product Operations Lead','Vollzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'GoodHabitz helps organisations build learning habits at scale. We\'re a B2B SaaS platform operating in the human skills development space — and we\'re mid-transformation, moving from a sales-led model to one where the product itself drives activation, engagement, and renewal.\n\nThat transformation is only real if strategy actually becomes execution. Right now, it doesn\'t always. That\'s why this role exists.\n\nAs our first Product Operations Lead, you will build the operating system that connects strategy to outcomes across a growing, multi-team product organisation. You\'ll own how the product org plans, decides, measures, and ships — not as a process enforcer, but as a system designer who makes the whole machine run faster and more deliberately.\n\nWhat you\'ll own\n\nProduct Operating System\n\nDesign and run the system that connects OKRs to execution across all product teams. This means planning cadences, prioritisation frameworks, documentation standards, and product rituals — built to eliminate ambiguity and reduce coordination overhead, not to add it.\n\nInsights and decision infrastructure\n\nBuild the layer that turns signals into action. You\'ll define how teams consume product analytics, customer research, support data, and CS feedback — and how that input flows into concrete decisions. The goal is higher signal quality and faster decision velocity.\n\nMetrics operationalisation\n\nWe have defined KPIs. We don\'t yet have a reliable operational system around them. You\'ll build it — consistent metric definitions, team-facing dashboards (in partnership with our Product Data Lead), and the review rhythms that make performance visible and trusted.\n\nExecution quality\n\nIdentify where work slows down and fix it. Improve planning reliability, reduce cycle time from idea to shipped outcome, and surface cross-team dependencies before they become blockers.\n\nCross-functional alignment\n\nProduct doesn\'t work in isolation. You\'ll improve how we work with Engineering, Design, Revenue, and Customer Success — aligning on outcomes, improving handoffs, and making sure the right people have the right context at the right time.\n\nAI and tooling enablement\n\nWe are actively building an AI agent layer across the product org. You\'ll help drive the adoption of high-leverage AI workflows, improve how we use Jira, Slack, and analytics tooling, and automate the operational work that shouldn\'t require human judgment.\n\nWhat you won\'t own\n\nThis role has a clear boundary. The Product Data Lead owns data infrastructure, pipelines, and analytics truth. PMs own product decisions and outcome spaces. You own how the system works — how data is used, how decisions are made, and how execution stays aligned.\n\nProduct Ops does not own \"truth\". It ensures truth is used effectively.\n\nWhat good looks like in 6 months\n\nThe product operating system is clearly defined, actively used, and trusted by teams\nData flows reliably and teams reference insights in their decisions — not just in retrospectives\nMetric ownership is unambiguous, definitions are consistent, and performance is reviewed regularly\nCross-team dependencies are visible and managed before they become fires\nCycle time from idea to shipped outcome is measurably shorter\nThe AI agent layer has grown, and tangible productivity improvements are visible\n\nRequirements\n\nWho you are\n\nYou\'ve built product operations before — or played a meaningfully similar role in a scaling product organisation. You know the difference between building an operating system and running a project plan. You\'re drawn to ambiguity because you know how to impose structure on it, not because you want someone else to resolve it first.\n\n You bring:\n\nHands-on experience in product ops, strategy & operations, or a closely adjacent function at a scaling B2B SaaS company\nSystems thinking — you see how rituals, tooling, incentives, and decision flows create (or destroy) execution quality\nData fluency — you don\'t need to run the pipelines, but you know what to ask for and how to use what you get\nStrong communication and influence — you earn trust with PMs, engineers, and execs through clarity and follow-through, not authority\nComfort with incomplete information — you can make progress without waiting for everything to be clean\n\n You\'ll thrive here if:\n\nYou\'d rather design the system than manage inside it\nYou\'re energised by transformation environments, not destabilised by them\nYou treat process as a hypothesis, not a policy\nYou can challenge a VP\'s framing while keeping the relationship intact\n\nBenefits\n\nBecome part of the leader online training company in the European market, the benchmark in our sector, and help organisations thrive while you grow professionally at a trailblazing company with unstoppable momentum on an exciting growth journey even as others in the industry face challenges.\n\nCompetitive salary and role-specific performance bonus because we value your contributions and reward your hard work.\n️ Paid time off – 25 days holiday.\nTravel budget.\nFlexible work & tools – work in a supportive environment with the comforts you need, plus a laptop.\nGrowth & development – unlimited access to GoodHabitz resources and MyAcademy to fuel your personal and professional growth.\nMental coaching – support from our partner, to keep your mind in top shape.\nDiverse & inclusive teams – work with colleagues from across Europe, bringing different cultures, perspectives, and ideas together.\nThemed events & team-building – from creativity workshops to vitality socials, our events are full of energy and fun surprises.\nAnnual Do-Good Day – a fully paid day to do volunteer work, alone or with your team, supporting a cause you care about.\n️ Pension & insurance – disability and pension coverage for your long-term security.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'GoodHabitz','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6992daa28704c993','scraped','vor 11 Tagen'),(2455,NULL,'job','Fullstack Entwickler (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','10117 Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Künstliche Intelligenz, Machine Learning, Hyper Automation, Value Chain Analysis, End-to-End Margin, E-Invoicing, Automatisierung digitaler Rechnungs- und Meldeprozesse, Compliance Management, End-to-End Prozessoptimierung, Predictive Analytics, Fast Close und Cloud-Lösungen gewinnen im Bereich Tax Technology rasant an Bedeutung. Wir unterstützen unsere Kunden bei der digitalen Transformation ihrer Rechnungs- und Meldeprozesse und setzen dabei modernste Technologien und Architekturen ein.\n\nIm Bereich Tax Technology & E-Invoicing arbeitest du an der Entwicklung und Weiterentwicklung innovativer Produkte für internationale Unternehmen. Du gestaltest digitale Lösungen für E-Invoicing in SAP- und Cloud-Systemen, integrierst komplexe steuerliche und gesetzliche Anforderungen und optimierst Prozesse entlang globaler Steuerlandschaften. Durch internationale Projekte sammelst du praxisnahes Wissen in Digital Finance und Produktentwicklung und entwickelst gemeinsam mit Kolleg:innen maßgeschneiderte, zukunftsorientierte Steuerlösungen.\n\nFür unser Scrum-basiertes Inhouse-Entwicklerteam in der Produktentwicklung suchen wir Unterstützung in Form eines Fullstack Entwicklers (m/w/d).\n\nWas Dich erwartet\nAnalyse, Entwurf und Entwicklung von Fullstack-Softwareprodukten und Applikationen im Bereich e-Compliance\nUmsetzung von Lösungen mit Integration in bestehende Systemlandschaften und Dritt-Systeme\nDurchführung von Systemtests, Code Reviews und Fehleranalysen\nKundenorientierte Weiterentwicklung und Optimierung der Software durch gezielte Architektur- und Komponentenstrukturierung\nErstellung und Pflege von technischer Dokumentation, Architekturdiagrammen und Design-Spezifikationen\nKoordination und Zusammenarbeit in einem agilen Entwicklungsteam (Scrum)\n\nWas wir uns wünschen\nAbgeschlossenes Studium der (Wirtschafts-)Informatik, (Wirtschafts-)Ingenieurwesen, Naturwissenschaften, Mathematik oder eine vergleichbare Qualifikation\nSehr gute Kenntnisse in Perl, JavaScript/TypeScript sowie Dart\nErfahrung in der Entwicklung von Fullstack-Anwendungen und API-basierten Architekturen\nSicherer Umgang mit Docker und containerisierten Anwendungen\nErfahrung mit relationalen Datenbanken wie PostgreSQL und/oder MS SQL Server\nKenntnisse in der Arbeit mit REST-APIs sowie Datenformaten wie JSON\nErfahrung im UI-Design, idealerweise mit Flutter\nGute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse\nEigenverantwortliche, lösungsorientierte Arbeitsweise sowie hohe Eigenmotivation\nTeamfähigkeit und Freude an agiler Zusammenarbeit\n\nUnsere Benefits:\n\nAus- und Weiterbildung\n\nSAP- und Salesforce-Zertifizierungen, Competence Center-Tage, Fachspezifische Schulungen\n\nBetriebliche Gesundheitsförderung\n\nZuschuss zur betrieblichen Altersvorsorge, Zusatzversicherungen, diverse Sportangebote wie Urban Sports Club, Yoga etc.\n\nEvents\n\nBeratertage, Weihnachtsfeier, Sommerfest, Teamevents, Alumni-Treffen, Jubiläumsfeiern und -reisen\n\nPrämien\n\nUmsatzbeteiligungen, Prämienzahlungen für erfolgreich abgeschlossene Projekte, Attraktive Gehaltsmodelle, Mitarbeiterempfehlungsprämien\n\nArbeitszeiten\n\nFlexible Arbeitszeitmodelle, mobiles Arbeiten, 30 Tage Urlaub, Workation\n\nAusstattung\n\nFirmenhandy (iPhone), Notebook / Macbook, Mitarbeiter PC Programm, Ergonomische Arbeitsplätze, Kostenlose Getränke, Gemeinschaftsräume mit Wohlfühlcharakter\n\nFirmenwagen\n\nFirmenwagen inkl. Tankkarte/ Mobilitätspauschale, Bahncard, Jobrad\n\nZuwendungen\n\nZuschüsse für Kindergarten/Kita und außerordentliche Zuwendungen je Lebenssituation und Betriebszugehörigkeit\n\nDein Ansprechpartner\n\nChristina Argyriadou\n\nSenior Recruiterin\n\n+49 15165577154\n\nchristina.argyriadou@cbs-consulting.de\n\nBereich: Technology Consulting\n\nAnsprechpartner: Christina Argyriadou\n\nPractice: Managed Cloud Services (MCS)\n\nFilter: Berufserfahrung: Professionals\n\nBenefits: Professionals','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'cbs Corporate Business Solutions GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=db8150b401ebcc81','scraped','vor 13 Tagen'),(2456,NULL,'job','Product Manager - Sustainability (all genders)','','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'City: Berlin\nJob Function: Corporate Functions\nJob Area: Product & IT\nSeniority Level: Mid-Senior level\nDate: Apr 24, 2026\nHRS AS A COMPANY\n\nHRS is reinventing the way businesses and governments work, stay and pay in today’s dynamic global marketplace. HRS’ advanced platform technology is extending its reach beyond hospitality to meetings, office space management, payment efficiency and crisis recovery. Beyond cost savings in the global post-pandemic economy, HRS clients gain from an unrivalled focus on essential aspects including safety, security and satisfaction. HRS is also recognized for its award-winning and TravelTech industry-first ISO certified Green Stay Initiative, an in-house proprietary technology that helps corporate hotel programs with high coverage of Green Stay certified properties and capabilities like abatement effects to help organizations achieve their NetZero targets.\n\nHRS works with more than 1.5 million hotels including global and regional chains and independent hotels across the globe to help a third of global Fortune 500 companies with end-to-end corporate lodging and meetings offerings in our two AI-powered state-of-art market facing solutions – Connect and Copilot.\n\nBUSINESS UNIT\n\nCorporate customers and companies today demand transparency on sustainability and environmental impact of each hotel stay — from carbon emissions to certifications and waste management standards. With regulations like CSRD (Corporate Sustainability Reporting Directive) and EU Taxonomy requiring detailed emissions reporting, Travel CEOs are under pressure to deliver measurable sustainability outcomes while managing costs and operational complexity.\n\nThe market is becoming saturated with basic carbon calculators and generic reporting tools. However, what corporations, many of which have net zero commitments made, truly need are vetted and actionable insights that help them minimize environmental impact while optimizing for business value. This is where HRS stands apart — our Green Stay Initiative has proven to be level-playing field for independent hotels and small-and-medium size hotel chains ensuring most sustainable hotels also deliver cost savings, and other way around. In short, we strive towards positioning HRS as the only end-to-end procure-to-pay solution in the blue-ocean Lodging & Meetings space by expanding Green Stay into a full Sustainable Stay platform with ESG-aligned insights, carbon reporting, and gamified engagement driving corporates toward net-zero goals.\n\nPOSITION\n\nAs Product Manager - Sustainability, you\'ll own how HRS collects, structures, and exposes sustainability-related content from our global hotel network. Your mission is to evolve our Green Stay Initiative into the comprehensive Sustainable Stay Initiative — expanding beyond environmental metrics to include Social and Governance (ESG) and Emissions Compensation Program (ECP) as a core strategic edge for us. You\'ll build the data infrastructure that enables Fortune 500 companies to not just report on emissions, but to actively reduce them through intelligent procurement and book-stay decisions.\n\nThis role sits at the intersection of sustainability and corporate travel innovation — perfect for a product leader ready to tackle one of the most pressing challenges facing global businesses today.\n\nCHALLENGE\nOwn the evolution of Green Stay to Sustainable Stay Initiative, integrating Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) dimensions to differentiate HRS in the market\nDesign and scale data collection frameworks to automate ingestion of sustainability metrics from 100,000+ properties globally via APIs, AI-powered certificate validation, and partner integrations\nEnable corporate customers to achieve Net Zero targets by building infrastructure for carbon pricing, budgeting, SBTi forecasting, and integration with the Emissions Compensation Program\nPartner with engineering and leverage machine learning for data validation, predictive recommendations, and automated sustainability scoring\nDrive customer adoption through sustainability nudging in booking flows.\nRepresent HRS externally with hotel partners, enterprise clients, and strategic partners to expand our sustainability offerings while also helping some key sustainability solution offering players to attract new customers building an ecosystem flywheel\nFOR THIS EXCITING MISSION YOU ARE EQUIPPED WITH...\n5+ years of product management experience in B2B SaaS, preferably in Travel or Hospitality Domain with some understanding of sustainability landscape (CSRD, EU Taxonomy, certification standards etc.).\nStrong technical foundation with API-first mindset, experience in large-scale data integration, SQL proficiency etc.\nExcellence in stakeholder management with ability to influence without authority across engineering, commercial, operations, and external partners while balancing diverse needs\nData-driven decision maker who uses experiments, A/B tests, and metrics to validate hypotheses and identify breakthrough opportunities in commoditized markets\nGenuine passion for sustainability and environmental impact, with the drive to make corporate travel a force for positive change\nPERSPECTIVE\nLOCATION, MOBILITY, INCENTIVE\n\nLocation: Germany (Berlin is a preferred location)\n\nReq ID: 18749','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'HRS','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=abd10f52e19011e5','scraped','vor 8 Tagen'),(2457,NULL,'job','Director of Information Security','Vollzeit','Deutschland',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About Triple\n\nTriple is building the intelligence platform for banking operations. We are the leading transaction enrichment engine, trusted by 60+ banks and fintechs across 30+ markets. We have raised $10M in funding, an experienced team, and a large network of investors behind our company.\n\nWe\'re now solving one of the most painful problems in payments: dispute and chargeback management. Our AI agents automate the dispute workflows for card issuers, from intake and classification through evidence evaluation and scheme submission to Mastercard and Visa. We value getting things done.\n\nRole\n\nThe Director of Information Security is a leadership position that will be accountable and responsible for Triple’s security across all functional areas. He/she will be responsible for the design, implementation and execution of Triple’s security program. The successful candidate will be in charge of planning and development of the security strategy and best practices to ensure that information and assets are adequately protected. This position requires a visionary leader with strong skills in IT security, risk and business sense. A key element of the role is to determine acceptable levels of risk for the organization and coordinate with the rest of the tech team the implementation.\n\nThe Director of Information Security will partner with Triple’s CTO to ensure that the security program components are aligned with Triple’s strategy. The Director of Information Security will report directly to the CTO, and will work closely with Triple’s infrastructure and engineering teams.\n\nRequirements\n\nKey responsibilities\nDevelop and implement a security program: design, promote and implement organization-wide security solutions which align to the business strategy focusing on application and platform service development, technology infrastructure, and overall Cyber Security.\nEngage with Sales and Customer Engineering team members and other business units in response to relevant inquiries and requests regarding risk and security requirements\nBe on top of communications with customer security teams\nAnswer RFPs, Questionnaires and Forms from integrations, explaining Triple Security practices to customers\nLead the promotion of security practices throughout the organization\nCollaboration with key business and IT leaders to ensure that security policies and standards are implemented, enforced, and enhanced where appropriate.\nCollaboration and coordination with leadership across all departments on risk and security related matters\nDevelop and implement guidelines that cover: risk assessments, issues and event management, impact analysis, monitoring and reporting.\nEvaluate complex business problems to ensure risks and exposures are properly mitigated\nIdentify potential areas of vulnerability and risk; develop/implement corrective action plans for resolution of issues, and provide general guidance on how to prevent or address similar situations in the future\nLead certification processes and own the audit structure for ISO 27001, SOC 2, GDPR, CSA etc.\nDevelops and implements security frameworks for agentic AI, and builds production-grade security tooling.\nMonitors AI systems to detect vulnerabilities and fraudulent activity\nOur ideal candidate\n5-10 years of Information Security experience with at least 5 years of managing complex, cross-functional teams and projects\nAbility to influence and to lead enterprise change\nAbility to deal effectively with ambiguity and complexity\nOutstanding oral/written communication, organization, and interpersonal skills and a demonstrated effectiveness in dealing with complex situations\nExperience with secure design principles, including broad knowledge of information security principles (e.g., architectural control, authorization, authentication, access control, confidentiality, integrity etc.)\nExperience performing both risk and impact assessments along with communicating issues in terms of both technical and business impact\nExperience in implementing an effective international security program to support the identification and implementation of controls to ensure that the program is seen as a business enabler\nExperience in designing, implementing, and managing cloud technologies\nKnowledge of AI/ML frameworks, data privacy techniques, cloud security, Python, Golang, JS, and container security.\nDeep understanding of cybersecurity principles combined with specialized knowledge in machine learning models','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Triple','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2c4aa1a758cbdaf7','scraped','vor 13 Tagen'),(2458,NULL,'job','Data Analyst','','Jena',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Your role\n\nThrough the management and analysis of our data sources, the data analyst will enable the business to make the right decisions quickly and drive efficiency in the Service organisation. In identifying key trends and opportunities through the analysis of complex data sets, they will support business growth and continuous improvement to drive operational excellence initiatives.\n\nTo succeed, you will need\n\nWe encourage you to apply even if you don\'t meet every single requirement. We value diverse experiences and perspectives and are excited to see what you bring to the role.\n\nCollaborate with management and business users to gather requirements and build strong stakeholder relationships.\nDesign, build, and maintain interactive Power BI dashboards and reports that are intuitive, visually engaging, and aligned with organizational goals.\nSupport and contribute to advanced analytics initiatives by simplifying complex issues into actionable analytical frameworks.\nDevelop robust, scalable data models, DAX measures, and optimized data structures to ensure accurate and efficient analytics.\nImplement and uphold best practices for usability, performance optimization, and data governance in all dashboards and data solutions.\nAnalyze complex and diverse data sets to identify trends, detect anomalies, and uncover opportunities that inform business strategy, deliver actionable insights.\nEvaluate and improve data quality by developing protocols for handling, processing, and cleaning data across internal systems.\nDocument data sources, models, and processes to ensure continuity, transparency, and consistent knowledge transfer within the organization.\nIdentify and support opportunities for automation and workflow optimization using tools such as Power Automate to streamline data workflows and reporting.\n\nDevelop scalable data models and contribute to digitalization, automation, and future machine learning initiatives to strengthen the organization’s analytical capabilities.\n\nIn return, we offer\nCulture of trust and accountability\nLifelong learning and career growth\nInnovation powered by people\nComprehensive compensation and benefits\nHealth and well-being\nJob location\n\n Hybrid\nThis role offers a hybrid working arrangement, allowing you to split your time between working remotely and being on-site.\n\nContact information\n\n Talent Acquisition Team: Roberta Bracey\nCompany: Atlas Copco Group\nFunctional area: Marketing\nLocation: Germany\nCity: Jena\nOn-site/remote: Hybrid\nBrand: Edwards\nCompany Name: Edwards GmbH\nDate of Posting: April 24, 2026\nApply for this position','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Atlas Copco Group','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=3f79f3f3fbcffb3d','scraped','vor 8 Tagen'),(2459,NULL,'job','IT-Architektin/ IT-Architekt für KI-gestützte Datenplattformen im Gesundheitswesen - Institut für Medizininformatik (IMI)','Vollzeit','Frankfurt am Main',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'...sind Sie mittendrin\n\nDas Institut für Medizininformatik (IMI) an der Universitätsmedizin Frankfurt ist eine Einrichtung des Fachbereichs Medizin der Goethe-Universität. Es versteht sich als Schnittstelle zwischen medizinisch-klinischen Fragestellungen und innovativen IT- Lösungen. Im Mittelpunkt unserer Arbeit stehen praxisnahe Forschungs- und Entwicklungsprojekte in verschiedenen Bereichen der Medizininformatik – insbesondere in den Themenfeldern Datenmanagement in der Medizin und Digital Health und Künstliche Intelligenz. Dabei arbeiten wir eng mit Partnern auf lokaler, nationaler und internationaler Ebene zusammen.\n\nDas Projekt „Digitales UKF 2.0“ der Universitätsmedizin Frankfurt treibt die digitale Transformation von Versorgung, Forschung und Verwaltung voran. Ziel ist es, moderne IT-Infrastrukturen, datenbasierte Anwendungen und digitale Services zu etablieren, um klinische Prozesse effizienter zu gestalten und die Qualität der Patientenversorgung nachhaltig zu verbessern.\n\nIm Projekt wird eine Plattform entwickelt, die verfügbare Patientendaten aus unterschiedlichen Quellsystemen (z. B. lokale Informationssysteme, elektronische Patientenakte) zusammenführt, strukturiert und für klinische Entscheidungsprozesse nutzbar macht. Ein Schwerpunkt liegt auf der Entwicklung und Integration von Machine-Learning-Modellen und Large Language Models (LLMs) zur Unterstützung medizinischer Workflows. Die Arbeit ist praxisnah an der klinischen Versorgung angesiedelt.\n\nDie Stelle ist auf 2 Jahre befristet.\n\nIhre Aufgaben:\n\nKonzeption und Entwicklung einer IT-Architektur für die webbasierte Plattform\nBereitstellung einer webbasierten Plattform zur Aggregation multimodaler Patientendaten\nKonzeption, Planung und Durchführung von Workshops mit ärztlichem Fachpersonal zur Erhebung fachlicher und technischer Anforderungen\nAnbindung und Integration externer Datenquellen\nEntwicklung, Training und Evaluation von KI-Modellen (Machine Learning, Deep Learning, LLMs)\nVerwertung der Ergebnisse (z.B. durch Publikationen)\n... ist Ihr Profil gefragt\n Abgeschlossenes Hochschulstudium (Master) in Informatik, Medizininformatik, Data Science oder vergleichbar\nSehr gute Kenntnisse in mindestens einer Programmiersprache (z. B. Python)\nInteresse an (digitalen) medizinischen Prozessen\nSelbstständige und strukturierte Arbeitsweise\nKommunikationsstärke und Durchsetzungsvermögen\nAufgrund gesetzlicher Bestimmungen ist ein gültiger Nachweis der Masernimmunität / Masernschutzimpfung notwendig.\n... wird Ihnen viel geboten\nTarifvertrag TV-UKF\n30 Tage Urlaub, 38,5 Stunden / Woche, Jahressonderzahlung, betriebliche Altersvorsorge\nKostenloses Landesticket Hessen\nMobiles Arbeiten\nUniklinik-Campus, Mensa, Cafés\nWork-Life-Balance, Teilzeitmöglichkeiten\nGesundheitsförderung\nCorporate Benefits: Rabatte & Vergünstigungen bei beliebten Marken für unsere Mitarbeitenden\nKitaplätze, Ferienbetreuung (Infos beim Familienservice)\nEinblicke: Instagram, YouTube, LinkedIn\nFAQ´s für neue Beschäftigte\nWerden Sie jetzt Teil unseres Teams\n\nKontakt: Frau To-Nga Truong für administrative Fragen und Dr. Richard Noll für fachliche Fragen\nMail: truong@med.uni-frankfurt.de und noll@med.uni-frankfurt.de\n\nBewerbungsfrist: 04.05.2026\n\nWir richten uns mit dieser Ausschreibung an Bewerbende jeden Geschlechts. Frauen sind in diesen Positionen am Universitätsklinikum Frankfurt unterrepräsentiert. Daher sind Bewerbungen von Frauen besonders willkommen. Schwerbehinderte Bewerbende werden bei gleicher persönlicher und fachlicher Eignung bevorzugt berücksichtigt.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Universitätsmedizin Frankfurt','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d483c577b08192a9','scraped','vor 13 Tagen'),(2460,NULL,'job','AI Data Lead - SAP-RPT Model Family (f/m/d)','Vollzeit','85748 Garching bei München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We help the world run better\n\nAt SAP, we keep it simple: you bring your best to us, and we\'ll bring out the best in you. We\'re builders touching over 20 industries and 80% of global commerce, and we need your unique talents to help shape what\'s next. The work is challenging – but it matters. You\'ll find a place where you can be yourself, prioritize your wellbeing, and truly belong. What\'s in it for you? Constant learning, skill growth, great benefits, and a team that wants you to grow and succeed.\n\nWhat you`ll do:\n\nAs the AI Data Lead for the SAP-RPT model family, you will own our data assets, drive the strategy to grow the asset base and ensure best usability and highest value for our foundation model research & engineering teams. Bridging the gap between AI research and enterprise data intricacies, you will set the vision and drive technical priorities. You will enable our research & engineering teams to build best-in-class AI models through providing the best data foundation, while ensuring adherence to SAP’s unwavering commitment to industry-leading compliance standards. You will work hands-on on data, processing pipelines and tooling as well as coordinate with a multitude of stakeholders in a multi-national company to achieve your goals. This is the ideal role for a highly focused, ambitious individual with both, a strong technical and coordinating background and your chance to contribute to one of the very few leading foundation models of European origin.\n\nThe Role:\n\nOwnership of Data Assets & strategy: Own pre-training, evaluation, and meta-data including proprietary, open-source, and synthetic datasets. Develop and execute vision.\n\nEnd-to-End Execution: Lead data extraction, curation, and quality analysis to produce high-impact training signals. Set technical priorities and define work packages across teams to ensure high-quality outcomes.\n\nDrive Partnership: Work closely with science leads to define data requirements and co-design the datasets necessary to push model capabilities. Build strong alliances with internal data and technology providers.\n\nDeep-Dive Data Exploration: Explore and analyze datasets to identify patterns, edge cases, and quality issues that inform model development.\n\nData Architecture: Influence data architecture decisions to ensure seamless data access for both model training and production environments.\n\nWhat you bring:\n\nEducation & Experience: PhD or Master’s degree in Computer Science, AI, or a relevant field, followed by 7+ years of professional experience in high-scale data environments.\n\nFunctional Leadership: Proven track record of leading large-scale, end-to-end technical projects, ideally with data and machine learning deliverables.\n\nSAP Data Expertise: Profound understanding of SAP’s relational business data, including key business objects and underlying table structures. You excel at navigating semantic models (e.g., VDM, CDS, OData) and possess a sophisticated understanding of the complex business logic and relational schemas inherent in the enterprise landscape.\n\nData Engineering & SAP Ecosystem: Extensive experience with high-performance databases (SQL) and SAP’s data stack (e.g. BDC, HANA & BTP) as well as with the development of cloud-native pipelines. Strong Python skills and ideally exposure to Knowledge Graphs (incl technologies like RDL).\n\nMachine Learning Skills: Solid ML knowledge with practical experience in solving real-world problems with AI - ideally in the tabular domain.\n\nOrganizational Influence: Ability to build partnerships with internal technology providers and lead cross-team technical initiatives and task prioritization.\n\nMeet your team:\n\nSAP is uniquely positioned to lead the next wave of AI by infusing intelligence directly into the business processes that run the world. Our team’s mission is to develop Foundation Models for structured data, starting with the launch and continued evolution of SAP-RPT-1. As the first generation of our relational model portfolio, SAP-RPT-1 represents our commitment to pioneering new research in a domain where SAP’s expertise in enterprise data structures provides an unmatched competitive edge. We are looking for innovators to join us in this journey to develop next-generation models with even higher impact, bridging the gap between cutting-edge AI research and the complex, structured reality of global enterprise data.\n\nBring out your best\n\nSAP innovations help more than four hundred thousand customers worldwide work together more efficiently and use business insight more effectively. Originally known for leadership in enterprise resource planning (ERP) software, SAP has evolved to become a market leader in end-to-end business application software and related services for database, analytics, intelligent technologies, and experience management. As a cloud company with two hundred million users and more than one hundred thousand employees worldwide, we are purpose-driven and future-focused, with a highly collaborative team ethic and commitment to personal development. Whether connecting global industries, people, or platforms, we help ensure every challenge gets the solution it deserves. At SAP, you can bring out your best.\n\nWe win with inclusion\n\nSAP’s culture of inclusion, focus on health and well-being, and flexible working models help ensure that everyone – regardless of background – feels included and can run at their best. At SAP, we believe we are made stronger by the unique capabilities and qualities that each person brings to our company, and we invest in our employees to inspire confidence and help everyone realize their full potential. We ultimately believe in unleashing all talent and creating a better world.\n\nSAP is committed to the values of Equal Employment Opportunity and provides accessibility accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are interested in applying for employment with SAP and are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to Recruiting Operations Team: Careers@sap.com.\n\nFor SAP employees: Only permanent roles are eligible for the SAP Employee Referral Program, according to the eligibility rules set in the SAP Referral Policy. Specific conditions may apply for roles in Vocational Training.\n\nAI Usage in the Recruitment Process\n\nFor information on the responsible use of AI in our recruitment process, please refer to our Guidelines for Ethical Usage of AI in the Recruiting Process.\n\nPlease note that any violation of these guidelines may result in disqualification from the hiring process.\n\nRequisition ID: 447798 | Work Area: Software-Design and Development | Expected Travel: 0 - 10% | Career Status: Professional | Employment Type: Regular Full Time #LI-Hybrid','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'SAP','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e29e5f78b5cf17d6','scraped','vor 8 Tagen'),(2461,NULL,'job','Abschlussarbeit / Werkstudententätigkeit: Entwicklung einer KI-basierten Supportanalyse (m/w/d)','Teilzeit','93049 Regensburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Abschlussarbeit / Werkstudententätigkeit: Entwicklung einer KI-basierten Supportanalyse (m/w/d)\n\nDu möchtest nicht nur Theorie schreiben, sondern an einer Lösung arbeiten, die in der Praxis wirklich etwas bewegt? Dann werde Teil unseres Teams und entwickle mit uns eine AI-basierte Lösung, die technische Supportfälle schneller analysierbar macht.\n\nIm Fokus steht die automatisierte Auswertung von Supportpaketen, Logfiles und weiteren technischen Informationen, um Ursachen schneller zu erkennen und passende Lösungsvorschläge abzuleiten. Das Besondere: Mit jedem abgeschlossenen Supportfall kann das System weiterlernen und immer besser werden.\n\nDeine Aufgaben\n\nEntwicklung eines Konzepts für eine AI-basierte Analyse von Supportpaketen\nAuswertung von Logfiles, Konfigurationsdaten und weiteren technischen Informationen\nErkennung von Mustern, Auffälligkeiten und möglichen Fehlerursachen in Supportfällen\nEntwicklung von Ansätzen für automatisierte oder teilautomatisierte Lösungsvorschläge\nAufbau eines kontinuierlichen Lernprozesses auf Basis abgeschlossener Supportfälle und dokumentierter Lösungen\nNice to have: Konzeption einer Anbindung an ein Ticket-System, um Supportfälle, Analyseergebnisse und Lösungen intelligent zu verknüpfen\nEnge Zusammenarbeit mit unseren Teams aus Support und Software-Entwicklung\nDokumentation und Präsentation Deiner Ergebnisse\nWir erwarten von Dir:\nStudium der Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Data Science, Künstlichen Intelligenz oder eines vergleichbaren Studiengangs\nInteresse an AI, Machine Learning und der Analyse technischer Daten\nErste Erfahrung mit Python oder einer vergleichbaren Programmiersprache\nSpaß daran, technische Zusammenhänge zu verstehen und in sinnvolle Lösungen zu überführen\nEine strukturierte, selbstständige und lösungsorientierte Arbeitsweise\nIdealerweise erste Berührungspunkte mit Logfile-Analyse, Supportprozessen oder technischen Systemen\nSehr gute Deutschkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift sowie gute Englischkenntnisse\nDas erwartet Dich:\nEin innovatives Thema mit echtem Praxisbezug\nDie Chance, an einer zukunftsorientierten Lösung im Bereich AI und Automatisierung mitzuarbeiten\nDirekter Einblick in reale technische Supportfälle\nAustausch mit erfahrenen Kolleginnen und Kollegen aus Entwicklung und Support\nViel Raum für eigene Ideen und eigenverantwortliches Arbeiten\nFlexible Rahmenbedingungen für die Vereinbarkeit von Studium und Praxis\nEin motiviertes Team an unserem Standort in Regensburg\nFaire Vergütung nach Vereinbarung\n\nWir freuen uns auf Deine aussagekräftigen Bewerbungsunterlagen! Teile uns gerne mit, ob Du Dich für eine Abschlussarbeit oder eine Werkstudententätigkeit interessierst.\nBitte gib in Deiner Bewerbung den folgenden Referenzcode an:\n110-04-26\n\nDie sichere Kommunikation und die Vernetzung von Daten in industriellen Anwendungen – das ist die Kernkompetenz von INSYS icom.\n\nWir sind der perfekte Partner, wo Maschinen, Anlagen und andere Geräte aus der Ferne erreicht und deren Betriebsdaten übermittelt werden müssen.\n\nMit unseren intelligenten Lösungen und Produkten sind wir im Marktsegment Energie und Wasserversorgung bereits Marktführer und wir positionieren uns als Premiumpartner im Bereich Maschinenbau.\n\nUm unseren Umsatz in diesen dynamischen Märkten weiter auszubauen und um die Realisierung der IIoT voranzutreiben, arbeiten wir jeden Tag mit neuer Leidenschaft.\n\nFür unseren Standort Regensburg suchen wir ab sofort:\n\nAbschlussarbeit / Werkstudententätigkeit: Entwicklung einer KI-basierten Supportanalyse (m/w/d)\n\nReferenzcode: 110-04-26\n\nINSYS icom GmbH\nz. Hd. Hr. Benjamin Zollitsch\nHermann-Köhl-Str. 22\nD-93049 Regensburg\nTel.: +49 941 586 92-0','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'INSYS icom GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9ec8498d323a74f8','scraped','vor 13 Tagen'),(2462,NULL,'job','Senior Applied Scientist for Tabular ML (f/m/d)','Vollzeit','85748 Garching bei München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We help the world run better\nAt SAP, we keep it simple: you bring your best to us, and we\'ll bring out the best in you. We\'re builders touching over 20 industries and 80% of global commerce, and we need your unique talents to help shape what\'s next. The work is challenging – but it matters. You\'ll find a place where you can be yourself, prioritize your wellbeing, and truly belong. What\'s in it for you? Constant learning, skill growth, great benefits, and a team that wants you to grow and succeed.\n\nWhat you`ll do:\n\nYou’ll work at the intersection of advanced AI research, enterprise applications, and real-world problem solving, partnering closely with internal teams and model researchers to evaluate and improve high-value use cases.\n\nIn this applied, hands-on role, you’ll analyze challenging use cases across the organization, understand their business context, and help push our tabular foundation models to their full potential. Through debugging, benchmarking, and deep technical iteration, you’ll uncover patterns, limitations, and opportunities, and turn them into actionable insights that directly inform model research and model architecture improvements.\n\nYou’ll collaborate deeply with application teams and domain experts, serving as a bridge between practical use-case execution and ongoing model research. Your input will have a direct impact on how our models evolve and how effectively they perform on meaningful enterprise problems.\n\nThe Role:\n\nPartner with internal teams and model researchers to evaluate high-value use cases and understand their business context.\n\nAnalyze use cases across the organization and advise on how to make them work effectively with our tabular foundation models.\n\nWork hands-on with cutting-edge tabular foundation models to debug and benchmark model behavior, pushing performance on meaningful enterprise problems.\n\nDistill patterns, limitations, and opportunities from applied work into actionable insights, including suggestions for improvements to model architecture.\n\nWhat you bring:\n\nPhD or Master\'s degree in Computer Science, Artificial Intelligence, or other relevant disciplines with 5+ years of professional experience in developing machine learning models.\n\nExtensive hands-on experience developing predictive use cases on tabular data in a data scientist role, ideally with S/4HANA data.\n\nDeep master of deep learning and Transformer architectures, including application to structured enterprise data, along with strong software engineering skills in Python and a proven track record of building and scaling experiments with PyTorch or TensorFlow.\n\nStrong communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively in cross-cultural teams.\n\nMeet your team:\n\nSAP is uniquely positioned to lead the next wave of AI by infusing intelligence directly into the business processes that run the world. Our team’s mission is to develop Foundation Models for structured data, starting with the launch and continued evolution of SAP-RPT-1. As the first generation of our relational model portfolio, SAP-RPT-1 represents our commitment to pioneering new research in a domain where SAP’s expertise in enterprise data structures provides an unmatched competitive edge. We are looking for innovators to join us in this journey to develop next-generation models with even higher impact, bridging the gap between cutting-edge AI research and the complex, structured reality of global enterprise data.\n\nBring out your best\nSAP innovations help more than four hundred thousand customers worldwide work together more efficiently and use business insight more effectively. Originally known for leadership in enterprise resource planning (ERP) software, SAP has evolved to become a market leader in end-to-end business application software and related services for database, analytics, intelligent technologies, and experience management. As a cloud company with two hundred million users and more than one hundred thousand employees worldwide, we are purpose-driven and future-focused, with a highly collaborative team ethic and commitment to personal development. Whether connecting global industries, people, or platforms, we help ensure every challenge gets the solution it deserves. At SAP, you can bring out your best.\n\nWe win with inclusion\nSAP’s culture of inclusion, focus on health and well-being, and flexible working models help ensure that everyone – regardless of background – feels included and can run at their best. At SAP, we believe we are made stronger by the unique capabilities and qualities that each person brings to our company, and we invest in our employees to inspire confidence and help everyone realize their full potential. We ultimately believe in unleashing all talent and creating a better world.\n\nSAP is committed to the values of Equal Employment Opportunity and provides accessibility accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are interested in applying for employment with SAP and are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to Recruiting Operations Team: Careers@sap.com.\n\nFor SAP employees: Only permanent roles are eligible for the SAP Employee Referral Program, according to the eligibility rules set in the SAP Referral Policy. Specific conditions may apply for roles in Vocational Training.\n\nAI Usage in the Recruitment Process\n\nFor information on the responsible use of AI in our recruitment process, please refer to our Guidelines for Ethical Usage of AI in the Recruiting Process.\n\nPlease note that any violation of these guidelines may result in disqualification from the hiring process.\n\nRequisition ID: 448375 | Work Area: Software-Design and Development | Expected Travel: 0 - 10% | Career Status: Professional | Employment Type: Regular Full Time #LI-Hybrid','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'SAP','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f534548b3567c6de','scraped','vor 8 Tagen'),(2463,NULL,'job','Technical Lead - Remote','','Home Office',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job Title: Technical Lead\n\nJob Type: Contractor\n\nLocation: Remote\n\nJob Summary:\n\nWe are seeking an expert Technical Lead to join our customer\'s team and drive innovation on a cutting-edge AI agent project. In this role, you will leverage your deep hands-on coding expertise to guide the design, development, and training of AI models. This is an exciting opportunity to work remotely with a dynamic, collaborative team on impactful technology initiatives.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nLead technical direction and architectural decisions for AI agent development using modern programming languages.\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to design, build, and optimize scalable AI solutions.\nWrite high-quality, production-level code in React, Python, Node.js, PHP, .NET, C#, or C++.\nMentor and support team members, fostering a culture of technical excellence and collaboration.\nDevelop, evaluate, and iterate on AI model training processes to enhance performance and accuracy.\nEnsure clear, concise, and effective written and verbal communication within the team and with stakeholders.\nContinuously research emerging trends in AI and software development to recommend improvements and drive innovation.\n\nRequired Skills and Qualifications:\n\n3+ years of hands-on experience developing with React, Python, Node.js, PHP, .NET, C#, or C++.\nProven leadership experience guiding technical teams and projects to successful delivery.\nStrong expertise in training AI models and implementing machine learning solutions.\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills, with a passion for clarity and collaboration.\nAbility to take ownership of complex tasks and drive projects from ideation to completion.\nSelf-motivated, proactive, and adaptable in a fast-paced remote environment.\nExperience working with distributed teams and agile development methodologies.\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\nExposure to multiple programming languages and willingness to learn new technologies.\nPrior involvement in AI agent or similar advanced technology projects.\nExperience working on customer-facing or client-driven teams.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'YO IT CONSULTING','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=cda93e861b82f184','scraped','vor 13 Tagen'),(2464,NULL,'job','Sr Machine Learning Engineer','Vollzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'The Company\n\nPayPal has been revolutionizing commerce globally for more than 25 years. Creating innovative experiences that make moving money, selling, and shopping simple, personalized, and secure, PayPal empowers consumers and businesses in approximately 200 markets to join and thrive in the global economy.\n\nWe operate a global, two-sided network at scale that connects hundreds of millions of merchants and consumers. We help merchants and consumers connect, transact, and complete payments, whether they are online or in person. PayPal is more than a connection to third-party payment networks. We provide proprietary payment solutions accepted by merchants that enable the completion of payments on our platform on behalf of our customers.\n\nWe offer our customers the flexibility to use their accounts to purchase and receive payments for goods and services, as well as the ability to transfer and withdraw funds. We enable consumers to exchange funds more safely with merchants using a variety of funding sources, which may include a bank account, a PayPal or Venmo account balance, PayPal and Venmo branded credit products, a credit card, a debit card, certain cryptocurrencies, or other stored value products such as gift cards, and eligible credit card rewards. Our PayPal, Venmo, and Xoom products also make it safer and simpler for friends and family to transfer funds to each other. We offer merchants an end-to-end payments solution that provides authorization and settlement capabilities, as well as instant access to funds and payouts. We also help merchants connect with their customers, process exchanges and returns, and manage risk. We enable consumers to engage in cross-border shopping and merchants to extend their global reach while reducing the complexity and friction involved in enabling cross-border trade.\n\nOur beliefs are the foundation for how we conduct business every day. We live each day guided by our core values of Inclusion, Innovation, Collaboration, and Wellness. Together, our values ensure that we work together as one global team with our customers at the center of everything we do – and they push us to ensure we take care of ourselves, each other, and our communities.\n\nJob Summary:\n\nThis job will design, develop, and implement machine learning models and algorithms to solve complex problems. You will work closely with data scientists, software engineers, and product teams to enhance services through innovative AI/ML solutions. Your role will involve building scalable ML pipelines, ensuring data quality, and deploying models into production environments to drive business insights and improve customer experiences.\n\nJob Description:\n\nEssential Responsibilities:\n\nDevelop and optimize machine learning models for various applications.\nPreprocess and analyze large datasets to extract meaningful insights.\nDeploy ML solutions into production environments using appropriate tools and frameworks.\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate ML models into products and services.\nMonitor and evaluate the performance of deployed models.\n\nMinimum Qualifications:\n\n3+ years relevant experience and a Bachelor’s degree OR Any equivalent combination of education and experience.\nExperience with ML frameworks like TensorFlow, PyTorch, or scikit-learn.\nFamiliarity with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP) and tools for data processing and model deployment.\nSeveral years of experience in designing, implementing, and deploying machine learning models.\n\nAdditional Responsibilities & Preferred Qualifications:\n\nRole and Responsibilities\n\nSupport the lead of the team in performing oversight of high-impact statistical model and AI applications in a variety of business function areas, including but not limited to fraud detection, credit underwriting, marketing analytics etc.\n\nConduct quantitative and qualitative model validation according to Model Risk Management Policy to identify and understand model risk issues\n\nCollaborate with business units and model developers to remediate model issues and provide subject-matter expert opinion on model improvements\n\nPerform model and AI risk governance related activities in line with enterprise risk framework, to ensure PayPal’s AI applications are compliant with ever evolving regulatory expectation such as Responsible AI.\n\nQualifications\n\nThis position requires the ability and curiosity to learn various advanced modeling methods/AI techniques, covering a broader business function. This role also requires candidate to have the capability in building effective relationship with various stakeholders including business owners, model owners, model developers and control officers. The candidate must possess excellent communication, writing and presentation skills.\n\nAn advanced degree in a quantitative field, such as statistics, mathematics, computer science or engineering essential\n\nAdvanced knowledge of statistical and machine learning models (e.g., logistic regression, time series analysis, random forests, SVMs, XGBoost, CNNs/RNNs)\n\nPossessing advanced coding skills in dealing with big data (e.g., Scikit-learn in Python, Tensorflow, Hadoop, Spark , SQL, etc.)\n\nRelevant Modeling experience in credit scoring, fraud detection, financial forecasting, or marketing analytics obtained either in academic or financial industry\n\nAbility to work effectively both independently and in a team environment\n\nAbility to communicate effectively and establish constructive relationship with stakeholders\n\nSubsidiary:\n\nPayPal\n\nTravel Percent:\n\n0\n\nPayPal does not charge candidates any fees for courses, applications, resume reviews, interviews, background checks, or onboarding. When making an application directly, we will never ask you to share passwords, one-time passcodes (OTP), or verification codes. Any such request is a red flag and likely part of a scam. All communication regarding your application will come from official PayPal email domains. If you suspect fraudulent activity, please report it immediately. To learn more about how to identify and avoid recruitment fraud please visit https://careers.pypl.com/contact-us.\n\nFor the majority of employees, PayPal\'s balanced hybrid work model offers 3 days in the office for effective in-person collaboration and 2 days at your choice of either the PayPal office or your home workspace, ensuring that you equally have the benefits and conveniences of both locations.\n\nOur Benefits:\n\nAt PayPal, we’re committed to building an equitable and inclusive global economy. And we can’t do this without our most important asset-you. That’s why we offer comprehensive, choice-based programs, to support all aspects of personal wellbeing—physical, emotional, and financial—delivering meaningful value where it matters most. We strive to create a flexible, balanced work culture with a holistic approach to benefits, including generous paid time off, healthcare coverage for you and your family, and resources to create financial security and support your mental health.\n\nWho We Are:\n\nCommitment to Diversity and Inclusion\n\nPayPal provides equal employment opportunity (EEO) to all persons regardless of age, color, national origin, citizenship status, physical or mental disability, race, religion, creed, gender, sex, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, genetic information, marital status, status with regard to public assistance, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state, or local law. In addition, PayPal will provide reasonable accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities. If you are unable to submit an application because of incompatible assistive technology or a disability, please contact us at paypalglobaltalentacquisition@paypal.com.\n\nBelonging at PayPal:\n\nOur employees are central to advancing our mission, and we strive to create an environment where everyone can do their best work with a sense of purpose and belonging. Belonging at PayPal means creating a workplace with a sense of acceptance and security where all employees feel included and valued. We are proud to have a diverse workforce reflective of the merchants, consumers, and communities that we serve, and we continue to take tangible actions to cultivate inclusivity and belonging at PayPal.\n\nAny general requests for consideration of your skills, please Join our Talent Community.\n\nWe know the confidence gap and imposter syndrome can get in the way of meeting spectacular candidates. Please don’t hesitate to apply.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'paypal','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ef9c4c5b7f4fed25','scraped','vor 9 Tagen'),(2465,NULL,'job','KI-Spezialist / KI-Referent (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','80335 München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Wir suchen zum nächstmöglichen Zeitpunkt einen KI-Spezialisten / KI Referenten (m/w/d). In dieser Rolle unterstützen Sie den fachlichen Aufbau, die Einführung und die Weiterentwicklung von KI-Anwendungen im Unternehmensumfeld. Dabei verbinden Sie technisches Know-how, organisatorische Fähigkeiten sowie beratende Tätigkeiten und wirken aktiv an der strategischen Ausrichtung und Governance von KI-Themen mit.\n\nIhre Aufgaben\nKI-Strategie, Governance und Organisation: Sie unterstützen die Weiterentwicklung von KI-Strategie und KI-Roadmap, gestalten Governance-Strukturen und das KI-Operating-Modell mit, identifizieren KI-Potenziale und Use Cases und stehen als fachlicher Ansprechpartner für KI-Themen zur Verfügung\nDaten- und Technologiebezug: Sie bringen Kenntnisse im Datenmanagement, in der Datengovernance, Datenqualität und Datensicherheit ein, agieren an der Schnittstelle zu den Datenverantwortlichen und verfügen über Grundlagen zu Datenbanken, APIs, Workflow- und Prozessoptimierung sowie Machine Learning, LLMs und Generative AI\nKI-Tools, Enablement und Umsetzung: Sie unterstützen die Einführung und Nutzung von KI-Tools, bewerten geeignete Business-Anwendungen je Use Case und wirken an der Entwicklung neuer sowie der Weiterentwicklung bestehender KI-Lösungen mit\nAustausch, Schulung und externe Schnittstellen: Sie fördern die Akzeptanz und Nutzung von KI-Anwendungen, organisieren und moderieren Austausch- und Netzwerkformate, führen Workshops durch, identifizieren Schulungsbedarfe und agieren als Schnittstelle zu externen Know-how-Trägern und KI-Dienstleistern\nTrends, Regulierung und Branchenbezug: Sie verfolgen aktuelle KI-Trends und -Technologien und bringen Grundlagenkenntnisse zu KI-Regulierung, Compliance, Datenschutz sowie zu den Prozessen und Rahmenbedingungen der Energiewirtschaft ein\nIhr Profil\nErfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium im Bereich Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik, Data & Analytics oder eine vergleichbare Qualifikation\nSie verfügen über fundierte Kenntnisse im KI- und Datenumfeld mit klarem Business-Bezug und besitzen ein sicheres Verständnis von KI-Technologien, Daten- und Systemzusammenhängen\nSie sind in der Lage, technische Inhalte strukturiert aufzubereiten und verständlich zu vermitteln und bringen Erfahrung in der Moderation, der Durchführung von Workshops sowie in der Wissensvermittlung mit\nSie zeichnen sich durch eine selbstständige, strukturierte und analytische Arbeitsweise sowie durch Kommunikationsstärke und ein sicheres Auftreten gegenüber unterschiedlichen Stakeholdern aus\nSie haben ein hohes Interesse an technologischen Entwicklungen im KI-Umfeld\nSie verfügen über sehr gute Deutschkenntnisse (mindestens C1-Niveau)\n\nNicht alle Punkte zu 100% erfüllt? Dann überzeugen Sie uns gerne dennoch im Rahmen Ihrer Bewerbung von Ihren Fähigkeiten! Wir freuen uns darauf, Sie kennenzulernen! Wir setzen uns für Diversität und Chancengleichheit ein und suchen Menschen, die so vielfältig sind wie unser Netzwerk. Mit spannenden Entwicklungs- und Karrieremöglichkeiten innerhalb der Thüga-Gruppe entfalten Sie Ihre Energie und Fähigkeiten und gestalten mit uns eine erfolgreiche Energie- und Wärmewende!','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Thüga Aktiengesellschaft','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=585f00fe6ad3ffb7','scraped','vor 9 Tagen'),(2466,NULL,'job','R&D Engineer – Machine Learning & Optimization (m/f/d)','','Weimar',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We Are:\n\nAt Synopsys, we drive the innovations that shape the way we live and connect. Our technology is central to the Era of Pervasive Intelligence, from self-driving cars to learning machines. We lead in chip design, verification, and IP integration, empowering the creation of high-performance silicon chips and software content. Join us to transform the future through continuous technological innovation.\n\nYou Are:\n\nYou are a curious and motivated engineer with a passion for developing innovative algorithms and cutting-edge machine learning solutions. You thrive in collaborative environments, enjoy tackling complex mathematical challenges, and are eager to contribute to real-world industrial applications. Your background in engineering, computer science, mathematics, or physics has equipped you with a solid foundation in programming and analytical thinking. You are comfortable working with C++ and Python, and you have experience or a keen interest in fields such as machine learning, artificial intelligence, data mining, optimization, and uncertainty quantification.\n\nYou approach problems with creativity and rigor, seeking not just to solve them, but to create robust, scalable solutions that drive product excellence. You value continuous learning, whether it’s deepening your theoretical knowledge, mastering new tools and libraries, or collaborating with experts across disciplines. You communicate effectively, are receptive to feedback, and believe that sharing ideas leads to better outcomes. You aspire to make a measurable impact in a high-tech environment and are excited by the possibility of contributing to patentable innovations and research publications. If you’re looking for a role where your technical skills and innovative mindset can shape the future of design optimization, you’ll find your place on our team.\n\nWhat You’ll Be Doing:\nDesigning, implementing, maintaining, testing, evaluating, benchmarking, and documenting advanced algorithms and mathematical functions for ANSYS optiSLang.\nCollaborating closely with customer support teams to ensure developed algorithms are applicable and effective for industrial scenarios.\nLearning and applying best practices in software development, machine learning, and optimization.\nPerforming bug verification, release testing, and providing support for assigned software products.\nInvestigating and resolving technical problems identified by QA or product support, and developing innovative solutions.\nWorking under the guidance of experienced development managers and lead developers, contributing to both new methods and the improvement of existing implementations.\nThe Impact You Will Have:\nAdvance the capabilities of ANSYS optiSLang, driving innovation in process integration and parametric design optimization.\nEnable robust machine learning-based sensitivity analysis, optimization, and uncertainty quantification, empowering customers to solve complex engineering challenges.\nEnhance the efficiency and reliability of industrial applications through state-of-the-art algorithmic developments.\nSupport the creation of high-performance, multi-disciplinary optimization tools, expanding the reach and impact of Synopsys solutions.\nContribute to research publications and patentable ideas, shaping the future of optimization technologies.\nFacilitate the seamless integration of numerical simulation tools, ensuring scalable and flexible design workflows for customers worldwide.\nWhat You’ll Need:\nMaster’s degree in Engineering, Computer Science, Mathematics, Data Science, Technical Physics, or a related field.\nStrong proficiency in C++ and Python programming, with experience in object-oriented development.\nBackground in at least one of the following: machine learning, artificial intelligence, data mining, single-objective optimization, multi-objective decision making, or uncertainty quantification.\nFamiliarity with Python libraries for machine learning and data analysis, such as TensorFlow, Theano, PyTorch, Scikit-learn, pandas, etc.\nTheoretical knowledge of regression and classification methods, and experience with high-dimensional applications.\nWho You Are:\nAnalytical thinker with strong problem-solving skills.\nEffective communicator, able to collaborate across teams and share ideas clearly.\nQuick learner, adaptable to new technologies and methodologies.\nTeam player, comfortable working in geographically distributed groups.\nDetail-oriented, committed to quality and excellence in all deliverables.\nThe Team You’ll Be A Part Of:\n\nYou’ll join the ANSYS optiSLang Research and Development team, a dynamic group dedicated to advancing state-of-the-art software for machine learning-based sensitivity analysis, optimization, and uncertainty quantification. The team fosters innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning, working closely with experts across engineering, mathematics, and software development disciplines to deliver impactful solutions for industrial applications.\n\nRewards and Benefits:\n\nWe offer a comprehensive range of benefits to cater to your needs. Our total rewards include both monetary and non-monetary offerings. Your recruiter will provide more details about the salary range and benefits during the hiring process.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Synopsys','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=25048307c6a2235f','scraped','vor 9 Tagen'),(2467,NULL,'job','Senior Developer: Safe Vehicle Identification (m/f/d)','Vollzeit','14776 Brandenburg an der Havel',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Your mission\n\nDesign, develop, and maintain software systems for vehicle identification and tracking using cameras\n\nPrototype advanced algorithms in Python and implement/optimize them for real-time applications using C++ or Rust to ensure high-performance data processing\n\nLeverage computer vision, machine learning, and signal processing methodologies to improve anomaly detection and pattern recognition in video and sensor streams\n\nEnsure system reliability, safety, and performance under real-world conditions\n\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams (AI/ML, robotics, embedded systems, UX) to integrate end-to-end solutions\n\nLead architectural decisions and enforce best practices in scalability, security, and maintainability\n\nStay updated with the latest advancements in computer vision, machine learning, and software development, applying innovative solutions to maintain our technological edge\n\nMentor junior developers and contribute to code reviews and technical guidance\n\nYour profile\n\nBachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field\n\n5+ years of professional software development experience\n\nStrong proficiency in languages such Rust and C/C++\n\nProficiency in using Python data analysis libraries (e.g., SciPy, NumPy) and version control systems (e.g., Git)\n\nSolid understanding of distributed systems and backend architecture\n\nExperience with real-time systems, performance optimization, and high-performance data analysis\n\nFamiliarity with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, or GCP)\n\nStrong problem-solving skills and attention to detail\n\nEnglish language proficiency\n\nWhat we offer\n\nPermanent contract with immediate start\nLearning & development support (tech training, German courses, driver’s license assistance)\nFree Urban Sports Club membership\nJob bike via JobRad & Deutschland Ticket (incl. private use)\nFlexible work setup (Berlin area office + remote)\nWork on cutting-edge autonomous driving projects with leading OEMs\nFlat hierarchies, high ownership, and real impact, every member has a big influence on the final product\nSupportive, collaborative team culture, team members are always ready to help\n\nAbout us\n\nAt Copernicus Autonomous Control Systems GmbH, a wholly owned subsidiary of Ford Motor Company, we are shaping the future of intelligent mobility through advanced autonomous driving and infrastructure-based control systems.\n\nBuilding on deep expertise in automated vehicle movement, we develop cutting-edge solutions that enable autonomous valet parking and maneuvering in complex real-world environments such as parking facilities, logistics hubs, and industrial sites. Our approach focuses on shifting intelligence from the vehicle to the surrounding infrastructure—leveraging AI, computer vision, and connected systems to orchestrate safe, precise, and efficient vehicle operations.\n\nAs part of Ford’s global innovation ecosystem, we play a key role in advancing Level 4 autonomous capabilities, delivering scalable and cost-effective solutions that enhance safety, optimize space utilization, and significantly improve user experience.\n\nDriven by a commitment to innovation, reliability, and safety, Copernicus Autonomous Control Systems GmbH is dedicated to enabling a future where vehicles move seamlessly and autonomously within smart environments—making parking and low-speed vehicle operations effortless and intelligent.\n\nVideo','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'CACS Copernicus Autonomous Control Systems GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f33c684506c29fc3','scraped','vor 9 Tagen'),(2468,NULL,'job','Head of Digitalization & AI (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','66740 Saarlouis',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Amphenol-Air LB ist Teil der Amphenol-Gruppe, einer der weltweit größten Hersteller von Verbindungstechniken. Zuverlässige Lösungen, Steckverbindungen und Verkabelungen sowie innovative Entwicklungen und präzise Fertigung mit hoher Qualität, dafür steht Amphenol-Air LB. Als Teil der international agierenden Amphenol-Gruppe mit weltweit über 190.000 Mitarbeitern garantieren wir allzeit erstklassige Kontakte.\n\nAufgaben\n\nSie treiben die digitale Transformation unseres Unternehmens mit Fokus auf den Einsatz von Künstlicher Intelligenz entlang unserer Kernprozesse – insbesondere in Engineering, Vertrieb sowie Compliance & Dokumentation.\n\nDabei übernehmen Sie nicht nur die strategische Steuerung, sondern setzen zentrale Lösungen auch selbst um und bauen schrittweise ein leistungsfähiges Team auf.\n\nIhr Ziel: Messbare Verbesserungen in Effizienz, Geschwindigkeit und Qualität durch den gezielten Einsatz von KI.\n\nEntwicklung und Umsetzung einer KI- und Digitalisierungsstrategie mit klarem Business-Fokus\nIdentifikation, Priorisierung und Umsetzung konkreter Use Cases (z. B. Angebotsautomatisierung, Engineering-Copilots, Dokumentationssysteme)\nEigenständige Umsetzung von Prototypen und Pilotprojekten (Hands-on)\nAufbau und Weiterentwicklung einer unternehmensweiten Daten- und KI-Architektur (z. B. LLMs, RAG-Systeme, Automatisierung)\nEnge Zusammenarbeit mit Engineering, Vertrieb und Qualitätsmanagement\nSteuerung externer Partner\nAufbau eines kleinen, schlagkräftigen internen Teams\nDefinition und Tracking von KPIs (z. B. Angebotsdauer, Entwicklungszeit, Automatisierungsgrad)\nQualifikation\n\nFachlich\n\nAbgeschlossenes Studium im Bereich Ingenieurwesen, Informatik, Wirtschaftsinformatik oder vergleichbar\nMehrjährige Erfahrung in Digitalisierung, Automatisierung oder KI-Projekten – idealerweise im industriellen Umfeld\nVerständnis für technische Produkte und Engineering-Prozesse\nErfahrung im Umgang mit Daten, APIs und modernen KI-Technologien (z. B. LLMs, Machine Learning, Automatisierungstools)\n\nPersönlich\n\nUnternehmerisches Denken und ausgeprägte Umsetzungsstärke\nFähigkeit, strategisch zu denken und gleichzeitig operativ zu arbeiten\nKommunikationsstärke und Fähigkeit, zwischen Fachbereichen und Technik zu vermitteln\nHands-on-Mentalität: Sie setzen Dinge selbst um, nicht nur konzeptionell\nHohe Eigenverantwortung und Gestaltungswille\n\nWas Sie mitbringen sollten (konkret)\n\nErfahrung mit Tools/Technologien wie:\n\nPython (für Prototyping)\n\nAPIs & Datenintegration\n\nCloud-Plattformen (z. B. Azure, AWS)\n\nLLM-Anwendungen (z. B. Chatbots, Dokumentenanalyse)\n\nErfahrung mit einem oder mehreren der folgenden Bereiche:\n\nEngineering / Produktentwicklung\n\nB2B-Vertrieb technischer Produkte\n\nQualitäts- oder Compliance-Prozesse\n\nBenefits\nDirekte Zusammenarbeit mit der Geschäftsführung\nHoher Gestaltungsspielraum und echte Verantwortung\nMöglichkeit, eine zentrale Zukunftsfunktion im Unternehmen aufzubauen\nKurze Entscheidungswege und mittelständische Struktur\nAttraktives Vergütungspaket inkl. Bonus, sowie attraktive Zusatzleistungen, z. B. arbeitgeberfinanzierte Altersvorsorge, Kinderbetreuungszuschuss und Essensgutscheine\nFlexible Arbeitszeiten (Gleitzeit) für eine bessere Vereinbarkeit von Beruf und Privatleben\nAttraktives Vergütungspaket inkl. Bonus, sowie attraktive Zusatzleistungen, z. B. arbeitgeberfinanzierte Altersvorsorge, Kinderbetreuungszuschuss und Essensgutscheine\n\nWir freuen uns auf Ihre Bewerbung!','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Amphenol-Air LB GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=321e941ee4cd8c60','scraped','vor 3 Tagen'),(2469,NULL,'job','System Engineer - German Speaker','','65396 Walluf',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Building an AI‑first organisation is central to Clinisys’ purpose and the impact we deliver. As a global provider of intelligent diagnostic informatics solutions, we build AI‑enabled, cloud‑based platforms to enhance diagnostic workflows across healthcare, life sciences, and public health. By applying intelligent technology thoughtfully and responsibly, we help laboratories and testing environments operate more effectively, generate meaningful insights at scale, and ultimately support healthier and safer communities. Operating across more than 30 countries, Clinisys expects all colleagues—regardless of role or function — to work confidently with AI‑enabled tools, apply digital and analytical thinking, and continuously adapt as technologies evolve, must drive an AI first sense of purpose and urgency.\n\nClinisys has built an unrivalled reputation for deploying complex diagnostic networks and academic centres – and is the only provider to repetitively deliver to all disciplines end-to-end – at scale. Fostering healthier communities.\n\nRole Description\n\nThe Systems Engineer is responsible for setting up Clinisys application environments and their migrations. They are an expert in their field of expertise and are the customer’s single point of contact during the intervention. In an increasingly data-driven and AI-enabled environment, the Systems Engineer also contributes to the deployment, operation, and reliability of platforms that leverage advanced analytics and AI-driven capabilities within Clinisys solutions.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nFollow the instructions of your manager and the project manager in the context of a new deployment.\n\nInform the project manager of recommendations and potential technical risks, including those related to performance, data quality, or AI-enabled components.\n\nPrepare interventions and associated technical documentation.\n\nEnsure that the CRM tool contains the necessary product licenses in the project and generate the key license file prior to on-site or remote installation.\n\nCarry out assigned project tasks according to the schedule defined by the project manager, respecting estimates and ensuring customer satisfaction.\n\nAct as the technical owner of assigned tasks, including environments hosting advanced analytics or AI-enabled services.\n\nSupport and operate application components that may include AI-driven features such as intelligent workflow optimization, decision support, or data analytics.\n\nCustomer training on-site or remotely, including explanations of AI-assisted functionalities where relevant.\n\nDraft intervention reports for each on-site or remote intervention and transmit them to administrative services.\n\nCommunicate outcomes and key information to the project manager after each intervention.\n\nImmediately alert the project manager or management to issues encountered, including data integrity, performance, or model-related concerns.\n\nEnsure that project task progress, time tracking, and intervention reporting are accurately maintained in the CRM tool.\n\nEstablish and maintain a strong customer relationship with a clear service-oriented mindset.\n\nAttend internal and customer-led meetings, with the project manager when necessary.\n\nParticipate in the drafting and maintenance of technical documentation, including documentation related to AI-enabled system behaviour and limitations.\n\nPropose product and service improvements, including opportunities for automation, intelligent monitoring, or AI-driven optimization, to improve delivery time and product quality.\n\nContribute to team spirit and actively promote a customer-oriented approach.\n\nKnowledge, Skills & Abilities:\n\nCore Technical Skills Knowledge and use of Linux (including vi).\n\nKnowledge, use, and administration of Windows Server.\n\nKnowledge of Oracle and SQL Server databases.\n\nKnowledge of PROGRESS database is a plus. Experience with Structured Query Language (SQL).\n\nKnowledge of healthcare and laboratory standards and protocols (HL7, Hprim, ASTM).\n\nNetwork skills and understanding of file transfer and sharing mechanisms (Samba, CIFS, sFTP, NFS).\n\nAbility to synthesize information and produce clear technical documentation using MS Office tools.\n\nGood level of English and Fluent German.\n\nKnowledge of the analytical laboratory environment and related vocabulary is a plus.\n\nAI & Data-Oriented Competencies\n\nGeneral understanding of AI and machine learning concepts (e.g. predictive models, rule-based systems, intelligent automation) as applied to healthcare and diagnostic workflows.\n\nAwareness of data quality, data integrity, and data governance principles, especially in regulated healthcare environments.\n\nAbility to support and operate systems integrating AI-enabled components, including monitoring, performance validation, and incident analysis.\n\nFamiliarity with AI-assisted observability tools (log analysis, anomaly detection, performance monitoring) is a plus.\n\nUnderstanding of ethical, regulatory, and security considerations related to AI in healthcare (explainability, traceability, privacy).\n\nInterest in automation and intelligent tooling to improve deployment, monitoring, and operational efficiency.\n\nAbility to collaborate effectively with data, product, and R&D teams on AI-related topics, acting as a technical bridge with customers.\n\nProfessional Skills\n\nRespect for deadlines and targets, individually and as part of a team.\n\nStrong analytical mindset with the ability to “think outside the box”.\n\nProactive attitude in proposing new ideas and continuous improvement initiatives.\n\nStrong customer focus and communication skills.\n\nOnboarding\nAs part of our onboarding process, all new employees will be required to attend / travel to the office on their first day of employment. This requirement is essential for onboarding activities, including the identity verification, completion of necessary documentation, receiving your IT equipment, introductions to key team members, and orientation to Clinisys policies and procedures.\n\nEqual Opportunity Statement\nClinisys is committed to fostering an inclusive and respectful workplace. In accordance with the German General Equal Treatment Act (AGG), we welcome applications from all individuals regardless of gender identity, including male, female, and diverse. We want to make it clear that all qualified candidates will be equally assessed and considered for employment.\n\nWe encourage applicants from all backgrounds to apply and help us advance our mission to improve diagnostic workflows and public health outcomes across communities.\n\n#LI-AD #LI-REMOTE','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Clinisys','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a7ede70c57bc1054','scraped','vor 9 Tagen'),(2470,NULL,'job','Associate Director of Engineering - Revenue Tech (m/f/d)','Vollzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nLaunched in 2021 with a simple yet bold mission, Flink set out to give people back their most valuable resource: time. We didn\'t just join the quick commerce race, we defined its potential. By enabling customers to order from a curated selection of over 3,000 groceries and household essentials through our user-centric app, we deliver what people need in minutes. We have fundamentally shifted the retail landscape across Germany and the Netherlands, while embedding sustainability into our core through an all-electric delivery fleet, recyclable packaging, and a focus on reducing food waste.\n\nToday, Flink has evolved from a disruptive startup into a resilient and sustainable powerhouse. In an industry defined by rapid change, we’ve mastered the balance of hyper-efficiency and massive scale. With a network of around 160 hubs, we now bring the Flink experience to more than 22 million people, making us an integral part of the urban infrastructure. This impact is driven by a dedicated team of more than 10,000 colleagues, including a fully employed rider fleet that serves as the backbone of our operations. By generating over €550m in revenue in 2025, we have proven that our model is not only desirable but financially formidable.\n\nHaving built a proven foundation, we are now shifting from establishing our presence to accelerating our impact. Backed by prestigious partners like Prosus, Mubadala, Bond, DoorDash, Btomorrow Ventures and REWE, and fueled by fresh investment, we are entering our next major growth phase. We are thinking bigger, expanding our footprint, and refining every link in our value chain.\n\nOur culture is defined by a shared bias for action and the commitment to being 1% better every day. We take ownership, stay close to the frontline, and support one another to ensure we never let another Flinker fail. We celebrate diversity and believe that our multicultural team is our greatest competitive advantage.\n\nAre you ready to shape the future of quick commerce with us?\n\nJob Description\n\nWe are creating a brand-new engineering domain: Revenue Technology (RevTech). This domain will own the full commercial technology stack that powers how the items in our assortment are selected for each hub, how they are priced, how promotions and retail media campaigns are managed, and how product data flows through the organization. It sits alongside our Consumer Tech, Operations Tech, and Platform domains.\n\nAs the Associate Director of Engineering - RevTech (m/f/d), you will be the founding engineering leader of this domain. Paired with our VP of Revenue, who leads the domain from the Product side, you will shape the technical vision, hire and grow the teams, and deliver the systems that directly drive Flink\'s gross profit and assortment relevance. This is a rare opportunity to build a domain from the ground up inside a company with real scale, real customers, and real urgency.\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\nLead the RevTech engineering organization. You will inherit a small group of engineers transferring from existing domains and grow it into a cohesive, high-performing group across multiple product teams — including Assortment, Master Data & ERP, Pricing & Promotions, and Commercial Back-office.\n\nPartner with the VP of Revenue to own the domain roadmap. Together you will prioritize across teams, balance build-vs-buy decisions, and ensure the engineering investment maps tightly to commercial outcomes like use-case coverage, GP per category, and pricing automation.\n\nHire and develop engineering managers and engineers. Several key roles, including an EM for Pricing & Promotions, backend and frontend engineers, and a data scientist, are open and waiting for you to shape and fill. You will also manage the relationship with an external development partner building some of our systems, ensuring quality, architecture alignment, and a clean path to internalization.\n\nDrive technical excellence in a greenfield-meets-brownfield context. Some systems are being built from scratch; others are being transferred and evolved. You will define the technical strategy that brings coherence to this landscape — shared APIs, data contracts, service boundaries, and on-call practices across small but critical teams.\n\nNavigate a matrix organization. Engineers functionally report into the CTO organization while being embedded in the RevTech domain. You will work closely with fellow Engineering Directors in Consumer Tech, Operations Tech, and Platform to maintain cross-domain standards, coordinate shared services, and ensure a consistent engineering culture.\n\nChampion AI and automation across the commercial stack. RevTech\'s core mission is to optimize processes via intelligent systems — from data-driven assortment engines and automated pricing to product data enrichment and demand forecasting. You will identify where AI and machine learning can create step-change improvements, partner with our Data Science team to bring models into production, and foster a culture where the team continuously leverages AI to multiply its impact.\n\nRepresent engineering in commercial conversations. RevTech sits at the intersection of technology, category management, and revenue strategy. You\'ll regularly engage with non-technical stakeholders — Revenue, Marketing, Supply Chain — and translate their challenges into well-scoped engineering problems.\n\nQualifications\nAn experienced engineering leader. You have 8+ years in software engineering with at least 3–4 years leading teams of teams (engineering managers reporting to you). You\'ve built or significantly scaled an engineering organization before, ideally in a product-driven company.\nExcited about AI and data-driven systems. You have a strong point of view on how AI, ML, and modern automation can transform commercial operations. Whether it\'s applying LLMs to product data enrichment, building recommendation engines for assortment, or using predictive models for pricing, you know how to move from experiment to production and are eager to push the boundary.\nA domain builder. You have experience standing up new teams or domains — not just inheriting established ones. You\'re energized by ambiguity, comfortable defining scope and structure, and skilled at earning trust across functions quickly.\nTechnically credible. You don\'t need to write code daily, but you can review architecture decisions, challenge technical trade-offs, and hold your own in discussions about system design, data modeling, API contracts, and service reliability. Experience with backend-heavy systems and system integrations (e.g., pricing engines, data pipelines, ERP integrations) is a strong plus.\nCommercially minded. You understand that engineering in this domain exists to move business metrics. You\'re comfortable working with concepts like gross profit, margin optimization, assortment logic, and retail media, or excited to learn them fast.\nA strong communicator and collaborator. You will operate at the seam between engineering, product, and business leadership. You need to be equally effective in a technical deep-dive, a tech strategy conversation with the CTO, and a roadmap review with the VP of Revenue.\nPragmatic about vendor management. You have experience working with external development agencies or outsourced teams, and you know how to maintain quality and architectural coherence when not all code is written in-house.\nAdditional Information\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nA leadership role with real ownership: you\'re not maintaining a domain, you\'re creating one\nA collaborative, low-ego leadership team that values craft and speed\nA €1000 annual L&D budget as well as individual coaching options to ensure you have plenty of opportunities to learn, grow and achieve your goals\n26 days of vacation, +1 day every year up to a maximum of 30 days\nA mobility budget of 35 EUR per month for Deutschland Ticket subsidy\nA discount on your Urban Sports Club membership\nAttractive company pension options\nUnlimited access to an e-learning and development platform, MyAcademy, including online German courses\nOnline discounts with Corporate Benefits and Future Bens\nA cool discount off your personal Flink orders; be the first to test out new products!\nA modern and dog-friendly office in the heart of Berlin - lots of delicious lunch spots available within short walking distance\n\nIt is our commitment that every applicant will be evaluated according to their skills regardless of age, gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability status, or religion.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Flink','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1d49f1488e0c6fed','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2471,NULL,'job','PLM Engineering Data Engineer (m/w/d)','','29345 Unterlüß',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'WOFÜR WIR SIE SUCHEN\nEinführung von Methoden und Tools des Data Engineerings für unsere Produkt-Management-Datenbanken im Rahmen des entwicklungszentrierten Product-Lifecycle-Managements (PLM)\nEntwicklung von intelligenten, skalierbaren, wiederverwendbaren und zuverlässigen Lösungen und Methoden für die Datenanalyse, -integration, -bereinigung und -verarbeitung\nGenerierung von neuen Insights zusammen mit unseren Domänen- und Datenexperten (m/w/d) unserer Entwicklungsbereiche und Partner (m/w/d)\nKategorie-Entwicklung, um diese mithilfe von Clustering- und Klassifikationsalgorithmen in informativere Datenstrukturen zu überführen\nAufbau von Machine-Learning Modellen, insbesondere im Bereich Clustering, Klassifikation und Textanalyse\nDefinition und Umsetzung von Anforderungen im Rahmen der Datenhaltungs- und Verarbeitungssysteme\nUnterstützung bei der automatischen Engineering-Datenbereitstellung für die Anwendungsfelder Collaborative Engineering und digitale Verwaltung von Produkt-Entwicklungsdaten\n\nDie Stelle kann an den Standorten Kassel, Kiel, Unterlüß oder Hamburg besetzt werden.\n\nWAS SIE MITBRINGEN SOLLTEN\nErfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium, z. B. Informatik, Ingenieurwesen, Data Science oder Mathematik, oder aber eine vergleichbare Qualifikation mit den Schwerpunkten Data Science, Data Analytics\nFundierte Erfahrungen zu Methoden der semantischen Analyse (z. B. Natural Language Processing) zur strukturierten Auswertung textbasierter Daten\nGute Kenntnisse in Datenbankabfragen und Automation mit SQL (PowerShell, Skripte, PowerBI), Datenvisualisierung und Data Queries sowie objektorientierter Softwareentwicklung\nBerufserfahrung im Umgang mit PLM Datenbanken und Datenmodellen von Vorteil\nKenntnisse in NLP-Frameworks (z. B. spaCy, NLTK, transformers) sowie ML-Bibliotheken wie scikit-learn oder PyTorch / TensorFlow wünschenswert\nHohe Bereitschaft, komplexe Datenmodelle zu verstehen, semantische Beziehungen zu erfassen und domänenspezifisches Wissen analytisch aufzubereiten\nSehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\nKommunikationsstärke sowie Teamfähigkeit\n\nWAS WIR IHNEN BIETEN\n\nAn unserem Standort in Kassel bieten wir Ihnen:\n\nArbeiten an Gesamtsystemen\nBetriebliche Altersvorsorge\nMitarbeiteraktienkaufprogramm\nErgebnisbeteiligung\nFlexible Arbeitszeitmodelle, Gleitzeitmodell sowie VIVA-Familien-Service\nSubventioniertes Mittagessen und Kiosk am Standort\nFitness- und Gesundheitsangebote\nCorporate Benefits Plattform mit exklusiven Mitarbeiterrabatten für zahlreiche Shops\nVergünstigtes Jobticket\nIndividuelle und vielfältige externe sowie interne Weiterentwicklungsmöglichkeiten, u.a. in der Rheinmetall Academy\nProfessioneller Einarbeitungsprozess begleitet durch ein digitales Onboarding-Tool\n\nMehr über unseren Standort und unsere Mitarbeiter (m/w/d) in Kassel erfahren Sie hier.\n\nKONTAKTDETAILS\n\nZuständige/r Ansprechpartner/in: Sherin Schümchen\n\nFür Fragen zu Ihrer Bewerbung, nutzen Sie bitte das Kontaktformular.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Rheinmetall Landsysteme GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=50fb230ee1b372c2','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2472,NULL,'job','Research Engineer Neuro-Symbolic AI & Mulitmodal Assistant Systems (f/m/div.)','Vollzeit','71272 Renningen',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nAt Bosch, we shape the future by inventing high-quality technologies and services that spark enthusiasm and enrich people’s lives. Our promise to our associates is rock-solid: We grow together, we enjoy our work, and we inspire each other. Welcome to Bosch.\n\nThe Robert Bosch GmbH is looking forward to your application!\n\nJob Description\n\nAre you passionate about building intelligent systems that truly understand and reason, especially within the complex fields of manufacturing, product development, and maintenance? Neuro-Symbolic AI is leading the next big step in AI, offering huge potential to improve production, boost automation, and enable smarter decisions, bringing us closer to human-like intelligence. We are seeking a highly motivated research engineer to strengthen our team, drive the development of Neuro-Symbolic AI approaches, and enable their practical application in concrete use cases.\n\nAs part of our advanced research team, you will conduct excellent research on Neuro-Symbolic AI methodologies to combine formal knowledge representations with machine learning techniques.\nYou will independently develop and integrate multi-modal data pipelines for Neuro-Symbolic AI.\nAdditionally, you will design and implement the architecture for advanced analysis and reasoning engines for solving complex problems.\nYou will design and implement knowledge-based AI systems with natural language interaction.\nFurthermore, you will work closely with an international team of experts to effectively transfer research solutions into business-relevant use cases such as product development, maintenance, and repair.\nLast but not least, you will proactively stay informed about the latest advances in AI and machine learning to keep Bosch at the forefront of innovation in this field.\n\nQualifications\n\nEducation: PhD in Computer Science, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, or a related field\nExperience and Know-how:\nexpertise in Neuro-Symbolic AI architectures and frameworks\nproven ability to design, implement, and integrate hybrid AI systems that combine machine learning with symbolic reasoning (e.g., knowledge graphs, rule sets, logic programming, ontologies) to meet complex requirements\nadvanced knowledge in building robust data pipelines for multi-modal integration (integration, cleaning, and preprocessing of heterogeneous data sources)\npractical experience in applying state-of-the-art NLP techniques (e.g., Transformers, LLMs, information extraction) to understand user queries, extract insights from texts, and contribute to the automatic construction and expansion of dynamic knowledge bases\nPersonality and Working Practice: you succeed in translating complex research findings into practical solutions and enjoy working in an international team.\nLanguages: very good English skills written and spoken, German is a plus\n\nAdditional Information\n\nhttps://www.bosch-ai.com\nwww.bosch.com/research\n\nPlease submit all relevant documents (CV, certificates, and links to GitHub or kaggle account).\n\nWe offer flexible working models: from various part-time options to mobile working and job sharing. Feel free to contact us.\n\nDiversity and inclusion are not just trends for us but are firmly anchored in our corporate culture. Therefore, we welcome all applications, regardless of gender, age, disability, religion, ethnic origin or sexual identity.\n\nNeed support during your application?\nKathrin Stipak (Human Resources)\n+49 711 811 38015\n\nNeed further information about the job?\nMirjam Steger (Functional Department)\n\nWork #LikeABosch starts here: Apply now!','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Bosch Group','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b8fb4b65a866b437','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2473,NULL,'job','PLM Engineering Data Engineer (m/w/d)','','24107 Kiel',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'WOFÜR WIR SIE SUCHEN\nEinführung von Methoden und Tools des Data Engineerings für unsere Produkt-Management-Datenbanken im Rahmen des entwicklungszentrierten Product-Lifecycle-Managements (PLM)\nEntwicklung von intelligenten, skalierbaren, wiederverwendbaren und zuverlässigen Lösungen und Methoden für die Datenanalyse, -integration, -bereinigung und -verarbeitung\nGenerierung von neuen Insights zusammen mit unseren Domänen- und Datenexperten (m/w/d) unserer Entwicklungsbereiche und Partner (m/w/d)\nKategorie-Entwicklung, um diese mithilfe von Clustering- und Klassifikationsalgorithmen in informativere Datenstrukturen zu überführen\nAufbau von Machine-Learning Modellen, insbesondere im Bereich Clustering, Klassifikation und Textanalyse\nDefinition und Umsetzung von Anforderungen im Rahmen der Datenhaltungs- und Verarbeitungssysteme\nUnterstützung bei der automatischen Engineering-Datenbereitstellung für die Anwendungsfelder Collaborative Engineering und digitale Verwaltung von Produkt-Entwicklungsdaten\n\nDie Stelle kann an den Standorten Kassel, Kiel, Unterlüß oder Hamburg besetzt werden.\n\nWAS SIE MITBRINGEN SOLLTEN\nErfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium, z. B. Informatik, Ingenieurwesen, Data Science oder Mathematik, oder aber eine vergleichbare Qualifikation mit den Schwerpunkten Data Science, Data Analytics\nFundierte Erfahrungen zu Methoden der semantischen Analyse (z. B. Natural Language Processing) zur strukturierten Auswertung textbasierter Daten\nGute Kenntnisse in Datenbankabfragen und Automation mit SQL (PowerShell, Skripte, PowerBI), Datenvisualisierung und Data Queries sowie objektorientierter Softwareentwicklung\nBerufserfahrung im Umgang mit PLM Datenbanken und Datenmodellen von Vorteil\nKenntnisse in NLP-Frameworks (z. B. spaCy, NLTK, transformers) sowie ML-Bibliotheken wie scikit-learn oder PyTorch / TensorFlow wünschenswert\nHohe Bereitschaft, komplexe Datenmodelle zu verstehen, semantische Beziehungen zu erfassen und domänenspezifisches Wissen analytisch aufzubereiten\nSehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\nKommunikationsstärke sowie Teamfähigkeit\n\nWAS WIR IHNEN BIETEN\n\nAn unserem Standort in Kassel bieten wir Ihnen:\n\nArbeiten an Gesamtsystemen\nBetriebliche Altersvorsorge\nMitarbeiteraktienkaufprogramm\nErgebnisbeteiligung\nFlexible Arbeitszeitmodelle, Gleitzeitmodell sowie VIVA-Familien-Service\nSubventioniertes Mittagessen und Kiosk am Standort\nFitness- und Gesundheitsangebote\nCorporate Benefits Plattform mit exklusiven Mitarbeiterrabatten für zahlreiche Shops\nVergünstigtes Jobticket\nIndividuelle und vielfältige externe sowie interne Weiterentwicklungsmöglichkeiten, u.a. in der Rheinmetall Academy\nProfessioneller Einarbeitungsprozess begleitet durch ein digitales Onboarding-Tool\n\nMehr über unseren Standort und unsere Mitarbeiter (m/w/d) in Kassel erfahren Sie hier.\n\nKONTAKTDETAILS\n\nZuständige/r Ansprechpartner/in: Sherin Schümchen\n\nFür Fragen zu Ihrer Bewerbung, nutzen Sie bitte das Kontaktformular.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Rheinmetall Landsysteme GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d1f118c9c1654d27','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2474,NULL,'job','PLM Engineering Data Engineer (m/w/d)','','22763 Hamburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'WOFÜR WIR SIE SUCHEN\nEinführung von Methoden und Tools des Data Engineerings für unsere Produkt-Management-Datenbanken im Rahmen des entwicklungszentrierten Product-Lifecycle-Managements (PLM)\nEntwicklung von intelligenten, skalierbaren, wiederverwendbaren und zuverlässigen Lösungen und Methoden für die Datenanalyse, -integration, -bereinigung und -verarbeitung\nGenerierung von neuen Insights zusammen mit unseren Domänen- und Datenexperten (m/w/d) unserer Entwicklungsbereiche und Partner (m/w/d)\nKategorie-Entwicklung, um diese mithilfe von Clustering- und Klassifikationsalgorithmen in informativere Datenstrukturen zu überführen\nAufbau von Machine-Learning Modellen, insbesondere im Bereich Clustering, Klassifikation und Textanalyse\nDefinition und Umsetzung von Anforderungen im Rahmen der Datenhaltungs- und Verarbeitungssysteme\nUnterstützung bei der automatischen Engineering-Datenbereitstellung für die Anwendungsfelder Collaborative Engineering und digitale Verwaltung von Produkt-Entwicklungsdaten\n\nDie Stelle kann an den Standorten Kassel, Kiel, Unterlüß oder Hamburg besetzt werden.\n\nWAS SIE MITBRINGEN SOLLTEN\nErfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium, z. B. Informatik, Ingenieurwesen, Data Science oder Mathematik, oder aber eine vergleichbare Qualifikation mit den Schwerpunkten Data Science, Data Analytics\nFundierte Erfahrungen zu Methoden der semantischen Analyse (z. B. Natural Language Processing) zur strukturierten Auswertung textbasierter Daten\nGute Kenntnisse in Datenbankabfragen und Automation mit SQL (PowerShell, Skripte, PowerBI), Datenvisualisierung und Data Queries sowie objektorientierter Softwareentwicklung\nBerufserfahrung im Umgang mit PLM Datenbanken und Datenmodellen von Vorteil\nKenntnisse in NLP-Frameworks (z. B. spaCy, NLTK, transformers) sowie ML-Bibliotheken wie scikit-learn oder PyTorch / TensorFlow wünschenswert\nHohe Bereitschaft, komplexe Datenmodelle zu verstehen, semantische Beziehungen zu erfassen und domänenspezifisches Wissen analytisch aufzubereiten\nSehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\nKommunikationsstärke sowie Teamfähigkeit\n\nWAS WIR IHNEN BIETEN\n\nAn unserem Standort in Kassel bieten wir Ihnen:\n\nArbeiten an Gesamtsystemen\nBetriebliche Altersvorsorge\nMitarbeiteraktienkaufprogramm\nErgebnisbeteiligung\nFlexible Arbeitszeitmodelle, Gleitzeitmodell sowie VIVA-Familien-Service\nSubventioniertes Mittagessen und Kiosk am Standort\nFitness- und Gesundheitsangebote\nCorporate Benefits Plattform mit exklusiven Mitarbeiterrabatten für zahlreiche Shops\nVergünstigtes Jobticket\nIndividuelle und vielfältige externe sowie interne Weiterentwicklungsmöglichkeiten, u.a. in der Rheinmetall Academy\nProfessioneller Einarbeitungsprozess begleitet durch ein digitales Onboarding-Tool\n\nMehr über unseren Standort und unsere Mitarbeiter (m/w/d) in Kassel erfahren Sie hier.\n\nKONTAKTDETAILS\n\nZuständige/r Ansprechpartner/in: Sherin Schümchen\n\nFür Fragen zu Ihrer Bewerbung, nutzen Sie bitte das Kontaktformular.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Rheinmetall Landsysteme GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=13c305378ee44790','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2475,NULL,'job','Softwareentwickler - Python / 3D / Computer Vision (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','90403 Nürnberg',NULL,'',4940080000.00,'49.400 € – 80.000 € pro Jahr','Über dev-threads GmbH\nWas entsteht, wenn Leidenschaft und fundiertes Fachwissen zusammentreffen? Wir gestalten die Zukunft der Softwareentwicklung, indem wir durchdachte und nachvollziehbare Lösungen für komplexe Herausforderungen schaffen. Du suchst eine Position, in der du deine Expertise in der Entwicklung anspruchsvoller Applikationen und Algorithmen einbringen kannst? Hier findest du die Möglichkeit, deine Fähigkeiten zu entfalten und einen echten Beitrag zu leisten, der dich persönlich und fachlich voranbringt.\nWas bieten wir Ihnen?\n\nAttraktive Projekte: Sie arbeiten an anspruchsvollen und abwechslungsreichen Projekten in Zukunftsfeldern wie Computergrafik, Machine Learning, AR/VR und Datenanalyse\nGestaltungsspielraum: Sie haben einen hohen Gestaltungsspielraum und die Möglichkeit, eigene Ideen aktiv einzubringen\nTechnologische Vielfalt: Sie arbeiten mit modernen Technologien und vielfältigen Tech-Stacks, darunter Python, C++, Web und DevOps\nTeamkultur: Sie profitieren von flachen Hierarchien und direkter Kommunikation im Team\nFlexibilität und Innovation: Sie genießen eine flexible Arbeitsweise in einem innovativen, entwicklungsorientierten Umfeld\nWeiterentwicklung: Sie haben die Möglichkeit zur kontinuierlichen fachlichen Weiterentwicklung und Zugang zu neuen Technologien\n\nWas erwartet Sie?\n\nSie entwickeln individuelle Softwarelösungen und Applikationen für Kundenprojekte\nSie setzen komplexe Algorithmen um und optimieren datengetriebene Anwendungen\nSie arbeiten an Projekten im Bereich Computergrafik, 3D, Computer Vision, Webanwendungen und moderner Softwarearchitekturen mit\nSie entwickeln Prototypen „from scratch“ und verbessern bestehende Systeme weiter\nSie analysieren technische Anforderungen und konzipieren geeignete Lösungen\nSie arbeiten in kleinen, hochqualifizierten Entwicklerteams, teilweise mit wissenschaftlichem Background, zusammen\n\nWas sollten Sie mitbringen?\nSie haben ein erfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium der Informatik (Master, Universität) oder vergleichbar\nSie verfügen über sehr gute Programmierkenntnisse, insbesondere in Python, und optional in TypeScript, React oder vergleichbaren Frontend-Technologien\nSie besitzen Kenntnisse im Bereich Computergrafik, 3D-Modellierung und visuelle Datenverarbeitung, wie Rendering, Geometrieverarbeitung, AR/VR\nSie haben ein fundiertes Verständnis von Algorithmen, Datenstrukturen und objektorientierter Programmierung\nSie haben Erfahrung im Umgang mit modernen Technologien und Tools, wie Git, Docker, CI/CD, von Vorteil\nSie verfügen über analytisches Denkvermögen, ausgeprägtes technisches Verständnis und die Fähigkeit, sich schnell in neue Themengebiete einzuarbeiten\n\nUnser Jobangebot Softwareentwickler - Python / 3D / Computer Vision (m/w/d) klingt vielversprechend?\n\nBei unserem Partner Workwise ist eine Bewerbung für diesen Job in nur wenigen Minuten und ohne Anschreiben möglich. Anschließend kann der Status der Bewerbung live verfolgt werden. Wir freuen uns auf eine Bewerbung über Workwise.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'dev-threads GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=03f29c86f40891ac','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2476,NULL,'job','Lead IT Architect - AIOps Plattform (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','80331 München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Als primärer Digitalisierungspartner der Bundeswehr erbringen wir stabile, sichere und effiziente IT-Services im In- und Ausland, vom Grundbetrieb bis in den einsatznahen Bereich und tragen so zur kontinuierlichen Erhöhung der Führungs- und Einsatzfähigkeit der Bundeswehr bei. Mit über 8.000 Kolleg*innen betreiben und modernisieren wir eine der größten und komplexesten IT-Infrastrukturen in Deutschland. Wir suchen verantwortungsvolle IT-Spezialist*innen, die die Bundeswehr-IT aus Überzeugung in herausfordernden Digitalisierungsvorhaben weiterentwickeln und so einen Beitrag zur Sicherheit Deutschlands leisten wollen.\n\nSorge gemeinsam mit uns für die digitale Zukunftsfähigkeit unseres Landes.\n\nLead IT Architect - AIOps Plattform (m/w/d)\n\nab sofort und in Vollzeit bundesweit an einem unserer BWI Standorte.\n\nWerde Teil des Teams Automation & Engineering! Wir verantworten die Architektur moderner System- und Service-Management-Applikationen. Durch das Management unserer komplexen Applikationslandschaften unterstützen wir unsere Fachbereiche mit intelligenter Automatisierung.\n\nDeine Aufgaben:\n\nÜbernahme der architektonischen Verantwortung für das Event Management System sowie den strategischen und technologischen Aufbau unserer AIOps-Plattform\n\nStrategische Konzeption von Maßnahmen zur Weiterentwicklung bestehender Strukturen sowie Steuerung der Migration und Integration auf die Plattform\n\nBewertung und Priorisierung komplexer Anforderungen aus Fachbereichen oder Projekten und Erstellung von Lösungskonzepten\n\nFederführende Erstellung und Qualitätssicherung technischer Konzepte (Architektur-, Implementierungs-, Sicherheits- und Migrationskonzepte)\n\nMitwirkung bei Projekten im Kontext von AIOps und Automatisierung\n\nDein Profil:\nErfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium mit Informatikbezug oder vergleichbar mit mind. 7 Jahre relevanter Berufserfahrung in der IT-Architektur\nTiefgreifende Produktkenntnisse zu IBM Netcool, Cloud Pak for AIOps oder vergleichbaren Enterprise-Lösungen\nExpertise im Bereich AIOps, Event Management sowie in der Anwendung von Machine Learning zur IT-Betriebsautomatisierung.\nNachweisbare Erfahrung in der fachlichen Steuerung von interdisziplinären Entwicklungsteams und externen Dienstleistenden in komplexen Projektumgebungen\nStrategisches Denkvermögen, Durchsetzungsstärke sowie die Fähigkeit, komplexe Sachverhalte zielgruppengerecht auf Management-Ebene zu moderieren\n\nFließende Deutschkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\n\nWir bieten:\n\nDurch abwechslungsreiche und gesellschaftlich relevante Aufgaben gewährleisten wir den reibungslosen IT-Betrieb und die Digitalisierung der Bundeswehr\n\nDas Ziel eint uns. Dabei sind für uns ein wertschätzender Umgang miteinander sowie ein großer Teamgeist elementar\n\nDie BWI bietet eine marktgerechte Vergütung, einen sicheren Arbeitsplatz sowie eine prämierte und arbeitgeberfinanzierte betriebliche Altersvorsorge\n\nDu startest grundsätzlich mit 30 Tagen Jahresurlaub mit Option auf individuelle Anpassungen\n\nÜber unsere Benefit-App stehen Dir ein monatliches Guthaben und Steuervergünstigungen auf Tickets für den ÖPNV zur Verfügung\n\nHaben wir dein Interesse geweckt?\n\nDann bewirb dich hier\n\nBei Fragen steht dir das Recruiting-Team unter Angabe der Stellen-ID: 65167 gerne zur Verfügung. Tel.: 02225 988 25000','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'BWI GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ec64ba01a0f93fe8','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2477,NULL,'job','PLM Engineering Data Engineer (m/w/d)','','34127 Kassel',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'WOFÜR WIR SIE SUCHEN\nEinführung von Methoden und Tools des Data Engineerings für unsere Produkt-Management-Datenbanken im Rahmen des entwicklungszentrierten Product-Lifecycle-Managements (PLM)\nEntwicklung von intelligenten, skalierbaren, wiederverwendbaren und zuverlässigen Lösungen und Methoden für die Datenanalyse, -integration, -bereinigung und -verarbeitung\nGenerierung von neuen Insights zusammen mit unseren Domänen- und Datenexperten (m/w/d) unserer Entwicklungsbereiche und Partner (m/w/d)\nKategorie-Entwicklung, um diese mithilfe von Clustering- und Klassifikationsalgorithmen in informativere Datenstrukturen zu überführen\nAufbau von Machine-Learning Modellen, insbesondere im Bereich Clustering, Klassifikation und Textanalyse\nDefinition und Umsetzung von Anforderungen im Rahmen der Datenhaltungs- und Verarbeitungssysteme\nUnterstützung bei der automatischen Engineering-Datenbereitstellung für die Anwendungsfelder Collaborative Engineering und digitale Verwaltung von Produkt-Entwicklungsdaten\n\nDie Stelle kann an den Standorten Kassel, Kiel, Unterlüß oder Hamburg besetzt werden.\n\nWAS SIE MITBRINGEN SOLLTEN\nErfolgreich abgeschlossenes Studium, z. B. Informatik, Ingenieurwesen, Data Science oder Mathematik, oder aber eine vergleichbare Qualifikation mit den Schwerpunkten Data Science, Data Analytics\nFundierte Erfahrungen zu Methoden der semantischen Analyse (z. B. Natural Language Processing) zur strukturierten Auswertung textbasierter Daten\nGute Kenntnisse in Datenbankabfragen und Automation mit SQL (PowerShell, Skripte, PowerBI), Datenvisualisierung und Data Queries sowie objektorientierter Softwareentwicklung\nBerufserfahrung im Umgang mit PLM Datenbanken und Datenmodellen von Vorteil\nKenntnisse in NLP-Frameworks (z. B. spaCy, NLTK, transformers) sowie ML-Bibliotheken wie scikit-learn oder PyTorch / TensorFlow wünschenswert\nHohe Bereitschaft, komplexe Datenmodelle zu verstehen, semantische Beziehungen zu erfassen und domänenspezifisches Wissen analytisch aufzubereiten\nSehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\nKommunikationsstärke sowie Teamfähigkeit\n\nWAS WIR IHNEN BIETEN\n\nAn unserem Standort in Kassel bieten wir Ihnen:\n\nArbeiten an Gesamtsystemen\nBetriebliche Altersvorsorge\nMitarbeiteraktienkaufprogramm\nErgebnisbeteiligung\nFlexible Arbeitszeitmodelle, Gleitzeitmodell sowie VIVA-Familien-Service\nSubventioniertes Mittagessen und Kiosk am Standort\nFitness- und Gesundheitsangebote\nCorporate Benefits Plattform mit exklusiven Mitarbeiterrabatten für zahlreiche Shops\nVergünstigtes Jobticket\nIndividuelle und vielfältige externe sowie interne Weiterentwicklungsmöglichkeiten, u.a. in der Rheinmetall Academy\nProfessioneller Einarbeitungsprozess begleitet durch ein digitales Onboarding-Tool\n\nMehr über unseren Standort und unsere Mitarbeiter (m/w/d) in Kassel erfahren Sie hier.\n\nKONTAKTDETAILS\n\nZuständige/r Ansprechpartner/in: Sherin Schümchen\n\nFür Fragen zu Ihrer Bewerbung, nutzen Sie bitte das Kontaktformular.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Rheinmetall Landsysteme GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8bfb1998456b5d7d','scraped','vor 4 Tagen'),(2478,NULL,'job','DATA ANALYST (f/m/d)','Vollzeit','Frankfurt am Main',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Frankfurt am Main\nFull-time\nPermanent employee\nYour Role\nAs part of the Growth business, the Analytics team at 360T is at the forefront of our data strategy, envisioning and executing initiatives to unlock the potential of big data and analytics across the organisation. Our global team, consisting of data strategists, analysts & quants, collaborate with data engineers to harness technology, innovation, and modern data practices. Together, we deliver a new generation of self-service tools, commercial data products and analytics services to our global client base and business stakeholders.\n\nAs a Data Analyst (f/m/d), you will be the bridge connecting business, technology, and data. You recognize data as a catalyst for innovation and digital transformation. In this role, you will collaborate with partner teams across the firm, engage with C-suite stakeholders and interact with clients tackle complex business data challenges. Your ability to create compelling visual storytelling will be crucial in turning data into actionable business value.\nYour Responsibilities\nData Visualization: create impactful data visualizations using Tableau, Jupyter Notebooks and Plotly Dash to effectively communicate findings to stakeholders\nInsights & Recommendations: generate actionable insights from data analysis and present recommendations to improve business performance\nData Automation: assist in optimizing internal data processes and workflows\nData Collaboration & Empowerment: work closely with cross-functional teams to support ongoing data needs of internal partners & stakeholders, clients and regulatory bodies\nStakeholder Management: build effective working relationships with key business stakeholders including C-suite executives, data engineers and other partners across the firm to achieve common data-driven goals and targets\nContinuous Improvement: stay up to date with the latest trends and best practices in data analysis and visualization, and implement them to enhance 360T’s data capabilities\nYour Profile\nAround 3 years’ experience as a data analyst in a buy or sell-side environment\nProvide a portfolio showcasing previous data visualization projects and analysis work\nPassionate about data: you understand the value of data and the benefits and commercial opportunities it offers\nExperience of business intelligence techniques including data modeling, data collection, data mining, data analysis, data visualization and best practices\nSelf-starter: be eager to learn and have the drive and will to succeed\nExcellent communication and data-storytelling skills: use data to tell a story to both technical and business audiences\nProficiency in data visualization tools or libraries such as Tableau, Power BI, Plotly Dash, D3, or equivalent\nStrong SQL skills\nFamiliarity with programming languages such as Python or JavaScript\nBachelor’s degree in Business Analytics, Computer Science, Statistics, Data Science, or a related field\nAn understanding of how the Foreign Exchange market operates\nNice to have: some experience working in a highly regulated environment and associated processes\nNice to have: experience of big data technologies (e.g. Hadoop, Spark) and machine learning\nOur Offer\nCompetitive Salary\nBonus scheme on a quarterly basis\nContingent of flexible home office days\n360T Academy for continuous professional development & training\nVarious career growth opportunities\nFrankfurt office located directly in the city center\nRegular social gatherings & company events\nHow to Apply\nIf your background and qualifications meet these specifications, please forward your application including your salary expectation, earliest starting date by clicking the “Apply” button.\nContact\nIrune Del Buey\nPeople & Culture Manager\n\nSend email\n\nGrüneburgweg 16-18\n60322 Frankfurt am Main\n\n#LI-DNI\nAbout us\n\n360T is one of the globally leading trading platforms for Foreign Exchange (FX). As Deutsche Börse Group’s powerhouse for FX, 360T provides a web-based trading technology for over-the-counter (OTC) instruments, integration solutions and related services. Since its inception in 2000, the company has developed and maintained a state-of-the-art multi-bank portal for foreign exchange, crypto assets, cash and money market products. With over 3,000 Buy-Side customers and more than 200 liquidity providers across 80 different countries, 360T is uniquely positioned to connect the global FX and Crypto industry.\n\nHeadquartered in Frankfurt am Main, Germany, 360T maintains subsidiaries in London (360 Trading Networks UK Limited), New York (360 Trading Networks Inc), Singapore (360T Asia Pacific Pte. Ltd.), Mumbai (ThreeSixty Trading Networks (India) Pvt Ltd), Kuala Lumpur (360 Trading Networks Sdn Bhd) and Dubai (360 Trading Networks (DIFC) Limited).','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'360 Treasury Systems','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b5a419992be3d5ba','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2479,NULL,'job','(Senior) Specialist Data Analytics (w/m/d)','Festanstellung','Deutschland',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'deutschlandweit\nVollzeit\nFestanstellung\nDein Arbeitsumfeld\nUnterstütze unser erfahrenes Team bei datengesteuerten Lösungen und Entscheidungsfindungen. Wir bieten unseren Kunden maßgeschneiderte Analysen, fortschrittliche Modelle und Visualisierungen, um ihnen dabei zu helfen, Erkenntnisse aus ihren Daten zu gewinnen.\nDeine Aufgaben\nFührende Mitarbeit in Datenprojekten von der Anforderungsaufnahme über Datenmanagement, Datenanalyse und Visualisierung bis zur Umsetzung\nAnwenden von Methoden aus den Bereichen Data Engineering, Data Science und Machine Learning\nErstellen von Datenvisualisierungen und Dashboards\nSchnittstellentätigkeiten zwischen Fachbereich und IT\nFachberatung zu Datenthemen\nDeine Stärken\nAbgeschlossenes Studium mit sehr gutem Erfolg (Master oder Promotion) in einem MINT-Studiengang, Psychologie oder VWL sowie fünf Jahre relevante Berufserfahrung\nAusgeprägtes analytisches Denkvermögen und hohes Technologieverständnis\nNeugier sowie Bereitschaft zur permanenten Weiterentwicklung und Erarbeitung neuer Themenfelder\nKommunikationsgeschick und Teamgeist\nVerhandlungssichere Deutsch- und sehr gute Englischkenntnisse\nReisebereitschaft (projektabhängig)\nWir bieten\nKollegiales und familiäres Arbeitsumfeld\nAbwechslungsreiche und spannende Tätigkeiten\nAttraktive Vergütung\nFrühzeitige Verantwortung und kurze Entscheidungswege\nFach- oder Führungslaufbahn\nIndividuelle Weiterentwicklung\nFlexible Wohnortwahl in Deutschland\nRegelmäßige Team- und Sportevents\nAusstattung auf dem neuesten Stand der Technik\nDein Kontakt\nDr. Guntram Hainke\nHead of Analytics\nkarriere@consileon.de\n+49 721 619016-70\nÜber uns\nConsileaner sind Teamworker, lernen mit- und voneinander und genießen den Erfolg gemeinsam. Respekt, Fairness, Menschlichkeit und Vertrauen treiben uns dabei an. Mit über 550 Mitarbeiterinnen und Mitarbeitern ist Consileon eine wachstumsstarke Top-Managementberatung für Lösungen mit IT- und KI-Bezug. Wir unterstützen DAX-Konzerne ebenso wie Hidden Champions von der Konzeption bis zur Umsetzung in allen Bereichen der Digitalisierung.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Consileon Applied Business GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1d55b87726e0c488','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2480,NULL,'job','Experte für Künstliche Intelligenz & Digitalisierung (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','Georgsmarienhütte',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Wer wir sind\nMit rund 6.000 Kolleginnen und Kollegen ist die GMH Gruppe das klimafreundlichste Stahlunternehmen Deutschlands. Bis 2039 liefern wir CO2-neutralen Stahl an unsere Kunden, die vor allem aus den Bereichen Mobilität, Energie und Maschinenbau stammen.\nWir setzen auf partnerschaftliche Zusammenarbeit mit flexiblen Strukturen, flachen Hierarchien und einem ausgeprägten Wir-Gefühl.\n\nAls IT-Dienstleister der GMH Gruppe mit 20 mittelständischen Produktionsunternehmen aus der Stahl-, Schmiede- und Gussindustrie, die rund 6.000 Experten beschäftigt, sowie weiteren namhaften Kunden außerhalb der GMH Gruppe bietet die GMH Systems GmbH ein breites Service-Portfolio, wozu Prozessberatung, IT-Lösungen und Betrieb der Infrastruktur gehören.\n\nWas wir vorhaben\nMitarbeit in unserem jungen, engagierten und kreativen Team Digital Lab\nSchwerpunkt: Projekte zum Thema KI (Fokus Machine Learning) und Digitalisierung\nIdentifizierung von digitalen Verbesserungspotenzialen in Geschäftsprozessen mittels KI\nAnalyse und Aufnahme von Kundenanforderungen im KI-Kontext\nUnterstützung im Data Management und Datenqualitätssicherung als Basis für den erfolgreichen KI-Einsatz\nRecherche, Konzeption und Umsetzung von neuen KI-Technologien\nWen wir suchen\nAbgeschlossenes Studium der Informatik / Wirtschaftsinformatik mit Schwerpunkt Machine Learning oder vergleichbare Qualifikation\nExzellente Kenntnisse im Umfeld von KI-Technologien (Fokus Machine Learning)\nKenntnisse im Bereich generativer KI wünschenswert, aber nicht zwingend\nTech Stack: Azure, Python, Git, REST APIs, JSON, etc.\nInteresse an den Produkten & Prozessen der metallverarbeitenden Industrie\nLernbereitschaft und Begeisterung für neue Entwicklungen von Data & AI Technologien\nSoft Skills: Freude an der direkten Zusammenarbeit mit Kunden und im Team, Eigeninitiative und eine strukturierte, zielorientierte Arbeitsweise, sehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\nWas wir bieten\n30 Urlaubstage\nAktives Gesundheitsmanagement\nAus- und Weiterbildung\nFirmenhandy\nFirmenlaptop\nUnfallversicherung\nSport- und Fitnessangebote\nParkplatz\nMobile Arbeit\nMitarbeiterevents\nMitarbeiterprämien\nMitarbeiterrabatte\nKantine\nKinderbetreuung\nInternetnutzung\nHunde geduldet\nFlexible Arbeitszeiten\nGute Verkehrsanbindung\nGewinnbeteiligung\nWir freuen uns, Dich kennenzulernen.\nBewirb Dich online in unserem Bewerberportal.\nMarie Kubitz\nHR Services\nTel: +49 5401 39 - 5128','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'GMH Gruppe SE & Co. KG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=10b2fecbc84229c5','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2481,NULL,'job','Ausbildung zum Fachinformatiker der Fachrichtung Anwendungsentwicklung (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','Unna',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Unna | Verwaltung\nVollzeit\nAusbildung/Trainee\nDein Profil\nDu begeisterst Dich für neue IT-Technologien und möchtest deswegen gerne im Bereich der Softwareentwicklung arbeiten? Denn dafür brauchen wir Dich! Was wir gut finden würden?\n\nDu hast erste Erfahrungen z.B. durch die Erstellung einer Website oder mit OpenSource Projekten gesammelt\nDu besitzt gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\nDu bringst Begeisterung für IT-Systeme, Digitalisierung und Software-Entwicklung mit\nDu interessierst Dich für logische Zusammenhänge und Technologien\nDu bringst Qualitätsbewusstsein, Genauigkeit und eine große Portion Motivation mit\nDeine Aufgaben\nWas wirst Du bei uns lernen? Du arbeitest mit den anderen aus Deinem Team an einem der besten Produkte zur Digitalisierung von Geschäfts- und Dokumentenprozessen und erhältst ein besonderes Knowhow durch verschiedene Bereiche:\n\nMit- und Weiterentwicklung der von uns programmierten Software zur Digitalisierung von Prozessen\nForschung in den Bereichen der künstlichen Intelligenz, Machine Learning & Computer Vision\nKonzeption, Entwicklung und Realisierung von eigenen Softwareprojekten\nAgile Software-Entwicklung\nFehlererkennung und -behebung mithilfe von Experten-, und Diagnosesystemen\nPräsentation Deiner entwickelten Anwendungen\nWarum wir?\nWir setzen auf die gemeinsame, dynamische Weiterentwicklung unserer innovativen Produkte und glauben an Lösungen und Chancen, nicht an Probleme. Wir sind überzeugt, dass wir uns mit den geballten Kräften unseres Teams, mit Transparenz und viel Spaß an der Arbeit gegenseitig motivieren, herausfordern und täglich zu neuen Höchstleistungen pushen. Werde Teil unseres großartigen Teams, bewirb Dich auf unserer Website und starte im Herbst 2026 Deine Ausbildung bei uns!\nÜber uns\nDie M.S.E. GmbH perfektioniert die Kombination aus exzellent auf den Kunden abgestimmten Hardware-Lösungen mit intelligenter, cloudbasierter Software-Technologie. Unser Ziel ist es, betriebliche Prozesse zu optimieren, maximal zu vereinfachen und zu automatisieren. Kurz gesagt – Wir machen den Menschen das Leben leichter!','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'MSE GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ea6299188b625a60','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2482,NULL,'job','Senior Database Administrator (m/f/d)','Vollzeit','Köln',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We are seeking a dedicated Senior Database Administrator to support the design, implementation, and ongoing management of database environments. In this role, you will be responsible for ensuring the performance, scalability, and reliability of critical systems through effective administration, monitoring, and optimization. You will collaborate closely with application development teams, contribute to key operational processes, and support deployments across on-premises and cloud environments. This position requires a proactive approach to problem-solving, a strong focus on automation and efficiency, and a commitment to maintaining high standards in security, compliance, and service delivery.\nSupport the design and implementation of relational and NoSQL databases.\nPerform core database administration tasks, including upgrades, patching, tuning, backups, troubleshooting, and support.\nCollaborate with application development teams to test, optimize, and troubleshoot database-driven applications.\nContribute to daily operational activities impacting key IT processes and systems.\nDevelop scripts and utilities to automate repetitive database tasks (non-development role).\n\nMonitor database environments (production, test, development) to ensure performance, scalability, and availability.\n\nSupport deployment of Verisk products across on-premises and cloud environments.\nAssist with enterprise security, auditing, and compliance initiatives.\nMentor junior DBAs on best practices and emerging trends.\nMaintain professional communication with all collaborations.\nParticipate in on-call rotation and occasional off-hours support to meet SLAs.\nStay current with industry trends through continuous learning and professional development.\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or equivalent experience.\n5+ years of database administration experience across multiple DBMS platforms.\nStrong experience with cloud databases, particularly AWS RDS, and 24/7 high-availability environments.\nHands-on expertise with databases such as PostgreSQL, MongoDB , MySQL, SQL Server, Oracle, DynamoDB, or Elastic.\nProven ability to troubleshoot database issues (performance, integrity, replication, connectivity, security, etc.).\nSolid knowledge of backup, recovery, performance tuning, and overall database health management.\nExperience implementing high availability solutions (clustering, replication).\nProficiency with enterprise database tools and Unix/Linux environments (scripting is a plus).\nStrong communication, mentoring, and problem-solving skills.\nFluent English (written and spoken).\n\n#LI-AA1\n\n#LI-Remote\nOur People, Our Culture\n\nFor more than 50 years, Verisk has helped property and casualty insurers make smarter decisions about risk through AI-powered risk modeling, advanced analytics, and technology solutions spanning the entire policy lifecycle. We are a leading strategic data, analytics, and technology partner to the global insurance industry, guided by core values of learning, caring, and results while maintaining the highest ethical standards as stewards of the industry\'s most comprehensive datasets. Learn more about Verisk and what we are doing within the insurance industry.\n\nFor the eighth consecutive year, Verisk is proudly recognized as a Great Place to Work® for outstanding workplace culture in the US, the fourth consecutive year in the UK, Spain, and India, and the second consecutive year in Poland. In addition, we’ve been recognized by The Wall Street Journal as one of the Best-Managed Companies and by Forbes as a World’s Best Employer, testaments to the value we place on workplace culture.\n\nOur Culture : Explore our inclusive, people-first culture that fosters innovation, collaboration, and belonging.\n\nAwards & Recognition : See why Verisk is consistently recognized as a Great Place to Work™ around the world.\n\nOur Businesses : Learn about the diverse industries we serve — from insurance and energy to financial services and beyond.\n\nLife at Verisk : Discover what it’s like to work at Verisk through employee stories, team highlights, and culture moments.\n\nCareers at Verisk : Join a global team of problem-solvers and innovators doing meaningful work that’s shaping the future of industries. Whether you\'re just starting out or looking to take your career to the next level, Verisk offers growth, purpose, and a people-first culture\n\nLet’s build something meaningful together!\n\nVerisk Analytics is an equal opportunity employer.\n\nAll members of the Verisk Analytics family of companies are equal opportunity employers. We consider all qualified applicants for employment without regard to race, religion, color, national origin, citizenship, sex, gender identity and/or expression, sexual orientation, veteran\'s status, age or disability. Verisk’s minimum hiring age is 18 except in countries with a higher age limit subject to applicable law.\n\nhttps://www.verisk.com/company/careers/\n\nUnsolicited resumes sent to Verisk, including unsolicited resumes sent to a Verisk business mailing address, fax machine, or email address, or directly to Verisk employees, will be considered Verisk property. Verisk will NOT pay a fee for any placement resulting from the receipt of an unsolicited resume.\n\nVerisk Employee Privacy Notice','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Ignite Insurance Systems','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1b14b0a778b0fdd8','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2483,NULL,'job','Consultant (w/m/d) Data Analytics – Financial Services','Festanstellung','Deutschland',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'deutschlandweit\nVoll- oder Teilzeit\nFestanstellung\nDein Arbeitsumfeld\nConsileon Frankfurt GmbH ist Teil der Consileon-Gruppe und auf die Beratung von Unternehmen aus der Finanzbranche spezialisiert. Als Beratungs-Boutique setzen wir nicht auf einen standardisierten Werkzeugkasten, sondern finden individuelle, unternehmerische Lösungen für unsere Kunden.\nDeine Aufgaben\nindividuelle Kundenberatung im Bereich Data Analytics – von der Strategie bis zur Umsetzung\nEntwicklung innovativer Lösungen im Team mit Personal des Klienten sowie Fachberatung zu Datenthemen\nErstellen von Datenvisualisierungen und Dashboards sowie Anwenden von Methoden aus den Bereichen Data Engineering, Data Science und Machine Learning\nAusbau unseres intellektuellen Kapitals im Bereich Data Analytics\nDeine Stärken\nHochschulabschluss mit mindestens guten Noten vorzugsweise in\n(Wirtschafts-)Informatik, (Wirtschafts-)Ingenieurwesen, (Wirtschafts-)Mathematik, Physik, Data Science, Wirtschaftswissenschaften oder einem vergleichbaren Studienfach\nArbeitspraxis im Bereich Data Analytics, idealerweise in der Beratungs- oder Finanzbranche, etwa einer Bank, Versicherung oder im Asset Management\nFundierte Kenntnisse in der Datenanalyse,-modellierung und – visualiserung (z.B. Microsoft Power BI) und in Programmiersprachen (z.B. Python)\nverhandlungssicheres Deutsch und Englisch\nWir bieten\nAttraktive Vergütung bei ausgewogenen Arbeitszeiten\nFlexibles Arbeiten, je nach Projekt im Homeoffice, vor Ort beim Kunden oder an einem unserer Standorte (Frankfurt, Düsseldorf, München)\nIndividuelle Entwicklung durch vielfältige Weiterbildungsangebote und Karrierepfade nach Deinen Stärken\nLangfristige Perspektive und hohe Freiheitsgrade: Stay & Grow statt Up or Out\nWertschätzende Kultur mit einem engagierten Team und fantastischen Events\nDein Kontakt\nWieland Voss\nPrincipal\nkarriere@consileon.de\n+49 69 678687-00\nÜber uns\nConsileaner sind Teamworker, lernen mit- und voneinander und genießen den Erfolg gemeinsam. Respekt, Fairness, Menschlichkeit und Vertrauen treiben uns dabei an. Mit über 550 Mitarbeiterinnen und Mitarbeitern ist Consileon eine wachstumsstarke Top-Managementberatung für Lösungen mit IT- und KI-Bezug. Wir unterstützen DAX-Konzerne ebenso wie Hidden Champions von der Konzeption bis zur Umsetzung in allen Bereichen der Digitalisierung.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Consileon Applied Business GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6deef29535e01cf4','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2484,NULL,'job','IT-Expertin / IT-Experte (w/m/d) im Geschäftsbereich Daten- und IT-Management im IAB','Befristeter Vertrag','Nürnberg',NULL,'',5500.00,'Ab 5.500 € pro Monat','Arbeitsumfeld\n\nDas Institut für Arbeitsmarkt- und Berufsforschung (IAB) ist eine besondere Dienststelle der Bundesagentur für Arbeit. Es zählt zu den führenden Einrichtungen der Arbeitsmarktforschung in Europa und berät Politik und Fachöffentlichkeit auf Basis neuester wissenschaftlicher Erkenntnisse. Unser Leitbild dient uns dabei als Kompass – erfahren Sie mehr auf www.iab.de.\n\nDie Stelle ist innerhalb des Geschäftsbereichs Daten- und IT-Management (DIM) verortet. Hier arbeiten Sie als IT-Expert/-in an datenbasierten Aufgaben mit Einsatz von Methoden der Künstlichen Intelligenz.\nAufgaben und Tätigkeiten\n\nPlanung, Umsetzung, Steuerung und Analyse von komplexen Konzepten, Modellen bzw. Methoden bei der Erschließung von neuartigem, unstrukturiertem Datenmaterial für die Forschung\nkomplexe Erweiterung, Validierung und Dokumentation methodischer Vorgehensweisen im Bereich Natural Language Processing und KI\nWeiterentwicklung von Auswerteverfahren im Bereich Analytics und Machine Learning inklusive der regelmäßigen Aktualisierung des für die Forschung neu erschlossenen Datenmaterials\nAnalyse und Bewertung von Fragestellungen zu innovativen Themenkomplexen im Tätigkeitsfeld\nBeratung der relevanten Anspruchsgruppen bei bereichsspezifischen IT-Projekten\nVoraussetzungen\n\nHochschulabschluss oder vergleichbare Qualifikation\nBevorzugte Fachrichtungen: Informatik / Mathematik oder Sozial- / Wirtschaftswissenschaften mit empirischer Ausrichtung\nLangjährige einschlägige Berufserfahrung oder vergleichbares Profil\nweitreichende Erfahrungen beim Einsatz von Modellen insbesondere Transformer-Modellen wie z.B. BERT, Analyseverfahren und statistischen Methoden im Bereich Analytics und Machine Learning\nErfahrung mit Datenbanken und -modellierung\ngute Kenntnisse des Datenschutzes\nFundierte Kenntnisse relevanter IT-Fachanwendungen: Programmierung mit Sprachen wie Python oder R\nFundierte Kenntnisse relevanter Forschungsmethoden sowie relevanter fachspezifischer Instrumente und Methoden)\nVertiefte Kenntnisse statistischer Methoden, Modelle und Analyseverfahren\nFundierte Kenntnisse des Projektmanagements\nFundierte Kenntnisse aufgabenspezifischer Fachgebiete\nFundierte Kenntnisse von Präsentations- und Moderationstechniken\nEnglisch (Kenntnisniveau B2 gem. GeR)\n\nPerfect Match? Muss nicht sein! Wir suchen motivierte Talente, die sich weiterentwickeln wollen. Sie können sich gern bewerben, auch wenn Sie nicht alle Kriterien erfüllen. Für uns zählen Ihre Qualifikation und Stärken.\nWir bieten\n\nBei der Stelle handelt es sich um eine Vollzeitstelle (100% AZ), befristet bis 31.12.2027.\nEs erwartet Sie eine vielfältige und interessante Tätigkeit in einem kompetenten und motivierten Team.\n\nIhre Bezahlung entspricht mindestens der Tätigkeitsebene I Stufe 1 nach dem Tarifvertrag der Bundesagentur für Arbeit (derzeit rund 5.500 € brutto in Vollzeit). Wenn Sie über einschlägige Berufserfahrung verfügen, können Sie ggf. auch mit einem Gehalt nach einer höheren Stufe einsteigen. Neben dem monatlichen Festgehalt ist die Zahlung weiterer Gehaltskomponenten möglich, z.B. Jahressonderzahlung. Darüber hinaus bieten wir ab einer bestimmten Beschäftigungsdauer eine zusätzliche betriebliche Altersvorsorge über die Versorgungsanstalt des Bundes und der Länder (VBL) und die Möglichkeit der Entgeltumwandlung.\n\nDas IAB ist seit 2009 durchgehend für seine strategisch angelegte familien- und lebensphasenbewusste Personalpolitik mit dem Zertifikat Audit „berufundfamilie“ ausgezeichnet.\nWir verfolgen eine familienbewusste Personalpolitik mit verschiedenen Angeboten zur Förderung der Vereinbarkeit von Beruf und Familie / Privatleben, u.a. flexible Arbeitszeit oder Freizeitausgleich bei Mehrarbeit. Zudem bietet der Familienservice der BA zahlreiche Unterstützungsmöglichkeiten an.\nEin Ansatz in Teilzeit ist möglich, sofern zwingende dienstliche Belange nicht entgegenstehen. Ein Teil der Arbeitszeit kann in Mobilarbeit erfolgen.\n\nWeitere Benefits:\n- Profitieren Sie von einer offenen und respektvollen Kommunikationskultur, die von Teamgeist und gegenseitiger Unterstützung geprägt ist.\n- Wir ermutigen unsere Mitarbeitenden, kreativ zu denken und neue Ideen einzubringen, um die Zukunft unseres Instituts aktiv mitzugestalten.\n- Wir bieten Weiterbildungs- und Aufstiegsmöglichkeiten in jeder Lebensphase und unterstützen Ihre berufliche Weiterentwicklung durch ein individuelles, umfangreiches Weiterbildungsangebot.\n- Wir garantieren einen sicheren Arbeitsplatz mit einem breiten Aufgabenspektrum von unterschiedlichen Tätigkeiten.\n- Wir legen großen Wert auf eine gesunde Work-Life-Balance und unterstützen Sie dabei, Ihre Arbeit erfolgreich zu gestalten.\n- Wir stellen verschiedene Maßnahmen zur Gesundheitsförderung bereit, wie z.B. ergonomische Arbeitsplatzgestaltungen, betriebliches Gesundheitsmanagement und Sportangebote.\n\nWir begrüßen alle Bewerbungen – unabhängig von Geschlecht, Nationalität, ethnischer und sozialer Herkunft, Religion, Weltanschauung, Behinderung, Alter sowie sexueller Orientierung und Identität.\n\nDas IAB setzt sich für die Chancengleichheit von Männern und Frauen ein und fordert daher Frauen auf, sich zu bewerben.\n\nBewerbungen von schwerbehinderten und diesen gleichgestellten Menschen sind ausdrücklich erwünscht. Wir bieten eine barrierearme Arbeitsumgebung, in der Sie Ihre Kompetenzen optimal nutzen können. Interessierte mit Schwerbehinderung oder Gleichstellung können sich gerne im Vorfeld an die Vertrauensperson für schwerbehinderte Menschen, Frau Doreen Makrinius-Hahn wenden (IAB.Schwerbehindertenvertretung@iab.de).\n\nIhre Ansprechpersonen:\nAli Athmani, Bereich DIM, Tel.: +49 911/179-4355, ali.athmani@iab.de\nBettina Müller, Bereich Personal, Tel.: +49 911/179-1189, bewerbungen@iab.de\n\nInteressiert?\nDann bewerben Sie sich online über unseren Bewerbungsassistenten. Klicken Sie dazu auf „Bewerben“ und registrieren Sie sich.\nWir freuen uns auf Ihre Bewerbung!','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Bundesagentur für Arbeit (BA)','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9a088f03d5cc0c57','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2485,NULL,'job','AI Research Manager | Translation Quality','Vollzeit','Köln',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Meet DeepL\n\nDeepL is a global AI product and research company focused on building secure, intelligent solutions to complex business problems. Over 200,000 business customers and millions of individuals across 228 global markets today trust DeepL\'s Language AI platform for human-like translation, improved writing and real-time voice translation.\nFounded in 2017 by CEO Jaroslaw “Jarek” Kutylowski, DeepL now has over 1,000 passionate employees and is supported by world-renowned investors including Benchmark, IVP, and Index Ventures.\n\nOur goal is to become the global leader in trusted, intelligent AI technology, building products that drive better communication, foster connections, and create a meaningful impact. To achieve this, we need talented people like you to join our journey. If you’re ready to shape the future of AI and grow your career in a fast-moving, purpose-driven environment, DeepL is your next destination.\n\nWhat sets us apart\n\nWhat sets us apart is our blend of cutting-edge AI technology, meaningful work, and a culture where people truly thrive. We’re a team of innovators, researchers, and creators driven by a shared purpose to unlock human potential by making work simpler, smarter, and more connected.\n\nWhen we share what it’s like to work at DeepL, the reactions are overwhelmingly positive. This might be because of our technology that helps millions of people and businesses communicate and work better every day, or because of the trust, curiosity, and care that shape our culture.\n\nWhat we know for sure is this: being part of DeepL means joining a team dedicated to innovation, growth, and well-being. Discover more about life at DeepL onLinkedIn,Instagram, and our Blog.\n\nMeet the team behind this journey\n\nYou will lead the Translation Quality Research team, focusing entirely on advancing and defending our core translation models. We sit at the intersection of cutting-edge research and product delivery, transforming promising ideas into reliable, scalable features customers use every day. Our emphasis is on measurable quality and real-world production impact.\n\nThis team’s work directly drives our commercial success and B2B strategy. You will be responsible for keeping DeepL’s baseline translation quality ahead of massive, top-tier general-purpose models in the market , driving strategic enterprise initiatives, and ensuring we consistently deliver the highest standard of translation quality to our B2B customers.\n\nYour responsibilities\n\nAs a Research Manager at DeepL, you will own both people leadership and technical direction for a team of research scientists , currently consisting of highly skilled ICs). While this is not a hands-on coding role , you will be deeply involved in technical discussions to unblock the team and validate approaches.\n\nYou will:\n\nDrive the achievement and rigorous evaluation of DeepL\'s baseline translation quality to ensure market dominance.\n\nShape and prioritize the research agenda, balancing clear product outcomes with bold, longer-term bets.\n\nDefine and communicate your team\'s strategic goals, roadmap, and success metrics in collaboration with key stakeholders across tech, product, sales enablement, and customer success.\n\nOwn the \"estimation\" aspect of our product pipeline, building models that determine when a translation requires human review.\n\nInspire, develop, recruit, and motivate a high-performing team ; build strong 1:1 relationships, set development plans, and foster a candid, non-retaliatory feedback culture.\n\nAct autonomously to make decisions, push for results, and define the team\'s path forward without waiting for product or customers to guide the way.\n\nQualities we look for\n\nYou hold a (preferable PhD) degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Physics, or a comparable subject , or possess a strong Machine Learning background with a PhD focused on a heavy research topic.\n\nYou have a strong research background—ideally with specific experience in Language Research—enabling you to deeply understand complex tech challenges, participate in technical discussions, and grasp the team\'s constraints.\n\nYou have hands-on experience in the following areas:\n\nSoftware development, ideally in the context of data science, ML engineering, systems engineering, or distributed services.\n\nTechnical and people leadership.\n\nDeep Learning.\n\nYou have a proven track record of successfully leading Research teams, ideally in a global, high-growth scale-up, and research-intensive environment. (Note: We are also highly open to newer leaders with just a few years of management experience, provided you are deeply motivated by people leadership).\n\nYou have a solution-oriented mindset and are able to navigate through ambiguity and change effectively.\n\nYou have excellent communication skills and the ability to closely collaborate with other teams across the organization.\n\nHigh level of English proficiency (knowledge of German and other languages is an advantage).\n\nWhat we offer\n\nDiverse and internationally distributed team: joining our team means becoming part of a large, global community with people of more than 90 nationalities. We\'re more than just colleagues; we\'re a group of professionals with a shared mission to connect diverse cultures. Our global presence is growing–we\'ve doubled in size nearly every year, with our employees based in the UK, Germany, the Netherlands, Poland, the US, and Japan, and we continue to expand our network.\n\nOpen communication, regular feedback: as a language-focused company, we value the importance of clear, honest communication. We value smooth collaboration, direct and actionable feedback, and believe that leading with empathy and growth mindset makes us better together.\n\nHybrid work, flexible hours: we offer a hybrid work schedule, with team members coming into the office twice a week. This allows you to engage directly with your team and experience the unique energy of our workspace, while still enjoying the flexibility and comfort of working from home. With flexible working hours and trust in your productivity, we are in sync with your team’s general locations and time zones to foster effective and seamless collaboration.\n\nVirtual Shares - An ownership mindset in every role. We believe everyone should share in our success, and that’s why every employee receives Virtual Shares, linking your contribution directly to DeepL’s growth and rewarding you with a stake in our future.\n\nRegular in-person team events: we bond over vibrant events that are as unique as our team, from local team and business unit gatherings, to new-joiner onboardings, to company-wide events that bring us all together–literally.\n\nMonthly full-day hacking sessions: every month, we have Hack Fridays, where you can spend your time diving into a project you\'re passionate about and get the opportunity to work with other teams–we value your initiatives, impact, and creativity.\n\n30 days of annual leave: we value your peace of mind. With 30 days off (excluding public holidays) and access to mental health resources, we make sure you\'re as strong mentally as you are professionally.\n\nCompetitive benefits: just as our team spans the globe, so does our benefits package. We\'ve crafted it to reflect the diversity of our team and tailored it to align with your unique location, to ensure you feel supported every step of the way.\n\nIf this role and our mission resonate with you, but you\'re hesitant because you don\'t check all the boxes, don\'t let that hold you back. At DeepL, it\'s all about the value you bring and the growth we can foster together. Go ahead, apply—let\'s discover your potential together. We can\'t wait to meet you!\n\nWe are an equal opportunity employer\n\nYou are welcome at DeepL for who you are - we appreciate authenticity here. Our product is for everyone, and so is our workplace. The more voices we have represented and amplified in our business, the more we will all succeed, contribute, and think forward! So bring us your personal experience, your perspectives, and your background. It’s in our diversity that we will find the power to break down language barriers in the world.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'DeepL','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=7b9da39007462f4f','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2486,NULL,'job','Machine Learning Engineer (m/w/d)','Festanstellung','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Über CIB\n\nWir sind Experten für Digitalisierung und Automatisierung von Prozessen mit künstlicher Intelligenz. Unser Ziel ist es, Unternehmen und Verwaltungen von lästigen Alltagsaufgaben im Dokumentenmanagement zu befreien. Dafür entwickeln wir innovative Apps und investieren in die Forschung und Entwicklung von KI.\n\nBewirb dich noch heute und werde Teil eines der führenden Unternehmen im Bereich Digitalisierung und Dokumentenmanagement mit über 35 Jahren Erfahrung. Wir freuen uns auf dich!\n\nUnser Angebot\nWorkation in München, Valencia, Las Palmas de Gran Canaria oder Faro\nUnbefristeter Arbeitsvertrag\nFlexible Arbeitszeiten mit Kernzeit\nArbeite im Homeoffice oder in einem unserer modernen Büros\nAttraktive Sozialleistungen & individuelle Incentives\nEin starkes Team mit flachen Hierarchien und echter Zusammenarbeit\nVielfältige Schulungen zur Förderung deiner fachlichen Entwicklung\nSpannende Lernchancen – z. B. durch Mitwirkung an staatlich geförderten Forschungsprojekten\nInteressante und abwechslungsreiche Aufgaben in einem innovativen Softwareunternehmen\nArbeit mit modernen Technologien und agilen Methoden\nFreiräume zur Mitgestaltung von Prozessen und Qualitätssicherungsstrategie\nDeine Aufgaben\nEntwicklung, Implementierung und Optimierung von Machine-Learning-Modellen und Algorithmen\nIntegration von ML-Modellen in produktive Systeme und Anwendungen\nAufbau und Skalierung von ML-Pipelines (Training, Deployment, Monitoring)\nAnalyse und Aufbereitung großer Datenmengen zur Modellverbesserung\nNutzung moderner Frameworks wie TensorFlow, PyTorch oder vergleichbarer Technologien\nEntwicklung und Durchführung von Modell-Evaluationen sowie Monitoring im Produktivbetrieb\nSicherstellung von Performance, Skalierbarkeit und Wartbarkeit der Lösungen\nDein Profil\nAnpack-Mentalität: Du übernimmst Ownership, treibst Themen eigenständig voran.\nDiskussions- & Kommunikationsstärke: Du bringst Ideen ein, forderst Annahmen heraus und arbeitest konstruktiv im Team.\nFreude am Neuen: Du hast Spaß, in einer schnell veränderten Technologielandschaft auf dem Laufenden zu bleiben und ständig dazuzulernen.\nAbgeschlossenes Studium in Informatik, Data Science, Mathematik oder vergleichbarer Fachrichtung\nErfahrung als Machine Learning Engineer oder in einer ähnlichen Rolle\nSehr gute Kenntnisse in Python sowie im Umgang mit ML-Frameworks (z. B. TensorFlow, PyTorch)\nErfahrung mit Deployment und Betrieb von ML-Systemen (APIs, Monitoring, CI/CD)\nKenntnisse in Datenverarbeitung, Feature Engineering und Modelloptimierung\nIdealerweise Erfahrung mit Cloud-Technologien (z. B. AWS, Kubernetes)\nNice-to-have\nErfahrung mit Suchtechnologien oder Vektor-Datenbanken (z. B. Elasticsearch, OpenSearch, Milvus)\nKenntnisse im Bereich Large Language Models (LLMs), RAG und Prompt Engineering\nErfahrung mit MLOps und automatisierten Trainingspipelines\n\nRichte dich bei Fragen an\nbewerbung@cib.de\n\nSende uns bitte folgende Unterlagen:\n Lebenslauf auf Deutsch oder Englisch\n Anschreiben: Stell dich vor!\n Abschlusszeugnisse, Eintrittstermin\n Was sonst noch relevant sein könnte!','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'CIB SOFTWARE GMBH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=0fd921982d172bde','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2487,NULL,'job','AI Software Developer (m/w/d)','Festanstellung','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Über CIB\n\nWir sind Experten für Digitalisierung und Automatisierung von Prozessen mit künstlicher Intelligenz. Unser Ziel ist es, Unternehmen und Verwaltungen von lästigen Alltagsaufgaben im Dokumentenmanagement zu befreien. Dafür entwickeln wir innovative Apps und investieren in die Forschung und Entwicklung von KI.\n\nBewirb dich noch heute und werde Teil eines der führenden Unternehmen im Bereich Digitalisierung und Dokumentenmanagement mit über 35 Jahren Erfahrung. Wir freuen uns auf dich!\n\nUnser Angebot\nWorkation in München, Valencia, Las Palmas de Gran Canaria oder Faro\nUnbefristeter Arbeitsvertrag\nFlexible Arbeitszeiten mit Kernzeit\nArbeite im Homeoffice oder in einem unserer modernen Büros\nAttraktive Sozialleistungen & individuelle Incentives\nEin starkes Team mit flachen Hierarchien und echter Zusammenarbeit\nVielfältige Schulungen zur Förderung deiner fachlichen Entwicklung\nSpannende Lernchancen – z. B. durch Mitwirkung an staatlich geförderten Forschungsprojekten\nInteressante und abwechslungsreiche Aufgaben in einem innovativen Softwareunternehmen\nArbeit mit modernen Technologien und agilen Methoden\nFreiräume zur Mitgestaltung von Prozessen und Qualitätssicherungsstrategie\nDeine Aufgaben\nEntwicklung von Softwareanwendungen mit integrierten KI-Funktionalitäten (z. B. ML-Modelle, LLMs, APIs)\nIntegration von KI-Systemen in bestehende IT-Infrastrukturen und Produkte\nEntwicklung und Orchestrierung von KI-gestützten Workflows (z. B. mit LLMs, APIs oder Services)\nEntwurf und Implementierung von Schnittstellen (APIs, Services) zur Anbindung interner und externer Systeme\nEntwicklung skalierbarer Backend-Komponenten und Microservices\nSicherstellung von Performance, Skalierbarkeit und Stabilität der Anwendungen (Testing, Monitoring)\nWeiterentwicklung bestehender Systeme sowie Integration neuer Technologien\nDein Profil\nAnpack-Mentalität: Du übernimmst Ownership, treibst Themen eigenständig voran.\nDiskussions- & Kommunikationsstärke: Du bringst Ideen ein, forderst Annahmen heraus und arbeitest konstruktiv im Team.\nFreude am Neuen: Du hast Spaß, in einer schnell veränderten Technologielandschaft auf dem Laufenden zu bleiben und ständig dazuzulernen.\nAbgeschlossenes Studium in Informatik, Software Engineering oder vergleichbarer Fachrichtung\nErfahrung in der Softwareentwicklung (z. B. mit Java, Python oder vergleichbaren Technologien)\nErfahrung mit der Entwicklung und Integration von APIs und Webservices\nErfahrung mit der Integration von LLM APIs (z. B. OpenAI, Azure OpenAI)\nVerständnis von Softwarearchitektur, Design Patterns und skalierbaren Systemen\nErfahrung im Umgang mit Daten (z. B. Datenbanken, Datenverarbeitung)\nKenntnisse in Testing, Debugging und Performanceoptimierung\nNice-to-have\nErfahrung mit Machine Learning, KI-Frameworks oder LLMs\nKenntnisse in Cloud-Technologien (z. B. AWS, Docker, Kubernetes)\nErfahrung mit MLOps oder der Integration von ML-Modellen in produktive Systeme\nErfahrung mit Vektor-Datenbanken oder Suchtechnologien\n\nRichte dich bei Fragen an\nbewerbung@cib.de\n\nSende uns bitte folgende Unterlagen:\n Lebenslauf auf Deutsch oder Englisch\n Anschreiben: Stell dich vor!\n Abschlusszeugnisse, Eintrittstermin\n Was sonst noch relevant sein könnte!','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'CIB SOFTWARE GMBH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d57f7e785716e9af','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2488,NULL,'job','Wissenschaftliche/r Mitarbeiter/in (m/w/d) - Maschinelles Lernen','Teilzeit','18055 Rostock',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Die Universität Rostock bietet Ihnen eine vielfältige, abwechslungsreiche und anspruchsvolle Tätigkeit in einer traditionsbewussten, aber dennoch innovativen, modernen und familienfreundlichen Hochschule in einer lebendigen Stadt am Meer.\n\nAn der Fakultät für Informatik und Elektrotechnik, Institut für Visual and Analytic Computing, Lehrstuhl für Marine Data Science besetzen wir vorbehaltlich haushaltsrechtlicher Regelungen zum 01.07.2026 befristet bis 30.06.2029 die folgende Stelle:\n\nWissenschaftliche/r Mitarbeiter/in (m/w/d) - Maschinelles Lernen\n\nStartdatum zum 01.07.2026\n\nArbeitszeit Vollzeit mit 40 Stunden\n\nEntgelt Entgeltgruppe 13 TV-L\n\nStandort Rostock\n\nAusschreibungsnummer W 22/2026\n\nBefristung befristet bis 30.06.2029, Weiterführung der Beschäftigung wird angestrebt\n\nBewerbungsfrist 08.05.2026\n\nFÜR WEITERE AUSKÜNFTE STEHEN WIR IHNEN ZUR VERFÜGUNG:\n\nPersonalservice:\nFranziska Schreier\nTel.-Nr.: 0381/498-1320\nE-Mail:\n\nFachbereich:\nProf. Dr.-Ing. Stefan Lüdtke\nTel.-Nr.: 0381/498-7432\nE-Mail:\n\nDAS SIND IHRE AUFGABEN:\nForschen im Bereich Deep Learning für maritime Anwendungen, insbesondere Unterwasser-Sensorik mit dem Ziel der wissenschaftlichen Qualifizierung (Habilitation)\nEntwickeln von Deep Learning-Modellen für akustische Sensorik, z.B. Sonar\nPublizieren wissenschaftlicher Artikel in Machine Learning-Konferenzen und -Journals\nwissenschaftliche, forschungsbasierte Lehre im Umfang von 2 SWS in Form von Übungen, Seminaren und Praktika auf den Themengebieten \"Künstliche Intelligenz\" und \" Machine Learning\"\nBetreuen von Bachelor- und Masterstudierenden\nOrganisieren und Durchführen von wissenschaftlichen Veranstaltungen\nAkquise von Drittmittelprojekten\nDAMIT PASSEN SIE ZU UNS:\nabgeschlossenes wissenschaftliches Hochschulstudium (Diplom, Master oder vergleichbarer Abschluss) in Informatik, Mathematik, Physik, Elektrotechnik, Ingenieurwissenschaften oder vergleichbaren Fachrichtungen\nabgeschlossene Promotion im Bereich Künstliche Intelligenz, Bildverarbeitung oder vergleichbarer Richtung mit Bewertung von mindestens magna cum laude\nsehr gute Kenntnisse in der Entwicklung und Anwendung von Deep Learning-Methoden und Programmierfähigkeiten, vorzugsweise Python\nErfahrung in der Entwicklung von Deep Learning-Methoden für Daten aus akustischen Verfahren, insbesondere Computer Vision-Methoden\nErfahrung in der Erstellung wissenschaftlicher Publikationen\nBereitschaft, ernsthaft und engagiert an einem Vorhaben der eigenen wissenschaftlichen Qualifizierung zu arbeiten\nwünschenswert sind Erfahrungen in der Durchführung von Lehrveranstaltungen in den Themengebieten Künstliche Intelligenz und Maschinelles Lernen\nsichere Kenntnisse der englischen und deutschen Sprache in Wort und Schrift\nKommunikationsfähigkeiten für die Arbeit in interdisziplinären Teams\nWIR ALS ARBEITGEBER:\n\nChancengleichheit ist uns wichtig. Bewerbungen geeigneter schwerbehinderter oder gleichgestellter Menschen sind uns willkommen. Wir streben eine Erhöhung des Anteils von Frauen in Forschung und Lehre an und bestärken deshalb einschlägig qualifizierte Frauen sich zu bewerben. Bewerbungen von Menschen anderer Nationalitäten oder mit Migrationshintergrund begrüßen wir.\n\nWIR BIETEN IHNEN:\nWEITERE HINWEISE:\n\nDie tarifliche Erfahrungsstufe legen wir unter Berücksichtigung Ihrer bisherigen Berufserfahrung individuell fest.\n\nSofern Sie diese Stelle in Teilzeit ausüben möchten, ist dies unter Berücksichtigung der dienstlichen Anforderungen grundsätzlich möglich.\n\nDie Befristung des Arbeitsverhältnisses richtet sich nach § 2 (1) Wissenschaftszeitvertragsgesetz.\n\nWir freuen uns auf Ihre Bewerbung (Anschreiben, Lebenslauf, Abschlusszeugnis mit Angabe der Abschlussnote) bis spätestens 08.05.2026. Wir können nur Bewerbungen berücksichtigen, die über unsere Homepage eingehen. Dazu senden Sie uns bitte Ihre Unterlagen über den Button „Online-Bewerbung“ am Ende eines Stellenangebots zu. E-Mail-Bewerbungen können wir leider nicht akzeptieren.\n\nBewerbungsunterlagen, die unvollständig sind, können im weiteren Verlauf des Auswahlverfahrens unberücksichtigt bleiben.\n\nBewerbungs- und Fahrkosten können wir leider nicht übernehmen.\n\nWerden Sie Teil des Teams\n\nWir freuen uns auf Ihre Bewerbung!\n\nKontakt\n\nUniversität Rostock\n18051 Rostock\nTel.: +49 381 498 - 0\n\nSitze des Rektorats:\nUniversitätsplatz 1\n18055 Rostock\n\nService\nZertifikate\n\nFamilienfreundliche Hochschule HRK-Audit\n\nSoziale Medien','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Universität Rostock','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9d240df4f31db50a','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2489,NULL,'job','Werkstudent (m/w/d) – Machine Learning Automated Driving','Studentenjob','München',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'STANDORT\nMunich\nGESELLSCHAFT\nARRK Engineering GmbH\nVERTRAGSART\nTeilzeit\nArbeitsform\nHybride\nWAS DICH ERWARTET\n\nIm Bereich Automatisiertes Fahren erwartet Sie eine innovative und zukunftsorientierte Arbeitsumgebung, in der Sie aktiv an der Entwicklung und Verbesserung modernster autonomer Fahrsysteme mitwirken. Sie werden Teil eines dynamischen Teams von Experten, das eng zusammenarbeitet, um fortschrittliche Machine-Learning-Modelle zu entwickeln und zu implementieren.\n\nDEINE AUFGABEN\n\nDEIN PROFIL\nUnterstützung bei der Entwicklung und Implementierung von Machine-Learning-Modellen zur Verbesserung von autonomen Fahrsystemen\nAnalyse von Datensätzen aus Fahrzeugsensoren (Kameras, LiDAR, Radar) zur Erkennung und Vorhersage von Verkehrssituationen\nZusammenarbeit mit Softwareentwicklern und Systemingenieuren zur Integration von Machine-Learning-Lösungen in unsere autonomen Fahrsysteme\nTeilnahme an der Erstellung und Pflege von technischen Dokumentationen und Berichten\nHybrides Arbeiten im Home Office und an unserem Standort in München Unterschleißheim möglich\n\nStudium in Informatik, Mathematik, Elektrotechnik oder einem verwandten Fachgebiet\nKenntnisse in den Bereichen Machine Learning, Deep Learning und Künstliche Intelligenz\nErfahrung mit Frameworks wie TensorFlow, PyTorch, Keras oder ähnlichen\nKenntnisse in der Verarbeitung und Analyse von Sensordaten wünschenswert\nProgrammierkenntnisse in Python, C++ und/oder anderen relevanten Programmiersprachen\nAusgeprägte Problemlösungsfähigkeiten und analytisches Denken\nEigenständige und strukturierte Arbeitsweise\nTeamfähigkeit und gute Kommunikationsfähigkeiten\nSehr gute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\nDEINE BENEFITS\n Spannende Projekte\n Flexible Zeiteinteilung\n Mitarbeiter-Events\n Attraktive Vergütung\n Angenehmes Betriebsklima\n Studenten-\nbindungs-\nprogramm\nKONTAKT\n\nPetra Wichmann\n\ncareer@arrk-engineering.com\n+ 49 (0)89 / 31857-0\nDatenschutzhinweise\n\nARRK Engineering ist Teil des internationalen ARRK Firmenverbundes und spezialisiert auf die Produktentwicklung. Innerhalb der ARRK-Firmengruppe setzen wir Produktentwicklungen von der virtuellen Entwicklung bis hin zum Prototypen und der Produktion in Kleinserien um.\nAus Gründen der Vereinfachung wird in dieser Stellenausschreibung ausschließlich die männliche Form verwendet. Es sind jedoch stets Personen jeden Geschlechts und jeglicher Orientierung gleichermaßen gemeint.\n\nUnser Stellenangebot richtet sich gleichermaßen an Schwerbehinderte Menschen und ihnen Gleichgestellte.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'ARRK Engineering GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2673f4219109e5a7','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2490,NULL,'job','Consultant Data Analytics (w/m/d)','Festanstellung','Deutschland',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'deutschlandweit\nVollzeit\nFestanstellung\nDein Arbeitsumfeld\nUnterstütze unser erfahrenes Team bei datengesteuerten Lösungen und Entscheidungsfindungen. Wir bieten unseren Kunden maßgeschneiderte Analysen, fortschrittliche Modelle und Visualisierungen, um ihnen dabei zu helfen, Erkenntnisse aus ihren Daten zu gewinnen.\nDeine Aufgaben\nMitarbeit in Datenprojekten von der Anforderungsaufnahme über Datenmanagement, Datenanalyse und Visualisierung bis zur Umsetzung\nAnwenden von Methoden aus den Bereichen Data Engineering, Data Science und Machine Learning\nErstellen von Datenvisualisierungen und Dashboards\nSchnittstellentätigkeiten zwischen Fachbereich und IT\nFachberatung zu Datenthemen\nDeine Stärken\nAbgeschlossenes Studium mit sehr gutem Erfolg (Master oder Promotion) in einem MINT-Studiengang, Psychologie oder VWL\nAusgeprägtes analytisches Denkvermögen und hohes Technologieverständnis\nNeugier sowie Bereitschaft zur permanenten Weiterentwicklung und Erarbeitung neuer Themenfelder\nKommunikationsgeschick und Teamgeist\nVerhandlungssichere Deutsch- und sehr gute Englischkenntnisse\nReisebereitschaft (projektabhängig)\nWir bieten\nKollegiales und familiäres Arbeitsumfeld\nAbwechslungsreiche und spannende Tätigkeiten\nAttraktive Vergütung\nFrühzeitige Verantwortung und kurze Entscheidungswege\nFach- oder Führungslaufbahn\nIndividuelle Weiterentwicklung\nFlexible Wohnortwahl in Deutschland\nBuddy-Programm für neue Kolleginnen und Kollegen\nRegelmäßige Team- und Sportevents\nAusstattung auf dem neuesten Stand der Technik\nDein Kontakt\nDr. Guntram Hainke\nHead of Analytics\nkarriere@consileon.de\n+49 721 619016-70\nÜber uns\nConsileaner sind Teamworker, lernen mit- und voneinander und genießen den Erfolg gemeinsam. Respekt, Fairness, Menschlichkeit und Vertrauen treiben uns dabei an. Mit über 550 Mitarbeiterinnen und Mitarbeitern ist Consileon eine wachstumsstarke Top-Managementberatung für Lösungen mit IT- und KI-Bezug. Wir unterstützen DAX-Konzerne ebenso wie Hidden Champions von der Konzeption bis zur Umsetzung in allen Bereichen der Digitalisierung.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Consileon Applied Business GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8e30a310c44265ea','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2491,NULL,'job','Senior Data Scientist','Vollzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Berlin\nFull-time\nPermanent employee\nIntro\n\nAdsquare\'s mission is centered on:\n\nPassion: Solving complex challenges with exceptional people, technology, and data.\n\nNiche: Specializing in Location Intelligence for Programmatic Advertisers.\n\nOur work is guided by our core values, and we look for candidates who embody them:\n\nDrive: Turning ambition into action that brings valuable outcomes.\n\nResilience: Adapting, persevering, and growing stronger through challenges.\n\nNo BS: Upholding honesty, transparency, and clear communication.\n\nHumble: Valuing modesty and letting results speak for themselves.\n\nMoral Compass: Acting with fairness, integrity, and respect.\n\nYour Mission\nAs a Senior Data Scientist at Adsquare, you will transform massive geospatial and behavioral datasets into production-ready intelligence. You won\'t just build models in a vacuum; you will collaborate with ML Engineers and Product owners to integrate advanced analytics into our core programmatic advertising platform. This role is a blend of high-scale engineering and rigorous scientific research.\nYour Profile\n\nExperience: 5+ years (B.S.), 3+ years (M.S.), or 1+ year (Ph.D.) in a hands-on Data Science role.\n\nTheoretical Mastery: Strong foundation in Probability, Inferential Statistics, Linear Algebra, and Experimental Design.\n\nPython Stack: Expert proficiency in pandas, scikit-learn, PyTorch/TensorFlow, and FastAPI.\n\nLarge-Scale Data: Proven experience querying and manipulating TB-scale datasets using SQL (e.g., BigQuery, Athena, Redshift, or Snowflake).\n\nCloud Production: Experience deploying and monitoring models within AWS (SageMaker, Lambda) or similar cloud environments.\n\nEducational Background:\n\nBachelor’s or Master’s degree (Ph.D. is an advantage) in a relevant quantitative empirical science field (e.g., Mathematics, Physics, Statistics, Engineering, Machine Learning, Computer Science, Economics, Social Sciences, Psychology, Neuroscience) or equivalent practical experience.\n\nSoft Skills & Personal Attributes:\n\nA strong commitment to Adsquare\'s core values: Drive, Resilience, No BS, Being Humble, and a strong Moral Compass.\n\nExceptional written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to translate complex technical concepts into clear, actionable insights.\n\nA proactive, research-driven approach to creatively and precisely solving complex challenges.\n\nWhat you will do\n\nEnd-to-End ML Development: Design, train, and deploy machine learning models at scale, focusing on location intelligence and audience attributes.\n\nProduction Excellence: Partner with Data/ML Engineers to ensure models are robust, monitored, and seamlessly integrated into our cloud-native production workflows.\n\nStrategic R&D: Lead research initiatives involving LLMs (LangChain, MCPs, specialized agents) and classical statistical/ML modeling to solve complex spatial problems.\n\nData Advocacy: Conduct rigorous EDA and experiment design to ensure data quality and provide actionable insights for strategic decision-making.\n\nScientific Contribution: Represent Adsquare by contributing to peer-reviewed publications and staying at the forefront of spatial data science.\n\nDesired Background\n\nData Modeling: Experience with dbt and modern data stack orchestration.\n\nGenerative AI: Hands-on experience building LLM-based applications using e.g., LangChain, MCPs, Streamlit.\n\nDomain Expertise: Prior experience in Programmatic Advertising or Geospatial/GIS data.\n\nOur Software Stack\n\nLanguages: Python, SQL\n\nTools: AWS (SageMaker, Redshift, Athena), Snowflake, dbt, FastAPI, Docker\n\nML/AI: PyTorch, Scikit-learn, LangChain, Streamlit\n\nYour Opportunities\n\nAt Adsquare, you will work at the cutting edge of data science and machine learning in a dynamic, value-driven environment. We are committed to our team\'s growth, empower you to challenge the status quo, and offer a platform where your contributions directly shape the future of location intelligence for programmatic advertisers.\n\nIf you are passionate about leveraging data science to drive innovation, eager to contribute to a talented team, and committed to our core values, we encourage you to apply.\n\nWhy us?\n\nOn top of a competitive package…\n\nWe are open to flexible work models: we work on a hybrid mode and remotely from anywhere in the world up to 3 months per year\nTo encourage education and professional growth, we offer an individual yearly budget of 1.200€\nYou are entitled to 30 vacation days per year\nWe offer Urban Sports Club membership, company pension scheme\nRegular team events and company events organised by our People team (Trust us, they know how to throw a party!)\nWe equip you with the latest hardware and provide you with all the tools you need to thrive\n\nLocations\nBerlin HQ\nAbout us\n\nAdsquare is the global audience & location intelligence company making marketing a whole lot smarter.\n\nWith eight offices around the world we are a truly international company but one united team working towards our vision: empowering companies to accelerate business growth by staying at the forefront of data-driven marketing.\n\nWe are pioneers in advertising and data. We were born mobile, before it was a necessity, and have pioneered data-driven advertising in display and now DOOH. We have the smartest people, working with the best tech, so we can drive the pace of change.\n\nWe are visionaries. We see a better way for marketers and are doing everything we can to make that a reality. We believe in innovation and the power of technology. We believe in constantly improving what we’re doing because the work is never done.\n\nWe believe in what we do and rise to meet our own high standards. If there’s a problem, we fix it, humbly and without fuss or delay. Although our technology is best-of-breed, we are unassuming and modest in our approach.\n\nWe are passionately candid, both with each other and with our clients. We take the time to explain our approach to their problem, confident there is nothing to hide.\n\nWe are consistent and true to our word. We don’t take shortcuts but focus on being our clients’ most reliable partner. We make promises - and we keep them. As a result, clients enjoy spending time with us, because we are good people.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'adsquare GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=eaf8eb7f4c76c27a','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2492,NULL,'job','Stellenausschreibung: wissenschaftliche*r Mitarbeiter*in (w/m/d), Universität Göttingen','','53113 Bonn',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'At the University of Göttingen -Public Law Foundation-, DNTW - Abt. Tierzucht und Haustiergenetik, there is a position as\n\nResearch Assistant (all genders welcome)\n\nEntgeltgruppe 13 TV-L/100%\n\nto be filled. Starting date is 9/15/2026. The position is permanent.\n\nWe Offer:\n\n Opportunities for advanced scientific qualification in the field of animal science, with a focus on livestock research\n Access to higher‑education didactic training and professional development programs\n Excellent interdisciplinary working opportunities within an innovative and dynamic research environment\n An open, collegial, and constructive working atmosphere\n Exposure to a wide range of diverse research projects\n Outstanding national and international networks in academia and industry\n Access to university sports and recreational programs\n\nYour Profile:\n\nWe are seeking a highly motivated and dedicated scientist with excellent expertise in experimental design, statistics, and the analysis of data from\n\nlivestock research. Applicants must hold a completed university degree (Master’s level) and a doctoral degree (PhD) in Agricultural Sciences, Biology,\n\nBioinformatics, or a closely related discipline.\n\nThe successful candidate will demonstrate strong proficiency in several programming languages (e.g., R, Python, C#) and practical experience in working\n\nwith Linux and high‑performance computing (HPC) systems. Proven research experience in livestock science is essential, including a solid understanding\nof complex scientific questions and the analysis of large‑scale (big data) datasets. A basic understanding of modern analysis methods (various methods of\nartificial intelligence, e.g. machine learning, neural networks, and deep learning) is expected. An excellent publication record in relevant peer‑reviewed\ninternational journals is expected.\n\nA key responsibility is contributing to academic teaching; therefore, experiences in academic teaching, including supervising Bachelor’s, Master’s, and\n\ndoctoral theses, are expected. Excellent written and spoken English skills, as well as good to very good German language proficiency (at least level B2) are\n\nrequired. In addition, the candidate should demonstrate strong social competence, the ability to work effectively in a team, and excellent communication\n\nskills.\n\nYour Responsibilities:\n\n Participation in academic teaching amounting to 10 lecturing hours per week, including the design and delivery of courses, as well as\nsupervision, academic mentoring, and statistical consultancy of Bachelor’s, Master’s, and doctoral students\n\n Analysis, statistical modeling, and interpretation of heterogeneous datasets from livestock research, including complex and large‑scale data\ntypes\n\n Application and further development of state‑of‑the‑art statistical methods, programming and analysis workflows (e.g., R, Python), and the\nuse of high‑performance computing infrastructures\n\n Conceptualization, planning, and independent as well as interdepartmental execution of research projects in livestock science\n Development of innovative scientific research questions and active acquisition of third‑party funding from national and international funding\n\nagencies\n\n Preparation, presentation, and publication of research results at national and international scientific conferences and in high‑quality,\npeer‑reviewed international journals\n\n Active participation in interdisciplinary research teams and engagement in scientific exchange and collaborative projects\n\nThe University of Göttingen is an equal opportunities employer and places particular emphasis on fostering career opportunities for women. Qualified\n\nwomen are therefore strongly encouraged to apply in fields in which they are underrepresented. The university has committed itself to being a\n\nfamily-friendly institution and supports their employees in balancing work and family life. The University is particularly committed to the professional\n\nparticipation of severely disabled employees and therefore welcomes applications from severely disabled people. In the case of equal qualifications,\n\napplications from people with severe disabilities will be given preference. A disability or equality is to be included in the application in order to protect\n\nthe interests of the applicant.\n\nPlease upload your application in one pdf file including the usual documents until 5/13/2026 on the application portal of the university using this link:\n\nhttp://obp.uni-goettingen.de/de-de/OBF/Index/76416. For more information get in touch with Prof. Dr. Christine Große-Brinkhaus directly via E-Mail:\n\nchristine.grosse-brinkhaus@uni-goettingen.de, Tel. +49 (0) 551 39-25604 .\n\nPlease note:\n\nWith submission of your application, you accept the processing of your applicant data in terms of data-protection law. Further information on the legal\n\nbasis and data usage is provided in the Information General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Deutsche Gesellschaft für Züchtungskunde e.V. (DGfZ)','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=af8ca4eb6570b27e','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2493,NULL,'job','Software Engineer (Program Analysis) (m/f/x)','Vollzeit','Sankt Ingbert',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Your future area of responsibility:\nDeveloping and extending program analysis engines to extract structured, security-relevant insights from code.\nWorking with graph-based code representations (e.g., ASTs, CPGs, call graphs) to model and analyze program behavior.\nIntegrating analysis components into larger systems, including pipelines that interface with AI agents.\nDesigning and maintaining scalable, testable, and maintainable code for analysis frameworks.\nBuilding APIs and services that expose analysis results for downstream systems.\nBuilding testing strategies (unit, integration, and end-to-end) to ensure the correctness and reliability of analysis results.\nCollaborating closely with machine learning, security, and systems researchers to translate research into a usable system.\n\nFor content-related questions regarding the position, Hossein Hajipour is available as your contact person via email.\n\nWe are looking for someone who is passionate about advancing the state of the art in software security and building systems that can reason about vulnerabilities at scale.\n\nYour qualifications profile:\nBachelor’s degree in computer science or a related field; master\'s or PhD preferred.\nStrong software engineering skills with experience building real-world systems.\nSolid understanding of program analysis concepts (e.g., static analysis, data-flow analysis, taint tracking).\nExperience with program analysis tools such as Tree-sitter.\nExperience writing clean, testable, and maintainable code, with a focus on reliability and scalability.\nAbility to effectively leverage AI coding agents and developer tools to accelerate development while maintaining high standards of code quality and reliability.\nWe’d be lucky if you also:\nHave hands-on experience integrating program analysis tools into real-world developer workflows or security pipelines.\nHave worked on vulnerability detection or secure code analysis in practice.\nAre comfortable bridging research and engineering.\nHave experience working with or alongside LLM-based systems or AI-assisted development tools\nEnjoy tackling ambiguous problems and shaping both the technical direction and implementation details.\n\nWhat we offer:\nWork on cutting-edge research at the intersection of AI and software security\nContribute to technology that addresses real-world, high-impact security challenges\nBe part of a highly ambitious, research-driven team\nShape the future of autonomous, intelligent security systems\nA challenging and exciting role with a high degree of creative freedom in a research institution dedicated to shaping the future of information security in a scientific and strongly international environment\nA strong commitment to work-life balance and equal opportunities; all positions are generally suitable for part-time work\nCompensation and social benefits in accordance with the German public sector collective agreement (TVöD Bund)\nA fixed-term position\nUp to two days of remote work per week (subject to operational requirements)\nFlexible working hours\nOccupational pension scheme (VBL)\nOpportunities for professional development and further training\nSubsidized job ticket\nSocial and team-building activities\nWorkplace health management programs','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'CISPA – Helmholtz-Zentrum für Informationssicherheit gGmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=0fe540e34e050dea','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2494,NULL,'job','Postdoc (w/m/d) - Ab-Initio-Simulationen für Al, Cu, Si und andere Materialien bei hohen Energiedichten','Vollzeit','Deutschland',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Mit Spitzenforschung in den Bereichen ENERGIE, GESUNDHEIT und MATERIE lösen wir am Helmholtz-Zentrum Dresden-Rossendorf (HZDR) einige der drängenden gesellschaftlichen Herausforderungen unserer Zeit. Werden Sie Teil des HZDR-Teams und schließen Sie sich 1.500 Mitarbeitenden aus mehr als 70 Nationen an!\n\nDie High Energy Density Initiative (HEDI) ist ein gemeinsames Projekt des Helmholtz-Zentrums Dresden-Rossendorf und der Universität Rostock zur Untersuchung von Materie bei extrem hohen Temperaturen und Drücken mit absehbaren Anwendungen in den Bereichen Astrophysik, Materialwissenschaften und Fusionsforschung. Im Rahmen von HEDI soll ein neues Forschungsgebäude auf dem Campus der Universität Rostock errichtet und betrieben werden. Für Aufbau und Betrieb von HEDI suchen wir zum frühestmöglichen Zeitpunkt einen\n\nPostdoc (w/m/d) - Ab-Initio-Simulationen für Al, Cu, Si und andere Materialien bei hohen Energiedichten\n\nzur Verstärkung des Teams. Die Stelle ist zunächst befristet auf 2 Jahre. Die wöchentliche Arbeitszeit beträgt 39 Stunden. Die Vergütung erfolgt nach dem Tarifvertrag für den öffentlichen Dienst des Bundes (TVöD-Bund). Der Arbeitsort ist Rostock.\n\nDas sind Ihre Aufgaben:\n\nDurchführung von Ab-Initio-Simulationen für Al, Cu, Si und andere Materialien bei hohen Energiedichten\n\nAnwendung von Machine Learning Tools für die entsprechenden Datensätze\n\nEntwicklung von Auswerte-Tools für die Simulationen\n\nDurchführung von Literaturrecherchen\n\nMithilfe bei der Planung, Durchführung und Auswertung von Experimenten, speziell am European XFEL\n\nPublikation wissenschaftlicher Ergebnisse\n\nAnleitung von wissenschaftlichen und studentischen Hilfskräften sowie Praktikanten\n\nDas zeichnet Sie aus:\nAbgeschlossene Promotion in einer einschlägigen Fachrichtung\nPostdoktorale Erfahrung in eigenständiger Forschung\nErfahrung in eigenständiger sichtbarer Publikation von Forschungsergebnissen\nSicherer Umgang mit gängigen Softwareanwendungen im Office Bereich, zur Datenerfassung, Auswertung und Publikation\nGute Deutsch- und Englischkenntnisse in Wort und Schrift\nDas bieten wir Ihnen:\nEin spannendes Arbeitsumfeld auf einem attraktiven Forschungscampus\nEine hohe wissenschaftliche Vernetzung und wissenschaftliche Exzellenz\nEin breites Spektrum an Qualifizierungsmöglichkeiten und eine individuelle Karriereberatung durch das Postdoc Center HZDR-TUD\nDie Vergütung und Sozialleistungen nach dem Tarifvertrag des öffentlichen Dienstes (TVöD-Bund) - u. a. 30 Urlaubstage pro Jahr, Betriebliche Altersvorsorge (VBL)\nDie Vereinbarkeit von Privatleben und Beruf unterstützen wir mit der Möglichkeit zur Teilzeitbeschäftigung und zum mobilen Arbeiten sowie flexiblen Arbeitszeiten\nEine Vielzahl von Angeboten des betrieblichen Gesundheitsmanagements\nMitarbeiterrabatte bei namhaften Anbietern über die Plattform Corporate Benefits\nEinen Arbeitgeberzuschuss zum Deutschland-Ticket Jobticket\n\nIhre vollständigen Bewerbungsunterlagen (Anschreiben, Lebenslauf, Zeugnisse, usw.) reichen Sie bitte ausschließlich über unser Online-Bewerbungsportal ein.\nOrganisationseinheit:\nHED-Forschung Rostock\n\nArbeitsort/ Arbeitszeit:\nRostock\nVollzeit\n\nEinstellung:\n1. Juni 2026\n\nBefristung:\n24 Monate\n\nFragen zur Stelle beantwortet Ihnen gern:\nHerr Prof. Dr. Dominik Kraus Tel.: +49 381 498 6930\n\nBewerbungsschluss:\n7. Mai 2026\n\nJob-Id: 2026/55 (2228)\n\nAm HZDR fördern und schätzen wir die Diversität unserer Mitarbeitenden. Wir freuen uns über Bewerbungen von Menschen mit vielfältigen Hintergründen unabhängig von Geschlecht, ethnischer und sozialer Herkunft, Weltanschauung, Behinderung, Alter sowie sexueller Orientierung. Schwerbehinderte Menschen werden bei gleicher Eignung bevorzugt eingestellt.\n\nHelmholtz-Zentrum\nDresden-Rossendorf\nBautzner Landstraße 400\n01328 Dresden','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Helmholtz-Zentrum Dresden-Rossendorf','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5447c6b84035695c','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2495,NULL,'job','R&D Quality Engineer (m/w/d)','Vollzeit','Mülheim-Kärlich',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We’re looking for an experienced R&D Quality Engineer who doesn’t just “audit” processes, but actively partners with engineering teams to build better products.\n\nIn this role, you’ll play a key part in strengthening our Automotive SPICE maturity while ensuring that quality is embedded into how we design, develop, and deliver cutting-edge automotive systems.\n\nIf you enjoy working hands-on with development teams, influencing engineering practices, and turning process frameworks into real-world impact, this role is for you.\n\nWhat will your job look like:\n\nPartner with system and software engineering teams to implement and improve ASPICE-compliant processes.\n\nDrive continuous improvement of product quality, not just process adherence\n\nSupport and guide teams through ASPICE assessments (internal & external)\n\nTranslate ASPICE requirements into practical, scalable engineering workflows\n\nIdentify gaps, risks, and improvement opportunities across the development lifecycle\n\nCoach teams on best practices in systems & software engineering\n\nContribute to building a quality-driven engineering culture\n\nAll you need is:\n\nB.Sc. in Software Engineering, Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Systems Engineering, or a related technical field.\n\nStrong background in systems & software engineering\n\nAt least 4 years\' experience in implementing ASPICE\n\nProven experience implementing ASPICE in real projects\n\nASPICE Provisional Assessor certification with Cybersecurity extension (Competent assessor is a plus)\n\nCollaborative mindset with strong communication skills\n\nExcellent communication skills in English (both verbal and written)\n\nASPICE for Machine Learning- an advantage\n\nVW SQIL certification - an advantage\n\nGerman language skills - an advantage\nMobileye changes the way we drive, from preventing accidents to semi and fully autonomous vehicles. If you are an excellent, bright, hands-on person with a passion to make a difference come to lead the revolution!\n\nWe may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Mobileye','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c90d282b1e0761a6','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2496,NULL,'job','Blade Architect (all genders)','','Wolfsburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Join us as a Blade Architect (all genders) in our Embedded Team and help shape the future of autonomous mobility!\nWhat you will do\nDefine and evolve the software architecture for embedded in‑vehicle systems operating on multicore and multi‑virtual‑machine platforms.\nDrive architecture decisions across performance, cost, and functional constraints.\nAlign the software architecture with Safety, Homologation, and Security stakeholders.\nContribute architectural expertise directly within the development team, shaping concepts and requirements together to enable efficient implementation.\nCoordinate architecture concepts and requirements with external suppliers.\nCreate and maintain comprehensive documentation of architecture designs, decision records, and system behavior.\nDevelop the long‑term architecture roadmap for future platform evolution.\nWhat will help you to fulfill your role\nDeep expertise in automotive embedded architectures, with emphasis on high‑performance SoCs.\nSolid methodological knowledge in architecture design and documentation.\nProven experience in managing and collaborating with external suppliers.\nStrong understanding of compute platforms (e.g., Qualcomm Ride, custom automotive SoCs).\nExcellent facilitation, communication, and stakeholder‑alignment skills.\nFamiliarity with networking technologies, including TCP/IP, IPv6, VLAN configuration, and SOCKS proxies.\nProven track record in industries with high reliability and quality demands (automotive, medical, aerospace, or similar), specifically considering ASPICE, ISO26262, homologation.\n\nWe welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds — even if you don\'t meet every requirement. If you\'re excited about the role and MOIA\'s mission, we\'d love to hear from you!\n\nOur benefits in a nutshell\nCompetitive salary (including bonus)\nHybrid work setup: Work from home or one of our offices - you and your team decide how often to meet, blending flexibility with collaboration!\nFlexible working hours and the possibility of flexible work arrangements depending on your needs (parenting, care work, volunteering, etc.)\nBudget and monthly expense allowance for home office setup\nPossibility of remote work from outside Germany for up to 6 weeks per year from over 35 countries - learn more in our blog!\nPublic transport ticket (fully subsidized \"Deutschlandticket\") for commuting and travelling throughout Germany and discount on MOIA rides\nSubsidized fitness club membership or bike leasing\nLearning environment with continuous learning days, job rotation, trainings and workshops, coaching, conferences, books, and language classes\nMental health support, 1:1 sessions with external professionals and mental unload workshops\n30 vacation days, sabbatical and unpaid leave option\nRelocation support with service provider (visa, administration, etc.)\nDog-friendly offices\n\nFor student & internship positions, we have an adjusted set of benefits. You can find them here.\n\nBe who you are!\n\nWe are a member of Charta der Vielfalt and are dedicated to actively fostering a workplace that celebrates and promotes diversity in various aspects such as age, gender identity, race, sexual orientation, physical or cognitive ability, and ethnicity. At MOIA, we embrace a culture where people are accepted, respected, valued, appreciated, and included.\n\nIn our commitment to promoting diversity and inclusivity, we regularly provide unconscious bias training to all our employees. Furthermore, we continuously strive to enhance our hiring process by ensuring a diverse hiring panel.\n\nHow we work\n\nAt MOIA, our teams are typically distributed across locations and collaborate in a hybrid setup. We work together both remotely and on site, choosing the mode of collaboration that fits the context, the work at hand, and each team\'s rhythm.\n\nSpending time together in our offices is an important part of how we stay connected, build trust, and solve complex problems. At the same time, we value flexibility and give teams and individuals autonomy to shape their ways of working, with everyone having the freedom to organise their routines in a way that aligns with their work and their team\'s needs.\n\nIf you\'d like to learn more about how we work, visit our blog for insights into our culture and hiring process, or follow us on Instagram for a look behind the scenes at MOIA.\n\nWho we are\n\nAt MOIA we\'re reimagining the future of mobility – safe, autonomous and tailored to the needs of cities and their people. As a tech company with more than 400 employees, we build mobility solutions that truly move cities forward.\n\nWe launched our ridepooling service in Hamburg in 2019 and have been part of the city\'s public transport system since 2023. Since launch, we have transported over 12 million passengers. Currently, MOIA is evolving from a mobility provider to a tech provider offering a scalable and safe turnkey solution for autonomous driving.\n\nWith office locations in Berlin and Hamburg, our diverse and international team comprising more than 60 nationalities works together toward that shared mission.\n\nMOIA is more than a technology provider – we are a partner to cities and public transport operators committed to creating more livable spaces and delivering mobility solutions that are reliable, safe and comfortable.\n\nYour application to MOIA\n\nWe value authenticity and personal insights in your application responses. While AI tools can be useful, we encourage you to answer the following questions based on your own experiences and understanding. This helps us keep a human touch and better evaluate your unique perspective and match for the role.\n\nTo reinforce an unbiased screening process, we kindly ask you not to include your picture, age, address, or any other details unrelated to your qualifications and suitability for the role. Additionally, we anonymize applications during the initial review phase by removing personally identifiable information. This ensures that our evaluation focuses solely on your skills, experience, and potential – supporting a fair and inclusive hiring experience for all candidates.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'MOIA GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=7e7ecdca0a46d818','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2497,NULL,'job','Senior Consultant MLOps Engineering (m/w/d)','Festanstellung','53229 Bonn',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Bonn oder freie Arbeitsplatzwahl\nVollzeit\nFestanstellung\n\nDeine Aufgaben\nJe nach Bedarf im Kundenprojekt übernimmst du mehrere Rollen:\n\nAls technische/r Experte/in / Architekt:in für MLOps bist du der/die primäre Ansprechpartner:in für die technische Konzeption und Umsetzung der MLOps-Infrastrukturen und Automatisierungslösungen\nAls Implementierer / Engineer baust du Plattformen und Pipelines auf, konfigurierst Tools und schreibst den notwendigen Code (IaC, CI/CD-Konfigurationen, Automatisierungsskripte)\nAls Enabler / Unterstützer hilfst du Data Science Teams und anderen Stakeholdern bei unseren Kunden, die MLOps-Plattformen und -Prozesse effektiv zu nutzen und ihre Machine Learning Modelle erfolgreich in Produktion zu bringen\nAn der Schnittstelle zwischen Data Science, Softwareentwicklung (DevOps), IT-Betrieb und ggf. Security stimmst du technische Anforderungen ab, um Lösungen zu integrieren\nDeine Aufgaben\n\nDu behältst den Überblick über aktuelle Technologien und bewertest neue Entwicklungen im Bereich MLOps und DevOps\nDu konzipierst, entwickelst und wartest MLOps-Plattformen – einschließlich dem Design der technischen Infrastruktur und Toolchains (z. B. basierend auf Kubeflow und Kubernetes) – zur Unterstützung und Automatisierung des gesamten Machine Learning Lifecycles\nDu unterstützt beim skalierbaren Deployment von Machine Learning Modellen und automatisierst deren Workflows durch CI/CD-Pipelines (z. B. mit GitLab CI/CD oder GitHub Actions) – inklusive Troubleshooting und technischem Support\nDu integrierst und betreibst zentrale MLOps-Tools wie MLflow für Experiment Tracking, Model Registry und Deployment – und bindest sie nahtlos in CI/CD-Prozesse ein\nDu implementierst GitOps-Praktiken (z. B. mit Argo CD) für die automatisierte Auslieferung von Infrastruktur- und Applikationskomponenten\nDu baust Monitoring- und Logging-Lösungen zur Überwachung der Plattform, der Pipeline-Ausführungen sowie des Verhaltens produktiver Machine Learning Modelle auf und entwickelst sie weiter\nDu gestaltest DevSecOps-Prozesse aktiv mit – inklusive Container-Scanning, Secret Management und Zugriffskontrollen – und arbeitest dabei eng mit unseren Security-Teams zusammen, um Sicherheit nahtlos in automatisierte Prozesse zu integrieren\nDein Profil\nDu hast dein Masterstudium oder deine Promotion in einem der MINT-Fächer erfolgreich abgeschlossen\nDu verfügst über mindestens 4 Jahre relevante Berufserfahrung, idealerweise als (Senior) Consultant bei einer IT-Beratung\nDu beherrschst Python sehr gut und nutzt es regelmäßig für Automatisierungen und zur Integration von Machine-Learning-Komponenten\nDu arbeitest sicher mit Bash- bzw. Shell-Skripting, insbesondere im Kontext von CI/CD-Pipelines und Infrastrukturaufgaben\nDu hast idealerweise erste Erfahrungen mit Ruby, Go oder Rust – das ist ein Plus, aber kein Muss\nDu verfügst über ein tiefes Verständnis von Containerisierung mit Docker und kannst komplexe Container-Umgebungen selbstständig aufsetzen und betreiben\nDu kennst dich sehr gut mit Kubernetes aus – inklusive Administration, Netzwerk-Architekturen und Security Policies\nDu hast Erfahrung mit MLOps-Plattformen wie Kubeflow und MLflow. Wenn du dich auch mit SageMaker, Azure ML oder ähnlichen Lösungen auskennst, ist das von Vorteil\nDu bist vertraut mit CI/CD-Tools wie GitLab CI/CD, GitHub Actions oder Jenkins und weißt, wie man damit automatisierte Deployments umsetzt\nDu hast ein grundlegendes Verständnis von GitOps-Ansätzen und kennst Tools wie Argo CD oder FluxCD\nDu arbeitest routiniert mit Infrastructure as Code, insbesondere mit Terraform und Ansible. Auch Helm-Charts für Kubernetes-Deployments gehören zu deinem Repertoire\nDu bringst fundierte Erfahrung mit mindestens einer großen Cloud-Plattform mit – z. B. AWS, Azure oder Google Cloud (GCP) – und kennst deren Kubernetes-Angebote (EKS, AKS, GKE) sowie relevante ML- und DevOps-Services\nDu richtest Monitoring- und Logging-Lösungen wie Prometheus, Grafana oder den ELK-Stack (oder Alternativen) selbstständig ein und nutzt sie aktiv zur Systemüberwachung und Fehleranalyse\nDu kommunizierst überzeugend und effizient in deutscher und englischer Sprache\nDu hast Spaß daran, in einem flexiblen Mix aus Homeoffice, an unserem Standort in Bonn und bei Kunden vor Ort zu arbeiten\nWarum wir?\nMit deinem Team stehst du unseren Kunden zur Seite und hilfst ihnen dabei, ihre Daten zu verstehen und die Erkenntnisse daraus gewinnbringend zu nutzen\nKundenprojekte nach dem Fließbandprinzip sind nicht unser Ding: Du arbeitest durchschnittlich an mindestens zwei Kundenprojekten gleichzeitig, sodass du dich intensiv mit den Anforderungen beschäftigen kannst und siehst, wie deine Lösungen ihre Wirkung entfalten\nAbwechslung im Arbeitsalltag bringt die Vielfalt unserer Kunden aller Branchen, vom großen Mittelstand bis zum DAX-Konzern\nMit deinen zukünftigen Kolleg:innen tauschst du dich fachlich auf Augenhöhe aus und erhältst Budget und Zeit für eure eigenen Innovationsprojekte\nDu wächst bei uns fachlich und persönlich durch speziell auf dich abgestimmte Weiterbildungen, Zertifizierungen und Laufbahnprogramme\nIn deinen Spezialgebieten kannst du deinen Schwerpunkt setzen und ausbauen\nNeben einem attraktiven Fixgehalt zzgl. Umsatz- und Ergebnisbeteiligung kannst du Überstunden ausgleichen und Reisezeiten als Arbeitszeit buchen\nDurch freie Wahl des Arbeitsorts und flexible Arbeitszeit gestaltest du deinen Arbeitsalltag passend zu deinem Lebensstil\nDich erwarten außerdem ein top ausgestatteter Arbeitsplatz, JobRad, Body & Mind Workout, GamesNights, Grillen auf unserer Dachterrasse, Team-Aktionen mit unternehmungslustigen Kolleg:innen, Sommerfeste mit deinen Familienmitgliedern und viele weitere Benefits','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Comma Soft AG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f2fea270238fc623','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2498,NULL,'job','Senior Digitalization Engineer (m/f/d)','','44141 Dortmund',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Group presentation\n\nthyssenkrupp is an international industrial and technology group with more than 93,000 employees. In the fiscal year 2024/2025, the company generated sales of around €33 billion in 48 countries. Its business activities are bundled in five segments: Automotive Technology, Decarbon Technologies, Materials Services, Steel Europe and Marine Systems. With extensive technological know-how, outstanding engineering competence and a high level of innovative strength, the group develops solutions for the challenges of the future, especially in the fields of climate protection and energy transition, digital transformation in industry and mobility of the future.\n\nCompany presentation\n\nThe Decarbon Technologies segment is positioning itself as a technology leader for the energy transition and showcasing its credentials as a \'green industrial powerhouse’ with extensive capabilities for the green transformation. It comprises the thyssenkrupp rothe erde, thyssenkrupp nucera, thyssenkrupp Uhde and thyssenkrupp Polysius businesses. thyssenkrupp rothe erde is the world’s No. 1 supplier of the latest generation of bearings, with which it is making the energy transition possible. thyssenkrupp nucera is one of the world\'s leading providers of electrolysis plants for the production of green hydrogen. thyssenkrupp Uhde is a global technology leader in the ammonia value chain (including ammonia cracking), where production will increasingly be through green methods in the future. thyssenkrupp Polysius is one of the pioneers for the climate-neutral transformation of the cement industry with its green technologies, such as the patented oxyfuel technology. The businesses combine many years of experience, in-depth expertise in international plant engineering, an extensive installed base and close customer relationships. Approximately 12,335 employees work in the segment, which generated sales of around 3.5 billion euros in fiscal 2024/2025.\n\nthyssenkrupp Uhde combines unique technological expertise and decades of global experience in the engineering, procurement, construction and service of chemical plants. We develop innovative processes and products for a more sustainable future and thus contribute to the long-term success of our customers in almost all areas of the chemical industry. Our portfolio includes leading technologies for the production of base chemicals, fertilizers and polymers as well as complete value chains for green hydrogen and sustainable chemicals.\n\nYour responsibilities\n\nAbout the Role:\n\nAs a Senior Digitalization Engineer, you will play a key role in shaping the digital future of Uhde GmbH and our Engineering Services. You will develop modern web solutions, create digital products for internal and external customers, and optimize our engineering and business processes through modern, data‑driven approaches.\n\nYou will be supported by a highly committed and motivated team, the strong backing of our board to drive digitalization, and the creative mindset of our service department, which actively encourages new digital products and ideas.\n\nYour Responsibilities:\n\nCollaborate closely with business units to understand, prioritize, and translate requirements into technical solutions.\nDevelop modern software solutions based on C#/Blazor, and Python; experience with React (Native) or TypeScript is a plus.\nDesign and implement robust backend architectures as well as web or code‑behind applications.\nConceptualization and design of modern user interfaces – from mockup and alignment to an appealing and intuitive final product.\nIntegrate modern data platforms (e.g., Microsoft Fabric, Azure AI Foundry) and develop AI‑powered solutions in the fields of LLMs, machine learning, and data‑driven workflow optimization.\nWork with relational and time‑series databases.\nIdentify optimization and automation potential of internal workflows.\nEngage in troubleshooting, continuous improvement, and contribute to shaping our digitalization strategy.\nOptional: Analysis of data using modern data‑science libraries.\n\nYour profile\n\nTechnical affinity or experience in process engineering, plant engineering, or related technical fields; ability to quickly understand complex subject matter.\nStrong programming skills in C#/Blazor, and Python; additional experience in React/JavaScript is advantageous.\nDeep understanding of UI/UX design, proficient handling of CSS, prototyping, and performance‑optimized modern frontends.\nExperience with cloud technologies, preferably Microsoft Azure.\nKnowledge of LLM/ML technologies, data platforms (Fabric/Foundry), and data‑driven products.\nSolid experience with relational databases and time‑series databases.\nHigh degree of learning agility, innovation mindset, and strong self‑initiative; willingness to take product ownership throughout the entire PLM cycle.\nAbility to act as a troubleshooter in dynamic situations.\nLanguage skills:\nGerman: desirable\nEnglish: fluent in spoken and written form (mandatory)\nWillingness to undertake short, occasional international travel to our plant sites.\n\nLocation & Work Model\n\nPlease note: This position is based at the Dortmund site of Uhde GmbH. We do offer mobile working to a certain extent but a regular on‑site presence is required to successfully fulfill the role. We cannot offer a fully remote position.\n\nA Final Note\n\nWe know: this profile is ambitious.\nIf you don’t meet every single requirement but cover most of them and consider yourself a fast‑learning, proactive personality, we strongly encourage you to apply.\n\nExperience matters – and a solid technical education is highly appreciated.\n\nContact details\n\nCagla Coskun\n\nTel:\n\nYour benefits with us\n\nWe work together closely and respect each other, for over 200 years now and up till today. If that is just as important to you as it is to us, please apply online now under specification of your salary requirement and your notice period.\n\nIt goes without saying, that we would like to offer attractive working conditions. This includes for example:\n\nPerformance-related compensation according to collective agreement Metal & Electro NRW (30 days vacation, 35 hour week, vacation pay, special payments according to collective agreement)\nAttractive old-age provision models\nGroupwide learning measures\nthyssenkrupp internal health campaigns\n\nDiversity\n\nWe value diversity and therefore welcome all applications, irrespective of gender, nationality, ethnic and social background, religion and beliefs, disability, age, or sexual orientation and identity.\n\nJob Reference: DE_RS_18186','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'thyssenkrupp Uhde GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=aeeed50875a5dbcc','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2499,NULL,'job','(Senior) Quality Specialist (all genders) - Passenger Interaction','','Hamburg',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Join us as a (Senior) Quality Specialist (all genders) in our Passenger Interaction team and help shape the future of autonomous mobility!\n\nJoin our Passenger Interaction team as a (Senior) Quality Specialist, ensuring the quality and reliability of the Human Machine Interface (HMI) that riders interact with during their autonomous vehicle journeys.\n\nAs a (Senior) Quality Specialist, you\'ll work on the in-vehicle passenger experience — from welcome screens and check-in flows to safety checks, navigation displays, and emergency communication systems.\n\nOur HMI is an Android-based application running on embedded displays inside autonomous vehicles, providing passengers with essential ride information and safety features. As the team\'s quality advocate, you\'ll help ensure our riders have a seamless, intuitive experience throughout their journey.\n\nWhat you will do\nChampion quality across HMI features including check-in flows, safety checks, map views, buckling verification, and SOS functionality.\nDevelop and execute tests across multiple environments (SiL, HiL, ViL) and vehicle platforms.\nDrive shift-left practices — be involved early in epic planning and feature definition, not just at the testing phase.\nOwn the quality definition for HMI — establish what \"quality\" means for passenger-facing Android applications with a strong UX focus.\nValidate user experience — ensure the HMI is intuitive, responsive, and accessible for all passengers.\nBuild test automation and integrate it into CI/CD pipelines for faster feedback loops.\nMaster testbench environments and enable the team to run HMI software independently.\nPerform defect analysis and root-cause investigation, especially for UX issues and edge cases.\nCollaborate cross-functionally with developers, system engineers, designers, and product managers — breaking QA out of silos.\nCoach the team on testing best practices and facilitate continuous improvement.\nEnsure traceability between requirements and tests, maintaining transparency on quality and risk.\nWhat will help you to fulfill your role\n\nTechnical Skills\n\nExtensive experience in quality assurance/testing with embedded systems and mobile applications (we are building with Flutter framework for Android Automotive).\nProven experience with distributed systems spanning embedded devices and backend services, preferably with AWS.\nExperience with Flutter and/or Android development/testing tools and frameworks.\nUnderstanding of UX principles and ability to identify usability issues\nFamiliarity with ALM tools (e.g. Polarion) for requirements management\nExperience with test automation frameworks, testing methodologies, and CI/CD integration\nExperience with testbench environments (HiL, ViL) and AI assisted development are valued.\nAwareness of automotive standards (ASPICE, ISO 26262) is a plus.\n\nSoft Skills\n\nProactive, quality-driven mindset with a strong focus on improving user experience.\nDetail-oriented, especially in ensuring UI/UX consistency and polish.\nEffective communicator across technical and non-technical stakeholders and the ability to coach teams to level up, not just finding bugs.\nComfortable navigating complexity and ambiguity, with a genuine interest in autonomous driving and passenger experience.\n\nWe welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds — even if you don\'t meet every requirement. If you\'re excited about the role and MOIA\'s mission, we\'d love to hear from you!\n\nOur benefits in a nutshell\nCompetitive salary (including bonus)\nHybrid work setup: Work from home or one of our offices - you and your team decide how often to meet, blending flexibility with collaboration!\nFlexible working hours and the possibility of flexible work arrangements depending on your needs (parenting, care work, volunteering, etc.)\nBudget and monthly expense allowance for home office setup\nPossibility of remote work from outside Germany for up to 6 weeks per year from over 35 countries - learn more in our blog!\nPublic transport ticket (fully subsidized \"Deutschlandticket\") for commuting and travelling throughout Germany and discount on MOIA rides\nSubsidized fitness club membership or bike leasing\nLearning environment with continuous learning days, job rotation, trainings and workshops, coaching, conferences, books, and language classes\nMental health support, 1:1 sessions with external professionals and mental unload workshops\n30 vacation days, sabbatical and unpaid leave option\nRelocation support with service provider (visa, administration, etc.)\nDog-friendly offices\n\nFor student & internship positions, we have an adjusted set of benefits. You can find them here.\n\nBe who you are!\n\nWe are a member of Charta der Vielfalt and are dedicated to actively fostering a workplace that celebrates and promotes diversity in various aspects such as age, gender identity, race, sexual orientation, physical or cognitive ability, and ethnicity. At MOIA, we embrace a culture where people are accepted, respected, valued, appreciated, and included.\n\nIn our commitment to promoting diversity and inclusivity, we regularly provide unconscious bias training to all our employees. Furthermore, we continuously strive to enhance our hiring process by ensuring a diverse hiring panel.\n\nHow we work\n\nAt MOIA, our teams are typically distributed across locations and collaborate in a hybrid setup. We work together both remotely and on site, choosing the mode of collaboration that fits the context, the work at hand, and each team\'s rhythm.\n\nSpending time together in our offices is an important part of how we stay connected, build trust, and solve complex problems. At the same time, we value flexibility and give teams and individuals autonomy to shape their ways of working, with everyone having the freedom to organise their routines in a way that aligns with their work and their team\'s needs.\n\nIf you\'d like to learn more about how we work, visit our blog for insights into our culture and hiring process, or follow us on Instagram for a look behind the scenes at MOIA.\n\nWho we are\n\nAt MOIA we\'re reimagining the future of mobility – safe, autonomous and tailored to the needs of cities and their people. As a tech company with more than 400 employees, we build mobility solutions that truly move cities forward.\n\nWe launched our ridepooling service in Hamburg in 2019 and have been part of the city\'s public transport system since 2023. Since launch, we have transported over 12 million passengers. Currently, MOIA is evolving from a mobility provider to a tech provider offering a scalable and safe turnkey solution for autonomous driving.\n\nWith office locations in Berlin and Hamburg, our diverse and international team comprising more than 60 nationalities works together toward that shared mission.\n\nMOIA is more than a technology provider – we are a partner to cities and public transport operators committed to creating more livable spaces and delivering mobility solutions that are reliable, safe and comfortable.\n\nYour application to MOIA\n\nWe value authenticity and personal insights in your application responses. While AI tools can be useful, we encourage you to answer the following questions based on your own experiences and understanding. This helps us keep a human touch and better evaluate your unique perspective and match for the role.\n\nTo reinforce an unbiased screening process, we kindly ask you not to include your picture, age, address, or any other details unrelated to your qualifications and suitability for the role. Additionally, we anonymize applications during the initial review phase by removing personally identifiable information. This ensures that our evaluation focuses solely on your skills, experience, and potential – supporting a fair and inclusive hiring experience for all candidates.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'MOIA GmbH','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=409b5d07ef62b428','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2500,NULL,'job','AI Operations & Automation Manager - Europe/LaTAM','','Home Office',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Storyblok is a headless CMS that enables marketers and developers to create with joy and succeed in the AI-driven content era. It empowers you to deliver structured and consistent content everywhere: websites, apps, AI search, and beyond.\n\nMarketers get a visual editor with reusable components, in-context preview, and workflows to launch fast and stay on brand. Developers have freedom to use their favorite frameworks and integrate with anything through the API-first platform. Brands get one source of truth for content that is accurate, flexible, and measurable.\n\nLegendary brands like Virgin Media O2, Oatly, and TomTom use Storyblok to make a bigger, faster market impact. It\'s Joyful Headless™, and it changes everything.\n\nWHAT IS IN IT FOR YOU\n\nYou will be joining a growing company where you can contribute to many \"firsts\". Plus these benefits:\n\nMonthly remote work stipend (home internet costs, electricity). Home office equipment package right at the start (laptop, keyboard, monitor…)\nHome office equipment upgrade (furniture, ear plugs …) or membership to a local co-working space after your onboarding\nSick leave benefit, parental leave and 25 days of annual leave plus your local national holidays\nPersonal development fund for courses, books, conferences, and material\nVSOP (Virtual Stock Option Plan)\nThe annual international team-building trip, quarterly and monthly online get-togethers\nAs a fully remote company, with work-life balance at its core, you\'ll enjoy flexible schedules\nAn international team that loves to have fun at work and works hard together to accomplish shared goals\n\nJOB SUMMARY\n\nStoryblok is scaling rapidly. As AI Operations & Automation Manager, you will own the optimisation of the Operations (finance and people teams) application stack and you will assume end‑to‑end ownership of the finance-specific tech stack. Your primary objective will be to optimise existing Operations processes and elevate them to best-in-class standards. By championing automation and process optimization with the help of AI and other leading tools, you will boost data quality and integrity as well as maximise output of the existing resources. Partnering with Operations as well as Sales, Product, Data, and Revenue Operations, you will guide system changes, shape development roadmaps, and safeguard data integrity company‑wide. Your blend of technical depth, AI affinity and finance expertise will keep our infrastructure running smoothly, unlock faster, cleaner insights for every team, and enable you to step in hands‑on wherever your skills add the most significant value.\n\nESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS\n\nProcess Automation & AI Implementation: Identifying, designing, and implementing automation opportunities using AI tools, machine learning, and robotic process automation (RPA) to streamline workflows. Spot bottlenecks in processes and implement pragmatic solutions.\nAI Tool Optimization: Proactively monitor the automation and AI landscape, produce structured assessments for new tools, and lead stakeholder alignment for the adoption or deprecation of tooling, owning the outcome of these decisions. Monitoring, maintaining, and improving the existing AI toolchain to ensure data governance and continuous performance improvements.\nRisk Management: Using AI for proactive, predictive maintenance and risk assessment to prevent operational failures, with main focus in Finance, Human Resources and Operations.\nPerformance Tracking (ROI): Defining and monitoring key metrics (e.g., efficiency gains, reduction in manual effort) to measure the success of automated solutions.\nSupport month‑end close and internal reporting: support the optimisation of the financial close process; automate data extracts and variance analyses as well as other recurring processes.\nOwnership of finance tools: such as NetSuite Oneworld, Sigma, Spiff, Yokoy, Deel, and others, and their integrations/APIs, ensuring configurations align with finance policies and ensuring an accurate data flow, manage any external consultants.\nInformation‑security projects and audits: implement technical solutions that enhance our security posture, and support ISO 27001/SOC 2 or other audits.\nData integrity, backups, and availability: Schedule and monitor system exports, snapshots, and core‑IT backups; maintain retention policies to guarantee data completeness and recoverability.\nUser support, training, and documentation: troubleshoot finance‑system issues, maintain runbooks, and deliver regular training sessions to all Operations teams and other stakeholders on system usage and security best practices.\nCollaborate and Coach the HRIS Manager who owns the HR systems/tech stack in identifying and implementing automation opportunities and AI usage to improve efficiencies, while keeping the employee experience in mind.\n\nEDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE\n\nEducation and Certifications: Bachelor\'s degree in Information Systems, Computer Science, Accounting, Finance, Business Informatics,, or a related field required; Master\'s degree preferred. Professional accounting qualification (ACCA, CPA, CIMA) and/or NetSuite credentials (SuiteFoundation, Administrator) are a plus, but not a deal‑breaker.\nOverall Experience: Minimum 6+ years in finance or HR/people operations, or workflow automation in operations/backoffice departments in fast-paced companies, ideally within a SaaS or technology‑driven environment.\nTechnical Skills: Claude Code proficiency is required, familiar with SuiteScript/workflow configuration or Javascript. SQL/Python would be a plus.\nFamiliar with Google Sheets/Excel modelling and the ability to replace those.\nFamiliarity with good coding practices, e.g. version control, structured error handling, workflow testing, release notes, and excellent command of Git.\nSolid understanding of APIs, webhooks, and JSON-based integrations.\nAt least 3 of those years working with NetSuite OneWorld (or comparable ERP) in a multi‑entity, multi‑currency setup; hands‑on with at least one satellite tool (Sigma, Spiff, Yokoy, Deel, etc.).\nFamiliarity with HRIS and ATS systems (BambooHR, Greenhouse, and similar).\nGood working knowledge of N8N, Zapier, Celigo, familiarity with Sigma or similar BI visualisation tools.\nExcellent and pragmatic decision-making skills with the ability to assess multiple options and to identify the best choice to serve a specified goal\nExcellent English communication and written skills; other languages a plus.\nDemonstrates AI literacy, with the ability to leverage AI tools to enhance productivity, decision-making, and quality of work while applying sound judgment and critical thinking.\n\nMENTAL, PHYSICAL AND ENVIRONMENTAL REQUIREMENTS\n\nRemote (home) work opportunity or funded by Storyblok co-working space\n\nGENERAL TERMS\n\nStoryblok has a commitment to diversity and inclusion. We strive to create a hiring environment in which all people feel they are equally respected and valued, irrespective of gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, ethnicity, age, religion, citizenship or any other characteristic. You can find more information about our privacy policy here.\n\nAll communications regarding job opportunities at Storyblok will come from an official Storyblok employee with an email address ending in @storyblok.com. We will never redirect you to another portal or another site that is unrelated to our domain (storyblok.com).\n\nHere is a sneak peek of Storyblok\'s Visual Editor\n\nIf you need an accommodation for any part of the application process, please email talent.acquisition@storyblok.com','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Storyblok','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=92ba562645ccff37','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2501,NULL,'job','(Senior) Quality Specialist (all genders) - Passenger Interaction','','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Join us as a (Senior) Quality Specialist (all genders) in our Passenger Interaction team and help shape the future of autonomous mobility!\n\nJoin our Passenger Interaction team as a (Senior) Quality Specialist, ensuring the quality and reliability of the Human Machine Interface (HMI) that riders interact with during their autonomous vehicle journeys.\n\nAs a (Senior) Quality Specialist, you\'ll work on the in-vehicle passenger experience — from welcome screens and check-in flows to safety checks, navigation displays, and emergency communication systems.\n\nOur HMI is an Android-based application running on embedded displays inside autonomous vehicles, providing passengers with essential ride information and safety features. As the team\'s quality advocate, you\'ll help ensure our riders have a seamless, intuitive experience throughout their journey.\n\nWhat you will do\nChampion quality across HMI features including check-in flows, safety checks, map views, buckling verification, and SOS functionality.\nDevelop and execute tests across multiple environments (SiL, HiL, ViL) and vehicle platforms.\nDrive shift-left practices — be involved early in epic planning and feature definition, not just at the testing phase.\nOwn the quality definition for HMI — establish what \"quality\" means for passenger-facing Android applications with a strong UX focus.\nValidate user experience — ensure the HMI is intuitive, responsive, and accessible for all passengers.\nBuild test automation and integrate it into CI/CD pipelines for faster feedback loops.\nMaster testbench environments and enable the team to run HMI software independently.\nPerform defect analysis and root-cause investigation, especially for UX issues and edge cases.\nCollaborate cross-functionally with developers, system engineers, designers, and product managers — breaking QA out of silos.\nCoach the team on testing best practices and facilitate continuous improvement.\nEnsure traceability between requirements and tests, maintaining transparency on quality and risk.\nWhat will help you to fulfill your role\n\nTechnical Skills\n\nExtensive experience in quality assurance/testing with embedded systems and mobile applications (we are building with Flutter framework for Android Automotive).\nProven experience with distributed systems spanning embedded devices and backend services, preferably with AWS.\nExperience with Flutter and/or Android development/testing tools and frameworks.\nUnderstanding of UX principles and ability to identify usability issues\nFamiliarity with ALM tools (e.g. Polarion) for requirements management\nExperience with test automation frameworks, testing methodologies, and CI/CD integration\nExperience with testbench environments (HiL, ViL) and AI assisted development are valued.\nAwareness of automotive standards (ASPICE, ISO 26262) is a plus.\n\nSoft Skills\n\nProactive, quality-driven mindset with a strong focus on improving user experience.\nDetail-oriented, especially in ensuring UI/UX consistency and polish.\nEffective communicator across technical and non-technical stakeholders and the ability to coach teams to level up, not just finding bugs.\nComfortable navigating complexity and ambiguity, with a genuine interest in autonomous driving and passenger experience.\n\nWe welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds — even if you don\'t meet every requirement. If you\'re excited about the role and MOIA\'s mission, we\'d love to hear from you!\n\nOur benefits in a nutshell\nCompetitive salary (including bonus)\nHybrid work setup: Work from home or one of our offices - you and your team decide how often to meet, blending flexibility with collaboration!\nFlexible working hours and the possibility of flexible work arrangements depending on your needs (parenting, care work, volunteering, etc.)\nBudget and monthly expense allowance for home office setup\nPossibility of remote work from outside Germany for up to 6 weeks per year from over 35 countries - learn more in our blog!\nPublic transport ticket (fully subsidized \"Deutschlandticket\") for commuting and travelling throughout Germany and discount on MOIA rides\nSubsidized fitness club membership or bike leasing\nLearning environment with continuous learning days, job rotation, trainings and workshops, coaching, conferences, books, and language classes\nMental health support, 1:1 sessions with external professionals and mental unload workshops\n30 vacation days, sabbatical and unpaid leave option\nRelocation support with service provider (visa, administration, etc.)\nDog-friendly offices\n\nFor student & internship positions, we have an adjusted set of benefits. You can find them here.\n\nBe who you are!\n\nWe are a member of Charta der Vielfalt and are dedicated to actively fostering a workplace that celebrates and promotes diversity in various aspects such as age, gender identity, race, sexual orientation, physical or cognitive ability, and ethnicity. At MOIA, we embrace a culture where people are accepted, respected, valued, appreciated, and included.\n\nIn our commitment to promoting diversity and inclusivity, we regularly provide unconscious bias training to all our employees. Furthermore, we continuously strive to enhance our hiring process by ensuring a diverse hiring panel.\n\nHow we work\n\nAt MOIA, our teams are typically distributed across locations and collaborate in a hybrid setup. We work together both remotely and on site, choosing the mode of collaboration that fits the context, the work at hand, and each team\'s rhythm.\n\nSpending time together in our offices is an important part of how we stay connected, build trust, and solve complex problems. At the same time, we value flexibility and give teams and individuals autonomy to shape their ways of working, with everyone having the freedom to organise their routines in a way that aligns with their work and their team\'s needs.\n\nIf you\'d like to learn more about how we work, visit our blog for insights into our culture and hiring process, or follow us on Instagram for a look behind the scenes at MOIA.\n\nWho we are\n\nAt MOIA we\'re reimagining the future of mobility – safe, autonomous and tailored to the needs of cities and their people. As a tech company with more than 400 employees, we build mobility solutions that truly move cities forward.\n\nWe launched our ridepooling service in Hamburg in 2019 and have been part of the city\'s public transport system since 2023. Since launch, we have transported over 12 million passengers. Currently, MOIA is evolving from a mobility provider to a tech provider offering a scalable and safe turnkey solution for autonomous driving.\n\nWith office locations in Berlin and Hamburg, our diverse and international team comprising more than 60 nationalities works together toward that shared mission.\n\nMOIA is more than a technology provider – we are a partner to cities and public transport operators committed to creating more livable spaces and delivering mobility solutions that are reliable, safe and comfortable.\n\nYour application to MOIA\n\nWe value authenticity and personal insights in your application responses. While AI tools can be useful, we encourage you to answer the following questions based on your own experiences and understanding. This helps us keep a human touch and better evaluate your unique perspective and match for the role.\n\nTo reinforce an unbiased screening process, we kindly ask you not to include your picture, age, address, or any other details unrelated to your qualifications and suitability for the role. Additionally, we anonymize applications during the initial review phase by removing personally identifiable information. This ensures that our evaluation focuses solely on your skills, experience, and potential – supporting a fair and inclusive hiring experience for all candidates.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'MOIA','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=7151814a84162205','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2502,NULL,'job','Senior Applied Scientist - Demand Forecasting (all genders)','Vollzeit','Berlin',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Ort\nGermany - Berlin\nVertrag\nFull time\nJob-Kategorie\nApplied Science & Research\nTHE ROLE & THE TEAM\n\nZalando fulfills more than a hundred million customer orders every year and volumes are increasing. Fulfillment Core within Zalando builds and operates systems that are at the core of Zalando’s platform strategy and ensure timely, efficient, and correct delivery of every one of our customers’ 185+ million orders every year.\n\nEnabling the fulfillment of orders is a complex process, involving the choice of physical locations of our warehouses and the placement of stock, the planning of inner warehouse processes and capacity management, the management of a diverse range of fulfillment and delivery configurations, all while optimizing towards various competing targets.\n\nAt the core of this system is demand forecasting. Accurate predictions of customer demand determine not just what to stock, but where and how to store and move inventory across our operations.\n\nWe’re looking for a collaborative, thoughtful, and impact-driven Senior Applied Scientist to join our Fulfillment Core team. In this role, you’ll help build intelligent, large-scale forecasting models that influence how we plan, stock, and deliver fashion across Europe. You’ll work closely with other scientists, engineers, and business partners to co-create solutions that are both technically sound and deeply aligned with real-world needs.\n\nYou’ll find our Berlin campus and HQ in the vibrant area of Friedrichshain. With amazing views of the Spree river and East Side Gallery, it’s a campus designed to inspire. Berlin is the city that has shaped our business. Are you up for a new experience in one of the most vibrant, diverse, and green cities in Europe?\n\nINCLUSIVE BY DESIGN\n\nIf you think you have what it takes, we encourage you to apply even if you don\'t meet every single requirement. You may just be the right candidate for this or other roles!\n\nAt Zalando, our vision is to be the leading pan-European ecosystem for fashion and lifestyle e-commerce – one that thrives on diversity and is truly inclusive by design. We believe that diverse teams fuel innovation and creativity, and we actively seek out talent from all backgrounds.\n\nWe actively seek to reduce bias in our hiring and employment processes, focusing on your qualifications, skills, and contributions. To support this, we kindly ask that you refrain from including personal details such as your photo, age, or marital status in your CV, ensuring a fair and equitable evaluation based solely on your abilities and potential.\n\nWe are committed to providing an exceptional and accessible candidate experience for everyone. If you require any accommodations to support you throughout the hiring process, please let us know – we are here to assist you.\n\nDiscover more about our commitment to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace: https://jobs.zalando.com/en/our-culture/diversity-and-inclusion\n\nWHAT WE’D LOVE YOU TO DO (AND LOVE DOING)\n\nCollaborate with a cross-functional team of applied scientists, engineers, and analysts within the Fulfillment Core to design and develop robust, scalable, and accurate demand forecasting models using machine learning and deep learning techniques.\n\nWork hand-in-hand with engineering teams to bring your models into production - ensuring they’re robust, maintainable, and responsive to evolving needs.\n\nEngage openly with stakeholders to understand the challenges they face and identify how forecasting insights can empower better decisions.\n\nDesign and improve models serving diverse forecasting use cases at different levels of granularity, such as inventory allocation and predictive storage management.\n\nContribute to broader research efforts across the business unit, sharing insights and collaborating on exploratory initiatives.\n\nEngage with Zalando’s growing community of Applied Scientists through reading groups, knowledge-sharing sessions, and mentoring opportunities.\n\nWE’D LOVE TO MEET YOU IF…\n\nHands-on extensive experience in time-series forecasting within an industrial setting. Experience with large-scale forecasting applications is highly desirable.\n\nSolid understanding of machine learning and deep learning techniques applied to forecasting problems.\n\nAcademic background in a quantitative field such as computer science, engineering, mathematics, statistics, or a related discipline.\n\nProficiency in Python and ML libraries and frameworks such as PyTorch, TensorFlow, LightGBM, Scikit-learn, Pandas, and NumPy.\n\nFamiliarity with data-intensive systems and ML engineering tools, including PySpark, Databricks, AWS (e.g. SageMaker, S3), Airflow, MLflow, CI/CD, Docker, Git, and model versioning tools.\n\nA proactive and self-driven mindset with a strong sense of ownership and accountability.\n\nA team player with excellent collaboration skills who enjoys working with stakeholders to solve real-world challenges.\n\nComfort working in a diverse, inclusive, and international environment where English is the main language.\n\nOUR OFFER\n\nZalando provides a range of benefits, here’s an overview of what you can expect. Ask your Talent Acquisition Partner to learn more about what we offer.\n\n27 days of holiday a year to start for full-time employees (+1 day for every calendar year up to 30 days)\n\n2 paid volunteering days a year\n\nHybrid working model with up to 60% remote per week, actual practice is up to each team to best support their collaboration\n\nWork from abroad for up to 30 working days a year\n\nEmployee shares program\n\n40% off fashion and beauty products sold and shipped by Zalando, 30% off Lounge by Zalando, discounts from external partners\n\nRelocation assistance available (subject to prior agreement)\n\nFamily services, including counseling and support\n\nHealth and wellbeing options (including Wellhub, formerly Gympass)\n\nMental health support and coaching available\n\nDrive your development through our training platform and biannual peer-to-peer review\n\nRecruiter\n\nRafael Galiani\n\nrafael.galiani@zalando.de\n\n Nach der Prüfung werden unsere Recruiter*innen über eine offizielle Zalando E-Mail-Adresse (@zalando.de) Kontakt aufnehmen.\n\nIn einigen Fällen arbeiten wir auch mit einer Auswahl von Headhunter*innen und Agenturen zusammen, um bestimmte Positionen zu besetzen. Bitte beachte, dass weder Zalando noch unsere Rekrutierungspartner*innen irgendeine Art von Bezahlung verlangen, um sich für eine Stelle zu bewerben oder an einem Vorstellungsgespräch teilzunehmen.\nÜber Zalando\n\nZalando wurde 2008 in Berlin gegründet und ist die führende europäische Technologieplattform für Mode und Lifestyle. Wir verbinden 62 Millionen aktive Kund*innen mit mehr als 7.000 Marken in 29 Märkten. Unser Geschäft basiert auf einer einzigartigen, KI-gestützten Daten- und Infrastrukturplattform. Für unsere Kund*innen bietet unser Multi-App-Ansatz – bestehend aus Zalando, ABOUT YOU und Lounge by Zalando – ein inspirierendes, hochgradig personalisiertes Einkaufserlebnis. Für unsere Partner bauen wir das Betriebssystem für den E-Commerce. Über ZEOS, Tradebyte und SCAYLE öffnen wir unsere Logistik-, Software- und Servicekapazitäten für Marken und Einzelhändler*innen zur nahtlosen, grenzüberschreitenden Skalierung ihres Geschäfts.','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Zalando','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6ffb05ffbf21a049','scraped','vor 5 Tagen'),(2503,NULL,'job','(Associate) Consultant MLOps Engineering (m/w/d)','Festanstellung','53229 Bonn',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Bonn oder freie Arbeitsplatzwahl\nVollzeit\nFestanstellung\n\nDeine Aufgaben\nJe nach Bedarf im Kundenprojekt übernimmst du mehrere Rollen:\n\nAls technischer Experte für MLOps bist du der primäre Ansprechpartner für die technische Konzeption und Umsetzung der MLOps-Infrastrukturen und Automatisierungslösungen\nAls Implementierer / Engineer baust du Plattformen und Pipelines auf, konfigurierst Tools undschreibst den notwendigen Code (IaC, CI/CD-Konfigurationen, Automatisierungsskripte)\nAls Enabler / Unterstützer hilfst du Data-Science-Teams und anderen Stakeholdern bei unserenKunden, die MLOps-Plattformen und -Prozesse effektiv zu nutzen und ihre ML-Modelle erfolgreich in Produktion zu bringen\nAn der Schnittstelle zwischen Data Science, Softwareentwicklung (DevOps), IT-Betrieb und ggf.Security stimmst du technische Anforderungen ab, um Lösungen zu integrieren\nDeine Aufgaben\n\nDu verfolgst aktuelle Entwicklungen im Bereich MLOps und DevOps und lernst, neue Technologien zu bewerten und einzusetzen\nGemeinsam mit erfahrenen Kolleg:innen arbeitest du an der Konzeption, Entwicklung und Weiterentwicklung von MLOps-Plattformen – einschließlich des Designs der technischen Infrastruktur und Toolchains (z. B. basierend auf Kubeflow und Kubernetes) – zur Unterstützung und Automatisierung des gesamten Machine-Learning-Lifecycles\nDu unterstützt beim Deployment von ML-Modellen und wirkst an der Automatisierung von Workflows durch CI/CD-Pipelines (z. B. mit GitLab CI/CD oder GitHub Actions) mit – inklusive Troubleshooting und Support\nDu hilfst bei der Integration und dem Betrieb zentraler MLOps-Tools wie MLflow für Experiment Tracking, Model Registry und Deployment und lernst, diese in CI/CD-Prozesse einzubinden\nDu arbeitest bei der Implementierung von GitOps-Praktiken (z. B. mit Argo CD) zur automatisierten Auslieferung von Infrastruktur und Applikationen mit\nDu unterstützt beim Aufbau von Monitoring- und Logging-Lösungen, um Plattformen, Pipelines und produktive ML-Modelle zu überwachen\nGemeinsam mit Security-Teams wirkst du an der Umsetzung von DevSecOps-Praktiken mit (z. B. Container-Scanning, Secret Management, Zugriffskontrollen) und lernst, wie Sicherheit in automatisierte Prozesse integriert wird\nDein Profil\nDu hast dein Masterstudium oder deine Promotion in einem der MINT-Fächer erfolgreich abgeschlossen\nAls Consultant verfügst du über mindestens zwei Jahre relevante Berufserfahrung, idealerweise in der Rolle als (Associate) Consultant bei einer IT-Beratung\nDu beherrschst Python und hast erste Erfahrungen mit Automatisierungen und Integrationen von Machine-Learning-Komponenten\nDu arbeitest mit Bash- bzw. Shell-Skripting, insbesondere im Kontext von CI/CD-Pipelines und Infrastrukturaufgaben\nDu hast Erfahrung in der Containerisierung mit Docker\nIdealerweise kennst du dich mit Kubernetes aus – inklusive Administration, Netzwerkarchitekturen und Security Policies – und hast ein grundlegendes Verständnis von GitOps-Ansätzen und kennst Tools wie Argo CD oder FluxCD\nEs ist auch von Vorteil, wenn du dich mit MLOps-Plattformen wie Kubeflow, MLflow und Azure ML auskennst\nEin weiteres Plus ist es, wenn du praktische Erfahrungen mit mindestens einer großen Cloud-Plattform wie z. B. AWS, Azure oder Google Cloud (GCP) mitbringst und deren Kubernetes-Angebote (EKS, AKS, GKE) sowie relevante ML- und DevOps-Services kennst\nDu kommunizierst überzeugend und effizient in deutscher und englischer Sprache\nDu hast Spaß daran, in einem flexiblen Mix aus Homeoffice, an unserem Standort in Bonn und bei Kunden vor Ort zu arbeiten\nWarum wir?\nMit deinem Team stehst du unseren Kunden zur Seite und hilfst ihnen dabei, ihre Daten zu verstehen und die Erkenntnisse daraus gewinnbringend zu nutzen\nKundenprojekte nach dem Fließbandprinzip sind nicht unser Ding: Du arbeitest durchschnittlich an mindestens zwei Kundenprojekten gleichzeitig, sodass du dich intensiv mit den Anforderungen beschäftigen kannst und siehst, wie deine Lösungen ihre Wirkung entfalten\nAbwechslung im Arbeitsalltag bringt die Vielfalt unserer Kunden aller Branchen, vom großen Mittelstand bis zum DAX-Konzern\nMit deinen zukünftigen Kolleg:innen tauschst du dich fachlich auf Augenhöhe aus und erhältst Budget und Zeit für eure eigenen Innovationsprojekte\nDu wächst bei uns fachlich und persönlich durch speziell auf dich abgestimmte Weiterbildungen, Zertifizierungen und Laufbahnprogramme\nIn deinen Spezialgebieten kannst du deinen Schwerpunkt setzen und ausbauen\nNeben einem attraktiven Fixgehalt zzgl. Umsatz- und Ergebnisbeteiligung kannst du Überstunden ausgleichen und Reisezeiten als Arbeitszeit buchen\nDurch freie Wahl des Arbeitsorts und flexible Arbeitszeit gestaltest du deinen Arbeitsalltag passend zu deinem Lebensstil\nDich erwarten außerdem ein top ausgestatteter Arbeitsplatz, JobRad, Body & Mind Workout, GamesNights, Grillen auf unserer Dachterrasse, Team-Aktionen mit unternehmungslustigen Kolleg:innen, Sommerfeste mit deinen Familienmitgliedern und viele weitere Benefits','2026-05-07 01:37:30','open',0,'Comma Soft AG','https://de.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8882bd71e04258c3','scraped','vor 10 Tagen'),(2504,NULL,'job','Grow Officer','Permanent','Belgian Gardens QLD 4810',NULL,'',3586.50,'$34.00 - $37.73 an hour','AI Job Summary\nWilling to complete a fully funded Certificate IV in Community Services or Diploma in Financial Counselling.\nUnderstand Indigenous cultures and communicate effectively with community.\nHave Microsoft Word/Excel skills (or willingness to learn).\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nOn-site • Permanent • Full-time • Entry Level\nPay Rate\n34 AUD – 37.73 AUD (Hour)\nDescription\nGrow Officer – Townsville\n\nIndigenous Consumer Assistance Network (ICAN)\n\nEmpower your community. Build financial resilience. Create real change in Townsville and on Palm Island.\n\nKick-start a meaningful career in community services with ICAN. We’re looking for a motivated Townsville Local who wants to help strengthen financial wellbeing, support families, and contribute to long-term community empowerment.\n\nWhat We Offer\nCompetitive salary and benefits\nFull-time role with an early finish every Friday\n5 weeks annual leave\nGifted time between Christmas and New Year\nOngoing paid professional development\nFully funded traineeship (Certificate IV or Diploma)\nA supportive team who are committed to your success\n\nThis is an Identified Position and is open only to Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander people, as permitted under section 25 of the Anti-Discrimination Act 1991 (Qld).\n\nAbout Us\n\nThe Indigenous Consumer Assistance Network (ICAN) is a not-for-profit organisation supporting Indigenous peoples across Queensland through financial counselling, financial capability programs and consumer advocacy.\n\nOur mission, “Empowering Indigenous Consumers,” guides everything we do from frontline service delivery to systemic advocacy aimed at improving laws and industry practices.\n\nICAN delivers services in Cairns, Townsville, Atherton, and several remote communities. We are now expanding opportunities on Palm Island, and we are committed to training, supporting, and developing a Palm Island local to grow into this important role.\n\nWhy This Opportunity Is Perfect\n\nThis is more than a job—it’s a pathway to a meaningful career. As a Grow Officer, you will:\n\nGain real hands-on experience working with community members\nBuild confidence and professional capability at your pace\nReceive ongoing mentorship from experienced ICAN staff\nHelp strengthen financial resilience on Palm Island\nStudy towards a Certificate IV in Community Services or Diploma of Financial Counselling, fully funded by ICAN\n\nWhether you’re looking for a long-term career or a stepping stone into broader community service work, this traineeship gives you the skills and support to succeed.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nAs a Grow Officer, you will support financial wellbeing work in Townsville and on Palm Island through:\n\nTraining & Qualification\nComplete a fully funded Cert IV or Diploma\nLearn alongside ICAN’s experienced financial counsellors and capability workers\nDevelop practical knowledge you can use immediately in community\nFinancial Literacy & Client Support\nSupport clients with budgeting, financial education and accessing grants\nHelp community members understand bills, debt, consumer rights and financial options\nCommunity Connection\nBuild relationships with local services, Elders, community groups and support networks\nWork in a culturally safe, strengths-based way\nClient Empowerment\nAssist clients to access essential services, financial products and government supports\nReporting & Program Support\nCollect basic data to help ICAN understand community needs and demonstrate outcomes\nWho We’re Looking For\nEssential Criteria\nIdentifies as Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander, is of Indigenous descent and accepted by the community\nIs excited to complete a Certificate IV in Community Services or Diploma in Financial Counselling\nHas sound LLN skills (extra support available if needed)\nUnderstands Indigenous cultures and communicates effectively with community\nHas a positive attitude, willingness to learn and a strong sense of community pride\nSkills & Knowledge\nEager to learn new skills and grow professionally\nPassionate about helping others in a respectful and non-judgmental way\nBasic computer skills (Microsoft Word/Excel or willingness to learn)\nInterest in financial resilience and community support work\nWhy Join ICAN?\nStart your career with practical skills, qualifications and ongoing mentoring\nWork in a role that directly supports Townsville and Palm Island community members\nChoose from two clear career pathways financial capability or financial counselling\nBe part of a supportive organisation committed to Indigenous leadership and community empowerment\nSelection Criteria\n\nPlease provide short responses to the following in your cover letter:\n\nUnderstanding of Indigenous Cultures Describe your connection to Indigenous Culture and how this will help you engage with community members.\nInterest in the Role Tell us why you are interested in a traineeship in financial capability or financial counselling.\nTeamwork Skills Share an example of working with others to achieve a goal (work, school, sport, community—anything is fine).\nBasic Computer Skills Explain your experience with Microsoft Word, Excel or similar programs (or your willingness to learn).\n\nSimple, clear responses are welcome we want to get to know you.\n\nHow to Apply\n\nPlease upload:\n\nCovering Letter (max 2 pages) addressing the selection criteria\nResume (max 4 pages) including two referees contactable by phone and email\nImportant Notes\nShortlisting is based on your responses to the selection criteria\nApplicants who do not address the criteria will be ineligible for interview\nProvide examples where possible (work, community, personal experiences)\n\nICAN is an Equal Employment Opportunity employer and uses merit-based selection to ensure the best person for the role.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f3b93f11aa8ff763','scraped','Just posted'),(2505,NULL,'job','Zabbix Consultant','Permanent','Carlton VIC',NULL,'',95000.00,'From $95,000 a year','*Company Description*\n\nOpasa is dedicated to empowering businesses by enhancing their technology capabilities and driving measurable growth through innovative solutions. With expertise in four core areas—Data/AI, Cloud, Cyber Security, and Digitization of customer journeys and business processes—Opasa offers consulting, advisory services, program management, and staff augmentation. Recognized as a trusted partner, Opasa helps solve complex IT challenges and supports the achievement of strategic business objectives. Clients rely on Opasa\'s technical expertise and strategic insight to deliver tangible results.\n\n*Role Description*\n\nOpasa is seeking an experienced IT Zabbix Consultant for a full-time, on-site role in the Greater Melbourne Area. The Consultant will be responsible for designing, implementing, and maintaining Zabbix monitoring solutions to address business and operational needs. Daily tasks include consulting with stakeholders, configuring and troubleshooting Zabbix systems, performing technical support, analyzing system performance, and ensuring efficient IT operations. The role requires close collaboration with clients and internal teams to deliver effective monitoring and IT solutions.\n\n*Qualifications*\n\n* 6+ years Experience in IT Consulting and Consulting with the ability to provide strategic guidance to clients\n* Hands-on experience and skills with IT monitoring systems, ideally Zabbix.\n* Understanding of monitoring metrics for compute and network devices.\n* Strong Linux and IP network skills work experience required to work in Specialized Networks.\n* Motivated and able to learn complex IT systems without significant guidance.\n* Able to work constructively in a team with varying skills and capabilities\n* Strong Analytical Skills and proficiency in assessing systems to deliver optimized solutions\n* Practical experience and deep understanding of Information Technology and Technical Support\n* Exceptional problem-solving abilities and attention to detail\n* Proficient communication and collaboration skills for effective stakeholder engagement\n* Experience with Zabbix is preferred.\n* Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field is preferred\n* Relevant certifications in monitoring tools or IT consulting are a plus\n\nWork Location: Melbourne,AUS\n\nEmployment type: Permanent FTE role\n\nPreferred Visas: PR\'s , AU, NZ Citizens\n\nSalary packages: As per market standard\n\nJob Types: Full-time, Permanent\n\nPay: From $95,000.00 per year\n\nBenefits:\n* Referral program\n* Work from home\n\nWork Location: In person','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Opasa Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d32704cc738b90da','scraped','Just posted'),(2506,NULL,'job','Data Product Manager (12 Month Fixed Term)','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'See yourself in our team\n\nRetail Advanced Analytics and Data (RAAD) partners closely with Retail Banking Services to enable best practice across data, advanced analytics, and AI. The team plays a key role in shaping data‑led decision making across the Everyday Banking domain, delivering trusted, well‑governed data products that support customers, colleagues, and the broader business.\n\nYou will join a diverse community of data and analytics professionals who combine strong technical capability with business context to solve meaningful problems at scale.\n\nDo work that matters\n\nThis opportunity is available as a 12‑month fixed‑term contract or internal secondment.\n\nAs a Data Product Manager, you will support the execution of the domain data strategy and own the delivery, governance, and lifecycle management of high‑quality, reusable data products and data assets. You will help ensure data is discoverable, trustworthy, and fit‑for‑purpose, while meeting Group standards across data management, security, privacy, and record‑keeping.\n\nThe role has a strong focus on enabling ethical and effective use of data and AI, recognising that data quality and governance directly influence outcomes.\n\nMore specifically, you will:\n\nSupport execution of the domain data strategy aligned to business priorities and outcomes\n\nOwn the delivery, governance, and lifecycle of reusable Data Products and Data Assets, including business‑critical data, in line with Group policies\n\nDefine Data Products with clear business context and metadata to ensure discoverability, reuse, trust, and interoperability\n\nEnsure compliance with Group standards across enterprise semantics, metadata, data lineage, retention, and disposal\n\nChampion continuous improvement of the data estate, including modernisation, rationalisation, optimisation, and transition to strategic consumption pathways\n\nEmbed strong data management practices that enable effective and ethical use of data and AI\n\nPartner with Crew Leads, Tech Leads, Delivery Product Owners, and CIO teams to deliver data product roadmaps\n\nEnable effective data producer–consumer collaboration across Business Units and Support Units\n\nEnsure Data Products comply with Group Information Security and Privacy policies\n\nSet, monitor, and maintain data quality standards, including usage and quality metrics\n\nDrive uplift and remediation where Data Products no longer meet required standards\n\nDefine and manage appropriate access and usage of Data Products and Data Assets\n\nPromote data literacy and adoption of Group data management best practices\n\nWe’re interested in hearing from people who have:\n\n8+ years’ experience across data management, data governance, data engineering, or control frameworks\n\nProven experience delivering enterprise‑scale data initiatives in complex or regulated environments\n\nA strong data product mindset, aligned to business outcomes\n\nExperience engaging and influencing stakeholders across business and technology teams\n\nPassion for building capability, fostering collaboration, and driving continuous improvement\n\nExperience supporting data cloud migration and exposure to the AWS ecosystem (desirable)\n\nTech skills\n\nStrong background in data management, data engineering, stewardship, and large‑scale data platforms\n\nExperience designing, deploying, and operating solutions in AWS or Snowflake environments\n\nHands‑on experience with language such as Python, SQL and tools like Alation, AWS Data Exchange, Glue and AWS integration services\n\nExposure to version control and CI/CD pipelines (for example, GitHub) is desirable\n\nQualifications\n\nBachelor’s degree in Engineering, or\n\nMaster’s degree in Computer Science or a related discipline\n\nIf you\'re already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest, x15ventures), you\'ll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We’re keen to support you with the next step in your career.\n\nWe\'re aware of some accessibility issues on this site, particularly for screen reader users. We want to make finding your dream job as easy as possible, so if you require additional support please contact HR Direct on 1800 989 696.\n\nAdvertising End Date: 17/05/2026','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Commonwealth Bank','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=36874ede6069c7af','scraped','Just posted'),(2507,NULL,'job','English Tutor','Part-time','Chatswood NSW 2067',NULL,'',65.00,'$40 - $90 an hour','Are you passionate about education and eager to be part of Australia’s most innovative hybrid teaching company?\n\nAt *Realus Education*, we combine *Human Expertise × AI Intelligence* to deliver a next-generation learning experience for students from *Year 1 to Year 12*.\n\nRealus is part of *First Education & Technology Group Pty Ltd*, founded in 2009. With campuses in *Box Hill (Melbourne), Glen Waverley (Melbourne)* and *Chatswood (Sydney)*, and our award-winning AI platform *MarsLadder*, we are redefining how children learn – blending face-to-face teaching with intelligent, personalised AI support.\n\n*Our Achievements*\n\nSince *2009*, First Education & Technology Group has helped *over 10,000 K–12 students* achieve their academic goals.\n\nFrom *2016 to 2024*, more than *20% of our senior students* achieved an *ATAR of 99.00+*, and across *nine consecutive years*, we proudly nurtured *25 ATAR 99.95 top scorers*.\n\nMany of our students have gone on to win *scholarships*, gain entry to *selective schools*, and secure places in *Australia’s top universities* — making Realus Education a trusted choice for ambitious learners and families.\n\n*Why Join Us*\n\n✅ *Be part of an EdTech pioneer* – MarsLadder is recognised as a finalist for the *Bett Awards, The EdTech Awards, and GESS Education Awards*.\n\n✅ *Clear career pathway* – Tutor → Senior Tutor → *Mentor* → *Campus Director*.\n\n✅ *Equity opportunities* – Mentors and Campus Directors are eligible to join our *company equity option pool* and share in the company’s growth.\n\n✅ *Supportive culture* – Warm, inclusive team with strong training and development support.\n\n✅ *Cutting-edge teaching tools* – Teach alongside an advanced AI platform that automates feedback, tracks student progress, and enhances every lesson.\n\n*Your Role*\n\nAs a Y1–Y6 English Tutor/Lecturer at Realus, you will:\n\n· Deliver engaging lessons that spark curiosity and build strong foundations in English.\n\n· Teach not only enrichment classes, but also exam-focused programs (e.g. Scholarship, Selective School and OC) where required.\n\n· Use MarsLadder AI to create a seamless after-class learning loop – guiding students from explanation to practice, feedback, and mastery.\n\n· Provide constructive feedback to parents and collaborate with the teaching team to improve lesson materials.\n\n· Actively contribute to our mentor-led training system, sharing insights and improving our hybrid teaching model.\n\n· Inspire students with positivity, patience, and energy.\n\n*What We’re Looking For*\n\n· *Strong communication skills in English*, with the ability to teach in full English.\n\n· *Passion for education* and the ability to teach in a lively, inspiring, and student-friendly way.\n\n· Willingness to learn and integrate AI tools into teaching.\n\n· Attention to detail, professionalism, and a high standard of work.\n\n· Experience in teaching exam-focused programs (e.g. Scholarship, Selective, OC, AMC) is highly regarded.\n\n· Previous K–6 enrichment or tutoring experience preferred.\n\n· Must hold (or be able to obtain) a *Working With Children Check* (Employee type).\n\n· Availability to teach weekend classes.\n\n*Benefits & Perks*\n\n· ✅ Warm and inclusive work environment.\n\n· ✅ Competitive salary and bonus structure.\n\n· ✅ Clear promotion pathway leading to Mentor and Campus Director positions.\n\n· ✅ Eligibility to join the *company equity option pool* at senior levels.\n\n· ✅ Comprehensive training program (“Firestarter Plan”) – learn our *AI-powered teaching workflows, class engagement techniques, and company culture*.\n\n*How to Apply*\n\nWe value *teaching quality, professionalism, and cultural fit*. Our recruitment process is designed to ensure every tutor we hire meets the highest standards.\n\n*1 Initial Phone Call* – We will contact shortlisted candidates for a brief phone conversation to understand your background, subject expertise, and availability.\n\n*2 Demo Assignment *– You will receive an email with *Demo instructions* (prepare a 10–15 minute teaching video)\n\n*3 Demo Video Submission* – Record and submit your *10–15 minute demo video* for evaluation.\n\n*4 Panel Review* – All of our full-time lecturers will review your demo to assess your teaching style, clarity, and engagement. *Only candidates who pass this stage will move forward.*\n\n*5 On-Site Interview & Trial Lesson* – Selected candidates will be invited for a *30-minute on-site trial lesson*, where we evaluate your live teaching ability and classroom presence.\n\n*6 Final Evaluation & Offer* – Successful candidates will receive an official offer to join *Realus Education* as part of our tutor team.\n\n*Apply now* by sending your CV to *Chatswood@realus.com.au* with the subject line *“Y1–Y12 Tutor Application”*.\n\nJob Types: Full-time, Part-time, Casual\n\nPay: $40.00 – $90.00 per hour\n\nWork Location: In person','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Realus Education Chatswood','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=0ca07c87d20e1fa0','scraped','Just posted'),(2508,NULL,'job','Student Work Experience – Digital Marketing and Community','Part-time','Surry Hills NSW 2010',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'*Job Title: Student Work Experience – Digital Marketing and Community*\n\n*Location:* Sydney NSW (Hybrid) *Job Type:* Vocational / Work Experience\n\n*Role Overview:* We are offering a structured work experience placement for a student passionate about digital storytelling and community building. This placement provides a unique opportunity to learn how a startup builds a national brand identity across multiple social platforms.\n\n*Educational & Learning Outcomes:*\n\n* *Multi-Channel Strategy:* Learn how to establish and synchronize a brand voice across Instagram, Facebook, LinkedIn, and RedNote.\n* *Growth Marketing:* Study the mechanics of membership acquisition and community engagement within the student demographic.\n* *Digital Content Creation:* Gain experience using Canva and AI-driven creative tools to develop professional marketing assets.\n* *Forum Moderation:* Learn community management best practices using the Discourse platform.\n\n*Requirements:*\n\n* Current student in Marketing, Communications, or Digital Media.\n* Active interest in social media trends and community-led growth.\n* Enthusiastic about using AI to enhance creative workflows.\n\n*Placement Structure:* Highly flexible remote-first structure (up to 8 hours per week). This is a non-salaried role for students looking to build a professional portfolio or meet course requirements. Travel and meal expenses for Sydney-based collaboration sessions are reimbursed.\n\nBenefits:\n* Employee mentoring program\n* Work from home\n\nWork Location: Hybrid remote in Surry Hills NSW 2010','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'International Students Movement Inc.','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=fb306d2659675869','scraped','Just posted'),(2509,NULL,'job','Services Solution Architect - COE','Full-time','Deakin ACT 2600',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We help the world run better\nAt SAP, we keep it simple: you bring your best to us, and we\'ll bring out the best in you. We\'re builders touching over 20 industries and 80% of global commerce, and we need your unique talents to help shape what\'s next. The work is challenging – but it matters. You\'ll find a place where you can be yourself, prioritize your wellbeing, and truly belong. What\'s in it for you? Constant learning, skill growth, great benefits, and a team that wants you to grow and succeed.\n\nLead the Future of ERP Migrations – Join Our Centre of Excellence\n\nAre you passionate about the power of the cloud? Are you ready to help Australia\'s public sector unlock greater efficiency and productivity through smarter ERP migrations?\n\nJoin SAP and lead a bold new initiative that’s redefining how key government agencies move to the cloud.\n\nWith the creation of a Centre of Excellence (CoE) for Federal Australian Agencies we’re building a high-performance team to guide major agencies through the how of ERP migration — with proven strategy, expert delivery, and scalable, lasting impact.\n\nInitially, an 18-month transformation program, this high-profile, strategic initiative will be the successful candidate’s initial assignment, before transitioning into the broader Customer Success and Delivery area to extend the best practices and knowledge gained there.\n\nThis is your chance to set new industry benchmarks and drive real transformation where it matters most.\n\nPlease note - This role is base in Canberra and given the role works with Australian Public Sector - Australian Citizens with the capability to secure and maintain government security clearance are preferred.\n\nAbout the Role:\nThis is a role for a highly respected and senior resource with strong solution knowledge and deep implementation experience, capable of designing, driving and rationalising solutions to support customer outcomes. The Services Solutioning Architect is essential to translate customer expectations into a sellable and deliverable compelling proposal based on CS&D Portfolio and in close coordination with Subject Matter Experts and all Sales teams (Services Sales, Industry Account Executives and Solution Sales Specialists).\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nOrchestrate the overall solution to meet the customer requirements, addressing solution and implementation approach, completing effort and cost estimates for the proposed solution, leveraging and coordinating input from subject matter experts as required. Formulate the solution details including timelines, approach, scope, risks and assumptions. Take into account various delivery options considering, scope, cost, quality and risk.\n\nContribute actively towards the development of Business Cases for clients\n\nWork collaboratively with clients to solution and generate Rough Order of Magnitude estimates\n\nConsolidation of all requirements and inputs from multiple SME’s into a single solution response, including completion of solutioning details in a Deal Sheet and Scope Document.\n\nAlign and engage all stakeholders required for Deal Execution – including Delivery, Risk, Bid Management, License and Commercial Finance.\n\nAct as a Single Point of Contact (SPOC) for the collation and overall design of the solution bid response or pro-active proposal.\n\nProvide input to the services sales strategy for each opportunity, acting as part of the overall bid team.\n\nLiaise and coordinate with other knowledgeable resources including Delivery, Practice Leads, other Solutioning Team members, Lines of Service and Industry experts as necessary to ensure delivery feasibility.\n\nEngage with Adoption Solution Centre (ASC) as necessary where they are engaged to support the bid response.\n\nWillingness to extend knowledge to other solution areas, especially the SAP cloud offerings, to a level satisfactory to support initial service solutioning for opportunities.\n\nEnsure the effective positioning and usage of relevant Service Portfolio items in the solution.\n\nUnderstand the RISE with SAP methodology for Cloud deployments.\n\nSupport and reflect relevant regional and global services strategies into the services deals.\n\nResponsible for contribution of services solution content to the proposal response, including reviewing, writing, or editing, aligned with the proposal win themes.\n\nProactively identify opportunities for the cross selling of services.\n\nCommunication and handover of the solution design to the project delivery team, supporting the initial stage of project execution.\n\nParticipate in and support regional Solutioning community (knowledge share and contributions).\n\nExperience:\n\nThe applicant should be highly experienced with at least 5 years implementation and have fully participated in multiple full cycle implementations. A thorough understanding of SAP project methodologies for Cloud is necessary.\n\nThe applicant should have experience in building Value Based business cases.\n\nApplicant should have significant experience in project estimation methodologies.\n\nApplicant should have significant exposure to the services sales process, and have been involved in successful services sales campaigns.\n\nIdeally have deep experience in more than one functional solution area, with some broader knowledge of some other solution suite areas.\n\nIdeally have knowledge of SAP’s Premium Engagement Services and Cloudify Services portfolio.\n\nBring out your best\nSAP innovations help more than four hundred thousand customers worldwide work together more efficiently and use business insight more effectively. Originally known for leadership in enterprise resource planning (ERP) software, SAP has evolved to become a market leader in end-to-end business application software and related services for database, analytics, intelligent technologies, and experience management. As a cloud company with two hundred million users and more than one hundred thousand employees worldwide, we are purpose-driven and future-focused, with a highly collaborative team ethic and commitment to personal development. Whether connecting global industries, people, or platforms, we help ensure every challenge gets the solution it deserves. At SAP, you can bring out your best.\n\nWe win with inclusion\nSAP’s culture of inclusion, focus on health and well-being, and flexible working models help ensure that everyone – regardless of background – feels included and can run at their best. At SAP, we believe we are made stronger by the unique capabilities and qualities that each person brings to our company, and we invest in our employees to inspire confidence and help everyone realize their full potential. We ultimately believe in unleashing all talent and creating a better world.\n\nSAP is committed to the values of Equal Employment Opportunity and provides accessibility accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are interested in applying for employment with SAP and are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to Recruiting Operations Team: Careers@sap.com.\n\nFor SAP employees: Only permanent roles are eligible for the SAP Employee Referral Program, according to the eligibility rules set in the SAP Referral Policy. Specific conditions may apply for roles in Vocational Training.\n\nQualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to their age, race, religion, national origin, ethnicity, gender (including pregnancy, childbirth, et al), sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, protected veteran status, or disability, in compliance with applicable federal, state, and local legal requirements.\n\nSuccessful candidates might be required to undergo a background verification with an external vendor.\n\nAI Usage in the Recruitment Process\n\nFor information on the responsible use of AI in our recruitment process, please refer to our Guidelines for Ethical Usage of AI in the Recruiting Process.\n\nPlease note that any violation of these guidelines may result in disqualification from the hiring process.\n\nRequisition ID: 435499 | Work Area: Consulting and Professional Services | Expected Travel: 0 - 30% | Career Status: Professional | Employment Type: Regular Full Time | Locations: Canberra | #LI-Hybrid','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'SAP','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ef121535abec402c','scraped','Just posted'),(2510,NULL,'job','Data Product Manager','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'See yourself in our team\n\nRetail Advanced Analytics and Data (RAAD) partners closely with Retail Banking Services to enable best practice across data, advanced analytics, and AI. The team plays a key role in shaping data‑led decision making across the Everyday Banking domain, delivering trusted, well‑governed data products that support customers, colleagues, and the broader business.\n\nYou will join a diverse community of data and analytics professionals who combine strong technical capability with business context to solve meaningful problems at scale.\n\nDo work that matters\n\nAs a Data Product Manager, you will support the execution of the domain data strategy and own the delivery, governance, and lifecycle management of high‑quality, reusable data products and data assets. You will help ensure data is discoverable, trustworthy, and fit‑for‑purpose, while meeting Group standards across data management, security, privacy, and record‑keeping.\n\nThe role has a strong focus on enabling ethical and effective use of data and AI, recognising that data quality and governance directly influence outcomes.\n\nMore specifically, you will:\n\nSupport execution of the domain data strategy aligned to business priorities and outcomes\nOwn the delivery, governance, and lifecycle of reusable Data Products and Data Assets, including business‑critical data, in line with Group policies\nDefine Data Products with clear business context and metadata to ensure discoverability, reuse, trust, and interoperability\nEnsure compliance with Group standards across enterprise semantics, metadata, data lineage, retention, and disposal\nChampion continuous improvement of the data estate, including modernisation, rationalisation, optimisation, and transition to strategic consumption pathways\nEmbed strong data management practices that enable effective and ethical use of data and AI\nPartner with Crew Leads, Tech Leads, Delivery Product Owners, and CIO teams to deliver data product roadmaps\nEnable effective data producer–consumer collaboration across Business Units and Support Units\nEnsure Data Products comply with Group Information Security and Privacy policies\nSet, monitor, and maintain data quality standards, including usage and quality metrics\nDrive uplift and remediation where Data Products no longer meet required standards\nDefine and manage appropriate access and usage of Data Products and Data Assets\nPromote data literacy and adoption of Group data management best practices\n\nWe’re interested in hearing from people who have:\n\n8+ years’ experience across data management, data governance, data engineering, or control frameworks\nProven experience delivering enterprise‑scale data initiatives in complex or regulated environments\nA strong data product mindset, aligned to business outcomes\nExperience engaging and influencing stakeholders across business and technology teams\nPassion for building capability, fostering collaboration, and driving continuous improvement\nExperience supporting data cloud migration and exposure to the AWS ecosystem (desirable)\n\nTech skills\n\nStrong background in data management, data engineering, stewardship, and large‑scale data platforms\nExperience designing, deploying, and operating solutions in AWS or Snowflake environments\nHands‑on experience with language such as Python, SQL and tools like Alation, AWS Data Exchange, Glue and AWS integration services\nExposure to version control and CI/CD pipelines (for example, GitHub) is desirable\n\nQualifications\n\nBachelor’s degree in Engineering, or\nMaster’s degree in Computer Science or a related discipline\n\nIf you\'re already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest, x15ventures), you\'ll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We’re keen to support you with the next step in your career.\n\nWe\'re aware of some accessibility issues on this site, particularly for screen reader users. We want to make finding your dream job as easy as possible, so if you require additional support please contact HR Direct on 1800 989 696.\n\nAdvertising End Date: 17/05/2026','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Commonwealth Bank','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=82fc2bd516d07b2f','scraped','Just posted'),(2511,NULL,'job','Marketing Assistant','','Dandenong VIC 3175',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Starting your marketing career and want real responsibility from day one? This is not a “sit and observe” role. It is hands on, fast moving, and gives you exposure across the full marketing mix.\n\nWe are looking for a Marketing Assistant to join our commercial team in Melbourne, Australia.\n\nYou will play a key role in supporting the delivery and maintenance of sales and marketing materials, and bring both internal and customer-facing initiatives to life - all while building practical experience across digital content, events and marketing operations.\n\nThis role is ideal for someone early in their career who wants to learn quickly, contribute meaningfully, and be part of a collaborative and growing business.\n\nWhat you will be doing\n\nYou will be working closely with both marketing and sales, supporting a wide range of activities:\n\nCreate and update marketing and sales materials such as presentations, brochures, banners and digital content\n\nWrite and edit internal and customer-facing communications, product and website content.\n\nKeep our marketing assets, templates, and image libraries organised and up to date\n\nSupport the sales team with proposals, presentations and client communications\n\nMaintain CRM data and enquiry tracking to ensure accuracy and usability\n\nUpdate website content using our CMS\n\nHelp plan and execute events and internal initiatives\n\nCoordinate with external partners and suppliers to deliver marketing materials\n\nEnsure brand consistency across everything we produce\n\nSupport general coordination and admin tasks where needed\n\nWhat you bring\n\nYou do not need years of experience, but you do need curiosity, structure, and drive:\n\nComfortable using Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint\n\nFamiliar with tools like Adobe Creative Suite (Illustrator, InDesign, Photoshop), Canva or Adobe Express\n\nBasic video editing skills are a plus\n\nStrong attention to detail and ability to stay organised across multiple tasks\n\nA proactive mindset and willingness to take initiative\n\nClear communication skills and a professional approach\n\nAbility to work in a fast paced environment and manage deadlines\n\nA positive attitude and openness to learning\n\nWhy this role\n\nThis is a great opportunity to build real marketing experience across multiple disciplines, not just one niche. You will work closely with experienced colleagues, get exposure to commercial decision making, and see how marketing directly supports business growth.\n\nThere are no management responsibilities in this role, but there is strong potential to grow your skills and develop your career as the business evolves.\n\nAbout the role and structure\n\nThis position is part of Safer Storage Systems (SSS) and currently follows established ways of working within that business. As integration with Element Logic continues, the role may evolve over time to align with the wider organisation.\n\nIf you are looking for a role where you can learn fast, contribute from day one, and build a strong foundation in marketing, we would like to hear from you.\n\nFor further questions about the position or process, contact by email to Vice President Talent Acquisition & Employer Branding: beate.hall-hofso@elementlogic.net.\n\nAgency notice: We’re proud to handle all our recruitment in-house at Element Logic. That means we don’t accept candidates or approaches from external recruiters or headhunters. All hiring processes are managed exclusively by our own specialized Talent Acquisition team.\n\nBe yourself, in your element.\n\nAt Element Logic, our people are our greatest resource. We believe individuals should be in their element and we recognize, celebrate, and nurture the strength of diversity. We offer equal opportunities and welcome applicants regardless of age, race, ethnicity, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, language, national origin, mental and physical abilities, religious and political affiliations, stage of life, or family circumstances. We desire a work environment where people flourish with their unique abilities, perspectives, and life experiences.\n\nAbout Element Logic\nElement Logic is a global technology company specializing in intelligent warehouse automation. Since its founding in 1985, the company has grown to employ over 950 people across 30 countries and has established itself as the first - and leading - AutoStore partner worldwide.\n\nRenowned for its commitment to innovation and people-centric approach, Element Logic enhances warehouse performance through a unique combination of cutting-edge technology, AI-powered software, and tailor-made solutions. This enables businesses across industries to improve efficiency, accuracy, and scalability in their logistics operations.\n\nWith a proven track record and deep expertise in intralogistics, Element Logic has become the go-to partner for organizations seeking to gain a competitive edge through automation. The company’s culture is rooted in bravery, passion, and reliability - qualities that continue to drive its mission of optimizing warehouse performance. In 2024, Element Logic reported revenue of EUR 549 million.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Element Logic','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=88e2956b9d719b53','scraped','Just posted'),(2512,NULL,'job','Vocational Placement – Events and Business Development','Part-time','Surry Hills NSW 2010',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'*Job Title: Vocational Placement – Events and Business Development*\n\n*Location:* Sydney NSW (Hybrid) *Job Type:* Vocational / Work Experience\n\n*Role Overview:* This is a structured vocational placement designed for a current tertiary student seeking to complete industry-relevant experience as part of their studies. You will be mentored by the founders of ISM (www.ism.org.au), an organization dedicated to improving the international student experience in Australia. This placement focuses on the strategic planning and logistics of a major brand launch in Sydney.\n\n*Educational & Learning Outcomes:*\n\n* *Event Management:* Observe and participate in the end-to-end planning of launch events.\n* *Stakeholder Engagement:* Gain exposure to identifying and communicating with potential corporate sponsors and venue partners.\n* *AI-First Operations:* Learn how to utilize emerging AI technologies (Gemini, ChatGPT, and automation tools) to optimize business research and event logistics.\n* *Networking:* Develop professional connections within the Sydney business and student services sector.\n\n*Requirements:*\n\n* Currently enrolled in a relevant course (Marketing, Business, or Event Management) at a Sydney-based institution.\n* A proactive interest in supporting the international student community.\n* Familiarity with modern AI productivity tools.\n\n*Placement Structure:* Flexible hours (up to 8 hours per week) designed to integrate with your academic calendar. This placement is a non-salaried vocational position; however, all work-related travel and meal expenses for in-person workshops are fully reimbursed.\n\nBenefits:\n* Employee mentoring program\n* Work from home\n\nWork Location: Hybrid remote in Surry Hills NSW 2010','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'International Students Movement Inc.','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2a895d8e702c1b7f','scraped','Just posted'),(2513,NULL,'job','Senior Environmental Advisor - 1-year Tenure','Full-time','Alligator Creek QLD 4816',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'AI Job Summary\n4+ years on a mine site in an environmental role with responsibilities including monitoring, reporting, and managing env\nCoordinate and prepare internal and external environmental reports.\nBasic knowledge of Environmental Management Systems, including interpreting monitoring results against standards.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nOn-site • Contract • Full-time • Mid-level Senior\nDescription\n\nSenior Environmental Advisor – Senior Environmental Advisor – 1-year Tenure with possibility of extension\n\nThis exciting role is reporting to the Environment Superintendent, and you will be part of an outstanding team of dynamic environment, approvals, and community professionals, committed to high performance.\n\nKey Responsibilities Include:\n\nAn absolute commitment to working safely, complying with all site safety standards and ensuring a safe and environmentally healthy workplace is essential.\nCoordinate and track monitoring and sampling for Air, Surface water, Groundwater Soils, Sediments, potable water and wastewater.\nAssessment of results against standards\nParticipation and input into the ongoing development and implementation of the site’s Environmental Management System, including the development of Work Instructions and Procedures and assisting with Plans\nCoordinate reporting programs involving NGERS, NPI, weekly/monthly reporting, DES waste reporting and Permit Returns\nManaging, investigating, and reporting on environmental incidents\nProviding general environmental advice and assistance to the site operations\nCoordinating and development of environmental projects\nAssist EAC department and others as required.\nLearning and growing with our team, sharing your ideas and being part of creating innovative solutions to complex issues\n\nAbout you:\n\nEssential\n\nA passion to excel as an environmental professional.\n4+ years’ experience working on a mine (preferably metalliferous) site in an environmental role with similar responsibilities\nStrong commitment and focus on achieving positive environmental and safety outcomes.\nTertiary qualification(s) in environmental science or closely related disciplines.\nHigh level of attention to detail, an ability to interpret data and problem solve.\nBasic knowledge of Environmental Management Systems\nExperienced at coordinating and preparing internal and external reports\nA current manual drivers’ licence approved in Queensland.\nExperience in managing environmental consultants and contractors\nWell-developed written and verbal communication skills\nAbility to deliver quality work within tight deadlines\nAbility to work both independently and as part of a team\nExperience with Microsoft suite, GIS software and environmental databases\nMust live within the Townsville, Burdekin, Charters Towers region, or surrounding areas (within – 200km of Ravenswood) or be willing to relocate to the area.\n\nDesirable\n\nExperience in the Queensland legislative environment\nAUSRIVAS accreditation.\n4WD driving experience\nStrong QGIS skills and experience.\n\nNestled 120kms south of Townsville, in the vibrant landscapes of north-east Queensland, Ravenswood Gold Mine stands as a testament to both a rich legacy and the forefront of innovation. Ravenswood Gold is a private Australian company jointly owned by EMR Capital (EMR) and Golden Energy and Resources Limited (GEAR).\n\nWhat We Offer:\n\nAn opportunity to work within a reputable mining organisation, with a long term future, and to be part of its growth and development.\nContract position with a reputable mining company with a mine life in excess of 10 years with potential for extension\nA competitive remuneration package based on experience and skills\nSupport from a team with extensive industry, site knowledge and experience\nDIDO on an 8/6 roster\nOn-site accommodation and Meals provided\n\nApplications should include the following documentation in PDF format:\n\nCurrent Resume\nCover letter addressing suitability as outlined above.\n\nAll preferred candidates will undergo pre-employment checks, including a Nationally Coordinated Police Check, medical assessments, reference checks, and verification of qualifications.\n\nRavenswood Gold acknowledges the Traditional Owners of the Country on which we walk, live and work. We recognise their long history on the lands upon which our operations exist today and the care they gave to these lands for thousands of years. We pay our respect to their cultures and Elders past, present and future, and recognise their continuing connection to land, air and sea. Ravenswood Gold specifically acknowledges the Birriah People who are the Traditional Owners of the Country where the Ravenswood Gold Mine operates, the Bindal People who are the Traditional Owners of the Country where the Ravenswood Gold Townsville office and warehouse are located and the Yuggera and Turrbal People who are the Traditional Owners of the Country where the Ravenswood Gold head office is located in Brisbane.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=60bef6d490375956','scraped','Just posted'),(2514,NULL,'job','Team Lead – Aged Care Customer Service (Call Centre)','Permanent','Nedlands WA 6009',NULL,'',85000.00,'$80,000 - $90,000 a year','AI Job Summary\nExperience managing a team of customer service officers in a call centre environment.\nExperience coaching/supporting/motivating for high-quality, person-centred service and service-level/quality targets.\nHigh proficiency in ICT—databases, data analysis, and Microsoft Office Suite.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nOn-site • Permanent • Full-time • Associate\nPay Rate\n80000 AUD – 90000 AUD (Annum)\nDescription\n\nIndigo (formerly Independent Living Centre WA) is a leading provider of Assistive technology (devices and equipment), home modifications, therapy, and professional education. We provide tailored allied health and AT solutions to people with disability, seniors, carers, health professionals and educators. Through our customer-centric services we aim to achieve greater independence and inclusion for all.\n\nThe Role\n\nWith the continued success of Indigo and the GEAT2Go (Goods, Equipment and Assistive Technology) program, we are seeking a passionate and professional Team Lead to join our Aged Care Customer Service call centre.\n\nThe Team Lead is responsible for the day-to-day leadership and performance management of a team of Customer Service Officers, operating within call centre environment. The role focuses on coaching, supporting and motivating the team to deliver high-quality, person-centred service outcomes while consistently meeting service levels, quality standards and operational targets.\n\nThe duties will include but not limited to:\n\nLead a team of customer service officers to provide assessment and recommendation of assistive technology that support individuals to meet their goals, retain their independence and remain living at home.\nEnsure customers of the goods and equipment and home modification programs are reviewed to ensure goals are met prior to discharge from service.\nDevelop strategies to ensure customers receive timely and appropriate services to meet their needs.\nContribute to the development of the service, raise opportunities for innovation and ensure clinical best practice in service delivery.\nCoach, educate, inspire and provide clinical supervision and performance reviews\nIdentify any training gaps for individual staff, and through leadership support team members to achieve within their role\nIdentify staffing requirements and assisting with recruitment and retention\nContribute to, and demonstrate by example, the vision, mission and values\n\nThe Candidate\n\nExperience managing a team\nHigh standard of communication, problem solving, and initiative\nDemonstrated high proficiency in ICT – databases, data analysis, and Office Suite\nExperience in aged care and/or disability services and an understanding of the standards\nAbility to liaise with leaders and key stakeholders both internally and externally\nCall centre environment experience Highly desirable\n\nWe Offer\n\nRewarding work and being part of a “Values based” organisation – making a difference in people’s lives\nOngoing support, mentorship, and professional development\nGenerous salary packaging, up to an additional $18,549 tax free FBT (including the ability to package relocation expenses for those eligible)\nTrue work life balance with additional 3.5 days leave (pro-rata) / ability to purchase additional leave.\nEmployee Assistance Program for you and your immediate family to access in time of need\nHealth & Well-being Program including flu vaccination, EAP support and fun active social committee\n\nApply\n\nIf you are ready to join a supportive team and are passionate about the work you do – Register your interest today by submitting your curriculum vitae and a cover letter, addressing how you meet the work-related requirements (in no more than 2 pages).\n\nShort listing will commence immediately, along with interviewing. We thank you for your interest in Indigo and reserve the right to fill the position before the close date.\n\nA NDIS Worker Screener Check is a pre-requisite for all positions at Indigo.\n\nOnly those with the right to live & work in Australia need apply. No agency applications at this time.\n\nMission: We strive towards our mission of a community in which all abilities are valued, where people have the knowledge, tools, and confidence to participate.\n\nValues: Passion, Integrity, Creativity, Together\n\nWe value our people at Indigo and strive to have a positive and adaptive culture, one that aligns with our values; so cultural fit is just as important to us as qualifications, technical skill and experience.\n\nWe are committed to equal employment opportunities and embracing diversity and inclusion within our workforce. People from diverse backgrounds including people with disabilities, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people and people from culturally diverse backgrounds are encouraged to apply. If you require any additional support during the recruitment/interview phase, please contact hr@indigo.org.au','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6dd0961585e2123f','scraped','Just posted'),(2515,NULL,'job','Senior Analyst (Public Sector, Defense and Security) - BCG Vantage','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Who We Are\n\nBoston Consulting Group partners with leaders in business and society to tackle their most important challenges and capture their greatest opportunities. BCG was the pioneer in business strategy when it was founded in 1963. Today, we help clients with total transformation-inspiring complex change, enabling organizations to grow, building competitive advantage, and driving bottom-line impact.\n\nTo succeed, organizations must blend digital and human capabilities. Our diverse, global teams bring deep industry and functional expertise and a range of perspectives to spark change. BCG delivers solutions through leading-edge management consulting along with technology and design, corporate and digital ventures-and business purpose. We work in a uniquely collaborative model across the firm and throughout all levels of the client organization, generating results that allow our clients to thrive.\n\nWhat You\'ll Do\n\nAs a Senior Analyst – BCG Vantage on our Client Focus path within BCG\'s Public Sector Practice Area for Defence & Security, you will work in a growing global team, delivering value to clients via individual expertise and/or institutionalized BCG Vantage assets (products, tools, data, workshops, frameworks, surveys, domain-specific data and related expertise, etc.). You will contribute on cases and proposals by contributing relevant analysis and insights and help case teams create strong impact for the client. While contributing to client cases, workshops and proposals, occasional travel to serve clients onsite during staffing assignments is expected to understand client requirements, and design / develop solutions.\nYou will support commercialisation efforts for the topic/sector working, in conjunction with business leaders, through contributing analysis and insights to proposals, client workshops and marketing materials. Additionally, as a Senior Analyst – BCG Vantage, you will contribute to developing intellectual property & assets for the business and assist in onboarding and training junior colleagues based on your topic/sector expertise.\nYour work within our Defence & Security topic will primarily focus on supporting our engagement with Australian defence ministry and industry clients, providing expertise and insights to advance client objectives. You will work on topics that include acquisition, sustainment, shipbuilding, organisational design, and IT and technology transformations. Your focus will be on helping defence clients to adapt to a fast-changing security environment that increasingly depends upon spurring innovation and leveraging technology for national defence.\n\nYOU\'RE GOOD AT\n\nSolving client problems through formulating relevant research and/or analytical approaches in defence and security topics\nCommunicating with case teams and clients team members, in a credible and confident way\nWorking collaboratively and effectively in a group dynamic often virtual, proficient in agile ways of working\nBeing flexible and bringing a curious and creative mindset, open to new things and able to propose innovative ideas\nNavigating complexity and ambiguity\n\nWhat You\'ll Bring\n\n2+ years of consulting experience in defence and/or technology required; candidates with consulting experience strongly preferred\nIn lieu of consulting experience, 3+ years minimum industry experience required; 4-6+ years of industry experience strongly preferred\nStrong knowledge and experience in the Australian defence enterprise, or prior military or civilian service in the Australian Ministry of Defence or the Australian Defence Force, is highly desirable\nExperience with technology or digital strategy to include developing technology strategies, forming business cases, supporting large-scale technology transformations, or assisting AI transformations\nBachelor\'s Degree required (advanced degree preferred)\nFluency in English\nSuccessful candidate is subject to obtain and maintain an Australian government security clearance\nStrong business acumen and problem-solving capabilities\nStrong written and verbal communication skills\nOutstanding interpersonal and communication skills to interact with internal and external stakeholders while working in a global collaborative team environment\nSelf-starting and entrepreneurial spirit\n\nWho You\'ll Work With\n\nAs a Senior Analyst – BCG Vantage on our Client Focus path, you will work face to face with clients and with BCG Project Leaders, Associates and Consultants. In the period between cases, you will collaborate with global topic leads and colleagues across BCG to bring expertise and capabilities to the service of our internal and external clients. Our team is made up a diverse pool of BCG Vantage positions that allow us to pursue exciting, innovative BCG Vantage careers.\n\nAdditional info\n\nBCG Vantage is a powerhouse of expertise, seamlessly embedded within Practice Areas and markets to drive extraordinary impact. It equips BCG case teams and clients with cutting-edge expertise, proprietary assets, actionable data, and transformative insights that empower our case teams and enable our clients to achieve their aspirations.\nWith global experts across 20 Practices, covering more than 100 topics, sectors and offers, plus four focused geographic markets, BCG Vantage delivers unparalleled depth and breadth of insight & expertise. BCG Vantage consists of three career paths, each playing a crucial role in delivering value to clients, case teams and practice teams.\n\nClient Focus (Embedded Expertise)\n\nIntegrates into client-facing teams to deliver direct client impact through expertise, know-how, and proprietary tools and assets\n\nTopic Activation (Sector Expertise with Proprietary Tool & Data Solutions)\n\nCombines deep domain insights with our know-how and proprietary assets to address targeted challenges directly with clients and project teams; co-creates insights on industry trends and functional topics, proprietary data and tools, and teams to codify IP that all enables BCG to deliver excellent business value with its clients\n\nResearch (Practice Topic and Sector-Aligned Research and Insights)\n\nDelivers actionable research and insights tailored to the client project’s needs; works with qualitative and quantitative data, conducts research and provides synthesized results from sources including commercial data, public and open source, company and industry research, macro-economic, commodities and trade data.\n\nBoston Consulting Group is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, age, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity / expression, national origin, disability, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected under national, provincial, or local law, where applicable, and those with criminal histories will be considered in a manner consistent with applicable state and local laws.\nBCG is an E - Verify Employer. Click here for more information on E-Verify.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Boston Consulting Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6d6dbee9ece57ced','scraped','1 day ago'),(2516,NULL,'job','Blockchain Intelligence Analyst','Full-time','Australia',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Build a Safer World.\n\nTRM Labs provides AI-powered intelligence solutions that help public and private sector agencies investigate and disrupt crime. TRM\'s platforms enable investigators to trace illicit activity, build cases, and construct operating pictures of threat networks. Leading agencies and businesses worldwide rely on TRM to make the world safer and more secure.\n\nAs a Blockchain Intelligence Analyst, you will drive TRM’s collection, analysis, and reporting on key areas of the crypto economy (e.g., crypto exchanges, fraud). You will ensure that TRM has best-in-class intelligence through your subject matter expertise, first-principles problem solving, and ability to turn data into insights. You will collaborate with an experienced team of engineers, data scientists, and product managers to build scalable systems to detect, prevent, and mitigate cryptocurrency fraud and financial crime.\n\nThe impact you’ll have here:\n\nYou’ll track, analyze, and report on key areas of the crypto economy to detect suspicious activities.\n\nYour OSINT skills will help uncover hidden threats and improve our security posture.\n\nYou’ll provide key insights that contribute to real-world action against threat actors.\n\nYou’ll collaborate with data and engineering teams to enhance the TRM product.\n\nYour intelligence reports will help law enforcement, internal teams, and clients stay ahead of cyber risks.\n\nWhat we’re looking for:\n\nProven experience working in intelligence-related positions previously, ideally in Blockchain Intelligence (This is not an entry-level position).\n\nOSINT Expertise - Proficiency in using open-source tools to gather and analyze intelligence.\n\nAnalytical Skills - Strong ability to synthesize and report complex information clearly and accurately.\n\nExperience in Blockchain Analysis - Knowledge of blockchain technologies, with a focus on tracing transactions and identifying malicious activity.\n\nCommunication & Collaboration - Excellent communication skills to collaborate with cross-functional teams and produce actionable intelligence reports.\n\nOwnership - You demonstrate full ownership of your work, taking an 80/20 approach to accomplish objectives.\n\nCertifications & Background - Relevant certifications (e.g., GIAC, CEH) and experience in cybersecurity or intelligence gathering.\n\nFluency in Russian, Chinese (Mandarin or Cantonese), or Arabic, with the ability to conduct research and analysis in that language, is strongly preferred and may be required in some cases. Please specify your language proficiency and any relevant experience in your application.\n\nAbout the team:\n\nOur team values open communication and a collaborative work environment, where feedback and ideas are encouraged from all members.\n\nWe prioritize flexibility and adaptability, ensuring that everyone stays aligned through regular check-ins and progress updates. Operating with a strong focus on shared goals, we work together to meet deadlines while supporting individual growth and innovation.\n\nWe are a globally distributed team that leans heavily on asynchronous communication. While we aim for ~3–4 hours of overlap with the Pacific Time Zone, schedules are flexible and may occasionally adjust to support team collaboration.\n\nLearn about TRM Speed in this position:\n\nUtilizes sound judgment and the 80/20 principle to drive rapid, high-impact outcomes.\n\nDemonstrates the ability to iterate quickly in response to evolving threat landscapes.\n\nLeverages creative problem-solving to ensure prompt and effective threat actor engagement to acquire attribution within 24 hours.\n\nEmploys a diverse set of methodologies to scale and optimize threat intelligence production for customer needs within 72 hours.\n\nLife at TRM\n\nWe are building a safer world. That promise shows up in how we work every day.\n\nTRM moves quickly. We are a high velocity, high ownership team that expects clarity, follow-through, and impact. People who thrive here are energized by hard problems, experimentation, and continuous feedback. If something takes months elsewhere, it will ship here in days.\n\nOur work sits at the intersection of AI, national security, and fighting crime. The problems are complex, the stakes are real, and the environment evolves quickly. The pace and intensity of the work reflect the importance of the mission. As a result, the way we operate requires a high level of ownership, adaptability, collaboration, and creative problem-solving.\n\nAt TRM, you should expect:\n\nPriorities and targets to change quickly as we experiment and iterate\n\nWork that often requires operating with a high degree of ambiguity\n\nA high level of personal ownership and accountability\n\nClose collaboration across teams and functions\n\nFrequent, high-touch communication\n\nCreative problem solving and out-of-the-box thinking\n\nA pace that rewards urgency, adaptability, and outcomes\n\nThis environment is energizing for people who enjoy building, solving hard problems, and making progress in situations that are not always fully defined. It also requires comfort navigating ambiguity, adjusting course as new information emerges, and maintaining focus and positivity in a fast-moving and intense environment.\n\nWe also recognize that this style of operating is not for everyone. If you are primarily optimizing for predictability or a consistently balanced workload, we encourage you to use the interview process to pressure test whether this environment is truly the right fit. We want teammates who thrive here, not just survive here.\n\nAt the same time, many people find this work deeply rewarding. If you are excited by meaningful problems, motivated by ambitious goals, and energized by working alongside mission-driven colleagues, there is a good chance you will find TRM to be an exceptional place to grow and contribute. Learn more: Interviewing at TRM: How We Hire and What Success Looks Like\n\nAI Fluency at TRM\n\nAI fluency is a baseline expectation at TRM.\n\nWe believe AI meaningfully changes how top performers operate. We expect every team member to use AI to accelerate and reimagine their craft, not just automate surface tasks.\n\nAt TRM, AI fluency means you are among the top 10 percent of operators in your function in how you apply AI to:\n\nAccelerate repeatable workflows\n\nStructure and solve problems\n\nImprove output quality\n\nIncrease speed and leverage\n\nYou will be evaluated on applied AI fluency during the interview process.\n\nLeadership Principles\n\nWe hire and grow against three leadership principles. They’re the standards for how we operate, treat each other, and make decisions.\n\nImpact-Oriented Trailblazer: We put customers first and move with speed, focus, and adaptability. We treat every plan like an experiment – test, ship, measure, and iterate quickly.\n\nMaster Craftsperson: We care deeply about our craft. We balance speed with high standards, own outcomes end‑to‑end, and invest in getting better everyday.\n\nInspiring Colleague: We add clarity and energy, not noise. We bring humility, candor, and a one‑team mindset — giving and receiving feedback to make the team stronger.\n\nJoin our Mission\n\nAt TRM we care deeply about our craft. We are looking for individuals who want their work to matter, who experiment with speed and rigor, and who take pride in building a safer world for billions of people. If you’re excited by TRM’s mission but don’t check every box, we encourage you to apply — we hire for slope, judgment, and the will to learn fast.\n\nTRM is a Series C company with $220M in total funding, backed by Blockchain Capital, Goldman Sachs, Bessemer, Y Combinator, Thoma Bravo, and others. Headquartered in San Francisco, TRM operates as a distributed-first company with hubs in Los Angeles, San Francisco, New York, Washington D.C., London, and Singapore.\n\nPrivacy Policy and Additional Information\n\nBy submitting your application, you are agreeing to allow TRM to process your personal information in accordance with the TRM Privacy Policy.\n\nOur typical hiring cycles for specialized roles span 24 to 36 months. Accordingly, we retain your personal information for up to 36 months to evaluate your application and to consider you for current and future employment opportunities, unless you request earlier deletion or a different retention period is required or permitted by law.\n\nTo notify TRM Labs that you believe this job posting is non-compliant, please submit a report through this form. No response will be provided to inquiries unrelated to job posting compliance.\n\nThe use of AI tools of any kind (including but not limited to notetakers, interview assistants, and real-time coaching tools such as Otter.ai, Fireflies, Fathom, Cluey, or similar) during TRM interviews is not permitted without prior approval from TRM. TRM uses its own internal tools for note-taking to ensure a consistent and confidential experience for all candidates.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made via this form.\n\nRecruitment agencies\n\nTRM Labs does not accept unsolicited agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to TRM employees. TRM Labs is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes and will not pay fees to any third-party agency or company without a signed agreement.\n\nLearn More: Company Values | Interviewing | FAQs','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'TRM Labs','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=4dc0d28a40f91d83','scraped','1 day ago'),(2517,NULL,'job','Rehabilitation Consultant (NES)','Permanent','Melbourne VIC 3000',NULL,'',97500.00,'$85,000 - $110,000 a year','AI Job Summary\nRegistration with AHPRA or membership with ASORC.\nMinimum 1 year occupational rehabilitation and/or clinical experience.\nExceptional verbal and written communication skills.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nPermanent • Full-time • Experienced\nPay Rate\n85000 AUD – 110000 AUD (Annum)\nDescription\n\nRehabilitation Consultant (NES) – Rehabilitation Counsellor or Psychologist\n\nWork type: Full time (minimum 4 days part time also available)\n\nLocation: Melbourne VIC\n\nAbout PHSA\n\nPrestige Health Services Australia (PHSA) is a national rehabilitation provider delivering best in industry injury management; disability management and occupational rehabilitation services.\n\nYour Role\n\nPHSA are seeking Rehabilitation Consultants to deliver New Employer Services (NES) including assessment, intervention and case management services to clientele across varying schemes including TAC (Transport Accident Commission), WorkSafe VIC, Comcare, Life Insurance and Self Insurance with the primary function of supporting recovery and return to work.\n\nWhat You’ll Need\n\n• Registration with AHPRA (Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency) or membership with ASORC (Australian Society of Rehabilitation Counsellors)\n\n• Exceptional verbal and written communication skills\n\n• Minimum 1 year experience in occupational rehabilitation and/or clinical experience highly regarded\n\n• Direct experience working with TAC referred cases desirable\n\n• Have a current driver’s licence, motor vehicle and willingness to travel to deliver face-to-face servicing as required\n\nWhy Choose PHSA?\n\n• Flexibility & Autonomy: Shape your own work schedule and enjoy the freedom to work independently, with support always within reach. Flexible work arrangements also available.\n\n• Career Growth: Unlock pathways to advancement with our comprehensive induction, ongoing training, and mentoring programs.\n\n• Tools for Success: We equip you with a laptop, smartphone, and access to the latest technology.\n\n• Rewarding Salary & Bonuses: Enjoy a highly competitive salary, tailored to your experience, plus a lucrative bonus system for employees.\n\n• Supportive Team Culture: Be part of a passionate, purpose-driven team that values your contributions and celebrates your achievements.\n\nReady to take the next step in your career? Apply today!\n\nCompany Overview\nPrestige Health Services Australia (PHSA) is a national rehabilitation provider delivering best in industry injury management; disability management and workplace rehabilitation services. Our mission is to achieve sustainable health, social and return to work outcomes for our clientele through the delivery of innovative workplace; injury management; disability management and rehabilitation services undertaken by experienced consultants with a focus on quality, integrity and belief that we can and will achieve outcomes.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a20752388868b2d1','scraped','Just posted'),(2518,NULL,'job','AI Automation & Ecommerce Systems Lead (Remote)','Full-time','Melbourne VIC 3004',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Join a fast growing & market leading health brand!\nWork remote or in our Melbourne, AU office.\nExcellent career progression and bonus opportunities!\nAbout Us\n\nWe are a fast-growing D2C ecommerce group selling eco-friendly and sustainable products designed to make everyday life better for people and the planet.\n\nWe are building a lean, high-output business and want AI, automation and smart systems to become a core part of how we operate.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nWe are looking for an exceptional AI Automation & Ecommerce Systems Lead to help us scale our ecommerce business without scaling headcount at the same rate.\n\nThis is a hands-on builder role for someone who understands ecommerce, digital marketing, automation, AI tools, workflows and commercial outcomes.\n\nYour role will be to identify high-leverage manual work across the business, then build AI-powered workflows, automations and internal systems that reduce labour, increase output, improve marketing performance and help a small team operate like a much larger one.\n\nThis is not a role for someone who only uses ChatGPT casually or simply recommends tools. We need someone who can design, build, implement and improve practical systems that the team actually uses.\n\nKey Responsibilities AI Automation & Workflow Building\nIdentify repetitive, manual or inefficient workflows across marketing, ecommerce, customer service, operations and reporting\nBuild AI-powered automations, agents, workflows and internal tools to reduce manual workload\nConnect tools and systems using APIs, webhooks, Make, Zapier, n8n, Airtable, Google Apps Script, Python, JavaScript or similar\nCreate practical workflows that improve speed, output quality, accuracy and consistency\nDocument systems clearly so the team can use and maintain them\nEcommerce Growth & Marketing Systems\nBuild AI-assisted workflows across SEO, PPC, CRO, lifecycle marketing, content, creative production and analytics\nHelp scale content, landing page briefs, product copy, ad creative ideas, research and reporting\nImprove marketing efficiency across channels such as Google Ads, Meta, TikTok, email/SMS and organic search\nSupport smarter creative testing, campaign analysis, customer research and competitor monitoring\nUse AI and automation to improve website performance, conversion rate, AOV and customer journeys\nCustomer Service & Operations Automation\nIdentify opportunities to improve customer service efficiency using AI, automation and better knowledge systems\nBuild or improve AI-assisted response templates, macros, helpdesk workflows, FAQs and self-service flows\nUse customer enquiry data to identify recurring issues, product questions, website friction and improvement opportunities\nHelp automate operational workflows across tasks, SOPs, planning, product research, supplier research and internal communication\nData, Reporting & Insights\nBuild dashboards and reporting workflows that give clear visibility across sales, marketing, customer service and operations\nUse AI and data to identify growth opportunities, efficiency gains and business risks\nTrack the impact of automation projects on time saved, cost reduced, output increased and revenue improved\nPresent recommendations clearly and commercially to leadership\nWhat We’re Looking For\n\nWe are looking for someone who is highly practical, commercially minded and technically capable.\n\nYou should be able to look at a manual business process and ask:\n\nCan this be automated?\nCan AI do 70–90% of this?\nCan we make this faster, cheaper or more accurate?\nCan we turn this into a repeatable system?\nCan we increase output without adding more people?\nEssential Skills & Experience\nStrong hands-on experience building AI automations, workflows, agents or internal tools\nPractical understanding of ecommerce, digital marketing and customer journeys\nExperience using AI to improve marketing, content, analysis, customer service, reporting or workflow efficiency\nExperience with automation platforms such as Make, Zapier, n8n, Airtable, Relevance AI, Retool, Pipedream or similar\nAbility to work with APIs, webhooks, data flows and system integrations\nStrong understanding of prompt engineering, AI workflow design and reusable prompt systems\nExperience with tools such as Shopify, Klaviyo, Google Analytics, Google Search Console, Meta Ads, Google Ads, helpdesks or similar ecommerce platforms\nAbility to turn messy processes into clean, usable workflows\nStrong analytical skills and commercial judgement\nAbility to move quickly, test ideas, implement solutions and improve over time\nHighly Regarded\nPython, JavaScript, Google Apps Script or SQL experience\nExperience with RAG systems, embeddings, vector databases or AI knowledge bases\nExperience building dashboards, reporting systems or internal tools\nExperience with AI creative, image, video or content production workflows\nExperience in D2C ecommerce, retail, consumer brands or digital agencies\nExperience with Shopify-based businesses\nUnderstanding of SEO, PPC, CRO, email marketing and lifecycle marketing\nWhat Success Looks Like\n\nIn this role, success means:\n\nManual work is reduced across key areas of the business\nMarketing, creative, research and reporting output increases\nTeam members spend less time on repetitive admin and more time on high-value work\nAI workflows are reliable, documented and actually used by the team\nCustomer service and operational processes become faster and more consistent\nGrowth initiatives are prioritised based on commercial impact\nThe business becomes more efficient, scalable and data-driven\nThe Type of Person We Want\n\nYou are likely a strong fit if you are:\n\nA builder, not just a strategist\nCommercially focused, not just technically curious\nFast, practical and resourceful\nObsessed with AI, automation and better systems\nComfortable working in a fast-moving ecommerce environment\nAble to work with ambiguity and turn ideas into working solutions\nInterested in creating real business leverage, not just experimenting with tools\nWhy Join Us\n\nThis is a high-impact role in a growing ecommerce business where your work will directly shape how the company operates.\n\nYou will work closely with leadership to build AI systems that improve growth, efficiency, customer experience and profitability across multiple brands.\n\nIf you are already experimenting with AI every day and want to apply it to real commercial ecommerce problems, this is an opportunity to build meaningful systems with real business impact.\n\nHow to Apply\n\nPlease apply with:\n\nA short summary of your AI automation and ecommerce experience\nExamples of AI workflows, automations, agents, tools or internal systems you have built\nThe platforms and tools you are strongest with\nA brief explanation of how you would use AI to help an ecommerce business operate like a much larger team','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Retail Smart Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8e198a828da494fa','scraped','1 day ago'),(2519,NULL,'job','Senior Manager, Business Controls & Monitoring (Mob Way Applicants must identify as Aboriginal and / or Torres Strait Islander)','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Senior Manager, Business Controls & Monitoring – Mob Way Applicants must identify as Aboriginal and / or Torres Strait Islander\n\nWhat’s the role?\n\nThis role sits within the Product Governance & Business Controls & Monitoring (BCM) Centre of Excellence and is part of Westpac’s Mob Way program a culturally grounded pathway into senior leadership for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples. As a Senior Manager, you’ll design, build and operate AI-enabled and automated solutions that uplift group wide Risk Practices, improve insight quality, and reduce reliance on manual processes.\n\nFurthermore, you will ensure solutions are explainable and auditable to meet AI risk standards, acts as an escalation point for complex matters, evolving risk standards/tooling, and mentoring team members.\n\nThrough Mob Way, you’ll be supported with strong executive connection, opportunities to build your networks, and dedicated time for community connection and elder-led cultural immersion.\n\nThis is a full-time, permanent role based in Sydney , with working options available.\n\nWhat do I need?\n\nExperience applying analytics, automation or AI-enabled approaches in complex environments\nAbility to design or contribute to data, analytics or technology solutions\nDemonstrated experience developing Power Platform solutions that embed analytics into business-as-usual (BAU) workflows\nExperience building dashboards, tools, workflows or analytical pipelines\nAbility to work with senior stakeholders and explain complex topics clearly\n\nWhy join us?\n\nAs part of Mob Way, you will receive tailored career support through executive coaching, culturally safe leadership development, and opportunities to strengthen your connection to community and culture.\n\nAt Westpac, we’re passionate about becoming our customers’ #1 banking partner for life and we know that starts with creating the best workplace in the country. For Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, that means more than just a job.\n\nSpecial offers on banking products and discounts from top brands, including generous employee-only mortgage rates!\nWe offer flexible work arrangements to support your work/life balance, along with a variety of leave options including Culture (such as dedicated Sorry Business Leave), Lifestyle, and Wellbeing Leave.\nTailored career support through our Indigenous Careers Team, and growth opportunities like the Echo mentoring program and Jawun secondments.\nLots of opportunities to ‘give back’ to the Community by getting involved in our many volunteering initiatives including our Brothers & Sisters Employee Advocacy Group.\n\nCreate your future today\n\nTo get started, simply click on the APPLY or APPLY NOW button\n\n#mobway\n\nCreate your future today through a role supported by our Mob Way program and a workplace committed to supporting your career.\n\nWe’re all about creating a supportive and inclusive community. We welcome everyone – no matter your age, gender, background, or abilities. We also provide additional support to welcome our veterans, Indigenous Australians and neurodiverse community.\n\nIf you need any adjustments during the recruitment process, you can find out more information and additional contact details by visiting the \"People with Disability and/or needing Accessibility Requirements\" page on our website.\n\nAt Westpac we aim to help Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Australians succeed by supporting Indigenous employees to build meaningful careers. Westpac has been granted an S126 Exemption to sections eight (8) and fifty-one (51) of the Anti-Discrimination Act 1977 (NSW); this allows us to advertise and recruit this role exclusively to Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander applicants. This forms part of Westpac’s strategy to foster a multicultural, vibrant and diverse workforce','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Westpac Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=14ff1dd5cd50657b','scraped','1 day ago'),(2520,NULL,'job','Threat Intelligence Analyst, Finanical Networks','Full-time','Australia',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Build a Safer World.\n\nTRM Labs provides AI-powered intelligence solutions that help public and private sector agencies investigate and disrupt crime. TRM\'s platforms enable investigators to trace illicit activity, build cases, and construct operating pictures of threat networks. Leading agencies and businesses worldwide rely on TRM to make the world safer and more secure.\n\nRole Overview:\n\nThe threats TRM\'s analysts work to disrupt aren\'t abstract — they fund violence, enable exploitation, and undermine global security. As a Threat Intelligence Analyst, Financial Networks, you will drive TRM\'s collection, analysis, and reporting on the actors and networks behind these harms, applying threat intelligence tradecraft to identify, track, and expose adversaries who use traditional financial systems alongside crypto to move value, evade sanctions, and obscure their activity.\n\nThe impact you’ll have here:\n\nDevelop novel collection strategies and analytic methodologies to surface threat actor activity that isn\'t visible through conventional tooling or open databases\n\nConduct proactive threat hunting across on-chain and off-chain data sources to identify emerging illicit networks before they\'re widely known\n\nMap financial networks used for sanctions evasion — including commodity flows, corporate ownership structures, and offshore financial centers — and connect them to on-chain activity\n\nTrack, analyze, and report on threat actors, campaigns, and illicit networks that operate across both traditional financial infrastructure and the crypto ecosystem\n\nIdentify and assess adversary TTPs, infrastructure, and behavior to support detection and attribution efforts\n\nLeverage OSINT and other intelligence methods to uncover hidden threats and generate actionable insights\n\nProduce high-quality intelligence that reaches law enforcement and government partners worldwide\n\nCollaborate with data, engineering, and product teams to enhance TRM\'s intelligence capabilities\n\nBe a leading voice on how adversaries exploit the intersection of traditional finance and crypto to move illicit value\n\nWhat we’re looking for:\n\nProven experience in threat intelligence, cyber intelligence, or national security intelligence roles (this is not an entry-level position)\n\nFluency in Russian, Chinese (Mandarin or Cantonese), or Farsi, with the ability to conduct research and analysis in that language, is strongly preferred and may be required in some cases. Please specify your language proficiency and any relevant experience in your application.\n\nA track record of generating net-new intelligence — developing original hypotheses, pursuing non-obvious investigative threads, and surfacing findings that others miss\n\nBackground in sanctions enforcement, financial intelligence, or corporate investigations is strongly preferred\n\nWorking knowledge of blockchain and cryptocurrency — including how transactions work, on-chain tracing concepts, and the role of crypto in financial crime (e.g., ransomware, sanctions evasion, darknet markets)\n\nDemonstrated ability to analyze corporate ownership structures, beneficial ownership, and cross-border fund flows — including how adversaries use trade finance, commodity flows, and offshore financial centers to move value\n\nExperience tracking threat actors, nation-state activity, or sanctioned entities — including analysis of TTPs, infrastructure, and financial behavior to support attribution\n\nStrong analytical and communication skills with the ability to produce clear, actionable intelligence reports with high intelligence tradecraft standards.\n\nAbility to collaborate cross-functionally with technical and non-technical stakeholders\n\nComfort operating in ambiguous, low-signal environments where the analytic path forward has to be constructed, not followed — and the ownership mindset to drive it independently\n\nHands-on experience with blockchain analysis tools (e.g., Chainalysis Reactor, TRM, Elliptic) or formal cryptocurrency investigation experience\n\nRelevant certifications (e.g., GIAC, CEH, Chainalysis Reactor Certification) or background in cybersecurity, intelligence, or investigations\n\nAbout the team:\n\nOur team values open communication and a collaborative work environment, where feedback and ideas are encouraged from all members.\n\nWe prioritize flexibility and adaptability, ensuring that everyone stays aligned through regular check-ins and progress updates. Operating with a strong focus on shared goals, we work together to meet deadlines while supporting individual growth and innovation.\n\nWe are a globally distributed team that leans heavily on asynchronous communication. While we aim for ~3–4 hours of overlap with the Pacific Time Zone, schedules are flexible and may occasionally adjust to support team collaboration.\n\nLearn about TRM Speed in this position:\n\nUtilizes sound judgment and the 80/20 principle to drive rapid, high-impact outcomes.\n\nDemonstrates the ability to iterate quickly in response to evolving threat landscapes.\n\nLeverages creative problem-solving to ensure prompt and effective threat actor engagement to acquire attribution within 24 hours.\n\nEmploys a diverse set of methodologies to scale and optimize threat intelligence production for customer needs within 72 hours.\n\nLife at TRM\n\nWe are building a safer world. That promise shows up in how we work every day.\n\nTRM moves quickly. We are a high velocity, high ownership team that expects clarity, follow-through, and impact. People who thrive here are energized by hard problems, experimentation, and continuous feedback. If something takes months elsewhere, it will ship here in days.\n\nOur work sits at the intersection of AI, national security, and fighting crime. The problems are complex, the stakes are real, and the environment evolves quickly. The pace and intensity of the work reflect the importance of the mission. As a result, the way we operate requires a high level of ownership, adaptability, collaboration, and creative problem-solving.\n\nAt TRM, you should expect:\n\nPriorities and targets to change quickly as we experiment and iterate\n\nWork that often requires operating with a high degree of ambiguity\n\nA high level of personal ownership and accountability\n\nClose collaboration across teams and functions\n\nFrequent, high-touch communication\n\nCreative problem solving and out-of-the-box thinking\n\nA pace that rewards urgency, adaptability, and outcomes\n\nThis environment is energizing for people who enjoy building, solving hard problems, and making progress in situations that are not always fully defined. It also requires comfort navigating ambiguity, adjusting course as new information emerges, and maintaining focus and positivity in a fast-moving and intense environment.\n\nWe also recognize that this style of operating is not for everyone. If you are primarily optimizing for predictability or a consistently balanced workload, we encourage you to use the interview process to pressure test whether this environment is truly the right fit. We want teammates who thrive here, not just survive here.\n\nAt the same time, many people find this work deeply rewarding. If you are excited by meaningful problems, motivated by ambitious goals, and energized by working alongside mission-driven colleagues, there is a good chance you will find TRM to be an exceptional place to grow and contribute. Learn more: Interviewing at TRM: How We Hire and What Success Looks Like\n\nAI Fluency at TRM\n\nAI fluency is a baseline expectation at TRM.\n\nWe believe AI meaningfully changes how top performers operate. We expect every team member to use AI to accelerate and reimagine their craft, not just automate surface tasks.\n\nAt TRM, AI fluency means you are among the top 10 percent of operators in your function in how you apply AI to:\n\nAccelerate repeatable workflows\n\nStructure and solve problems\n\nImprove output quality\n\nIncrease speed and leverage\n\nYou will be evaluated on applied AI fluency during the interview process.\n\nLeadership Principles\n\nWe hire and grow against three leadership principles. They’re the standards for how we operate, treat each other, and make decisions.\n\nImpact-Oriented Trailblazer: We put customers first and move with speed, focus, and adaptability. We treat every plan like an experiment – test, ship, measure, and iterate quickly.\n\nMaster Craftsperson: We care deeply about our craft. We balance speed with high standards, own outcomes end‑to‑end, and invest in getting better everyday.\n\nInspiring Colleague: We add clarity and energy, not noise. We bring humility, candor, and a one‑team mindset — giving and receiving feedback to make the team stronger.\n\nJoin our Mission\n\nAt TRM we care deeply about our craft. We are looking for individuals who want their work to matter, who experiment with speed and rigor, and who take pride in building a safer world for billions of people. If you’re excited by TRM’s mission but don’t check every box, we encourage you to apply — we hire for slope, judgment, and the will to learn fast.\n\nTRM is a Series C company with $220M in total funding, backed by Blockchain Capital, Goldman Sachs, Bessemer, Y Combinator, Thoma Bravo, and others. Headquartered in San Francisco, TRM operates as a distributed-first company with hubs in Los Angeles, San Francisco, New York, Washington D.C., London, and Singapore.\n\nPrivacy Policy and Additional Information\n\nBy submitting your application, you are agreeing to allow TRM to process your personal information in accordance with the TRM Privacy Policy.\n\nOur typical hiring cycles for specialized roles span 24 to 36 months. Accordingly, we retain your personal information for up to 36 months to evaluate your application and to consider you for current and future employment opportunities, unless you request earlier deletion or a different retention period is required or permitted by law.\n\nTo notify TRM Labs that you believe this job posting is non-compliant, please submit a report through this form. No response will be provided to inquiries unrelated to job posting compliance.\n\nThe use of AI tools of any kind (including but not limited to notetakers, interview assistants, and real-time coaching tools such as Otter.ai, Fireflies, Fathom, Cluey, or similar) during TRM interviews is not permitted without prior approval from TRM. TRM uses its own internal tools for note-taking to ensure a consistent and confidential experience for all candidates.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations to applicants with disabilities, and requests can be made via this form.\n\nRecruitment agencies\n\nTRM Labs does not accept unsolicited agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to TRM employees. TRM Labs is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes and will not pay fees to any third-party agency or company without a signed agreement.\n\nLearn More: Company Values | Interviewing | FAQs','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'TRM Labs','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=bef0014c42ac8c93','scraped','1 day ago'),(2521,NULL,'job','APAC Technical Support & Cloud Consultant-Syndey/Melbourne','','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'NeoXam is a growing international financial software company headquartered in Paris, with a strong and expanding presence across Australia. Through our combined expertise and transparent approach, we help Buy-Side and Sell-Side organizations - across banking, asset management, and insurance - navigate the continuous changes shaping the financial industry. Our solutions span the complete financial value chain, from centralized data management to front- and back-office software.\n\nWith 750+ dedicated staff across 21 offices worldwide - including Sydney, Melbourne, New York, Boston, Paris, Frankfurt, Luxembourg, Zurich, Geneva, Milan, London, Hong Kong, Shanghai, Singapore, Noida, Chennai, and more - NeoXam combines global scale with an entrepreneurial, collaborative culture. More than 150 clients across the globe trust NeoXam to run their most critical workflows.\n\nJoin us and be part of a thriving, internationally recognized financial software company making waves in the industry.\nAs part of our expanding NeoXam as a Service (NXaaS) operating model, we are looking for a motivated and technically strong Technical Support & Cloud Consultant to join our Australian team. This is a hands-on role that blends client-facing support with cloud infrastructure ownership, making it ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of financial software and modern cloud operations. As we continue to grow our global SaaS footprint, this role will evolve alongside increasing monitoring, observability, and operational responsibilities. NXaaS operates a follow-the-sun support model across APAC, EMEA, and the Americas - this role covers Australian business hours.\n\nYou will support NeoXam\'s core product suite, including:\n\nNeoXam DataHub – a centralized data management platform purpose-built for financial institutions, serving as a hub for all data consumed or produced across the enterprise.\n\nNeoXam IBOR – a uniquely independent and flexible Investment Book of Record, providing asset managers with a single, continuously updated source for positions, valuations, and forecasts across multiple views.\n\nNeoXam Aro – an intelligent, low-code reconciliation and data lifecycle platform that transforms fragmented, manual processes into a unified, AI-powered solution.\n\nNeoXam Impress – an end-to-end solution for client, digital, and regulatory reporting, covering data integration, performance calculations, production workflows, and data visualization.\n\nYour Missions\n· Serve as the first technical point of contact for NeoXam\'s global clients, covering Australian business hours within NeoXam\'s follow-the-sun support model and ensuring seamless handoff with APAC and EMEA counterparts.\n\n· Triage, analyze, and own support tickets end-to-end - from anomaly identification and root cause investigation through to resolution, including software-level fixes in Java and escalation to R&D when required.\n\n· Review and respond to monitoring alerts and operational dashboards, identifying and acting on anomalies before they impact clients; monitor and manage cloud resources (primarily AWS) to ensure performance and availability against production SLAs.\n\n· Troubleshoot and enhance cloud-based deployments; implement patches and configuration fixes; support data migration and cloud onboarding initiatives in collaboration with clients and internal teams.\n\n· Manage technical installations, upgrades, and environment refreshes for client-facing deployments; maintain internal environment replicas for issue reproduction and testing.\n\n· Collaborate with the Paris R&D team and global support counterparts to resolve complex issues and contribute to the NXaaS knowledge base.\n\n· Support pre-sales and implementation teams on technical matters; participate in client calls, project updates, and cross-team coordination.\n\nYour Profile\n\n· Bachelor\'s or Master\'s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.\n\n· 3-5 years of experience in technical support, implementation, or infrastructure roles within financial software or the banking/financial services industry.\n\n· Solid working knowledge of AWS (EC2, RDS, ALB, S3, CloudWatch, VPC, IAM); AWS certification is a plus.\n\n· Proficient in Java application troubleshooting - log analysis, memory management, thread dumps, and configuration.\n\n· Ability to diagnose and interpret common database performance issues - including slow queries, missing indexes, lock contention, and execution plan analysis. Experience with Oracle and/or PostgreSQL query tuning is strongly preferred.\n\n· Experience with relational databases - Oracle, PostgreSQL, or SQL Server.\n\n· Scripting ability (Shell, Python, or equivalent) for automation and diagnostics.\n\n· Familiarity with web application servers (Tomcat, JBoss, or WebSphere) and messaging systems (IBM MQ, Kafka, or equivalent).\n\n· Working knowledge of XML, REST/SOAP web services, and API integrations.\n\n· EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service): Strong understanding of Kubernetes fundamentals and practical experience with Amazon EKS for container orchestration from support perspective.\n\n· Monitoring & Observability Tools: Hands-on experience with solutions such as Datadog, Grafana, CloudWatch or similar platforms for system monitoring, logging, and performance visualization.\n\n· Familiarity with Git and standard version control workflows.\n\n· Hands-on experience with Linux/Unix environments and command-line operations.\n\n· Understanding of Agile/Scrum methodology and ITIL support practices.\n\n· Strong written and verbal communication skills; ability to manage client relationships professionally and independently.\n\n· Self-motivated, proactive, and collaborative — comfortable working across time zones with global teams.\n\nWhy NeoXam?\n\nAt NeoXam, we love people who are curious, involved, and self-driven. We encourage creativity and strive to promote an environment and culture based on personal growth and development. We want you to express your full potential and become a major contributor to our continued growth across Australia and beyond.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'NeoXam','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=93bace7cbae3c1c4','scraped','1 day ago'),(2522,NULL,'job','Dementia Consultant','Permanent','Subiaco WA 6008',NULL,'',4871.50,'$46.15 - $51.28 an hour','AI Job Summary\nManage contracts, meet deadlines, and complete reports.\nStrong knowledge of best-practice dementia care and quality assurance principles.\nBuild and nurture stakeholder relationships with professionalism and integrity.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nOn-site • Permanent • Full-time • Mid-level Senior\nPay Rate\n46.15 AUD – 51.28 AUD (Hour)\nDescription\n\nAbout Us\n\nSince 1982, Alzheimer’s WA has been a leading voice and support for people living with dementia, their families, and carers. As we continue to grow and expand our services, we are moving in a positive and promising direction—championing person-centred care, advocacy, education, and holistic support through our CHSP, SaH, and Grant funding, as well as day and overnight respite across Perth, Mandurah, and Albany. Our mission is to walk alongside those living with dementia, making a meaningful difference every day.\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\nSalary packaging up to $18,550 per annum.\n5 weeks of annual leave and 17.5% leave loading.\nOn-site free parking.\nMarket leading Employee Assistance Program.\nOn-going professional development.\n\nPosition Summary\n\nAre you passionate about making a difference in the lives of people living with dementia? Reporting to the Education/Consulting Lead, Alzheimer’s WA is seeking an experienced Dementia Consultant to lead strategic initiatives, drive innovation, and champion best-practice dementia care across Western Australia.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nDevelop and implement strategies that position Alzheimer’s WA as a leader in dementia care.\nMeet service agreements and grant funding budgets, reporting requirements and drive outcomes\nLead research and data-driven projects to inform service delivery and enhance outcomes.\nLiaise with and build industry Dementia Change Champions through a scholarship program\nBuild and nurture stakeholder relationships, representing Alzheimer’s WA with professionalism and integrity.\nGuide campaigns and key activities, increasing awareness and driving growth in line with our strategic plan.\n\nAbout You\n\nTertiary qualifications in social sciences, human services, aged care, or equivalent experience (desirable).\nStrong knowledge of best-practice dementia care and quality assurance principles.\nProven ability to manage contracts, meet deadlines and complete reports.\nExcellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills.\nAdvanced proficiency in Microsoft 365 and related tools.\nExperience in health or aged care, regional service delivery, and understanding of Support at Home frameworks is preferred.\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\nBe part of a growing organisation with a bright future\nMake a real difference in the lives of people living with dementia and their carers\nShape the future of dementia care in WA\nMentor and support junior staff as you grow your own career\nBlend creativity with passion in a values-driven environment\nEnjoy a supportive, collaborative team that values your contribution\n\nReady to Grow Your Career with Purpose? Apply now and help us build a safer, more supportive environment for our staff and the people we care for.\n\nIf you have questions about the position, you can contact us at\n\nhr@alzheimerswa.org.au\n\nPlease note: We reserve the right to close the position without notice.\n\nAt Alzheimer’s WA, we believe that we have an important role to play in promoting diversity, equality, respect and inclusion in our society. People from culturally diverse backgrounds are encouraged to apply.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=959600370a388122','scraped','1 day ago'),(2523,NULL,'job','ICT Support','Permanent','North Sydney NSW 2060',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'AI Job Summary\nFoundational knowledge of networking, server environments, and end-user computing.\nAbility to troubleshoot and resolve hardware, software, and network issues methodically.\nFull Australian work rights to be eligible for the role.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nOn-site • Permanent • Full-time • Entry Level\nDescription\n\nAbout the role\n\nNetStrategy works exclusively in K–12 education. We have supported over 400 schools across Australia for more than 40 years. ICT is not a sideline for us — it is the business. The people we hire are responsible for the technology that keeps schools running.\n\nThis ICT Support role sits at the centre of that work. You will be based on-site at a leading independent school, embedded in the day-to-day technology operations of the school. You will work alongside experienced engineers and service delivery professionals, contributing to real infrastructure across servers, networks, cloud platforms, and end-user environments.\n\nThis is an entry-to-junior role. We hire on aptitude and attitude as much as experience. If you are early in your career and serious about growing into a systems and infrastructure specialist, this is a structured path to do that.\n\nWhat you’ll be doing\n\nProviding day-to-day ICT support across end-user computing, connectivity, and core infrastructure\nTroubleshooting hardware, software, and network issues — working through problems methodically and escalating when needed\nContributing to infrastructure projects alongside senior engineers\nWork within a team to support broad and varied systems from leading vendors.\nMaintaining clear, timely communication with school staff and stakeholders when issues arise\nKeeping technical documentation accurate and up to date\n\nWho we’re looking for\n\nYou may be finishing a degree or certification, or you may have one to three years of hands-on experience. What matters more than credentials is how you approach the work.\nYou work through problems logically and know when to ask for help\nYou communicate clearly with people who aren’t technical — and you don’t make them feel like they should be\nYou follow through. If you say you’ll do something, you do it\nYou’re curious about technology and take it on yourself to stay current\nYou take the work seriously but don’t need to be chased to do it well\n\nSkills and Experience\n\nEssential:\n\nFoundational knowledge of networking, server environments, and end-user computing\nFamiliarity with Microsoft 365 and cloud-based infrastructure\nAbility to troubleshoot and resolve technical issues methodically\nClear written and verbal communication\nFull Australian work rights\n\nAdvantageous:\n\nExperience with VMware, Hyper-V, or Azure environments\nFamiliarity with ITSM tools or ticketing systems (ConnectWise is a plus)\nExposure to Extreme Networks, HPE Aruba, Juniper MIST, or similar switching/Wi-Fi platforms\nExperience with backup technologies (Veeam, Barracuda)\nMacOS and JAMF experience\nCCNA, JNCP, ACMP or equivalent certification\nAny prior experience in or with a school environment\n\nWhy NetStrategy?\n\nWe work in one sector. That means the context you build here is deep rather than scattered. You will understand schools — their operations, their rhythms, their risk profile — in a way that generalist IT providers never do.\n\nNetStrategy invests in the development of its technical staff. This role has a clear path forward, and we support people who want to move along it.\n\nOur Values\n\nOwn It\nGo Further\nLift Others\nStay Grounded\n\nNote: NetStrategy is not in a position to offer visa sponsorship. Applications open to those with full Australian Work Rights. Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. No recruiters please.\n\nCompany Overview\nFor over 35 years, NetStrategy has partnered with Australian K–12 schools to deliver technology solutions that enhance learning without adding complexity. As the only wholly education-focused provider in the Australian market, we combine specialised IT support, consulting, and cybersecurity services with a collaborative approach that strengthens and uplifts in-house IT teams. Guided by our values—Own It, Stay Grounded, Lift Others, Go Further—we continue to deliver trusted, education-centric technology outcomes.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=19239e3fa8747865','scraped','1 day ago'),(2524,NULL,'job','Software Engineer, Platform - Sydney, Australia','','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'The mission of Speechify is to make sure that reading is never a barrier to learning.\n\nOver 50 million people use Speechify\'s text-to-speech products to turn whatever they\'re reading – PDFs, books, Google Docs, news articles, websites – into audio, so they can read faster, read more, and remember more. Speechify\'s text-to-speech reading products include its iOS app, Android App, Mac App, Chrome Extension, and Web App. Google recently named Speechify the Chrome Extension of the Year and Apple named Speechify its 2025 Design Award winner for Inclusivity.\n\nToday, nearly 200 people around the globe work on Speechify in a 100% distributed setting – Speechify has no office. These include frontend and backend engineers, AI research scientists, and others from Amazon, Microsoft, and Google, leading PhD programs like Stanford, high growth startups like Stripe, Vercel, Bolt, and many founders of their own companies.\n\nOverview\n\nThe responsibilities of our Platform team include building and maintaining all backend services, including, but not limited to, payments, analytics, subscriptions, new products, text to speech, and external APIs.\n\nThis is a key role and ideal for someone who thinks strategically, enjoys fast-paced environments, is passionate about making product decisions, and has experience building great user experiences that delight users.\n\nWe are a flat organization that allows anyone to become a leader by showing excellent technical skills and delivering results consistently and fast. Work ethic, solid communication skills, and obsession with winning are paramount.\n\nOur interview process involves several technical interviews and we aim to complete them within 1 week.\n\nWhat You\'ll Do\n\nDesign, develop, and maintain robust APIs including public TTS API, internal APIs like Payment, Subscription, Auth and Consumption Tracking, ensuring they meet business and scalability requirements\nOversee the full backend API landscape, enhancing and optimizing for performance and maintainability\nCollaborate on B2B solutions, focusing on customization and integration needs for enterprise clients\nWork closely with cross-functional teams to align backend architecture with overall product strategy and user experience\n\nAn Ideal Candidate Should Have\n\nProven experience in backend development: TS/Node (required)\nDirect experience with GCP and knowledge of AWS, Azure, or other cloud providers\nEfficiency in ideation and implementation, prioritizing tasks based on urgency and impact\nPreferred: Experience with Docker and containerized deployments\nPreferred: Proficiency in deploying high availability applications on Kubernetes\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nA dynamic environment where your contributions shape the company and its products\nA team that values innovation, intuition, and drive\nAutonomy, fostering focus and creativity\nThe opportunity to have a significant impact in a revolutionary industry\nCompetitive compensation, a welcoming atmosphere, and a commitment to an exceptional asynchronous work culture\nThe privilege of working on a product that changes lives, particularly for those with learning differences like dyslexia, ADD, and more\nAn active role at the intersection of artificial intelligence and audio – a rapidly evolving tech domain\n\nThink you\'re a good fit for this job?\n\nTell us more about yourself and why you\'re interested in the role when you apply.\nAnd don\'t forget to include links to your portfolio and LinkedIn.\n\nNot looking but know someone who would make a great fit?\n\nRefer them!\n\nSpeechify is committed to a diverse and inclusive workplace.\n\nSpeechify does not discriminate on the basis of race, national origin, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, protected veteran status, disability, age, or other legally protected status.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Speechify','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a6c2f24109dc2c8f','scraped','1 day ago'),(2525,NULL,'job','Rehabilitation Consultant (OES)','Permanent','Melbourne VIC 3000',NULL,'',98000.00,'$85,000 - $111,000 a year','AI Job Summary\nRegistration with AHPRA or membership with ESSA.\nMinimum 1 year experience in occupational rehabilitation and/or clinical experience.\nExperience delivering Original Employer Services: assessment, intervention and case management.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nPermanent • Full-time • Experienced\nPay Rate\n85000 AUD – 111000 AUD (Annum)\nDescription\n\nRehabilitation Consultant – OT, Physio, EP, Osteo\n\nWork type: Full time (minimum 4 days part time)\n\nLocation: Melbourne VIC\n\nAbout PHSA\n\nPrestige Health Services Australia (PHSA) is a national rehabilitation provider delivering best in industry injury management; disability management and occupational rehabilitation services.\n\nYour Role\n\nPHSA are seeking Rehabilitation Consultants to deliver Original Employer Services (OES) including assessment, intervention and case management services to clientele across varying schemes including TAC (Transport Accident Commission), WorkSafe VIC, Comcare, Life Insurance and Self Insurance with the primary function of supporting recovery and return to work.\n\nWhat You’ll Need\n\n• Registration with AHPRA (Australian Health Practitioner Regulation Agency) or membership with ESSA (Exercise and Sports Science Australia)\n\n• Exceptional verbal and written communication skills\n\n• Minimum 1 year experience in occupational rehabilitation and/or clinical experience highly regarded\n\n• Direct experience working with TAC referred cases desirable\n\n• Have a current driver’s licence, motor vehicle and willingness to travel to deliver face-to-face servicing as required\n\nWhy Choose PHSA?\n\n• Flexibility & Autonomy: Shape your own work schedule and enjoy the freedom to work independently, with support always within reach. Flexible work arrangements also available.\n\n• Career Growth: Unlock pathways to advancement with our comprehensive induction, ongoing training, and mentoring programs.\n\n• Tools for Success: We equip you with a laptop, smartphone, and access to the latest technology.\n\n• Rewarding Salary & Bonuses: Enjoy a highly competitive salary, tailored to your experience, plus a lucrative bonus system for employees.\n\n• Supportive Team Culture: Be part of a passionate, purpose-driven team that values your contributions and celebrates your achievements.\n\nReady to take the next step in your career? Apply today!\n\nCompany Overview\nPrestige Health Services Australia (PHSA) is a national rehabilitation provider delivering best in industry injury management; disability management and workplace rehabilitation services. Our mission is to achieve sustainable health, social and return to work outcomes for our clientele through the delivery of innovative workplace; injury management; disability management and rehabilitation services undertaken by experienced consultants with a focus on quality, integrity and belief that we can and will achieve outcomes.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d567770c2884770d','scraped','1 day ago'),(2526,NULL,'job','Share point and infrastructure engineer','Full-time','Yarralumla ACT 2600',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'AI Job Summary\nAdminister and maintain Microsoft SharePoint environments for optimal performance and user experience.\nDesign, implement, and manage infrastructure solutions supporting business operations.\nTroubleshoot and resolve technical issues related to SharePoint and infrastructure components.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nOn-site • Contract • Full-time • Mid-level Senior\nDescription\n\nSummary:\n\nWe are seeking a skilled SharePoint and Infrastructure Engineer to join our IT team in Canberra on a contract basis. This role is crucial for enhancing our digital collaboration tools and ensuring robust infrastructure support. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in SharePoint administration and infrastructure management, contributing to the optimisation of our IT services and systems.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nAdminister and maintain SharePoint environments, ensuring optimal performance and user experience.\nDesign, implement, and manage infrastructure solutions that support business operations.\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to gather requirements and deliver effective IT solutions.\nTroubleshoot and resolve technical issues related to SharePoint and infrastructure components.\nMonitor system performance and implement improvements to enhance efficiency and reliability.\nProvide technical support and training to end-users on SharePoint functionalities.\nDocument processes, configurations, and changes to maintain accurate records.\n\nQualifications:\n\nBachelor’s degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, or a related field.\nMinimum of 5 years of experience in SharePoint administration and infrastructure management.\nStrong knowledge of Microsoft SharePoint, Windows Server, and networking concepts.\nExperience with cloud services and virtualisation technologies.\nProficient in scripting and automation tools to streamline processes.\nExcellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail.\nStrong communication and interpersonal skills to work effectively with team members and stakeholders.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c1c792040ad1c396','scraped','1 day ago'),(2527,NULL,'job','Planning Manager','Permanent','North Sydney NSW 2060',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'AI Job Summary\nProven experience working with property developers and major growth projects.\nStrong background in greenfield and brownfield utilities infrastructure, ideally in water and/or wastewater networks.\nDemonstrated capability in capacity planning, development approvals and growth-driven infrastructure delivery.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nPermanent • Full-time • Mid-level Senior\nDescription\n\nPlanning Manager – Development & Growth Enablement\n\nWater, Wastewater & Recycled Water Networks\n\nWe are seeking an experienced Planning Manager with a strong development-sector background to lead the planning and delivery of developer-driven water, wastewater and recycled water infrastructure. This is a leadership role at the interface between the utility and the development industry, enabling sustainable growth across residential, commercial and industrial developments.\n\nThis role is ideal for a planning or infrastructure leader who thrives in fast-paced growth environments, understands development pressures, and can balance commercial outcomes with technical integrity and long‑term network performance.\n\nThe Opportunity\n\nAs Planning Manager, you will be the primary point of contact for the development sector, coordinating servicing strategies, growth infrastructure, and capacity planning to ensure developments are delivered on time, on budget and compliant. You will influence outcomes across councils, regulators, developers, consultants and internal stakeholders, ensuring network capacity stays ahead of growth.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nDevelopment & Growth Leadership\n\nAct as the key interface between the utility and the development industry, providing clear, consistent and timely servicing outcomes\nLead the planning, coordination and delivery of developer-funded infrastructure, including reticulation, augmentations and growth-driven upgrades\nReview developer reticulation and connection applications, designs and staging plans, issuing permits and approvals that protect asset performance and service quality\n\nPlanning, Capacity & Program Delivery\n\nManage long-range capacity forecasting for treatment, storage and network assets across multiple schemes\nPlan and schedule greenfield and brownfield upgrades, aligning growth triggers, delivery timing and funding\nAdminister Project Delivery Agreements (PDAs), including forecasting, budgeting and capacity tracking (estimate vs design vs actuals)\n\nCommercial, Regulatory & Stakeholder Management\n\nMaintain strong controls over financial performance, forecasting and funding requirements\nManage regulatory approvals and compliance (EPA, IPART, Councils), ensuring schemes remain fully licensed and audit-ready\nRepresent the organisation professionally with developers, councils, regulators and industry bodies\n\nLeadership & Governance\n\nLead with a strong safety focus, embedding WHS compliance across all activities\nEstablish and maintain fit-for-purpose policies, plans and procedures\nDevelop and mentor a high-performing team, building capability in development servicing and infrastructure planning\n\nWhat You’ll Bring\n\nEssential Experience\n\nProven experience working with property developers and major growth projects\nStrong background in greenfield and brownfield utilities infrastructure, ideally within water and/or wastewater networks\nDemonstrated capability in capacity planning, development approvals and growth-driven infrastructure delivery\n\nQualifications & Background\n\nEngineering degree or 10+ years relevant industry experience (wastewater and/or water networks)\nUtilities construction experience\nUtilities project management experience\nStrong stakeholder and commercial management skills\nCurrent driver’s licence\n\nIf you are a strategic planning leader with deep development experience and a passion for enabling growth through smart infrastructure, we’d love to hear from you.\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\nWe are an innovator and look to solve problems no one else can\nSupportive leadership and clear development pathways\nModern office in North Sydney with great transport access and end of trip facilities\nLeadership that invests in coaching, not just metrics\nA team environment that backs each other during peak periods\nWe value performance, ownership and collaboration and we reward people who step up and contribute.\n\nApply now. Let’s have a conversation. We review applications as they come in so don’t delay.\n\nCompany Overview\nAre you a forward-thinker? Are you passionate about creating a brighter future for all? Are you full of ideas on how to better utilise power, water and data? If so, Altogether could just be the place for you. Working alongside developers and body corporates you have the opportunity to play an influential role in delivering ethical, sustainable solutions for communities and their residents – making positive change with real impact. So what’s it like working at Altogether? Here, we take a refreshing and diverse approach to culture. We understand the power of brilliant ideas. It’s what drives us. By prioritising collaboration and championing forethought, together we can solve some of the planet’s most pressing issues. We’re looking for pioneers and creators, people who are eager to make a difference. It’s not about former glories or fancy CV’s. If you’re a good human being and brimming with potential we will provide you with an opportunity. One where you’re able to craft a unique career path, supported by a range of initiatives including transformational eLearning, mentoring and professional development. Over the last two years, the idea of the office has shifted dramatically and we’ve shifted with it with technology and systems adapting to individual needs. There is life outside of work. We understand that. Your wellbeing is of the utmost importance and is key to producing consistently great work. From the introduction of Wellbeing Day to health discounts and transformational parental leave, we place the emotional and physical wellness of its staff above all. At Altogether, we’re not just going through the motions. What we do here matters. Working here, you’ll make a direct and lasting impact on the quality of life of people all across Australia. It’s about creating a better future for communities – an ambition you’ll feel driven to achieve each and every day. Altogether Group Pty Ltd is an equal opportunities employer and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any kind. All employment decisions at Altogether are based on business needs, job requirements and individual qualifications, without regard to race, colour, religion or belief, family or parental status, or any other status protected by the laws or regulations in the locations where we operate. Altogether will not tolerate discrimination or harassment based on any of these characteristics. We encourage applicants of all ages.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e3b7bd8dd261552f','scraped','1 day ago'),(2528,NULL,'job','Platform Engineer','','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We’re a leading business management solution with a core purpose: helping more businesses in Australia and New Zealand start, survive and succeed.\n\nAt MYOB, we believe what’s good for one business is good for all business—and for all of us. Whether you support them, work for them, or dream of building your own, when businesses run smoothly, everybody feels it. Owners, employees, customers, suppliers—even families. That’s why we’re here: to give every person in business the tools they need to focus on what really matters and do Big Things—whatever big looks like for them.\n\nAnd for you? Joining MYOB means being part of that impact. It means using your skills to help businesses thrive, shaping the future of work, and growing alongside the people and communities we support. Because while we’re the business of software, we’re really in the business of people. And that makes MYOB Everyone’s Business.\n\nHelp Shape the Future of AI-Powered Innovation at MYOB\n\nThis is a high-impact role at the heart of our AI transformation journey. As an AI Platform Engineer, you’ll design and build the cloud foundations that empower teams across the organization to innovate with AI—safely, at scale, and with speed.\n\nYour work will support the development of innovative products, insights, and efficiencies that will impact the future of our business. From embedding FinOps and observability to staying ahead of the latest in AI infrastructure, you’ll play a critical role in making advanced AI capabilities accessible, sustainable, and enterprise-ready.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\nBuild secure, reusable AWS infrastructure components to support internal AI and data solution teams.\nImplement platform observability with proactive monitoring and alerting for all AI and ML workloads.\nEmbed FinOps practices into platform design to drive cloud cost visibility and optimisation.\nStay across emerging AI tech and AWS updates to continually enhance platform capabilities.\nInfluence internal standards and tooling to reflect high-quality AI infrastructure.\nProvide clear guidance and enablement materials to support team adoption of platform services.\nWhat You’ll Bring\nSolid experience in cloud platform engineering, DevOps, data infrastructure, or MLOps roles.\nStrong hands-on skills with AWS services like SageMaker, Bedrock, Lambda, S3, IAM, CloudWatch, Step Functions, and API Gateway.\nConsistent record applying FinOps practices for cost tracking, tagging, reporting, and optimisation.\nExperience deploying and running data and ML workloads in AWS environments.\nSkilled in infrastructure-as-code using Terraform, AWS CDK, or CloudFormation.\nExperience integrating security, compliance, and governance into cloud-native platforms.\nFamiliarity with emerging AI technologies such as LLMs, vector databases, and orchestration frameworks.\nBachelor’s or Master’s degree or equivalent experience in Computer Science, Data Science, Machine Learning, or a related field and relevant certifications (e.g., AWS Certified Machine Learning – Specialty) are highly desirable.\nOur Culture & Benefits\nAt MYOB our values are at the heart of everything we do. If you want to work and collaborate where opinions are valued, and your ideas can make a difference, come to a place where Your Work Matters.\n\nEnjoy a flexible, hybrid workplace that brings balance to how you work, all of our centrally located offices come together for a number of in-person celebrations and social events\nSet up your home office with a little financial help from us, and take advantage of great corporate discounts and vouchers from top retailers\nBenefit from our partnership with Sonder, which supports the wellbeing of our team members\nUnlock your potential via in-house training and programs, LinkedIn Learning, conferences and study assistance\nAccess to a variety of leave options available to support your wellbeing, including up to an additional four weeks of purchased leave, generous parental leave, domestic violence leave, transgender leave, community leave, study leave, and more\nJoin our communities, built around ‘Wellness’, ‘Belonging’ and the ‘Planet’ where you can make a meaningful contribution\n\nAt MYOB, we’re all about embracing difference and backing people to be their true selves. We’re proud to be an equal opportunity employer and big believers that the best hires don’t just fit our culture — they add to it. That means bringing your unique contributions, lived experiences, and fresh perspective to the table.\n\nLove the sound of MYOB and this role but don’t tick every single box in this ad? Apply anyway! Studies show that women and underrepresented groups often hold back if they don’t meet every requirement — but we want to hear from you.\n\nWe’re proud to be a Circle Back Initiative Employer and we commit to responding to every applicant.\nWe may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Axsys','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8ae31befa102f08c','scraped','2 days ago'),(2529,NULL,'job','Full Stack Engineer','Contract','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job details\nPosted01 May 2026\nSalaryNegotiable\nLocationSydney CBD\nJob type Contract\nDiscipline Digital & Product Engineering\nReference90M0707195_1777609373\nJob description\n\nFinXL by Randstad Digital focuses on accelerating client\'s infrastructure, digital and AI transformation journeys by providing specialised skills, managed programs and strategic consulting across various industries.\n\nWe solve complex technological and business challenges with highly talented people.\n\nWe are currently seeking a Full Stack Developer to join FinXL and drive the architectural uplift, build complex wealth calculation engines and modernise legacy platforms into a scalable, cloud-native ecosystem.\n\nSkills and Experience\n\nFull Stack Engineer experience\nExperience in Java, React, MongoDB and JBoss\nExperience in Financial Advice, Wealth Management - Superannuation-Insurance or BFSI\nExperience in XPLAN, Endeavour or Midwinter\nExperience utilising AI productivity tools like GitHub Copilot or Claude\nExperience designing & developing robust back-end services and responsive front-end interfaces\nExperience writing clean, secure, and scalable code and leveraging AI productivity tools\nExperience integrating APIs and working within microservices architectures\nExperience mentoring mid-level engineers and providing technical leadership\n\nNext Steps\n\nIf you would like to apply to this fantastic opportunity please apply online or call Jackie Gibbons on 0432 268 298\n\nCode: S12','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'FinXL','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=fd0bfc6ea215bf2f','scraped','2 days ago'),(2530,NULL,'job','Account Coordinator','Internship','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Who we are:\n\nBurson, part of WPP, is the global communications leader built to create value for clients through reputation. With highly specialized teams, industry-leading technologies and breakthrough creative, we help brands and businesses redefine reputation as a competitive advantage so they can lead today and into the future. When you work at Burson, you are part of a global community of lifelong learners who thrive at the edge of innovation.\n\nWPP (LSE/NYSE: WPP) is the trusted growth partner for the world’s leading brands. We unite cutting-edge media intelligence and data solutions, world-class creativity, next-generation production, transformative enterprise solutions and expert strategic counsel in a single company – powered by exceptional talent and our agentic marketing platform, WPP Open, to help our clients navigate change, capture opportunity and deliver transformational growth. For more information, visit WPP.com\n\nFor more information visit bursonglobal.com and follow us on LinkedIn and Instagram.\n\nMore About The Role\n\nWe’re on the lookout for our next Account Coordinator to join our Corpsumer team at Burson\n\nIf you’re early in your PR & communications career and keen to work across exciting consumer brands, campaigns, and culture led moments, this could be the role for you.\n\nYou’ll join our corpsumer team, supporting integrated campaigns that span media, social, and influencer. This is a great opportunity to build your foundations in PR while gaining hands on experience across the full communications mix, from day to day media relations through to larger campaign moments.\n\nYou’ll be part of a collaborative team, learning directly from experienced consultants and getting exposure to how we bring ideas to life for some of the world’s most recognised and emerging brands.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nSupport day-to-day client servicing across consumer accounts\nMonitor media, trends, and cultural moments relevant to your clients\nAssist with drafting materials including media releases, reports, and campaign summaries\nHelp coordinate press materials, events, influencer activity, and media outreach\nSupport social and digital campaign execution\nContribute to research, ideas, and new business opportunities\nLearn from senior team members to build your storytelling and client management skills\n\nExperience That Contributes To Success\n\n6-12 months experience or internship in PR, communications, or a related field\nPassion for consumer brands, media, and pop culture and corporate\nStrong written and verbal communication skills\nCurious, proactive, and eager to learn\nInterest in social, influencer, and digital trends\nStrong attention to detail and ability to multitasks\nA team player who thrives in a fast-paced environment\n\nAdvantageous: exposure or interest in one or more of our key capability areas:\n\nEarned creative\nSocial & influence\nData & intelligence (including AI/digital)\nStrategy\n\nAt Burson, we’re driven by Craft, Curiosity, Counsel, and Camaraderie and we’re always looking for people who bring energy, ideas, and a willingness to grow.\n\nIf this sounds like you (or someone in your network), we’d love to hear from you.\n\n#PRJobs #ConsumerPR #Communications #Burson #AgencyLife #Hiring\n\nYou belong at Burson:\n\nOur vision is for Burson to be the leading ‘academy company’ for creative communications professionals and emerging leaders. We provide a dynamic environment where ambitious colleagues come to elevate their skills, expand their networks, and ultimately, produce the best solutions for today’s leading brands. Our commitment to your growth is reflected in our robust benefits and people programs, which include professional development opportunities, mentorship programs with industry leaders, a vibrant and inclusive company culture fostering collaboration and innovation and packages designed to reward and retain top talent. We invest in our people because we believe their success is our success.\n\nAt Burson, we’re an agency of learn-it-alls. We recognize that the things we do best, creativity and communications, require a level of nuanced understanding. That’s why it’s imperative for us to hire extraordinarily talented people of all backgrounds and identities. Without that we can’t do the essential work of inspiring bold ideas, fostering constructive dialogue, cultivating meaningful experiences, and driving innovation and creativity for our partners. Your unique point of view—your talent—is what makes you a #BursonPerson, and it’s how we deliver exceptional results for our clients, together.\n\nWe believe the best work happens when we\'re together, fostering creativity, collaboration, and connection. That\'s why we’ve adopted a hybrid approach, with teams in the office around four days a week. If you require accommodations or flexibility, please discuss this with the hiring team during the interview process.\n\n this will send any information you add below to Burson. Before you do this, we think it\'s a good idea to read through our Recruitment Privacy Policy. California residents should read our California Recruitment Privacy Notice. This explains what we do with your personal data when you apply for a role with us, and, how you can update the information you have provided us with or how to remove it.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Burson Global','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d17f06675918df0f','scraped','2 days ago'),(2531,NULL,'job','Platform Engineer','','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We’re a leading business management solution with a core purpose: helping more businesses in Australia and New Zealand start, survive and succeed.\n\nAt MYOB, we believe what’s good for one business is good for all business—and for all of us. Whether you support them, work for them, or dream of building your own, when businesses run smoothly, everybody feels it. Owners, employees, customers, suppliers—even families. That’s why we’re here: to give every person in business the tools they need to focus on what really matters and do Big Things—whatever big looks like for them.\n\nAnd for you? Joining MYOB means being part of that impact. It means using your skills to help businesses thrive, shaping the future of work, and growing alongside the people and communities we support. Because while we’re the business of software, we’re really in the business of people. And that makes MYOB Everyone’s Business.\n\nHelp Shape the Future of AI-Powered Innovation at MYOB\n\nThis is a high-impact role at the heart of our AI transformation journey. As an AI Platform Engineer, you’ll design and build the cloud foundations that empower teams across the organization to innovate with AI—safely, at scale, and with speed.\n\nYour work will support the development of innovative products, insights, and efficiencies that will impact the future of our business. From embedding FinOps and observability to staying ahead of the latest in AI infrastructure, you’ll play a critical role in making advanced AI capabilities accessible, sustainable, and enterprise-ready.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\nBuild secure, reusable AWS infrastructure components to support internal AI and data solution teams.\nImplement platform observability with proactive monitoring and alerting for all AI and ML workloads.\nEmbed FinOps practices into platform design to drive cloud cost visibility and optimisation.\nStay across emerging AI tech and AWS updates to continually enhance platform capabilities.\nInfluence internal standards and tooling to reflect high-quality AI infrastructure.\nProvide clear guidance and enablement materials to support team adoption of platform services.\nWhat You’ll Bring\nSolid experience in cloud platform engineering, DevOps, data infrastructure, or MLOps roles.\nStrong hands-on skills with AWS services like SageMaker, Bedrock, Lambda, S3, IAM, CloudWatch, Step Functions, and API Gateway.\nConsistent record applying FinOps practices for cost tracking, tagging, reporting, and optimisation.\nExperience deploying and running data and ML workloads in AWS environments.\nSkilled in infrastructure-as-code using Terraform, AWS CDK, or CloudFormation.\nExperience integrating security, compliance, and governance into cloud-native platforms.\nFamiliarity with emerging AI technologies such as LLMs, vector databases, and orchestration frameworks.\nBachelor’s or Master’s degree or equivalent experience in Computer Science, Data Science, Machine Learning, or a related field and relevant certifications (e.g., AWS Certified Machine Learning – Specialty) are highly desirable.\nOur Culture & Benefits\nAt MYOB our values are at the heart of everything we do. If you want to work and collaborate where opinions are valued, and your ideas can make a difference, come to a place where Your Work Matters.\n\\uD83C\\uDFA5 See what it\'s like to work at MYOB and what we\'re all about.\n\n\\uD83D\\uDFE3Enjoy a flexible, hybrid workplace that brings balance to how you work, all of our centrally located offices come together for a number of in-person celebrations and social events\n\\uD83D\\uDFE3Set up your home office with a little financial help from us, and take advantage of great corporate discounts and vouchers from top retailers\n\\uD83D\\uDFE3Benefit from our partnership with Sonder, which supports the wellbeing of our team members\n\\uD83D\\uDFE3Unlock your potential via in-house training and programs, LinkedIn Learning, conferences and study assistance\n\\uD83D\\uDFE3Access to a variety of leave options available to support your wellbeing, including up to an additional four weeks of purchased leave, generous parental leave, domestic violence leave, transgender leave, community leave, study leave, and more\n\\uD83D\\uDFE3Join our communities, built around ‘Wellness’, ‘Belonging’ and the ‘Planet’ where you can make a meaningful contribution\n\nAt MYOB, we’re all about embracing difference and backing people to be their true selves. We’re proud to be an equal opportunity employer and big believers that the best hires don’t just fit our culture — they add to it. That means bringing your unique contributions, lived experiences, and fresh perspective to the table.\n\nLove the sound of MYOB and this role but don’t tick every single box in this ad? Apply anyway! Studies show that women and underrepresented groups often hold back if they don’t meet every requirement — but we want to hear from you.\n\nWe’re proud to be a Circle Back Initiative Employer and we commit to responding to every applicant.\n\nWe may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'MYOB','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f50512186ef4e701','scraped','2 days ago'),(2532,NULL,'job','Head of Business Lending Analytics','Permanent','Australia',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Head of Business Lending Analytics\nJob number: 806906\nPrimary position location: Hybrid: Work from any Capital City in Australia\nPrimary position location: NSW- Sydney CBD\nPrimary position location: VIC- Melbourne CBD\nCategory: Business Banking\nCategory: Data & Analytics\nCategory: Information, Communication & Technology\nWork type: Permanent Full time\n Closing at: May 15 2026 - 23:55 AEST\n\nLead a high-impact team with enterprise-wide visibility and influence.\nShape the future of data-driven decisioning in NAB’s Business Lending portfolio.\nWork with a talented team and senior leaders to deliver meaningful customer and commercial outcomes.\n\nOur people are customer obsessed. They prioritise the needs and satisfaction of the customer above all else. Our mindset fosters innovation and creates strong, lasting customer relationships as we strive to be the most customer centric company in Australia and New Zealand.\n\nIn this Head of Business Lending Analytics role, you will join the Digital Data and AI team that’s doubling down on customer obsession.\n\nEach day, you’ll go above and beyond to:\n\nLead and develop a team of data & analytic professionals to design and develop actionable insights (analytic, data science, data management and/or reporting) that make a positive and demonstrable impact to Business Lending strategy and performance.\nDeliver commercial insights and recommendations that inform product development, customer proposition and risk management strategies. Support the identification and work with the business on prioritisation of analytics projects that address emerging market trends, customers’ needs and competitive dynamics.\nLead the design of innovative solutions that drive better customer outcomes, drive growth, increase efficiency and simplify processes through the adoption of new and emerging data and analytic solutions.\nPartner with business leaders to ensure alignment between analytics outputs and overall business objectives such as improving customer experiences, lifting Net Promoter Scores and increasing market share.\nUse analytics to enhance the end-to-end customer journey, identifying pain points and opportunities to digitise and improve customer interactions.\nOversee the integrity and quality of data used in analytics, ensuring compliance with regulatory requirements and internal risk frameworks.\n\nWe’re looking for the best and brightest to deliver the best for our customers. You’ll need:\n\nExtensive experience in applied advanced analytics and decision science success in Financial Services.\nExperience in Business Lending / Business Banking.\nGovernance processes and procedures, regulatory risk and compliance management.\nHands on experience leading technology / data and analytics teams.\n\nA diverse and inclusive workplace works better for everyone\n\nWe know that our people make us who we are. That’s why we have built a culture of equity and respect - where everyone feels valued and appreciated for being their authentic selves. In partnership with our multiple Employee Resource Groups (ERGs), we continue to foster an inclusive environment, where all NAB colleagues’ unique backgrounds and identities are understood, respected and celebrated. We are committed to providing an environment where you can work your way.\n\nFor details on the recruitment process, and accessibility, or alternate methods to apply for this role, please visit https://www.nab.com.au/about-us/careers/apply-for-job. To discuss adjustment requirements, please contact the NAB Careers team via nab.careers@nab.com.au (please reference job number) or visit our Careers page through the link above for other contact options.\n\nJoin NAB\n\nIf you think this role is the right fit for you, we would love to hear from you. Please note candidate screening and interviews may be conducted prior to the closing date of the job advert. Unsolicited CVs from agencies will not be accepted.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'NAB','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=23ff320fd7da3545','scraped','2 days ago'),(2533,NULL,'job','AI Automation Specialist','Contract','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job details\nPosted01 May 2026\nSalaryNegotiable\nLocationSydney\nJob type Contract\nDiscipline Digital & Product Engineering\nReference90M0707228_1777619607\nJob description\n\nAI Automation Specialist (Dev)\n\nLead AI industrialisation in Wealth Management\n\nFinXL Professional Services is a leading IT consultancy that partners with clients to bridge the gap between business needs and technology capabilities. Since 2003, we\'ve been delivering high-value ICT services across government, finance, telecommunications, and enterprise sectors.\n\nFinXL is looking for a AI Automation Specialist (Dev) to join our consulting team, and wealth management client. This isn\'t a \"lab project\", you\'ll be deployed on-site with a top-tier Wealth Management client to lead a 12-month mission-critical transformation. You will be the architect responsible for integrating Claude LLM to revolutionise paraplanning and automate the generation of reports and analytics.\n\nVisa Support: FinXL is a registered sponsor-we are able to take over existing visas or provide new sponsorship for the right candidate.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nImplement AI/LLM technologies (Claude) into financial advice workflows.\n\nBuild robust human-in-the-loop controls for AI outputs.\n\nAutomate complex data entry and claims processing.\n\nIndustrialise the paraplanning and SOA document generation process.\n\nProvide leadership on safe AI application in enterprise environments.\n\nIntegrate LLMs into manual workflows and scenario modelling.\n\nEnsure AI outputs remain fully compliant with financial regulations.\n\nKey Skills & Experience\n\nProven experience deploying AI/ML solutions in commercial settings.\n\nStrong software engineering background with LLM API integration.\n\nDeep understanding of scenario modelling and complex calculations.\n\nExperience with data engineering and table-intensive data processing.\n\nFamiliarity with regulatory constraints in financial services.\n\nPractical experience with risk mitigation in enterprise AI.\n\nAbility to provide thought leadership on pragmatic AI application.\n\nWhy Join FinXL?\n\nCutting-edge LLM and AI integration project\n\nLong-term 12-month contract opportunity\n\nLead AI industrialisation in Wealth Management\n\nNext Steps\n\nIf you would like to apply for this opportunity, please submit your CV via SEEK. Please note that due to the volume of responses, only shortlisted consultants will be contacted.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'FinXL','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=dd4249601e062616','scraped','2 days ago'),(2534,NULL,'job','B2B Campaign Manager','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Sydney/Hybrid - Full Time Employee\nWhat We Do\nPosition Summary\nWhat You’ll Do\nRequired Skills\nStrongly Preferred\nWhat you are joining\nAbout Us\n\nWe design for a world where machines see.\n\nUnleash live is transforming industries with computer vision and live data analytics. Our platform ingests video and sensor streams, processes them with machine learning, and drives decisions in real time. We build and deploy two products, Orb (Inspections) and Prism (Monitoring), for Tier 1 infrastructure operators in Utilities, Mining/Resources, and Oil & Gas. Our customers include Fortune 50 global companies.\n\nWe are an enterprise B2B provider. Our buyers are COOs, VP Operations, and Asset Managers at organisations running critical infrastructure across multiple sites. Our deals are complex, multi-stakeholder, and high value. Our marketing has to match.\n\nYou will be the engine behind pipeline growth across our primary verticals. You will work directly with the sales team, support named account campaigns, run HubSpot-native campaign execution, and build the marketing presence we need in key markets, particularly Mining, Oil & Gas North America & Australia.\n\nThis role sits between strategy and execution. You are not a channel specialist. You are not a brand person. You are a commercially minded B2B marketer who looks at a pipeline gap and asks what it will take to close it, then builds and runs the campaigns to do it.\n\nYou will operate within the CMO Engine, Unleash live\'s Claude marketing operating system, and will have access to AI tooling built specifically to accelerate research, content deployment, and campaign activation. Comfort with AI tools is not optional. This is an AI-first environment.\n\n5+ years in B2B marketing with enterprise deal sizes above $100K. You must have worked in environments where the sales cycle is 6 months or longer and the buying committee involves multiple stakeholders. SaaS growth marketing or consumer-adjacent roles are not the background we need.\n\nHubSpot Proficiency & Contact Database Ownership. You can build lists, set up sequences, create campaigns, configure tracking, and pull attribution reports without support. Beyond execution, you will own the health of the marketing contact database, actively managing contact limits, auditing and cleaning segment lists, and ensuring every list we run against is targeted, accurate, and commercially relevant. You will suppress dead weight, enrich where gaps exist, and maintain segmentation logic that reflects how we actually sell. If you need a MarTech specialist to run basic campaign infrastructure or a data analyst to tell you your lists are broken, this is not the right role.\n\nAI-first working habits. You use AI tools daily, not occasionally. You understand how to prompt effectively, how to integrate AI into research and campaign workflows, and how to operate within a governed AI system. Comfort with structured AI tooling, agent-assisted workflows, and Notion-based operating systems is essential.\n\nCommercial instinct. You look at pipeline data and draw conclusions. You understand why a deal stalls at the introduction stage and what marketing can do about it. You are not a channel executor waiting to be briefed.\n\nExperience in one or more of Energy, Utilities, Oil and Gas, or Mining. Not required, but the mental models of selling into regulated, asset-intensive infrastructure operators takes time to build.\n\nExperience with ABM programmes or named account campaign execution. Not the title, the actual work: building target account lists, running multi-touch campaigns against named accounts, tracking account-level engagement, feeding intelligence back to sales.\n\nExperience operating in a fast-moving, resource-constrained environment where you have had to make judgment calls about where to spend your time rather than working through a fully resourced campaign team.\n\nA marketing function with a structured operating system, governed AI tooling, and direct access to commercial data. You will not be starting from scratch. The Unleash marketing Kernel, the target account list, the HubSpot infrastructure, and the product marketing foundation are in place. What is missing is the person who runs campaigns consistently against named accounts and generates pipeline in the verticals where we have the most commercial runway.\n\nThe company is growing and the marketing function is growing with it. This role has a clear development path as the team scales toward FY27 and FY28.\n\nUnleash live is a leading Australian-born deep tech company transforming how the world’s most critical industries interact with data. We specialize in cutting-edge computer vision, turning live visual data into immediate, actionable insights across the globe.\n\nBy operating at the intersection of AI and autonomy, our platform enables enterprises and governments to monitor and optimize infrastructure with unprecedented precision. From bushfire detection to energy grid resilience, we help machines not just capture the world, but understand it.\n\nAward-Winning Innovation\n\nOur commitment to excellence has been recognized on the global stage:\n\nForbes 100 to Watch: Named one of the most promising startups in the Asia-Pacific region.\n\nAFR AI Award (2025): Winner for Productivity & Efficiency in Energy.\n\nAustralian AI Awards: Finalist for AI Innovator in Critical Infrastructure.\n\nTrusted by Global Leaders\n\nWe are proud to partner with industry giants to solve complex operational challenges, including:\n\nChevron, BHP, and Alcoa\n\nSouth32 and Weatherford\n\nFlorida Power & Light, Endeavour Energy, Essential Energy, Ausgrid\n\nOur Culture\n\nOur diverse team of \"thinkers and tinkerers\" is driven by a shared obsession: solving hard problems with impactful technology. Whether you are seeking world-class industrial solutions or a fast-moving team to join, we are leading the way in tapping the true potential of live data.\n\nPipeline activation across Energy, Mining, and O&G (Priority Focus). Work directly with the global sales leads across Tier 1 verticals to build account-level campaign programmes. This means account research, outbound sequence support, content amplification, event coordination, and HubSpot campaign execution tied to named accounts. The output is qualified pipeline, not impressions.\n\nSales-aligned campaign execution. You will be the strategic marketing partner to the sales team, not just executing behind requests, but advising on best-practice activation (email, webinar/podcast, events, sponsorship, ad campaigns etc), coaching reps on what works, and bringing market-tested campaign thinking to every account pursuit. When a rep is working an account, you shape the campaign strategy around it. When a deal needs content or sequencing, you bring a point of view on what will move it. You will own HubSpot campaign architecture, contact segmentation, sequence design, and attribution tracking and you will hold the standard on CRM discipline across the team.\n\nPipeline Gap Analysis & Cross-Channel Activation. You will identify where pipeline is thin, absent, or stalled across verticals and buying stages and build the activation strategy to address it. Where ICP accounts are under-represented, you will design and run targeted cross-channel campaigns to create presence and generate qualified demand. This includes paid social (LinkedIn), content distribution, event presence, and coordinated outbound sequences into named accounts. You will work closely with the PMM function to ensure campaign assets are vertical-specific and commercially grounded, not generic, so that every activation speaks directly to the economic and operational priorities of the buyer.\n\nMid-funnel support. You will support activation of existing pipeline through nurture content, account follow-up sequences, and coordinated outreach that helps uncover the specific operational problems that moves a conversation forward.\n\nMetrics and attribution. You will own campaign-level reporting. Every campaign you run will have a defined objective, a target account list, HubSpot tracking, and a result. You will report to the Head of Marketing on pipeline contribution, engagement rates across target accounts, and deal-level marketing activity.\n\nApply Now\n\nPlease enter your details and attach your resume to the form to apply now.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Unleash live','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=386ed26abcbbadc8','scraped','2 days ago');
INSERT INTO `offerings` VALUES (2535,NULL,'job','Expression of Interest — Heidi Entry Program','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'This is truly a once-in-an-eon opportunity for the smartest young folk across the globe.\n\nWe review EOIs on a rolling basis and reach out directly when roles open. Submitting early puts you at the front of the queue. This is not a live vacancy, it is your chance to get on our radar first.\n\nRare is it that one of the world\'s fastest-growing startups opens its ranks to junior generalists for on-the-job experience that requires no prior track record.\n\nThis is not about whether you already know Growth, Product, Operations or anything else. What we care about is raw intelligence, judgment, and a bias toward building real things.\n\nThe specific skills can be taught quickly. The underlying hardware cannot.\n\nPolish is irrelevant. Execution is not.\n\nIf your instinct is to explain what you would do rather than to actually do it, you will struggle here.\n\nWho We Are\n\nHealthcare needs a better rhythm: one that keeps care continuous and deeply human. Heidi is building an AI Care Partner that works alongside clinicians to make that possible.\n\nWe’re a team of doctors, engineers, designers, researchers, and creatives building tools that help clinicians stay focused on what matters most: their patients.\n\nIn just 18 months, Heidi has given back more than 18 million hours to healthcare professionals — supporting 73 million patient visits in 116 countries. Today, more than two million patient visits each week are powered by Heidi worldwide.\n\nBacked by nearly $100 million in funding, we’re growing in the US, UK, Canada, and Europe, partnering with leading health systems including the NHS, Beth Israel Lahey Health, and Monash Health.\n\nWhat We’re Looking For\n\nYou’ll need to be impeccably sharp and omnitalented - context switching across multiple functions\n\nYou DON\'T need any experience. That\'s a plus - what we’re really looking for is the correct raw ingredients (intelligence / agency)\n\nYou’ll bear the existential weight of the company as much as the founders & early employees.\n\nIf you’re the right fit - you’ll love every moment of it.\n\nSomeone looking for uncapped growth. You don\'t want to be limited by yearly promotion programs and the general lameness of the corporate world. Your ability to win defines the gradient of your growth.\n\nYou studied math/physics/chem deeply or are a gifted writer. It\'s a proxy for general raw ability.\n\nWhat do we believe in?\n\nHeidi builds for the future of healthcare, not just the next quarter, and our goals are ambitious because the world’s health demands it. We believe in progress built through precision, pace, and ownership.\n\nLive Forever - Every release moves care forward: measured, safe, and built to last. Data guides us, but patients define the truth that matters.\n\nPractice Ownership - Decisions follow logic and proof, not hierarchy. Exceptional care demands exceptional standards in our work, our thinking, and our character.\n\nSmall Cuts Heal Faster - Stability earns trust, speed delivers impact. Progress is about learning fast without breaking what people depend on.\n\nMake others better - Feedback is direct, kindness is constant, and excellence lifts everyone. Our success is measured by collective growth, not individual output.\n\nOur mission is clear: expand the world’s capacity to care, and do it without losing the humanity that makes care worth delivering.\n\nWhy You’ll Flourish With Us\n\nReal Impact: Work on a product that genuinely saves clinicians’ time and improves patient care.\n\nDedicated Mentorship: Learn from experienced engineers who are invested in your growth.\n\nFlexible Environment: A flexible, hybrid setup to help balance work and study.\n\nCareer Growth: High-performers will be strongly considered for full-time graduate roles.\n\nA Great Team: Join a passionate, motivated, and friendly team building the future of healthcare.\n\nHeidi is dedicated to creating an equitable, inclusive, and supportive work environment that brings people together from diverse backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives. Our strength is in our differences. We\'re proud to be an equal opportunity employer and welcome all applicants as we\'re committed to promoting a culture of opportunity for all.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Heidi','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f01375fda9867399','scraped','2 days ago'),(2536,NULL,'job','Platform Engineer','Full-time','Eight Mile Plains QLD 4113',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job\n\nThe Platform Engineer designs, builds, and maintains the Simpro platform infrastructure to ensure scalability, reliability, and performance. Operating with a 70% development and 30% platform focus, this role requires a strong software engineering background to build the tools and abstractions that power our systems. The Platform Engineer will automate testing, deployment, and configuration management processes; select appropriate hardware and software components; configure networking and storage resources; and create security policies.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nAt Simpro, we build the software that powers the trades and field service industry across Australia, New Zealand, North America, and the UK. Our platform team sits at the heart of that owning the cloud infrastructure, the internal developer platform, and the pipelines that get code from development into production safely and fast.\n\nWe\'re looking for a Platform Engineer who\'s genuinely comfortable on both sides of the fence: someone who understands how applications work and knows AWS inside out. If you\'ve come from a development background and gravitated toward the infrastructure side of things, this role was probably written for you.\n\nYou\'ll join a team of six based in Brisbane, working directly with development teams across the business to architect, maintain, and improve our AWS cloud environment. That means owning infrastructure-as-code in Terraform, contributing to our Internal Developer Platform (already ~70% built and growing), and helping developers ship services to production quickly and safely. You\'ll also be part of an on-call rotation so when things go sideways, you\'ll be the person who knows how to fix it.\n\nWhat You’ll Bring\n\nDeep, working knowledge of AWS - Lambda, EC2, EKS, RDS, SQS, IAM, SSM, and the broader ecosystem. Not just the concepts, but knowing what breaks and how to fix it.\n\nKubernetes - cluster management, scaling groups, ports, and production-level troubleshooting\n\nTerraform - we run everything through it, so this is non-negotiable\n\nCI/CD pipeline experience - we use Jenkins, but if you know GitHub Actions or Buildkite, you\'ll pick it up\n\nPostgreSQL / SQL database fundamentals\n\nA development background, or strong experience working closely with engineering teams on application architecture\n\nClear communication - you\'ll be translating between infra and dev teams regularly, and writing RCAs during incident\n\nWhat would set you apart\n\nAWS Solutions Architect certification\n\nExperience with cloud security practices - IAM policies, secrets management, security group design, and compliance controls\n\nExperience with HashiCorp tooling beyond Terraform\n\nExposure to Internal Developer Platform concepts\n\nComfort using AI coding tools (Claude Code is part of our workflow) with the judgement to know when not to trust them\n\nThe environment\n\nThis team moves fast. There are real incidents, real pressure, and a genuine on-call commitment. The flip side is a team culture that\'s relaxed, collaborative, and not at all corporate. New starters are expected to be in office full-time.\n\nWhat We Can Offer You\n\nNovated leasing via salary packaging\n\nEmployee Assistance Program (24/7 confidential support on relationships, bereavement, finances)\n\nGenerous Parental Leave Program\n\nPaid Volunteer Leave Days\n\nPublic Holiday Exchange Scheme\n\nTalent Referral Program – get rewarded for referring a friend to join our team!\n\nCasual dress and relaxed office environment\n\nFun team camaraderie and events\n\nOpportunities for career progression and development\n\nDiverse training & internal networking opportunities across all of our product lines\n\nService recognition awards\n\nClick here to find out more about working at Simpro Group!\n\nOur Core Values\n\nWhile experience in the above areas will be highly considered, it’s important to note it will be secondary to the person with the right determination, attitude and compatibility. Our culture and core values are very important to us:\n\nWe Are One Team\n\nWe Are Customer Centric\nWe Are Growth Minded\nWe Are Accountable\nWe Celebrate Success\n\nSimpro, AroFlo, BigChange & ClockShark are equal opportunity employers with a best-of-class onboarding program and supportive team environments. We embrace and support culture diversity and Equal Employment Opportunity. Aboriginals, Torres Strait Islanders and minority groups are encouraged to apply. .\n\nVisit simprogroup.com/au/company/careers to learn more about us and our values.\n\nWe would like to take this opportunity to thank all candidates for their application.\n\n*Please note, no agencies will be accepted in the recruitment of this role.\nWelcome\n\nWelcome to Simpro! Together with AroFlo, BigChange and ClockShark we are one team made up of many nationalities. We are customer-centric, always putting our customers and teammates first. We take accountability, owning both our innovations and our mistakes. We\'re growth-minded, constantly learning and evolving. And most of all, we celebrate our successes together!\n\nAbout Us\n\nSimpro Group provides best-in-class SaaS field service management solutions to trade and field service businesses worldwide. The group comprises four industry-leading companies, Simpro, AroFlo, BigChange and ClockShark, with offices across North America, Australia, New Zealand and the UK. Simpro, AroFlo & BigChange provide comprehensive field service management software for growth-minded trade and field service businesses, while ClockShark specializes in time-tracking and scheduling software solutions. Together, these companies seek to drive businesses forward with solutions that empower teams to work smarter, provide foundations for business scaling, and offer data-driven insights to fuel decision-making. Simpro Group serves over 22,000 businesses and over 400,000 users worldwide and has a global workforce of more than 600 employees.\nReady to transform your business? Explore our products at simprogroup.com, aroflo.com, bigchange.com and clockshark.com.\n\nHeadline: Important Recruitment Fraud Alert\n\nSimpro Group has been made aware of fraudulent recruitment activity where individuals are impersonating our company and hiring managers to deceive job applicants.\n\nThese scammers are using a fraudulent website and email domain (simprogroupcareers.com) and may contact you with illegitimate job offers. Their goal is typically to steal your personal information for identity theft or to trick you into paying for fake application fees, background checks, or equipment. If you have been contacted by someone you suspect is not a legitimate Simpro Group recruiter, or if you have any doubts about a job posting, please do not respond. Do not provide any personal information or payment.\n\nWe take this matter very seriously and have reported this fraudulent activity to the relevant global authorities. We are committed to ensuring a safe and transparent recruitment process for all candidates.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Simpro','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=bbf16023bed60167','scraped','2 days ago'),(2537,NULL,'job','Digital Political Journalist - Canberra','Full-time','Canberra ACT',NULL,'',94000.00,'Up to $94,000 a year','At SBS, we embrace difference, and we welcome applications from people of all backgrounds.\n\nWe also acknowledge the unique contribution that Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples make to our society and our workplace through their enduring and continued connection to land, sea, sky and community.\n\nThis role is classified as a Level 3 role under SBS Australia\'s current Enterprise Agreement with a base salary of up to $94,000. The successful applicant will be offered remuneration that is commensurate with their skills and experience and in alignment with this framework.\n\nThis role is a permanent, full-time position based in Canberra.\n\nThis role is primarily structured around a Monday to Friday roster; however, it may include irregular hours, weekends and public holidays depending on operational requirements. Shift patterns may change over time, and SBS may require you to work reasonable overtime, which will be paid in accordance with the SBS Enterprise Agreement.\n\nThe Role\n\nWe have an exciting opportunity for a passionate and driven Digital Journalist to join SBS News in Canberra, reporting from Parliament House.\n\nWe’re looking for someone with a strong interest in politics who shares our vision and is committed to delivering distinctive journalism that reflects modern Australia.\n\nThis is a digital-first role focused on producing timely, accurate and engaging political content, while also contributing to broader SBS News coverage across platforms where required.\n\nThis role will contribute news, feature and explainer articles to SBS News as well as working in collaboration with our digital video team, providing coverage on SBS News site and app, YouTube, TikTok, Instagram and Facebook.\n\nThis role will see you:\n\nProducing breaking news, analysis, features and explainers on Australian politics for SBS News’ digital platforms\nReporting from Parliament House, delivering timely and insightful coverage of national political developments\nGenerating and progressing original story ideas across a broad range of political topics, including national politics, foreign policy, immigration and defence\nApplying sound editorial judgement to complex or sensitive issues to ensure accuracy, balance and clarity\nFiling engaging multi-format content, including articles, live blog contributions and visual or data-led storytelling\nContributing to editorial discussions and forward planning, identifying upcoming stories and opportunities\nCollaborating with colleagues across SBS News (Digital, TV, Audio, Social and NITV) to maximise coverage and storytelling\nBuilding and maintaining a strong network of political contacts to support reporting\n\nAbout you\n\nYou are a confident and capable journalist with strong political awareness and editorial judgement, who thrives in a fast-paced newsroom and is passionate about delivering distinctive journalism.\n\nIdeally, you will:\n\nHave proven experience delivering digital journalism in a fast-paced newsroom environment\nHave strong knowledge of the Australian political landscape\nBe able to deliver complex or sensitive reporting with accuracy and clarity\nHave excellent writing skills and the ability to produce content for digital audiences\nBe confident generating original story ideas and pursuing them with initiative\nHave an understanding of media law, editorial standards and the SBS Charter\n\nYou should also bring:\n\nA strong understanding of digital publishing, including SEO, headline writing and audience engagement\nExperience using analytics tools (e.g. Chartbeat, Adobe) to inform editorial decisions\nThe ability to manage competing priorities in a fast-paced news environment\nA collaborative mindset and strong communication skills\nFlexibility to work outside standard hours, including occasional weekends and travel as required\nAn existing network of political contacts, and the ability to build and develop it to support reporting and sourcing\n\nAs part of our recruitment process, SBS may conduct reference checks and review information that is publicly available online, including social media profiles, in line with privacy and anti-discrimination laws. If we collect information from any other sources, candidates will be notified in line with privacy laws.\n\nWe value authenticity and expect all applications and submissions to reflect your own voice, ideas, opinions and critical thinking. While we recognise that AI tools may be used to support drafting CVs or cover letters, the final content must remain your own. Throughout the recruitment process, including interviews and assessment tasks, we ask that you do not use AI tools unless we explicitly advise otherwise.\n\nSome of the reasons to consider working with us:\n\nThe people! We truly celebrate and welcome difference at SBS and encourage everyone to bring their whole self to work & you’ll be part of one of the most inclusive companies in Australia!\nThe culture and the engagement of our workforce! 90% of our employees have stated that they are proud to work for SBS!\nWe offer a range of benefits from, health care checks, salary packaging, Employee Assistance Programme, flexible work arrangements and discounted gym membership nationally with Fitness Pass.\nWe’re agile and innovative in the way we work, as well as being a trusted and established brand. At SBS we have been broadcasting for over 50 years and our future is packed with many more exciting developments!\nWe also love to promote from within! Our divisions support development opportunities to help team members grow and move into new roles.\n\nWant to learn more? Then hit apply and take the first step to applying not just for another job but a possible whole new career in a purpose led organisation.\n\nFor other opportunities within our organisation please visit our careers website SBS Careers - Working at SBS\n\nAbout Us\n\nSBS is one of the world\'s most unique and innovative media organisations, producing trusted, meaningful, and engaging content that exists for all Australians to inspire, support and celebrate the diversity of our multicultural society.\n\nOur purpose, for over 50 years, has reflected and explored the evolving diversity of Australia, investing in initiatives to deepen connections with communities, sharing their stories and giving a voice to those often unheard, with the aim of increasing understanding and respect of the differences that make up Australia.\n\nSBS is a truly distinctive network, showcasing multicultural, multilingual and First Nations stories otherwise untold in the Australian media.\n\nReasonable adjustments\n\nSBS recognises that everyone is unique, and you might require some adjustments to ensure you have the best opportunity to apply and put your skills forward for consideration. If we can make some adjustments to the SBS recruitment/interview process to better enable you to shine, then please contact careers@sbs.com.au and let us know.\n\nAdjustments include but are not limited to; alternative application methods, interview setups, physical requirements, guidance for trans or gender diverse applicants, specific interview availability times and more.\n\nTo find out more about reasonable adjustments with SBS, please view our video here.\n\nWe are shortlisting applications as they come in, so don’t delay, apply today!\n\nPosition Description','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'SBS','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=62d12604a93c4eae','scraped','2 days ago'),(2538,NULL,'job','Account Coordinator','Internship','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Who we are:\n\nBurson, part of WPP, is the global communications leader built to create value for clients through reputation. With highly specialized teams, industry-leading technologies and breakthrough creative, we help brands and businesses redefine reputation as a competitive advantage so they can lead today and into the future. When you work at Burson, you are part of a global community of lifelong learners who thrive at the edge of innovation.\n\nWPP (LSE/NYSE: WPP) is the trusted growth partner for the world\'s leading brands. We unite cutting-edge media intelligence and data solutions, world-class creativity, next-generation production, transformative enterprise solutions and expert strategic counsel in a single company – powered by exceptional talent and our agentic marketing platform, WPP Open, to help our clients navigate change, capture opportunity and deliver transformational growth. For more information, visit WPP.com\n\nFor more information visit bursonglobal.com and follow us on LinkedIn and Instagram.\n\nMore About The Role\n\nWe\'re on the lookout for our next Account Coordinator to join our Corpsumer team at Burson\n\nIf you\'re early in your PR & communications career and keen to work across exciting consumer brands, campaigns, and culture led moments, this could be the role for you.\n\nYou\'ll join our corpsumer team, supporting integrated campaigns that span media, social, and influencer. This is a great opportunity to build your foundations in PR while gaining hands on experience across the full communications mix, from day to day media relations through to larger campaign moments.\n\nYou\'ll be part of a collaborative team, learning directly from experienced consultants and getting exposure to how we bring ideas to life for some of the world\'s most recognised and emerging brands.\n\nWhat You\'ll Do\n\nSupport day-to-day client servicing across consumer accounts\nMonitor media, trends, and cultural moments relevant to your clients\nAssist with drafting materials including media releases, reports, and campaign summaries\nHelp coordinate press materials, events, influencer activity, and media outreach\nSupport social and digital campaign execution\nContribute to research, ideas, and new business opportunities\nLearn from senior team members to build your storytelling and client management skills\n\nExperience That Contributes To Success\n\n6-12 months experience or internship in PR, communications, or a related field\nPassion for consumer brands, media, and pop culture and corporate\nStrong written and verbal communication skills\nCurious, proactive, and eager to learn\nInterest in social, influencer, and digital trends\nStrong attention to detail and ability to multitasks\nA team player who thrives in a fast-paced environment\n\nAdvantageous: exposure or interest in one or more of our key capability areas:\n\nEarned creative\nSocial & influence\nData & intelligence (including AI/digital)\nStrategy\n\nAt Burson, we\'re driven by Craft, Curiosity, Counsel, and Camaraderie and we\'re always looking for people who bring energy, ideas, and a willingness to grow.\n\nIf this sounds like you (or someone in your network), we\'d love to hear from you.\n\n#PRJobs #ConsumerPR #Communications #Burson #AgencyLife #Hiring\n\nYou belong at Burson:\n\nOur vision is for Burson to be the leading \'academy company\' for creative communications professionals and emerging leaders. We provide a dynamic environment where ambitious colleagues come to elevate their skills, expand their networks, and ultimately, produce the best solutions for today\'s leading brands. Our commitment to your growth is reflected in our robust benefits and people programs, which include professional development opportunities, mentorship programs with industry leaders, a vibrant and inclusive company culture fostering collaboration and innovation and packages designed to reward and retain top talent. We invest in our people because we believe their success is our success.\n\nAt Burson, we\'re an agency of learn-it-alls. We recognize that the things we do best, creativity and communications, require a level of nuanced understanding. That\'s why it\'s imperative for us to hire extraordinarily talented people of all backgrounds and identities. Without that we can\'t do the essential work of inspiring bold ideas, fostering constructive dialogue, cultivating meaningful experiences, and driving innovation and creativity for our partners. Your unique point of view—your talent—is what makes you a #BursonPerson, and it\'s how we deliver exceptional results for our clients, together.\n\nWe believe the best work happens when we\'re together, fostering creativity, collaboration, and connection. That\'s why we\'ve adopted a hybrid approach, with teams in the office around four days a week. If you require accommodations or flexibility, please discuss this with the hiring team during the interview process.\n\nWhen you click the \"Submit Application\" button below, this will send any information you add below to Burson. Before you do this, we think it\'s a good idea to read through our Recruitment Privacy Policy. California residents should read our California Recruitment Privacy Notice. This explains what we do with your personal data when you apply for a role with us, and, how you can update the information you have provided us with or how to remove it.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Burson','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=61535f11d93e0c32','scraped','2 days ago'),(2539,NULL,'job','Support Engineer, Region Services','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nApplicants must be Australian citizens and hold or be eligible to obtain an Australian Government Security Clearance with the ability to successfully complete an Organisational Suitability Assessment. For more information regarding security clearances please visit (https://www.agsva.gov.au/).\n\nThe AWS Region Services team combines AWS global cloud leadership with Australian security expertise to deliver highly secure, scalable environments for sensitive workloads. We’re creating innovative ways to use cloud computing, artificial intelligence, and machine learning while maintaining the highest standards of security and operational excellence.\n\nThe Engineering organisation within Region Services is structured across core capability pillars: Compute & Machine Learning, Security Identity & Compliance, Storage & Databases, and a growing capability domain. Collectively these pillars encompass a team of varying technical skillsets, including Engineers; Technical Program Managers and Subject Matter Experts, organised into focused sub-teams.\n\nThis is an opportunity to make a lasting impact on Australia’s digital future. You’ll work with AWS services, implement innovative solutions, and help customers succeed in their most important missions. We’re committed to helping our builders grow through continuous learning, mentoring, and collaboration with industry experts. Are you ready to build the future of secure cloud computing in Australia?\n\nKey job responsibilities\n- Apply advanced troubleshooting techniques to provide unique solutions to our customers\' needs\n- Interact with engineers and partner with other AWS teams to help reproduce and resolve issues\n- Leverage your extensive Linux and technical experience to provide feedback to internal AWS teams on how to improve our services\n- Drive service team communication during critical events\n- Drive projects that improve support-related processes and our operational experience\n- Write tutorials, how-to videos, and other technical articles for the developer community\n- Work on critical, highly complex problems that may span multiple AWS services\n- Apart from working on a broad spectrum of technical issues, an AWS Support Engineer may also coach/mentor new hires, develop & present training, partner with development teams on complex issues or contact deflection initiatives, participate in new hiring, write tools/script to help the team, or work with leadership on process improvement and strategic initiatives\n- Applicants must be Australian citizens and hold or be eligible to obtain an Australian Government Security Clearance with the ability to successfully complete an Organisational Suitability Assessment. For more information regarding security clearances please visit (https://www.agsva.gov.au/).\n\nA day in the life\nFirst and foremost this is a Linux technical support role – in the Cloud. On a typical day, a Support Engineer will be primarily responsible for solving internal operational issues, preparing or reviewing operational dashboards, working through our change management system to modify systems, writing new run-books for newly onboarded services, training other new Support Engineers, and using our internal AI systems in problem solving and diagnosis.\n\nYou will be required to occasionally participate in an “on-call” rotations to resolve incidents occurring out-of-hours.\n\nAbout the team\nRegion Services provides the highest caliber Operational Solutions and Cleared Support for services within our Regions. We provide \'hands on keyboard\' support to our service teams by deploying changes into these isolated regions, monitoring the results, and reporting any issues that are observed.\n\nDiverse Experiences\nAmazon values diverse experiences. Even if you do not meet all of the preferred qualifications and skills listed in the job description, we encourage candidates to apply. If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying.\n\nWhy AWS\nAmazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.\n\nWork/Life Balance\nWe value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve in the cloud.\n\nInclusive Team Culture\nAWS values curiosity and connection. Our employee-led and company-sponsored affinity groups promote inclusion and empower our people to take pride in what makes us unique. Our inclusion events foster stronger, more collaborative teams. Our continual innovation is fueled by the bold ideas, fresh perspectives, and passionate voices our teams bring to everything we do.\n\nMentorship and Career Growth\nWe’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional.\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- 5+ years support engineering or system admin experience on Linux or Unix systems\n- Deep understanding of scalable computing systems\n- Good working knowledge/experience on highly distributed virtual environment, networking, software build and deployment process\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Experience troubleshooting and debugging technical systems\n- Bachelor\'s degree or equivalent in a related technical field\n- Knowledge of cloud computing concepts and design considerations\n- Experience with networking fundamentals including hands-on experience with load balancers, switches, routers, etc.\n- Familiar with the challenges surrounding efficient operations and failure mode analysis in large complex distributed systems\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Support Services Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=181c1acf8b3943c1','scraped','2 days ago'),(2540,NULL,'job','Sales Operations - Scheduling Coordinator','Contract','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',61407.00,'$54,576 - $68,238 a year','At SBS, we embrace difference and we welcome applications from people of all backgrounds.\nWe also acknowledge the unique contribution that Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples make to our society and our workplace through their enduring and continued connection to land, sea, sky and community.\n\nThis role is classified as Level 1 role under SBS Australia\'s current Enterprise Agreement (with a base salary range of $54,576 - $68,238 pro-rata). The successful applicant will be offered remuneration that is commensurate with their skills and experience and in alignment with this framework.\n\nThe Role\n\nThe SBS Media Sales Operations team is looking for a motivated Sales Operations Scheduling Coordinator who is eager to learn the fundamentals of media sales in a supporting entry level role.\n\nThis position is ideal for someone looking to build a long-term career in Media Sales. The successful candidate will assist the media sales team by providing sales support, administrative coordination, and managing the delivery of advertising materials.\n\nThe duties include but are not limited to:\n\nProvide general support to the sales team: this goes from basic administrative duties to making sure all advertising materials/ spots are received and spots booked.\nSchedule and book TV Advertisement spots across, SBS, SBS Viceland, NITV, SBS World Movies, SBS FOOD and SBS Worldwatch.\nAssist and advise with e-mails from Group Sales Managers, Sales Representatives and their Coordinators.\nDaily spot booking duties/ Schedule Validation/ Sponsorship adherence/ General Scheduling Duties.\nMonitor inventory and work in a fantastic team to create an error free on-air environment.\nExciting projects include World Cup, Eurovision, Tour De France and new SBS commissions.\n\nAbout you\n\nWe are looking for a team player who is proactive and has a can-do attitude. Ideally the candidate will be able to work autonomously as well as in a team. Ideally, you would have:\n\nStrong computer skills (Microsoft Outlook, Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint) and be keen to learn new software packages.\nExcellent communication skills and good attention to detail (a must).\nWell-developed written and verbal communication skills, strong interpersonal skills, with a polite yet confident demeanour.\nDemonstrated ability to balance competing priorities to meet set targets/outcomes.\nWell-developed customer service skills, with the ability to be flexible and uphold these in a demanding deadline driven environment.\nA tertiary education is preferred but not necessary.\n\nAs part of our recruitment process, SBS may conduct reference checks and review information that is publicly available online, including social media profiles, in line with privacy and anti-discrimination laws. If we collect information from any other sources, candidates will be notified in line with privacy laws.\n\nWe value authenticity and expect all applications and submissions to reflect your own voice, ideas, opinions and critical thinking. While we recognise that AI tools may be used to support drafting CVs or cover letters, the final content must remain your own. Throughout the recruitment process, including interviews and assessment tasks, we ask that you do not use AI tools unless we explicitly advise otherwise.\n\nSome of the reasons to consider working with us\n\nThe people! We truly celebrate and welcome difference at SBS and encourage everyone to bring their whole self to work, you’ll be part of one of the most inclusive companies in Australia!\nThe culture and the engagement of our workforce! 90% of our employees have stated that they are proud to work for SBS!\nWe offer a range of benefits, from health checks, salary packaging, Employee Assistance Programme, flexible work arrangements and discounted gym membership nationally with Fitness Pass.\nWe’re agile and innovative in the way we work, as well as being a trusted and established brand. At SBS we have been broadcasting for over 50 years and our future is packed with many more exciting developments!\nWe also love to promote from within! Our divisions support development opportunities to help team members grow and move into new roles.\n\nWant to learn more? Then hit apply and take the first step to applying not just for another job but a possible whole new career in a purpose led organisation.\n\nFor other opportunities within our organisation please visit our careers website SBS Careers - Working at SBS\n\nAbout Us\n\nSBS is one of the world\'s most unique and innovative media organisations, producing trusted, meaningful and engaging content that exists for all Australians to inspire, support and celebrate the diversity of our multicultural society.\nOur purpose, for the last 40 years, has reflected and explored the evolving diversity of Australia, investing in initiatives to deepen its connections with communities, sharing their stories and giving a voice to those often unheard, with the aim of increasing understanding and respect of the differences that make up Australia.\nSBS is a truly distinctive network, showcasing multicultural, multilingual and First Nations stories otherwise untold in the Australian media.\n\nReasonable adjustments\n\nSBS recognises that everyone is unique, and you might require some adjustments to ensure you have the best opportunity to apply and put your skills forward for consideration. If we can make some adjustments to the SBS recruitment/interview process to better enable you to shine, then please contact careers@sbs.com.au and let us know.\n\nAdjustments may include but are not limited to; alternative application methods, interview setups, physical requirements, guidance for trans or gender diverse applicants, specific interview availability times and more.\n\nTo find out more about reasonable adjustments, please view our short video here.\n\nWe are shortlisting applications as they come in, so don’t delay, apply today!\n\nJob Description','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'SBS','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a780be56b09f626e','scraped','2 days ago'),(2541,NULL,'job','Operations Capability Consultant','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'General Information\nLocation\nSydney, New South Wales\nAlternative Location(s)\nPosting Location: Sydney, New South Wales\n\nWorking Schedule\nFull-Time\nWork Arrangement\nHybrid\nRelocation Assistance Available\nNo\nPosted Date\n01-May-2026\nJob ID\n17237\nDescription and Requirements\n\nThe Operations Capability Consultant plays a critical role in strengthening capability across MetLife Australia’s Operations teams by designing, delivering and continually improving learning solutions that support business performance. Guided by our purpose — always with you, building a more confident future — and our New Frontier strategy, this role focuses on equipping teams with the technical, regulatory and behavioural skills required to deliver strong customer and business outcomes.\n\nWorking closely with Operations, Claims, Underwriting and People & Culture leaders, you’ll act as a trusted learning partner, supporting continuous improvement and capability uplift across the organisation.\n\nKey Responsibilities\nDesign, deliver and evaluate engaging face‑to‑face, virtual and hybrid training solutions aligned to operational capability needs.\nDevelop and facilitate life insurance technical training programs across underwriting, claims and operations, including assessments and curriculum management.\nAnalyse quality assurance findings to identify capability gaps and partner with leaders to implement targeted training solutions.\nCoach and mentor team members to support skill development, performance improvement and change adoption.\nManage training administration, learning content and compliance within the Learning Management System (LMS).\n\nRequired Qualifications\nCertificate IV in Training and Assessment (Diploma or Degree preferred).\n3–5 years’ experience in a life insurance underwriting and/or claims environment.\nStrong understanding of life insurance principles, underwriting guidelines and risk management practices.\nDemonstrated experience designing and delivering technical and soft‑skills learning in operational environments.\nExcellent communication, facilitation and stakeholder engagement skills.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\nExperience delivering virtual and hybrid learning solutions, including eLearning and digital content.\nKnowledge of medical terminology and insurance regulatory and compliance frameworks.\nExperience supporting organisational change and continuous improvement initiatives.\nWillingness to travel occasionally to other MetLife locations to support training deliver.\nComfort using AI-enabled and digital productivity tools (e.g. Microsoft 365 Copilot or similar), where appropriate, to support productivity and continuous improvement in line with MetLife policies and controls.\n\nBenefits We Offer\n\nWhen you join MetLife Australia, you are joining a company that demonstrates holistic care and wellbeing for employees with benefits and programs that address physical, mental, social and financial health. We offer life insurance benefits, generous paid parental leave, market leading menopause and fertility leave, car leasing and more. As well as Employee Assistance Program (EAP), access to 360Health medical support, volunteer leave and study assistance.\n\nAbout MetLife\n\nRecognised on Fortune magazine\'s list of the \"World\'s Most Admired Companies\", Fortune World’s 25 Best Workplaces™, as well as the Diversity Council of Australia Inclusive Employer Award, MetLife, through its subsidiaries and affiliates, is one of the world’s leading financial services companies; providing insurance, annuities, employee benefits and asset management to individual and institutional customers. With operations in more than 40 markets, we hold leading positions in the United States, Latin America, Asia, Europe, and the Middle East.\n\nOur purpose is simple - to help our colleagues, customers, communities, and the world at large create a more confident future. United by purpose and guided by our core values - Win Together, Do the Right Thing, Deliver Impact Over Activity, and Think Ahead - we’re inspired to transform the next century in financial services. At MetLife, it’s #AllTogetherPossible. Join us!','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'MetLife','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f2d253428d982811','scraped','2 days ago'),(2542,NULL,'job','Customer Project Manager','','North Ryde NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Join our Team\n\nAbout this opportunity\nJoin Ericsson as a Customer Project Manager within ANZA Cloud Software & Services, where you will lead the delivery of complex, high-impact customer programs across 5G core networks, cloud-native platforms, and service transformation initiatives. In this role, you will take full ownership of project strategy, governance, and execution, leveraging industry-leading methodologies and tools to deliver scalable, future-ready solutions. You will act as a trusted delivery partner to customers, translating business and network needs into tangible outcomes while ensuring efficiency, innovation, and operational excellence.\n\nWhat you will do\n\nLead end-to-end delivery of customer projects across scope, schedule, cost, risk, and quality\nDevelop robust project plans, secure resources, and drive execution to successful completion\nOwn project financials including budgeting, forecasting, margin management, and cost control\nProactively identify and manage risks, issues, changes, and interdependencies\nLead governance forums, steering committees, and provide clear, data-driven status reporting\nBuild and maintain strong, trusted relationships with customers, partners, and internal stakeholders\nEnsure compliance with contractual obligations, safety standards, and governance frameworks\nSupport pre-sales and transition activities, including solution alignment and contract inputs\nDrive continuous improvement through automation, innovation, and delivery optimization initiatives\nCapture lessons learned and contribute to evolving project management best practices\n\nThe skills you bring\n\nBachelor’s degree in Engineering, Telecommunications, Computer Science, or a related discipline\nProject Management certification (PMP, PMI-ACP, or equivalent preferred)\n5+ years of experience managing complex customer or delivery programs, with 3+ years in telecom or IT environments\nStrong financial and commercial acumen, with proven experience managing budgets, forecasts, and resources\nSolid understanding of networked systems, service delivery models, and operational KPIs\nExperience working in customer-facing, contractual delivery environments with senior stakeholder exposure\nStrong analytical, problem-solving, and decision-making capabilities\nPractical understanding of automation and AI tools (e.g., Microsoft Copilot, Glean) and their application in delivery excellence\nAbility to translate customer business needs into actionable delivery outcomes\n\nHighly desirable:\n\nExposure to 5G Core network applications and/or cloud infrastructure, including cloud-native architectures, containers, virtualization, and hyperscaler platforms\n\nKey attributes:\n\nStrong leadership and stakeholder management skills with the ability to influence at all levels\nConfident communicator, comfortable engaging with senior executives and customer leadership teams\nResults-driven, resilient, and able to manage competing priorities in dynamic environments\nStructured, proactive, and solutions-oriented mindset\nComfortable operating in fast-paced, multi-stakeholder, and technology-driven environments\n\nWhy join Ericsson?At Ericsson, you´ll have an outstanding opportunity. The chance to use your skills and imagination to push the boundaries of what´s possible. To build solutions never seen before to some of the world’s toughest problems. You´ll be challenged, but you won’t be alone. You´ll be joining a team of diverse innovators, all driven to go beyond the status quo to craft what comes next.\n\nWhat happens once you apply?Click Here to find all you need to know about what our typical hiring process looks like.Encouraging a diverse and inclusive organization is core to our values at Ericsson, that\'s why we champion it in everything we do. We truly believe that by collaborating with people with different experiences we drive innovation, which is essential for our future growth. We encourage people from all backgrounds to apply and realize their full potential as part of our Ericsson team. Ericsson is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. learn more.\n\nWe are proud to announce at Ericsson Australia, our employees have once again voted us as a Great Place to Work® and we have been officially Certified™ in 2025. Every year, more than 10,000 organizations from over 60 countries partner with the Great Place to Work® Institute for assessment, benchmarking and planning actions to strengthen their workplace culture and this Certification acknowledges our employees value their employee experience and our workplace culture.\n\nEricsson Australia Employee Benefits\n• Wellness: Ericsson Australia offers a variety of programs crafted to support your physical and emotional wellbeing.\n• Paid Time Off: We encourage all employees to switch off to recuperate and recharge through paid time off.\n• Work Conditions: Looking to find better work / life balance? Speak to us about flexible work arrangements**\n• Employee Discounts: We offer employees access to discounted health insurance, groceries and entertainment through our partner providers.\n• Employee Development: Working at Ericsson gives you access to Degreed, an integrated learning platform where you can learn, upskill, develop and measure your skills.\n\nPrimary country and city: Australia (AU) || Sydney\n\nReq ID: 783807','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Ericsson','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=bbe1a648fe818b85','scraped','2 days ago'),(2543,NULL,'job','Software Engineer','Permanent','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Join our Payments Platform and play a key role in the engineering delivery of our Open Payments Platform. We\'re building a modern real-time Payments platform that is highly reliable, scalable, and based around no-ops technology. As a Payments Platform within a Digital Bank, software engineering is at the core of what we do. Our engineers operate in an autonomous environment where they are empowered to \"do it right\" and continuously learn, becoming masters in their craft.\nAt Macquarie, our advantage is bringing together diverse people and empowering them to shape all kinds of possibilities. We are a global financial services group operating in 31 markets and with 56 years of unbroken profitability. You’ll be part of a friendly and supportive team where everyone - no matter what role - contributes ideas and drives outcomes.\nWhat role will you play?\n\nWe are seeking a Senior Engineer to contribute to the engineering and technical direction of our Open Payments Platform. This is a great opportunity for an experienced engineer looking to deepen their craft, take ownership of critical platform components, and grow their influence within a high-performing team.\n\nIn this role, you will work on one or more core components of the Payments Platform, contributing to reliability, performance, and operational excellence. Reporting to the Engineering Manager and working closely with the lead engineer, you will be an active voice in technical discussions and decision-making within the team, and a go-to resource for peers seeking technical guidance.\n\nYou will bring a hands-on, high-output approach to delivering high-quality code, and will help elevate the technical proficiency of the team through knowledge sharing, mentorship, and rigorous code reviews. You will translate architectural guidance into solid technical designs and implementation plans, balancing ideal solutions with delivery timelines and business needs.\n\nWhat you offer\n\nConsistently and quickly delivers high-quality, robust features and components.\nDeep, hands-on experience with Java and Spring Boot, with solid exposure to Google Cloud and NoSQL databases.\nStrong working knowledge of microservices and event-driven architecture, design patterns, and integration approaches.\nA good understanding of security best practices for financial transactions and payments.\nExperience participating in and leading incident management, seeing incidents through to resolution.\nActive contributor to tech debt management and DevOps/reliability practices.\nExperience and understanding of using AI tools to enhance and improve the development process\nAbility to mentor and uplift other engineers through code reviews, coaching, and knowledge sharing.\nClear communicator who can collaborate effectively with product managers, other engineering teams, and other stakeholders.\nExperience in payments/cards domain preferred.\n\nWe love hearing from anyone inspired to build a better future with us, if you\'re excited about the role or working at Macquarie we encourage you to apply.\nWhat we offer\n\nAt Macquarie, you’re empowered to shape a career that’s rewarding in all the ways that matter most to you. Macquarie employees can access a wide range of benefits which, depending on employment type, include:\n\n1 wellbeing leave day per year\nUp to 5 additional service bonus leave days per year\nUp to 20 weeks’ paid parental leave for primary caregivers along with 12 days of transition leave upon return to work, and 6 weeks’ paid leave for non-primary caregivers\n2 days of paid volunteer leave and donation matching\nUp to 12 months’ gender affirmation leave, including 6 weeks’ paid leave\nAccess to Employee Assistance Program and wellbeing benefits including skin and health checks, and flu vaccinations\nAccess to a wide range of salary packaging options\nAccess to a wide range of learning and development opportunities, including reimbursement for professional membership or subscription\nHybrid and flexible working arrangements, dependent on role\nReimbursement for work from home equipment\nAbout Banking and Financial Services\n\nBanking and Financial Services is our technology-driven retail bank. You will be part of a team that supports clients to achieve their full potential - whether that’s buying a home, growing a business or investing to manage wealth.\nOur commitment to diversity, equity and inclusion\n\nWe are committed to fostering a diverse, equitable and inclusive workplace. We encourage people from all backgrounds to apply and welcome all identities, including race, ethnicity, cultural identity, nationality, gender (including gender identity or expression), age, sexual orientation, marital or partnership status, parental, caregiving or family status, family and domestic violence status, neurodiversity, religion or belief, disability, or socio-economic background. We welcome further discussions on how you can feel included and belong at Macquarie as you progress through our recruitment process. To learn more, contact our team by clicking here.\n\nOur aim is to provide reasonable adjustments to individuals who may need support during the recruitment process and through working arrangements. If you require additional assistance, please let us know in the application process.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Macquarie Group Limited','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2ef1213572323a48','scraped','2 days ago'),(2544,NULL,'job','Education and Training Manager - HSECi','Full-time','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'General Information\nLocation\nMelbourne, Victoria\nAlternative Location(s)\nPosting Location: Melbourne, Victoria\n\nWorking Schedule\nFull-Time\nWork Arrangement\nHybrid\nRelocation Assistance Available\nNo\nPosted Date\n01-May-2026\nJob ID\n17410\nDescription and Requirements\n\nThe Education and Training Manager plays a key role in building capability across MetLife’s HSECi team, supporting our partnership with Hostplus to deliver a market‑first service experience for members. Guided by our purpose — always with you, building a more confident future — and our New Frontier strategy, this role focuses on equipping employees with the skills, knowledge and ways of working required to deliver high‑quality, compliant and efficient member outcomes.\n\nYou will design, deliver and continuously improve practical learning solutions, leveraging digital and AI‑enabled tools (where appropriate) to enhance learning effectiveness, productivity and engagement in line with MetLife‑approved technologies and governance.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nDesign and maintain practical training programs aligned to HSECi service models, operational priorities and regulatory requirements.\nDeliver and facilitate face‑to‑face, virtual and digital learning solutions, including induction, refresher and upskilling programs.\nDevelop and refresh learning materials (e‑learning, SOPs, guides, assessments and facilitator content) to reflect process, system and policy changes.\nApply and promote responsible use of MetLife‑approved AI and digital tools (including Microsoft 365 Copilot) to enhance learning outcomes and efficiency.\nMonitor and improve training effectiveness using participation data, feedback, quality insights and performance outcomes.\n\nRequired Qualifications\n\nMinimum 5 years’ experience in learning and development, with a strong focus on training design and delivery.\nProven instructional design and facilitation capability across in‑person, virtual and digital learning environments.\nPractical experience using digital learning platforms and tools, with applied experience using AI tools to support work outputs.\nStrong judgement, attention to quality and ability to operate effectively in regulated environments.\nExcellent stakeholder engagement, communication and prioritisation skills.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\nTertiary qualifications in Education, Learning and Development or a related discipline.\nCertifications in instructional design or digital learning tools.\nExperience supporting learning in insurance, superannuation or financial services environments.\nExposure to change, transformation or capability uplift programs within operational teams.\n\nBenefits We Offer\n\nWhen you join MetLife Australia, you are joining a company that demonstrates holistic care and wellbeing for employees with benefits and programs that address physical, mental, social and financial health. We offer life insurance benefits, generous paid parental leave, market leading menopause and fertility leave, car leasing and more. As well as Employee Assistance Program (EAP), access to 360Health medical support, volunteer leave and study assistance.\n\nAbout MetLife\n\nRecognised on Fortune magazine\'s list of the \"World\'s Most Admired Companies\", Fortune World’s 25 Best Workplaces™, as well as the Diversity Council of Australia Inclusive Employer Award, MetLife, through its subsidiaries and affiliates, is one of the world’s leading financial services companies; providing insurance, annuities, employee benefits and asset management to individual and institutional customers. With operations in more than 40 markets, we hold leading positions in the United States, Latin America, Asia, Europe, and the Middle East.\n\nOur purpose is simple - to help our colleagues, customers, communities, and the world at large create a more confident future. United by purpose and guided by our core values - Win Together, Do the Right Thing, Deliver Impact Over Activity, and Think Ahead - we’re inspired to transform the next century in financial services. At MetLife, it’s #AllTogetherPossible. Join us!','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'MetLife','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6bc306f6755ff45b','scraped','2 days ago'),(2545,NULL,'job','Client Technical Support','Full-time','Blenheim Road NSW 2113',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Let’s be unstoppable together!\n\nAt Circana, we are fuelled by our passion for continuous learning and growth, we seek and share feedback freely, and we celebrate victories both big and small in an environment that is flexible and accommodating to our work and personal lives. We have a global commitment to diversity, equity, and inclusion as we believe in the undeniable strength that diversity brings to our business, employees, clients, and communities. With us, you can always bring your full self to work. Join our inclusive, committed team to be a challenger, own outcomes, and stay curious together.\n\nCircana is proud to be Certified™ by Great Place To Work®. This prestigious award is based entirely on what current employees say about their experience working at Circana.\n\nLearn more at www.circana.com.\n\nSo, why Circana?\n\nWe’re progressive, inclusive and people focused. We seek to create a down-to-earth culture which balances work and home life and enables our team to be the best that it can be. Our people are important to us, and we offer a number of fantastic benefits including;\n\nFlexible and hybrid working\nUp to 5 weeks annual leave and holiday buy back scheme\n16 weeks paid parental leave\nBirthday leave\nSummer half days\nCircana “Me” Days (4 per year!)\nCultural swap days\n\nWhat will you be doing?\n\nThis role sits at the heart of delivering an outstanding client experience. You will be the go to expert for helping internal and external customers solve AI driven technical challenges and get the best out of Circana’s products and services. You will troubleshoot issues, simplify complex concepts, and turn challenges into wins for our clients.\n\nBy responding quickly and thoughtfully, you will help build lasting partnerships and high levels of customer satisfaction. You will also work closely with cross functional teams to continually improve service quality and shape a seamless end to end client experience.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nAct as the first point of contact for clients, diagnosing and resolving issues across AI solutions including model performance, integrations, and configuration challenges\nPartner with clients to help them get the most from AI products by sharing best practices for setup, customisation, and ongoing optimisation\nOwn support requests end to end by tracking, prioritising, and resolving tickets efficiently, with clear escalation to L2 and L3 teams when required\nMonitor AI applications and data pipelines for errors, anomalies, or outages, taking proactive action to prevent client impact\nDevelop and maintain clear, helpful resources such as knowledge base articles, troubleshooting guides, FAQs, and client training materials\nCapture client insights and feedback and collaborate with product and engineering teams to influence enhancements and future feature development\nAssist with validating bug fixes, patches, and product updates to ensure a reliable and high-quality experience before release to clients\nGuide clients on data preparation, formatting, preprocessing, and best practices for security and compliance when working with AI tools\nWork closely with product managers, engineers, and customer success teams to resolve issues, improve services, and deliver exceptional client outcomes\n\nRequirements\n\nBachelor’s degree in computer science, information technology, engineering, or a related field preferred\nPrevious experience in technical support, help desk, or client success roles, ideally within SaaS, enterprise, or AI driven products\nStrong problem solving skills, with experience diagnosing issues across applications, APIs, and system integrations\nFoundational knowledge of AI concepts, cloud platforms, and APIs, with a strong interest in how these technologies are applied\nFamiliarity with AI systems, natural language processing tools, or machine learning based products\nExperience using tools such as Jira, Confluence, CRM platforms, or similar bug tracking and documentation systems\nFamiliarity with Circana tools, including Unify+, model and report building, and ideally Emiri, with prior experience considered a strong advantage\nExcellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to clearly explain technical concepts to non technical audiences\nConfidence creating clear documentation, including FAQs, support articles, and knowledge base content\nBilingual capability is a plus, particularly English with Spanish, German, or Italian\nProven ability to manage multiple client priorities with professionalism, organisation, and efficiency\nFlexibility to work across different time zones, shifts, or on call rotations when required\nA genuine passion for technology, combined with curiosity and a desire to continuously learn about emerging AI tools and trends\n\nCircana Behaviours\n\nAs well as the technical skills, experience and attributes that are required for the role, our shared behaviours sit at the core of our organization. Therefore, we always look for people who can continuously champion these behaviours throughout the business within their day-to-day role:\n\nStay Curious: Being hungry to learn and grow, always asking the big questions\nSeek Clarity: Embracing complexity to create clarity and inspire action\nOwn the Outcome: Being accountable for decisions and taking ownership of our choices\nCentre on the Client: Relentlessly adding value for our customers\nBe a Challenger: Never complacent, always striving for continuous improvement\nChampion Inclusivity: Fostering trust in relationships engaging with empathy, respect and integrity\n Commit to each other: Contributing to making Circana a great place to work for everyone\n\nReady to make an impact?\n\nIf you’re passionate about solving complex technical problems with AI, thrive in a collaborative environment, and want to be part of a company that truly values your growth, we’d love to hear from you. Apply now and let’s build something great together.\n\nIf you require accessibility support or would like to request reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process, we encourage you to reach out to us at accessibility@circana.com\n\nProspective candidates may be asked to consent to background checks (in accordance with local legislation and our candidate privacy notice). Your current employer will not be contacted without your permission.\n\n#LI-JM2','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Circana','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5049f6baa11c0f0a','scraped','2 days ago'),(2546,NULL,'job','AI Data and Automation Analyst','Permanent','Tomago NSW 2322',NULL,'',3000.00,'Up to $3,000 a year','Posted Date: 1 May 2026\nLocation:\n\nTomago, NSW, AU\n\nAt WesTrac, we’re made for more of what matters most. More family time, with paid parental leave, flexible working arrangements and purchased leave programs to give you the work life balance you’ve always wanted. More development opportunities, with WesTrac\'s own in house RTO - 50737, access to your own guided learning platform and a range of pathways to help you steer your career in the direction of your dreams. More diversity, with over 4,000 team members with a tonne of differences, united by our passion for building a better tomorrow. As an industry leader and employer of choice, we’re Made for More.\n\nWe have an exciting opportunity to join WesTrac on a full-time, permanent basis (40 hours) as an AI data and Automation Specialist in a newly created, business‑facing role. This position is ideal for someone who is keen to get stuck in, build capability from the ground up, and help shape how automation, data and AI are used across the organisation.\n\nWhat you will do:\n\n· Analyse and document current processes, systems and ways of working, providing clear feedback and practical recommendations on improved and more efficient ways of doing things\n\n· Identify opportunities to apply automation, data and AI to improve efficiency, insight and business outcomes\n\n· Work with stakeholders to assess feasibility, value, risk and readiness for change\n\n· Develop clear, well‑reasoned business cases to support investment decisions\n\n· Support and project manage approved initiatives through each stage of the stage‑gate process\n\n· Oversee implementation, embedding and training to ensure solutions are adopted and deliver value\n\n· Manage stakeholders throughout the change, balancing business needs, expectations and outcomes\n\n· Ensure all solutions align with data governance, privacy, ethical AI principles and GDPR requirements\n\nWhat you will need:\n\nExperience in business analysis, automation, data or AI‑related roles (typically 3–6 years)\nStrong ability to analyse current ways of working and identify better, more efficient approaches\nExperience developing business cases and supporting technology or process change initiatives\nProven stakeholder engagement and communication skills\nAn understanding of data governance, privacy and ethical considerations in AI implementation\nA practical, outcomes‑focused mindset with the ability to follow initiatives through end‑to‑end\nExperience in construction, mining or industrial environments is beneficial but not essential.\n\nWhat we can offer you:\n\nAs one of the World\'s leading Caterpillar dealers, WesTrac services a broad range of customers across NSW, ACT & WA. Our ongoing success is attributed to the individuals that make up our teams, which is why we offer a competitive benefits package and pride ourselves on our Safe, Engaged and Customer Focused Culture. As a WesTrac team member you will receive:\n\nJob security and serious potential for advancement.\n program – work alongside your mates and receive up to $3000!\nAnnual Remuneration and performance review.\nFitness Passport for the whole family.\nFlexible work arrangements.\nIncome protection with 24/7 coverage.\n12 weeks paid parental leave.\nOnline Learning Library to support your continued development.\nSalary Packaging + Novated leases.\nDiscounts with Blackwood’s, Apple, JB Hi-Fi, Qantas, Travel Club and more.\nEmployment Assistance Program (EAP) – This is available for you and your family.\nAbility to purchase additional annual leave.\n\nIf you believe you have the skills and experience to thrive in this role, please submit your application online. For further information, contact the Recruitment Team on 1300 797 028 and qoute job number 5659.\n\nAt WesTrac, our focus is our people. We proudly support equal employment opportunities and foster a diverse and inclusive workplace culture where everyone can succeed.\n\nAt WesTrac, our primary focus is our people. As we look to the future, we\'re focused on harnessing the best talent and providing them with the support they need to achieve success. WesTrac is a member of the Diversity Council of Australia and recognises the value of and strongly supports the principles of equal employment opportunities in the workplace, and is committed to continuing to build our workplace culture.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'WesTrac','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=47ca7f69705a6df7','scraped','2 days ago'),(2547,NULL,'job','Consultant (HR/IR and Payroll Assurance)','Permanent','Australia',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'AI Job Summary\nExperience drafting employment agreements and policies.\nExperience with case research, case preparation and advocacy support.\nCompleted or close to completing a degree in Industrial Relations, HR, Law, Business or related field.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nOn-site • Permanent • Full-time • Associate\nDescription\n\nWelcome to Exant Advisory: where new ideas flourish and careers thrive.\n\nAre you ready to shape the future of business and make a real difference in the lives of clients? At Exant Advisory (Exant), we believe strong relationships, collaboration, experience and new thinking are the keys to lasting success—for our clients, our team, and you.\n\nExant combines the multi-disciplined specialist knowledge expected in a top-tier firm with the approachability and care factor of an independent firm.\n\nExant Advisory is a relationship-focused firm, combining over 40 years’ experience with new thinking to deliver practical, tailored solutions across accounting, audit, business advisory and business consulting, corporate finance, HR & IR consulting, outsourcing, superannuation, tax and wealth management.\n\nWith 14 partners and more than 160 professionals, we collaborate closely with clients to develop bespoke strategies, drawing on our deep expertise and forward-looking approach. We prioritise people and relationships, investing in the ongoing success of our clients, our team, and the wider community.\n\nExperience. New Thinking.\n\nThis role is for people who want variety, exposure and complexity, not narrow experience in one practice area. It is for someone who wants to build real capability in human resources, industrial relations and payroll assurance, with coaching from recognised leading industry experts.\n\nYou will be involved in:\n\nDrafting of employment agreements and policies\nCase research, case preparation and other advocacy support\nInterpretation of legislation, Awards and Enterprise agreements\nPayroll audit and assurance\nWorkplace investigations\nProvision of advice in relation to performance and development, discipline and dismissal\nOrganisational restructuring\nEnterprise bargaining\nConflict management\nEmployee engagement and cultural reviews\n\nThis role suits someone who:\n\nHas completed (or is close to completing) a degree in Industrial Relations, Human Resources, Law, Business or related field\nIs curious, analytical, enjoys problem-solving and can communicate clearly\nWants exposure to a variety of work and industries\nIs comfortable forming views and solutions, backed by research\nIs open to a consulting career\n\nDiscover the benefits of working at Exant\n\nYour Growth. Your Well-being. Our Commitment.\n\nAt Exant, your talents are nurtured, your ambitions are celebrated, and your well-being is our top priority. As a valued member of our team, you’ll experience more than just a job—you’ll find a supportive environment where professional growth and personal fulfillment go hand in hand. From opportunities for ongoing learning to a culture that champions balance and innovation, Exant is dedicated to empowering you every step of the way. Explore the unique advantages of joining our community:\n\nWellbeing initiatives\nEmployee assistance program\nVolunteering opportunities\nEmployee referral program\nCharity and community events\nSocial club and activities\nDiscounts on products and services\nLearning and development programs\nStudy assistance\nParental leave payments\nYears of service rewards\nRecognition rewards\n\nJoin Us—Shape Your future with Exant\n\nWe invite you to discover the opportunity to join a team that challenges the status quo, drives positive change, and makes a real-world impact every day. Whether you’re just beginning your career or looking to reach new heights, Exant is where your future can flourish.\n\nExperience New Thinking. Experience Exant.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=62918fec9913f438','scraped','2 days ago'),(2548,NULL,'job','Clinical Innovation and Medical Engagement Lead','Full-time','Inner West NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job Description:\n\nBetter and fairer care. Always.\n\nSt Vincent\'s has been a leader in Australia\'s health and aged care landscape for more than 165 years. Since our founders, the Sisters of Charity, opened our first hospital in 1857, our services and nearly 30,000 people have been behind some of Australia\'s most important medical breakthroughs. We are a microcosm of Australia’s health and aged care system and are uniquely positioned to lead and respond to our rapidly changing environment.\n\nYou will be joining St Vincent’s as we launch our exciting new vision Bringing Care Home, which will take the best of St Vincent’s care beyond our hospitals and aged care homes directly into the homes of our communities across the country, making care more personal and accessible. Bringing Care Home is more than a strategy. It’s how we’ll deliver care that is better, fairer, and more connected – for everyone we serve.\n\nWe are looking for a special kind of person - a St Vincent’s kind of person. Someone who puts excellence, compassion, connection and caring for other people at the heart of everything they do.\n\nThe Opportunity\n\nReporting directly to the National Chief Medical Officer, the Clinical Innovation and Medical Engagement Lead is an enterprise role created for a doctor who wants to help shape the future of clinical practice across St Vincent’s Health Australia.\n\nThis role is designed for a clinician with curiosity, credibility and an innovation mindset, someone who sees the opportunity to work beyond traditional boundaries while remaining deeply connected to the realities of medical practice. You will help strengthen medical engagement and experience across SVHA, while enabling clinicians to access innovation, digital capability, AI‑enabled tools, and “tools of the trade” that genuinely support care delivery.\n\nYou will act as a trusted connector between clinicians, executives and product and digital teams, ensuring that innovation is clinician‑centred, practical, and grounded in real workflows. Working primarily through influence rather than formal authority, you will help translate strategy into meaningful clinical change and support the shift from disconnected pockets of excellence to deliberate, enterprise‑wide collaboration.\n\nThis is a role for a doctor who wants to have impact at scale, improve how clinicians experience work, and help build the next generation of care models, workforce capability and clinical leadership across the organisation.\n\nThis is a permanent full‑time position based at any of our Group Head Offices in Sydney, Brisbane or Melbourne. The role supports a hybrid working arrangement, ideally two days per week onsite and three days working from home. Travel to SVHA facilities will be required several times per month.\n\nKey responsibilities of the role:\n\nEnterprise Medical Engagement: Build trusted relationships with doctors (JMOs through to VMOs) to strengthen connection and a shared identity as St Vincent’s clinicians.\nClinical Innovation: Enable collaboration to move from isolated pockets of excellence to coordinated, shared approaches to clinical innovation and new models of care.\nDigital & AI Enablement: Support the adoption of digital and AI-enabled clinical tools by working with clinicians to understand needs and address concerns.\nStrategic Project Enablement: Partner with programs like Bringing Care Home to support the design and development of new clinical services.\nMedical Workforce Future: Contribute to shaping the skills, roles, and career pathways of St Vincent’s future medical workforce.\nActing CMO: Provide high-level support with the ability and willingness to act as the National CMO when required.\n\nThings that work for us:\n\nA registered medical practitioner with a minimum of 5 years post-qualification experience.\nDiverse professional background outside the clinical setting, ideally experience in management consulting, a health start-up, or relevant/similar settings.\nDemonstrated ability to frame problem statements, manage complex projects, and synthesise ideas into clear briefs and presentations.\nStrong stakeholder management skills with the ability to influence and build trust without formal authority.\nA willingness to \"roll up your sleeves\" and facilitate workshops, create presentations, and drive initiatives forward while maintaining a growth mindset for professional development.\nPostgraduate experience ideally in digital health, AI enabled healthcare or innovation programs (desirable).\n\nThings that work for you:\n\nYour work directly influences the efficiency of a leading healthcare provider, ensuring more resources reach those in our care\nEnjoy a genuine balance with a hybrid model based out of our modern offices in Sydney, Brisbane, or Melbourne\nCompetitive salary packaging options\nDirect mentorship from the National CMO and support for further professional development\nDiscounted private health insurance\nEmployee Assistance Program for staff and their families\nAccess to the Fitness Passport (FP)\n\nAt St Vincent’s we value inclusivity and diversity and acknowledge the importance of creating a work environment that is welcoming, safe, fair and impartial and invites people from all backgrounds to join us.\n\nPre-Employment Checks\n\nYour employment is conditional upon the completion of all required pre-employment checks, including relevant immunisations.\n\nEqual Opportunity\n\nWe celebrate diversity & inclusion and are committed to equal employment opportunity for everyone.\n\nHow To Apply\n\nPlease submit your application via the Apply button, include your resume and a brief cover letter outlining your experience and suitability.\n\nRespectfully, no recruitment agencies.\n\nClosing Date:\n22 May 2026 11:59pm\n\nReconciliation Action Plan:\n\nAt St Vincent\'s we acknowledge the importance of creating a work environment that is welcoming, safe, equitable and inclusive for Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander Employees. As part of our Commitment to Reconciliation and Closing the Gap in employment related outcomes, we encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples.\n\nFor further information, visit https://www.svha.org.au/about-us/reconciliation or get in contact at indigenouscareers@svha.org.au','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'St Vincent\'s Health Australia','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a5e1e2d30b13800c','scraped','2 days ago'),(2549,NULL,'job','Public Relations Lead','Full-time','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'At AustralianSuper, we truly care about our colleagues.We know work and life are intertwined. That ’ s why we support the diverse needs of everyone and have policies that enable us all to thrive and be truly flexible. We ensure diversity is celebrated for the opportunity it provides us all to learn and grow and deliver better outcomes for members. We are dedicated to building a high-performance environment underpinned by a strong risk culture, ensuring we deliver the best outcomes for our members.\n\nYour New Role\n\nThe Public Relations Lead is a key member of the team responsible for leading and coordinating public relations campaigns, consumer media engagement and content development in the Corporate Affairs area.\n\nThis 3-month role will help position, promote and protect the Fund’s reputation in earned and owned channels with a particular focus on consumer media.\n\nKey duties include but are not limited to:\n\nSupport the development and execution of public relations strategies and plans to position and promote the Fund through consumer media, owned and other channels.\nBuild and enhance relationships with key consumer media representatives to support the successful execution of the Fund’s public relations and consumer media activity.\nMonitor the consumer media landscape to support the provision of insights to the Chief Strategy Officer, Head of Corporate Affairs and the Head of Corporate Affairs and Public Relations, to inform the Fund’s positioning on key issues and help identify opportunities to enhance the Fund’s reputation through public relations activity and consumer media engagement.\nSupport the execution of the Corporate Affairs & Public Relations content plan, ensuring it is consistent with the Fund’s broader corporate communications strategy, compliant, and is in line with the Fund’s corporate narratives and messaging.\nEnsure Corporate Affairs & Public Relations content, including but not limited to website, social media, and other digital content is accurate, up-to-date and compliant with the Fund’s regulatory obligations and internal guidelines.\nEnsure risk is managed in accordance with the Fund’s Risk Management Framework including risk identification and management, risk profiling, risk reporting and incident management.\nWhere appropriate, ensure third party suppliers and service providers are managed in accordance with the Fund’s Supplier Relationship Management Framework.\nWork with service providers and internal stakeholders to secure strong governance arrangements, including reporting and service standard frameworks.\n\nWhat You’ll Need\n\nMinimum 5 years’ relevant public relations experience preferably in an agency setting or in similar in-house role in a highly regulated industry.\nDemonstrated experience executing public relations activity that achieves measurable outcomes and drives engagement with consumers.\nProven stakeholder management skills.\nExceptional written and verbal communications skills.\nDemonstrated experience developing compelling and effective digital content in a highly regulated environment.\nDemonstrated ability to work collaboratively and engage positively with colleagues.\n\nLife at AustralianSuper\n\nAustralianSuper is committed to colleague development, and we support our people with ongoing learning, coaching and training, as well as career opportunities across our expanding global organisation. We offer generous leave entitlements and promote a blended working environment in which all roles can flex, and we’re happy to discuss what this looks like for you.\n\nWe cultivate a workplace that champions safety, respect, inclusiveness and diversity. We are committed to supporting our diverse workforce in a way that is inclusive and embraces diversity in all its forms. If you require any reasonable adjustments to the recruitment process or the role, please let our recruitment team know.\n\nWhat’s Next\n\nApply now, if you share our values of Energy, Integrity, Generosity of Spirit and Excellent Outcomes and would like the opportunity to work in a challenging, growing and rapidly evolving team to deliver outstanding results.\n\nAustralianSuper uses AI to review resumes and conduct initial phone interviews. This involves processing your resume, cover letter, and voice recording in Australia and the USA to help assess your suitability for the applied role. When invited to an AI phone screening, you may opt for a traditional phone screening instead. For information on how we handle your personal data, please refer to our Candidate Privacy Policy.\n\nhttps://www.australiansuper.com/careers/candidate-privacy-notice\n\nAustralian or New Zealand citizenship or Australian permanent residency status is required.\n\nAgencies please note: this vacancy is being managed directly by AustralianSuper’s Talent Acquisition team. We will contact our preferred agency partners should we require additional support. Thank you.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'AustralianSuper','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=908e24813f520121','scraped','2 days ago'),(2550,NULL,'job','Data & Performance Analyst (Sydney/Melbourne/Brisbane)','Permanent','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'AI Job Summary\nStrong SQL skills to write queries independently.\nExperience configuring HubSpot CRM, managing data, and workflow automation.\nPower BI proficiency including DAX and multi-source data modelling.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nPermanent • Full-time • Mid-level Senior\nDescription\n\nAbout JMC Academy\n\nFounded in 1982, JMC Academy is Australia’s premier institution in Creative Industries education, offering a diverse range of Degrees and Diplomas in Music, Songwriting, Audio Engineering, Film and Television Production, Acting, Entertainment Business Management, Visual Communication (Design), Animation, Game Design, and Music Production.\n\nWith a 40-year legacy, JMC Academy provides cutting-edge and technologically advanced programs that meet the global demands of the creative industries. JMC operates from 3 large footprint campuses across the east coast of Australia (VIC, NSW & QLD), teaches ~2,500 students per annum and is positioned as one of the largest private higher education providers in Australia.\n\nWith advanced-design campuses, ongoing technology upgrades, a dedicated team of academics and industry professionals, and a network of international master class lecturers, JMC Academy is committed to ensuring our graduates make their own indelible mark on industry.\n\nOur Purpose\n\nWe educate and inspire creative minds to shape their careers and our world\n\nAt JMC Academy, we educate and empower creative minds to transform their passion into lifelong careers and meaningful contributions to the world.\n\nAs a vibrant, inclusive community of innovators and explorers, we deliver rigorous, real-world education in the creative industries, uniting academic excellence with practical experience, emerging technologies and industry engagement.\n\nWe nurture resilience, compassion, and curiosity in every student, helping them chart their unique path, shape their careers, and become creative leaders who inspire, connect, and thrive, locally and globally.\n\nOur Vision\n\nTo be the global leader in creative education, chosen by creatives, trusted by industry.\n\nOur Values\n\nCreative Innovators – An opportunity to dream, bring our creative genius to life, making meaningful contribution and delivering innovation to the world stage\n\nCurious & Resilient Explorers – In a world of uncertainly, we are a team of curious minds, who embrace the uncertain, creating a life of learning, exploration and inspiration. At JMC we grow our voice to be confident, and unstoppable. We aren’t afraid to fall, as we know we will rise\n\nInclusive Community of Connectors – We create meaningful pathways, only possible through our connections and impact\n\nEmpathetic & Compassionate Leaders – We care about every individual who walks through our doors, with kindness in our hearts and purpose in our minds\n\nHonest, Accountable & of Uncompromising Quality – Our honesty, integrity and quality will not be compromised, as we strive to achieve our best. We are determined to reach our goals, as we hold ourselves and each other accountable\n\nOur Difference\n\nCreative education requires a unique approach. This is why the JMC student experience is different. Our world-class studios, student spaces and hands on learning inspires creative exploration, collaboration and innovation.\n\nRole Summary\n\nThe Data & Performance Analyst is the data engine of JMC Academy’s Customer Division — providing the intelligence that drives performance across marketing, sales, admissions, onboarding, product, pricing, industry partnerships and alumni engagement.\n\nThis role sits at the intersection of data engineering, business intelligence, digital analytics and performance marketing. You will manage data pipelines into our Microsoft Fabric data lakehouse, maintain CRM data quality in HubSpot, build Power BI dashboards, integrate external demand and market intelligence data, drive digital channel performance, and help the entire Customer function make faster, smarter, data-driven decisions.\n\nTechnology Environment\n\nHubSpot CRM | Microsoft Fabric | Power BI | SQL | Dynamics 365 ERP | Paradigm SMS | Canvas LMS | VTAC / UAC / QTAC | Burning Glass / Lightcast | Claude AI | Google Analytics 4 | Google Ads | Meta Ads Manager | Microsoft Ads\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nBuild and maintain data pipelines from Dynamics ERP, Paradigm SMS, Canvas LMS and HubSpot into Microsoft Fabric\nWrite and maintain SQL queries to extract, transform and load data across JMC’s systems and third-party sources\nOwn digital analytics across GA4, HubSpot and paid media platforms — conversion, attribution and ROAS\nDesign and maintain Power BI dashboards for marketing, sales, admissions and the CCO\nAnalyse TAC demand data, DoE datasets and Burning Glass labour intelligence to inform strategy\nBuild CRM-driven audience segments for activation across Google, Meta and programmatic channels\nEmbed Claude as an active analytics and decision-support tool across the Customer Division\n\nWhat We’re Looking For\n\nEssential:\n\n3–6 years in data analytics, BI, digital performance or marketing technology\nStrong SQL skills — you write queries without assistance\nHubSpot CRM configuration, data management and workflow automation experience\nMicrosoft Fabric, Azure Data Factory or Synapse experience\nPower BI proficiency including DAX and multi-source data modelling\nGA4 and paid media analytics experience (Google, Meta, Microsoft)\nAbility to translate complex data into clear, actionable insights for non-technical stakeholders\n\nHighly regarded:\n\nVTAC, UAC or QTAC tertiary admissions data experience\nBurning Glass / Lightcast or LinkedIn Talent Insights\nPython or R for advanced analysis and automation\nExperience using AI tools — Claude, ChatGPT or similar — for analytics workflows\n\nWhy This Role\n\nTechnology transformation moment — join as we build our Microsoft Fabric data lakehouse, migrate to HubSpot and embed AI-driven decision making\nExtraordinary data breadth — internal CRM, ERP, LMS and SMS unified with TAC demand feeds, DoE datasets and Burning Glass labour intelligence\nAI-forward environment — Claude is actively embedded into analytics workflows\nWhole-of-function impact — analytics backbone for every team in the Customer Division\nExecutive visibility — direct reporting line to the Chief Customer Officer\nFlexible campus base — Sydney, Melbourne or Brisbane\n\nHow to Apply\n\nPlease apply with your CV and a brief note telling us:\n\nThe most complex data environment you have worked in and how you made sense of it\nA specific example of how your analysis changed a business or marketing decision\nThe tools and platforms you are most proficient in and what you are currently learning\n\nJMC Academy is committed to diversity, equity and inclusion. We encourage applications from people of all backgrounds, cultures and identities.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=7b599b47116e54b3','scraped','2 days ago'),(2551,NULL,'job','SBS News Audio Lead - Sydney','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',131000.00,'Up to $131,000 a year','At SBS, we embrace difference, and we welcome applications from people of all backgrounds.\n\nWe also acknowledge the unique contribution that Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples make to our society and our workplace through their enduring and continued connection to land, sea, sky and community.\n\nThis role is classified as Level 6 role under SBS Australia\'s current Enterprise Agreement, with a base salary of up to $131,000. The successful applicant will be offered remuneration that is commensurate with their skills and experience and in alignment with this framework.\n\nThe role works Monday-Friday. Shift patterns may change over time depending on operational needs.\n\nThe role\n\nThe Audio Lead is a key editorial and people leadership role within SBS News and Current Affairs, responsible for shaping the direction and impact of our audio journalism. Working with the Managing Editor, you’ll lead a team of Audio Journalists and Supervising Producers, you’ll drive daily news coverage, podcasts and major series - ensuring our content is accurate, engaging and reflective of Australia’s diverse communities. You’ll collaborate with Digital, TV, SBS and NITV teams to make the most of our distinctive newsgathering. You’ll use audience insights and a deep understanding of the news landscape to grow and evolve SBS Audio, delivering distinctive content that connects with audiences wherever they are.\n\nNews podcasting is an exciting and growing area, and this role presents an opportunity to make an impact in this field, innovate and bring compelling, distinctive and original journalism to podcast audiences. You’ll play a key role in shaping how audiences connect with our news, driving excellence in storytelling, production and digital delivery across audio platforms.\n\nOur Audio News team is unique in the Australian media landscape. Along with distributing daily news content on Spotify, Apple Podcasts and other leading podcast providers, it provides daily news and feature stories for translation by our 60+ language teams and plays a positive role in helping inform all Australians about the stories that matter to them.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nAs Audio Lead, you’ll oversee commissioning and production of our suite of news podcasts and audio news content provided to our in-language teams.\n\nIn the role, you’ll:\n\nLead the daily and forward news agenda for SBS Audio, overseeing bulletins, daily in-depth podcasts and news podcast series, distributing on SBS platforms, Spotify, Apple Podcasts and podcast platforms\nCommission and shape engaging, accessible audio journalism aligned with SBS’s Charter and editorial standards\nGuide storytelling, ensuring accuracy, balance and strong multicultural and Indigenous perspectives\nDrive breaking news and forward planning, collaborating across Digital, TV, ALC and NITV teams\nUse data and audience insights to inform content, formats and audio distribution strategies\nMaintain high production standards, coaching teams on scripting, storytelling, voice and sound\nGrow and optimise SBS news audio products across platforms and third-party channels\nLead, mentor and develop a high-performing, inclusive team culture\n\nThis role is perfect for you if...\n\nYou’re an experienced journalist and confident editorial leader with a passion for audio\nYou thrive in a fast-paced news environment and can balance daily output with long-term projects\nYou have strong editorial judgement and a solid understanding of media law and news coverage\nYou’re confident in audio production, across podcast trends and know how to use data to reach and engage audiences\nYou’re a collaborative, people-focused leader who supports and develops others\nYou’re motivated to create distinctive, inclusive journalism that reflects diverse communities\n\nIf you’re motivated to help shape distinctive, trusted audio journalism that reflects SBS’s unique voice - this role is for you.\n\nAs part of our recruitment process, SBS may review information that is publicly available online, including social media profiles, in line with privacy and anti-discrimination laws.\n\nAs part of our recruitment process, SBS may conduct reference checks and review information that is publicly available online, including social media profiles, in line with privacy and anti-discrimination laws. If we collect information from any other sources, candidates will be notified in line with privacy laws.\n\nWe value authenticity and expect all applications and submissions to reflect your own voice, ideas, opinions and critical thinking. While we recognise that AI tools may be used to support drafting CVs or cover letters, the final content must remain your own. Throughout the recruitment process, including interviews and assessment tasks, we ask that you do not use AI tools unless we explicitly advise otherwise.\n\nAbout Us\n\nSBS is one of the world\'s most unique and innovative media organisations, producing trusted, meaningful, and engaging content that exists for all Australians to inspire, support and celebrate the diversity of our multicultural society.\n\nOur purpose, for the last 50 years, has reflected and explored the evolving diversity of Australia, investing in initiatives to deepen its connections with communities, sharing their stories and giving a voice to those often unheard, with the aim of increasing understanding and respect of the differences that make up Australia.\n\nSBS is a truly distinctive network, showcasing multicultural, multilingual and First Nations stories otherwise untold in the Australian media.\n\nSome of the reasons to consider working with us:\n\nThe people! We truly celebrate and welcome difference at SBS and encourage everyone to bring their whole self to work & you’ll be part of one of the most inclusive companies in Australia!\nThe culture and the engagement of our workforce! 90% of our employees have stated that they are proud to work for SBS!\nWe offer a range of benefits from, health care checks, salary packaging, Employee Assistance Programme, flexible work arrangements and discounted gym membership nationally with Fitness Pass.\nWe’re agile and innovative in the way we work, as well as being a trusted and established brand. At SBS we have been broadcasting for over 50 years and our future is packed with many more exciting developments!\nWe also love to promote from within! Our divisions support development opportunities to help team members grow and move into new roles.\n\nWant to learn more? Then hit apply and take the first step to applying not just for another job but a possible whole new career in a purpose led organisation.\n\n For other opportunities within our organisation please visit our careers website SBS Careers - Working at SBS\n\nReasonable adjustments\n\nSBS recognises that everyone is unique, and you might require some adjustments to ensure you have the best opportunity to apply and put your skills forward for consideration. If we can make some adjustments to the SBS recruitment/interview process to better enable you to shine, then please contact careers@sbs.com.au and let us know.\n\nAdjustments include but are not limited to; alternative application methods, interview setups, physical requirements, guidance for trans or gender diverse applicants, specific interview availability times and more.\n\nTo find out more about reasonable adjustments with SBS, please view our video here.\n\nWe are shortlisting applications as they come in, so don’t delay, apply today!\n\nPosition Description','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'SBS','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=560ff8da2e3d1e96','scraped','2 days ago'),(2552,NULL,'job','Senior Consultant - JAVA API','','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',114322.00,'$108,751 - $119,893 a year','About Us:\nInfosys is a global leader in next-generation digital services and consulting. We enable clients in more than 56 countries to navigate their digital transformation. With over four decades of experience in managing the systems and workings of global enterprises, we expertly steer our clients through their digital journey. We do it by enabling the enterprise with an AI-powered core that helps prioritize the execution of change. We also empower businesses with agile digital at scale to deliver unprecedented levels of performance and customer satisfaction. Our always-on learning agenda drives their continuous improvement through building and transferring digital skills, expertise, and ideas from our innovative ecosystem.\nRecognized as the #1 Top Employerin Australia for the second year in a row, Infosys offers a workplace where careers grow with purpose. As an AI‑first organization, we empower our people to work on next‑generation technologies, continuously learn, and create impact at scale—supported by a culture rooted in care, inclusion, and excellence.\n ️Join Infosys and be part of a culture that’s not just promised—it’s certified. #TopEmployer2026 #ThriveAtInfosys\nVisit www.infosys.com to see how Infosys (NYSE: INFY) can help your enterprise navigate your next.\n\nRole Description: Are you passionate about leading transformative technology strategies? We’re looking for a Site Reliability engineer to join our team\nWe’re seeking a seasoned Site reliability engineer to keep on top of day-to-day incident management in the digital domain working back with customer\'s business / IT teams and Infosys offshore delivery teams.\nLocation: Sydney\nSalary: AUD 108751 - 119893 Annual Gross\nPlease Note: - The above salary range is only indicative and maybe subject to suitable enhancements, based on internal company processes\nFlexible working arrangements (hybrid, reviewed case-by-case basis). Feel free to connect with your recruiter to learn more about how this works in practice.\nRoles and Responsibilities:\nAPI development- code, build and deployment.\nFull Hands On with java, spring boot, microservices\nPeer Code reviews\nJunit test cases\nSonarqube – code quality\n\nPreferred:\nJAVA API - Spring boot, java 1.8 and above, microservices, Security, hibernate & bitbucket.\nDevops\nSwagger\nBamboo\nSonarqube\nADDITIONAL\nExcellent customer-facing skills\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills\nStrong attention to detail and outstanding analytical and problem-solving skills.\nIn addition to compensation aligned with your role, you’ll have access to a wide range of benefits that support your health, career growth, and overall well-being (AU)\nIncome Protection Insurance\nPaid Parental and Volunteer leaves\nEmployee Assistance Program (EAP)\nFlexible working arrangements (hybrid, reviewed case-by-case basis)\nHealth Insurance Discount and Well-being Program\nAccess to Fitness and Gym Memberships\nSalary packaging and novated leasing\nOur recruitment and selection process is designed to create the best match for both you and Infosys. Depending on the role, it may include an initial screening, technical or functional interviews, and conversations focused on cultural alignment and shared values. We are committed to making the experience transparent, respectful, and engaging at every step.\n\nHear from our recruiter on their experience working with Infosys as an Employer\nAt Infosys, we recognize that everyone has individual requirements. If you are a person with disability, illness, or injury and require adjustments to the recruitment and selection process, please contact our Recruitment team for adjustment either via the following email Infosys_ta@infosys.com or call 1-866-472-0935. Alternatively, you can include your preferred method of communication in email, and someone will be in touch.\n\nPlease note in order to protect the interest of all parties involved in the recruitment process, Infosys does not accept any unsolicited resumes from third-party vendors. In the absence of a signed agreement, any submission will be deemed as non-binding and Infosys explicitly reserves the right to pursue and hire the submitted profile. All recruitment activity must be coordinated through the Talent Acquisition department.\n\n“All aspects of employment at Infosys are based on merit, competence and performance. We are committed to embracing diversity and creating an inclusive environment for all employees. Infosys is proud to be an equal opportunity employer.”','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Infosys','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1874c7b494fa61fd','scraped','2 days ago'),(2553,NULL,'job','Senior Case Manager - NSW','Full-time','Macquarie Park NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job Description:\n\nSenior Case Manager\n\nWhy join DXC Technology?\n\nDXC\'s Insurance Software and BPS (ISB) helps insurers around the world modernize and run their core operations at scale by combining deep industry expertise, proven software platforms, and innovative AI-driven solutions. A global market leader in core insurance platforms, ISB delivers solutions across policy administration, claims, billing, analytics, and digital engagement supporting Life & Annuity, Property & Casualty, and Specialty insurance markets. You’ll directly shape how the world\'s leading insurers operate by helping to transform the policy, underwriting, and claims systems that millions of people rely on every day.\n\nWhat you will be doing\n\nThe Workers\' Compensation Case Manager is responsible for overseeing and managing all aspects of workers\' compensation claims for injured workers within a self-insured framework. This role involves coordinating medical care, facilitating return-to-work programs, and ensuring compliance with applicable laws and regulations. The Case Manager will collaborate with medical providers, employees, and management to promote a safe and efficient work environment.\n\nThe skills you’ll bring\n\nEducation:\n\nBachelor’s degree in human resources, Business Administration, Nursing, or related field is desirable.\n\nExperience :\n\nMinimum of 2 years of experience in workers\' compensation case management, preferably in a self-insured environment.\n\nSkills:\n\nStrong knowledge of workers\' compensation laws and regulations.\nExcellent communication and interpersonal skills.\nAbility to manage multiple cases simultaneously and prioritise effectively.\nProficient in Microsoft Office Suite.\n\nCompetencies:\n\nAnalytical Skills: Ability to assess complex information and make informed decisions.\nAttention to Detail: Strong organisational skills with a focus on accuracy.\nProblem-solving: Ability to identify issues and implement effective solutions in a timely manner.\nEmpathy: Understanding the challenges injured workers face and providing compassionate support.\n\nOur culture and benefits\n\nDXC is committed to building better futures for our customers, colleagues, environment, and communities. We take care of each other and foster a culture of inclusion, belonging and corporate citizenship. We put this to action developing and implementing societal initiatives within our Social Impact Practice . #WeAreDXC\n\nAs an employer of choice, our “people first” philosophy means we offer competitive remuneration, benefits, training and career opportunities that reflect our commitment to improving the lives of our employees, and the communities in which we live and work. Some of these include;\n\nExtensive resources to support your onboarding and continual development including DXC University.\nWe know that great people refer great people. We will reward you when you bring your friends and family to work at DXC.\nMore time to do the things you love with flexible leave options, including purchased leave.\nTake time to give back with charitable and emergency services volunteer days.\nWell-being matters to us and our Employee Assistance Program is there to support you and your family.\nAnd of course, all the basics; novated leasing, discounted health insurance, paid parental leave and many other discounts.\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer\n\nDXC is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and we welcome submissions from people from all walks of life. We celebrate our diversity and recognise it is the unique contributions of our people that give us our edge. We stand by the ‘bring your whole-self to work’ philosophy. It is our inclusive culture that powers our results, and our company grows only if our people grow.\n\nAccommodation of special needs for qualified candidates may be considered within the framework of the DXC Accommodation Policy. In addition, DXC Technology is committed to working with and providing reasonable accommodation to support qualified individuals with physical and mental disabilities .\n\nAt DXC Technology, we believe strong connections and community are key to our success. Our work model prioritizes in-person collaboration while offering flexibility to support wellbeing, productivity, individual work styles, and life circumstances. We’re committed to fostering an inclusive environment where everyone can thrive.\n\nRecruitment fraud is a scheme in which fictitious job opportunities are offered to job seekers typically through online services, such as false websites, or through unsolicited emails claiming to be from the company. These emails may request recipients to provide personal information or to make payments as part of their illegitimate recruiting process. DXC does not make offers of employment via social media networks and DXC never asks for any money or payments from applicants at any point in the recruitment process, nor ask a job seeker to purchase IT or other equipment on our behalf.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'DXC Technology','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=712de55e04064a91','scraped','2 days ago'),(2554,NULL,'job','Technology Product Manager - AI & Innovation','Permanent','Brisbane QLD',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Posted: 01/05/2026\nClosing Date: 05/06/2026\nJob Type: Permanent - Full Time\nLocation: Collingwood, Bendigo, Traralgon, Moe, Mascot or Brisbane\nJob Category: Banking and Financial Services\n\nThrough the merger of Bank Australia and Qudos Bank we’re creating a better, stronger and more resilient bank for our customers and employees. As one company with two trusted brands, we’re building on the strong foundations of our history and shared values as we bring together the best of both banks.\n\nThe Technology Product Manager – Innovation & AI is accountable for the strategic ownership, investment and continuous improvement of the bank’s innovation & AI platforms. Working closely with a wide range of stakeholders across the business, the role defines and delivers a clear platform roadmap aligned to business priorities, overseeing the full product lifecycle from requirements analysis through to design, build, testing, implementation and ongoing optimisation. The role ensures platforms are reliable, scalable and well governed, enabling efficient financial operations and strong business outcomes.\n\nThis role is based in Collingwood, Bendigo, Traralgon, Moe, Mascot or Canberra.\n\nWhy join us\n\nWe have big plans to become Australia’s leading purpose-driven bank.\nAs a certified B Corp, we’re part of a global business community who meet the highest social and environmental standards, putting purpose over profit.\nEvery role and person in our bank are essential to bringing our values, purpose and aspiration to life.\nWe offer flexible working options, competitive salary and 14% super.\nOur staff have access to a range of meaningful benefits to support their physical and mental wellbeing including 24/7 free counselling, free flu vaccinations and subsidised gym memberships.\nWe also support staff with study assistance, paid parental leave (regardless of gender or carer responsibility), fertility treatment, volunteer, bereavement, gender transition and family violence leave, and the opportunity for bonus annual leave.\nWe support our staff to grow their careers through learning and development and an organisational culture where we reward and recognise innovation and values, not long hours.\nWe are committed to building an inclusive culture and a diverse workforce that reflects the Australian community.\nWe care for a conservation reserve – where we work with key partner organisations to protect threatened species and involve staff in conservation.\n\nWhat you will be doing\n\nOwn the end-to-end technical lifecycle of our innovation roadmap platforms, ensuring effective investment, reliability and continuous optimisation.\nDefine and implement the bank’s strategy around AI rollout, ensuring effective investment, value add, and continuous optimisation.\nPartner with relevant stakeholders to maximise capability, utilisation and operational efficiency.\nDefine and manage product roadmaps, priorities and backlogs using insights from user needs, market trends and data.\nLead the full product lifecycle from requirements, design and build through to testing, implementation and ongoing improvement.\nApply appropriate governance, product and delivery methodologies to balance business priorities, compliance and efficiency outcomes.\nCoordinate user testing, releases, communications and training to support successful adoption and change.\nProvide expert technical advice, translating strategy into operational delivery and informed leadership decisions.\nMaintain and share specialist knowledge, drawing on internal expertise and third-party providers.\nWhere applicable manage third party vendors, including performance monitoring, issue resolution and service improvement planning.\nDeliver initiatives iteratively, ensuring stakeholders are informed on progress, risks and backlog status.\nLead and support direct reports to deliver consistent, high quality product outcomes.\n\nWhat you will bring\n\nDemonstrated experience in product or project management, including delivery of innovation roadmaps or AI capabilities.\nTertiary qualifications in Technology, Engineering, Commerce or Finance (preferred)\nExperience in innovation in a highly regulated environment.\nClear, confident communication and strong stakeholder management skills, able to influence, provide direction and support decision making across all levels.\nStrong analytical and problem-solving capability, including requirements gathering, gap analysis, process mapping (as is/to be), budgeting and performance tracking.\nAbility to define business and data requirements, develop insights, and manage data integrity and confidentiality.\nStrategic, continuous improvement mindset, able to adapt plans, manage competing priorities and deliver results in complex, regulated environments.\nStrong understanding of AI offerings and the broader banking systems ecosystem, with capability to operate as a senior functional analyst.\nAbility to translate complex technical and strategic concepts into clear, actionable outcomes for non-technical audiences.\nExperience working with third party vendors and representing the organisation externally.\nSelf-driven, results focused approach with the ability to lead or contribute effectively within multidisciplinary teams.\nCommitment to Bank Australia’s purpose, aspiration, values and brand as well as the B Corp ethos.\n\nBy submitting an application you agree to Bank Australia’s Privacy Policy for applicants and confirm that you are legally able to work in Australia. Bank Australia is an equal opportunity employer committed to sustainable development. We encourage people from different backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people from different cultural backgrounds and people with disabilities because we want to reflect the diversity of our communities. We are committed to making reasonable adjustments to provide a positive, barrier-free recruitment process and supportive workplace.\n\nBank Australia reserves the right to withdraw this advertisement at any time. Candidates will be progressed as applications are received, rather than after the advertisement closure date. If you wish to be considered, please submit your application as soon as possible. Please note, the successful candidate will be subject to satisfactory background checks including but not limited to police and previous employment.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Bank Australia','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=dada6d994eb1cff1','scraped','2 days ago'),(2555,NULL,'job','Instrument Chemist','Full-time','Wangara WA',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'At ALS, we encourage you to dream big.\n\nWhen you join us, you’ll be part of a global team harnessing the power of scientific testing and data-driven insights to build a healthier future.\n\nThe role\n\nWe are pleased to announce an exciting opportunity at our ALS Environmental site. We are currently seeking an experienced Instrument Chemist to join our dedicated Organics team.\n\nBased at Wangara , the successful candidate will play a key role in ensuring the team consistently delivers high-quality results on time while striving to exceed expectations.\n\nThis full-time position encompasses a range of key responsibilities, including:\n\nEnsuring all activities are conducted in accordance with the Quality Procedures Manual\n\nSupervision and training of laboratory staff\n\nPrioritising daily workloads\n\nOperation and maintenance of instrumentation\n\nReporting of results in accordance with Quality Work Instructions\n\nEnsuring compliance with the laboratory’s QC and HSE requirements\n\nPreparing standards for sample analysis\n\nMaintaining relevant documentation\n\nThe essentials\n\nBachelor of Science or equivalent (Honours and Chemistry disciplines advantageous but all sciences backgrounds are encouraged to apply)\n\nAt least 2 years’ experience in a commercial laboratory\n\nPrevious experience operating with GC/FID, GCMS or LCMSMS would be advantageous\n\nAvailable to work Monday to Friday on either day or afternoon shifts, with the flexibility to occasionally work on Saturdays as required.\n\nUnderstanding of sample preparation for organics analysis for soil and water matrices highly regarded\n\nCompetent in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, Outlook)\n\nA working knowledge of organic sample preparation techniques for Environmental samples. PFAS experience would be highly regarded.\n\nAbility to work autonomously as well as part of a team\n\nInterest in method development, verification, and validation\n\nA working knowledge of lab safety requirements\n\nAbility to work under pressure in a team environment\n\nA keen interest in organic chemistry and associated analysis\n\nAdditionally, the following skills and interests are advantageous and desirable:\n\nA demonstrated interest or personal hobby in areas such as computer building, circuitry, automation, Excel macros, scripting, or 3D printing\n\nCoding or programming capability (e.g. VBA, Python, R, SQL or similar)\n\nExposure to or interest in robotics, AI, process automation or digital optimisation\n\nWorking at ALS\n\nThe ALS team is a diverse and dedicated community united by our passion to make a difference in the world.\n\nOur values are important to us, and shape how we work, how we treat each other and how we recognise excellence.\n\nAt ALS, you’ll be supported to develop new skills and reach your full potential. We invest in our people with programs and opportunities that help you build a diverse career with us.\n\nWe want everyone to have a safe, flexible and rewarding career that makes a positive impact on our people, the planet and our communities.\n\nEveryone Matters\n\nALS is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and is committed to fostering an inclusive work environment where the strengths and perspectives of each employee are both recognised and valued.\n\nALS also welcomes applications from people with all levels of ability. Reasonable adjustments to support candidates throughout the recruitment process are available upon request.\n\nEligibility\nTo be eligible to work at ALS you must be a Citizen or Permanent Resident of the country you are applying for, or either hold or be able to obtain, a valid working visa.\n\nHow to apply\nPlease apply on-line and provide a resume & cover letter that best demonstrate your motivation and ability to meet the requirements of this role.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'ALS','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a0a54efe35b0e55d','scraped','2 days ago'),(2556,NULL,'job','Business Readiness Implementation Manager','Contract','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job details\nPosted01 May 2026\nSalaryNegotiable\nLocationSydney\nJob type Contract\nDiscipline Customer Experience\nReference90M0707174_1777604364\nJob description\n\nAbout FinXL IT\nFinXL IT Professional Services is a leading IT consultancy that partners with clients to bridge the gap between business needs and technology capabilities. Since 2003, we\'ve been delivering high-value ICT services across government, finance, telecommunications, and enterprise sectors.\n\nThe Opportunity\nFinXL IT is seeking a Senior Project Manager/ Business Readiness Implementation Manager to join our consulting team for a strategic engagement with a leading Insurance client. You will lead the business readiness and implementation of SAP Signavio, uplifting the division\'s Business Process Management (BPM) and Customer Journey capabilities.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nSignavio Implementation: Drive the rollout of SAP Signavio as the tool of choice for BPM and Customer Journeys.\n\nBusiness Readiness: Link operational processes to customer experience (CX), ensuring a smooth transition from iServer and mitigating process decay.\n\nDelivery Management: Execute the delivery plan, managing scope, sequencing, and trade-offs across complex business and tech workstreams.\n\nGovernance & Standards: Establish clear ownership and governance frameworks enabled by modern AI-supported tooling (mining and analytics).\n\nProcess Redesign: Enable the redesign of workflows from the ground up to effectively shape and capture AI opportunities.\n\nStakeholder Integration: Build deep relationships with business and technology leads to drive decisions, manage dependencies, and ensure high user adoption.\n\nFinancial Oversight: Manage project budgeting and forecasting to ensure delivery stays within financial parameters.\n\nKey Skills & Experience\n\nProven background as a Senior Project Manager or Implementation Manager within the General Insurance industry.\n\nProven hands-on experience as part of a team responsible for the implementation and delivery of SAP Signavio in a similar sized environment and ecosystem is non-negotiable.\n\nDemonstrated experience delivering diverse portfolios including business transformation and cultural change.\n\nExceptional senior executive engagement skills with the ability to align diverse parties under tight timeframes.\n\nAbility to drive business-led solutions while navigating complex technology impacts and legacy system transitions.\n\nStrong judgement with the ability to provide practical support and apply design-thinking principles to process uplift.\n\nWhat\'s On Offer?\n\nInitial 12 months\' contract, with a view to extend\nLocated in Sydney CBD\nHybrid working arrangement to get your best work done!\nLead a mission-critical project moving an industry leader toward AI-supported process management.\nJoin a consultancy that values professional development and high-level stakeholder partnership.\n\nNext Steps: If you would like to apply for this opportunity, please submit your CV via SEEK. Please note that due to the volume of responses, only shortlisted consultants will be contacted.\n\nJob number (S4)','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'FinXL','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c0b3c91174a2810c','scraped','2 days ago'),(2557,NULL,'job','Principal Engineer','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Are you a seasoned Principal Engineer who thrives on driving technical excellence and delivering seamless digital experiences?\n\nAs we expand our presence in the Sydney area, we are seeking an experienced Principal Engineer to join our Digital Experience practice. This role involves leading our team in developing innovative go-to-market solutions for our customers and supporting their digital transformations to achieve outstanding outcomes.\n\nAs a Principal Engineer, you will be crucial in setting the technical direction for our customers. You will act as the liaison between the engineering team and stakeholders, lead a small team of engineers, and provide guidance and support in implementing cutting-edge technologies. Your expertise will be key to ensuring seamless delivery and surpassing client expectations.\n\nOn a day to day, you\'ll be doing;\n\nLead an engagement technically providing thought leadership and technical direction focusing on customer needs and achieving project goals.\nLeading and building engineering and design best practice, standards and deliverables in production ready systems, to meet customer agreed outcomes to time, budget and quality.\nProducing and gaining customer approval on high level designs, detailed designs, solution architectures, operational and handover documentation; sequencing of projects and backlog that provide clarity and direction for the engineering team with team endorsement and support as the key metric.\nLead a team of engineers, providing leadership, direction and mentorship\nDrive innovation and excellence in digital and cloud native solutions\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure alignment with business goals\nUtilise your Digital AppDev and Cloud expertise to deliver high-quality technical solutions\nChampion craftsmanship and quality outcomes in all aspects of technology delivery\nExtensive experience in software engineering, across AWS and Azure platforms\nProven track record of technical leadership and delivering successful projects\nStrong communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively in a team environment\nPassion for technology craftsmanship and a commitment to delivering quality outcomes\nPeople lead a small team of seniors and engineers\nRequired Skills & Experience\nProven experience as a Principal or Lead Engineer delivering complex, cloud-native solutions in enterprise environments\nStrong full stack engineering capability, with deep expertise in backend services and distributed systems\nProficiency in core languages including Java (Spring Boot), TypeScript/JavaScript, Python or similar\nFrontend development experience using React and/or Next.js or similar\nDeep hands-on experience with AWS, including designing and building cloud-native architectures\nStrong experience with microservices and event-driven architectures\nHands-on expertise with Docker and Kubernetes in production environments\nSolid understanding of DevOps practices, including CI/CD pipelines, Infrastructure as Code, and observability\nExperience using AI-assisted coding tools (e.g., GitHub Copilot, Claude Code or similar) ideally in real-world development\nProven ability to lead technical delivery, including architecture, design, and implementation oversight\nHighly Desirable\nExperience in financial services (banking, payments, or superannuation)\nExperience building go-to-market products or reusable engineering platforms\nTrack record of mentoring and developing engineers in high-performing teams\n\nLife at Versent\n\nWe\'re a diverse team of motivated humans who think outside the box and strive to deliver what others might consider impossible. At Versent we truly care about our people and put real focus on cultivating a culture of learning, collaboration and growth. We provide our teams with the space, trust, and support, to deliver the best work of their careers. To enable this, we have a culture that places a high value on continual feedback, excellence, and invention anchored in customer success.\n\nWe also offer our team:\n\nFlexibility: We give you the freedom to excel, providing as much autonomy and flexibility around when you work so you can manage your time in a way that best suits you to get the job done.\n\nLearning: We are passionate about continuous improvement and care about you investing in and developing your craft. Our Craft 180 Program is a holistic strategy for ongoing, meaningful skill and capability development with an ultimate goal to create an environment where people can learn and contribute in different ways to develop, practice and become masters of their craft.\n\nAccess to Benefits That Fit Your Life: From salary packaging and purchased leave to novated leasing options, we offer a range of benefits designed to suit different lifestyles and priorities. There’s something for everyone.\n\nHealth & Wellbeing Programmes: We focus on you as a whole person, with wellbeing initiatives that are to support you mentally, physically, emotionally and financially.\n\nConnection: Regular social activities across your team and the organisation.\n\nRecognition: We offer several reward & recognition programmes to acknowledge the amazing work that you do!\n\nCareer opportunity: We provide the opportunity to work on diverse projects and initiatives that enable you to create a brilliant career.\n\nAt Versent, we don\'t adhere to a one-size-fits-all hiring strategy. We understand that you might not fulfill all the criteria for this position. Our celebration of diverse perspectives isn\'t just a value, it\'s a way to gain an edge. If you believe this opportunity is where you can thrive, don\'t be shy and apply!\n\nIf you require any accommodations throughout the interview process, please get in touch with us by emailing careers@versent.com.au.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Versent','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2d1c91fd02fe27bc','scraped','2 days ago'),(2558,NULL,'job','Manager, Global Web Production','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'The APAC Global Web Production Manager (GWPM) leads the coordination, planning, and execution of adobe.com projects across the Asia Pacific region, ensuring alignment with Adobe\'s strategy and business objectives. Leading the APAC production team, the GWPM ensures projects are delivered on time and to the highest standard, through effective management of schedules, resources and risks.\n\nThe role involves daily communication with partners from both Sales and Marketing to ensure the wider team is well-informed of project status. The GWPM champions AI adoption across the web production function by embedding AI-first thinking into daily workflows and upskilling the team on emerging tools. Operating within an agile delivery model, they are accountable for the smooth running of sprints and ongoing optimization of team processes.\n\nResponsibilities\nPartner with the Director of Global Web Production to support revenue growth across international sites\nLead, mentor, and grow a distributed team of web producers and specialists,\nDevelop and embed an AI-first approach to web production, driving team proficiency in AI tools, agentic workflows, and emerging tech\nRun agile delivery, including sprints, ceremonies, and continuous improvement of ways of working across cross-functional business and implementation partners\nOwn process and quality improvements, gathering input from the wider Marketing team to remove blockers and streamline workflows\nManage team budget, expenses, and operational administration\n\nRequirements\n5+ years managing web production or web project delivery in a complex, global environment, including multiple successful global site launches\nHands-on experience with AI tools and agentic workflows, with a track record of embedding them into production\nStrong command of agile and sprint-based delivery (Scrum certification a plus)\nExperience with web content management systems; working knowledge of Jira and AEM desirable\nProven leader who builds credibility with teams and senior collaborators, and influences outcomes across functions\nSharp prioritization, problem-solving, and decision-making under pressure\nBachelor\'s degree or equivalent experience\nAPAC market experience with a strong grasp of regional nuances a plus\nAbout Adobe\nAdobe empowers everyone to create through innovative platforms and tools that unleash creativity, productivity and personalized customer experiences. Adobe’s industry-leading offerings including Adobe Acrobat Studio, Adobe Express, Adobe Firefly, Creative Cloud, Adobe Experience Platform, Adobe Experience Manager, and GenStudio enable people and businesses to turn ideas into impact, powered by AI and driven by human ingenuity.\n\nOur 30,000+ employees worldwide are creating the future and raising the bar as we drive the next decade of growth. We’re on a mission to hire the very best and believe in creating a company culture where all employees are empowered to make an impact. At Adobe, we believe that great ideas can come from anywhere in the organization. The next big idea could be yours.\n\nLet’s Adobe together\nAt Adobe, we believe in creating a company culture where all employees are empowered to make an impact. Learn more about Adobe life, including our values and culture , focus on people, purpose and community , Adobe for All , comprehensive benefits programs , the stories we tell , the customers we serve, and how you can help us advance our mission of empowering everyone to create.\n\nAdobe is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on gender, race or color, ethnicity or national origin, age, disability, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, veteran status, or any other protected characteristic. Learn more.\n\nAdobe aims to make our Careers website and recruiting process accessible to any and all users. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation to navigate our website or complete the application process, email accommodations@adobe.com or call +1 408-536-3015.\n\nAI Use Guidelines for Interviews:\nOur interviews are designed to reflect your own skills and thinking. The use of AI or recording tools during live interviews is not permitted unless explicitly invited by the interviewer or approved in advance as part of a reasonable accommodation. If these tools are used inappropriately or in a way that misrepresents your work, your application may not move forward in the process.\n\nAt Adobe, we empower employees to innovate with AI — and we look for candidates eager to do the same. As part of the hiring experience, we provide clear guidance on where AI is encouraged during the process and where it’s restricted during live interviews. See how we think about AI in the hiring experience .','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Adobe','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=7eb688076d067f9f','scraped','2 days ago'),(2559,NULL,'job','SAP SuccessFactors EC Payroll Consultant','','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',160978.50,'$150,742 - $171,215 a year','About Us:\nInfosys is a global leader in next-generation digital services and consulting. We enable clients in more than 56 countries to navigate their digital transformation. With over four decades of experience in managing the systems and workings of global enterprises, we expertly steer our clients through their digital journey. We do it by enabling the enterprise with an AI-powered core that helps prioritize the execution of change. We also empower the businesses with agile digital at scale to deliver unprecedented levels of performance and customer satisfaction. Our always-on learning agenda drives their continuous improvement through building and transferring digital skills, expertise, and ideas from our innovation ecosystem.\nVisit www.infosys.com to see how Infosys (NYSE: INFY) can help your enterprise navigate your next.\n\nRole Description: Are you passionate about leading transformative technology strategies? We are looking for a seasoned SAP SuccessFactors Payroll Consultant to act as a subject matter expert for SAP Payroll solutions, specifically tailored to Australian payroll processes. The consultant will lead Employee Central Payroll implementations, collaborate with global delivery teams, and work closely with clients to design, build, and support scalable payroll solutions.\n\nLocation: Melbourne (VIC), Australia\nSalary: AUD 150742 - AUD 171215 (Annual Gross)\nPlease Note:- The above salary range is only indicative and maybe subject to suitable enhancements, based on internal company processes.\n\nFlexible working arrangements (hybrid, reviewed case-by-case basis). Feel free to connect with your recruiter to learn more about how this works in practice.\n\nRoles and Responsibilities:\nServe as the SME for SAP Payroll, guiding solution design and implementation.\nLead hands-on configuration and deployment of Employee Central Payroll.\nLiaise with clients for workshops, solution presentations, POCs, and approvals.\nEstimate efforts for proposed solutions and own delivery outcomes.\nRecommend innovative, best-practice-based solutions aligned with SAP standards.\nDevelop business process documentation and functional specifications.\nConduct implementation and training workshops for SAP power users.\nLead testing cycles (unit, SIT, regression) and support UAT.\nCoordinate integration requirements with other SAP modules (e.g., Finance, HCM).\nMentor junior consultants and contribute to payroll competency development.\nParticipate in strategic initiatives, proposals, and thought leadership activities.\nSkill / Competencies / Experience:\n\nESSENTIAL\nGood knowledge of technology landscape to be able to guide team.\nTertiary Qualification in IT / Computer Science / related discipline.\nPREFERRED\nExpertise in SAP SuccessFactors Employee Central Payroll.\n8–10 years of experience in Australian payroll implementations and support.\nStrong understanding of HCM processes and statutory compliance in Australia.\nExperience in integration with S/4HANA HCM and Finance modules.\nExcellent communication, stakeholder engagement, and problem-solving skills.\nAbility to work effectively in an onshore-offshore delivery model.\n\nADDITIONAL\nExcellent customer-facing skills\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills\nStrong attention to detail and outstanding analytical and problem-solving skills.\nIn addition to compensation aligned with your role, you’ll have access to a wide range of benefits that support your health, career growth, and overall well-being (AU)\nIncome Protection Insurance\nPaid Parental and Volunteer leaves\nEmployee Assistance Program (EAP)\nFlexible working arrangements (hybrid, reviewed case-by-case basis)\nHealth Insurance Discount and Well-being Program\nAccess to Fitness and Gym Memberships\nSalary packaging and novated leasing\nOur recruitment and selection process is designed to create the best match for both you and Infosys. Depending on the role, it may include an initial screening, technical or functional interviews, and conversations focused on cultural alignment and shared values. We are committed to making the experience transparent, respectful, and engaging at every step.\n\nHear from our recruiter on their experience working with Infosys as an Employer\nAt Infosys, we recognize that everyone has individual requirements. If you are a person with disability, illness, or injury and require adjustments to the recruitment and selection process, please contact our Recruitment team for adjustment either via the following email Infy_REC_Helpdesk@infosys.com or call 1-866-472-0935. Alternatively, you can include your preferred method of communication in email, and someone will be in touch.\n\nPlease note in order to protect the interest of all parties involved in the recruitment process, Infosys does not accept any unsolicited resumes from third-party vendors. In the absence of a signed agreement, any submission will be deemed as non-binding and Infosys explicitly reserves the right to pursue and hire the submitted profile. All recruitment activity must be coordinated through the Talent Acquisition department.\n\n“All aspects of employment at Infosys are based on merit, competence and performance. We are committed to embracing diversity and creating an inclusive environment for all employees. Infosys is proud to be an equal opportunity employer.”','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Infosys','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1956ecb15f9c96d7','scraped','2 days ago'),(2560,NULL,'job','Trial Coordinator','Part-time','St Leonards NSW',NULL,'',89755.00,'From $89,755 a year','1 year fixed term part time contract available\n\nContribute to the SLEEP – MSK study\n\nBase Salary starting from $89,755 + 17% superannuation ( Pro rata)\n\nAbout the opportunity\n\nThe Sydney School of Health Sciences is in a period of exciting and significant investment by the Faculty of Medicine and Health. In order to deliver on the University’s ambitious strategic plan, the University is seeking academics who are passionate about improving health outcomes and/or health equity in the local, national and global communities, who are committed to teaching and research, and area team player ready to contribute across the broad field of academic activities.\n\nThe University is seeking a highly motivated Clinical Trial Coordinator ( HEO 5) to contribute to the SLEEP-MSK adaptive basket randomised controlled trial, which evaluates whether adding cognitive behavioural therapy for insomnia (CBT-I) to usual physiotherapy care improves pain, sleep, and function in people with chronic low back pain, hip osteoarthritis, or knee osteoarthritis.\n\nSLEEP-MSK is a two-arm, superiority, adaptive basket randomised controlled trial including participants with one of three chronic MSK conditions—chronic low back pain, hip osteoarthritis, or knee osteoarthritis—and co-existing insomnia\n\nYour key responsibilities will be to:\n\nSupport the end-to-end clinical trial process, assisting with the planning, initiation, and execution of trials, and ensuring smooth operations from start-up to close-out\n\nSupport data capture and verification for clinical trials, maintaining accurate records and ensuring compliance with regulations\n\nFollow ethics guidelines and workplace health and safety regulations, preparing materials for committee submissions\n\nBuild productive relationships with research staff, trial sponsors, and external vendors, facilitating effective communication and collaboration\n\nUphold the principles of Good Clinical Practice (GCP) in all clinical trials, ensuring that ethical and scientific quality standards are met in design, conduct, recording, and reporting\n\nTake the lead in handling stakeholder communications, ensuring that concerns are addressed effectively and timely while fostering a culture of trust and collaboration within the work area and beyond\n\nFacilitate timely report submission, uphold data integrity according to university systems, and partner with managers to advance compliance initiatives\n\nSupported by the FMH media team, create patient avatars & eLearning for training physiotherapists to deliver Cognitive Behavioural Therapy for Insomnia in the trial.\n\nAbout you\n\nBachelors degree in relevant field or equivalent combination of relevant training and experience\n\nStrong knowledge of complex musculoskeletal conditions & their management\n\nExperience in delivering clinical skills training activities\n\nDesirable to have experience as a practising health professional\n\nExperience in manuscript writing\n\nWillingness to learn new skills in AI related fields\n\nWillingness to be trained in Phlebotomy for the trial\n\nExperience in clinical trial coordination or a similar role\n\nSolid understanding of clinical research and Good Clinical Practice\n\nExperience with ethics and governance processes and preparing and submitting trial documentation\n\nEffective communication, planning and organisation skills and strong attention to detail\n\nProven experience in a research-intensive environment.\n\nSponsorship / work rights for Australia\n\nYou must have unrestricted work rights in Australia for the duration of this employment to be eligible to apply. Visa sponsorship is not available for this appointment.\n\nPre-employment checks and declarations\n\n Your employment is conditional upon the successful completion of all pre-employment or background checks required for the role in terms satisfactory to the University. Also, to meet the University’s obligations under the National Higher Education Code to Prevent and Eliminate Gender-Based Violence you will be asked to declare if you have been investigated for, or found to engaged in, sexual harm or gender-based violence in the course of previous employment or in a legal process. Similarly, your ongoing employment is conditional upon the satisfactory maintenance of all relevant clearances and background check requirements. If you do not meet these conditions, the University may take any necessary step, including the termination of your employment.\n\nAs this position is located on an NSW Health site, it is a regulatory requirement to complete compulsory employment checks prior to starting in this position. For more information and instructions, please visit: NSW Health employment requirements\n\nEEO statement\n\nAt the University of Sydney, our shared values are trust, accountability and excellence and we strive to be a place where everyone can thrive. We are committed to creating a University community that thrives through diversity and reflects the wider community that we serve. We deliver on this through our commitment to diversity and inclusion , evidenced by our people and culture programs, as well as key strategies to increase participation and support the careers of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander People , women , people living with a disability , people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds , and those who identify as LGBTQIA+ . We welcome applications from candidates from all backgrounds.\n\nWe are proud to be recognised as an Australian Workplace Equality Index (AWEI) Platinum Employer. Find out more about our work on diversity and inclusion .\n\nHow to apply\n\nApplications (including a cover letter, CV, and any additional supporting documentation) can be submitted via the Apply button at the top of the page.\n\nFor employees of the University or contingent workers, please login into your Workday account and navigate to the Career icon on your Dashboard. Click on USYD Find Jobs and apply.\n\nFor a confidential discussion about the role, or if you require reasonable adjustment or any documents in alternate formats, please contact Rachel Ann Yazigi, Recruitment Operations by email to rachel.yazigi@sydney.edu.au .\n\n© The University of Sydney\n\nThe University reserves the right not to proceed with any appointment.\n\nClick to view the Position Description for this role.\n\nApplications Close\n\nSunday 10 May 2026 11:59 PM','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'University of Sydney','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=190baea2ccf79997','scraped','2 days ago'),(2561,NULL,'job','JAPAC Retention Operations & Analytics Manager','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'The Opportunity\nWe are hiring an exceptionally talented Sales Retention Operations & Analytics Manager to drive flawless retention programs, analytics, and operational consistency across the JAPAC region.\n\nAs part of our world-class Retention Strategy & Operations team, you will collaborate with Renewals Sales, Solution Account Managers, Customer Success Operations, Finance, and Sales Operations teams.\n\nYou will successfully implement retention programs, study data to identify trends and risks, and build decisions that improve renewal performance and increase customer retention throughout different JAPAC markets.\n\nThis position provides wide-ranging experience across various locations, business units, and priorities, with opportunities to expand your influence over time!\n\nWhat You’ll Do\nRetention Programs & Execution\n\nCoordinate with regional leadership to establish and provide retention programs across JAPAC.\n\nPlan and roll out initiatives passionate about renewal performance, customer health, and risk reduction.\n\nMonitor program progress and share insights to inform next steps and improvements.\n\nRetention Data, Reporting & Analytics\n\nManage retention and attrition data across JAPAC, ensuring accuracy and consistency.\n\nAnalyse data sets to identify trends, risks, and opportunities that inform action.\n\nBuild regular reports and deliver analysis for regional and leadership reviews.\n\nRespond to data requests with clear analysis that shapes renewal planning and decision making.\n\nQBR & Leadership Readiness\n\nPrepare retention inputs for QBRs spanning regional and geographic areas within JAPAC.\n\nBuild data packs, insights, and materials for leadership and performance discussions.\n\nContribute to consistency in important measurements and definitions used in reviews.\n\nPlanning, Coverage & Operations\n\nGather and examine data to support planning activities throughout the region.\n\nCoordinate coverage, quota, and goal validation with Sales Operations and Finance.\n\nWork with teams across the business to address data or process questions.\n\nCollaboration & Governance\n\nCollaborate with regional and global teams to carry out retention initiatives and improvements.\n\nContribute to training efforts, pilots, and operational improvements related to renewals.\n\nParticipate in testing and validation activities as tools or processes evolve.\n\nWhat You\'ll Need to Succeed\n\nExperience in program management, sales operations, retention operations, or analytics.\n\nExperience handling data to guide business decisions and convey a clear narrative.\n\nAbility to translate data into clear insights and recommendations.\n\nComfort working across regions, teams, and time zones.\n\nStrong communication skills and a collaborative working style.\n\nAdobe for All\nAdobe strives to create an environment where our employees can do their best work and drive their career growth and development based on their personal goals. From fair-pay practices to Employee Networks and programs designed to make everyone feel included, we\'re committed to fostering a diverse and inclusive workplace for all.\n\nTake the plunge and jump in\nLiking what you have read and keen to jump in? Thinking you might not have all the skills we are looking for? Just take the plunge and apply – we know that by bringing together a diverse group of people, we become so much better together. We\'d love to see where we can help drive Creativity for All together!\n\nAdobe Australia acknowledges Traditional Custodians of Country throughout Australia and recognises the continuing connection to lands, waters and communities. We pay our respect to Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander cultures; and to Elders past, present and emerging.\n\nWe will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment. Please contact us to request accommodation.\nAbout Adobe\nAdobe empowers everyone to create through innovative platforms and tools that unleash creativity, productivity and personalized customer experiences. Adobe’s industry-leading offerings including Adobe Acrobat Studio, Adobe Express, Adobe Firefly, Creative Cloud, Adobe Experience Platform, Adobe Experience Manager, and GenStudio enable people and businesses to turn ideas into impact, powered by AI and driven by human ingenuity.\n\nOur 30,000+ employees worldwide are creating the future and raising the bar as we drive the next decade of growth. We’re on a mission to hire the very best and believe in creating a company culture where all employees are empowered to make an impact. At Adobe, we believe that great ideas can come from anywhere in the organization. The next big idea could be yours.\n\nLet’s Adobe together\nAt Adobe, we believe in creating a company culture where all employees are empowered to make an impact. Learn more about Adobe life, including our values and culture , focus on people, purpose and community , Adobe for All , comprehensive benefits programs , the stories we tell , the customers we serve, and how you can help us advance our mission of empowering everyone to create.\n\nAdobe is proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer. We do not discriminate based on gender, race or color, ethnicity or national origin, age, disability, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, veteran status, or any other protected characteristic. Learn more.\n\nAdobe aims to make our Careers website and recruiting process accessible to any and all users. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation to navigate our website or complete the application process, email accommodations@adobe.com or call +1 408-536-3015.\n\nAI Use Guidelines for Interviews:\nOur interviews are designed to reflect your own skills and thinking. The use of AI or recording tools during live interviews is not permitted unless explicitly invited by the interviewer or approved in advance as part of a reasonable accommodation. If these tools are used inappropriately or in a way that misrepresents your work, your application may not move forward in the process.\n\nAt Adobe, we empower employees to innovate with AI — and we look for candidates eager to do the same. As part of the hiring experience, we provide clear guidance on where AI is encouraged during the process and where it’s restricted during live interviews. See how we think about AI in the hiring experience .','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Adobe','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=61ff247679929108','scraped','2 days ago'),(2562,NULL,'job','Senior QA Automation Engineer','Contract','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',850.00,'$800 - $900 a day','Job details\nPosted01 May 2026\nSalaryAU$800 - AU$900 per day\nLocationSydney CBD\nJob type Contract\nDiscipline Digital & Product Engineering\nReference90M0707180_1777606934\nJob description\nQA Automation Engineer with a leading finance client (consulting through FinXL)\n\nFinXL Professional Services is a leading IT consultancy that partners with clients to bridge the gap between business needs and technology capabilities. Since 2003, we\'ve been delivering high-value ICT services across government, finance, telecommunications, and enterprise sectors.\n\nFinXL is seeking a QA Automation Engineer to join our consulting team and be deployed with a leading finance client on a 12 months contract in Melbourne. FinXL is also able to take over existing visas and provide sponsorship for consultants.\n\nResponsibilities\nDesign, build, and maintain automated testing frameworks from scratch using Playwright.\nImplement non-functional testing including performance and security for calculation engines.\nDesign control frameworks to validate the accuracy of AI-generated advice logic.\nIntegrate automated test suites directly into established CI/CD pipelines.\nEnsure the platform supports frequent, low-risk releases through robust automation.\nDefine the overarching testing strategy for a newly formed onshore agile squad.\nMentor associate testers to maintain high quality standards across the team.\nKey Skills & Experience\nExtensive commercial experience in QA automation specifically using Playwright.\nStrong technical background working with JBoss environments.\nProven track record of integrating automated tests into CI/CD pipelines.\nExperience testing within highly regulated environments, preferably Banking & Finance.\nDemonstrated ability to develop testing strategies and frameworks from the ground up.\nExcellent communication and interpersonal skills.\nEngagement Details\n12 months contract with a leading finance client.\nHybrid working model with 2-3 days/ week in the office in Sydney CBD.\nNext Steps\nApply now highlighting relevant skills and experience and address your application to Julia Leung. Due to the high volume of applications only shortlisted candidates can be contacted.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'FinXL','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a8b0bf971c44b1f5','scraped','2 days ago'),(2563,NULL,'job','Senior GenAI/Agentic AI Sales Specialist, AWS ANZ Specialist Team','Full-time','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nAWS Global Sales drives adoption of the AWS cloud worldwide, enabling customers of all sizes to innovate and expand in the cloud. Our team empowers every customer to grow by providing tailored service, unmatched technology, and consistent support. We dive deep to understand each customer\'s unique challenges, then craft innovative solutions that accelerate their success. This customer-first approach is how we built the world\'s most adopted cloud. Join us and help us grow.\n\nWould you like to be part of a team shaping the future of the IT industry through responsible and innovative use of Artificial Intelligence? Amazon Web Services (AWS) is advancing the next evolution of cloud computing with Generative AI and Agentic AI technologies. We are seeking a Senior GenAI / Agentic AI Sales Specialist who brings strong technical AI knowledge together with a customer-centric, outcome-focused approach to revenue growth.\n\nThis role partners closely with customers to understand their goals, translate complex AI capabilities into clear business value, and support successful AI adoption at scale. If you enjoy collaborating with diverse stakeholders, communicating technical concepts with clarity, and contributing to long-term customer success, we encourage you to apply.\n\nAWS Global Sales supports customers of all sizes across the region to innovate and grow in the cloud. As organizations increasingly adopt foundation models, large language models (LLMs), and agentic AI, we are expanding our team of technical sales professionals. We are seeking to hire people who can help customers identify and prioritise AI use cases to create AWS opportunities, build sustainable pipelines, and guide customers through complex AI adoption journeys across Australia and New Zealand.\n\nKey job responsibilities\nSales & Revenue Contribution\n• Support the achievement of sales targets by developing and maintaining a healthy pipeline and guiding customers through end-to-end sales cycles, from discovery through to agreement;\n• Create thoughtful account plans and territory strategies in partnership with internal teams, while maintaining accurate forecasting using CRM tools;\n• Collaborate with customers to identify and qualify high-impact AI use cases aligned to their business priorities and strategic objectives.\nTechnical Sales & Solution Advisory\n• Act as a trusted advisor on AWS GenAI and Agentic AI services, helping customers understand potential outcomes, value, and return on investment;\n• Lead technical discovery sessions and contribute to demonstrations, proofs of concept, and solution design, including model selection, fine-tuning, and deployment approaches;\n• Provide guidance on model evaluation, responsible AI practices, governance considerations, and relevant compliance requirements.\nCustomer Engagement & Market Development\n• Build and maintain strong relationships with decision-makers and executive stakeholders through a consultative, collaborative approach;\n• Partner with internal teams to deliver workshops, enablement sessions, and solution reviews that support customer learning and adoption;\n• Share customer insights and feedback with AWS AI product teams to help inform product direction and improvements.\n\nAbout the team\nAbout the team\nDiverse Experiences\nAWS values diverse experiences. Even if you do not meet all of the qualifications and skills listed in the job description, we encourage candidates to apply. If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying.\n\nWhy AWS?\nAmazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.\n\nInclusive Team Culture\nHere at AWS, it’s in our nature to learn and be curious. Our employee-led affinity groups foster a culture of inclusion that empower us to be proud of our differences. Ongoing events and learning experiences, including our Conversations on Race and Ethnicity (CORE) and AmazeCon (gender diversity) conferences, inspire us to never stop embracing our uniqueness.\n\nMentorship & Career Growth\nWe’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional.\n\nWork/Life Balance\nWe value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve in the cloud.\n\nWhat if I don’t meet all the requirements?\n\nThat’s okay! We hire people who have a passion for learning and are curious. You will be supported in your career development here at AWS. You will have plenty of opportunities to build your technical, leadership, business and consulting skills. Your onboarding will set you up for success, including a combination of formal and informal training. You’ll also have a chance to gain AWS certifications and access mentorship programs. You will learn from and collaborate with some of the brightest technical minds in the industry today.\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- 7+ years of direct sales or business development in software, cloud or SaaS markets selling to C-level executives experience\n- 10+ years of business development, partner development, sales or alliances management experience\n- Experience positioning and selling technology to new customers and new market segments\n- Experience proactively growing customer relationships within an account while expanding their understanding of the customer\'s business\n- Ability to operate with a high degree of ambiguity and in a matrix organization\n- Proven track record in engaging with C-Suite contacts in customers communicating and present with impact towards agreed project outcomes.\n- Proven track record of successful engagements with customers in Australia & New Zealand.\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Track record of success driving adoption of new and disruptive technologies within Enterprise accounts.\n- Track record of consistent territory growth and sales quota attainment\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Web Services Australia Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c3f5d334944a5392','scraped','Just posted'),(2564,NULL,'job','Principal Business Development Specialist APJC, Betting and Gaming Technology','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nThe Principal Business Development Specialist for Betting & Gaming serves as a dedicated industry expert embedded within Asia Pacific Japan China (APJC) account teams, driving AWS adoption through line-of-business opportunities across the betting, gaming, and lottery sectors. This role combines deep industry expertise with strategic account planning to identify, develop, and launch opportunities that address specific Betting and Gaming customer workflows and business challenges across the APJC region.\n\nKey job responsibilities\nAccount Strategy & Planning\n- Contribute Betting and Gaming industry perspective to Account Plans for assigned proactive coverage accounts in APJC\n- Identify and map Line of Business (LOB) contacts and stakeholders within betting and gaming operators\n- Utilize Industry Score Card to identify whitespace opportunities across five Betting and Gaming solution areas: Player Engagement, Compliance & Player Protection, Payment & Risk Management, Operations, and Casino Game Development\n- Collaborate with account teams to develop jurisdiction-specific strategies aligned with APJC regulatory environments\nOpportunity Development & Execution\n- Drive Betting and Gaming opportunities from Qualified stage through Launch, focusing on measurable business outcomes\n- Evangelize AWS services, partner solutions, and Professional Services tailored to betting and gaming use cases\n- Achieve 70% partner attachment rate on launched opportunities, leveraging Betting and Gaming ecosystem partners\n- Participate in Executive Briefing Centers (EBCs) and executive engagements with C-suite stakeholders\n- Act as facilitator to bring in specialized AWS resources, world-wide specialist teams, ProServe, and partner capabilities\nThought Leadership & Enablement\n- Conduct internal enablement sessions for APJC account teams on Betting and Gaming industry trends, use cases, and AWS solutions\n- Lead external thought leadership sessions with customers and at industry events\n- Contribute to Go-to-Market packages for scale Betting and Gaming customers\n- Build and maintain relationships with key industry associations and regulatory bodies in APJC jurisdictions\nRegional Market Development\n\n- Develop deep understanding of APJC betting and gaming regulatory landscape across key markets (Australia, NZ, Philippines, Singapore, Vietnam, Hong Kong, etc.)\n- Identify regional trends, competitive dynamics, and market opportunities specific to APJC\n- Build partner ecosystem relationships with regional Betting and Gaming technology providers and system integrators\n\nA day in the life\nYour primary focus is being the go-to expert on betting and gaming for our teams working with customers across Asia-Pacific. You\'re the person who understands how operators actually run their businesses and can connect those challenges to solutions.\n\nMost days, you\'re embedded with account teams having conversations with betting and gaming companies. You might start your morning on a call with a sports betting operator in Australia, helping the team understand what their Chief Marketing Officer really cares about when it comes to player engagement. You\'re translating between the business side and the technical side, making sure everyone\'s speaking the same language.\n\nYou\'ll spend a good chunk of time in customer meetings - sometimes it\'s a formal executive briefing where you\'re presenting to C-level folks, other times it\'s a working session with their operations team diving into the specifics of how they could modernize their platform. You\'re not just talking about technology; you\'re talking about their business outcomes, their regulatory challenges, and how they can actually move faster in their market.\n\nBetween customer engagements, you\'re also teaching. You\'ll run sessions for our account teams to help them understand what\'s happening in the industry - new trends in responsible gaming, how payment fraud is evolving, what\'s changing in different regulatory environments across the region. You become their trusted advisor on all things betting and gaming.\n\nWhat makes this role interesting is the variety. One day you might be helping a casino game studio figure out how to deploy across multiple countries, the next you\'re at an industry conference sharing insights on player protection technology, and the day after that you\'re working with partners to put together a comprehensive solution for a major operator.\n\nYou\'ll also get pulled into strategic planning - helping teams think through which opportunities to pursue, where the white space is in an account, and how to approach complex deals that might take months to close. It\'s part detective work, part strategy, part relationship building.\n\nTravel is definitely part of the mix - you\'ll be visiting customers, attending industry events, and collaborating with teams across the region. But it\'s purposeful travel that lets you build real relationships and stay connected to what\'s actually happening in the market.\n\nAbout the team\nThe AWS Industries team is committed to helping industry customers enable their digital transformation journeys. Our primary goal is to meet customers in their cloud journeys and work backwards from their industry-specific needs to transform their businesses and industries. Our team focuses on business outcomes and industry use cases on behalf of our customers, whether that is how we build products and solutions, how we sell, how we deliver, or how we partner.\n\nYou\'ll be part of the Geo Industry Specialist Team (GIST) within the broader Media, Entertainment & Games and Sports Industry Business Unit. The team operates with a strong focus on customer obsession and delivering results, guided by organizational tenets that emphasize measuring what matters, building diverse perspectives, and scaling bright spots.\n\nThe team works collaboratively across multiple segments including studios, platforms, publishers, game services, and the full spectrum of betting and gaming operators and suppliers as well as regulators. The team culture emphasizes going forward with the customer, fostering innovation through curiosity, and empowering high-velocity decisions.\n\nYou\'ll work closely with account teams, Solutions Architects, AWS Professional Services, Industry Marketing, and an extensive partner ecosystem. The team values collaboration and operates with a builder mentality, focusing on strategic initiatives like accelerating time to market, market expansion, systems modernization, optimizing player acquisition and engagement, and helping customers achieve sustainable profitability through data-driven personalization and AI.\n\nBased in the APJC region (Hong Kong, or Australia preferred), you\'ll be part of a geographically distributed team that comes together regularly for strategy sessions, planning meetings, and collaborative workshops focused on driving customer success and business growth.\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- 7+ years of developing, negotiating and executing business agreements experience\n- 10+ years of Go-To-Market, Business Development, Sales, or Consulting experience\n- 5+ years of working with Core Cloud Technology Services, including, but not limited to Compute, Edge, Hybrid, Security, and/or Networking experience\n- 7+ years of solving problems with technology in the Media & Entertainment Industry experience\n- 7+ years of solving problems with technology in the Global Financial Services Industry experience\n- 5+ years of working with Enterprise Application Modernization and Migration technologies, including, but not limited to, Mainframe, Serverless, Containers, or Cloud Operations experience\n- Bachelor\'s degree\n- Experience developing strategies that influence leadership decisions at the organizational level\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Experience as a founder or executive focused on related segments, or as a practice leader or business unit owner\n- Experience selling to Fortune 1000 or Global 2000 organizations\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Web Services Australia Pty Ltd - D81','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=cede0c6561be47f3','scraped','Just posted'),(2565,NULL,'job','Sr. Analytics Sales Specialist, AWS ANZ Specialist Team','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nAWS Global Sales drives adoption of the AWS cloud worldwide, enabling customers of all sizes to innovate and expand in the cloud. Our team empowers every customer to grow by providing tailored service, unmatched technology, and consistent support. We dive deep to understand each customer\'s unique challenges, then craft innovative solutions that accelerate their success. This customer-first approach is how we built the world\'s most adopted cloud. Join us and help us grow.\n\nWould you like to be part of a team shaping the future of business, helping customers put their data to work by building modern data foundations with cloud services? Amazon Web Services (AWS) is advancing the next evolution of cloud computing with comprehensive analytics, business intelligence and AIML technologies. We are seeking a Senior Analytics Sales Specialist who brings a combination of customer transformation experience and strong technical analytics knowledge together with a customer-centric, outcome-focused approach to revenue growth for our Analytics business in ANZ.\n\nThis role partners closely with customers to understand their goals, translate complex analytics capabilities into clear business value, and support successful analytics adoption at scale. If you enjoy collaborating with diverse stakeholders, communicating technical concepts with clarity, and contributing to long-term customer success, we encourage you to apply.\n\nAWS Global Sales supports customers of all sizes across the region to innovate and grow in the cloud. As organizations seek to use AIML more effectively, we need to help them transform their data lakes, real-time analytics, and business intelligence solutions into a modern data architecture. We are expanding our team of technical sales professionals to scale our impact, hiring people who can help customers identify and prioritise analytics use cases to create AWS opportunities, build sustainable pipelines, and guide customers through complex analytics adoption journeys across Australia and New Zealand.\n\nKey job responsibilities\nSales & Revenue Contribution\n\n• Support the achievement of sales targets by developing and maintaining a healthy pipeline and guiding customers through end-to-end sales cycles, from discovery through to agreement;\n• Create thoughtful account plans and territory strategies in partnership with internal teams, while maintaining accurate forecasting using CRM tools;\n• Collaborate with customers to identify and qualify high-impact AI use cases aligned to their business priorities and strategic objectives.\nTechnical Sales & Solution Advisory\n• Act as a trusted advisor on AWS GenAI and Agentic AI services, helping customers understand potential outcomes, value, and return on investment;\n• Lead technical discovery sessions and contribute to demonstrations, proofs of concept, and solution design, including model selection, fine-tuning, and deployment approaches;\n• Provide guidance on model evaluation, responsible AI practices, governance considerations, and relevant compliance requirements.\n\nCustomer Engagement & Market Development\n\n• Be the leading evangelist for our prescriptive recommendations to customer business and technology leaders on transforming to a modern data architecture. Visibly lead this externally and internally on stage, on social media and in-person;\n• Build and maintain strong relationships with decision-makers and executive stakeholders through a consultative, collaborative approach;\n• Partner with internal teams to deliver workshops, enablement sessions, and solution reviews that support customer learning and adoption;\n• Share customer insights and feedback with AWS Analytics and AIML product teams to help inform product direction and improvements.\n\nAbout the team\nDiverse Experiences\nAWS values diverse experiences. Even if you do not meet all of the qualifications and skills listed in the job description, we encourage candidates to apply. If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying.\n\nWhy AWS?\nAmazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.\n\nInclusive Team Culture\nHere at AWS, it’s in our nature to learn and be curious. Our employee-led affinity groups foster a culture of inclusion that empower us to be proud of our differences. Ongoing events and learning experiences, including our Conversations on Race and Ethnicity (CORE) and AmazeCon conferences, inspire us to never stop embracing our uniqueness.\n\nMentorship & Career Growth\nWe’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional.\n\nWork/Life Balance\nWe value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve in the cloud.\n\nWhat if I don’t meet all the requirements?\n\nThat’s okay! We hire people who have a passion for learning and are curious. You will be supported in your career development here at AWS. You will have plenty of opportunities to build your technical, leadership, business and consulting skills. Your onboarding will set you up for success, including a combination of formal and informal training. You’ll also have a chance to gain AWS certifications and access mentorship programs. You will learn from and collaborate with some of the brightest technical minds in the industry today.\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- 10+ years of business development, partner development, sales or alliances management experience\n- Experience positioning and selling technology to new customers and new market segments\n- Experience proactively growing customer relationships within an account while expanding their understanding of the customer\'s business\n- Experience with customer relationship management, especially C-suite level customer engagement\n- 7+ years of direct sales or business development in software, cloud or SaaS markets selling to C-level executives experience\n- Experience building and leading large teams and have worked in matrixed operating structures\n- Experience architecting, migrating, transforming or modernizing customer requirements to the cloud\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Experience influencing innovation through a partner ecosystem with either solutions or programs that have demonstrated success at enterprise customers\n- Experience meeting revenue targets and quotas\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Web Services Australia Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=180b548da34ea456','scraped','Just posted'),(2566,NULL,'job','Partner Success Specialist, AWS Specialist and Partner Organization','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nAs a Partner Success Specialist (PSS) within the AWS Specialists & Partners (ASP) org, you will be responsible for scaling AWS\'s customer success methodologies across our partner ecosystem to drive measurable business outcomes and accelerate customer value realization. You will architect and implement frameworks that enable partners to drive and measure customer value post-implementation. This role combines strategic enablement with hands-on execution to establish partners as extensions of AWS\'s customer success organization.\n\nKey job responsibilities\nStrategy and approach:\n- Develop strategies to align partner success initiatives with AWS’ long-term growth objectives\n- Design and adapt CS CoE\'s \'Activate to Advocate\' framework for partner implementation\n- Create partner-specific success metrics, health scoring models, and value realization playbooks\n- Develop governance models and operational excellence guidelines for partners\n- Architect scalable approaches to measure and improve partner-led customer outcomes\n- Contribute to the AWS Value Realization Toolkit for Partners\nPartner enablement and program execution:\n- Enable partners to build and scale their customer success practices by helping demonstrate how creating a customer success COE/customer success capabilities positively impacts their business model\n- Guide partners through post-sale stages\n- Deploy customer health frameworks and intervention strategies through partner channels\n- Build adoption, change management and stakeholder engagement toolkits\n- Coach partners in establishing systematic approaches to value realization\n- Build feedback mechanisms to continuously evolve success frameworks based on partner insights\n- Establish mechanisms to measure and track partner-led customer value realization\n- Drive partner-led adoption through technical milestones and usage metrics\n- Implement value realization frameworks to meet business KPIs\nOrganizational Leadership & Influence:\n- Partner with PDMs to drive adoption of success frameworks across partner organizations\n- Collaborate with Partner Sales to accelerate consumption through systematic approaches\n- Work with Partner Development Specialists to create industry-specific success playbooks\n- Build relationships across AWS organizations to drive program adoption and refinement\n- Influence senior stakeholders to drive organizational transformation\n- Develop business cases demonstrating quantifiable business impact and ROI of systematic partner enablement\nWe\'re looking for individuals with:\n- Deep expertise in partner enablement and post-sale value delivery\n- Strong program management and operational excellence capabilities\n- Proven ability to influence and drive change across complex organizations\n- Experience working with enterprise partners and cloud services\n- Experience using AI to automate and scale work more effectively\n\nAbout the team\nAbout AWS\n\nDiverse Experiences\nAWS values diverse experiences. Even if you do not meet all of the preferred qualifications and skills listed in the job description, we encourage candidates to apply. If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying.\n\nWhy AWS?\nAmazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.\n\nInclusive Team Culture\nAWS values curiosity and connection. Our employee-led and company-sponsored affinity groups promote inclusion and empower our people to take pride in what makes us unique. Our inclusion events foster stronger, more collaborative teams. Our continual innovation is fueled by the bold ideas, fresh perspectives, and passionate voices our teams bring to everything we do.\n\nMentorship & Career Growth\nWe’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional.\n\nWork/Life Balance\nWe value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve.\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- 10+ years of progressive technology implementation experience\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Experience working with Global System Integrators or strategic technology partners\n- Deep understanding of cloud services and enterprise digital transformation\n- Track record of building partner capabilities and driving partner-led growth\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Web Services Australia Pty Ltd - D81','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e2c8394219305638','scraped','Just posted'),(2567,NULL,'job','Head of Security, Public Sector ANZ, Worldwide Public Sector','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nOverview: The Principal Security Leader role drives strategic security adoption across the entire Australia and New Zealand Public Sector portfolio, encompassing Federal Government, National Security, Defence, Healthcare and Life Sciences, Education and Research, and State/Local Government segments. This role combines deep cross-sector security expertise with business development acumen to create repeatable patterns for security modernization and adoption at scale within diverse government contexts.\nStrategic Impact: Operating across multiple public sector domains with distinct security requirements, regulatory and compliance frameworks, this role architects and executes security-focused GTM strategies that enable both \"market creation\" and \"market scaling\" across varied maturity levels. The position requires sophisticated engagement across technical and business stakeholders to drive cloud adoption through both one-to-one and one-to-many motions, while understanding the unique security and regulatory requirements of each sector. The position works in collaboration with partner teams including Compliance & Security Assurance, Public Policy and OCISO capabilities ensuring proactive positioning of cloud centric security models that enable broad based adoption whilst lifting the watermark of government and customer cyber capability.\n\nKey job responsibilities\nCross-Sector Security Leadership\n• Drive security adoption strategies across all public sector segments\n• Develop sector-specific security frameworks and adoption patterns\n• Navigate diverse regulatory requirements including:\n• ISM ‘Protected’/NZISM ‘Restricted/Confidential’ data classifications for Federal Government\n• IRAP and Essential Eight for National Security and Regulated Industries\n• NEHTA and Privacy Act for Healthcare\n• CAUDIT and AARNet requirements for Education\n• State-specific security frameworks for State Government\n• Enable security modernization across all government tiers\nTechnical Security Excellence\n• Design multi-sector security architectures and patterns\n• Guide security implementations across varied compliance regimes\n• Develop sector-specific security reference architectures\n• Enable cross-sector security integration patterns\nMarket Development\n• Create sector-specific security adoption programs\n• Design vertical-aligned security GTM strategies\n• Build security patterns that scale across sectors\n• Enable cross-sector security knowledge sharing\nStakeholder Collaboration\n• Engage with sector-specific regulatory bodies\n• Partner with vertical-focused AWS teams\n• Coordinate with state and federal security agencies\n• Build relationships with industry peak bodies including:\n• Digital Health Agency\n• Education Standards bodies\n• State Government CIO forums\n• Federal security agencies\n• Local Government Associations\nSecurity Policy Influence\n• Shape multi-jurisdiction security frameworks\n• Drive alignment across federal and state requirements\n• Influence sector-specific security standards\n• Enable cross-sector security initiatives\nProgram Development:\n• Create vertical-specific security adoption frameworks\n• Develop cross-sector security implementation patterns\n• Design security programs that scale across jurisdictions\n• Build sector-specific security modernization roadmaps\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- 7+ years of developing, negotiating and executing business agreements experience\n- 7+ years of business development, partnership management, or sourcing new business experience\n- 7+ years of professional or military experience\n- Experience writing technical articles, speaking at technology conferences, and contributing to open source\n- Experience developing and executing on GTM strategies that are large in scope\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Experience developing, deploying and managing AI products at scale\n- Experience interfacing with customers (Enterprise, SMB, and Startups) and ability to convert customer requirements to high level architecture solutions to build on\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Web Services Australia Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=7d23cb98f9ebfc6d','scraped','Just posted'),(2568,NULL,'job','Senior AI Specialist Sales, Data and AI, Specialist Team','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nWould you like to be part of a team shaping the future of the IT industry through responsible and innovative use of Artificial Intelligence? AWS seeks a Senior AI Specialist Sales professional to drive adoption of AWS\'s full stack AI services across Australia.\nAmazon Web Services (AWS) is advancing the next evolution of AI adoption. We are seeking a Senior AI Sales Specialist who brings strong technical AI knowledge together with a customer-centric, outcomes-focused approach to revenue growth.\n\nThis role partners closely with customers to understand their goals, translate complex AI capabilities into clear business value, and support successful adoption at scale. If you enjoy collaborating with diverse stakeholders, communicating technical concepts with clarity, and contributing to long-term customer success, we encourage you to apply.\n\nAbility to engage with CEO/LOB owners for strategic conversations to leverage AI for business transformation, as well as with CTO/CAIO for AI-implementation linked technical architecture conversations. AI specialist solution architects will support technical deep dives.\n\nAWS Global Sales supports customers of all sizes across the region to innovate and grow in the cloud. As organizations increasingly adopt foundation models, large language models (LLMs), and autonomous AI agents, we are expanding our team of technical sales professionals who can identify opportunities, build sustainable pipelines, and guide customers through complex AI adoption journeys across Australia.\n\nKey job responsibilities\nSales & Revenue Contribution\n• Support the achievement of sales targets by developing and maintaining a healthy pipeline and guiding customers through end-to-end sales cycles, from discovery through agreement\n• Create thoughtful account plans and territory strategies in partnership with internal teams, while maintaining accurate forecasting using CRM tools\n• Collaborate with customers to identify and qualify high-impact AI use cases aligned to their business priorities and strategic objectives\nTechnical Sales & Solution Advisory\n• Act as a trusted advisor on AWS GenAI and Agentic AI services, helping customers understand potential outcomes, value, and return on investment\n• Lead technical discovery sessions and contribute to demonstrations, proofs of concept, and solution design, including model selection, fine-tuning, and deployment approaches\n• Provide guidance on model evaluation, responsible AI practices, governance considerations, and relevant compliance requirements\nCustomer Engagement & Market Development\n• Build and maintain strong relationships with decision-makers and executive stakeholders through a consultative, collaborative approach\n• Partner with internal teams to deliver workshops, enablement sessions, and solution reviews that support customer learning and adoption\n• Share customer insights and feedback with AWS AI product teams to help inform product direction and improvements\n• Engage C-suite executives to drive AWS AI services adoption: CEOs (business transformation), CTOs/CAIOs (technical architecture), CFOs (ROI models), line of business owners (use cases). Lead AI-focussed Executive Briefing Centers, board presentations, and strategic planning workshops.”\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- 7+ years of experience in technology roles, including technical or solution-oriented sales, with a demonstrated history of contributing to revenue goals\n- Experience supporting complex, multi-stakeholder sales engagements and managing pipelines with a focus on accuracy and transparency\n- Strong communication skills, with the ability to explain complex technical topics in a clear, engaging way for both technical and executive audiences\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Experience working with Generative AI technologies, including foundation models, LLMs, or autonomous agent frameworks\n- Exposure to AI model development, fine-tuning, or production deployment\n- Familiarity with prompt engineering, retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) architectures, fine-tuning techniques, and AI deployment patterns\n- Bachelor\'s degree in computer science, machine learning, engineering, or related fields, or Master\'s degree\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Web Services Australia Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5953fe200d8bcfa0','scraped','Just posted'),(2569,NULL,'job','Sr AI Solution Architect, Data & AI Specialist Solutions Architect team','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nAmazon Web Services (AWS) is leading the next phase of AI adoption and is seeking a hands-on AI Specialist Solution Architect (SSA). AWS Specialist Solutions Architects (SSAs) are technologists with deep domain-specific expertise, able to address advanced concepts and feature designs.\nAs part of the AWS sales organization, SSAs work with customers who have complex challenges that require expert-level knowledge to solve. SSAs craft scalable, flexible, and resilient technical architectures that address those challenges. This might involve guiding customers as they refactor an application or design an entirely new cloud-based system.\nSpecialist SAs play a critical role in capturing customer feedback, advocating for roadmap enhancements and anticipating customer requirements as they work backwards from their needs. As domain experts, SSAs also participate in field engagement and enablement, producing content such as whitepapers, blogs, and workshops for customers, partners, and the AWS Technical Field.\nThis role focuses on converting AI ambition into programs that can be delivered, operated, and scaled in production environments.\n\nKey job responsibilities\n• The AI Specialist SA team builds technical relationships with customers of all sizes and operate as their trusted advisor, ensuring they get the most out of the cloud at every stage of their journey while adopting GenAI/ML and Agentic technologies across their organisation.\n• You’ll manage the overall technical relationship between AWS and our customers, making recommendations on security, cost, performance, reliability and operational efficiency to accelerate their challenging GenAI/ML and Agentic projects.\n• Internally, you will be the voice of the customer, sharing their needs with regard to their usage of our services impacting the roadmap of AWS GenAI/ML and Agentic features.\n• In this role, your creativity will link technology to tangible solutions, with the opportunity to define cloud-native GenAI/ML and Agentic architectural patterns for a variety of use cases.\n• You will participate in the creation and sharing of best practices, technical content and new reference architectures (e.g. white papers, code samples, blog posts) and evangelize and educate about running GenAI/ML and Agentic workloads on AWS technology (e.g. through workshops, user groups, meetups, public speaking, online videos or conferences).\n• Technical Leadership & Mentorship: Lead hands-on deep dives and technical workshops, contributing reusable code, reference architectures, and internal technical assets for the broader engineering organization.\n\nAbout the team\n#genai\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- 7+ years of design, implementation, or consulting in applications and infrastructures experience\n- 5+ years of specific technology domain areas (e.g. software development, cloud computing, systems engineering, infrastructure, security, networking, data & analytics) experience\n- Ability to influence customer and internal business decision makers as a technical thought leader and ability to effectively communicate across an increasing diversity of audiences internally and externally\n- Hands-on experience with AWS ecosystems (including Bedrock, AgentCore, and SageMaker) to set up secure, private-network AI environments, and practical experience implementing Retrieval-Augmented Generation using embeddings, vector stores, and semantic search optimization.\n- Experience implementing AI solutions that can include integration of LLMs/multi-modal FMs in large scale systems, fine-tuning LLMs, deployment and distributed inference of LLMs, RAG, FM evaluation, Vector DBs, Agentic workflows, prompt/context engineering, and MLOps.\n- 6+ years of design/implementation of production AI systems\n- 5+ years management of technical, customer facing resources\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Cloud Technology Certification (such as Solutions Architecture, Cloud Security Professional or Cloud DevOps Engineering)\n- Ability to lead a team or small organization-wide initiative with business objectives that are partially defined. Strong ability to determine solution strategy and where to simplify or extend solutions for the best outcome\n- Proven ability to lead projects with complex challenges with extensible, operationally excellent, cost optimized, and aligned solutions outcomes\n- Technical Cloud Certification & Master\'s degree in computer science, mathematics, statistics, machine learning or equivalent quantitative field, or PhD\n- Experience in running & fine-tuning Large and Small Language Models using advanced techniques like LoRA/QLoRA, Instruction Tuning, and RLHF to optimize for specific domain tasks.\n- Expertise in architecting AI systems within highly regulated or security-sensitive environments (e.g., Financial Services, Healthcare, Public Sector).\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Web Services Australia Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=807c92468f83d6a1','scraped','Just posted'),(2570,NULL,'job','Senior Applied AI Solutions Architect, Amazon Connect, AWS Applied AI Solutions','Full-time','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nThe Applied AI Solutions Architecture team within AWS is seeking a hands-on, customer-obsessed Solutions Architect to accelerate customer adoption of Amazon Connect\'s AI capabilities. This role is part of the AI Velocity Team, a service-specific approach that assigns dedicated advisory and hands-on development resources directly to customers to achieve production-ready outcomes in weeks instead of months.\n\nAs an Applied AI Solutions Architect, you will be embedded with customers to help them prepare their Amazon Connect implementations for production by focusing on three pillars of agentic AI:\nModel Selection: Guiding customers through evaluating and selecting the right foundation models (via Amazon Bedrock) for their contact center use cases, balancing latency, accuracy, cost, and compliance requirements.\n\nPrompt Engineering: Designing, testing, and optimizing AI prompts and system instructions for Amazon Connect AI agents, including self-service agents, answer recommendation agents, and custom orchestrator agents.\n\nTooling: Architecting and building the tool integrations (APIs, Lambda functions, data connectors, knowledge bases) that agentic AI systems use to take actions on behalf of customers and agents. This included configuring MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers for standardized tool discovery and invocation, and enabling A2A (Agent-to-Agent) communication patterns for multi-agent orchestration across enterprise systems.\n\nA key dimension of this role is Customer Data Readiness. Assessing, preparing, and structuring customer data assets so that AI agents can reliably access, retrieve, and act on the right information. You will help customers evaluate their data landscape, identify gaps, establish data pipelines, and ensure their knowledge bases, CRMs, and backend systems are AI-ready before agents go live.\n\nYou will work at the intersection of contact center operations and applied AI, helping customers move from proof-of-concept to pre-production for their Amazon Connect Unlimited AI deployments. This is a deeply technical, hands-on role, you will write code, build integrations, configure agents, and pair-program with customer engineering teams.\n\nKey job responsibilities\nLead technical discovery sessions to understand customer business requirements, contact center architecture, and AI readiness, translating these into solution designs and implementation plans.\n\nConduct data readiness assessments across customer systems (CRMs, knowledge bases, ticketing, order management) to identify gaps, recommend remediation, and establish the data foundation for AI agent tool use and RAG-powered responses.\n\nDesign and configure agentic AI solutions within Amazon Connect, including multi-agent orchestration, prompt engineering, model selection, guardrails, and tool integration.\n\nDeploy Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers to expose customer tools, data sources, and APIs in a standardized format for dynamic AI agent discovery and invocation.\n\nArchitect agent-to-agent communication patterns enabling multi-agent workflows across enterprise boundaries (e.g., billing, order management, IT support).\n\nBuild serverless integrations (Lambda, API Gateway, Step Functions, Python/Node.js) connecting AI agents with customer data systems and cloud-based data stores (DynamoDB, RDS, S3, OpenSearch, Kendra/Knowledge Bases for Bedrock).\n\nLeverage agentic development environments (e.g., Kiro) to accelerate spec-driven development, MCP configuration, and AI-assisted code generation.\n\nGuide customers through AI agent testing, evaluation, and validation against success criteria prior to production deployment.\n\nCreate reusable artifacts (reference architectures, implementation guides, prompt libraries, data readiness checklists) to scale best practices.\n\nA day in the life\nDiverse Experiences\nAWS values diverse experiences. Even if you do not meet all of the preferred qualifications and skills listed in the job description, we encourage candidates to apply. If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying.\n\nWhy AWS?\nAmazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.\n\nInclusive Team Culture\nAWS values curiosity and connection. Our employee-led and company-sponsored affinity groups promote inclusion and empower our people to take pride in what makes us unique. Our inclusion events foster stronger, more collaborative teams. Our continual innovation is fueled by the bold ideas, fresh perspectives, and passionate voices our teams bring to everything we do.\n\nMentorship & Career Growth\nWe’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional.\n\nWork/Life Balance\nWe value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve.\n\nAbout the team\nAmazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating, that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.\n\nThis position is part of the Amazon Specialist and Partner Organization (ASP). Specialists own the end-to-end go-to-market strategy for their respective technology domains, providing the business and technical expertise to help our customers succeed. Partner teams own the strategy, recruiting, development, and growth of our key technology and consulting partners. Together they provide our customers with the expertise and scale needed to build innovative solutions for their most complex challenges\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Experience in design, implementation, or consulting in applications and infrastructures\n- Experience communicating across technical and non-technical audiences, including executive level stakeholders or clients\n- 5+ years of experience building integrations across AI, Agentic AI, CRM, and contact center solutions or experience with communications protocols and APIs such as WebRTC and SIP or similar CCaaS technology.\n- 5+ years of experience building integrations across WFM, CRM, and contact center solutions or experience with communications protocols and APIs such as WebRTC and SIP or similar CCaaS technology\n- Experience with complex Contact Center as a Service (CCaaS) implementations\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Experience in infrastructure architecture, database architecture and networking\n- AWS certification, such as, AWS Solutions Architect, or a similar cloud certification, or Associate\'s degree or above\n- Knowledge of presentations and whiteboarding skills with a high degree of comfort speaking with internal and external executives, IT management, and developers\n- History of successful technical consulting and/or architecture engagements with large-scale customers or enterprises.\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Web Services Australia Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=bbbc35db017e753f','scraped','Just posted'),(2571,NULL,'job','Account Executive, ANZ Public Sector (Greenfield)','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nAre you passionate about helping Government, Healthcare, and Not-for-Profit organizations transform how they deliver services to citizens and communities through cloud technology?\n\nAs a Greenfield Account Executive within Amazon Web Services (AWS) ANZ Public Sector, you will join a newly formed team focused on expanding AWS adoption in emerging public sector accounts. You will own the full sales cycle—from prospecting through close—helping public sector organizations reinvent their IT strategy through cloud computing.\n\nThis role demands creative problem-solving, tenacity, and the ability to develop novel approaches for reaching and engaging prospective customers. You will engage customers across all organizational levels, building relationships with both technical teams and business leaders to drive cloud adoption.\n\nThis position requires working from the local office when not at customer sites.\n\nKey job responsibilities\nSales Execution\n\n- Prospect and qualify emerging public sector accounts across Government, Healthcare, Education, and Not-for-Profit sectors\n- Manage the full sales cycle from prospecting through close\n- Meet or exceed quarterly revenue targets while maintaining robust pipeline coverage\n- Maintain accurate sales forecasts and pipeline reporting in Salesforce\n\nCustomer Engagement\n\n- Develop and execute territory plans to maximize market penetration\n- Translate cloud and AI capabilities into mission-relevant use cases for public sector organizations\n- Build relationships across customer organizations, including executive leadership, technical teams, IT/operations, and procurement\n- Conduct discovery calls to understand organizational missions and technical challenges\n\nPublic Sector Expertise\n\n- Navigate public sector procurement processes including RFPs, cooperative contracts, and federal/state/local contract vehicles\n- Apply knowledge of public sector compliance requirements, certifications, and fiscal year buying cycles\n- Structure deals that meet public sector regulatory, compliance, and grant-funded operating requirements\n\nCollaboration\n\n- Partner with Solutions Architects, AWS Professional Services, AWS partners, and internal stakeholders to accelerate deal velocity\n- Collaborate with the partner ecosystem (systems integrators, resellers, distributors) to drive customer success and extend market reach\n- Use data, AI, and insights to prioritize outreach and identify high-potential prospects\n\nA day in the life\nYour day starts reviewing your pipeline and identifying which emerging accounts need attention. You\'ll research target organizations across Government, Healthcare, Education, and Not-for-Profit sectors—understanding their missions and key stakeholders. You\'ll execute outreach campaigns, make prospecting calls, and secure meetings with decision-makers exploring cloud transformation.\n\nYou\'ll conduct discovery conversations, collaborate with Solutions Architects and AWS Professional Services to shape compelling propositions, and navigate procurement processes. You\'ll update your CRM, refine your territory strategy, and forecast accurately. This role offers the autonomy to innovate, think differently, and make an impact across a new team whilst helping public sector organisations transform through cloud technology.\n\nAbout the team\nDiverse Experiences\nAWS values diverse experiences. Even if you do not meet all of the preferred qualifications and skills listed in the job description, we encourage candidates to apply. If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying.\n\nWhy AWS?\nAmazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.\n\nInclusive Team Culture\nAWS values curiosity and connection. Our employee-led and company-sponsored affinity groups promote inclusion and empower our people to take pride in what makes us unique. Our inclusion events foster stronger, more collaborative teams. Our continual innovation is fueled by the bold ideas, fresh perspectives, and passionate voices our teams bring to everything we do.\n\nMentorship & Career Growth\nWe’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional.\n\nWork/Life Balance\nWe value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve.\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Experience in consulting, sales strategy, sales operations, business development or program management at a mid-to-large scale company with increasing influence and responsibility\n- Experience with sales CRM tools such as Salesforce or similar software\n- 5+ years technology sales, business development or sales program management experience with a track record of exceeding sales goals\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Experience managing and growing complex business relationship at scale\n- Experience in strategic thinking about business, enterprise software products, and new technology platforms and architectures or equivalent\n- Experience driving new business in greenfield accounts, working with partners to drive customer engagements and revenue growth\n- Experience navigating public sector procurement processes and contract vehicles with demonstrated ability to build and execute territory plans\n- Experience building and managing sales pipeline (directly or indirectly) focused on driving revenue, adoption, and market penetration\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Web Services Australia Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e630ac3984043605','scraped','Just posted'),(2572,NULL,'job','Amazon Quick Strategist, Amazon Quick Customer Success Team, AWS','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nAWS is known for its relentless customer obsession. Our Professional Services teams are on the front line of helping customers succeed using AWS technologies that align with the new ways of managing people and rearchitecting critical processes to leverage the capabilities of Gen AI. AWS Amazon Q Customer Success Team (Q-CST) members leverage their deep knowledge of AWS services and market trends in collaboration with our sales and partner teams to propose, architect, and implement transformational solutions for customers. We make customer success a reality using AWS Gen AI services as an enabler.\n\nAmazon Quick Strategists are dynamic professionals who architect and propel customer success, expertly guiding organizations from initial proof-of-concept to full-scale production implementation of Amazon Quick. These visionaries excel at crafting strategic roadmaps that expand Amazon Quick footprint across the enterprise, driving innovation and efficiency. With a strong executive presence, they skillfully navigate interactions with internal leadership (VPs, Directors) and diverse stakeholders, while rapidly building trust with Account Teams and customers at all levels, from Enterprise Architects to C-Suite executives. As technology specialists with keen business acumen, they possess the unique ability to identify high-impact use cases, quantify value, and drive measurable ROI, positioning them as indispensable partners in their customer\' digital transformation journeys.\n\nStrategists orchestrate contractual agreements, align customer expectations, and ensure flawless delivery of solutions. This hybrid role combines AWS expertise, hands-on building skills, and cross-industry business acumen. Ideal candidates are customer-obsessed professionals who seamlessly blend technical expertise with strategic insight to drive outcomes, while maintaining a strong commitment to continuous learning and growth.\n\nKey job responsibilities\n- Lead comprehensive generative AI transformation programs from sales to delivery, partnering closely with customers to drive successful adoption, implementation, and measurable business value realization\n- Orchestrate high-level discussions on complex, industry-specific business and technical concepts, fostering alignment among C-suite executives, line managers, and technologists.\n- Design and facilitate engaging workshops that bridge customer technical and business teams, showcasing the transformative potential of Amazon Q and our Gen AI offerings to uncover high-impact business value opportunities\n- Support delivery teams with hands-on programming, blocker remediation, escalations, and ideating and delivering custom solutions when needed\n- Cultivate and maintain strong, trusting relationships with both customers and internal stakeholders including the Generative AI Innovation Center, solutions architects, service teams, business development, marketing, industry specialists, partners and regional organizations\n- Stay informed on Amazon Q service updates and advancements in generative AI technology through continuous learning and industry engagement\n- Proactively identify areas for improvement across processes and initiatives, taking ownership to develop and implement effective solutions\n\nA day in the life\nDiverse Experiences\nAWS values diverse experiences. Even if you do not meet all of the preferred qualifications and skills listed in the job description, we encourage candidates to apply. If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying.\n\nWhy AWS?\nAmazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.\n\nInclusive Team Culture\nAWS values curiosity and connection. Our employee-led and company-sponsored affinity groups promote inclusion and empower our people to take pride in what makes us unique. Our inclusion events foster stronger, more collaborative teams. Our continual innovation is fueled by the bold ideas, fresh perspectives, and passionate voices our teams bring to everything we do.\n\nMentorship & Career Growth\nWe’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional.\n\nWork/Life Balance\nWe value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve.\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- 5+ years of cloud architecture and solution implementation experience\n- 7+ years of cloud architecture and solution implementation experience\n- 5+ years of external or internal customer facing, complex and large scale project management experience\n- 3+ years of working with Data & AI related technologies, including, but not limited to, AI/ML, GenAI, Analytics, Database, and/or Storage experience\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Experience developing, deploying and managing AI products at scale\n- 5+ years of highly scalable systems experience\n- Experience in representing and advocating for a variety of critical customers and stakeholders during executive-level prioritization and planning\n- Experience with vertical industry sales and delivery work of contemporary services and solutions\n- Experience with business development work including complex agreements w/ integrators and ISVs\n- Experience with international sales and delivery work with global F500 enterprise customers and partners\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Web Services Australia Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=3509905c731489df','scraped','Just posted'),(2573,NULL,'job','Print Technician','Permanent','Bendigo VIC 3550',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'AI Job Summary\nProven experience as a Print Technician or similar technical support role.\nStrong ability to diagnose and repair multi-function printers and print devices.\nCurrent and valid driver’s licence required for the role.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nOn-site • Permanent • Full-time • Mid-level Senior\nDescription\n\nDeliver reliable print performance through expert support, maintenance, and smart solutions.\n\nAt efex, no two days are the same. You’ll be hands-on across diverse client sites, diagnosing print issues, maintaining devices, and ensuring minimal downtime, backed by a supportive team that values practical problem solving and great service.\n\nWho we are:\n\nWith over 20 local branches supported by a strong national presence, efex is one of Australia’s leading IT and digital services providers. We deliver right-sized solutions in IT, print, and communications that help businesses run smarter, simpler, and more efficiently.\n\nOur culture is approachable and business-focused: we speak in plain language, build real relationships, and always put people first, our clients and our team.\n\nThe Role:\n\nWe’re looking for a Print Technician to join our Bendigo team full-time.\n\nIn this role, you’ll play a key part in delivering high-quality print support across our Managed IT and Print customer base. You’ll be responsible for installations, maintenance, and troubleshooting, ensuring our clients experience minimal downtime and maximum efficiency.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nProvide onsite and remote support for print devices and related software\nDeliver repairs, installations, and preventative maintenance across a range of devices\nBuild strong relationships with customers through clear communication and reliable service\nEnsure all work is completed in line with SLA requirements and service delivery processes\nMaintain accurate job documentation, system updates, and stock management\nProactively identify opportunities to improve service delivery and customer outcomes\n\nAbout You\n\nProven experience as a Print Technician or in a similar technical support role\nStrong experience diagnosing and repairing multi-function printers and print devices\nSolid understanding of print software and troubleshooting\nExposure to IT environments will be highly regarded\nExperience in production print environments will be highly regarded\nExperience working with Canon devices/solutions will be highly regarded\nExcellent customer service and communication skills, with the ability to explain technical issues clearly\nStrong attention to detail and commitment to quality outcomes\nAbility to work independently and as part of a team\nCurrent and valid driver’s licence\nBlue Card (or ability to obtain one) for working with children\n\nWhat we offer:\n\nCompetitive Salary: We recognize and value your expertise, offering top-tier compensation commensurate with your skills and experience.\nBirthday Leave: Take a well-deserved day off to celebrate your special day, because we believe in recognizing and celebrating our team members’ milestones.\nWellbeing leave: take up to two days from your personal leave each year to focus on your wellbeing\nVaried, hands-on role across multiple clients and technologies\nOpportunities to grow your technical skills in both print and IT environments\n\nIf you’re passionate about delivering exceptional service and enjoy working in a hands-on technical role, we’d love to hear from you.\n\nPlease note: all shortlisted candidates will be required to undergo a National Police Check as part of the recruitment process.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=58fb9babf007d9bf','scraped','1 day ago'),(2574,NULL,'job','Staff or Senior Technical Application Engineer – Windows 11 PC Ecosystem (Australia)','','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company:\nQualcomm International, Inc. Australia Branch Office\n\nJob Area:\nEngineering Group, Engineering Group > Software Applications Engineering\n\nGeneral Summary:\n\nGeneral Summary:\n\nQualcomm is enabling a world where everyone and everything can be intelligently connected. You interact with products and technologies made possible by Qualcomm every day, including 5G-enabled smartphones that double as pro-level cameras and gaming devices, smarter vehicles and cities, and the technology behind the smart, connected factories that manufactured your latest purchase. Qualcomm 5G and AI innovations are the power behind the connected intelligent edge. You will find our technologies behind and inside the innovations that deliver significant value across multiple industries and to billions of people every day.\n\nWindows Copilot+ PCs powered by Snapdragon are revolutionizing the PC industry by leading the technology transformation for AI, graphics, multimedia, connectivity, power, and performance. The Field Application Engineer – Windows Copilot+ PC Ecosystem, will have a pre-sales focus and will drive technical adoption of the Windows on Snapdragon Compute platform across the Commercial space.\n\nIn this position you will be responsible for helping enterprise customers with Windows on Snapdragon (WoS) compute product commercialization and support enterprise needs for a timely, faster, and smooth product evaluation. You will have the opportunity to show your strong customer support skills by resolving enterprise issues on the WoS platform and the Windows application ecosystem.\n\nJob Responsibilities:\n\nAssisting with the Execution of Qualcomm’s Worldwide Compute Go-To-Market strategy\nSupport enterprise customers trouble shooting and helping with detailed issue triage/analysis/resolution on BIOS/Driver.\nSupport debugging enterprise application issues and collaborate with platform and technology teams. This includes reproducing the issues and helping with detailed issue triage/analysis/resolution.\nAnalyze and root cause the application issue on customer software/hardware systems.\nSupport Snapdragon eco system issue analysis and engagement .\n\nSkills, Knowledge, & Expertise:\n\nApplication development, debugging, testing with C/C++ & familiarity with embedded system software.\nExperience with IT working and debugging issues in Window 11 environment and tools preferred.\nDriver debugging techniques, problem solving, and documentation skills.\nDebugging with tools such as WinDbg, MSFT Trace tool.\nFamiliarity with Windows OS such as Windows drivers development or Windows debugging, or familiarity with Windows command lines tools such as PowerShell.\nStrong knowledge of C/C++ programming. Experience on window application developer a plus.\n\nMinimum Qualifications:\n\n• Bachelor\'s degree in Engineering, Information Systems, Computer Science, or related field and 4+ years of Software Applications Engineering, Software Development experience, or related work experience.\n\nOR\n\nMaster\'s degree in Engineering, Information Systems, Computer Science, or related field and 3+ years of Software Applications Engineering, Software Development experience, or related work experience.\n\nOR\n\nPhD in Engineering, Information Systems, Computer Science, or related field and 2+ years of Software Applications Engineering, Software Development experience, or related work experience.\n\n• 2+ years of experience with window 11/10 troubleshooting with i ndependent problem solving , etc .\n\nMinimum Qualifications:\n\nBachelor’s or Master’s degree in engineering, Information Systems, Computer Science, or related field\n5 to 8 years of working experience including application engineering, Field application engineering on window 10/11 OS .\nAble to duplicate issue and analysis on customer side to identify solution by remotely support from internal team.\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\nTechnical sales management expertise, the ability to manage change and the desire to operate effectively across organizations and customers\nExperience building complex solutions and driving new device adoption in Commercial accounts\nExperience in support of launching new technologies/products\nAbility to communicate, educate and evangelize both internally & externally\nExcellent communication and people skills\nCreative problem solving with strong analytical skills\n\nMinimum Qualifications:\n\n• Bachelor\'s degree in Engineering, Information Systems, Computer Science, or related field and 4+ years of Software Applications Engineering, Software Development experience, or related work experience.\nOR\nMaster\'s degree in Engineering, Information Systems, Computer Science, or related field and 3+ years of Software Applications Engineering, Software Development experience, or related work experience.\nOR\nPhD in Engineering, Information Systems, Computer Science, or related field and 2+ years of Software Applications Engineering, Software Development experience, or related work experience.\n\n• 2+ years of experience with Programming Language such as C, C++, Java, Python, etc.\n• 1+ year of experience with debugging techniques.\n\nApplicants : Qualcomm is an equal opportunity employer. If you are an individual with a disability and need an accommodation during the application/hiring process, rest assured that Qualcomm is committed to providing an accessible process. You may e-mail disability-accomodations@qualcomm.com or call Qualcomm\'s toll-free number found here . Upon request, Qualcomm will provide reasonable accommodations to support individuals with disabilities to be able participate in the hiring process. Qualcomm is also committed to making our workplace accessible for individuals with disabilities. (Keep in mind that this email address is used to provide reasonable accommodations for individuals with disabilities. We will not respond here to requests for updates on applications or resume inquiries).\n\nQualcomm expects its employees to abide by all applicable policies and procedures, including but not limited to security and other requirements regarding protection of Company confidential information and other confidential and/or proprietary information, to the extent those requirements are permissible under applicable law.\n\nTo all Staffing and Recruiting Agencies : Our Careers Site is only for individuals seeking a job at Qualcomm. Staffing and recruiting agencies and individuals being represented by an agency are not authorized to use this site or to submit profiles, applications or resumes, and any such submissions will be considered unsolicited. Qualcomm does not accept unsolicited resumes or applications from agencies. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias, Qualcomm employees or any other company location. Qualcomm is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes/applications.\n\nIf you would like more information about this role, please contact Qualcomm Careers .','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Qualcomm','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c171b0ad6a169d55','scraped','1 day ago'),(2575,NULL,'job','Senior Associate - Energy & Decarbonisation','Permanent','Perth WA 6000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'AI Job Summary\nAt least five years’ post-admission experience.\nExperience advising on energy transition matters incl. decarbonisation, renewables (solar/BESS), and emerging tech (hyd/\nWell-developed drafting and negotiation skills; strong client outcomes on project/commercial documents.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nPermanent • Full-time • LP – Senior Associate\nDescription\n\nHopgoodGanim is a leading independent Australian law firm, known for delivering exceptional outcomes for our clients while staying deeply connected to the communities in which we work. We are proud to be a firm where people genuinely enjoy coming to work. Our lawyers are trusted with challenging, meaningful matters and supported to grow through a culture that is inclusive, collaborative and uncompromising on our values.\n\nAbout The Role\n\nJoin our Perth-based Resources & Energy team, advising on complex energy transition matters including decarbonisation initiatives, renewable energy developments and emerging technologies. You will work closely with a highly regarded Partner and a supportive, collaborative team delivering practical, commercial advice to leading Australian and international clients.\n\nIn this role, you will draft and negotiate key project and commercial documents, manage matters day-to-day with appropriate supervision, and support the team across a diverse pipeline of work including:\n\nDecarbonisation and emissions reduction projects for major Australian companies\nRenewable energy projects including grid-connected solar and battery energy storage systems (BESS), as well as remote hybrid systems for mining operations\nNew technology trials and demonstration projects, including international collaborations across battery minerals and hydrogen\nDevelopment projects involving Traditional Owner groups, including renewable energy for data centres and export-focused green hydrogen and ammonia initiatives\nRegulatory advice and assessment of evolving industry frameworks as the energy transition progresses\nSupport on broader team matters across mining and oil and gas, including due diligence, contracting and project support\n\nAbout You\n\nYou are an experienced and motivated Senior Associate who enjoys working on complex matters, building strong client relationships and contributing to a supportive, collaborative team environment. You will also bring:\n\nAt least five years’ post-admission experience\nWell-developed drafting and negotiation skills, with a demonstrated ability to deliver strong client outcomes\nExperience in a projects or commercial team at an Australian or international law firm (energy transition or broader energy exposure is advantageous)\nSome experience providing regulatory advice and/or working within regulated markets\nA collaborative, team-oriented mindset, with a commitment to mentoring and supporting junior lawyers\nMotivation to expand your knowledge and expertise across new industries and technologies\nAbility to build trusted client relationships through clear communication, responsiveness and professional insight\n\nAt HopgoodGanim, you’re not just a small piece of a big machine; you’re a valued, integral member of the team. We are committed to delivering exceptional service and while being recognised for our deeply connected and collaborative culture, shared by a team of people who have a genuine love for the work we do. As a law firm of just over 300 people nationally, HopgoodGanim offers flexible and hybrid working arrangements and a number of benefits including:\n\nDedicated learning & development programs for all employees\nRealistic billable targets for legal practitioners\nPractitioner performance and new client incentives\nA dedicated in-house business development team to build your external profile\nPathways to Partnership program for legal practitioners\nClear annual review and promotion cycle\nOnsite gym and end-of-trip facilities\nAccess to paid parental leave (up to 20 weeks for eligible employees)\nPaid fertility leave\nPaid birthday leave\nFun mid-year and end-of-year team celebrations including our HG Way Awards night\nEmployee assistance program and wellbeing initiatives','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ab0f428d62eb0966','scraped','1 day ago'),(2576,NULL,'job','Referrer Engagement Manager | Business Development | Healthcare','Permanent','Brisbane QLD 4000',NULL,'',130000.00,'$120,000 - $140,000 a year','AI Job Summary\n3 to 5 years in referrer engagement, business development, account management, or similar field-based role.\nBuild/manage relationships across GP practices, urgent care centres, ambulance services, employers, Defence and DVA.\nValid driver’s licence and flexibility to travel nationally more than 50% of the time.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nPermanent • Full-time • Mid-level Senior\nPay Rate\n120000 AUD – 140000 AUD (Annum)\nDescription\n\nPrivate Emergency Health Australia (PEHA), Brisbane, Queensland (with national travel >50%) Full-time, Permanent\n\nAbout PEHA\n\nPrivate Emergency Health Australia (PEHA) is Australia’s leading provider of emergency medicine services across the private hospital sector. We partner with private hospitals to deliver high-quality, patient-centred emergency care across a growing national network of emergency departments and emergency care centres.\n\nWe are a values-driven organisation built on care, confidence, partnership, and opportunity. As we continue to grow, we are investing in the people and relationships that will drive sustainable long-term performance across our existing sites.\n\nThe Opportunity\n\nThis is a rare opportunity to join PEHA’s leadership team in a newly created, highly autonomous role focused on growing patient referrals across our existing national ED network.\n\nAs Referrer Engagement Manager, you will be the face of PEHA in the field. This is an execution-focused business development role where your success is measured by real, tangible growth with more patients being seen, more referral pathways activated, and stronger relationships built with the right people in the right communities.\n\nYou will report directly to the General Manager and work closely with our site-based Practice Managers and Site Directors across the country.\n\nWhat You Will Be Doing\n\nYour focus will be on growing referrals at existing PEHA sites through hands-on, relationship-based business development. Specifically, you will:\n\nSpend a minimum of 50% of your time in the field, building and managing relationships across GP practices, urgent care centres, ambulance services, employers, Defence and DVA networks, and large community and tourism organisations\nDevelop and formalise Workplace Injury Management SLAs with employers, maintain quarterly contact cadence, and track injury management presentation growth\nEstablish and manage GP and specialist referral relationships across all sites, with a focus on measurable referral volume growth\nMap and profile local urgent care centres by site to identify diversion and referral opportunities, and develop strategies to reduce avoidable presentation loss\nActivate and track Defence and DVA presentation pathways\nPlan and execute GP education dinners, employer events, and injury management forums\nCoach and develop Practice Managers to independently own stakeholder relationships at the site level\nMaintain a structured stakeholder database, engagement logs, and monthly KPI reporting\nDevelop and maintain relationships with hospital stakeholders\nMonitor local competitive dynamics and incorporate market intelligence into site-specific action plans\n\nWhat We Are Looking For\n\nYou are a natural relationship builder who is equally comfortable pitching to a GP principal partner, negotiating a WorkCover SLA with an employer, and coaching a Practice Manager through their first stakeholder conversation. You are organised, accountable, and comfortable working autonomously across a national portfolio.\n\nYou will bring:\n\n3 to 5 years of experience in referrer engagement, business development, account management, or a similar field-based role\nExperience in healthcare is preferred; pharmaceutical or injury management sales experience would be well-regarded\nA genuine understanding of healthcare financing streams and the ability to navigate clinical environments with credibility\nDemonstrated ability to manage and report against KPIs and performance metrics\nExperience coaching, mentoring, or developing others\nA bachelor’s degree in business, management, marketing, health services, or a related field\nA valid driver’s licence and the flexibility to travel nationally for more than 50% of your time\n\nWhy Join PEHA?\n\nReport to the General Manager and work with PEHA’s operations team in a role that genuinely shapes the business\nJoin a high-growth,purpose-driven private healthcare organisation with a national footprint\nBe given real autonomy and accountability to drive measurable outcomes\nPlay a central role in one of private emergency medicine’s most exciting growth phases\n\nHow to Apply\n\nIf you have a track record in healthcare business development or referrer engagement and you are ready to take on a nationally significant role with real impact, we would love to hear from you.\n\nApply now with your resume and a brief cover letter outlining your relevant experience.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e8597630785b77a4','scraped','1 day ago'),(2577,NULL,'job','ANZ AI Leader – AWS Global Sales (AGS)','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nThe ANZ AI Leader creates and sets the vision to drive AI/ML and Agentic AI adoption across the ANZ region. Leading a team of Specialists, you will partner with and influence local sales teams to accelerate customer adoption of AWS AI/ML services, Agentic AI solutions, and Accelerated Compute capabilities. This is a critical role reporting directly to the Area VP with ownership of developing and executing the strategic plan for ANZ-wide AI/ML specialist resource investments and go-to-market execution, accelerating customer outcomes from current and future AI/ML services.\n\nThis team encompasses two core areas: 1) AI/ML Sales Team providing Level 200-300 support for complex, high-value solution selling to qualified AI/ML use cases, and 2) AI/ML Specialist SA’s providing Level 300-400 support for complex AI/ML architectures, integrations and agentic workflows in Tech Validation, Committed and Launched stages of the sales cycle. The team drives both customer organizations and AWS Sales teams to adopt Agentic AI to transform operations, addressing technical and non-technical topics with C-suite and boards including AI ethics, governance, security, risk, change management, and Agentic Ops.\n\nAWS is looking for an accomplished leader with experience across product, business, and technology who has worked with large Enterprises and high-growth organizations to accelerate their AI/ML and cloud-native journey. In this capacity, the leader will have revenue responsibility while leading a cross-functional team of Sales, and Solution Architects,. The Specialist team acts as an important feedback ingestion point from customers that directly feeds into the roadmap for AWS AI/ML product and services teams.\n\nYou will lead AI/ML and Agentic AI discussions with C-suite executives and boards of directors and play a critical role in taking the voice of the customer and sharing it back to the Worldwide Specialist Organization (WWSO) team to ensure customer feedback effectively influences our technology roadmaps and Go-To-Market strategy. This role will contribute to the overall performance of the business globally measured by revenue growth, net new AI/ML customers, and product and service influence.\n\nYou will have experience as a leader of leaders, with significant multi-vertical ANZ exposure. You will have overachieved throughout your career and built strong, deep relationships with F1000 and/or G2000 organizations.\n\nKey job responsibilities\n• Influence at the CxO/VP and Board level, as well as developers and technical architects, to develop AI/ML pipeline, secure lighthouse customers, drive top-line revenue, and explore strategic partnerships in AI/ML and Agentic AI;\n\n• Build, manage, and close a pipeline which exceeds the Area AI/ML revenue goal while driving Agentic AI transformation across customer organizations;\n\n• Lead and develop the AI/ML Sales and SA Team, s to deliver exceptional customer outcomes;\n\n• Develop and deploy AI/ML sales motions and programs that leverage AWS Field Sales teams, as well as technology and consulting partner channels. Go-to-market elements may include consultative workshops on Agentic AI, sales/partner/customer enablement, solution blueprints, customer proposal and offer development, internal and external collateral, Proofs of Concept (POC), incentives, target customers, and success measures;\n\n• Define, develop, and execute against comprehensive account/territory plans supporting multiple account teams to drive achievement of AI/ML revenue and win goals;\n\n• Create & articulate compelling value propositions for AI/ML services (AgentCore, Kiro, Quick Suite, Nova models) and address competitive positioning a;\n\n• Drive customer adoption of Agentic AI through well-developed sales engagements and successful GTM Strategy, addressing AI ethics, governance, security, risk, and transformational change management;\n\n• Interface with WWSO GTM and global AI/ML leadership, manage technical escalations for GPU capacity and AIML service/feature availability;\n\n• Partner with cross-functional teams across Solution Architecture, Business Development, Marketing, Partners, and Training to execute customer acquisition programs and strategies focused on AI/ML adoption;\n\n• Define and drive operational processes and excellence with sales teams, ensuring AI/ML thought leadership and specialist request resolution;\n\n• Achieve personal AI/ML sales quota while leading the team to exceed Area AI/ML goals.\n\nAbout the team\nDiverse Experiences\nAWS values diverse experiences. Even if you do not meet all of the qualifications and skills listed in the job description, we encourage candidates to apply. If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying.\n\nWhy AWS?\nAmazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.\n\nInclusive Team Culture\nHere at AWS, it’s in our nature to learn and be curious. Our employee-led affinity groups foster a culture of inclusion that empower us to be proud of our differences. Ongoing events and learning experiences, including our Conversations on Race and Ethnicity (CORE) and AmazeCon (gender diversity) conferences, inspire us to never stop embracing our uniqueness.\n\nMentorship & Career Growth\nWe’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional.\n\nWork/Life Balance\nWe value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve in the cloud.\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Demonstrated expertise in technical sales of AI/ML, Agentic AI, and cloud computing products and services. 15+ years of enterprise technology sales with 10+ years leading sales teams;\n- Proven track record of taking ownership and driving results. Ability to effectively lead a scaled sales organization focused on emerging technologies, and work with a variety of organizations, management levels, cultures, and personalities;\n- Exceptional interpersonal and communication (both written and verbal) skills, particularly in explaining complex AI/ML concepts to non-technical audiences;\n- Experience communicating with both technical and non-technical stakeholders across multiple teams, as well as internal and external executive stakeholders including boards of directors;\n- Established track record of building rapport with customer executives (e.g. CEO, COO, CIO, CTO, CMO, Chief AI Officer), building close relationships, and closing large revenue accounts in AI/ML or emerging technology domains;\n- Experience and success in negotiating complex deals with customers and partners. You\'ve not only carried quotas, you\'ve consistently exceeded them by doing the right thing for your customers;\n- Hiring, developing and motivating a sales organization to consistently exceed expectations against defined goals and objectives, particularly in fast-moving technology domains;\n- BA/BS degree required, MBA or advanced technical degree preferred.\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Relevant AI/ML sales experience. Breadth and depth in multiple enterprise functional areas in multiple industries a plus;\n- Experience in a heavily matrixed sales environment, including developing, implementing, managing, and executing cross-functional solutions-led go-to-market growth initiatives and sales motion for AI/ML services;\n- Deep understanding of AI/ML technologies, Agentic AI, Large Language Models, and Accelerated Compute (GPU) infrastructure; technical background in engineering, computer science, data science, or MIS a plus;\n- Understanding of AI ethics, governance, security frameworks, and risk management in enterprise AI deployments;\n- Recognized industry expertise in AI/ML with proven public speaking and media prowess;\n- Professional traits that are not unique to this position, but necessary for Amazon leaders:\n- Exhibits excellent judgment;\n- Inclusive leader who inspires others to share unique points of view to better inform decisions;\n- Hires and develops great people;\n- Has relentlessly high standards;\n- Thinks strategically, but stays on top of tactical execution;\n- Expects and requires innovation of her/his team;\n- Thinks big and has convictions;\n- Results-oriented;\n- Has the innate ability to inspire passion in others.\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Web Services Australia Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c58e3efea28e60ba','scraped','Just posted'),(2578,NULL,'job','Partner Account Manager, Worldwide Public Sector - ANZ','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'DESCRIPTION\n\nAWS Partners are an integral part of the success that drives adoption of AWS, enabling customers of all sizes to innovate. Partners empower our customers by providing tailored service and unmatched technology guidance.\n\nPartners specialising in Public Sector have also chosen to invest in delivering services for customers that ensure the ongoing delivery of core citizen facing services in a secure, reliable and scalable way.\n\nWe work together to dive deep to understand our customer\'s unique challenges, then craft innovative solutions that accelerate their success. Join us and help us support the SI partners that share our customer obsessed mindset.\n\nDo you want to own the AWS relationship with some of the world\'s and our region\'s largest and most trusted Solutions Integration Partners? Want to be part of a cross-functional team focused on increasing technology adoption of cloud computing in public sector by engaging directly with C-level executives and influencers at all levels?\n\nAs part of a single-threaded team focusing on partner management, you will be working with enterprise Public Sector SI partners. You will engage with our Solution Architects, Sales, and Marketing organizations to drive opportunities to closure at a large scale. Your commitments will include driving platform adoption, identifying use cases with our partners to transform their business outcomes, and ensuring success at scale.\n\nYour responsibilities will include working within a Public Sector partner team, partnering to co-sell partner solutions with account and channel teams, as well as working with partners to define key market segments to target, identifying ways to deliver increased value via use of cloud. You will drive the necessary business and technical relationships with partners to establish new business in those markets. You’ll also work closely with other specialist teams to help partners evolve their products/services and address concerns.\n\nThe ideal candidate will possess both a business background that enables them to drive an engagement and interact at the CxO/VP level, as well as a technical background that enables them to easily interact with services partners. Thinking strategically and analytically about business, product, and technical challenges, you’ll have the ability to build and convey compelling value propositions, and work organisationally to build consensus. The ideal candidate will also have experience working in a partner channel, be it in a partner / alliance management role or for a vendor as a partner manager and ideally with public sector partners or customers.\n\nKey job responsibilities\n• Support partners to leverage AWS to successfully deliver and grow their solutions across their market segments using all available program and technical assistance ay your disposal.\n• Contribute to the strategic partner plan to execute for target markets in line with both AWS and partner strategic direction\n• Execute the strategic business development plan while working with key internal stakeholders (e.g. account teams, partner teams, specialist teams, Solution Architects and support).\n• Relevant technical experience/knowledge is helpful, such as: AI (Generative & Agentic), data and analytics, core distributed computing concepts, fundamentals of cloud computing and migration, big data concepts, storage systems.\n\nBASIC QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- 7+ years of direct sales or business development in software, cloud or SaaS markets selling to C-level executives experience\n- 8+ years of business development, partner development, sales or alliances management experience\n- Experience proactively growing customer relationships within an account while expanding their understanding of the customer\'s business\n- Experience working with global teams and diverse partners\n- Experience engaging with customer relationships at the CXO level\n- Ability to operate with a high degree of ambiguity and in a matrix organization\n- Proven track record of successful engagements with Public Sector customers in Australia & New Zealand\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS\n\n- Experience influencing innovation through a partner ecosystem with either solutions or programs that have demonstrated success at enterprise customers\n\nAcknowledgement of country:\nIn the spirit of reconciliation Amazon acknowledges the Traditional Custodians of country throughout Australia and their connections to land, sea and community. We pay our respect to their elders past and present and extend that respect to all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples today.\n\nIDE statement:\nAmazon is an equal opportunity employer and does not discriminate on the basis of protected veteran status, disability, or other legally protected status.\n\nOur inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amazon Web Services Australia Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f382ff2bc1c27e13','scraped','Just posted'),(2579,NULL,'job','Literacy Instructor - Willmot Public School','Part-time','Blacktown NSW 2148',NULL,'',4274.50,'$42.00 - $43.49 an hour','AI Job Summary\nBachelor of Education (Primary), Certificate IV in Education Support, or related qualification.\nExperience working with primary school aged children (Years 2–6) and supporting diverse backgrounds.\nUnderstanding of phonics-based literacy instruction and child-centred learning principles.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nOn-site • Contract • Part-time • Mid-Level\nPay Rate\n42 AUD – 43.49 AUD (Hour)\nDescription\n\nWHO ARE WE?\n\nThe Rev. Bill Crews Foundation (‘BCF’) is one of Sydney’s most trusted frontline charities and has been supporting the community for over 40 years. Our mission is to address homelessness and hardship by providing essential services including food, social welfare, healthcare, education and community programs.\n\nFor more than 20 years BCF has also delivered literacy programs in primary schools across NSW and the Northern Territory. Our program supports children who have fallen behind in reading to rebuild confidence and strengthen their literacy skills.\n\nUsing the ‘All About Reading’program and other structured resources, our Literacy Instructors create engaging, supportive learning environments that help students improve their reading, spelling and phonics skills and return to grade level.\n\nTHE ROLE\n\nWe are currently seeking a Literacy Instructor to deliver BCF’s literacy program at a participating primary school in Willmot.\n\nThis role works with students in Years 2–6 in small groups of 3–6 students, allowing you to tailor teaching approaches to individual learning needs. Each instructor supports approximately 20–30 students per school.\n\nThis is a part time role working Monday to Thursday from 9.00am to 2.00pm within the school environment.\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\nDeliver structured and engaging literacy sessions using evidence-based teaching resources\nPlan lessons and set weekly learning objectives\nSupport students to strengthen reading, spelling and phonics skills\nConduct regular student assessments and track progress\nMaintain accurate records of attendance and student performance\nLiaise with school staff and the NSW Literacy Program Coordinator\nPrepare learning materials and teaching resources\nWrite student progress reports and assist with end of term graduations\nParticipate in training to support high quality program delivery\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BRING\n\nYou are a patient and engaging educator who enjoys working with children and supporting their learning development.\n\nYou will also bring:\n\nBachelor of Education (Primary), Certificate IV in Education Support or related qualification\nExperience working with primary school aged children\nExperience supporting children from diverse backgrounds\nUnderstanding of phonics based literacy instruction and child centred learning\nStrong organisational and communication skills\nConfidence building positive relationships with teachers, students and school staff\nProficiency using Microsoft Office programs such as Word and Excel\nWillingness to travel to school locations if required\nAlignment with the mission and values of BCF\n\nWHY JOIN US?\n\nProfessional Development Opportunities\nEAP (Employee Assistance Program)\nNFP Salary Packaging Benefit ($15,900 Tax Free Benefit)\nHealth and Wellbeing Program (WHEREFIT)\n\nOUR RECRUITMENT PROCESS\n\nIf your resume is shortlisted the next steps may include:\n\nPhone screen\nInterview\nA short trial which allows you to meet the team observe the program and experience the environment before making a decision\n\nThis process helps ensure you feel informed supported and confident about whether BCF is the right fit for you.\n\nREADY TO APPLY?\n\nIf you are passionate about helping children build confidence in their literacy skills we would love to hear from you.\n\nThe Bill Crews Charitable Trust and the Exodus Foundation are separate but closely aligned entities. Together, they deliver services and programs under the Rev. Bill Crews Foundation brand, working in partnership to support those most in need.\n\nAll Bill Crews Foundation employees are required to have completed at least three (3) COVID-19 vaccinations, including booster doses approved by the Therapeutic Goods Administration (TGA). Proof of vaccination will be required prior to commencing employment.\n\nApplicants must have the right to work in Australia. The successful candidate will also be required to complete a Working With Children Check and a National Police Check as part of the employment process.\n\nPlease Note: This position is managed directly by the BCF People and Culture team. While we appreciate the interest of recruitment agencies and external providers, we are not seeking third-party assistance for this role at this time.\n\nCompany Overview\nThe Rev. Bill Crews Foundation provides direct assistance to address the cause and effect of homelessness, poverty and disadvantage. We succeed in achieving this through caring services including food provision, social welfare and education support.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5f43c9affa075e5d','scraped','1 day ago'),(2580,NULL,'job','Community Engagement Coordinator','Full-time','Ashfield NSW 2131',NULL,'',50.50,'$50 - $51 an hour','AI Job Summary\nTertiary qualification in social work, social science, welfare or related field.\nExperience delivering/supporting community-based programs and facilitating group activities.\nAbility to engage guests directly with a respectful, non-judgemental approach.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nOn-site • Contract • Full-time • Mid-Level\nPay Rate\n50 AUD – 51 AUD (Hour)\nDescription\n\nAbout us:\n\nThe Rev. Bill Crews Foundation (‘BCF’) is one of Sydney’s most trusted frontline charities and has been supporting the community for nearly 40 years. Our mission is to address homelessness and hardship by providing essential services including food, social welfare, healthcare, education and community programs.\n\nOur Social Health & Wellbeing (‘SHW’) team is often the first point of contact for people facing complex challenges. Through crisis support, case management and community-based services, we work to reduce isolation and support people to reconnect with community and services.\n\nTHE ROLE\n\nWe are seeking a Community Engagement Coordinator to support the delivery of meaningful, guest-focused programs that promote connection, wellbeing and community participation.\n\nThis is a hands-on and varied role, combining program coordination, team support and direct engagement with guests. You will work closely with the Community Engagement team to deliver activities, support outreach initiatives and contribute to a welcoming and inclusive environment across BCF sites.\n\nThis is a full-time role, working Monday to Friday.\n\nWHAT YOU’LL YOU DO\n\nAs our Community Engagement Coordinator, you will:\n\nSupport day-to-day coordination of community engagement programs and activities\nFacilitate group activities such as Women’s Groups, art sessions and other initiatives\nAssist in planning and delivering events across the organisation\nProvide guidance and support to the Community Engagement team\nEngage directly with guests in a respectful, non-judgemental manner\nIdentify guest needs and refer to appropriate internal services\nSupport outreach initiatives, including food van engagement where required\nCoordinate bookings and maintain a community activity calendar\nMonitor program participation and contribute to reporting and evaluation\nAssist in resolving non-clinical complaints in a timely and appropriate manner\nBuild relationships with internal teams and external community partners\n\nWHAT WE ARE LOOKING FOR\n\nYou are a compassionate and proactive individual who enjoys working with people and creating inclusive, engaging environments for those doing it tough.\n\nYou bring a calm, solutions-focused approach and are confident supporting both guests and team members in a dynamic environment.\n\nYou’ll also bring:\n\nTertiary qualification in social work, social science, welfare or related field\nExperience delivering or supporting community-based programs\nStrong interpersonal and communication skills\nAbility to manage competing priorities and stay organised\nConfidence engaging with people from diverse and vulnerable backgrounds\nStrong problem-solving and conflict resolution capability\nProficiency in Microsoft Office programs\nAlignment with the mission and values of BCF\n\nWHY JOIN US\n\nAt BCF, you’ll be part of a supportive, purpose-driven team working directly with the community.\n\nWe offer:\n\nNot-for-Profit salary packaging benefits (up to $15,900 tax-free)\nAccess to Employee Assistance Program (‘EAP’)\nHealth and Wellbeing Program (‘WHEREFIT’)\nA collaborative team environment with meaningful, community-focused work\n\nOUR RECRUITMENT PROCESS\n\nIf your application is shortlisted, the next steps may include:\n\nA phone screen\nAn interview\nA practical component where you meet the team and observe or engage in aspects of the role\n\nWe recognise that BCF is a unique environment. These steps are designed to give you a clear understanding of the role, the team and the work we do, while ensuring you feel supported and informed throughout the process.\n\nReady to apply?\n\nIf you’re passionate about community health and supporting people impacted by substance use, we’d love to hear from you! Click “Apply Now” to submit your application. When applying, please specify your availability in a cover letter.\n\nBill Crews Charitable Trust and the Exodus Foundation are separate but closely cooperating entities. Together, they deliver services and programs under the Rev. Bill Crews Foundation brand name, working to support those in need.\n\nAll Bill Crews Foundation employees are required to have completed at least three (3) COVID-19 vaccinations, including booster doses approved by the Australian Therapeutic Goods Administration (TGA). Proof of COVID-19 vaccination status will be required prior to commencing employment.\n\nApplicants must have the right to work in Australia. The successful candidate will also need to complete a Working With Children Check and a Police Check as part of the employment process.\n\nPlease Note: This position is managed directly by the BCF People and Culture team. While we value the interest of recruitment agencies and external businesses, we are not seeking third-party support for this role at this time.\n\nCompany Overview\nThe Rev. Bill Crews Foundation provides direct assistance to address the cause and effect of homelessness, poverty and disadvantage. We succeed in achieving this through caring services including food provision, social welfare and education support.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f67c77ccfa9e3b0b','scraped','1 day ago'),(2581,NULL,'job','Principal Software Engineer – AI Customer Support Experiences','Full-time','Perth WA',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We\'re embarking on an engineering transformation with the key focus on Agentic AI & Chatbot customer support experiences.\n\nYou have knowledge that spans across development, AI and strategic leadership across a multi crew domain.\n\nTogether we will build tomorrow’s bank today, using world-leading engineering, technology, and innovation.\n\nDo work that matters:\n\nBankwest has a rich heritage. We’re proud to be part of the fabric of Western Australia with a strong culture built on local support. With the support of a strong partner in CBA, we share a belief in the value of our brand, our potential for growth and a big aspirational Vision. As a Principal Software Engineer in the Bankwest Customer Support Experience Crew, you’ll lead the build of next-generation AI-powered support that is always on, deeply personalised, and designed for critical customer moments.\n\nThis is a hands-on role driving the evolution from NLU-based chatbots to agentic AI systems, engineering intelligent agents that can reason, act, and resolve in real time. You’ll work across a modern .NET ecosystem, leveraging Microsoft Dynamics 365, Omnichannel, and Copilot Studio, and operating within a multi-cloud architecture across Azure and AWS to deliver scalable, resilient, 24/7 support solutions that redefine how customers interact with the bank.\n\nOperating across a multi-crew model, you’ll act as the SME for the Group’s AI chatbot services, building strong strategic, technical, and functional relationships while aligning architecture and delivery at scale. This role combines deep engineering expertise with AI-native system design and strategic leadership, setting the direction for agentic AI adoption and shaping a future where customer support is faster, smarter, and purpose-built through cutting-edge technology.\n\nSee yourself in our team:\n\nThe Bankwest Customer Support Experience Crew sits at the intersection of modern software engineering, AI, and customer-centric design redefining how customers interact with the bank when it matters most. Their mission is to deliver fast, accurate, and seamless support through intelligent digital experiences, especially in urgent or high-stress moments where trust is critical.\n\nBuilt on a modern .NET ecosystem and deeply integrated with Microsoft platforms like Dynamics 365, Omnichannel, and Copilot Studio, the crew engineers scalable, resilient solutions across a multi-cloud environment spanning Azure and AWS. This enables tightly orchestrated customer journeys that are both efficient for the bank and intuitive for customers.\n\nToday’s capability is anchored in Natural Language Understanding (NLU) -driven chatbot services that interpret intent and automate support, but the crew is actively evolving toward an agentic Large Language Model (LLM) based architecture. This shift moves from reactive conversations to proactive, context-aware AI agents capable of reasoning, orchestrating workflows, and dynamically resolving customer needs.\n\nIt’s where software engineering meets AI-native system design, requiring strength in distributed systems, cloud engineering, and emerging disciplines like agent design and LLM governance. The result is a strategic, forward-looking capability that is not just improving support, but fundamentally reshaping how the bank delivers intelligent, scalable customer experiences.\n\nWe’re interested in hearing from people who:\n\nPlay a critical role in evolving a modern customer support platform built on Microsoft Copilot Studio, Power Platform, and Dynamics 365 Omnichannel, integrated with AWS and underpinned by .NET engineering, leading the transformation of chatbot and agent-assist capabilities where software engineering meets AI agentic services.\n\nDesign, build, and scale AI-powered, agentic customer support solutions, enabling intelligent self-service, smart routing, and seamless handoff to human agents.\n\nLead end-to-end architecture and delivery of complex AI systems across NLU, LLMs, and agentic frameworks, owning the capability from strategy through to production and operations.\n\nOperate as a hands-on Technical SME across AI platforms, Copilot Studio, and .NET services, driving design, contributing to code, and setting technical direction with deep expertise.\n\nDrive enterprise AI strategy, establishing scalable patterns, governance, and foundational frameworks to support adoption of agentic AI services.\n\nProvide strong cross-crew technical leadership, mentoring engineers, fostering autonomy and psychological safety, and aligning teams to clear engineering standards and vision.\n\nPartner with senior stakeholders across multiple crews to translate complex business challenges into secure, scalable, and high-impact AI-driven solutions, continuously evolving chatbot platforms toward advanced agentic LLM architectures.\n\nTech skills:\n\nWe don\'t expect you to know everything, but experience in several of the following will set you up for success:\n\nBack End / Engineering: Python (AI/ML & backend services), .NET (C#, ASP.NET Core), API design (REST, OAuth, webhooks).\n\nAI / GenAI / Agentic: LLMs (Azure OpenAI, OpenAI, Claude), Agentic frameworks (LangChain, LangGraph, LlamaIndex, AutoGen, Semantic Kernel, MCP, Strands), RAG architectures & vector DBs (Pinecone, Weaviate), AI evaluation, monitoring, governance, Responsible AI.\n\nMicrosoft Stack: Copilot Studio (Power Virtual Agents), Power Platform (Power Apps, Power Automate, Dataverse), Dynamics 365 Customer Service / Omnichannel, M365.\n\nCloud & Platform: AWS (preferred), Azure, IaC (CloudFormation, CDK), Containers (Docker, Kubernetes), Serverless.\n\nDevOps: CI/CD (GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, Jenkins), Git version control.\n\nQuality: Testing (unit, integration, E2E – Playwright).\n\nObservability & Operations: Observability tooling, monitoring, alerting, production support.\n\nIf you\'re already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest, x15ventures), you\'ll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We’re keen to support you with the next step in your career.\n\nWe\'re aware of some accessibility issues on this site, particularly for screen reader users. We want to make finding your dream job as easy as possible, so if you require additional support please contact HR Direct on 1800 989 696.\n\nAdvertising End Date: 31/05/2026','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Bankwest','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=4cdc9de45e6d4fa6','scraped','1 day ago'),(2582,NULL,'job','Ai Trainer/Data Annotator - Remote','Contract','Remote',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job Title: AI Evaluation Specialist\n\nJob Type: Contractor\n\nLocation: Remote\n\nJob Summary:\n\nAs a AI Evaluation Specialist, you\'ll apply your expertise to help train next-generation AI systems. Your work will shape how models learn, reason, and perform through high-quality, real-world input. No prior experience in AI is required , your domain knowledge is what matters.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nReview and critically assess AI-generated outputs for quality, clarity, usability, and overall user experience.\nIdentify inconsistencies, weaknesses, and improvement opportunities across diverse content types and visual experiences.\nApply structured evaluation guidelines and provide insightful, nuanced feedback to inform model improvements.\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to define and refine quality standards, scoring criteria, and review processes.\nMaintain high accuracy and consistency across evaluations, ensuring reliable and actionable results.\nContribute to the continuous enhancement of evaluation workflows and best practices.\nSupport the development of training data that enhances AI system performance and reliability.\n\nRequired Skills and Qualifications:\n\nExceptional reading comprehension and acute attention to detail.\nStrong observational skills with excellent aesthetic or editorial judgment.\nAbility to think critically and deliver consistent, high-quality evaluations in ambiguous scenarios.\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills.\nComfort working across various content types and evaluation guidelines.\nStrong sense of ownership, reliability, and commitment to delivering high-quality work for the customer\'s team.\nOpen-minded approach to learning and quickly adapting to new workflows.\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\nBackground in design, UX/UI, creative direction, editing, or content strategy.\nExperience reviewing creative, visual, or AI-generated content.\nFamiliarity with annotation, QA, moderation, or evaluation workflows, as well as working with AI tools or LLMs.\n\nWe’re seeking highly perceptive and detail-oriented trainers passionate about shaping the future of AI. Bring your refined judgment, critical thinking skills, and commitment to excellence to our customer\'s team and make a meaningful impact on emerging AI technologies.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'YO IT CONSULTING','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=21fc360559de4581','scraped','1 day ago'),(2583,NULL,'job','Sales Manager/ Business Development Lead (All Rounder)','Part-time','Vermont VIC 3133',NULL,'',120000.00,'From $120,000 a year','*About Us*\n\nWe are a *growing group of complementary businesses* operating across:\n\n* Beyond Zero Technologies\n* Boutique AV\n* Plugin Spaces\n\nOur focus spans AI, smart buildings, EV infrastructure, digital platforms, and high-end AV solutions. We design and deliver future-focused environments that combine technology, sustainability, and commercial outcomes.\n\nFollowing a business relaunch, we are seeking a *high-performing Sales Manager / Commercial Lead* to take ownership of growth across multiple business lines.\n\n*The Opportunity*\n\nThis is a hands-on, end-to-end sales role for someone who can build, sell, and scale.\n\nYou will operate as a true commercial all-rounder, responsible for:\n\n* Generating opportunities (including via AI tools and automation)\n* Converting leads into revenue\n* Building scalable outbound systems\n* Establishing offshore sales capability\n\nYou will work directly with leadership to drive revenue growth and shape the commercial strategy of the group.\n\n*Key Responsibilities*\n\n*End-to-End Sales & Revenue Ownership*\n\n* Own the full sales lifecycle: lead generation → qualification → demo → close\n* Conduct calls, presentations, and tailored demonstrations\n* Build and maintain a strong, active sales pipeline\n\n*AI-Driven Lead Generation*\n\n* Leverage AI tools and agents to identify and nurture leads\n* Build automated outbound workflows and optimise conversion rates\n* Continuously improve lead quality and acquisition efficiency\n\n*Multi-Business Sales*\n\n* Sell across multiple offerings (AI solutions, AV systems, digital platforms, workspace solutions)\n* Adapt messaging and value propositions quickly across industries\n* Identify cross-sell and upsell opportunities\n\n*Offshore Call Centre Setup*\n\n* Establish and scale an AI and/or overseas call centre function\n* Develop scripts, KPIs, and performance frameworks\n* Recruit, train, and manage AI and/or offshore team members\n\n*Client Engagement & Deal Execution*\n\n* Build strong client relationships and act as a trusted advisor\n* Prepare proposals, pricing, and commercial agreements\n* Close deals and ensure seamless onboarding\n\n*Strategic Growth*\n\n* Identify new markets, partnerships, and revenue opportunities\n* Contribute to business strategy and scaling initiatives\n* Track and report on pipeline, conversions, and revenue performance\n\n*About You*\n\nYou are commercially driven, adaptable, and execution-focused.\n\n*Essential:*\n\n* Proven experience in sales, business development, or commercial leadership\n* Strong ability to generate and close new business\n* Comfortable working across multiple industries and products\n* Excellent communication, negotiation, and presentation skills\n* Experience using CRM systems and sales tools\n* Ability to operate in a fast-moving, entrepreneurial environment\n\n*Highly Regarded:*\n\n* Experience with AI tools, automation, or digital platforms\n* Experience setting up or managing offshore teams / call centres\n* Background in technology, AV, telecom, or digital services\n* Experience building sales systems from scratch\n\n*What Success Looks Like*\n\n* Strong and consistent pipeline generation\n* High conversion rates from lead → deal\n* Scalable outbound and offshore sales systems\n* Measurable revenue growth across all business units\n\n*Why Join Us*\n\n* Work across cutting-edge AI, tech, and commercial solutions\n* High level of autonomy and ownership\n* Direct access to leadership and strategic decision-making\n* Opportunity to build and scale multiple businesses\n* Competitive base salary + uncapped commission upside\n\n*Apply Now*\n\nIf you’re a hands-on sales leader who can generate opportunities, close deals, and build scalable systems, we want to hear from you.\n\nJob Types: Full-time, Part-time, Casual\n\nPay: From $120,000.00 per year\n\nBenefits:\n* Gym membership\n* Profit sharing\n\nWork Location: In person','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'EFZero Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=bce5908b0460b153','scraped','1 day ago'),(2584,NULL,'job','Customer Success Manager (EOI)','','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'At monday.com, we aren’t just building a tool; we are building the AI work platform that runs modern businesses. With $1.3B+ in annual revenue and over 250,000 customers globally, we empower brands like Canva, Flight Centre, and Uber to move at the speed of light.\n\nAs we scale across APJ, our Melbourne hub is becoming the strategic engine for our Enterprise and Mid-Market success. We aren’t looking for a relationship expert; we are looking for Product Solutions Experts who get into the weeds of a customer’s business to build the high-impact solutions that redefine how they work.\n\nExpression of Interest Only. Send us your CV to be considered for future opportunities. Note: We will only contact shortlisted candidates.\n\nAbout The Role\n\nAt monday.com, we aren’t just building a tool; we are building the AI work platform that runs modern businesses. With $1.3B+ in annual revenue and over 250,000 customers globally, we empower brands like Canva, Flight Centre, and Uber to move at the speed of light.\n\nAs we scale across APJ, our Melbourne hub is becoming the strategic engine for our Enterprise and Mid-Market success. We aren’t looking for a relationship expert; we are looking for Product Solutions Experts who get into the weeds of a customer’s business to build the high-impact solutions that redefine how they work.\n\nExpression of Interest Only. Send us your CV to be considered for future opportunities. Note: We will only contact shortlisted candidates.\n\nDrive Implementation & Evolution: You won’t just set up a board; you’ll partner with Enterprise stakeholders to deploy high-impact use cases that directly solve their biggest business bottlenecks.\nBe a Product Visionary: Master the technical depth of the platform to integrate monday.com into the customer\'s existing tech stack, ensuring we are the \"Single Source of Truth.\"\nDemonstrate ROI: Clearly articulate the \"so what?\" to key stakeholders. You’ll connect platform adoption directly to their bottom line and business goals.\nGuard the Revenue: Proactively manage health scores, identify expansion opportunities, and mitigate churn risk by ensuring customers aren\'t just using the tool—they\'re obsessed with it.\n\nVoice of the Customer: Act as a bridge between Melbourne and our global Product/Engineering teams, ensuring the needs of ANZ’s biggest brands are heard.\n\nArchitect, Don\'t Just Manage: You’ll move beyond \"support\" to help Enterprise leaders solve complex business challenges using our multi-product suite (CRM, Dev, Service, and Work Management).\nAI-First Environment: Be at the forefront of the AI revolution, helping customers bake automation and intelligence into their daily DNA.\nGlobal Impact, Local Ownership: Work within a global SaaS leader while having the autonomy to shape the strategy for your portfolio.\nYour Experience & Skills\nSaaS Experience: You have 5+ years of experience in Customer Success or Consulting, ideally within a high-growth SaaS environment.\nThe Strategic Solver: You don’t just find bugs; you diagnose business process issues and design the solution.\nThe AI Enthusiast: You are genuinely excited by how AI can maximize efficiency and you\'re eager to teach customers how to use it.\nThe Relationship Builder: You’re comfortable navigating the complexities of medium-to-large enterprises and can influence stakeholders from the front line to the boardroom.\n\nThe Self-Starter: You thrive in a fast-paced environment and enjoy the \"creative chaos\" of a scaling company.\n\nWhat’s In It For You?\n\nCompetitive Salary & Perks: We take care of our people with top-tier benefits and a vibrant Melbourne office culture.\nA Seat at the Table: Your feedback directly impacts our product roadmap.\nWorld-Class Enablement: Ongoing coaching and access to the best tools in the industry to ensure you succeed.\nThe \"Monday\" Magic: Join a high-performance team that actually enjoys working together in a flexible, hybrid environment.\n\nReady to build the future of work? We’d love to meet you.\n\n#LI-DNI\n\nApply to this job','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'monday.com','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e17acd04f24a3381','scraped','1 day ago'),(2585,NULL,'job','OSHC Manager','Permanent','Bassendean WA 6054',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'AI Job Summary\nHold a relevant qualification in Early Childhood, OSHC, Social Work, Community Services or similar.\nHave experience leading teams or in a supervisory role within OSHC or a similar child-focused setting.\nCurrent First Aid and CPR, National Police Clearance, and Working with Children Check (or willingness to obtain).\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nOn-site • Permanent • Full-time • Mid-level Senior\nDescription\n\nWe’re looking for a passionate and values-driven leader to manage our Out of School Hours Care (OSHC) program in Lockridge. Our 35-place service is situated in the heart of Lockridge, with Lockridge Primary School a short, ‘walking bus’ away! This newly created role will lead from the front to shape a safe, engaging, and high-quality environment for children.\n\nYou will be the Nominated Supervisor for the service and your responsibilities will include:\n\nCreating a safe, inclusive, and supportive environment for all children.\nOverseeing the day-to-day operations of the OSHC service\nWhile our Compliance Team maintains oversight of legislative changes and sets policies & procedures, you will ensure the effective implementation and integration into everyday practice\nLeading, mentoring, and developing a team of educators\nDesigning and embedding engaging, inclusive programs that reflect children’s interests and needs\nBuilding strong, positive relationships with families, schools, and the local community\nTake ownership of enrolment growth and service visibility\nManage the enrolment process and debt management\nManaging rosters, budgets, resources, and service sustainability\nDriving continuous improvement through reflection, assessment, and quality initiatives.\n\nWhat We’re Looking For\n\nA proactive, solutions-focused approach with a commitment to deliver high quality outcomes for children\n\nDemonstrated ability to understand and apply regulatory frameworks in practice\nExperience leading teams and implementing change\nStrong communication and relationship-building skills\nSound organisational skills with the ability to manage competing priorities.\n\nSelection criteria\n\nA relevant qualification in Early Childhood, OSHC, Social Work, Community Services or similar\nExperience in a leadership or supervisory role is highly regarded\nFamiliarity with the National Quality Framework and My Time, Our Place\nCurrent First Aid, CPR, National Police Clearance and Working with Children Check (or willingness to obtain).\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\nChild Australia is a leading early childhood education organisation operating across Western Australia and the Northern Territory. We proudly partner with children, families, educators, and communities to deliver high-quality early learning and care during the most critical years of a child’s life.\n\nAs a recognised authority in the early childhood sector, we are committed to capacity building through professional development, sector resources, coaching, and innovation. Joining Child Australia means joining a values-driven organisation dedicated to excellence, collaboration, and positive impact.\n\nOur benefits include\n\n• Recognition through our Aspire Reward & Recognition Program\n\n• Employee Assistance Program with access to psychological services, leadership coaching, exercise physiology, nutrition and financial counselling\n\n• Discounted childcare fees across our services\n\n• Ongoing professional development opportunities and chance to attend interstate conferences.\n\nChild Australia is an equal-opportunity employer. We encourage applications from candidates of all backgrounds and experiences.\n\nShortlisting will commence immediately.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f1dd70b4cb825655','scraped','1 day ago'),(2586,NULL,'job','Marketing Assistant','Full-time','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Starting your marketing career and want real responsibility from day one? This is not a “sit and observe” role. It is hands on, fast moving, and gives you exposure across the full marketing mix.\n\nWe are looking for a Marketing Assistant to join our commercial team in Melbourne, Australia.\n\nYou will play a key role in supporting the delivery and maintenance of sales and marketing materials, and bring both internal and customer-facing initiatives to life - all while building practical experience across digital content, events and marketing operations.\n\nThis role is ideal for someone early in their career who wants to learn quickly, contribute meaningfully, and be part of a collaborative and growing business.\n\nWhat you will be doing\n\nYou will be working closely with both marketing and sales, supporting a wide range of activities:\n\nCreate and update marketing and sales materials such as presentations, brochures, banners and digital content\n\nWrite and edit internal and customer-facing communications, product and website content.\n\nKeep our marketing assets, templates, and image libraries organised and up to date\n\nSupport the sales team with proposals, presentations and client communications\n\nMaintain CRM data and enquiry tracking to ensure accuracy and usability\n\nUpdate website content using our CMS\n\nHelp plan and execute events and internal initiatives\n\nCoordinate with external partners and suppliers to deliver marketing materials\n\nEnsure brand consistency across everything we produce\n\nSupport general coordination and admin tasks where needed\n\nWhat you bring\n\nYou do not need years of experience, but you do need curiosity, structure, and drive:\n\nComfortable using Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint\n\nFamiliar with tools like Adobe Creative Suite (Illustrator, InDesign, Photoshop), Canva or Adobe Express\n\nBasic video editing skills are a plus\n\nStrong attention to detail and ability to stay organised across multiple tasks\n\nA proactive mindset and willingness to take initiative\n\nClear communication skills and a professional approach\n\nAbility to work in a fast paced environment and manage deadlines\n\nA positive attitude and openness to learning\n\nWhy this role\n\nThis is a great opportunity to build real marketing experience across multiple disciplines, not just one niche. You will work closely with experienced colleagues, get exposure to commercial decision making, and see how marketing directly supports business growth.\n\nThere are no management responsibilities in this role, but there is strong potential to grow your skills and develop your career as the business evolves.\n\nAbout the role and structure\n\nThis position is part of Safer Storage Systems (SSS) and currently follows established ways of working within that business. As integration with Element Logic continues, the role may evolve over time to align with the wider organisation.\n\nIf you are looking for a role where you can learn fast, contribute from day one, and build a strong foundation in marketing, we would like to hear from you.\n\nFor further questions about the position or process, contact by email to Vice President Talent Acquisition & Employer Branding: beate.hall-hofso@elementlogic.net.\n\nAgency notice: We’re proud to handle all our recruitment in-house at Element Logic. That means we don’t accept candidates or approaches from external recruiters or headhunters. All hiring processes are managed exclusively by our own specialized Talent Acquisition team.\n\nBe yourself, in your element.\n\nAt Element Logic, our people are our greatest resource. We believe individuals should be in their element and we recognize, celebrate, and nurture the strength of diversity. We offer equal opportunities and welcome applicants regardless of age, race, ethnicity, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, language, national origin, mental and physical abilities, religious and political affiliations, stage of life, or family circumstances. We desire a work environment where people flourish with their unique abilities, perspectives, and life experiences.\n\nAbout Element Logic\nElement Logic® is a global technology company specializing in intelligent warehouse automation. Since its founding in 1985, the company has grown to employ over 950 people across 30 countries and has established itself as the first - and leading - AutoStore™ partner worldwide.\n\nRenowned for its commitment to innovation and people-centric approach, Element Logic enhances warehouse performance through a unique combination of cutting-edge technology, AI-powered software, and tailor-made solutions. This enables businesses across industries to improve efficiency, accuracy, and scalability in their logistics operations.\n\nWith a proven track record and deep expertise in intralogistics, Element Logic has become the go-to partner for organizations seeking to gain a competitive edge through automation. The company’s culture is rooted in bravery, passion, and reliability - qualities that continue to drive its mission of optimizing warehouse performance. In 2024, Element Logic reported revenue of EUR 549 million.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'S&P Computersysteme GmbH','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=fa2536907a037c0e','scraped','1 day ago'),(2587,NULL,'job','Senior Full Stack Engineer (Part-time Contract)','Temp to perm','Australia',NULL,'',100.00,'$90 - $110 an hour','Role Overview\n\nPraxio AI builds an AI-powered tax research assistant for Australian accountants and finance teams. We have a live SaaS product, paying customers, and a clear roadmap. We need a hands-on full-stack engineer to help own the application, maintain stability and security, and deliver the next phase of the product.\n\nThe product includes a modern TypeScript web app, relational data layer (Postgres), managed backend services, and Python-based AI services using RAG and vector search. Automated pipelines maintain embeddings and indexes.\n\nYou will work closely with the founder across product, engineering, AI services, and operations.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n1. Product Delivery\n- Ship features end-to-end across UI, APIs, and data\n- Improve performance, quality, and reliability of research workflows\n- Add analytics and feedback loops\n\n2. Web Application Development\n- Build and maintain customer and admin apps (TypeScript/React-style)\n- Manage authentication, permissions, and Postgres schema\n\n3. Backend, AI & RAG\n- Maintain Python APIs and automation jobs\n- Improve retrieval quality, latency, and cost\n- Maintain and extend ingestion and vector refresh pipelines\n\n4. Integrations & Commercial\n- Manage billing, email, and third-party integrations\n\n5. DevOps & Reliability\n- Support deployments and environments\n- Improve logging, monitoring, and operational visibility\n\n6. Security & Data\n- Apply access controls and handle sensitive data responsibly\n\nSkills & Experience\n\n- Strong TypeScript/JavaScript and modern web frameworks\n- Solid Python for APIs and automation\n- Strong SQL/Postgres skills\n- Experience with RAG, LLMs, and vector search\n- Experience with managed auth and real-world permissions\n- Familiarity with DevOps, deployments, and monitoring\n- Ability to work autonomously in a founder-led team\n- Strong communication skills\n- Effective use of AI coding tools\n\nNice to have:\n- Experience in accounting, tax, or finance domains\n- LLM evaluation or prompt design experience\n- Product analytics experience\n\nPay: $90.00 – $110.00 per hour\n\nExpected hours: 10.0 – 15.0 per week\n\nWork Location: Remote','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Praxio AI Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=bf3c1d8b26798f2b','scraped','1 day ago'),(2588,NULL,'job','IT Manager','','Melbourne VIC 3000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'IT Manager\nAbout Us\n\nKCL Law is a medium-sized Melbourne law firm led by a diverse and progressive group of expert lawyers. We provide quality advice and deliver highly strategic outcomes to our clients, achieved by a balance of expert legal acumen, creative thinking and informed commercial insight, in a concise and accessible manner.\n\nThe Role\n\nWe are currently seeking an experienced and professional IT Manager to join our well-established firm. Reporting to the Chief Executive Officer, the IT Manager is responsible for overseeing the firm’s technology environment, with a strong focus on the delivery of key IT projects, system improvements and the ongoing development of the firm’s technology capabilities.\n\nThe IT Manager will demonstrate both initiative and professionalism within the Practice Support Group and provide support to all members of the firm when required.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nLeading and delivering key IT projects and system improvements across the firm;\nIdentifying and driving opportunities to enhance systems, workflows and efficiencies through technology, including the practical application of emerging tools such as AI;\nOverseeing the implementation of system upgrades, enhancements and new technology initiatives;\nLiaising with and managing the Firm’s external IT provider/MSP to ensure effective delivery of services and support;\nManaging and optimising firm-wide IT systems, tools and platforms, including Document Management (iManage Work 10) and Practice Management (LexisNexis Affinity);\nProviding IT training and updates to staff, including supporting the rollout and adoption of new technologies;\nManaging IT-related issues, including computer software and systems in a Microsoft Windows environment;\nOverseeing the maintenance, replacement and repair of hardware and office machinery; and\nAttending various meetings, including preparation of agendas and minutes.\nThe Candidate\n\nThe successful candidate will have experience as an IT Manager within a law firm or professional services environment, with a demonstrated ability to lead and deliver technology projects and system improvements. You will bring strong organisational and interpersonal skills, with the ability to manage competing priorities and take ownership of initiatives from concept through to delivery.\n\nYou will be a confident problem-solver with strong attention to detail, capable of working both independently and collaboratively. Experience managing external service providers and engaging effectively with internal stakeholders is essential, along with the ability to guide and support staff in the use of systems and technology. A proactive and solutions-focused approach is key, with a genuine interest in improving how technology is used across the firm.\n\nTo apply for this role, send your CV together with a covering letter to Joel Chidiac, Human Resources Manager at careers@kcllaw.com.au','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'KCL Law','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=4aac668f6d6f00c5','scraped','2 days ago'),(2589,NULL,'job','Environmental Consultant','','Brisbane QLD',NULL,'',85000.00,'$80,000 - $90,000 a year','Environmental Consulting\n Asia Pacific Region\n BRI0001TD\n\nJoining Arup\n\nArup’s purpose, shared values and collaborative approach has set us apart for over 75 years, guiding how we shape a better world.\n\nArup is widely recognised for delivering high quality, timely environmental impact assessments and securing regulatory approvals across Queensland.\n\nIn this role you will contribute to a range of environmental projects and statutory approvals, spanning major infrastructure and smaller scale projects across sectors such as energy, water, and local and state government. The role sits within a regional team based in Brisbane and may involve some interstate travel.\n\nThe Opportunity\n\nTo provide core environmental input for a broad range of projects, both within the Queensland Environment and Biodiversity team and for multi-disciplinary projects undertaken in the office/region, particularly major transport projects.\n\nTo support on a range of projects undertaken by the Sustainability Team.\n\nTo provide environmental input to bids and tenders.\n\nTo prepare project reports for clients summarising environmental outcomes and strategically advising on best outcomes.\n\nTo participate in field work with the ecology team as required.\n\nIs this role right for you?\n\n3-4 years relevant industry experience in a consulting, private industry or a government environment.\n\nRecognised relevant tertiary qualifications in Environmental Management, Science, Planning, Engineering or similar.\n\nAbility to support environmental project delivery, with additional experience assisting on sustainability related work (e.g. ESG reporting, supply chain program development, and materiality assessments) on major transport projects.\n\nExperience in ArcGIS, specifically creating figures and analysing spatial data.\n\nDemonstrated experience as a Microsoft Copilot, driving adoption through knowledge sharing and coaching, and contributing to innovative, firm wide initiatives that build AI capability through research and strategic networking.\n\nDemonstrated experience contributing to internal committees, communities or employee networks, supporting initiatives that enhance culture, inclusion and Corporate social responsibility (CSR).\n\nWhat we offer you\n\nAt Arup, we care about each member’s success, so we can grow together.\n\nGuided by our values, we provide an attractive total reward package that recognises the contribution of each of our members to our shared success. As well as competitive, fair, and equitable pay, we offer a career in which all of our members can belong, grow and thrive – through benefits that support health and wellbeing, a wide range of learning opportunities and many possibilities to have an impact through the work they do.\n\nWe are owned in trust on behalf of our members, giving us the freedom, with personal responsibility, to set our own direction and choose work that aligns with our purpose and adds to Arup’s legacy. Our members collaborate on ambitious projects to deliver remarkable outcomes for our clients and communities. Profit Share is a key part of our reward, enabling eligible members to share in the results of our collective efforts.\n\nExplore the perks of a career with Arup Australia:\n\nPaid parental leave for the primary carer of 16 weeks or 32 weeks at half pay and as well as generous unpaid leave benefits.\n\nPaid parental leave for the support carer of 4 weeks plus the opportunity to access extra paid and unpaid leave if you later become the primary carer.\n\nBirthday leave\n\nAnnual leave loading\n\nAbility to purchase additional leave of up to 20 days for permanent employees.\n\nInternational mobility opportunities\n\nInsurances (life & income protection)\n\nInterest free solar energy and bicycle loans\n\nNovated car lease\n\nOvasaver including discounts, vouchers, cashback, and exclusive offers on more than 300 retailers.\n\nSalary range for the role: $80k-90k per annum.\n\nDifferent people, shared values\n\nArup is an equal opportunity employer that actively promotes and nurtures a diverse and inclusive workforce. We welcome applications from individuals of all backgrounds, regardless of age (within legal limits), gender identity or expression, marital status, disability, neurotype or mental health, race or ethnicity, faith or belief, sexual orientation, socioeconomic background, and whether you’re pregnant or on family leave. We are an open environment that embraces diverse experiences, perspectives, and ideas – this drives our excellence.\n\nGuided by our values and alignment with the UN Sustainable Development Goals, we create and contribute to equitable spaces and systems, while cultivating a sense of belonging for all. Our internal employee networks support our inclusive culture: from race, ethnicity and cross-cultural working to gender equity and LGBTQ+ and disability inclusion – we aim to create a space for you to express yourself and make a positive difference. Discover more about life at Arup at www.arup.com/careers/your-life-at-arup.\n\nWe are committed to making our recruitment process and workplaces accessible to all candidates. Please let us know if you need any assistance or reasonable adjustments throughout your application or interview process, and/or to perform the essential functions of the role. We will do everything we can to support you.\n\nOur Application Process\n\nPlease apply directly through our applicant tracking system. Shortlisted candidates will be contacted by Talent Acquisition to discuss next steps. Stay safe online – Arup will never ask for your bank details as part of our recruitment process.\n\nArup does not accept unsolicited resumes from recruiters or employment agencies.\n\n#LI-RH1','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Arup','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=76b30ac453c43743','scraped','2 days ago'),(2590,NULL,'job','Customer Success Manager, Warehouse Automation APAC','','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Locus Robotics is a global leader in warehouse automation, delivering unmatched flexibility and unlimited throughput, and actionable intelligence to optimize operations. Powered by LocusONE, an AI-driven platform, our advanced autonomous mobile robots seamlessly integrate into existing warehouse environments to enhance efficiency, reduce costs, and scale operations with ease.\n\nTrusted by over 150 industry leading retail, healthcare, 3PL, and industrial brands in over 350 sites worldwide, Locus enables warehouse operators to achieve rapid ROI, minimize labor costs, and continuously improve productivity. Our industry-first Robots-as-a-Service (RaaS) model ensures ongoing innovation, scalability, and cost-effectiveness without the burden of significant capital investments. With proven capabilities in diverse workflows—from picking and replenishment to sorting and pack-out—Locus Robotics empowers businesses to meet peak demands and adapt to ever-changing operational needs.\n\nAre you ready to help global brands unlock the full value of robotics automation in their warehouses? As a Customer Success Manager, you\'ll drive success for customers in the APAC region, leading the rollout of cutting-edge warehouse automation solutions. You\'ll turn complex deployments into seamless operations, working closely with technical teams to deliver lasting impact. Your skills in project management, relationship-building, and technical aptitude will be key to long-term customer satisfaction. This is an opportunity to join an elite team at the forefront of innovation, delivering transformative logistics solutions to industry leaders.\n\nThis role is based in Sydney/Melbourne Australia, and we are only accepting local candidates who are authorized to work in Australia.\n\nThis role requires travel within Australia and APAC countries.. Travel outside of Australia would likely be 10% per year.\nA valid passport and a valid driver\'s license are required.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nOversee daily operations at customer sites, ensuring seamless Locus robots functionality.\nSupport project management, technical delivery, and customer relationship-building to ensure successful, scalable, and high-performing robotic solutions.\nEstablish and execute clear communication plans; deliver regular, data-driven status updates to stakeholders.\nResponsible for the full lifecycle of Locus Robotics warehouse automation deployments, managing everything from planning and installation to post-launch support.\nPerform post-project evaluations to capture lessons learned and identify areas for continuous improvement and expansion.\nSupport on-site preventive maintenance, diagnostics, testing, repairs, and system upgrades; manage service documentation, RMA, and support tickets (Salesforce).\nAct as the primary technical escalation point, providing both on-site and remote support for troubleshooting, mapping, and system improvements.\n\nQualifications\n\nBachelor\'s degree in Industrial Engineering, Computer Science, Information Systems, Business Administration, Project Management, or related technical field.\n3+ years of hands-on experience with Project Management.\n3+ years of experience with WMS (Warehouse Management Systems).\n3 + years of experience in 3PL, logistics and supply chain.\nProficiency with Microsoft Office Suite, including PowerPoint\nStrong experience managing outward-facing project teams involving dedicated cross functional staff, client resources, and outside vendors.\nUnderstanding of network technology, such as routers, WIFI, switches, and firewalls.\nA valid passport for APAC travel and a valid driver\'s license are required.\nExcellent written and verbal English communication skills, with the ability to effectively engage with internal and external stakeholders at all levels of the organization.\nAbility to travel to customer sites across the APAC region, with a primary focus on Australia and occasional travel to New Zealand, Singapore, and Japan.\nMust be based in Sydney or Melbourne, Australia, and legally authorized to work in Australia without sponsorship now or in the future.\n\nAdditional Details\n\nLocus Robotics is an equal opportunity employer','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Locus Robotics','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1c9784969af28123','scraped','2 days ago'),(2591,NULL,'job','Junior Account Manager – Sales','Full-time','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job Description:\n\nDXC Technology (NYSE: DXC) is a leading enterprise technology and innovation partner delivering software, services, and solutions to global enterprises and public sector organisations — helping them harness AI to drive outcomes at a time of exponential change with speed. With deep expertise in Managed Infrastructure Services, Application Modernisation, and Industry-Specific Software Solutions, DXC modernises, secures, and operates some of the world’s most complex technology estates. Learn more on dxc.com.\n\nAbout the Role\nWe’re looking for a motivated and commercially minded Junior Account Manager – Sales to join our high-performing team supporting a flagship enterprise client in the Banking sector.\n\nThis is a unique opportunity to work side-by-side with an experienced Client Partner on a Tier-1 account, gaining hands-on exposure to strategic account management, stakeholder engagement, sales governance, and growth initiatives.\n\nDesigned as a fast-track development role, this position will set you up for a long-term career in enterprise sales and client leadership.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nSupport the development of account plans, governance reporting, and executive presentations\n\nMaintain a holistic view of account performance including revenue, pipeline, delivery milestones, and KPIs\n\nCoordinate internal and client meetings, actions, and stakeholder communications\n\nPrepare content for QBRs, SteerCos, proposals, and client presentations\n\nManage dashboards for financials, utilisation, backlog, and CRM accuracy\n\nMonitor contracts, SLAs, risks, and drive issue escalation and resolution\n\nConduct market research, client mapping, and competitor analysis to support growth opportunities\n\nCapture key insights from meetings and ensure effective knowledge sharing across the team\n\nAbout You\n\nMBA or Master’s degree in Business, IT, Strategy, or a related discipline\n\n2–4 years’ experience in client engagement, consulting, sales support, or account coordination\n\nStrong analytical, organisational, and communication skills\n\nHigh emotional intelligence with the confidence to engage senior stakeholders\n\nAdvanced skills in Excel and PowerPoint\n\nExposure to enterprise clients or regulated industries (such as banking) is advantageous\n\nOur culture and benefits\nDXC is committed to building better futures for our customers, colleagues, environment, and communities. We take care of each other and foster a culture of inclusion, belonging and corporate citizenship. We put this to action developing and implementing societal initiatives within our Social Impact Practice. #WeAreDXC\n\nAs an employer of choice, our “people first” philosophy means we offer competitive remuneration, benefits, training, and career opportunities that reflect our commitment to improving the lives of our employees, and the communities in which we live and work.\n\n﻿ How to apply & our commitment to you in return\nIf you would like to be part of a culture that drives innovation, delivers results, rewards performance and encourages ideas, then please press the \"Apply Now\" button to submit your resume.\n\nIn return, we agree to ensure a hiring process that is enjoyable, thorough, and fair. We strive to provide an environment that lets you thrive and show off the very best version of yourself, while learning about us at the same time.\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer\nDXC is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and we welcome submissions from people from all walks of life. We celebrate our diversity and recognise it is the unique contributions of our people that give us our edge. We stand by the ‘bring your whole-self to work’ philosophy. It is our inclusive culture that powers our results, and our company grows only if our people grow.\n\nAccommodation of special needs for qualified candidates may be considered within the framework of the DXC Accommodation Policy. In addition, DXC Technology is committed to working with and providing reasonable accommodation to support qualified individuals with physical and mental disabilities.\n\nAt DXC Technology, we believe strong connections and community are key to our success. Our work model prioritizes in-person collaboration while offering flexibility to support wellbeing, productivity, individual work styles, and life circumstances. We’re committed to fostering an inclusive environment where everyone can thrive.\n\nRecruitment fraud is a scheme in which fictitious job opportunities are offered to job seekers typically through online services, such as false websites, or through unsolicited emails claiming to be from the company. These emails may request recipients to provide personal information or to make payments as part of their illegitimate recruiting process. DXC does not make offers of employment via social media networks and DXC never asks for any money or payments from applicants at any point in the recruitment process, nor ask a job seeker to purchase IT or other equipment on our behalf.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'DXC Technology','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8c635b81c994ed8e','scraped','2 days ago'),(2592,NULL,'job','Personal Assistant','Permanent','Toowong QLD 4066',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Your new team\n\nTo serve as a strategic administrative and process partner to the Associate Director of Development & Delivery. This dynamic role ensures the seamless operation of the Software Development & Project Delivery teams by providing high-level administrative support, optimizing executive workflows, and fostering a culture of efficiency, innovation, and engagement across the leadership team. You\'ll be part of a team that values proactivity, adaptability, and a hands-on approach to leveraging our technology and systems to explore improved ways of working that increase productivity.\n\nThe role\n\nProactively manage the AD’s schedule, prioritizing high-impact meetings and protecting \"deep work\" time, understanding the urgency and importance of communications.\nDrive efficiency by leveraging AI tools, automation, and our core systems (Google Workspace, Google Looker Dashboards, Confluence) to streamline administrative tasks, document drafting, reporting, and information flow. You\'ll be encouraged to \"play\" with these technologies to find innovative solutions.\nEnd-to-end management of Departmental Purchase Orders, vendor invoicing, and reconciliation. Ensure accuracy and timely submission to Accounts Payable. Support the AD with data-backed recommendations for departmental and budgetary approvals.\nTrack and monitor the AD’s budget, including Reward & Recognition expenditure and gift registers.\nAct as a gatekeeper and agile point of contact, translating and routing communications within a fast-paced Technology environment, ensuring priorities are understood and actioned.\nSupport the planning and execution of team-based events and engagement programs to boost department morale and foster a fun, collaborative atmosphere.\nCoordinate internal and external meetings, including agenda preparation, high-quality minute-taking, and tracking actionable outcomes with a focus on urgency.\nSupport the leadership team in meeting mandatory reporting deadlines and maintaining software license registers.\nAssist in adhering to APRA prudential standards by monitoring compliance metrics and flagging critical correspondence for the AD.\nContribute to the identification of operational and financial risks, supporting the maintenance of robust internal controls.\nSupport the department’s response to internal and external audits/examinations.\n\nWhat experience you’ll bring\n\nEarly in your career, with 1-3 years of experience as a Personal or Executive Assistant, or in a similar supportive administrative or project coordinator role within a fast-paced environment. We\'re looking for adaptability and a fresh perspective rather than deeply ingrained operational habits.\nAdvanced proficiency in Google Workspace (Docs, Sheets, Slides) and a genuine enthusiasm for leveraging data tools like Google Looker Dashboards and collaboration platforms like Slack or MS Teams and Confluence.\nComfortable using AI tools (e.g., Gemini, ChatGPT, automation scripts) to enhance productivity and output quality, with a desire to explore new technological solutions.\nExceptional written and verbal skills with an uncompromising eye for detail.\nPractical experience with financial processes, including invoicing and budget tracking.\nHigh emotional intelligence (EQ) and the ability to build relationships at all levels, matched with a fun-loving, jovial personality and good banter.\nA proactive, \"solution-first\" mindset when resolving administrative or process bottlenecks and a willingness to tackle low-to-moderate complexity administrative processes.\nAt least some understanding of technology terminology, perhaps from prior experience in a tech company, a semi-technical role, or even personal coding interests\n\nLocation\n\nClose to a variety of public transport and easy parking options, the Toowong office has excellent end of trip facilities (including secure bike storage and showers), outdoor spaces and plenty of modern collaborative areas to work and connect with colleagues.\n\nConveniently based at Toowong Village tower with views of the mountains and the Brisbane River, our location is only 4 km from the city and provides access to retail, restaurants and other amenities.\n\nThe benefits of working at A&G\n\nBe rewarded - we recognise high performance and reward our people for their hard work through bonuses and other perks.\nWork flexibility - with options to work from home two days per week.\nOptions for leave - life happens, so we’ve got volunteer days, an additional paid ‘ME’ day, paid parental leave and the opportunity to purchase additional leave to cover all of the big stuff.\nGrow with us - we’ve got learning and professional development opportunities to suit everyone.\nGive back - our A&G Difference program gives you the power to change our community for the better through volunteering, fundraising and donation opportunities for causes that you’re passionate about.\nTake care of yourself - your wellbeing is important to us and our healthy mind and body hub, mental-health support and fitness discounts will help you be your best self.\nCelebrate the wins - we love sharing our successes and celebrating together - join us and you’ve got a ticket to our many on-site events throughout the year, family fun days and annual celebrations.\nSave money - as well as discounts on insurance products, we’ve teamed up with some incredible retailers, hospitality providers and others to bring you discounts on your purchases, no matter where you are in Australia\n\nAbout us\n\nAuto & General (A&G) is the fastest-growing major Motor and Home insurer in Australia, providing insurance products and solutions to safeguard a brighter future for our customers and community.\n\nOur range of general insurance products including Car, Motorcycle, Home, Contents Pet and Travel products are delivered through our multi-award-winning brand Budget Direct and partnerships with leading brands - ING, Qantas, Virgin Money and Coles Insurance.\n\nWe’re excited about the future and we’re always on the lookout for talented, passionate individuals who can help us achieve our goal of being Australia’s best insurer! If this sounds like you, apply today.\n\nAuto & General values individual differences and believes in fostering an inclusive culture that creates a great place to work for all.\n\n*A note from Auto & General to recruitment agencies: We politely ask that you avoid making any approaches or sending any unsolicited resumes to our Recruitment Team or Hiring Leaders across our business. Auto & General is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.\n\nPlease ensure your manager or team leader is aware of your application. If this sounds like your next challenge, click on the APPLY NOW button and submit your application.\n\nWe are accepting referrals for this position. If you know someone who has the right skills & experience, please encourage them to apply and advise our recruitment team.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Auto & General Holdings','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=09fe3748ff179c45','scraped','2 days ago'),(2593,NULL,'job','Senior Software Engineer (AI-First, Full Stack) - Gold Coast, QLD','Full-time','Gold Coast QLD',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job no: 530742\nBrand: AuntBetty and BYOJet\nWork type: Full time\nLocation: Queensland\nCategories: Data and Business Intelligence\n\nAt Flight Centre Travel Group (FCTG) our purpose is to \'open up the world for those who want to see\'. Every day, we give people all around the world the opportunity to experience something really amazing – travel!\n\nWe’re building the future of AI‑augmented engineering and are looking for a Senior Software Engineer who doesn’t just write code, they multiply impact using AI\n\nThis is a newly created role driven by rapid growth and global expansion. You’ll play a critical role in scaling large‑scale, customer‑facing travel platforms integrated with partners such as Google Flights, Skyscanner, and Kayak.\n\nThis is not a traditional engineering role. You’ll be expected to think like an engineer, operator, and product‑minded problem solver, using AI as a core part of how you work.\n\nDAY TO DAY\n\nOwn software solutions end‑to‑end, from detection and diagnosis through to resolution\nBuild, maintain, and evolve backend and frontend systems with a focus on reliability and scale\nDesign and maintain effective monitoring, logging, and alerting across platforms\nEnsure issues are identified proactively, before they impact customers\nRapidly respond to production incidents and defects across multiple systems\nBalance speed, quality, and stability in a high‑throughput environment\nUse logs, telemetry, and metrics to perform root‑cause analysis and remediation\nContinuously improve performance, resilience, and maintainability of systems\nBuild backend solutions using .NET (C#) and modern frontend solutions using JavaScript / TypeScript\nDesign clean, scalable APIs and data models backed by SQL\nWork across the full SDLC, contributing to architecture, implementation, testing, and release\nLeverage AI tools daily to accelerate development, debugging, testing, and operations\nDesign and experiment with AI‑assisted workflows and automation across engineering processes\nIdentify high‑leverage work and prioritise based on business impact\nCollaborate closely with product, architecture, and engineering stakeholders\nGuide and support an offshore IT support team\nMentor other engineers and uplift engineering standards across the team\nTake ownership of technical direction within your domain as the team grows\n\nYOU’LL BE PERFECT FOR THE ROLE IF YOU HAVE\n\nAn AI‑first mindset, you actively use AI tools to move faster and smarter\nExperience using tools like Copilot, Claude, Codex, Rovo, or similar in daily workflows\nStrong full‑stack engineering fundamentals with .NET (C#) and modern JavaScript (ES6+)\nExperience with frameworks such as React, Vue, or Angular\nStrong understanding of system architecture, scalability, and API design\nSolid SQL and data modelling experience\nHands‑on experience with cloud platforms (Azure preferred)\nExperience implementing observability, monitoring, and alerting solutions\nStrong debugging skills and a track record of owning production outcomes\nA builder mindset, you take ownership, move quickly, and thrive in ambiguity\nCommercial and product awareness, understanding how your work drives business value\nStrong written and verbal communication skills across technical and non‑technical audiences\nComfort working with offshore teams and across time zones\nA bias toward shipping, learning, and iterating over over‑engineering\n\nWhat you\'ll Enjoy:\n\n    ‍ ️Culture: you will be employed by an inclusive company that offers a team culture like no other in the industry - Flight Centre Travel Group Australia is proud to be a certified Great Place To Work® Australia New Zealand Pty Ltd\n\n     Our People: FCTG is an Equal Opportunity Employer and encourage all suitably qualified applicants to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander People and people from racial, ethnic, or ethno-religious minority groups and people with disability\n\n  Development: Individualised Learning & Development pathway options\n\n  Access to \' Learning\' for ongoing skills development: over 24,500 courses in over 20 languages\n\n  Exclusive Staff Discounts: Accessible via our employee-only portal with 350+ of Australia’s leading retailers, health and wellness discounts, financial planning advice, employee share plan and more\n\n  Travel Discounts: Including family and friends - flights, hotels, tours, cruises, travel insurance and more\n\n  Brightness of Future: Career opportunities in a network of brands and businesses across the globe - we promote from within\n\n  Corporate Health Discounts: Access exclusive discounts on health insurance plans for you and your family with our partner, BUPA, access to internal gym\n\n  Mental Health: Support and Employee Assistance Program for staff and family\n\n  Social: Regular awards nights, social team-building and industry events, with the opportunity to attend global conferences (Bangkok in 2026)\n\n     Giving Back: Corporate Social Responsibility program supporting nominated charities through Workplace Giving, volunteering and fundraising; paid parental and volunteer leave\n\n  Sustainability: The protection of our environment is essential to the future of tourism, as a leading travel group, we have made efforts to affect positive change to the environment\n\n   Be part of a workplace committed to reconciliation through our Reconciliation Action Plan - we proudly support Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander inclusion, cultural safety, and dedicated cultural leave\n\n#LI-KC1#LI#onsite\n\nApplications close:','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'AuntBetty and BYOJet','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b202c821526a66c2','scraped','2 days ago'),(2594,NULL,'job','Design Lead - Acumatica','','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We’re a leading business management solution with a core purpose: helping more businesses in Australia and New Zealand start, survive and succeed.\n\nAt MYOB, we believe what’s good for one business is good for all business—and for all of us. Whether you support them, work for them, or dream of building your own, when businesses run smoothly, everybody feels it. Owners, employees, customers, suppliers—even families. That’s why we’re here: to give every person in business the tools they need to focus on what really matters and do Big Things—whatever big looks like for them.\n\nAnd for you? Joining MYOB means being part of that impact. It means using your skills to help businesses thrive, shaping the future of work, and growing alongside the people and communities we support. Because while we’re the business of software, we’re really in the business of people. And that makes MYOB Everyone’s Business.\n\nAbout the role:\n\nMYOB Acumatica is the leading ERP for mid-market businesses in Australia and New Zealand. Our strength is not only in the industry-leading ERP itself, but also the ecosystem we have built around it: the products, services, connected workflows, and intelligent capabilities that help our customers simplify complexity, move faster, and succeed. Design plays a central role in shaping that ecosystem, ensuring it is built on a genuine understanding of the people it serves.\n\nAs Design Lead, you will lead a small, senior design team that shapes how MYOB builds and delivers value across this ecosystem. Your role operates at two levels: leading and developing a team of service and product designers and working as a hands-on design practitioner in the strategic spaces that require senior judgement, cross-team coordination, and direct stakeholder engagement.\n\nAs Design Lead, you will:\nLead and develop a talented design team, driving high engagement, strong delivery, and exceptional partner and customer outcomes.\nHelp shape the design strategy for MYOB Mid-Market, ensuring design investment is focused on the highest-leverage opportunities for partners and customers, not just the most visible or most requested problems.\nChampion design thinking and human evidence across the product organisation, ensuring both are integrated into how the team prioritises, discovers, and builds.\nBuild and maintain a connected view of the end-to-end experience across our ecosystem, generating the insights that help the business see where value is being created and where it is being lost.\nStay at the forefront of how AI is reshaping design practice, and bring that thinking into the team: ensuring MYOB leads with AI where it creates genuine value for customers, and that the design team is equipped to discover, prototype, and validate AI-enabled experiences.\nBuild strong working relationships with Product Managers, PMM, Pricing, Engineering, Marketing, and senior stakeholders, making design’s contribution to partner outcomes, customer experience, and business performance visible and impactful.\nThe skills you\'ll need:\nDeep understanding of service, experience and product design disciplines, with fluency across all three.\nProven ability to lead, inspire, and develop cross-functional design teams to deliver high-quality, customer-centred outcomes.\nStrong experience in systems thinking, able to connect end-to-end journeys across multiple products, channels, and organisational boundaries.\nExperience operating in a B2B, platform, channel-led, or enterprise software context where design works around and beyond a core product.\nAbility to articulate and balance customer, commercial, and strategic perspectives, translating insight into actionable design priorities.\nWell versed with AI-enabled design, automation, or data-driven experiences, and curiosity to continue evolving these capabilities within the team.\nStrong experience design leadership role.\nOur Culture & Benefits\nAt MYOB our values are at the heart of everything we do. If you want to work and collaborate where opinions are valued, and your ideas can make a difference, come to a place where Your Work Matters.\n\nEnjoy a flexible, hybrid workplace that brings balance to how you work, all of our centrally located offices come together for a number of in-person celebrations and social events\nSet up your home office with a little financial help from us, and take advantage of great corporate discounts and vouchers from top retailers\nBenefit from our partnership with Sonder, which supports the wellbeing of our team members\nUnlock your potential via in-house training and programs, LinkedIn Learning, conferences and study assistance\nAccess to a variety of leave options available to support your wellbeing, including up to an additional four weeks of purchased leave, generous parental leave, domestic violence leave, transgender leave, community leave, study leave, and more\nJoin our communities, built around ‘Wellness’, ‘Belonging’ and the ‘Planet’ where you can make a meaningful contribution\n\nAt MYOB, we’re all about embracing difference and backing people to be their true selves. We’re proud to be an equal opportunity employer and big believers that the best hires don’t just fit our culture — they add to it. That means bringing your unique contributions, lived experiences, and fresh perspective to the table.\n\nLove the sound of MYOB and this role but don’t tick every single box in this ad? Apply anyway! Studies show that women and underrepresented groups often hold back if they don’t meet every requirement — but we want to hear from you.\n\nWe’re proud to be a Circle Back Initiative Employer and we commit to responding to every applicant.\nWe may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Axsys','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=62f236c3358978f9','scraped','2 days ago'),(2595,NULL,'job','Management Consultant - Remote','Contract','Remote',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job Title: Management consultant\n\nJob Type: Contractor\n\nLocation: Remote\n\nJob Summary: As a Management consultant, you\'ll apply your expertise to help train next-generation AI systems. Your work will shape how models learn, reason, and perform through high-quality, real-world input. No prior experience in AI is required , your domain knowledge is what matters.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nProvide expert insights on management consulting methodologies, strategic analysis, and business transformation practices.\nReview, assess, and refine complex business scenarios, documents, and case studies to ensure accuracy and relevance.\nDeliver high-quality, detailed written and verbal feedback to help improve AI system outputs and reasoning capabilities.\nCollaborate remotely with the customer’s team to support the training and evaluation of AI models with real-world management consulting perspectives.\nLeverage your advanced experience to identify gaps, propose improvements, and ensure alignment with industry best practices.\nUtilize strong communication skills to clearly articulate recommendations and process flows in both written and spoken formats.\nContinually stay updated on management consulting trends to provide current, impactful input into the AI training process.\n\nRequired Skills and Qualifications:\n\nMinimum of 4+ years’ experience as a management consultant, ideally with a top-tier consulting firm.\nProven expertise in strategic projects, business process improvement, and organizational transformation.\nExceptional written and verbal communication skills with high attention to detail.\nAbility to synthesize complex problems and deliver practical, actionable insights.\nStrong analytical skills and experience working with cross-functional teams in remote environments.\nExperience developing or reviewing case studies, business frameworks, and client-ready deliverables.\nSelf-motivation and discipline required for high-quality independent work.\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\nMBA or advanced degree in business, management, or a related field.\nFamiliarity with digital transformation initiatives or AI-driven business models.\nDemonstrated experience mentoring or training consultants or business professionals.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'YO IT CONSULTING','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=32ff4126007a9c65','scraped','1 day ago'),(2596,NULL,'job','Digital Strategy Consultants (Technology & Digital Advantage) Melbourne or Sydney Based','Full-time','Melbourne VIC 3000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Locations: Melbourne | Sydney\n\nWho We Are\n\nWho We Are Boston Consulting Group partners with leaders in business and society to tackle their most important challenges and capture their greatest opportunities. BCG was the pioneer in business strategy when it was founded in 1963. Today, we help clients with total transformation-inspiring complex change, enabling organizations to grow, building competitive advantage, and driving bottom-line impact.To succeed, organizations must blend digital and human capabilities. Our diverse, global teams bring deep industry and functional expertise and a range of perspectives to spark change. BCG delivers solutions through leading-edge management consulting along with technology and design, corporate and digital ventures-and business purpose. We work in a uniquely collaborative model across the firm and throughout all levels of the client organization, generating results that allow our clients to thrive.\n\nPractice Area\n\nBCG’s Technology and Digital Advantage practice area focuses on helping clients deliver competitive advantage and business superior performance through the use of data, technology and digital. Tech and Digital is the fastest growing practice at BCG and at the heart of the strategic impact we have with our clients. Our consultants and experts globally work across all industries and provide deep experience and expertise across a number of topics including Digital Transformation, Data & Digital Platforms, AI at Scale, Agile, Cybersecurity and Digitizing the Tech Function. Our Tech and Digital offer encompasses tech experts across BCG and Platinion, providing seamless multidisciplinary solutions to our clients.\n\nWhat You\'ll Do\n\nAs a Digital & Technology Consultant, you\'ll be given end-to-end responsibility for the larger and more complex \'modules\' within a BCG project and begin to develop specialised knowledge to help you solve our clients\' problems. You\'ll work on a variety of digital topics, applying generalist consulting skills to strategic digital & technology questions. Working together with clients to understand their issues, you\'ll create strategies for change, win buy-in for your recommendations, and collaborate with fellow BCGers to transform client potential into performance. Our consultants within TDA are an integral part of BCG\'s core consulting team; we work side-by-side with all practice areas to create value and competitive advantage for our clients. You\'ll help your clients answer questions such as \'How will AI disrupt my business model?\', \'How can businesses use data and analytics to create highly personalised outreach delivered through a seamless omnichannel experience\', \'How can I ship higher quality digital services to my customers faster by using agile?\' and many more.\n\nWhat You\'ll Bring\n\nWe\'re looking for exceptional talent from consulting and/or industry. You would typically have:\n\nA minimum of 4 years\' experience working with a leading consulting firm (focused on technology/digital initiatives), in a corporate role focused on strategy/technology/digital initiatives, in a tech start-up strategic role or in a \'consulting-like\' industry (e.g. technology/digital strategy, digital marketing)\nAn outstanding academic track record; a bachelor\'s degree\nThrive in a hypothesis-led environment and ability to frame strategic challenges from a digital/technology perspective\nStrong analytical skills, problem solving ability and conceptual thinking\nExcellent communication, storylining, client facing skills\nFlexibility to travel within ANZ and Asia Pacific region\n\nA broad skillset and passion for digital and technology is important. You\'ll be supported by an extensive training curriculum (the same program all BCG consultants), plus digital-specific training and mentoring to help you build your skills.\n\nAt BCG, we offer multiple career paths for the world\'s best talent to have a real impact on business and society. As part of our team, you will benefit from the breadth and diversity of what we are doing today and where we are headed next. We count on your authenticity, exceptional work, and strong integrity. In return, we are committed to supporting you in discovering the most fulfilling career journey possible - and unlocking your potential to advance the world.\n\nDiversity of thought, background, and experience is a core part of our BCG values and is key to delivering value to clients.\n\nWe are committed to fostering a diverse, equitable, and inclusive environment where everyone feels valued, connected, and empowered to be themselves and contribute to their fullest potential. Applications are encouraged from people of all backgrounds, including people of Aboriginal, Torres straight island, Māori or Pacific Island origin, individuals with a disability, those from culturally or linguistically diverse backgrounds, LGBTIQA+ individuals, women, and gender diverse individuals.\n\nBCG’s efforts toward diversity, equity, and inclusion are recognised locally and globally: BCG Australia and New Zealand hold a WGEA Employer of Choice for Gender Equality citation and are awarded the Australian Workplace Equality Index Silver award for LGBTQIA+ inclusion.We want to make sure everyone experiences a positive, barrier-free recruiting process. Please reach out to Rachael Keating at recruitmentinANZ@bcg.com at any stage if you require additional support or adjustments to assist you with your experience, including support in submitting your application, providing identity documents, attending a job interview. This includes any specific support for transgender and gender-diverse individuals.\n\nBoston Consulting Group is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, age, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity / expression, national origin, disability, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected under national, provincial, or local law, where applicable, and those with criminal histories will be considered in a manner consistent with applicable state and local laws.\nBCG is an E - Verify Employer. Click here for more information on E-Verify.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Boston Consulting Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=bd17e83a25d16732','scraped','2 days ago'),(2597,NULL,'job','Senior Sales Engineer (Australia)','Full-time','Remote',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Uniphore is one of the largest B2B AI-native companies—decades-proven, built-for-scale and designed for the enterprise. The company drives business outcomes, across multiple industry verticals, and enables the largest global deployments.\n\nUniphore infuses AI into every part of the enterprise that impacts the customer. We deliver the only multimodal architecture centered on customers that combines Generative AI, Knowledge AI, Emotion AI, workflow automation and a co-pilot to guide you. We understand better than anyone how to capture voice, video and text and how to analyze all types of data.\n\nAs AI becomes more powerful, every part of the enterprise that impacts the customer will be disrupted. We believe the future will run on the connective tissue between people, machines and data: all in the service of creating the most human processes and experiences for customers and employees.\n\nJob Description:\n\nJob Description\n\nUniphore, a global Business AI technology company, is seeking an experienced Senior Sales Engineer to join its high-performance Sales Engineering team to support its customer and strategic partners in Australia . As a Senior Sales Engineer , you will be a trusted technical advisor and strategic partner to our enterprise clients. You’ll collaborate closely with account executives, product management, and engineering to demonstrate the power of Uniphore’s Business AI Cloud platform - helping Fortune 1000 organizations design, prototype, and deploy intelligent AI systems that drive measurable business outcomes. You’ll lead the technical sales cycle from discovery to proof of concept, translating complex enterprise challenges into transformative AI solutions that showcase Uniphore’s innovation, scalability, and value.\n\nTeam Charter and/or Mission: Our mission is to become trusted advisors to the clients and partners we work with, while advocating Uniphore’s AI platform . The sales engineering organization bridges our cutting-edge AI technologies with customer business outcomes—designing, showcasing , and delivering solutions that accelerate adoption, drive growth, and ensure customer success across industries and geographies. We will keep our client’s interests in the forefront while solving unique business problems harnessing the power of Uniphore’s AI platform and pre-built solutions .\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nAct as the technical lead in the sales cycle, partnering with Account Executives to drive enterprise opportunities from qualification to close .\n\nHave a perspective on how AI can drive value in Enterprises and understand the power of language models and agents to impact business value across verticals and business functions .\n\nUnderstand customer pain points in driving and implementing AI solutions .\n\nDeliver compelling technical presentations, demos showcasing GenAI, Agentic AI, RAG, and LLM-based solutions.\n\nBuild and deliver custom demos and POCs to validate business value and technical feasibility.\n\nConduct discovery sessions with key business and technical stakeholders to uncover needs, pain points, and desired outcomes.\n\nTranslate business requirements into AI solution architectures that leverage Uniphore’s capabilities , collaborating with product and engineering teams.\n\nRespond to RFPs/RFIs with detailed technical responses and solution designs.\n\nAdvise clients on AI adoption strategies , integration with multi-modal data platforms, and industry best practices.\n\nContribute to a culture of technical excellence, customer obsession, and innovation.\n\nBuild and maintain deep domain expertise in AI trends, competitor offerings, and the evolving landscape of agentic applications and enterprise AI adoption .\n\nSkills and Qualifications\n\n6+ years of experience in pre-sales, solution engineering, or technical consulting – preferably within enterprise SaaS, AI, or automation platforms .\n\nDeep knowledge of data ingestion, identity resolution, event tracking, and API-based integrations.\n\nHands-on understanding of AI concepts: Large Language Models (LLMs), Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), prompt engineering, Agentic AI architectures , AI security and governance, and ethical AI\n\nExperience designing or selling AI platforms, data orchestration, or enterprise automation solutions.\n\nExpertise in major Cloud Platforms: Demonstrated understanding of cloud computing principles and architecture, particularly as they relate to deploying and scaling enterprise AI/SaaS solutions (e.g., AWS, Azure, or GCP). This includes familiarity with core services like compute , storage, networking, and serverless functions.\n\nSolid Understanding of API Integration and Security: Practical experience with designing, integrating, and securing API connections between AI platforms and underlying business applications (e.g., CRM, ERP, data warehouses). Knowledge of protocols (e.g., REST, GraphQL ) and authentication mechanisms (e.g., OAuth 2.0, API keys) is essential.\n\nData and Network Architecture Acumen: Ability to discuss and propose solutions regarding data governance, network segmentation, and enterprise security requirements when deploying cloud-native or hybrid AI solutions.\n\nStrong ability to explain technical concepts to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.\n\nProven track record supporting enterprise sales cycles and closing large deals.\n\nExcellent communication, presentation, and stakeholder management skills with the ability to engage with all levels within large enterprises , from C-suite to technician .\n\nStrong problem-solving and storytelling skills—able to connect AI capabilities to strategic business outcomes.\n\nAbility to travel as needed for client engagements.\n\nLocation preference:\n\nAustralia - Remote\n\nUniphore is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity in the workplace. We evaluate qualified applicants without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, disability, veteran status, and other protected characteristics.\n\nFor more information on how Uniphore uses AI to unify—and humanize—every enterprise experience, please visit www.uniphore.com.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Uniphore','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=7e92efb0d8790dce','scraped','1 day ago'),(2598,NULL,'job','Marketing Coordinator at Intaks','Part-time','Remote',NULL,'',39.00,'$28 - $50 an hour','Marketing Coordinator\n\nThis is a fantastic opportunity for a results-driven and hands-on individual to join our team at Intaks. This role is remote, with company headquarters in Australia.\n\nAs the Marketing Coordinator, you will be responsible for coordinating, planning, and executing marketing campaigns across multiple media channels.\n\nYou will establish a collaborative working relationship with the business owner, who will work with you on strategic and big-picture goals while taking charge of tactical implementation and execution.\n\nThe ability to organize, plan and structure your workload in an autonomous fashion will be absolutely key to your success in this role. We neither have the time nor the inclination to micromanage you. You’ll have a lot of freedom in this role but also a lot of responsibility.\n\nThe Six Non-Negotiables of This Role Are\nCopywriting. You’ll be crafting direct marketing campaigns across email, direct mail, web and social media. Your written skills need to be excellent, and we will expect to see samples of your previous work.\nBeing tech-savvy. You don’t need to be a technical expert, but you must be tech-savvy and be able to quickly learn how to use new marketing tools and technologies. While we don’t expect you to know all of the tools we use, we do expect you to be comfortable with them and able to pick up the concepts. Your daily tools of the trade will be CRM systems, content management systems, email marketing, etc.\nLeadership potential. Initially, you’ll be our only in-house marketing person, but as you hit goals, we fully expect this role to morph into a marketing team leader role where you will manage a team of marketing assistants.\nProject management. Ideally, you’ve had experience in project management. A large part of this role is creating and adhering to deadlines, drafting budgets, and moving simultaneous projects forward to completion.\nBeing teachable and coachable. There will be a LOT of learning on the job as we do marketing very differently. There is no place here for know-it-alls. We hire based primarily on attitude.\nBeing a self-starter. Goals will be clearly defined from the outset. Often, it will be your job to determine what needs to happen, when, and how. The attitude of continually starting things on your own is very important.\nPerks of The Job\nThis is a completely remote position, so you’ll have the ability to create your own schedule.\nFlexible work hours (though irregular hours may be expected based on working with different time zones).\nGain management and marketing experience.\nThis role starts at 30 hours per week with the potential for full-time after an initial period.\nSalary expectation of 28$-$37USD / $40-50 AUD based on experience\nContract role\nSkills Needed/Day-to-Day Tasks and Responsibilities\nDeveloping and executing email marketing campaigns and managing a CRM management: Write, schedule, and manage emails, automations, and workflows. Build out email marketing campaigns, sequences, and newsletters.\nOptimize marketing systems and processes from top-of-funnel awareness through to customer acquisition. Optimize the customer experience and increase customer lifetime value.\nGraphic design and developing marketing materials: Designing lead magnets, resources, content, brochures, and landing pages.\nCreate and manage content calendar: Develop a content plan, create, schedule, and analyze content. Build high-value content assets and repurpose them across media channels. Manage the company\'s social media presence, including creating and posting content, responding to comments, and monitoring metrics.\nWriting and editing marketing copy for various channels such as social media, email, and website content.\nTracking KPIs and campaign performance: Weekly tracking of key metrics related to marketing activities, performance of marketing campaigns and initiatives, including monitoring metrics such as website traffic, leads generated, and customer engagement**.**\nVideo production: Coordinating and managing video content and production pipelin, and scheduling video content. Basic video editing skills a plus!\nCreating and managing project timelines to ensure that campaigns and initiatives are completed on time.\nManaging the company\'s website, including updating content, ensuring website functionality, and improving website performance.\nCoordinating and executing events, such as trade shows, conferences, and product launches.\nGo High Level Experience\nAI Experience\nPPC experience welcomed\nB2B experience\n\nThe application deadline is May 8th\nc6RkD1wyAM','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Lean Marketing','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8a19008656de61d6','scraped','1 day ago'),(2599,NULL,'job','AI Content Analyst','Part-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'*Help Shape the Future of AI — From Anywhere*\n\nAI is revolutionising how we interact with technology. From news feeds to navigation, machine learning can tailor our digital experiences to meet our needs — anytime, anywhere.\n\nWith *Peroptyx*, you’ll have an opportunity to help make those experiences even smarter. We\'re looking for *AI Content Analysts *to assess the accuracy and relevance of human and AI-generated content.\n\nYou’ll evaluate everything from search results to news stories, images, music and transit data — ensuring it all makes sense in the real world.\n\n*What’s in it for you?*\n\n✅ Total flexibility — set your own hours (weekends, evenings, whenever suits you)\n\n✅ Fully remote — work from home, skip the commute\n\n✅ Earn a competitive hourly rate\n\n✅ Boost your research and analytical skills\n\nWhether you\'re a student, a parent, a professional seeking part-time hours, or just someone who loves a flexible role — this is an opportunity to make a real impact from your home location.\n\n*You’ll Succeed If You Are:*\n\n* Fluent in English\n* A sharp researcher with great local knowledge (news, culture, media)\n* Familiar with search engines, maps, and social platforms\n* Analytical, self-motivated, and comfortable working independently\n* Living in your country for 5+ consecutive years\n\n*Requirements:*\n\n* Minimum 10–20 hours/week availability\n* Must pass an online open-book assessment\n* Laptop/PC with unique user account & up-to-date antivirus\n* Only one applicant per household\n* All tools/equipment at your own expense\n\nHelp train the next generation of AI — on your time, your terms\n\n*Join the Peroptyx Team — Apply Online Today!*\n\n*Note: *_*This is a freelance, independent contractor position.*_\n\nJob Type: Part-time\n\nBenefits:\n* Work from home\n\nWork Location: Remote','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Peroptyx','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d2e3582693663dca','scraped','2 days ago'),(2600,NULL,'job','Assistant Project Manager - Industrial','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',100000.00,'$100,000 a year','Fast-track your career with a reputable PM company & a tier 1 Industrial project\nReceive constant support and mentorship from industry leading professionals\nHybrid working environment with high levels of autonomy and flexibility\n\nAbout RP Infrastructure\n\nRP Infrastructure (RPI) is one of Australia\'s leading Project Management and Advisory practices, recognised for delivering complex and high-profile projects across the Public and Private Sector.\n\nWith a focus on quality and collaboration, we deliver Advisory, Project Management and Asset Management services across the entire Infrastructure spectrum.\n\nCommunity is at the heart of everything we do, and we’re proud to make a difference with the projects we deliver. We partner with many of Australia’s most iconic businesses, Local, State & Federal Government entities, and Not-For-Profit bodies.\n\nSpecialising in Education, Civic & Culture, Accommodation, Health/Aged Care, Sports & Recreation, Justice, Retail, Industrial, Aviation, Roads, Rail and Ports sectors, we’re dedicated to delivering extraordinary outcomes by converting visions to reality, in an innovative and sustainable way.\n\nRole Description\n\nWe’re looking for a confident and motivated Junior Assistant Project Manager to support the delivery a major Industrial project worth over $650M. Located in Western Sydney, this is a complex, sophisticated project which is currently in the construction phase.\n\nWorking alongside a team of Project Managers, Senior Project Managers, Project Directors and the Associate Director, you’ll be part of a team responsible for delivering a critical building for our client. In other words, you’re far more than “just a number” on this project.\n\nDue to the high-profile, \'one of a kind\' nature of this particular project, this role will ensure that your career is quickly catapulted beyond your peers as you receive mentorship and invaluable guidance from some of the industry\'s top leading experts within this field.\n\nDigital & AI‑Enabled Project Support\n\nThe project is actively exploring and trialing the use of AI‑enabled tools to support and enhance core project management functions. This includes assisting with activities such as report preparation, meeting minutes, project registers, and contract administration, as well as identifying opportunities to streamline processes, improve consistency, and enhance productivity across the project lifecycle. The role provides an opportunity to contribute to the responsible adoption of digital and AI‑enabled practices within a structured project governance environment.\n\nLocated in our Sydney CBD office, you’ll be responsible for:\n\nDrafting reports, briefs and other documentation for our Project Managers.\nAssisting with scoping of works and tender processes.\nAssisting with consultant engagement and contractor appointment.\nAssisting with contract management and client invoicing.\nProviding regular updates to stakeholders and building relationships with key international clients.\n\nCandidate Profile\n\nTo be successful, you’ll need a professional and confident attitude, paired with motivation and a keen eye for detail. Your passion for data and analytics is what will set you apart from other applicants.\n\nThe idea with this role is to quickly transform a high-performing Assistant Project Manager to Project Manager within the next 2-3 years. The opportunity for growth in this position is vast.\n\nYou’ll also need:\n\nQualifications in Project Management, Engineering, Construction, or a related discipline.\nIdeally you will have relevant experience in a similar role within a consulting environment.\nStrong communication skills and an ability to build rapport with busy stakeholders.\nAn understanding of contracts administration and AI management.\nHigh attention to detail and a client-focused mindset.\nA willingness to work with team members and deliver outstanding outcomes for clients.\nExperience with design and construction phases of projects from the Property & Buildings sector is desirable.\n\nWhat’s In It For You\n\nThis role is a huge opportunity for someone ready to springboard their career ahead of their peers.\n\nWith experience on this highly sought-after project, you’ll stand out from the crowd and create tremendous strides in your career progression.\n\nSuccessful delivery of this project is sure to be noticed amongst the industry.\n\nAs an Assistant Project Manager at RPI, you’ll also receive:\n\nThe ability to broaden your project expertise – we offer a range of projects across multiple sectors, giving you access to the full Infrastructure spectrum.\nPhenomenal support from our talented leadership team – you’ll play an integral part in shaping the further development of our business.\nA hybrid working environment, with high levels of autonomy and flexibility.\nOngoing career development and continuous progression opportunities. Upon joining RPI, you’ll receive your own tailored Professional Development Plan, as well as a senior mentor to help you reach your next career goals.\nA strong, supportive management team that cares about you. We’re passionate about what we do, and we’re proud to prioritise the development of our staff.\nAccess to events, activities and initiatives driven by our popular Health & Wellbeing + Diversity & Inclusion committees.\n\nIf you’d like to hear more about what we can offer you, please apply with your latest CV attached.\n\nRPI supports a diverse and inclusive work environment as well as equal employment opportunities. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people living with a disability, and people of all ages, sexual orientations, nationalities, backgrounds, and cultures.\n\nDisclaimer: We do not accept unsolicited agency resumes and are not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'RP Infrastructure','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b0be2baf765bdca0','scraped','2 days ago'),(2601,NULL,'job','UAT Test Lead (Brisbane Based) - Hybrid','','Brisbane QLD',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Work options: Hybrid\n\nKJR is looking for a UAT Test Lead to drive the planning and delivery of User Acceptance Testing for a cloud migration, ensuring all business processes, integrations, and system changes are production-ready and meet acceptance criteria.\n\nCommencement Date: As soon as possible\n\nDuration: 12 Months\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nDefine and implement the UAT strategy and approach aligned to overall test planning\nDevelop and manage UAT test scenarios, cases, and data across business processes and integrations\nCoordinate and lead UAT execution with business stakeholders and SMEs\nManage defect lifecycle, including triage, prioritisation, and resolution tracking\nProvide test reporting and status updates, including risks, issues, and readiness assessments\nPrepare UAT summary reports\nEnsure traceability between requirements, test coverage, and outcomes\nCollaborate with performance and technical teams to ensure end-to-end validation\nSupport regression and automation readiness for key business scenarios\nDrive UAT sign-off and go-live readiness\n\nKey Skills and Experience\n\nProven experience as a UAT Test Lead on large-scale transformation programs\nStrong background in enterprise applications / ERP systems (e.g. Agresso, SAP, Oracle)\nExperience in cloud migration or integration-heavy programs\nStrong knowledge of test methodologies, test management, and defect management processes\nHands-on experience with Azure DevOps or similar test tools\nAbility to engage and manage business stakeholders and SMEs\nStrong analytical, problem-solving, and communication skills\nExperience working in Agile and/or PRINCE2 environments\nApplicants must be Australian Citizens or hold Permanent Residency to be considered for this role.\n\nWho are we?\n\nStarted in a garage on the Gold Coast in 1997, KJR is now a leading Software Quality Engineering consultancy with offices in Melbourne, Brisbane, and Canberra. We specialise in software assurance, AI adoption, and technology risk management, helping organisations unlock real value from emerging technologies.\n\nAt the forefront of Trusted AI Adoption, we ensure AI solutions are ethical, compliant, and drive meaningful business outcomes.\n\nOur people—The Collective—are central to our success. We support your growth through career development, recognition programs and our annual team conference.\n\nKJR is proud to be Certified by Great Place To Work® and to foster a diverse and inclusive culture, recognised by the 2023 AIIA Diversity Award.\n\nWe’re driven to make a difference—and you can help make it happen.\n\nLearn more: www.kjr.com.au\n\nExplore our innovation projects: https://kjr.com.au/corporate-social-responsibility/','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'KJR','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c867d7bf85109c65','scraped','2 days ago'),(2602,NULL,'job','Test Automation Manager','','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Test Automation Manager\n\nDate:\n\n1 May 2026\n\nLocation:\n\nSydney, NSW, AU\n\nDepartment:\n\nTechnology & Transformation\n\nDescription:\n\nShape automation strategy across complex cloud engineering engagements end to end.\n\nAccelerate your growth with world-class training, certifications and mentoring.\n\nWork flexibly while staying connected to clients and your team.\n\nLead the way in building smarter, scalable test automation that helps clients move faster with confidence.\n\nWhat will your typical day look like?\n\nYou will work closely with delivery stakeholders to shape the automation strategy, scope and approach for each engagement. From there, you will assess the client context and architecture, choose the right tools and frameworks, and design automation solutions that are reusable, maintainable and built to scale.\n\nYou will lead a team of 5+ automation testers, setting clear direction, mentoring team members and maintaining high quality standards. You will also collaborate with cross-functional teams to embed automation into CI/CD pipelines, measure automation effectiveness and ROI, and spot opportunities to use AI-driven and agentic AI approaches to improve testing outcomes across engagements.\n\nAbout the team\n\nThis role sits within Deloitte’s Cloud and Engineering Practice, which helps clients unlock the value of transformational technologies to solve complex challenges. You will join a team with deep engineering, delivery and advisory capability, known for collaborative problem-solving, strong coaching and a culture that genuinely enjoys working together.\n\nEnough about us, let\'s talk about you. You may have all or some of the following skills / experiences:\n\nExperience defining automation strategies for different project and client contexts\n\nStrong background selecting automation tools and frameworks based on architecture and scalability\n\nExperience building automation frameworks from scratch across UI, API or hybrid testing\n\nStrong understanding of test architecture, design patterns and maintainability principles\n\nHands-on experience with Playwright, Selenium, Cypress, WebdriverIO, Karate, UiPath, Tricentis Tosca or similar tools\n\nExperience integrating automation into CI/CD pipelines such as Jenkins, GitHub Actions or Azure DevOps\n\nStrong coding skills in Java, JavaScript, TypeScript or Python\n\nLeadership experience managing and mentoring teams of 5+ automation engineers\n\nAbility to define governance, standards and best practices for automation delivery\n\nExperience measuring automation ROI and reporting meaningful outcomes to stakeholders\n\nWhy Deloitte?\n\nAt Deloitte, we focus our energy on interesting and impactful work. We\'re always learning, innovating and setting the standard; making a positive difference to our clients and our society. We put coaching at the heart of what we do, helping our people grow their careers in any direction – whether it be up, moving into something new, or even moving across the world.\n\nWe embrace diversity, equity and inclusion. We have a diverse collection of people from different backgrounds, with different experiences, gender identities, abilities and thinking styles. What binds us together is a shared commitment to value everyone\'s perspective and to cultivate inclusion; so that our work environment is a safe space we can all belong.\n\nWe value in-person connection with our clients and our colleagues. We offer several ways for you to work flexibly so that you can serve your clients, stay connected with your team, and manage your personal priorities.\n\nWe help you live and work well. To support your personal and professional life, we offer a range of perks and benefits, including retail discounts, wellbeing leave, paid volunteering days, twelve flexible working options, market-leading parental leave and return to work support package.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Deloitte','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f87ed753fde7260d','scraped','2 days ago'),(2603,NULL,'job','Digital Strategy Consultants (Technology & Digital Advantage) Melbourne or Sydney Based','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Locations: Melbourne | Sydney\n\nWho We Are\n\nWho We Are Boston Consulting Group partners with leaders in business and society to tackle their most important challenges and capture their greatest opportunities. BCG was the pioneer in business strategy when it was founded in 1963. Today, we help clients with total transformation-inspiring complex change, enabling organizations to grow, building competitive advantage, and driving bottom-line impact.To succeed, organizations must blend digital and human capabilities. Our diverse, global teams bring deep industry and functional expertise and a range of perspectives to spark change. BCG delivers solutions through leading-edge management consulting along with technology and design, corporate and digital ventures-and business purpose. We work in a uniquely collaborative model across the firm and throughout all levels of the client organization, generating results that allow our clients to thrive.\n\nPractice Area\n\nBCG’s Technology and Digital Advantage practice area focuses on helping clients deliver competitive advantage and business superior performance through the use of data, technology and digital. Tech and Digital is the fastest growing practice at BCG and at the heart of the strategic impact we have with our clients. Our consultants and experts globally work across all industries and provide deep experience and expertise across a number of topics including Digital Transformation, Data & Digital Platforms, AI at Scale, Agile, Cybersecurity and Digitizing the Tech Function. Our Tech and Digital offer encompasses tech experts across BCG and Platinion, providing seamless multidisciplinary solutions to our clients.\n\nWhat You\'ll Do\n\nAs a Digital & Technology Consultant, you\'ll be given end-to-end responsibility for the larger and more complex \'modules\' within a BCG project and begin to develop specialised knowledge to help you solve our clients\' problems. You\'ll work on a variety of digital topics, applying generalist consulting skills to strategic digital & technology questions. Working together with clients to understand their issues, you\'ll create strategies for change, win buy-in for your recommendations, and collaborate with fellow BCGers to transform client potential into performance. Our consultants within TDA are an integral part of BCG\'s core consulting team; we work side-by-side with all practice areas to create value and competitive advantage for our clients. You\'ll help your clients answer questions such as \'How will AI disrupt my business model?\', \'How can businesses use data and analytics to create highly personalised outreach delivered through a seamless omnichannel experience\', \'How can I ship higher quality digital services to my customers faster by using agile?\' and many more.\n\nWhat You\'ll Bring\n\nWe\'re looking for exceptional talent from consulting and/or industry. You would typically have:\n\nA minimum of 4 years\' experience working with a leading consulting firm (focused on technology/digital initiatives), in a corporate role focused on strategy/technology/digital initiatives, in a tech start-up strategic role or in a \'consulting-like\' industry (e.g. technology/digital strategy, digital marketing)\nAn outstanding academic track record; a bachelor\'s degree\nThrive in a hypothesis-led environment and ability to frame strategic challenges from a digital/technology perspective\nStrong analytical skills, problem solving ability and conceptual thinking\nExcellent communication, storylining, client facing skills\nFlexibility to travel within ANZ and Asia Pacific region\n\nA broad skillset and passion for digital and technology is important. You\'ll be supported by an extensive training curriculum (the same program all BCG consultants), plus digital-specific training and mentoring to help you build your skills.\n\nAt BCG, we offer multiple career paths for the world\'s best talent to have a real impact on business and society. As part of our team, you will benefit from the breadth and diversity of what we are doing today and where we are headed next. We count on your authenticity, exceptional work, and strong integrity. In return, we are committed to supporting you in discovering the most fulfilling career journey possible - and unlocking your potential to advance the world.\n\nDiversity of thought, background, and experience is a core part of our BCG values and is key to delivering value to clients.\n\nWe are committed to fostering a diverse, equitable, and inclusive environment where everyone feels valued, connected, and empowered to be themselves and contribute to their fullest potential. Applications are encouraged from people of all backgrounds, including people of Aboriginal, Torres straight island, Māori or Pacific Island origin, individuals with a disability, those from culturally or linguistically diverse backgrounds, LGBTIQA+ individuals, women, and gender diverse individuals.\n\nBCG’s efforts toward diversity, equity, and inclusion are recognised locally and globally: BCG Australia and New Zealand hold a WGEA Employer of Choice for Gender Equality citation and are awarded the Australian Workplace Equality Index Silver award for LGBTQIA+ inclusion.We want to make sure everyone experiences a positive, barrier-free recruiting process. Please reach out to Rachael Keating at recruitmentinANZ@bcg.com at any stage if you require additional support or adjustments to assist you with your experience, including support in submitting your application, providing identity documents, attending a job interview. This includes any specific support for transgender and gender-diverse individuals.\n\nBoston Consulting Group is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, age, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity / expression, national origin, disability, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected under national, provincial, or local law, where applicable, and those with criminal histories will be considered in a manner consistent with applicable state and local laws.\nBCG is an E - Verify Employer. Click here for more information on E-Verify.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Boston Consulting Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2f6c356140048143','scraped','2 days ago'),(2604,NULL,'job','Infrastructure Architect - Remote','Permanent','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Who we are\n\nEmployment Hero is on a mission to make employment easier and more valuable for everyone. Our Employment Operating System brings hiring, HR, payroll and benefits into an all-in-one solution.\n\nSince our inception in 2014, we’ve scaled to a $2 billion valuation and gained a presence in 6 countries globally - Australia, New Zealand, Singapore, Malaysia, the UK and Canada. We now service over 300,000 businesses and more than 2 million employees.\n\nThe EH Way\n\nAt Employment Hero, we’re proud of our unique DNA, which we call The EH Way.\n\nWe are Mission First - everything we do (from what we work on, to how we allocate capital and where we focus) is driven by our Mission\nWe are Remote First - we champion a remote environment with a preference for asynchronous communication and a high degree of autonomy\nWe are AI First - we are committed to using AI to accelerate our mission; AI is not just a tool, it’s a fundamental part of how we operate, innovate, and scale\nWe are Apolitical - we do not take a position on political or social topics, unless it relates to our Mission\nWe Live by Our Values - we role model our values 100% of the time\nWe Expect High Performance - we set a high standard and we’re not satisfied with being average\n\nThis role\n\nWe are looking for a skilled and forward-thinking Infrastructure Architect to join our Architecture team. In this role, you will be responsible for designing, reviewing, and evolving secure, scalable, and resilient infrastructure solutions with a strong focus on AWS cloud environments and containerised workloads. You will play a pivotal role in shaping our technical direction, collaborating closely with Application Security and DevOps teams to ensure our platforms meet the highest standards for performance, reliability, and security. You will work alongside an existing Infrastructure Architect within the team, with both roles bringing complementary strengths — the existing architect with a deeper focus on network and platform architecture, and this role bringing specialist expertise in AWS ECS, containerisation, and application-layer infrastructure. The two roles are expected to collaborate closely, share knowledge, and provide input into each other’s designs, with the existing architect offering guidance drawn from their experience in the organisation.\n\nAs an Infrastructure Architect, you will be involved in:\n\nInfrastructure Design & Architecture\n\nLead the design of new cloud infrastructure solutions on AWS, ensuring alignment with scalability, security, and reliability requirements.\nArchitect and document containerised workload platforms using AWS EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service) and AWS ECS (Elastic Container Service) on Linux.\nDevelop and maintain architecture blueprints, decision records (ADRs), and reference architectures.\nDefine infrastructure standards, patterns, and guardrails to guide engineering teams.\n\nReview & Continuous Improvement\n\nConduct architecture reviews of existing systems and infrastructure, identifying risks, gaps, and opportunities for improvement.\nDrive the evolution of legacy infrastructure toward modern, cloud-native patterns.\nEvaluate and recommend new tools, services, and approaches to improve infrastructure maturity.\nEnsure infrastructure designs comply with internal security policies and industry best practices.\n\nCollaboration & Stakeholder Engagement\n\nPartner with Application Security teams to embed security-by-design principles throughout infrastructure architecture.\nWork closely with DevOps teams on platform engineering, CI/CD pipeline design, and automation strategies.\nProvide technical guidance and mentorship to engineers across architecture and infrastructure topics.\nCommunicate complex infrastructure concepts clearly to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.\n\nGovernance & Documentation\n\nMaintain and improve architecture governance processes, including design reviews and approval workflows.\nProduce high-quality documentation including architecture diagrams, runbooks, and technical specifications.\nContribute to the Architecture team\'s knowledge base and communities of practice.\n\nWho you are\n\nTo thrive at Employment Hero, you’ll need to embody The EH Way - operating with focus, agility, and an obsession with impact. For this role, you’ll also bring\n\nRequired Experience & Skills\n\n5+ years of experience in infrastructure architecture, cloud engineering, or a similar senior technical role.\nDeep hands-on expertise with AWS services — particularly networking (VPC, Transit Gateway, Route 53), compute (EC2, Fargate), and storage (S3, EBS, EFS).\nProven experience designing and operating containerised workloads using AWS EKS and/or AWS ECS on Linux.\nStrong knowledge of Kubernetes, including cluster architecture, RBAC, networking (CNI plugins), and workload management.\nProficiency with Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tools such as Terraform and/or AWS CloudFormation.\nUnderstanding of DevSecOps practices and the ability to integrate security controls into infrastructure pipelines.\nExpertise in deploying Threat Detection & Remediation tooling within an AWS environment. The ability to enforce security guardrails across multi-account environments, and a deep knowledge of IAM, Compliance & Monitoring\nExperience with CI/CD tooling (e.g. GitHub Actions) and GitOps workflows.\nSolid Linux systems administration skills.\n\nHighly Regarded\n\nAWS certifications (e.g. Solutions Architect Professional, DevOps Engineer Professional, Security Specialty).\nExperience with service mesh technologies (e.g. Istio, AWS Service Connect).\nFamiliarity with observability tooling (e.g. Datadog, AWS CloudWatch).\nExperience working in regulated industries (e.g. financial services, healthcare) with compliance frameworks such as SOC 2, ISO 27001, or PCI-DSS.\nBackground working in an Architecture chapter or Centre of Excellence (CoE) function.\n\nPersonal Attributes\n\nStrong analytical and problem-solving mindset — you enjoy decomposing complex problems into elegant solutions.\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to create clear, compelling architecture documentation.\nCollaborative by nature — you build effective working relationships across engineering, security, and product teams.\nPragmatic and delivery-focused, balancing technical idealism with real-world constraints.\nA continuous learner who stays current with cloud and infrastructure trends.\n\nWhat we can offer\n\nAt Employment Hero, we don’t just talk about a better way to work - we live it. Joining Employment Hero means\n\nYou will work remotely, with the flexibility to own your time and impact\nYou will access cutting-edge tools to amplify your work, knowledge and outputs\nYou’ll surround yourself with ambitious, outcome-driven colleagues who challenge you to do the best work of your life\nYou’ll own ESOP (employee share options) in one of the world’s fastest-growing tech companies\nYou’ll also have access to a wide range of benefits that includes - a very generous parental leave policy, subsidised egg freezing (so you can make the choice that’s right for you, on your terms), a WFH office expense budget, and outstanding learning & development opportunities\n\nAt Employment Hero, we are committed to safeguarding the privacy of your application data. To understand how we do so, you can read our Applicant Privacy Policy here employmenthero.com/legals/applicant-policy/\n\nEmployment Hero celebrates diverse perspectives and experiences, we invite people of all backgrounds and identities to apply for this position.\n\nCompany Overview\n\nEmployment Hero is the world’s first Employment Operating System: an end-to-end system built to make employment easier for everyone. From hired to retired, everything employment is managed in one place. Employment Hero helps over 300,000 businesses worldwide hire great people and manage everything from hiring, HR and payroll, through to rewards, recognition and offboarding —all automated behind the scenes. And for the 2M+ employees and jobseekers using Employment Hero, Employment OS is their work passport to unlock great job opportunities, manage work admin and grow their career.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=db4f4838d1df2686','scraped','2 days ago'),(2605,NULL,'job','Pathfindr – AI Training Facilitator','Full-time','Melbourne VIC 3000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About Pathfindr\nWe\'re on a mission to help clients improve their business using AI today and prepare for tomorrow by empowering their teams to stay at the forefront of innovation. We are passionate about helping our clients achieve their goals and realise the promise of AI-generated value in their organisations. They are the reason we love to work in AI, and we want to make sure they - and, most importantly, their people - are at the forefront of today\'s rapidly changing technology landscape.\n\nThe role\nAt Pathfindr, we help teams reimagine what’s possible with AI - but to start, we upskill organisations across AAPAC on how to actually use AI tools. Our AI Accelerators combine real-world tools, practical training, and hands-on support to help organisations embed AI capability at every level. Now, we’re looking for facilitators to help us deliver these programs with clarity, energy, and impact.\n\nWe’re looking for a curious, confident communicator who can turn AI concepts into lightbulb moments for teams. You’ll work with our frameworks, pathways, and expert team - then take the lead in shaping and delivering engaging, practical sessions to help achieve adoption. You will become an AI expert, be hungry to learn, comfortable in front of a room, and excited to help people actually use AI tools in their work.\n\nWhat you’ll do\nResearch, design and deliver AI learning sessions for mid-sized and enterprise clients\nTailor content to different industries, roles, and AI maturity levels\nWork with our AI Explorer to bring tools like ChatGPT, Copilot and Gemini to life\nCreate practical resources (cheat sheets, toolkits, exercises)\nShare real-world use cases and keep content fresh\nHelp teams build the confidence and capability to use AI every day\n\nWhat you’ll bring\n2–4 years’ experience in a role involving training or facilitation - e.g. customer onboarding, product enablement, or digital adoption\nComfortable leading sessions in front of a group (in-person and virtual)\nStrong communication skills - make complex ideas simple and engaging\nInterest in AI and willingness to get hands-on with tools quickly\nHungry to grow - you want a role that will stretch and develop you\n\nWho this is not for\nSenior L&D leaders or managers looking for a strategic-only role (this is an executor role and is supported by the business)\nPeople who prefer to stay behind the scenes and avoid facilitation\nThose looking for a slow-paced environment - we move fast\nLack of curiousity about AI and how it can be applied in the workplace\n\nWhat success looks like\nCustomers leave your sessions ready to apply what they’ve learned\nClients see real changes in how people work\nYou’re growing your own skills while helping shape Australia’s most respected AI capability team\n\nCompensation & location\nCompensation:\nFinal package is negotiable based on skills and experience\nLocation:\nMelbourne-based, with national travel for in-person client delivery.\nWe value in office connections with flexible working arrangements\n\nHow to apply\nSubmit in PDF format a short cover letter and your CV\n\nekG1fcbhNP','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Affinda Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=560c0cde26ce7a61','scraped','2 days ago'),(2606,NULL,'job','Pathfindr - Leadership Facilitator & Learning Designer','Full-time','Melbourne VIC 3000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About Pathfindr\nWe\'re on a mission to help clients improve their business using AI today and prepare for tomorrow by empowering their teams to stay at the forefront of innovation. We are passionate about helping our clients achieve their goals and realise the promise of AI-generated value in their organisations. They are the reason we love to work in AI, and we want to make sure they - and, most importantly, their people - are at the forefront of today\'s rapidly changing technology landscape.\n\nThe role\nThis role sits at the intersection of our three leadership-facing workstreams: Activate Leader delivery for enterprise clients, Leadership Cohort program design and facilitation, and internal facilitator development. It reports to the Director of Accelerator and works closely with the CEO on content design and delivery calibration.\n\nThis is a senior, hands-on role that combines facilitation delivery with learning design and internal capability building.\n\nWorkstream 1: Activate Leaders - Enterprise client delivery\nDeliver the leadership layer of our enterprise AI programs. These are in-person sessions for General Managers and senior leaders nominated by the client, run as small interactive groups of approximately 15 attendees.\nCo-deliver Activate Leaders for Enterprise customers with Dawid initially to calibrate on tone, depth, and the Pathfindr way, then transition to solo delivery.\nTailor session content to each client’s context, industry, and audience\nProduce session recordings and supporting resources for each engagement\nContribute to evolving the Activate Leader methodology\n\nWorkstream 2: Leadership Cohort - design and delivery\nCo-design the Leadership Cohort program with CEO, then own the facilitation and ongoing iteration. This is our cohort-based leadership development product – distinct from the Activate Leader masterclasses in that it runs as a structured multi-session program with different companies’ leadership.\nCo-design the Leadership Cohort curriculum, session flow, and participant experience\nOwn facilitation of cohort sessions once the program design is established\nWork with Academy team to develop session materials, facilitation guides, and supporting resources\nIterate on program design based on participant feedback and delivery learnings\n\nFuture Workstream: Internal L&D - facilitator development\nBuild and run Pathfindr’s internal facilitator development capability. As we scale delivery across more clients and programs, we need a structured way to onboard new facilitators into our methodology and continuously develop the existing bench.\nDesign and deliver onboarding for new facilitators joining Pathfindr - covering methodology, session design principles, facilitation standards, and client expectations\nBuild ongoing skill development programming for the existing facilitator bench - including observation, feedback, peer learning, and targeted coaching\nCreate facilitator playbooks, session design templates, and quality standards that codify the Pathfindr way\nIdentify skill gaps across the facilitator team and design interventions to close them\nEstablish a consistent quality bar for facilitation delivery across all programs and clients\n\nWhat you’ll bring\nEssential:\nExecutive presence – experienced at facilitating at GM-and above level audiences\nStrong facilitation craft - you design for interaction, breakout exercises, real-time adaptation\nLearning design capability - you can build a program from a brief, not just deliver someone else’s slides\nEnterprise consulting or corporate L&D experience - you understand how large organisations think, move, and resist change\nExperience developing other facilitators - you’ve coached, observed, given feedback, and lifted the standard of a delivery team\nComfort with ambiguity and evolving content - AI is moving fast and so are we\nNice to have:\nWorking knowledge of AI tools (ChatGPT, Copilot, Claude) and their application in business contexts\nExperience facilitating technology adoption or digital transformation programs\nBackground in change management, organisational development, or leadership coaching\n\nCompensation & location\nCompensation:\nFinal package is negotiable based on skills and experience\nLocation:\nMelbourne-based, with national travel for in-person client delivery.\nWe value in office connections with flexible working arrangements\n\nHow to apply\nSubmit in PDF format a short cover letter and your CV\n\nTMe6PeSzbQ','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Affinda Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ac4a4a52e2ad8f73','scraped','2 days ago'),(2607,NULL,'job','Contract Administrator / Assistant Project Manager','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'JLL empowers you to shape a brighter way.\n\nOur people at JLL are shaping the future of real estate for a better world by combining world class services, advisory and technology for our clients. We are committed to hiring the best, most talented people and empowering them to thrive, grow meaningful careers and to find a place where they belong. Whether you’ve got deep experience in commercial real estate, skilled trades or technology, or you’re looking to apply your relevant experience to a new industry, join our team as we help shape a brighter way forward.\n\nShaping the future of real estate for a better world!\n\nAt JLL, we see a Brighter Way forward for our clients, our people, our planet, and our communities. With over 200 years of real estate experience, we are, and always have been, in continual pursuit of brighter ways of working.\n\n We bring to life see a Brighter Way in all that we do by seeking better, smarter, more innovative ways of working. We approach our work in a warmer, more optimistic, and inclusive way.\n\nAbout Us:\n\nOur Projects and Development Services (PDS) team provide corporate and institutional clients with the management of design, construction, and relocation services to minimise risk and eliminate unnecessary cost.\n\nProjects range from greenfield developments to major fitouts and refurbishments, from single one-off projects to state, national multi-site and regional roll-out projects requiring consistent nationwide delivery.\n\nAs one of the largest project management firms in Australia with a team of over 320 professional staff, we operate in sectors including commercial, industrial, education, data centres, hotels, retail and defence\n\nThe Opportunity:\n\nAs a Contract Administrator – Assistant Project Manager at JLL Design and Build team NSW, you\'ll play a vital role in managing the full lifecycle of client contracts across our diverse real estate portfolio. You\'ll be responsible for drafting, reviewing, and negotiating service agreements while ensuring compliance with company policies and legal requirements. This position requires meticulous attention to detail as you manage both head and subcontract variations, take charge of the subcontractor and supplier claims process in line with our subcontract and HSEQ systems, and demonstrate a strong understanding of SOPA and payment claims. At JLL, we are collectively shaping a brighter way — for our clients, ourselves and our fellow employees — and your contributions will directly support seamless service delivery and strong client relationships. You\'ll manage critical contract finalization tasks including defect management, manual creation, financial disputes, and variation tracking, while working with the team to compile monthly reports that keep projects on track.\n\nWhat sets JLL apart is our culture of collaboration, locally and across the globe, which means you\'ll have the opportunity to work with colleagues and clients across different markets and service lines. We believe the most effective teams are built when everyone is empowered to thrive, and this role offers the chance to develop deep expertise in construction and commercial real estate contracts while contributing to the operational excellence that defines JLL\'s industry leadership.\n\nA snapshot of the role:\n\nManage head contracts and subcontract variations to ensure all changes are properly documented, approved, and executed in accordance with contractual terms\nAdminister the subcontractor and supplier claims process, ensuring compliance with subcontract agreements and HSEQ systems while maintaining accurate records\nProcess SOPA payment claims and related contractual payment obligations in accordance with legislative requirements and company procedures\nCoordinate with finance teams to ensure accurate billing, payment terms, and invoice reconciliation aligned with contractual obligations\nCompile monthly reports on contract status, variation summaries, payment schedules, and key performance indicators for management review\nServe as the primary point of contact for contract-related inquiries from project teams, subcontractors, suppliers, and clients\nSupport procurement processes by evaluating vendor proposals, managing supplier agreements, and ensuring alignment with project specifications\nCoordinate RFI’s and maintain change register (design)\n\nSound like you? This is what we’re looking for:\n\nBachelor\'s degree in Construction, Engineering, Project Management, Business Administration, or related field\n3+ years of commercial experience in contract and financial administration, with demonstrated time working on construction sites\nProven experience administering contracts valued between $1M and $10M, preferably in high-quality office fit-outs, end-of-trip amenities, or retail spaces\nStrong understanding of construction contract law, SOPA legislation, payment claims, and commercial terms\nExceptional organizational abilities and attention to detail with proven capacity to manage multiple contracts and variations simultaneously\nStrong analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to assess risk and recommend mitigation strategies\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills with the ability to work effectively across project teams and with diverse stakeholders\n\nWhat you can expect from us:\n\nYou’ll join an entrepreneurial, inclusive culture. One where the best inspires the best. Where like-minded people work naturally together to achieve great things. Join us to develop your strengths and enjoy a fulfilling career full of varied experiences. Keep those ambitions in sight and imagine where JLL can take you.\n\n As an organisation, we don’t just accept that we are a place of many different people, but we embrace it, we celebrate it, and we proactively support the needs that difference brings. JLL is committed to equal opportunity regardless of race, gender, age, sexual orientation, or disability, and that is why, for more than a decade, we continue to rank among the World’s Most Ethical Companies. We are dedicated to offering veterans from all ranks and services a successful civilian career as they transition out of the military. We recognise and appreciate the skills acquired in their service careers as vital and transferable to our workforce.\n\nLocation:\n\nOn-site –Sydney, NSW\n\nIf this job description resonates with you, we encourage you to apply even if you don’t meet all of the requirements. We’re interested in getting to know you and what you bring to the table!\n\nAt JLL, we harness the power of artificial intelligence (AI) to efficiently accelerate meaningful connections between candidates and opportunities. Using AI capabilities, we analyze your application for relevant skills, experiences, and qualifications to generate valuable insights about how your unique profile aligns with the specific requirements of the role you\'re pursuing.\n\nJLL Privacy Notice\n\nJones Lang LaSalle (JLL), together with its subsidiaries and affiliates, is a leading global provider of real estate and investment management services. We take our responsibility to protect the personal information provided to us seriously. Generally the personal information we collect from you are for the purposes of processing in connection with JLL’s recruitment process. We endeavour to keep your personal information secure with appropriate level of security and keep for as long as we need it for legitimate business or legal reasons. We will then delete it safely and securely.\n\nFor more information about how JLL processes your personal data, please view our Candidate Privacy Statement.\n\nFor additional details please see our career site pages for each country.\n\nJones Lang LaSalle (“JLL”) is an Equal Opportunity Employer and is committed to working with and providing reasonable accommodations to individuals with disabilities. If you need a reasonable accommodation because of a disability for any part of the employment process – including the online application and/or overall selection process – you may email us at HRSCLeaves@jll.com. This email is only to request an accommodation. Please direct any other general recruiting inquiries to our Contact Us page > I want to work for JLL.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'DAB-Jones Lang LaSalle (NSW) Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9248ed3c766b1aa6','scraped','2 days ago'),(2608,NULL,'job','Customer Success and Enablement Lead','Full-time','Perth WA 6000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We power insights for better, safer workplaces…together.\n\nAre you ready to be Kin-at-i-can? As our Customer Success and Enablement Lead, you will own the full journey from customer sign-on to confident, measurable value. This is a builder role: you will establish the foundational processes, content, and frameworks from the ground up, creating scalable approaches for future growth while personally delivering outcomes that drive retention, expansion, and advocacy.\n\nOUR TEAM’S STRENGTH COMES FROM EVERYONE’S INDIVIDUALITY\n\nAbout Kinatico:\n\nKinatico is an ASX-listed Reg-Tech company revolutionising people management workflow. Our background screening platform, Kinatico CVCheck, has served over 10,000 organisations and helped more than 1.6 million individuals meet regulatory requirements. Our newest product, Kinatico Compliance, gives organisations everything they need to manage workforce compliance in one centralised place, from automated workflows and credential tracking to proactive alerts and seamless HRIS integration. We move quickly, think commercially, and back each other.\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BRING\n\nYou are a self-directed professional who thrives on building structure in dynamic environments. You bring a genuine mix of customer empathy, digital learning expertise, and commercial instinct, and you understand adult learning theory, design content that drives real behaviour change, and use data and predictive models to continuously improve. You bring:\n\n5 or more years in platform enablement, customer success, implementation management, or delivery leadership, with a track record of executing programs at scale\nExperience managing complex, enterprise-level platform implementations, working cross-functionally with Sales, Product, Technology, and Executive teams\nStrong analytical skills with the ability to map the customer journey, identify friction points, and make evidence-based improvements\nThe coordination and delivery experience to manage competing priorities in a fast-moving environment\n\nIt would be great if you also have:\n\nInstructional design, learning design, or adult education qualifications\nSaaS, HRIS, HCM, compliance, or workforce management domain experience\nExperience in early-stage or high-growth technology companies and enthusiasm for AI-powered learning and emerging enablement technologies\n\nDELIVERING THE GOOD, STRIVING FOR THE GREAT\n\nThis is a hands-on role with real scope. You will combine customer advocacy with practical enablement expertise, working across customers, sales, product, and technology teams to deliver outcomes that matter. Here is what you will be doing:\n\nDesign and own the end-to-end customer activation journey that drives rapid time-to-value, leading platform implementation from discovery through to go-live, UAT oversight, and milestone tracking for enterprise customers (200+ users), and acting as the key point of escalation for platform-related delivery matters\nBuild and maintain a sales team that knows the product inside out, through regular training, quarterly certifications, individual coaching, and observation on sales calls, tracking and reporting on demonstration effectiveness\nDesign and deliver comprehensive sales enablement programs covering demonstration frameworks, competitive positioning, use-case storytelling, battle cards, ROI calculators, objection handling guides, and first call deck frameworks\nLead high-stakes customer and investor demonstrations in partnership with sales and executive teams, supporting discovery workshops and focus groups to understand client requirements and accelerate deal velocity\nIncrease win rates and protect revenue by ensuring every customer achieves value from day one, identifying upsell and cross-sell opportunities, and preventing early churn\nCreate interactive learning content including video tutorials, product tours, and embedded in-app guidance, and develop a best-in-class documentation strategy that makes complex compliance concepts immediately actionable\nGenerate pipeline through customer advocacy, case studies, and reference relationships, and collaborate with Marketing to leverage activation success stories for demand generation\nPartner with Product to embed activation thinking into release cycles, influence the roadmap with customer data and adoption insights, and work with Sales on pre-sales enablement that sets accurate expectations and accelerates post-sale time-to-value\n\nARE YOU READY TO BE A KINATICAN?\n\nWhere our passion, talent, delivery and impact collide, our purpose lives. We power insights for better, safer workplaces, helping organisations truly know their people. We are a global leader in Reg-Tech, and we are just getting started.\n\nFlexible working\nA team that genuinely invests in your growth, with regular development conversations and real room to own your career path\nFriday Funaticans: our weekly team ritual for connecting, in person at our Perth CBD office or online wherever you are\nRecognition that means something: from KinatiKudos shoutouts to a culture that celebrates wins big and small\nA purpose-led mission you will feel every day: our technology helps keep workplaces safer and more compliant\nThe stability of an ASX-listed company with the energy of a high-growth Reg-Tech business\n\nAt Kinatico, we believe the best teams are built from diverse perspectives and growth mindsets. Research shows that while men apply to roles when they meet around 60% of the criteria, women and other underrepresented groups often wait until they tick every box. If you are excited about this role but do not meet every requirement, we still want to hear from you. Let’s have a chat and explore the possibilities.\n\nApply Now!','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Kinatico','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=215eef9a03ef6a96','scraped','2 days ago'),(2609,NULL,'job','Client Technical Support','','Blenheim Road NSW 2113',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Let’s be unstoppable together!\n\nAt Circana, we are fuelled by our passion for continuous learning and growth, we seek and share feedback freely, and we celebrate victories both big and small in an environment that is flexible and accommodating to our work and personal lives. We have a global commitment to diversity, equity, and inclusion as we believe in the undeniable strength that diversity brings to our business, employees, clients, and communities. With us, you can always bring your full self to work. Join our inclusive, committed team to be a challenger, own outcomes, and stay curious together.\n\nCircana is proud to be Certified™ by Great Place To Work®. This prestigious award is based entirely on what current employees say about their experience working at Circana.\n\nLearn more at www.circana.com.\n\nSo, why Circana?\n\nWe’re progressive, inclusive and people focused. We seek to create a down-to-earth culture which balances work and home life and enables our team to be the best that it can be. Our people are important to us, and we offer a number of fantastic benefits including;\n\nFlexible and hybrid working\nUp to 5 weeks annual leave and holiday buy back scheme\n16 weeks paid parental leave\nBirthday leave\nSummer half days\nCircana “Me” Days (4 per year!)\nCultural swap days\n\nWhat will you be doing?\n\nThis role sits at the heart of delivering an outstanding client experience. You will be the go to expert for helping internal and external customers solve AI driven technical challenges and get the best out of Circana’s products and services. You will troubleshoot issues, simplify complex concepts, and turn challenges into wins for our clients.\n\nBy responding quickly and thoughtfully, you will help build lasting partnerships and high levels of customer satisfaction. You will also work closely with cross functional teams to continually improve service quality and shape a seamless end to end client experience.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nAct as the first point of contact for clients, diagnosing and resolving issues across AI solutions including model performance, integrations, and configuration challenges\nPartner with clients to help them get the most from AI products by sharing best practices for setup, customisation, and ongoing optimisation\nOwn support requests end to end by tracking, prioritising, and resolving tickets efficiently, with clear escalation to L2 and L3 teams when required\nMonitor AI applications and data pipelines for errors, anomalies, or outages, taking proactive action to prevent client impact\nDevelop and maintain clear, helpful resources such as knowledge base articles, troubleshooting guides, FAQs, and client training materials\nCapture client insights and feedback and collaborate with product and engineering teams to influence enhancements and future feature development\nAssist with validating bug fixes, patches, and product updates to ensure a reliable and high-quality experience before release to clients\nGuide clients on data preparation, formatting, preprocessing, and best practices for security and compliance when working with AI tools\nWork closely with product managers, engineers, and customer success teams to resolve issues, improve services, and deliver exceptional client outcomes\n\nRequirements\n\nBachelor’s degree in computer science, information technology, engineering, or a related field preferred\nPrevious experience in technical support, help desk, or client success roles, ideally within SaaS, enterprise, or AI driven products\nStrong problem solving skills, with experience diagnosing issues across applications, APIs, and system integrations\nFoundational knowledge of AI concepts, cloud platforms, and APIs, with a strong interest in how these technologies are applied\nFamiliarity with AI systems, natural language processing tools, or machine learning based products\nExperience using tools such as Jira, Confluence, CRM platforms, or similar bug tracking and documentation systems\nFamiliarity with Circana tools, including Unify+, model and report building, and ideally Emiri, with prior experience considered a strong advantage\nExcellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to clearly explain technical concepts to non technical audiences\nConfidence creating clear documentation, including FAQs, support articles, and knowledge base content\nBilingual capability is a plus, particularly English with Spanish, German, or Italian\nProven ability to manage multiple client priorities with professionalism, organisation, and efficiency\nFlexibility to work across different time zones, shifts, or on call rotations when required\nA genuine passion for technology, combined with curiosity and a desire to continuously learn about emerging AI tools and trends\n\nCircana Behaviours\n\nAs well as the technical skills, experience and attributes that are required for the role, our shared behaviours sit at the core of our organization. Therefore, we always look for people who can continuously champion these behaviours throughout the business within their day-to-day role:\n\nStay Curious: Being hungry to learn and grow, always asking the big questions\nSeek Clarity: Embracing complexity to create clarity and inspire action\nOwn the Outcome: Being accountable for decisions and taking ownership of our choices\nCentre on the Client: Relentlessly adding value for our customers\nBe a Challenger: Never complacent, always striving for continuous improvement\nChampion Inclusivity: Fostering trust in relationships engaging with empathy, respect and integrity\n Commit to each other: Contributing to making Circana a great place to work for everyone\n\nReady to make an impact?\n\nIf you’re passionate about solving complex technical problems with AI, thrive in a collaborative environment, and want to be part of a company that truly values your growth, we’d love to hear from you. Apply now and let’s build something great together.\n\nIf you require accessibility support or would like to request reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process, we encourage you to reach out to us at accessibility@circana.com\n\nProspective candidates may be asked to consent to background checks (in accordance with local legislation and our candidate privacy notice). Your current employer will not be contacted without your permission.\n\n#LI-JM2','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'IRI Worldwide (Australia)','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1d0fc6cb1511846c','scraped','2 days ago'),(2610,NULL,'job','Customer Account Manager','Full-time','Perth WA',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'See what you can do with Prophix\n\nProphix helps finance teams work smarter and reduce busywork through Prophix One™, our Financial Performance Platform. We bring planning, reporting, and automation together so people can focus on meaningful work instead of repetitive tasks. As we introduce more AI-enabled capabilities, you will join a team where modern tools support better outcomes and people guide the decisions that matter.\n\nWe have teams and offices across the UK, Europe, North America, and Australia.\n\nAs a Customer Account Manager at Prophix, you\'ll take ownership of a portfolio of existing customers across your territory — building senior-level relationships and uncovering meaningful opportunities to grow the Prophix footprint through license expansions and cloud migrations. You\'ll work closely with customers as their primary Prophix contact, partnering internally with teams across Professional Services, Customer Success, Sales, and more to deliver real value. This is a role for a commercially minded relationship-builder who thrives on turning strong customer connections into measurable business outcomes.\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\nOwn and grow a portfolio of existing customer accounts, identifying and closing expansion opportunities including license add-ons and on-premise to cloud migrations\nProspect daily within your customer base to uncover new revenue opportunities and keep your pipeline active and accurate\nServe as the primary point of contact for your accounts, building trusted relationships at the senior level (CFO, CIO, VP Finance) and ensuring customers achieve ongoing value from Prophix\'s solutions\nManage complex, multi-stakeholder sales cycles by collaborating with Professional Services, the Cloud Team, Direct Sales, Legal, Customer Support, and Customer Success\nDeliver timely account plans, renewal forecasts, and CRM updates in Salesforce.com that give sales leadership clear visibility into your territory\nPartner with internal teams to design and execute marketing campaigns and customer enablement programs that deepen engagement within the customer base\nEscalate significant opportunities and customer concerns through the right channels, ensuring nothing falls through the cracks\n\nRequirements\n\nWhat You Will Bring\n\nIf this role excites you, but you don’t meet every requirement, we still encourage you to apply. At Prophix, curiosity, adaptability, and diverse perspectives matter. Your experience may be exactly what we need.\n\nRequired Qualifications\n\nA mix of experience, training, or education that helps you succeed in this role.\n3–5 years of direct or customer-facing software sales experience; CPM or Fintech Software background preferred\nDemonstrated track record of meeting or exceeding sales performance targets\nHands-on experience with CRM platforms as a user, specifically Salesforce.com\nAdvanced working knowledge of Microsoft Office Suite\nSolid understanding of both on-premise and cloud business models\nExcellent communication and presentation skills, with proven ability to engage and influence senior stakeholders\nComfortable using AI tools responsibly to support day-to-day tasks such as research, drafting, or data review\nCurious and adaptable — open to learning new tools and approaches as technology evolves\nCollaborative by nature, with the ability to work effectively across teams and alongside technology\nMust be legally entitled to work in Australia\nComfort using AI tools responsibly to support tasks such as research, drafting, or data review\nAbility to learn new tools and adapt as technology evolves\nCuriosity and openness to exploring new approaches\nCollaborative mindset when working with teams and technology\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\nWorking knowledge of CPM software and how it supports financial planning and reporting processes\nAcademic or practical understanding of accounting and financial concepts such as planning, budgeting, forecasting, or consolidation\nStrong negotiation skills with experience navigating complex deal structures\nProven ability to manage multiple priorities, accounts, and deadlines in a fast-moving environment\nExceptional presentation skills with the ability to clearly articulate a value proposition to finance and technology leaders\n\nBenefits\n\nWhat Success Looks Like\n\n30 days: You understand our tools, product, and people\nWithin 90 days: You work independently on meaningful tasks\nWithin 6 months: You contribute ideas, improvements, and measurable impact\n\nWhy Join Prophix?\n\nProphix builds technology that helps organisations plan, forecast, and make better decisions with confidence. You will collaborate with colleagues across regions, contribute to a platform used globally, and grow your skills through hands-on experience and AI-enabled tools. Flexibility is supported depending on team needs and location, and our work is guided by our values: Pursue Excellence, Build with Purpose, Create Wins for All, and Drive Continuous Innovation.\n\nWhat’s Included for You?\n\nA work environment that offers flexibility\nPartial reimbursement for gym membership, home broadband, home office equipment, and mobile phone plans\nFinancial assistance for career-related training\nPaid leave that complies with Australian employment standards, along with additional company leave benefits\nSocial gatherings and opportunities to engage with coworkers\nChances to participate in Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) initiatives\nQuarterly Town Halls and Kickoff meetings that unite teams to celebrate achievements, share updates, and discuss future plans\n\nApply Now!\n\nIf this feels like the right environment for you, we’d love to meet you and help you build your career as a Phixer!\n\nAccessibility & AI Transparency\n\nProphix promotes an accessible hiring process. If you need accommodation at any stage, we’ll work with you. Some interviews may be recorded so our hiring team can review and assess responses fairly and consistently. As part of our commitment to Responsible AI, we use a small number of AI-supported tools to help with tasks like resume review, shortlisting, or creating interview summaries. AI is never used as the sole basis for hiring decisions, and your personal data is never used to train AI models. If you\'d prefer not to take part in any AI-assisted step, just let us know and we’ll be happy to accommodate.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Prophix','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1e2116e72a2731b0','scraped','2 days ago'),(2611,NULL,'job','Manager Intelligent Automation Engineering','Permanent','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We are seeking a Technical Lead to join our Agentic Automation team and work with our clients to deliver high-quality automation. You will be responsible for leading client engagements and managing a team of consultants to deliver high-quality services. You will work closely with leaders in the agentic automation division to develop and implement strategies to drive growth and profitability.\n\n*Responsibilities & tasks for this role*\n\n* Lead the analysis, design, development, testing, and deployment of agentic automation solutions.\n* Lead and train a team of developers to deliver agentic automation solutions.\n* Oversee end-to-end project delivery, ensuring quality, timeliness, and client satisfaction.\n* Act as the primary point of contact for clients, building strong, trust-based relationships.\n* Identify business development opportunities and support proposal and pre-sales efforts.\n* Drive continuous improvement in delivery processes, methodologies, and team capabilities.\n* Stay current with emerging technologies (e.g., agentic AI, etc.) and translate them into client value.\n\n*Must-have qualifications & competencies*\n\n* Minimum of 4 years of experience in automation\n* Proven track record of managing client engagements and developing strong client relationships\n* Knowledgeable in at least one area of consulting, such as strategy, operations, technology, or finance\n* Strong team leadership skills, with the ability to motivate and develop team members.\n* Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to build and maintain strong client relationships\n* Bachelors degree in a relevant field, with an MBA or other advanced degree preferred\n\nJob Types: Full-time, Permanent\n\nWork Location: Hybrid remote in Sydney NSW 2000','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Procensol Australia - A Roboyo Group Company','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=58788edc32da4657','scraped','2 days ago'),(2612,NULL,'job','Full Stack AI Principal Engineer','','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About V2 AI\n\nV2 AI is a leading AI-Native consultancy backed by $30m in VC funding, allowing us to meet our customers\' needs. We harness the power of AI to accelerate business outcomes for some of the world\'s largest brands. We bring decades of experience and a unique delivery model to partner with our customers on the most complex problems for immense, measurable impact.\n\nOur Services\n\nAI Strategy & Governance\nAI Literacy & Enablement\nAI Build & Assurance\nAI & Data Security\n\nAbout the Role\nAs a Principal Full Stack AI Engineer, you will lead the design, architecture, and delivery of production-ready AI applications at scale. You’ll own full stack projects using React and Node.js, integrating cutting-edge AI/ML solutions, and deploying robust, scalable cloud architectures on AWS. You’ll collaborate closely with product teams, architects, and engineers to deliver complex solutions, including GenAI applications, LLM integrations, and agent-based systems.\n\nIn this role, you will also mentor engineers, influence technical strategy, and help shape engineering standards and best practices across V2 AI, driving technical excellence across the organisation.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nDefine the architecture and technical direction for full stack AI applications across multiple teams.\nDrive the integration of AI/ML solutions, including LLMs, embeddings, and agent frameworks, into scalable production systems.\nSet standards and best practices for full stack development, cloud architecture, and AI workflows across the organization.\nCollaborate with product, AI, data, and architecture teams to shape technical strategy, design patterns, and project roadmaps.\nAdvise and mentor engineering leaders and senior engineers, influencing architecture decisions, code quality, and AI implementation strategies.\nOversee LLMOps frameworks, including prompt management, model pipelines, versioning, monitoring, and optimization.\nGuide the use of unstructured data (text, image, video, audio) to enable advanced AI-driven capabilities.\nChampion reusable libraries, frameworks, and organization-wide engineering standards.\nStay at the forefront of AI, cloud, and full stack technologies, driving innovation and sharing insights internally and externally.\n\nAbout You:\n\nExtensive experience designing and delivering full stack AI applications at a Principal Leadership level.\nDeep expertise with React, Node.js, and scalable cloud architectures across AWS and Azure, including services such as Bedrock, Lambda, ECS/EKS, SageMaker, and Azure AI/ML equivalents.\nHands-on understanding of AI/ML integration, including LLMs, embeddings, RAG workflows, and agent-based systems.\nProven experience with data platforms and pipelines, including Snowflake, Databricks, and other modern data ecosystems.\nStrong background in cloud architecture, distributed systems, and performance optimization.\nSkilled at defining technical strategy, setting architecture standards, and driving engineering best practices across teams and the organization.\nExperience mentoring engineering leaders and influencing technical decisions across multiple projects.\nPassionate about innovation, high-quality code, reusable frameworks, and organization-wide technical excellence.\nExcellent communicator and collaborator, able to translate complex technical concepts for stakeholders across engineering, product, and executive teams.\n\nWhat You Will Get:\n\nCompetitive salary package\nPick your equipment\nGifted Day Off (\"VersionUp Day\")\nGenerous parental leave\nWell-funded startup environment\nAnnual training budget\nMentorship program\nClear promotion pathways\nFlexible working arrangements\nMeet-ups & socials\n97% rating on corporate social responsibility\n\nApply Now:\nIf you’re passionate about leading AI-powered full stack projects, building scalable applications, and shaping the future of AI consulting, APPLY NOW and join V2 AI!','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'V2 Digital','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=eb37af3835b3a371','scraped','2 days ago'),(2613,NULL,'job','AI Engineer','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nBilue is a digital consultancy that designs and builds smart, user-friendly technology for some of Australia’s most well-known businesses. From mobile apps to beautifully designed web platforms and digital experiences, we create solutions that drive impact and deliver exceptional customer outcomes.\n\nOur culture is people-first and purpose-driven. We’re a down-to-earth, values-led team with offices in Sydney and Melbourne, and a growing presence in Manila. We genuinely enjoy working together, whether we’re solving tough tech problems, brainstorming creative solutions, or grabbing a coffee between meetings. Curiosity is encouraged. Collaboration is second nature.\n\nWe value excellence, not ego, and back each other to do great work without micromanagement. With low politics and high trust, it’s a place where delivery people, designers, and engineers genuinely connect, and where everyone has a voice, space to grow, and a little fun along the way.\n\nJob Description\n\nThe Role\n\nWe’re looking for an AI Engineer to join The Foundry and work at the intersection of client delivery and internal capability building. This is a hands-on engineering role where you’ll design, build, and ship production-grade AI systems for Bilue’s clients across financial services, government, insurance, and retail — while simultaneously contributing to the reference architectures, tooling, and engineering standards that define how AI Labs operates.\n\nThis isn’t a research role. It’s not a prompt-engineering role. You’ll be building agentic systems that survive contact with real users, integrating AI into enterprise environments, and setting the quality bar for what “production-grade” means at Bilue.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nClient Delivery (The Foundry)\n\nDesign and build production-grade AI solutions including agentic systems, memory systems, LLM-powered features, and intelligent automation for enterprise clients.\n\nArchitect cloud-native AI systems on AWS, Azure, or GCP with robust DevOps/LLMOps pipelines for scalability and reliability.\n\nIntegrate AI capabilities into existing enterprise platforms (CRM, ERP, lending systems, claims platforms) through well-designed APIs and data pipelines (leveraging AI of course).\n\nLead AI technical delivery within cross-functional squads alongside designers, strategists, and client stakeholders — translating complex AI concepts into high-impact outcomes.\n\nImplement responsible AI practices including red-teaming, bias testing, evaluation harnesses, and human-in-the-loop design before anything ships.\n\nInternal Capability (The AI Foundry)\n\nContribute to Bilue’s reference architectures for common delivery patterns: knowledge/context pipelines, agentic systems, LLM integrations, and evaluation frameworks.\n\nHelp define and evolve engineering standards for AI Labs work — code quality, testing approaches, prompt evaluation frameworks, and what “production-grade” means in practice.\n\nBuild reusable tooling, accelerators, and “skills” that make the next project faster and more reliable.\n\nParticipate in model evaluation, cost optimisation, and architecture reviews that sharpen Bilue’s technical edge.\n\nShare knowledge across the engineering team through documentation, tech talks, and hands-on mentoring.\n\nQualifications\n\nExperience & Mindset\n\nDemonstrable experience delivering AI or GenAI solutions in a production environment — not just prototypes or demos.\n\nStrong problem-solving ability and the analytical mindset to work with ambiguous, evolving requirements.\n\nThe ability to communicate technical concepts clearly to non-technical stakeholders and client executives.\n\nGenuine systems thought leadership — you understand why the system matters, not just how it works.\n\nA collaborative, low-ego approach, working across teams, clients, and contexts with adaptability.\n\nComfort operating in a fast moving environment where you’ll work across multiple clients and industries.\n\nStrong opinions, weakly held - curious mind with the ability to rapidly evolve when faced with contradictory evidence.\n\nTechnical Skills\n\nStrong programming skills in Python; familiarity with TypeScript or Java is a plus.\n\nHands-on experience with AI and agentic frameworks — LangChain, AgentCore , LlamaIndex, LangGraph, CrewAI, vector databases, or similar.\n\nWorking expertise with cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, or GCP)\n\nSolid understanding of data engineering fundamentals — SQL, ETL/ELT, distributed systems, handling large and unstructured datasets.\n\nExperience designing and deploying production AI systems with proper observability, monitoring, and evaluation.\n\nFamiliarity with LLMOps practices — prompt versioning, model drift detection, cost monitoring, A/B evaluation.\n\nUnderstanding of RESTful APIs, microservices, and enterprise integration patterns.\n\nBonus Points\n\nExperience with the AWS AI/ML stack (Bedrock, AgentCore, Strands, SageMaker, Lambda, Step Functions).\n\nFamiliarity with responsible AI frameworks, bias testing tools, or AI governance practices.\n\nPrior consulting or hyper-scaler experience where you’ve delivered for external clients under real constraints.\n\nContributions to open-source AI projects, AI research, or published technical writing.\n\nAdditional Information\n\nLife at Bilue\n\nPeople-first focus: We’re committed to delivering exceptional outcomes for our clients, but we know it starts with our people. You’ll join a values-led team that’s collaborative, curious, and genuinely cares about doing great work, together.\n\nConnection that counts: From monthly anchor days and team lunches to our annual offsite, we create intentional moments to connect, collaborate, and celebrate. These aren’t just fun perks — they’re part of how we work and grow together.\n\nFlexibility that works: We offer hybrid working, with 1–2 days per week in the office. It’s a balance that gives you the space to do your best work, while still creating time to connect and build strong relationships in person.\n\nStrong internal communities: We actively foster internal communities across tech, design, delivery, and beyond, giving you plenty of chances to connect, share knowledge, and learn from your peers.\n\nOpportunities to grow: We invest in your development with unlimited access to Go1’s learning library and support from our internal performance coach. Whether you want to deepen your technical skills or grow your leadership potential, we’ll back you.\n\nFlat structure, real impact: At Bilue, everyone’s voice matters. Our leadership team is hands-on and approachable, and we operate without unnecessary layers. We keep things open and transparent, and your ideas will be heard, no matter your title.\n\nBilue = Big + Blue Ocean. Are you ready to set sail? Apply now!\n\nNB. This is a full-time position based in Sydney, NSW or Melbourne, VIC. To be considered, candidates must have unrestricted working rights in Australia.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Bilue','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=438724604d7a491c','scraped','2 days ago'),(2614,NULL,'job','SDR Performance Coach (Sales Enablement)','Permanent','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Who we are\n\nEmployment Hero is on a mission to make employment easier and more valuable for everyone. Our Employment Operating System brings hiring, HR, payroll and benefits into an all-in-one solution.\n\nSince our inception in 2014, we’ve scaled to a $2 billion valuation and gained a presence in 6 countries globally - Australia, New Zealand, Singapore, Malaysia, the UK and Canada. We now service over 300,000 businesses and more than 2 million employees.\n\nThe EH Way\n\nAt Employment Hero, we’re proud of our unique DNA, which we call The EH Way.\n\nWe are Mission First - everything we do (from what we work on, to how we allocate capital and where we focus) is driven by our Mission\nWe are Remote First - we champion a remote environment with a preference for asynchronous communication and a high degree of autonomy\nWe are AI First - we are committed to using AI to accelerate our mission; AI is not just a tool, it’s a fundamental part of how we operate, innovate, and scale\nWe are Apolitical - we do not take a position on political or social topics, unless it relates to our Mission\nWe Live by Our Values - we role model our values 100% of the time\nWe Expect High Performance - we set a high standard and we’re not satisfied with being average\nWhat we need\n\nWe’re looking for SDR Sales Enablement Coach to drive performance coaching for our AU-based SDR team, across Micro, Core, and Mid-Market segments in both Inbound and Outbound. In this role, you’ll act as a hands-on coach and quality champion — spending your time in the field running 1:1 sessions, shadowing live calls and reviewing recorded calls, and quickly identifying and addressing performance gaps.\n\nYour mission is to elevate SDR performance by coaching to best-in-class standards and improving funnel metrics like MQL-to-SAO conversion, connect rates, demo sit rates, and revenue. You’ll drive excellence by lifting both quantity (activity, connect rates, pipeline coverage) and quality (targeting, messaging, and CRM discipline). This role is truly unique as you will be working in tandem with SDR managers and alongside a team of Performance Coaches developing reps skills, mindset and consistency to influence revenue. SDRs at Employment Hero are some of the most commercially astute and get the rare challenge to own deep discovery.\n\nAt Employment Hero, we believe SDRs are revenue influencers. This role will help embed that belief across the business. By setting clear standards, optimising processes, and coaching relentlessly, you’ll help reps balance high-volume activity with relevant, high-impact conversations. Your work will fuel pipeline growth, strengthen conversion rates, and scale a high-performing SDR engine.\n\nWe are open to candidates based in New Zealand OR Australia for this role.\n\nKey responsibilities\n\n1:1 Tactical Coaching & Performance Enablement:\n\nConduct regular 1:1 coaching sessions, live call shadowing, and structured roleplays.\nDeliver real-time feedback on messaging, objection handling, and conversion techniques.\nTrack and optimise funnel performance across MQL-to-SAO conversion, call to connect, connect to opportunity, demo sit rates, and revenue growth.\n\nSDR Quality Assurance & Workflow Uplift:\n\nAudit SDR calls and CRM hygiene to maintain a consistently high standard of execution, ensuring process adherence.\nIdentify performance bottlenecks using data and resolve through coaching or process change.\nCollaborate with Ops to improve workflows, sequences, and data accuracy.\nWork closely with SDR Managers to align coaching with performance needs.\n\nChannel Growth:\n\nStandardise SDR workflows against top-tier industry benchmarks and sales practices.\nDevelop SDRs’ proficiency in product knowledge, objection handling, and closing techniques.\nEmbed best practices in prospecting and lead qualification aligned with our SPICED sales methodology.\nFoster knowledge retention and continuous development through coaching initiatives.\n\nCollaborate & Commercial Impact\n\nWork closely with SDR Managers to support team coaching and performance goals.\nAlign strategy with GTM initiatives, product launches, and campaign priorities.\nChampion a culture of high performance, growth mindset, and measurable impact.\nAct as a force multiplier by amplifying strategic initiatives across Inbound and Outbound.\nWhat you’ll bring\nCommercial Acumen. You’re focused on what drives pipeline and revenue.\nExecution Mastery. You simplify complex problems and deliver results, fast.\nChange Driver. You turn ambiguity into opportunity and lead through change.\nForce Multiplier. You amplify Enablement’s impact, scaling what works.\nResults-Obsessed. You track, test, and improve relentlessly.\nWhat we’re looking for\nProven success coaching or leading Inbound and Outbound SDR teams, ideally in SaaS or tech scale-ups (essential)\nDeep understanding of Outbound pipeline generation and SDR performance levers\nStrong track record improving activity and conversion metrics\nFamiliarity with tools such as LinkedIn Sales Navigator, ZoomInfo, 6sense, Outreach, Spekit, Confluence, and Salesforce (preferred)\nSkilled in delivering feedback and coaching across all experience levels\nComfortable operating at both tactical and strategic levels in a fast-moving environment\nData-driven decision maker with a passion for scaling repeatable, high-impact sales motions\nStrong alignment to commercial goals and the ability to drive cross-functional outcomes\nAble to interpret data to diagnose performance gaps and pull the right levers to positively impact sales performance metrics\nCollaborative mindset, working well with cross-functional teams to drive outcomes\nWhat we can offer\n\nAt Employment Hero, we don’t just talk about a better way to work - we live it. Joining Employment Hero means\n\nYou will work remotely, with the flexibility to own your time and impact\nYou will access cutting-edge tools to amplify your work, knowledge and outputs\nYou’ll surround yourself with ambitious, outcome-driven colleagues who challenge you to do the best work of your life\nYou’ll own ESOP (employee share options) in one of the world’s fastest-growing tech companies\nYou’ll also have access to a wide range of benefits that includes - a very generous parental leave policy, subsidised egg freezing (so you can make the choice that’s right for you, on your terms), a WFH office expense budget, and outstanding learning & development opportunities\nAnnual Global Gathering - so far we’ve been to Thailand, Vietnam, Bali, Dubai and are excited to meet in Gold Coast in Australia in September 2026\n\nWe’re AI-first, so you may meet some of our AI tools early in the process. They help us cut the noise, surface great talent fast and make sure every candidate gets a fair, consistent experience.\n\nWe verify candidate identity and location as part of our hiring process.\n\nAt Employment Hero, we are committed to safeguarding the privacy of your application data. To understand how we do so, you can read our Applicant Privacy Policy here employmenthero.com/legals/applicant-policy/\n\nEmployment Hero celebrates diverse perspectives and experiences, we invite people of all backgrounds and identities to apply for this position.\n\nCompany Overview\n\nEmployment Hero is the world’s first Employment Operating System: an end-to-end system built to make employment easier for everyone. From hired to retired, everything employment is managed in one place. Employment Hero helps over 300,000 businesses worldwide hire great people and manage everything from hiring, HR and payroll, through to rewards, recognition and offboarding —all automated behind the scenes. And for the 2M+ employees and jobseekers using Employment Hero, Employment OS is their work passport to unlock great job opportunities, manage work admin and grow their career.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c1ef77f84b8b5eb4','scraped','2 days ago'),(2615,NULL,'job','AI Data Engineer (Librarian)','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nBilue is a digital consultancy that designs and builds smart, user-friendly technology for some of Australia’s most well-known businesses. From mobile apps to beautifully designed web platforms and digital experiences, we create solutions that drive impact and deliver exceptional customer outcomes.\n\nOur culture is people-first and purpose-driven. We’re a down-to-earth, values-led team with offices in Sydney and Melbourne, and a growing presence in Manila. We genuinely enjoy working together, whether we’re solving tough tech problems, brainstorming creative solutions, or grabbing a coffee between meetings. Curiosity is encouraged. Collaboration is second nature.\n\nWe value excellence, not ego, and back each other to do great work without micromanagement. With low politics and high trust, it’s a place where delivery people, designers, and engineers genuinely connect, and where everyone has a voice, space to grow, and a little fun along the way.\n\nJob Description\n\nThe Role\n\nAI systems don’t fail because of bad models. They fail because of bad libraries, outdated documents cited as current, knowledge that exists but can’t be found, datasets that are technically present but practically untrustworthy.\n\nThe AI Data Engineer (Librarian) owns that problem. This is not a traditional data engineering role. It sits at the intersection of data governance, knowledge management, and AI delivery. You will design and maintain the catalogues, metadata schemas, quality frameworks, and lineage structures that every AI system in The Foundry depends on, and you will work directly alongside AI Engineers to connect retrieval systems to the clean, context-aware knowledge stores you’ve built.\n\nThink of it this way: the AI Engineer builds the system that searches the library. You build the library.\n\nWhat You\'ll Do\n\nDesign and maintain data catalogues for AI projects using platforms such as DataHub, OpenMetadata, Apache Atlas, Collibra, or cloud-native equivalents (AWS Glue Data Catalog, Azure Purview, GCP Dataplex).\n\nDefine metadata schemas and taxonomy standards — type, version, jurisdiction, validity period, confidence tier — so retrieval systems know not just what a document is, but when it applies and how much to trust it.\n\nAssess data quality across client and internal assets using tools like Great Expectations, dbt tests, or Soda; flag stale, superseded, or ambiguous records before they reach the AI layer.\n\nBuild and maintain data lineage so every AI-generated output can be traced back to its source, version, and validity period — making outputs auditable, not just accurate.\n\nDesign automated ingestion workflows and nightly quality checks that keep catalogues current without constant manual intervention.\n\nPartner with The Foundry engineers to connect RAG pipelines and agentic retrieval systems to catalogue APIs, and with The Labs strategists to ma\n\nQualifications\n\nWhat We\'re Looking For\n\nA background in data governance, information management, knowledge management, or records management — with genuine interest in how that work enables AI delivery.\n\nHands-on experience with at least one data catalogue platform (DataHub, OpenMetadata, Collibra, Alation, Apache Atlas, or a major cloud equivalent) and familiarity with metadata standards such as JSON-LD, Dublin Core, or domain-specific ontologies.\n\nStrong SQL skills; working Python for data profiling, quality scripting, and metadata automation; and comfort with dbt or OpenLineage for lineage tracking.\n\nUnderstanding of vector databases and RAG architecture — enough to know how metadata quality directly affects retrieval precision.\n\nExperience in regulated or high-stakes data environments where provenance and auditability genuinely matter: financial services, insurance, government, healthcare, or similar.\n\nA collaborative, low-ego disposition. The Data Librarian’s work is structural and often invisible. The glory goes to the AI system. You are fine with that.\n\nBonus: A formal background in library or information science. Experience with knowledge graphs (Neo4j, RDF, SPARQL). Prior consulting or agency delivery experience.\n\nAdditional Information\n\nLife at Bilue\n\nPeople-first focus: We’re committed to delivering exceptional outcomes for our clients, but we know it starts with our people. You’ll join a values-led team that’s collaborative, curious, and genuinely cares about doing great work, together.\n\nConnection that counts: From monthly anchor days and team lunches to our annual offsite, we create intentional moments to connect, collaborate, and celebrate. These aren’t just fun perks — they’re part of how we work and grow together.\n\nFlexibility that works: We offer hybrid working, with 1–2 days per week in the office. It’s a balance that gives you the space to do your best work, while still creating time to connect and build strong relationships in person.\n\nStrong internal communities: We actively foster internal communities across tech, design, delivery, and beyond, giving you plenty of chances to connect, share knowledge, and learn from your peers.\n\nOpportunities to grow: We invest in your development with unlimited access to Go1’s learning library and support from our internal performance coach. Whether you want to deepen your technical skills or grow your leadership potential, we’ll back you.\n\nFlat structure, real impact: At Bilue, everyone’s voice matters. Our leadership team is hands-on and approachable, and we operate without unnecessary layers. We keep things open and transparent, and your ideas will be heard, no matter your title.\n\nBilue = Big + Blue Ocean. Are you ready to set sail? Apply now!\n\nNB. This is a full-time position based in Sydney, NSW or Melbourne, VIC. To be considered, candidates must have unrestricted working rights in Australia.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Bilue','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=07aa88c5d074585c','scraped','2 days ago'),(2616,NULL,'job','Head of Organisational Development and Capability','Part-time','Cremorne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About OES\n\nOES is a vibrant and values led organisation, and we are passionate about enhancing lives through education. We work with university partners, training institutes, and professional bodies worldwide, to develop and enable immersive and engaging learning experiences. We empower our teams to be student focused, innovative and embrace change with a growth mindset to ensure we achieve our vision of being the world’s most impactful enabler of education. We encourage our people to grow and develop through teamwork and a diverse range of projects, programs and challenging work. We trust our people to deliver, so when you work with OES, you will join a team who are empowered to impact every day.\n\nThe Opportunity:\n\nWe’re seeking an experienced and forward‑thinking Head of Organisational Development & Capability, to design and execute our global Organisational Development strategy and partner closely with the Executive team to shape the organisation of the future. This is a senior, enterprise‑level role with accountability for driving transformation across organisational design, leadership capability, ways of working, and future workforce readiness, which includes Generative AI and emerging technologies. OES is a medium sized organisation, and this role will have one direct report. As the Head of OD & Capability, you will not only think strategically but will be hands‑on, leading, designing, and delivering solutions end‑to‑end. This is a highly influential role suited to a leader who thrives in complexity, moves at pace, and is motivated by meaningful, visible impact.\n\nThis role is a permanent position working 4 days a week\n\n Key Responsibilities:\n\nPartner closely with the Executive team and senior leaders to deliver strategic organisational transformation\nShape organisational design, operating models, leadership capability, and ways of working aligned to a growth strategy\nLead complex, global change initiatives and embed fit‑for‑purpose change management practices\nDefine and deliver future‑focused leadership development & succession plans\nBuild organisational capability in Generative AI and digital ways of working, enabling responsible adoption at scale\nDesign and embed a high‑performance, engaged, and inclusive culture across the organisation\nOwn and evolve the Employee Value Proposition (EVP)\nLead and grow an Organisational Development function, role‑modelling agility, innovation, and impact\n\nAbout you:\n\nYou are a confident, credible OD leader who brings both strategic depth and practical execution capability.\nUndergraduate degree in Human Resources, Organisational Psychology, or a related discipline\nProven experience leading an Organisational Development function\nDemonstrated experience enabling organisations to scale for growth\nStrong background in organisational design within high‑growth, agile environments\nExperience influencing senior stakeholders across complex organisations\nExperience applying Human‑Centred design principles to organisational and leadership challenges\nCapability to design and implement change at scale in ambiguous environments\nThrives in a fast‑paced environment and enjoys complex challenges\nBrings a positive, can‑do approach with a strong growth mindset\nComfortable managing competing priorities and ambiguity\nOperates with integrity and credibility at all levels of the organisation\n\nWhat’s in it for you?\n\nAlong with joining a passionate, energetic and highly skilled team, this role will allow you to gain exposure to many growth and development opportunities. OES offers a hybrid, flexible approach to work, where we work 2-3 days from our state-of-the-art Cremorne office, and the rest from home (or wherever you choose!). Breakfast, snacks, table tennis, Nintendo Switch are all available in the office, as well as weekly staff drinks. Ultimately, you will be joining a values-driven, collaborative business where your creativity and innovation will be nurtured and celebrated.\n\nWe pride ourselves on being a \'People First\' employer and if you join the OES Team, you will benefit from:\n\nFlexible, hybrid work for genuine career-life fit (2-3 days in our Cremorne Office)\nProfessional development and mentoring\nOES Culture Club and events calendar\nHealth and wellbeing activities\nAnnual flu vaccinations\nPaid parental leave\nPurchased leave\nStudy assistance and leave for eligible employees\nMental health support resources and Employee assistance program (EAP)\nIncome protection insurance\nAccess to corporate health insurance rates\n\nIf this opportunity excites you, please APPLY NOW with your CV & Cover Letter\n\nAt OES, we are committed to creating an inclusive and diverse environment, where we encourage candidates of any nationality, age, background, disability, and gender identity to apply. If you feel aligned to the role and would like to further explore your suitability, we welcome your application and would love to consider your fit for the role at OES.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Online Education Services','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f292e12aaa600c6f','scraped','2 days ago'),(2617,NULL,'job','Head of People Partnering','Full-time','Brisbane QLD',NULL,'',200000.00,'$180,000 - $220,000 a year','Company Description\n\nMontu is Australia\'s largest healthtech business with a focus on alternative healthcare. Founded in 2019, it supports patients, doctors and pharmacies through its Alternaleaf clinic, offers accredited healthcare education to clinicians via its SAGED platform, and dispensing solutions to pharmacies across Australia through Leafio. Montu is also the founding member of Cannabis Council Australia, a non-for-profit advocacy body that advances legislative change across the healthcare landscape. Our mission is to make alternative healthcare more affordable and accessible for the millions who could benefit.\n\nMontu has been recognised as Australia’s fastest-growing tech company in the Deloitte TechFast 50 for two consecutive years (#1 in 2022 and 2023), achieving remarkable revenue growth of 26,000% and 9,000%. Named #1 on LinkedIn’s Top Startups Australia 2024, Montu has cemented its position as the largest business of its kind outside North America and continues to evolve on its journey.\n\nThis role is an Australia-based, fully work-from-home position, with access to co-working spaces in Sydney, Melbourne and Brisbane.\n\nJob Description\n\nThe Head of People Partnering leads our team of People Partners aligned to business areas across Montu, and personally takes on the most complex, sensitive, and executive-level Employment Relations matters that arise. You\'ll be accountable for the standard of partnering support delivered to managers and senior leaders, and you\'ll take hands-on accountability for the matters that need them.\nThis isn\'t a hands-off leadership role. You\'ll set the operating direction for the partnering function, lift manager capability across the business, and personally run the ER work that needs senior judgement: investigations, executive exits, deeds of release, Fair Work proceedings, settlement decisions. ELT exposure is real and constant. So is the ambiguity that comes with scale.\nYou\'ll report to the GM People and work closely with the broader People team and ELT.\n\nWhat you\'ll own\n\nStrategy and operating direction for the People Partnering function\nStandard of partnering support delivered across all business areas\nPersonal lead on complex, sensitive, and executive-level ER matters: investigations, executive exits, deeds of release, Fair Work proceedings\nDeterminations on legal risk, settlement parameters, and external counsel engagement on matters under your ownership\nManager capability uplift through the partnering team and direct senior engagement\nPerformance management cycles, calibration, talent reviews, and lifecycle delivery\nEngagement strategy, listening cycles, and action planning at business area level\nPractical, considered AI adoption across the partnering team\nDevelopment and performance of the People Partner team\n\nWhat we\'re looking for\n\n10+ years in senior HR roles spanning generalist or business partnering and substantive ER ownership\n3+ years leading People Partner or HR Business Partner teams\nDemonstrated experience personally managing complex, executive-level ER matters under Australian employment law\nSound judgement on legal risk, settlement decisions, and when to engage external counsel\nTrack record of building manager capability at scale, not just policy delivery\nComfort working at ELT level: writes well, briefs cleanly, holds a position when challenged\nCommercial mindset: balances people fairness with business sustainability\nGenuine curiosity about AI and HR technology, with a considered view on adoption\nBachelor\'s degree in HR or related field; postgraduate qualification preferred but not essential\n\nWhy this role\n\nGenuine seat at the table, not adjacent to it\nScope and complexity that\'s rare outside ASX-listed enterprise\nHands-on ER work without the team management overhead\nPragmatic culture that backs people who deliver and think commercially\nPermanent, full-time, work from home\n\nQualifications\n\nQualifications, Skills and Experience\n\nBachelor\'s degree in Human Resources, Master\'s degree preferred\n\nProven experience with 10+ years in senior HR generalist or business partnering roles, preferably in a fast-paced, dynamic environment\n\n3+ years leading People Partner or HR Business Partner teams\n\nStrong understanding of HR best practices, employment laws, and regulations (Australian context)\n\nExcellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to build rapport and influence stakeholders at all levels of the organisation\n\nDemonstrated leadership ability, including experience managing and developing high-performing HR teams\n\nStrategic thinker with the ability to translate business objectives into actionable people initiatives\n\nAnalytical mindset with the ability to leverage data to drive decision-making and measure the effectiveness of partnering programs\n\nConfident operator with senior business leaders, including ability to challenge constructively and hold a position when needed\n\nAdditional Information\n\nYou will be joining a high-performing, fast-paced team where your work drives meaningful impact in a leading tech company at the intersection of healthcare. We take pride in our driven and results-focused culture, where ambitious individuals can push the boundaries of innovation and contribute to better outcomes for Australians.\n\nOther benefits include:\n\nGaining access to SAGED courses and more through the Greenhouse learning platform fosters continuous growth and development.\nEnjoying discounts with over 450 retailers through our Reward and Recognition platform.\nFull-time, work-from-home role.\nAccess to co-working spaces in Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane, and select regional cities.\nMental health support through our wellbeing platform, Unmind.\nPrivate health insurance discount through Medibank.\nUp to 8 weeks of paid parental leave.\nSwag kits to celebrate key milestones in your journey with us.\nEnhance your home office with our work from home equipment allowance benefit.\nBeing part of one of the fastest-growing industries in Australia, improving the lives of hundreds of thousands of patients.\n\n#LI-JC1 #LI-Remote\n\nWe are committed to facilitating a barrier-free recruitment process and work environment. If you require any accommodations, we welcome you to let us know so we can work with you to participate fully in our recruitment experience.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Montu','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5f53dd30106a34f8','scraped','2 days ago'),(2618,NULL,'job','Software Services AI Solutions Engineer II','Full-time','Yatala QLD 4207',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'All Orbits, All Planets - Join us on our journey\n\nGilmour Space is a leading Australian space company, developing launch vehicles, satellite platforms, advanced propulsion technologies; and launching from our licensed orbital spaceport in Bowen, North Queensland.\n\nAre you a creative and experienced Software Services AI Solutions Engineer II looking for a dynamic role where your skills will make a real impact? Have you ever dreamt of building rockets right here in Australia? Well now’s your chance! Gilmour Space is seeking a talented individual to join our innovative team to send rockets to Space! Conveniently located between Brisbane and the Gold Coast, our new state-of-the-art facility, purpose-built for designing and manufacturing rockets in-house, is equipped with the latest technology and tools, providing an ideal environment for innovation and excellence. So, what are you waiting for? Join us and be a part of a forward-thinking team dedicated to pushing the boundaries of space exploration and let’s send Australia to Space together!\n\nHow you will contribute to our mission in getting Australia to space:\n\nThe below is designed to give you an idea of the role you will play. There will be many more exciting and innovative things to do:\n\nDefine and prioritize AI improvements aligned to business needs.\nHands-on development, testing and deployment of AI solutions and workflows through structured and achievable work plans to solve complex business challenges.\nStay across current and emerging AI technologies, particularly generative and agentic AI, and apply that knowledge to drive change.\nAnalyse and integrate with existing API endpoints to deliver AI-powered automation.\nDevelop and enhance AI agentic capabilities to augment and automate workflows.\nBuild automated pipelines and optimise model performance and system reliability.\nEvaluate and recommend where AI can deliver measurable business value across existing processes.\nArticulate complex AI concepts clearly to stakeholders without technical backgrounds.\nCoordinate with all parts of the business including engineering, supply chain and finance to identify potential improvements through AI assistance and learning.\nProduce and maintain clear technical documentation and user guides\nEvaluate training materials to support the adoption and understanding of AI tools across the business.\nEnsure that engineering activities are conducted and documented in accordance with Gilmour Space policies, plans and procedures.\nOther duties as requested by Management.\n\nMinimum Qualifications, Skills and Experience:\n\nBachelor\'s degree in artificial intelligence, machine learning, software, computer science, and/or relevant experience.\nSolid software engineering fundamentals including code quality, databases, APIs/integrations and delivery hygiene.\nAbility to operate in dynamic, fast paced environments.\nDemonstrated experience or strong foundational knowledge in AI/ML concepts, including generative AI, large language models and agentic frameworks.\nDesired Qualifications, Skills and Experience:\nUnderstanding of Machine Learning concepts and growing knowledge in Artificial Intelligence and Large Language Models (LLMs).\nUnderstanding of model evaluation, prompt design, and non-deterministic system behaviour.\nExperience working with cloud-based AI platforms.\nAbility to integrate AI solutions with data platforms, pipelines and governance frameworks.\nInterest in the development and maintenance of policies, standards and guidelines for AI/ML development practices, data governance and responsible AI use across the organisation.\nStrong critical thinking skills with the ability to objectively evaluate AI solutions, question outputs and distinguish genuine value from hype.\nUnderstanding of AI risk, bias, explainability and safe deployment practices.\nExperience working in Agile delivery environments.\nFamiliarity developing full-stack, production quality applications.\nA proactive mindset with a focus on continuous improvement and practical outcomes.\nExcellent communication and facilitation skills, demonstrating the capacity to effectively communicate with a range of technical and non-technical stakeholders.\nFamiliarity with any of C/C++, Golang, Python, JavaScript, TypeScript.\nExperience interacting with RESTful and GraphQL APIs.\nUnderstanding of Systems Engineering practices.\nInterest in developing testing and evaluation strategies for non-deterministic systems, including prompt regression testing and output quality benchmarks.\nExperience using git workflows and version control practices.\nAwareness of cybersecurity principles and the ability to develop and deploy AI solutions with secure coding practices, data protection and access controls in mind.\n\nHow to Apply:\n\nApplicants must be an Australian Citizen/Permanent Resident or have an appropriate Australian work visa or work entitlements.\n\nIf you are a proactive team player with a passion to get Australia to space and a desire to succeed, please apply now by clicking the apply button and including your resume and cover letter or head to our careers page: www.gspace.com/career\n\nGilmour Space Technologies is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all team members. We strongly encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples for all positions.\n\nNo Recruitment Agencies Please','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Gilmour Space Technologies Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9d2e96760ac86df3','scraped','2 days ago'),(2619,NULL,'job','D365 F&O Technical Consultant - Contract','Full-time','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nAt NCS Australia, we believe in doing technology services better. Our commitment to quality, focus on people, and willingness to challenge traditional thinking set us apart. Our team brings this belief to life by partnering with our clients and communities to make tomorrow together.\n\nWe are committed to creating an environment that prioritises innovation, collaboration, and purposeful work. Our diverse team is empowered to make a meaningful impact with curiosity, creativity and resilience to shape better outcomes. Join us and accept the challenge of creating a better tomorrow.\n\nPlease note we would look at either a contract or permanent person for this position\n\nJob Description\n\nWe are seeking an experienced D365 F&O Technical Consultant for a dedicated Transformation Project. This is a contract engagement focused on migrating legacy systems and optimizing business processes within the Dynamics 365 Finance & Operations ecosystem.\n\nAs part of a large-scale digital transformation, you will be responsible for the technical execution of system enhancements, data migrations, and complex integrations. The focus is on building a scalable, high-performing environment that aligns with modern architectural standards.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nDevelopment: Execute customizations and extensions using X++ and C# to meet specific transformation milestones.\n\nData Migration: Lead data mapping and migration activities using the Data Management Framework (DIXF) from legacy environments to D365 F&O.\n\nIntegrations: Develop and maintain interfaces via OData, Logic Apps, and Azure Service Bus.\n\nDeployment & Lifecycle: Manage builds and releases through Azure DevOps and Lifecycle Services (LCS).\n\nTroubleshooting: Resolve technical blockers during the SIT (System Integration Testing) and UAT (User Acceptance Testing) phases..\n\nQualifications\n\nTechnical Requirements\n\nProven track record as a Technical Consultant on at least one full-lifecycle D365 F&O transformation or implementation.\n\nDeep proficiency in X++ development and the D365 framework.\n\nStrong experience with Azure Integration Services and Power Platform.\n\nAbility to interpret functional design documents (FDD) into robust technical designs (TDD).\n\nPrior experience in a contract or project-based environment with defined deliverables\n\nAdditional Information\n\nWhy join us:\n\nNCS Australia is where you can feel at home, nurturing your talents and skills as we make tomorrow together, one day at a time. Our benefits include paid parental leave, initiatives focused on your well-being and discounted health insurance. You will also enjoy discounts on various products and services and be regularly recognised and rewarded for high performance. We are committed to your career development through our Capability Fingerprint, industry and partner training programs, special interest groups, and an AI-driven learning platform. No matter where you are in your career, we offer meaningful work and opportunities for growth.\n\nNCS Australia is an equal-opportunity employer, and we take pride in our commitment to valuing and supporting our people and the communities we serve.We are dedicated to attracting, retaining and developing our people regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability and age. Applications are encouraged from all sectors of the community and we strongly encourage applications from the Veterans, Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander community.\n\nAt NCS Australia, we are committed to supporting adjustments throughout the recruitment and selection process, as well as during employment. We actively support and encourage people with disability to apply.\n\nAgencies:\n\nWe’ve got this. We request that you do not contact NCS employees outside of the Talent Acquisition team. NCS exclusively accepts resumes from agencies on our preferred supplier panel through the NCS Agency Portal. Agencies that submit resumes must have a valid fee agreement and be assigned to the particular requisition by the Talent Acquisition team. Any resumes that are submitted outside of this process will become the sole property of NCS. If a candidate is hired outside of this process, no fee or payment will be given.\n\nWork rights and background checks:\n\nTo be eligible for a position with us, applicants will need to have valid work rights for Australia and be willing to undergo a comprehensive background checking process, including probity and police checks','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'NCS Australia','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=4e40265ddb650af5','scraped','2 days ago'),(2620,NULL,'job','Workplace Coordinator','Part-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We’re looking for an Office and Workplace Coordinator to own the day-to-day operations and onsite experience in our Sydney office. This is a highly visible, hands-on role with real impact on how employees experience the office each day. You’ll be the person who keeps the space running smoothly, removes friction for the team, and ensures the office is consistently organized, functional, and well supported.\n\nOur Sydney office is home to approximately 20-25 employees who work onsite and is quickly growing. We’re looking for someone who is in the office each day, takes pride in ownership of the space, and proactively keeps things running efficiently.\n\nThis role is part time working 20-24 hours per week.\n\n*Visa sponsorship is NOT available at this time\n\nWhat You\'ll Do:\n\nSet up and manage recurring office lunch and snack programs\n\nGreet guests and customers and help make their visits smooth and welcoming\n\nCoordinate office mail & deliveries and work with IT on equipment drop offs and pickups\n\nKeep the office tidy, stocked, and running efficiently (including light cleanup when needed)\n\nPlan and support team events like birthday treats, happy hours, and seasonal celebrations\n\nBe the go-to person for office questions, supply requests, and day to day logistics\n\nCommunicate with building staff, vendors, and the facilities team as needed\n\nSupport occasional admin or facilities-related tasks\n\nOffice supply ordering and inventory management\n\nWhat You\'ll Bring:\n\nBrings the energy and builds the buzz, transforming the office into a dynamic hub of positive interactions and unparalleled culture.\n\nStrong communication skils\n\nExperience in office coordination, workplace support, or administrative roles\n\nStrong sense of ownership and ability to work independently\n\nFriendly, approachable, and dependable presence in the office\n\nHighly organized with good time management and attention to detail\n\nComfortable jumping between different types of tasks throughout the day\n\nAble to lift up to 10kg (like lunch deliveries or office supplies)\n\nNice To Haves:\n\nExperience working in a small office or startup environment\n\nFamiliarity with workplace tools like Zoom, Google Workspace, or Slack\n\nLight events experience or interest in building a positive workplace culture\n\nComfortable communicating with vendors or building staff to troubleshoot issues\n\n#LI-BT1\n#LI-Onsite\n\nAbout FloQast:\nFloQast is the leading AI-powered Accounting Transformation Platform, uniquely built by former accountants for accountants. We automate complex, recurring accounting workflows—transforming preparers into strategic reviewers and relieving accountants from tedious manual work. Our cloud-based solution is trusted by over 3,500 world-class accounting teams, including Lululemon, Doordash, and the MLB, to drive collaboration and financial accuracy. Driven by a mission to continuously elevate the profession, FloQast is redefining both the practice and the perception of accounting on a global scale.\n\nOur values act as a guiding compass, shaping every decision we make, and are non-negotiable, particularly in our hiring process. Alongside our employees, partners, and customers, we embody these values every day:\nUnwaveringly Authentic\nAmbitious with Integrity\nEmpowered to Grow\nCommitted to Collaboration\nCustomer Obsessed in All Ways\n\nFloQast is regularly rated as a Best Place to Work!\n- Inc. Magazine’s Best Workplaces in 2025, 2024, 2023, 2022, and 2021\n- Best Places to Work by LA Business Journal since 2017 (that’s 9 years!)\n- Built In’s Best Place to Work in Los Angeles 7 years in a row!\n\nBecause we are Customer Obsessed in All Ways, check out what our customers have to say about FloQast on G2 Crowd.\n\nFloQast, Inc is committed to operating fair and unbiased recruitment procedures allowing all applicants an equal opportunity for employment, free from discrimination on the basis of religion, race, sex, age, sexual orientation, disability, color, ethnic or national origin, or any other classification as may be protected by applicable law. We aim to recruit the right people for the jobs we have to offer, and to assess applications on the basis of relevant skills, education, and experience. We welcome people of different backgrounds, experiences, abilities, and perspectives. We are an equal opportunity employer and strive to provide a professional and welcoming workplace for all employees.\n\nWe may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'FloQast','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8c108a04a02bb887','scraped','2 days ago'),(2621,NULL,'job','Data & AI Engineer','','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'00068600121\n\nDate published Apr 30 2026\nLocation Melbourne / Australia\nJob category Consulting\nWork model Hybrid\n\nAbout Cognizant Consulting\n\nCognizant Consulting is more than Cognizant’s consulting practice—we’re a global community of experts dedicated to helping clients reimagine their business. By combining deep industry knowledge with leading technology and data expertise, we design and deliver innovative solutions for some of the world’s most recognised organisations.\n\nAbout the role\n\nAs a Consulting Data & AI Engineer, you will make an impact by designing and delivering scalable, cloud-based data and AI solutions that solve complex business problems. You will be a valued member of Cognizant Consulting’s Data & AI practice, working closely with clients, architects, and cross‑functional consulting teams to translate data into actionable insights and business outcomes.\n\nIn this role, you will:\n\nDesign, build, and deliver enterprise-scale data engineering solutions using Snowflake, cloud platforms, and modern analytics tooling.\nDevelop robust, scalable data pipelines and transformation workflows (including ETL/ELT and dbt) to enable high-quality, analytics-ready data.\nCollaborate with technical leads and architects to implement solutions using modern engineering and DevOps best practices.\nPartner with business and technology stakeholders to understand requirements and deliver outcomes aligned to client priorities.\nContribute to solution design, technical decision-making, and continuous improvement across client engagements and the Data & AI practice.\n\nWork model\n\nWe believe hybrid work is the way forward as we strive to provide flexibility wherever possible. Based on this role’s business requirements, this is a hybrid position requiring 3 days a week in a client or Cognizant office in Melbourne, VIC. Regardless of your working arrangement, we are here to support a healthy work-life balance though our various wellbeing programs.\n\nWhat you must have to be considered\n\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Data Science, or a related discipline.\n3+ years’ experience in data engineering, analytics engineering, or applied Data & AI roles.\nStrong hands-on experience with Snowflake, including data modelling and performance optimisation.\nExperience building data pipelines on cloud platforms such as Azure, Azure Fabric, or AWS.\nProficiency in SQL and Python, with experience using modern data and analytics tools (including dbt).\n\nThese will help you succeed\n\nExperience with distributed data platforms such as Spark or Databricks.\nExposure to machine learning, MLOps, or AI-enabled solutions, including emerging AI technologies.\nStrong consulting mindset, with the ability to communicate complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.\nExperience working in fast‑paced, client-facing environments where priorities evolve.\n\nWhy work with us?\n\nWe’re excited to meet people who are curious, collaborative, and passionate about delivering impact through data and AI. Even if you don’t meet every requirement listed, we encourage you to apply—your transferable skills and experience could be exactly what we’re looking for.\n\nThe Cognizant community:\nWe are a high caliber team who appreciate and support one another. Our people uphold an energetic, collaborative and inclusive workplace where everyone can thrive.\n\nCognizant is a global community with more than 300,000 associates around the world.\nWe don’t just dream of a better way – we make it happen.\nWe take care of our people, clients, company, communities and climate by doing what’s right.\nWe foster an innovative environment where you can build the career path that’s right for you.\n\nAbout us:\nCognizant (Nasdaq: CTSH) is an AI Builder and technology services provider, building the bridge between AI investment and enterprise value by building full-stack AI solutions for our clients. Our deep industry, process and engineering expertise enables us to build an organization’s unique context into technology systems that amplify human potential, realize tangible returns and keep global enterprises ahead in a fast-changing world. See how at www.cognizant.com or @cognizant.\n\nCognizant is an equal opportunity employer. Your application and candidacy will not be considered based on race, color, sex, religion, creed, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, genetic information, pregnancy, veteran status or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local laws.\n\nIf you have a disability that requires reasonable accommodation to search for a job opening or submit an application, please email CareersIndia2@cognizant.com with your request and contact information.\n\nDisclaimer:\nCompensation information is accurate as of the date of this posting. Cognizant reserves the right to modify this information at any time, subject to applicable law.\n\nApplicants may be required to attend interviews in person or by video conference. In addition, candidates may be required to present their current state or government issued ID during each interview.\n\n d','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Cognizant','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9bc528d796a0c43d','scraped','2 days ago'),(2622,NULL,'job','Food Services Assistant- David Berry','Permanent','Berry NSW',NULL,'',3066.00,'$30.66 an hour','Classification: Hospital Assistant Grade 3\nEmployment Type: Permanent Part Time\nRemuneration: $30.66 per hour plus shift allowances and 12% superannuation\nHours per week: 16\nLocation: David Berry Hospital\nApplications Close: 11.59 PM, Thursday, 14 May 2026\n\nHealthShare NSW is committed to creating a diverse and inclusive environment which reflects the community we serve. We welcome applications from people of all backgrounds, experiences and identities, and we encourage applicants from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander communities, culturally and linguistically diverse groups, LGBTIQ+ communities, veterans, carers and people with disability.\n\nAbout the opportunity\n\nAre you looking a rewarding career that allows you to make a positive difference in the lives of others? HealthShare NSW is seeking a compassionate and dedicated Food Services Assistant.\n\nIn this role you will play a vital role in ensuring the comfort and well-being of patients in our hospital. Your responsibilities will include:\n\norder taking\nmeal assembly\nmeal preparation and distribution of patient meals\nrecording intake\ndishwashing and other associated cleaning duties\nwaste management\n\nAbout us\n\nHealthShare NSW touches the lives of NSW Health employees and patients every single day by delivering services that keep our public hospitals and health facilities running.\n\nWatch Our HealthShare NSW story video to learn more about the work we do and the diverse range of roles we have on offer.\n\nAdditional benefits\n\nWe reward our employees with a terrific range of benefits, including:\n\nGreat leave conditions: enjoy one day off each month as an ADO, annual leave loading (a bonus extra payment of 17.5%) and 14 weeks’ paid parental leave for eligible employees\nSalary packaging and novated leasing: you can access up to $2782 extra per year in your pay\nWellbeing programs: access an array of wellbeing programs designed to support your physical, mental, and emotional health\nCommitment to career development: expansive free online training, talent programs, study leave and internal development opportunities to accelerate your career\nRewarding role and community contribution: make a difference in people\'s lives by assisting those in need and actively contributing to your community.\n\nPlease note some benefits may only apply to certain employment types.\n\nHow to apply\n\nClick Apply Now at the top of the page.\nAttach your resume and answer the screening questions.\n\nWe recognise that AI tools are increasingly being used to assist with resumes and applications. While we accept their use, we encourage applicants to provide genuine responses in their own words.\n\nAdditional information\n\nHealthShare NSW assesses candidates in line with the NSW Public Sector Capability Framework, which describes the capabilities and behaviours required for roles across the NSW public sector. The specific capabilities for this role are outlined in the Position Description. Learn more: https://www.nsw.gov.au/nsw-government/public-sector-capability-framework\nIf successful following the application close date, you will be required to attend interview/complete comparative assessment as well as reference checks\nCandidates must have Australian work rights (citizens, permanent residents, or valid work visa). Permanent roles are open to Australian citizens and permanent residents, while temporary and casual roles welcome applicants with a visa.\nThis is a NSW Health Category A position which requires immunisation and Tuberculosis (TB) screening. Refer to NSW Health OASV Policy (Page 12) for a complete list of required vaccines. During application, please upload OASV Undertaking/Declaration Form and TB Assessment Tool with any vaccination evidence you have.\nIf you are identified as a preferred candidate and are external to HealthShare NSW, you will be required to complete a physical pre-employment health assessment (at no cost to you) to confirm your ability to safely perform the duties of the role. Employment is subject to successful completion of all pre-employment checks.\nAn eligibility list from this recruitment may be created for future casual, permanent, or temporary full-time or part-time positions within the next 6 months.\n\nContact information\n\nPlease contact Kelly.Tripp@health.nsw.gov.au if you have any questions about this role. Any career portal support questions can be directed to our customer service team at 1300 679 367.\n\nFor Aboriginal candidates who would like to talk to a HealthShare NSW Aboriginal Workforce Consultant, please contact HSNSW-AboriginalWorkforce@health.nsw.gov.au\nSupport is also available through the Stepping Up website.\n\nPlease let HSNSW-Diversity@health.nsw.gov.au know if you need any adjustments to the recruitment or interview process (e.g. physical accessibility, interview setup, or scheduling). Candidates with a disability can also use this email for confidential advice and support during the recruitment process.\n\n.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'NSW Health','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c0e20b9108ff965c','scraped','2 days ago'),(2623,NULL,'job','Land Solutions, Right of Way Title Specialist – Nationwide','','Atwell WA 6164',NULL,'',37.50,'$35 - $40 an hour','Who We Are\n\nAtwell, LLC is a bold leader in the consulting, engineering, and construction services industry, delivering a broad range of creative solutions to clients in the real estate & land development, and energy markets. We have a strong national presence and a diverse, award-winning project portfolio. Atwell is a privately owned company, with 2,000+ passionate team members across 70+ locations and growing!\n\nAtwell, LLC is a proud recipient of the following 2025 awards:\n\nTen consecutive years in a row as a “Best Place to Work” by Zweig Group (#11)\nRecognized as #70 in the ENR Top 500 Design Firms, ranked in every region\nRecognized in Crain\'s “Fast 50” as one of the fastest-growing companies (#14)\nRecognized as the 2025 ENR Design Firm of the year for the Southeastern US\n\nAtwell’s Land Solutions team is growing, and we’re looking for a Right of Way Acquisition Specialist with a strong title and land rights focus to support projects across the U.S. This is a field-based, project-driven role where your attention to detail, research capabilities, and ability to navigate landowner interactions directly support successful project delivery.\n\nYou’ll manage the full acquisition lifecycle — from initial landowner engagement through title research, documentation, and closeout — while partnering closely with internal teams across legal, survey, environmental, and project management.\n\nEngage landowners to explain project scope, address questions, and secure land rights including easements, rights of entry, and option agreements\nConduct detailed title research, ownership verification, and parcel analysis using county records, GIS systems, and public data sources\nPrepare, review, and execute land use agreements in alignment with client, state, and regulatory requirements\nNegotiate compensation agreements and support resolution of damage claims in coordination with project leadership\nMaintain accurate, organized parcel files and document all landowner communications\nRecord executed documents with appropriate county offices across multiple jurisdictions\nInterpret maps, plats, legal descriptions, and title reports to clearly communicate property impacts\nCoordinate access for survey, environmental, and project teams across active project areas\nSupport valuation efforts, appraisals, and damage assessments\nTrack acquisition progress in project systems and provide regular updates to leadership\nParticipate in project meetings and assist with closeout activities\n\nQualifications\n\n2–5 years of experience in right of way, title, land acquisition, or real estate\nStrong working knowledge of title research, land ownership, and property records across multiple jurisdictions\nExperience navigating county records, courthouse research, and GIS platforms\nAbility to work with a wide range of landowners and stakeholders with professionalism and clarity\nStrong negotiation skills and ability to resolve issues effectively\nHighly organized with strong attention to detail and documentation accuracy\nComfortable with nationwide travel and working in both field and remote environments\nIRWA coursework or certification is a plus\nAssociate degree or equivalent combination of education and experience\n\nDisclaimer\n\nWhile AI tools may support your application process, this role is built on human talent. Your judgment, experience, and character matter most, so we encourage you to showcase what makes you uniquely you.\n\nAtwell does not accept unsolicited resumes from any 3rd party agencies. No fee will be paid to 3rd parties who submit unsolicited resumes to any Atwell employee. Resumes from approved vendors must be specifically requested by Atwell and approved by the Atwell Talent Acquisition Team.\n\n#LI-CF1\n\nPay Range\n\n$35 - $40 USD\n\nAtwell Benefits: To attract and retain the best professionals in the industry, we aim to provide an excellent working environment and a progressive benefits program designed to support your personal and professional needs.\n\nWork/Life:\n\nGenerous Paid Time Off\nPaid Parental Leave\nFlexible work schedules are available for some positions\nTenure Awards — Travel Vouchers to see the world based on your travel preferences\n\nCompensation:\n\nCompetitive Compensation packages\nAnnual bonuses, spot bonuses and peer recognition awards\n401K match - 1:1 up to 4% of compensation\nTuition Assistance\nStudent Loan Repayment\nPaid Licensing / Certification Fees and Renewals\nFinancial Rewards for Obtaining Licensure\nEmployee Referrals\nAnnual Wellness Reimbursement for anything wellness related (Gym memberships, fitness tracker, home gym equipment, etc.)\nDependent Care Match\n\n‘Atwell’ness:\n\nMedical (BC/BS), Dental (Delta), and Vision (VSP)\nFamily Planning & IVF Benefits\nPet Insurance\nHealth Savings Account & Flex Spending Account options\nEmployer paid LTD, STD, and life insurance\nMetlife Supplemental Benefits covering accident, hospitalization, and critical illness\nMember Assistance Program (MAP) with complimentary counseling sessions, legal benefits, financial consultations, and work/life referral services','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Atwell, LLC','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f806d4c3ecdbc39b','scraped','2 days ago'),(2624,NULL,'job','Senior Software Engineer','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Senior Software Engineer\n\nYou are collaborative and enjoy solving analytical problems to help our team to reach highest potential\nWe are a team of big thinkers who are engineering the future of banking\nTogether we will build tomorrow’s bank today, using world-leading technology and innovation\n\nDo work that matters:\n\nWe’re building tomorrow’s bank today, which means we need creative and diverse engineers to help us redefine what customers expect from a bank. Envisioning new technologies that are still waiting to be invented and reimagining products that support our customers and help build Australia’s future economy.\n\nSee yourself in our team:\n\nYou will join our Automation and Optimization Fraud and Scam Engineering Chapter, where you will design and develop solutions to protect customers from fraud and scams. Your work supports creating advanced technologies that automate scam detection and digital intrusion alerts.\n\nWe’re interested in hearing from people who:\n\nDesign, build, and maintain production-grade software systems in modern languages.\nImplement automation frameworks for UI, API, performance, integration, and security testing.\nDrive shift-left practices: embedding unit, integration, and contract tests into CI/CD pipelines.\nCollaborate with the team to ensure testability, observability, and resilience in system design.\nDrive the quality strategy within their squad ensuring alignment with engineering and product goals.\nMentor grads & engineers, fostering a culture of engineering excellence and accountability.\nEstablish engineering dashboards that provide visibility into delivery quality and production health. ￼\nContinuously learn and grow across coding, testing, deployment, and operations.\nTake end-to-end ownership of features: from design code testing deployment monitoring.\n\nTechnical Skills:\n\nWe use a broad range of tools, languages, and frameworks. We don’t expect you to know them all but experience or exposure with some of these will set you up for success in this team:\n\nGood programming skills in one or more languages e.g. Java, JavaScript/TypeScript, or Python.\nExperience with CI/CD tools (e.g., TeamCity, GitHub, Jenkins)\nGood understanding of API testing, microservices, and cloud-native architectures (preferably AWS).\nFamiliarity with observability tools (e.g., Splunk, Observe, CloudWatch)\nDeep knowledge of test automation frameworks (e.g., Playwright, Devtest, Appium, Sahi).\nSolid grasp of DevSecOps, SDLC best practices, and release governance.\nUse of AI coding assistants (e.g., GitHub Copilot, Roo code) to accelerate everyday development/testing tasks.\n\nWorking with us:\n\nWe welcome applications from all internal candidates who meet the role requirements.\n\nAs an equal opportunity employer, we are committed to ensuring a fair and inclusive selection process.\n\nWe are seeking individuals who have proactively engaged in self-development through targeted learning pathways to transition into Software Engineering. All candidates with relevant, transferable skills are encouraged to apply.\n\nWe support our people with the flexibility to balance where work is done with at least half their time each month connecting in office. We also have many other flexible working options available including changing start and finish times, part-time arrangements and job share to name a few.\n\nIf you\'re already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest, x15ventures), you\'ll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We’re keen to support you with the next step in your career.\n\nWe\'re aware of some accessibility issues on this site, particularly for screen reader users. We want to make finding your dream job as easy as possible, so if you require additional support please contact HR Direct on 1800 989 696.\n\nAdvertising End Date: 14/05/2026','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Commonwealth Bank','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=aa2cb5658e1a2285','scraped','2 days ago'),(2625,NULL,'job','Automation Test Engineer','','Broadbeach QLD 4218',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Are you an Automation Test Engineer ready to shape quality from the ground up in a high-performing engineering team?\n\nAutoGuru is an award-winning Australian technology company and FleetGuru is our flagship B2B fleet management platform, now at the forefront of AI-powered fleet intelligence. As we scale FleetGuru nationally and internationally and accelerate our AI roadmap, quality engineering is a core part of how we build, not an afterthought.\n\nWe\'re looking for an Automation Test Engineer to join our Technology team and help us embed quality earlier, deeper and smarter across everything we ship.\n\nWhat you will be doing:\n\nAs an Automation Test Engineer, you\'ll work as an embedded quality partner within our Engineering team, sitting alongside developers, not separate from them.\n\nThis is a hands-on, technical role. You’ll build automation frameworks, get your hands on Playwright and leverage AI tools like Claude Code, and help us ship features the team is genuinely proud of.\n\nBuild and maintain E2E test suites using Playwright, growing coverage as the FleetGuru platform accelerates.\n\nPerform API, GraphQL, and integration testing as a core part of every feature delivery.\n\nUse Claude Code to turbocharge test authoring and build reusable, scalable testing frameworks.\n\nCollaborate with developers and BAs to define acceptance criteria before a single line of code is written.\n\nContribute to CI/CD pipelines so automated tests are baked into every build.\n\nChampion shift-left testing: partner with devs to catch issues earlier and reduce manual regression.\n\nSelect, implement, and maintain the testing tools that keep our engineering engine purring.\n\nKeep test repositories clean, fast, and meaningful; no flaky tests allowed in this garage.\n\nAbout You:\n\nIT degree or comparable industry experience.\n\nProven experience designing and building automation test suites.\n\nHands-on experience with Playwright for E2E test automation.\n\nStrong understanding of the SDLC and where quality fits across it.\n\nHands-on experience with API and GraphQL testing.\n\nComfortable working alongside developers and contributing to engineering conversations.\n\nExperience with CI/CD pipelines and integrating tests into build processes.\n\nCuriosity about AI and how tools like Claude Code can accelerate and enhance the quality engineering workflow.\n\nStrong communication skills, you can translate quality thinking into language developers and stakeholders both understand.\n\nBased on the Gold Coast or willing to relocate.\n\nBonus if you\'ve worked with:\n\nAWS cloud platform.\n\nPerformance and scalability testing.\n\nAI-assisted development tools, including using Claude Code or similar for test generation and automation.\n\nShift-left or BDD/TDD methodologies.\n\nPerks: We\'re an inclusive and flexible workplace, and our perks and culture are pretty sweet (if we say so ourselves). We offer:\n\nHybrid work options once fully trained.\n\nTake advantage of discounted car servicing and even enjoy a paid day off on your birthday - because you deserve it!\n\nOpportunity to excel in your career through ongoing learning and development from our internal ‘Guruversity’ program.\n\nBask in the contemporary charm of our industrial office, just a stone\'s throw away from the beach and public transport, complete with cozy chillout spaces and all-around good vibes.\n\nPark your worries (and your wheels) with free secure parking, bike racks, surfboard racks, and even a pool table for those well-deserved breaks.\n\nDive into a calendar packed with exciting team events led by our dedicated Culture Crew.\n\nWe build high-performing teams aligned to our values of \'here to help\', \'move with purpose\', \'think 10x\', \'play as a team\', \'numbers over hype\', and \'innovative for the future\'.\n\nHow to Apply: Submit your resume and cover letter outlining why you\'re the best fit for the role. Applications close at 5 pm on Thursday, 28th May.\n\nWe believe diverse perspectives lead to better decisions and stronger outcomes. We welcome applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and people of all backgrounds and experiences.\n\nConnect with us:\n\nLinkedIn: @AutoGuru\nInstagram: @autoguru\nFacebook: @autoguru.com.au','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'FleetGuru','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d1ab1d06df465e23','scraped','2 days ago'),(2626,NULL,'job','Brand Design Lead','','Fortitude Valley QLD 4006',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Heads up! This role is based in-person at our office in sunny Brisbane, Australia.\n\n––––––––––––––––––––\n\nAbout Askable\n\nHey, we’re Askable - the world’s most loved user research platform. Loved by whom you ask? Woolies, Qantas, Canva, BUPA, CommBank, NAB, Telstra, BBC, Mastercard and hundreds more. Not bad right?\n\nWe help teams run better research faster — from participant recruitment to insights — so they can build products people actually want.\n\nAskable began in 2017 as an idea scribbled on a sticky note, born out of frustration with the clunky, outdated research processes we’d experienced firsthand. So, we set out to build a new way—one that makes quality research accessible to everyone, from Fortune 500s to startups hungry for insights.\n\nNow with offices in Brisbane, London, and Chicago, we’re growing the team to bring Askable’s research power to researchers everywhere, so they can make smarter, user-driven decisions.\n\n––––––––––––––––––––\n\nWhy this role, why now\n\nEvery B2B SaaS company is now an \"AI company.\" Demos look the same. Landing pages look the same. The category is collapsing into a sea of identical aesthetics, identical claims, and identical product screenshots.\n\nIn that environment, we believe brand is the moat. The companies that win the next five years won\'t be the ones with the best AI features. They\'ll be the ones whose brand is so distinct, so consistently expressed, and so confident in its point of view that buyers remember them before they remember their feature list.\n\nThat\'s the job.\n\nYou\'ll own the visual identity, design system, and creative output at Askable. You\'ll evolve the brand from competent and clean to differentiated and unmistakable. And you\'ll do it leaning hard into AI as a creative force multiplier, not as a content factory.\n\n––––––––––––––––––––\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nLead the brand\n\nTake full ownership of the Askable brand and where it goes next\n\nEvolve the visual identity, typography, color, illustration, photography direction, and overall aesthetic point of view\n\nBuild and maintain a cohesive brand system across web, product marketing, social, events, and beyond\n\nPush the brand forward, not just maintain it\n\nLead the design system\n\nBuild the component library, templates, and usage guidelines that let other teams produce consistent, on-brand work without a designer in every loop\n\nSet the quality bar for all external-facing work\n\nMake the system the leverage that scales our output as we grow\n\nLead AI-augmented creative workflows\n\nSet the standard for how our team uses tools like Midjourney, Runway, Sora, Figma AI, and others to scale creative output without losing craft\n\nDefine what we make ourselves, what we generate, what we systemise, and what we outsource\n\nTreat AI as a creative force multiplier\n\nBring the product to life\n\nCreate product visuals, demos, and videos that clearly communicate value\n\nTranslate complex features into simple, compelling visual stories\n\nElevate how we present launches, updates, and new capabilities\n\nOwn key moments\n\nLead creative for hero campaigns, the website, and major launches\n\nDirect motion, video, event design, and global campaign production through external partners and contractors\n\nMake sure everything we ship reflects the level of the product\n\nPartner across the business\n\nWork closely with marketing, product, and sales to raise the bar on every external-facing surface\n\nDirect externals and contractors as our roster grows\n\nContribute to how we tell our story globally\n\n––––––––––––––––––––\n\nWho you are\n\n6+ years in brand or visual design, with at least 2 years in a senior role at a B2B SaaS company in scale-up mode. Bonus if you\'ve shipped a full brand evolution.\n\nA portfolio that shows craft and a point of view. We\'re not looking for safe. We\'re looking for distinct.\n\nA senior IC with leadership instincts. You can personally ship the brand work that matters most, and you know how to use systems, AI, and external partners to scale everything else. You\'ve seen a design function grow around you and you\'re ready to be the one building it.\n\nGenuinely AI-native in your workflow. Not \"I tried Midjourney once.\" We want to see work where AI was integrated into the creative process, examples of how you\'ve cut production time, and an opinion on where AI helps versus where it flattens.\n\nStrong design systems thinking. You\'ve built or substantially evolved a system that scaled across a team.\n\nRange across formats: web, motion, social, event, brand campaigns. You don\'t have to be world-class at all of them, but you can direct all of them.\n\nA clear view on what makes B2B brand stand out. You can articulate why certain B2B brands break through and what makes the rest forgettable.\n\nComfortable working closely with product and understanding how things work.\n\nDirect, collaborative, and an owner. You can defend a creative direction, take a strong note, and move fast.\n\nBonus\n\nMotion design, 3D, or video direction experience\n\nWorked in research, insights, AI, or developer tools categories\n\nBuilt creator or influencer content systems\n\nExperience working with founders or executives on personal brand visual identity\n\n––––––––––––––––––––\n\nThe mindset you’ll need\n\nWinning with your team: You’ll be proud of the individual work you do, but find winning as team ultimately more fulfilling. This includes having the emotional maturity to give and receive constructive feedback to better the team as a whole.\n\nIndependence and curiosity: You won’t find cabinets full of step by step instructions at Askable. You’ll need to think on your feet, manage your own workflow, problem-solve roadblocks, proactively ask questions, and take responsibility for the goals you set.\n\nGrowth focussed: You’ll enjoy the idea of a stretch goal and always be looking for opportunities to improve yourself, your team, and the business.\n\nQuick to learn: You’ll bring an ability to quickly learn and understand our product solutions and features, and keep up to date as our offerings evolve.\n\n––––––––––––––––––––\nPerks and benefits\n\nYour excitement about the role itself is what matters most to us. Perks are just the icing on the cake—but let us share a few to whet your appetite.\n\nCompetitive salary\n\nA vibrant and social work environment\n\nAskable Days: a bonus paid day off every month (giving you a total of 7 weeks annual leave!)\n\nBuffet lunch, every day! Prepared for us by our in-house Chef\n\nFree public transport to get you to and from the office\n\nAnd more! We\'ll be happy to chat about all our other perks during the interview process.\n\n––––––––––––––––––––\n\n️ Before you go...\n\nResearch shows many people (especially women and minority groups) hesitate to apply unless they meet every single requirement. At Askable, we’re committed to building diverse teams with unique perspectives. If you’re excited about this role but your experience doesn’t align perfectly, we’d still love to hear from you.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Askable','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=cd35e434e1f6e473','scraped','2 days ago'),(2627,NULL,'job','EY Parthenon - AI Manager','','Melbourne VIC 3000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'At EY, we’re all in to shape your future with confidence.\n\nWe’ll help you succeed in a globally connected powerhouse of diverse teams and take your career wherever you want it to go.\n\nJoin EY and help to build a better working world.\n\nThe opportunity\n\nAt EY-Parthenon, our unique combination of transformative strategy, transactions, tax and corporate finance delivers real-world value – solutions that work in practice, not just on paper. Benefiting from EY’s full spectrum of services, we’ve reimagined strategic consulting to work in a world of increasing complexity. With deep functional and sector expertise, paired with innovative AI-powered technology and an investor mindset, we partner with CEOs, boards, private equity and governments every step of the way.\n\nAs a Manager - AI Senior Architect, you will play a pivotal role in shaping and delivering innovative AI solutions for internal use & our clients. You will lead the architecture and implementation of advanced analytics and AI platforms, helping organisations unlock value through emerging technologies including Generative AI.\n\nThis is a leadership role that combines deep technical expertise with strategic thinking, enabling you to drive transformation across industries. This hybrid role can be performed from any of our EY offices across Australia. Our roles can potentially be adjusted to work flexibly with reduced hours. Please speak with us about potential options.\n\nYour key responsibilities\n\nLead the design and architecture of scalable AI and data solutions aligned to client business objectives\nTranslate complex business problems into innovative AI-enabled solutions and technical blueprints\nArchitect and implement GenAI solutions (e.g., LLMs, RAG, copilots) within enterprise environments\nEstablish AI engineering standards, governance frameworks, and best practices\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams including data scientists, engineers, and business stakeholders\nLead client engagements, providing trusted technical advisory and thought leadership\nMentor and develop junior team members, fostering a high-performing team culture\nStay at the forefront of AI trends and bring leading practices to clients\n\nSkills and attributes for success\n\n8+ years of experience in AI, data, or solution architecture\nProven experience in consulting or complex enterprise environments\nProficiency in Python and ML frameworks (e.g., TensorFlow, PyTorch)\nExperience with MLOps, APIs, and microservices architectures\nStrong experience in designing and delivering AI/ML solutions at scale\nExpertise in cloud platforms (Azure, AWS, or GCP) and modern data architectures\nHands-on experience with GenAI and LLM ecosystems\nAbility to bridge business and technology, translating strategy into execution\nStrong stakeholder engagement and communication skills\n\nIdeally, you’ll also have the skills and attributes below but don’t worry if you don’t tick all the boxes. We’re interested in your aptitude, attitude and willingness to learn.\n\nExperience with responsible AI and governance frameworks\nRelevant cloud or AI certifications\nPrior experience leading teams or large-scale transformation programs\n\nWhat we offer you\n\nAt EY, we’ll fuel you and your extraordinary talents in a diverse and inclusive culture of globally connected teams. Learn more.\n\nCareer development: At EY, your career is yours to shape! We’ll develop you with future-focused skills and equip you with world-class experiences ey.com/au/careerdevelopment\nFlexible work arrangements: Our flexible work policies empower you to balance your professional and personal life, fostering a culture of trust and autonomy.\nA comprehensive benefits package: From a yearly wellness incentive, to access to additional 8 weeks of flex leave per year, and family-friendly policies, including 26 weeks of gender-neutral paid parental leave, we cater to your diverse needs to help you thrive both personally and professionally www.ey.com/au/benefits\nSalary: We offer a competitive salary which is open to negotiation pending on skills and experience.\n\nAcknowledgement of Country\n\nEY acknowledges the Traditional Owners and Custodians of the lands on which EY offices are located around Australia. We pay our respects to their cultures, and to their Elders — past, present, and emerging. Find out more about our vision for reconciliation at ey.com/en_au/careers/indigenous\n\nDiversity, equity, and inclusiveness (DE&I) are core to who we are, how we work and how we live our values. We encourage applications from people of all ages, nationalities, abilities, cultures, sexual orientations, and gender identities and are committed to providing an equitable and barrier free recruitment experience for all. We encourage you to share any support and adjustments you need to be your best and participate equitably in our recruitment process. We understand sharing your needs with us can be daunting, so if you have questions before or during your application, we welcome you to get in touch at contactrecruitment@au.ey.com or +61 3 8650 7788 (option 2). Anything you tell us will be kept completely confidential.\n\nAre you ready to shape your future with confidence? Apply today.\n\n#LI-Hybrid\n\nEY | Building a better working world\n\nOur preferred applicant will be required to undertake employment screening by EY or our external third-party provider.\n\n© 2025 Ernst & Young Australia. A member firm of Ernst & Young Global Limited. All Rights Reserved. Liability limited by a scheme approved under Professional Standards Legislation.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'EY','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=029ce7ec99e62cde','scraped','2 days ago'),(2628,NULL,'job','Traditional Chinese/Cantonese- Fluent Speakers - AI Training - Australia','Freelance','Brisbane QLD',NULL,'',30.00,'$30 an hour','Traditional Chinese/Cantonese- Fluent Speakers - AI Training - Australia\n\nAbout Prolific\n\nProlific is not just another player in the AI space – we are building the biggest pool of quality human data in the world.\n\nOver 35,000 AI developers, researchers, and organizations use Prolific to gather data from paid study participants with a wide variety of experiences, knowledge, and skills.\n\nThe role\n\nWe\'re looking for Advanced Traditional Chinese/Cantonese- Fluent Speakers - AI Training to help train and evaluate cutting-edge AI models. If you have the necessary experience, we\'ll send you a quick test to assess your skills and suitability for AI tasks. If successful, you\'ll be invited to join Prolific as a Domain Expert participant, where you\'ll get paid to train and evaluate powerful AI models.\n\nResearchers looking for your skills tend to pay $30/hr per AI task completed. You must be prepared to complete paid tasks that require one hour of uninterrupted work, though many are shorter.\n\nWhat you\'ll bring\nAdvanced language skills and verifiable experience as being fluent in Traditional Chinese/Cantonese.\nA willingness to take our skills verification test to assess your suitability for our Domain Expert participant pool\nStrong attention to detail and the ability to concentrate on complex tasks for up to one hour at a time\nA reliable and fast internet connection and access to a computer\nA willingness to self-declare your earnings, as our participants are self-employed\nA PayPal account to receive payment from our clients\nWhat you\'ll be doing in the role\nCompleting AI training tasks such as analyzing, editing, and writing in Traditional Chinese/Cantonese\nJudging the performance of AI in performing Traditional Chinese/Cantonese prompts\nImproving cutting-edge AI models\nWhy Prolific is a great platform to join as a Participant\n\nJoining our platform as a Prolific participant will give you the chance to influence the AI models of the future using professional legal expertise. Once you pass our assessment, you can join Prolific in just 15 minutes, and start enjoying competitive pay rates, flexible hours, and the ability to work from home.\n\nWe\'ve built a unique platform that connects researchers and companies with a global pool of participants, enabling the collection of high-quality, ethically sourced human behavioural data and feedback. This data is the cornerstone of developing more accurate, nuanced, and aligned AI systems.\n\nWe believe that the next leap in AI capabilities won\'t come solely from scaling existing models, but from integrating diverse human perspectives and behaviours into AI development. By providing this crucial human data infrastructure, Prolific is positioning itself at the forefront of the next wave of AI innovation – one that reflects the breadth and the best of humanity.\n\nLinks to more information on Prolific\n\nWebsite\n\nYoutube\n\nPrivacy Statement\n\nBy submitting your application, you agree that Prolific may collect your personal data for recruiting and global organisation planning. Prolific\'s Candidate Privacy Notice explains what personal information Prolific may process, where Prolific may process your personal information, its purposes for processing your personal information, and the rights you can exercise over Prolific use of your personal personal information.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Prolific Academic Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1323564b1ffcc02a','scraped','3 days ago'),(2629,NULL,'job','Lead AI Engineer (Mob Way Applicants must identify as Aboriginal and / or Torres Strait Islander)','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Mob Way Applicants must identify as Aboriginal and / or Torres Strait Islander\nSydney, Melbourne or Brisbane Location\nHybrid Working Arrangement\n\nWhat’s the role?\n\nThis role is part of our Mob Way program , a culturally grounded pathway unlocking senior opportunities for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander leaders.\n\nThrough Mob Way, you will be supported to grow your career while staying connected to culture. This includes strong executive connection, opportunities to build your networks, and dedicated time for in‑community experiences and elder‑led cultural immersion.\n\nAn exciting opportunity is available for a Lead AI Engineer to complement our Data, Digital, and Artificial Intelligence (DDAI) team.\n\nThe role works within delivery squads focusing on building and operationalising AI applications and ML models that will further enhance our service and product offerings.\n\nAdditionally, the role is responsible for engineering design, development, and deployment of machine learning (ML) models and Gen-AI agentic applications that solve complex problems and enhance our products and services. This role will work closely with data scientists, software engineers, and product managers to integrate machine learning solutions into production systems.\n\nWhat do I need?\n\nHighly established people leadership experience whilst also being able to balance a hands-on senior AI Engineering workload.\nExpert programming skills in Python and strong familiarity with ML libraries such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, or scikit-learn.\nAdvanced experience building solutions leveraging frameworks such as LlamaIndex, LangChain, AutoGen, DSPy, etc.\nDeep experience building CI/CD pipelines and automation in Jenkins, GitHub and Bamboo, plus IaaC & configuration management tools such Terraform and Chef.\nAdvanced experience with big data technologies like Hadoop, Spark, or similar for data processing and feature engineering, and implementing solutions on Azure ML, Synapse and Azure AI Services.\nHighly experienced in dealing with diverse stakeholders at all levels within a complex enterprise setting.\nStrong familiarity with Graph databases and their usage pattern, with hands-on experience in backend & frontend development using Nodejs and React.\nAdvanced familiarity with scripting languages such as bash, PowerShell.\nPossess certification on Azure & AWS for solution design.\nDeep experience with A/B testing and experimental AI engineering design and architectural concepts.\nWell-rounded relationship management and business acumen with a default ability to cater language and style to suit any audience.\n\nWhy join us?\n\nAs part of Mob Way, you will receive tailored career support through executive coaching, culturally safe leadership development, and opportunities to strengthen your connection to community and culture.\n\nAt Westpac, we’re passionate about becoming our customers’ #1 banking partner for life and we know that starts with creating the best workplace in the country. For Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, that means more than just a job.\n\nSpecial offers on banking products and discounts from top brands, including generous employee-only mortgage rates!\nWe offer flexible work arrangements to support your work/life balance, along with a variety of leave options including Culture (such as dedicated Sorry Business Leave), Lifestyle, and Wellbeing Leave.\nTailored career support through our Indigenous Careers Team, and growth opportunities like the Echo mentoring program and Jawun secondments.\nLots of opportunities to ‘give back’ to the Community by getting involved in our many volunteering initiatives including our Brothers & Sisters Employee Advocacy Group.\n\nCreate your future today\n\nTo get started, simply click on the APPLY or APPLY NOW button\n\n#mobway\n\nCreate your future today through a role supported by our Mob Way program and a workplace committed to supporting your career.\n\nWe’re all about creating a supportive and inclusive community. We welcome everyone – no matter your age, gender, background, or abilities. We also provide additional support to welcome our veterans, Indigenous Australians and neurodiverse community.\n\nIf you need any adjustments during the recruitment process, you can find out more information and additional contact details by visiting the \"People with Disability and/or needing Accessibility Requirements\" page on our website.\n\nAt Westpac we aim to help Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Australians succeed by supporting Indigenous employees to build meaningful careers. Westpac has been granted an S126 Exemption to sections eight (8) and fifty-one (51) of the Anti-Discrimination Act 1977 (NSW); this allows us to advertise and recruit this role exclusively to Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander applicants.\n\nThis forms part of Westpac’s strategy to foster a multicultural, vibrant and diverse workforce.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Westpac','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=31fbd9ae072f8c64','scraped','2 days ago'),(2630,NULL,'job','Application Engineer (Fraud and Scams)','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Create your best future and join Westpac as an Application Engineer (Fraud and Scams).\n\nWhat’s the role?\n\nYou’ll join Westpac’s Group Fraud Management Platform Change team, supporting technology that helps detect and prevent fraud and scams. This is a hands on application engineering role where the work you do directly helps protect customers and strengthen trust.\n\nThis is a Sydney based role on Warrane, Gadigal Country , offered as a full time, permanent position with a hybrid way of working .\n\nYou’ll design, build, enhance and support applications and integrations across the fraud and scam detection ecosystem. The team supports Proactive Risk Manager, also known as PRM, an ACI provided platform used for proactive risk and fraud management. Experience with PRM, fraud, scams or banking is advantageous but not essential. If you bring strong core engineering capability, you’ll be supported to learn the platform.\n\nYou’ll work in Linux based environments, support Java applications, collaborate across teams, contribute to Agile delivery and help keep critical systems reliable and evolving.\n\nWhat do I need?\n\n• Strong hands on application engineering experience in complex environments\n• Solid capability with Linux or Unix shell scripting and Oracle databases, including SQL and PL SQL\n• Experience with integration technologies including XML, XSLT, APIs and messaging platforms such as Kafka or MQ\n• Hands on exposure to Java Spring Boot, developing or supporting REST or SOAP APIs, and tools such as Tomcat and Control M\n• Familiarity with DevOps and CI CD tooling such as GitHub, GitHub Actions, Bitbucket, Jenkins or Chef\n\nDesirable skills\n\n• Understanding of fraud detection systems or financial services technology\n• Experience using AI assisted coding tools to deliver efficient and consistent code\n• Experience working in Agile environments using tools such as JIRA and Confluence\n• Exposure to test driven development, testing frameworks and automation\n\nWhy join us?\n\nWe’re obsessed with becoming our customers #1 banking partner for life and we’re looking for people who are passionate about helping us achieve that goal. In return we’re committed to making Westpac the best place to work in the country. Here are just a few of the ways we’re already doing that:\n\n• Special offers on banking products and discounts from top brands, including generous employee only mortgage rates\n• Flexible work arrangements to help you achieve a greater work life balance, and a variety of leave options including Culture, Lifestyle and Wellbeing leave\n• Tailored learning and development opportunities to help your grow your career within the bank\n• Lots of opportunities to give back to the Community by getting involved in our many volunteering initiatives\n\nCreate your future today\n\nTo get started, simply click on the APPLY or APPLY NOW button\n\nWe’re all about creating a supportive and inclusive community. We welcome everyone no matter your age, gender, background, or abilities. We also provide additional support to welcome our veterans, Indigenous Australians and neurodiverse community.\nIf you need any adjustments during the recruitment process, you can find more information and contact details on our FAQs and how to contact us page , under the ‘Diversity, sustainability and flexibility’ section.\n\n#UNITEprogram','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Westpac Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b57c0b8143c2ff8b','scraped','2 days ago'),(2631,NULL,'job','Business Development Manager','Part-time','Remote',NULL,'',10923826.00,'$65,022.97 - $153,453.55 a year','*The Opportunity*\n\nAre you a high-energy hunter who thrives on the \"thrill of the chase\"? *Kanguru Tech* is looking for a tenacious *Business Development Manager* to spearhead our outbound sales efforts.\n\nWe provide elite Managed Execution Units and AI-driven tech solutions to businesses globally. Your mission is simple: find companies that need to scale, get them on the phone, and show them how our dedicated offshore teams and technical expertise can transform their operations.\n\n*The Role: New Business Acquisition*\n\nThis is a *pure growth role*. You will be responsible for building your own pipeline from the ground up through high-volume outbound activity.\n\n*Key Responsibilities:*\n\n* *Cold Calling & Prospecting:* Actively call potential clients daily to introduce Kanguru Tech’s services and book discovery meetings.\n* *Strategic Email Outreach:* Craft and execute personalized email sequences that cut through the noise and grab the attention of decision-makers.\n* *Pipeline Management:* Move leads through the sales funnel, from initial contact to closing the deal.\n* *Solution Selling:* Quickly understand a client\'s pain points (e.g., staffing shortages, digital marketing lag) and pitch our managed specialist models as the solution.\n* *Target Achievement:* Consistently meet or exceed weekly KPIs for calls, emails, and revenue generated.\n\n*What We Are Looking For*\n\n* *The \"Hunter\" Mentality:* You aren\'t afraid of the word \"no.\" You are resilient, persistent, and highly motivated by financial rewards.\n* *Proven Outbound Experience:* Experience in cold calling, lead generation, or B2B sales is essential.\n* *Exceptional Communication:* You have a professional phone manner and the ability to write persuasive, high-impact emails.\n* *Tech Literacy:* Ability to learn and discuss tech services (AI, Automation, Managed IT) with confidence.\n* *Self-Discipline:* You can manage your own desk and stay productive without constant supervision.\n\n*Why Join Us?*\n\n* *Uncapped Earning Potential:* We offer a solid *base salary* plus a *performance-based bonus structure*. The more business you bring in, the more you earn.\n* *Innovative Product:* You are selling services that businesses actually need—cost-effective, high-quality managed teams and cutting-edge AI automation.\n* *Direct Impact:* Work directly with leadership in a fast-paced, agile environment where your results are seen and rewarded.\n* *Office Culture:* Based at our Glenroy office with a supportive team that celebrates every win.\n\nPay: $65,022.97 – $153,453.55 per year\n\nWork Location: Remote','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Kanguru Tech Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=612faa80ab76bc72','scraped','3 days ago'),(2632,NULL,'job','Pathfindr - AI Adoption Specialist','Full-time','Melbourne VIC 3000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About Pathfindr\nWe\'re on a mission to help clients improve their business using AI today and prepare for tomorrow by empowering their teams to stay at the forefront of innovation. We are passionate about helping our clients achieve their goals and realise the promise of AI-generated value in their organisations. They are the reason we love to work in AI, and we want to make sure they - and, most importantly, their people - are at the forefront of today\'s rapidly changing technology landscape.\n\nThe role\nThe Delivery Lead owns enterprise engagements end to end — from kick-off to close — ensuring clients receive what was sold and that adoption lands inside their organisation. They hold the Statement of Work, coordinate with Content and facilitators to deliver an outstanding client experience and serve as the primary client contact throughout. This is a mid-to-senior, hands-on role combining program ownership, client partnership, and AI change management. It reports to the Director of Accelerator across enterprise accounts.\nWhat makes this role compelling\nSOW delivery and scope ownership: Deliver every commitment on time, in scope, and to Pathfindr\'s quality bar. Track and execute the SOW from kick-off to close, holding Pathfindr accountable to what was committed\n\nClient relationship and partnership: Be the client\'s primary point of contact across the engagement. Own the relationship from kick-off through to wrap. Map and actively manage stakeholders, including sponsors, program leads, and ambassadors\n\nCustomer journey and adoption: Own the customer journey across the engagement and the success of adoption inside the client organisation. Sessions and deliverables are inputs; behavioural change and embedded use are the outcome.\n\nWorking with Content and Academy: Work closely with the Content team and facilitators to deliver an outstanding customer experience. The Delivery Lead does not own content build or facilitation but makes sure the people who do have what they need, when they need it.\n\nEngagement outcomes and reporting: Make outcomes visible, internally and to the client, throughout the engagement and at wrap. Track adoption and usage metrics against program goals, visible to the client and internally throughout. Signal back to Sales on renewal opportunities, expansion potential, and client health, early enough for Sales to act\nWhat success looks like\nFirst 90 days\nHas taken ownership of at least one live enterprise engagement and is running it end to end\nSOWs for assigned accounts are tracked, reported against, and on plan\nClients on assigned accounts know who their Delivery Lead is and have a clear communication rhythm in place\nFirst 6 months\nMultiple enterprise accounts running concurrently, all on time and on scope\nAdoption is moving measurably forward on assigned accounts, against agreed program goals\nWrap deliverables and reporting cadences are landing consistently and being valued by clients\n\nWhat you\'ll bring\nEssential:\nTrack record of owning enterprise accounts end to end, with multiple stakeholders and concurrent workstreams - ideally in consulting, professional services, learning and development, or enterprise program delivery\nExposure to executive stakeholder management in ASX 200 or equivalent enterprise environments\nProven experience in applying change management practice in a delivery context; equivalent experience in digital transformation, technology adoption, or large-scale capability uplift\nSolid written and verbal communication, including with executive audiences\nHighly organised - can hold a complex SOW in their head and translate it into action for multiple internal teams\nConfident facilitating client conversations, including hard ones such as scope creep, missed inputs, and escalations and having comfort with ambiguity and to build structure around it\nPractical and outcomes-focused, able to move between strategic framing and operational delivery\nNice to have\nWorking knowledge of AI tools (ChatGPT, Copilot, Claude) and their application in business contexts\nFormal change management certification (Prosci, ACMP, or equivalent)\n\nCompensation & location\nCompensation:\nFinal package is negotiable based on skills and experience\nLocation:\nWe value in office connections with flexible working arrangements\n\nHow to apply\nSubmit in PDF format a short cover letter and your CV\n\nLUA2mP3PeB','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Affinda Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=e84151e97c99e5b6','scraped','3 days ago'),(2633,NULL,'job','Solution Architect','','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About the Company\n\nAt Future Secure AI, we\'re building something genuinely new — and we\'re looking for people bold enough to build it with us. We work at the frontier of AI, tackling big, real-world problems for global enterprises across multiple industries, armed with state-of-the-art technology and a culture that prizes courage, rigor, and relentless curiosity. Our BRAVER values aren\'t just words on a wall — they describe the kind of people we are and the standard we hold ourselves to every day. Our leadership team is entrepreneurial, experienced, and accessible, with an open-door policy that means you\'ll never be just a number here. We invest seriously in your growth because we know our success depends on yours. If you\'re ready to work alongside some of the brightest minds in the industry, push into uncharted territory, and do work that genuinely matters, Future Secure AI is the place for you.\n\nFuture Secure AI builds AI Co‑Workers that automate real operational work across enterprise environments. We design systems that move beyond prototypes into secure, scalable, production platforms. Architecture quality and design discipline are foundational to our success.\n\nWe are looking for a Solution Architect to design, shape, and guide the technical solutions underpinning AI Co‑Workers across complex client and platform environments. This is a hands‑on architecture role for someone who enjoys translating business needs into robust, cloud‑native, AI‑enabled systems.\n\nThe role\n\n• Define end‑to‑end solution architectures that map client business requirements to scalable technical designs\n• Design and guide Kubernetes‑based architectures supporting AI and application workloads\n• Lead solution design across cloud infrastructure, application services, data flows, and integrations\n• Work hands‑on with public cloud services to shape deployable, production‑ready solutions\n• Collaborate with engineers, AI developers, and platform teams to ensure architectures are implemented as designed\n• Support architecture workshops and design sessions with internal teams and client stakeholders\n• Ensure solutions align with SDLC practices from design through build, test, deployment, and operation\n• Design application and system architectures spanning APIs, services, and multi‑component systems\n• Contribute to platform engineering efforts that enable teams to build and operate AI Co‑Workers efficiently\n• Balance technical excellence with pragmatism, cost, scalability, security, and delivery speed\n\nMust have criteria\n\n• Hands‑on Kubernetes experience designing, building, or operating workloads on EKS, AKS, GKE, or self‑managed Kubernetes\n• Hands‑on experience with at least one public cloud provider such as AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud\n• Professional experience using at least two programming or scripting languages such as Python, Java, Go, C#, JavaScript/TypeScript, Ruby, Bash, or PowerShell\n• Experience working across the full software development lifecycle including CI/CD, testing, deployment, and operation\n• Demonstrated Solution Architect experience defining solutions that translate business needs into technology designs\n• Application architecture experience designing services, APIs, and multi‑component software systems\n• Platform engineering experience building or operating platforms that enable other teams or customers\n\nShould have criteria\n\n• Hands‑on Terraform experience for infrastructure provisioning and automation\n• Hands‑on Helm experience for Kubernetes application deployment\n• More than five years of relevant professional experience\n• Exposure to enterprise or domain‑wide architecture, including standards, roadmaps, or governance\n• Strong stakeholder management skills with senior or cross‑functional stakeholders\n• Experience contributing to complex or high‑stakes engagement scenarios such as large programmes, multi‑vendor delivery, or regulated environments\n\nPreferable criteria\n\n• Relevant certifications such as AWS, Azure, GCP, CKA, CKAD, DevOps, DevSecOps, or programming certifications\n• Strong DevOps or DevSecOps experience, including CI/CD ownership, security practices, and infrastructure automation as a primary responsibility\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\nA high-performance culture\nState-of-the-art technology\nExperience world-class leadership\nScale of impact and purpose\nA competitive salary and a huge growth trajectory\nWork with the best in the industry\nFlexible work environment\nDiversity and creativity\n\nDisclaimer: We do not wish to be contacted by recruitment agencies. Our hiring process is managed in-house and the best way for candidates to express interest is by applying with your resume through our company website.\n\nFuture Secure AI Privacy Policy\n\nAt Future Secure AI, we are committed to protecting your privacy and adhering to the principles of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs) under the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth). Our Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, share, and protect your personal data when you visit our website at www.futuresecure.ai (the \"Website\") and use our services.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Future Secure AI','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=086a01635cf14a7a','scraped','3 days ago'),(2634,NULL,'job','Mid-Level Full Stack Engineer','Full-time','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Join the National Leader in Cloud-Based Property Management\n\n Our Story\n\nPropertyMe is Australia’s #1 real estate agency platform, with 60%+ market share. More than 35,000 real estate professionals use PropertyMe to manage over 1.9 million properties.\n\nYour work will shape the day-to-day experience of real estate professionals, tenants, and owners across Australia and New Zealand.\n\n What you bring\n\nYou bring 3+ years of commercial software engineering experience, with practical experience in:\n\nModern .NET / C# and building maintainable backend services\nDesigning and building Web APIs\nJavaScript or TypeScript in modern web applications\n\nHow you work\nYou’re comfortable owning well-defined problems and collaborating with Product, Design, and other engineers to deliver high-quality solutions. You write clean, reliable code and value testing and maintainable software practices.\n\nYou’re growing in confidence when making technical decisions and weighing trade-offs across speed, quality, and maintainability. You use modern development workflows, including AI-assisted engineering tools, to improve productivity and quality\n\nNice to have\n\nBonus points if you have experience with:\n\nVue in production\nAWS or other cloud platforms\nCI/CD pipelines and automated testing practices\nWorking in Agile teams and contributing to technical discussions\n\n Responsibilities\n\nDesign and implement high-quality features and improvements\nWork closely with Product and Design to solve meaningful customer problems\nWrite maintainable code and automated tests\nParticipate in technical design discussions and contribute ideas\nProvide constructive feedback through pull requests and collaboration\nContinuously improve your technical skills and engineering practices\nSupport the practical use of Lean and Agile principles in software delivery\n\n The benefits and perks\n\nJob security working for one of Australia\'s leading PropTech companies\nSmall Scrum teams with a lot of autonomy\nNo on-call duty - you focus on delivering solutions\nFully remote\nRegular milestone parties and events\n\nIt’s uncertain times at the moment, but there’s nothing uncertain about the opportunity here at PropertyMe. We’re building something special, and we want to chat with you about joining us, no matter your background. Apply now or check out our Talent Acquisition team on LinkedIn; we’re always open for a chat!','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Property Me','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b9c167c52f942b48','scraped','3 days ago'),(2635,NULL,'job','Python Tutor - Mount Waverley','Part-time','Mount Waverley VIC 3149',NULL,'',30.00,'From $30 an hour','Are you passionate about coding and inspiring young minds?\n*ENJOY AI Australia* is seeking enthusiastic *Python Tutors* to join our growing education team, with opportunities available at our *Mount Waverley* campus in Melbourne.\n\n*What You’ll Do*\n\n* Teach *Python programming* to students aged *8–18* in small, engaging classes.\n* *Guide students from zero-based Python learning — starting with fundamental programming concepts, advancing to the Pygame Sprite Module, and eventually exploring basic game development.*\n* Foster creativity, problem-solving, and confidence through interactive learning.\n* Provide feedback and track student progress.\n\n*What We’re Looking For*\n\n* *Bachelor’s degree or higher.*\n* *Proficiency in Python*; experience with *Pygame* or *problem-solving algorithms* is preferred.\n* *Teaching or tutoring experience* with children or teenagers preferred.\n* Strong *communication* and *interpersonal skills*.\n* *English fluency* required, *Mandarin or Cantonese* a plus.\n\n*Hours & Pay*\n\n* *Flexible schedule* – mainly *after school hours and weekends*.\n* *$30 per hour*, depending on experience.\n* *Full-attendance bonus available for tutors with no absences or cancellations during the term.*\n\n*About ENJOY AI*\n\n*ENJOY AI* is a premier educational robotics and AI program designed specifically for young technology enthusiasts worldwide and a *global leader in AI robotics education and training*.\nWith a presence in *56 countries* and over *600,000 students*, we are committed to spreading knowledge of AI and robotics to youth across the globe.\n\nOur flagship program, the *ENJOY AI Global Youth AI Campaign*, includes:\n\n* *ENJOY AI Global Final* – Annual global championship.\n* *ENJOY AI Open* – Country-level competitions held annually.\n* *ENJOY AI Trial* – City/State-level competitions held annually.\n\nENJOY AI also partners with *U.S. News Global Education* and *IELTS*, providing outstanding participants with *pre-admission opportunities to prestigious universities worldwide*.\n\nJob Types: Part-time, Graduate, Casual\n\nPay: From $30.00 per hour\n\nBenefits:\n* Salary packaging\n\n\n\nEducation:\n* Bachelor Degree (Preferred)\n\nLanguage:\n* Mandarin or Cantonese (Required)\n\nLicence/Certification:\n* Working with Children Check (Preferred)\n\nWork Authorisation:\n* Australia (Preferred)\n\nWork Location: In person','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'ENJOY AI AU','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a2b18caa9112140d','scraped','3 days ago'),(2636,NULL,'job','Microsoft CSP Business Development Manager','Full-time','Macquarie Park NSW 2113',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'As one of the world’s leading IT distributors, we’re constantly seeking exceptional talent to help create and drive impact across the IT ecosystem. By joining our dynamic team, you’ll become part of a vibrant Australian workplace culture that celebrates success and is focused on what truly matters to our partners and vendors - being a valued added distributor! You’ll feel welcomed into an organisation that values diversity, fosters inclusion, and operates with a clear sense of purpose.\n\nIf you’re a seasoned professional, here is a great opportunity to develop your career in the technology industry alongside our network of best-in-class vendors and caring and collaborative co-workers.\n\nWe now have a great opportunity for a Business Development Manager within our Cloud business.\n\nAs the Microsoft CSP – Azure Business Development Manager, you will support the growth of Azure and Microsoft CSP outcomes across a defined set of channel partners. You will work with partners and internal teams to identify opportunities, assist with enablement activities, progress deals through the sales cycle, and maintain strong sales cadence and CRM discipline to meet agreed targets.\n\nKey responsibilities\n\n• Partner engagement: Build relationships with assigned partners and internal stakeholders; maintain regular contact to progress opportunities and action plans.\n\n• Opportunity management: Prospect within the partner base, qualify opportunities, and support partners to progress deals through to close.\n\n• Enablement and onboarding: Assist partners to understand Microsoft CSP offers, processes and tools; coordinate training and workshops with Microsoft and internal teams.\n\n• Solution knowledge: Maintain working knowledge of Azure, AI and Security offers and common partner use-cases (migration, modernisation, backup, security baseline, data/AI starters).\n\n• Sales cadence and reporting: Maintain pipeline hygiene, forecasting and activity tracking in CRM; provide regular updates to stakeholders.\n\n• Programs and incentives: Help partners access applicable Microsoft programs, incentives and promotions and ensure follow-through on required actions.\n\n• Collaboration: Work with customer success, operations, finance and marketing to deliver a smooth partner experience and resolve day-to-day issues.\n\n• Continuous improvement: Capture partner feedback, identify gaps and contribute ideas to improve partner tools, processes and campaigns.\n\nKnowledge, skills and experience\n\n• Experience: 1–3 years in business development, channel sales, inside sales or partner-facing roles within IT, software or cloud.\n\n• Learning mindset: Interest in building knowledge across Microsoft Azure and the partner ecosystem; ability to learn programs, tools and processes quickly.\n\n• Sales fundamentals: Comfortable prospecting, qualifying opportunities, following sales process and meeting activity targets.\n\n• Communication: Clear written and verbal communication; confident on calls and able to support basic presentations and enablement sessions.\n\n• Organisation: Strong time management and attention to detail; able to manage multiple partner requests and priorities.\n\n• Tools: Proficiency in Microsoft 365; experience using a CRM (HubSpot preferred) or willingness to learn.\n\n• Qualifications: Tertiary qualification in business, IT or related discipline (or equivalent experience) desirable.\n\n• Certifications (desirable): Azure Fundamentals (AZ-900) and/or AI-900 (or willingness to obtain within an agreed timeframe).\n\nWhats on offer\n\nBesides offering a very competitive remuneration package, we also offer:\n\n• Great team collaborative culture.\n\n• Great learning opportunities to grow professionally and personally through dedicated learning platforms, our education assistance program, focused individual development plans and from your co-workers.\n\n• Volunteering opportunities to give back to our community.\n\n• Flexible work arrangements.\n\n• Paid parental leave scheme including options to ramp up your hours back to your role, a great program that we are especially proud of;\n\n• Strong reward and recognition programs.\n\nIf you are seeking a new role or opportunity to further grow your sales and/ or business development career, we look forward to hearing from you soon!\n\nPlease note: candidates from Brisbane are also welcome to apply for this role.\n\nIf this role is not for you at this time or you are looking for other opportunities within Tech Data, you can join our Talent Communityhere\n\nKey Skills\nAtTech Data, a TD SYNNEX Company,our values guide everything we do: Together, We Own It, We Dare to Go, We Grow and Win, and above all, We Do the Right Thing. These principles shape how we work with each other, our partners, and our communities as we drive innovation and create lasting impact.\n\nWhat’s In It For You?\n\n• Elective Benefits: Our programs are tailored to your country to best accommodate your lifestyle.\n• Grow Your Career: Accelerate your path to success (and keep up with the future) with formal programs on leadership and professional development, and many more on-demand courses.\n• Elevate Your Personal Well-Being: Boost your financial, physical, and mental well-being through seminars, events, and our global Life Empowerment Assistance Program.\n• Diversity, Equity Inclusion: It’s not just a phrase to us; valuing every voice is how we succeed. Join us in celebrating our global diversity through inclusive education, meaningful peer-to-peer conversations, and equitable growth and development opportunities.\n• Make the Most of our Global Organization: Network with other new co-workers within your first 30 days through our onboarding program.\n• Connect with Your Community: Participate in internal, peer-led inclusive communities and activities, including business resource groups, local volunteering events, and more environmental and social initiatives.\n\nDon’t meet every single requirement? Apply anyway.\nAt Tech Data, a TD SYNNEX Company, we’re proud to be recognized as a great place to work and a leader in the promotion and practice of diversity, equity and inclusion. If you’re excited about working for our company and believe you’re a good fit for this role, we encourage you to apply. You may be exactly the person we’re looking for!\n\nWe are an equal opportunity employer and committed to building a diverse team that represents and empowers a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment based on merit, without regard to race, colour, religion, national origin, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, protected veteran status, disability, genetics, age, or any other characteristic protected by law. To support our diversity and inclusion efforts, we may ask for voluntary gender disclosure information. This data will be used solely to improve our hiring practices and ensure fair treatment for all candidates.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'TD Synnex','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=44953d29a3adc92f','scraped','2 days ago'),(2637,NULL,'job','Senior Associate - Resources & Energy','Permanent','Perth WA 6000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'AI Job Summary\nAt least five years’ post-admission experience.\nSenior Associate experience in mining, oil & gas, renewable energy or native title.\nExperience advising complex matters for mid to large Australian clients across WA and QLD.\n Sign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nPermanent • Full-time • LP – Senior Associate\nDescription\n\nHopgoodGanim is a leading independent Australian law firm, known for delivering exceptional outcomes for our clients while staying deeply connected to the communities in which we work. We are proud to be a firm where people genuinely enjoy coming to work. Our lawyers are trusted with challenging, meaningful matters and supported to grow through a culture that is inclusive, collaborative and uncompromising on our values.\n\nAbout the role\n\nJoin our Perth-based Resources & Energy team as a Senior Associate. You will be part of a collaborative, high‑performing projects and commercial work group with exposure to some of the most dynamic work in the energy and resources sector. This role offers both breadth of experience and the opportunity to build a meaningful specialisation aligned to your interests and strengths.\n\nWork as part of a multi‑disciplinary team advising across mining, oil and gas, renewable energy and native title\nBe mentored by three recognised partners, each providing strong technical guidance and support\nJoin a team known for its supportive, collaborative culture\nGain broad exposure across practice areas, with the opportunity to develop a specialisation aligned to your interests and capabilities\nAdvise on interesting and complex matters for mid to large Australian clients across WA and QLD, including:\nMining company acquisitions and divestments, due diligence, farm-in, joint ventures, split commodity and royalty agreements, land access, native title and heritage negotiations.\nUpstream and midstream oil & gas projects, including project development, joint ventures and long-term commercial arrangements.\nDecarbonisation projects, supporting some of Australia’s largest companies as they reduce emissions\nRenewable energy matters, including utility‑scale developments, BESS, and green development projects for traditional owner groups\n\nAbout You\n\nYou are an experienced and motivated Senior Associate who enjoys working on complex matters, building strong client relationships and contributing to a supportive team environment. You will also bring:\n\nAt least five years’ post‑admission experience\nDemonstrated experience at Senior Associate level in one or more of mining, oil and gas, renewable energy or native title, within an Australian or overseas law firm\nA genuine motivation to expand your knowledge and expertise, with the flexibility to engage across new work areas\nStrong drafting and negotiation skills, with the ability to lead discrete project components and deliver high‑quality client outcomes\nProven ability to build trusted client relationships through clear communication, responsiveness and professional judgement\nA collaborative, team‑oriented mindset, with a commitment to mentoring and supporting junior lawyers\n\nAt HopgoodGanim, you’re not just a small piece of a big machine; you’re a valued, integral member of the team. We are committed to delivering exceptional service and while being recognised for our deeply connected and collaborative culture, shared by a team of people who have a genuine love for the work we do. As a law firm of just over 300 people nationally, HopgoodGanim offers flexible and hybrid working arrangements and a number of benefits including:\n\nDedicated learning & development programs for all employees\nRealistic billable targets for legal practitioners\nPractitioner performance and new client incentives\nA dedicated in-house business development team to build your external profile\nPathways to Partnership program for legal practitioners\nClear annual review and promotion cycle\nOnsite gym and end-of-trip facilities\nAccess to paid parental leave (up to 20 weeks for eligible employees)\nPaid fertility leave\nPaid birthday leave – because your day should be celebrated!\nFun mid-year and end-of-year team celebrations including our HG Way Awards night\nEmployee assistance program and wellbeing initiatives','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Employment Hero','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=68f2622292173316','scraped','2 days ago'),(2638,NULL,'job','Remote Founding Team Opportunities - AutoCyber AI','Permanent','Remote',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'*Remote Founding Team Opportunities - AutoCyber AI*\n\n*Type:* Internship (Unpaid) / Expression of Interest for Future Paid Roles\n*Location:* Remote\n\n*About Us*\n\nAutoCyber AI is an Australian, remote-first startup building *AI-driven cybersecurity and compliance products*.\n\nWe focus on:\n\n* Secure, privacy-first systems\n* Agentic AI for real-world use\n* Practical tools for businesses, not theory\n\nWe’re early-stage, execution-focused, and building fast.\n\n*The Opportunity*\n\nWe’re not hiring traditionally.\n\nWe’re building a *Founding Talent Network* — a group of high-potential individuals who want to contribute early and grow with the company.\n\n*Open Tracks*\n\n* Customer Success & Product Enablement\n* Full Stack Development\n* Frontend / UI/UX\n* Sales & Outreach\n* Programs & Partnerships\n\nYou may be matched to one or more tracks.\n\n*What You’ll Actually Do*\n\nDepending on your track:\n\n* Work on real product features\n* Support customers and onboarding\n* Contribute to growth and outreach\n* Improve UX and usability\n* Help shape early-stage systems\n\nThis is *hands-on execution*, not observation.\n\n*Who This Is For*\n\nYou’re:\n\n* A strong communicator\n* Quick to learn\n* Comfortable with ambiguity\n* Self-driven and reliable\n* Interested in AI, cybersecurity, or SaaS\n\nNo coding required for non-technical tracks.\n\n*Who This Is NOT For*\n\n* Passive applicants\n* People looking for structured corporate roles\n* Those expecting immediate paid positions\n\n*What You’ll Gain*\n\n* Real startup experience\n* Exposure to AI cybersecurity products\n* Priority for future paid roles\n* Direct involvement in building something early\n\n*How We Work*\n\n* Remote-first, structured but flexible\n* Calm internally, professional externally\n* High ownership, low micromanagement\n* Execution over theory\n\n*Why This Matters*\n\nEarly-stage startups are built by people who show up early.\n\nThis is your chance to:\n\n* Get inside\n* Contribute\n* Grow with the company\n\n*How to Apply*\n\nApply here:\nhttps://forms.gle/qdo2iy3fj9A2toZz9\n\n*Important*\n\nBefore applying:\nFollow our page for updates, selection rounds, and future opportunities.\n\nWe prioritise candidates who stay engaged.\n\n*Want to stand out?*\n\nComment your preferred track (1–5) on the linkedin post or reach out directly.\n\n\n\nApplication Question(s):\n* Are you comfortable taking ownership of customer-facing challenges, learning complex products quickly, and proactively solving problems in a remote startup environment? \n* Are you confident guiding customers through new technology, answering questions clearly, and helping build trust from first interaction?\n* Can you quickly learn technical products independently and confidently explain them to customers in a clear, professional way?\n\nWork Location: Remote','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'AutoCyber AI','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9927dfa341270c32','scraped','3 days ago'),(2639,NULL,'job','Senior Developer','','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Position Purpose:\n\nServe as a Senior Full Stack Developer responsible for designing and delivering high-quality features\nHands-on development role while contributing to and influencing the overall technical direction of the product.\nTake ownership of feature technical design across the full stack, including cloud infrastructure.\nMentor and support junior engineers, fostering best practices and continuous improvement within the team.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nDesign and develop product software using appropriate modelling techniques, adhering to agreed design standards, patterns, and methodologies. Balance complexity, business requirements, cost, and timelines to achieve optimal outcomes for customers and the business.\nCreate and communicate multiple architectural and design views to address stakeholder concerns and ensure alignment with both functional and non-functional requirements.\nDevelop models and prototypes to validate proposed designs, secure stakeholder approval, and enable effective implementation.\nRecommend and refine designs that consider current and target environments, performance, security, and integration with existing systems. Conduct design reviews, providing constructive feedback to improve quality across the team.\nAnalyse and document the technical impact of new product features and architectural enhancements, including estimating effort and identifying dependencies.\nContribute to the selection of appropriate software development approaches to meet quality standards, delivery timelines, and risk management objectives.\nApply agreed development standards, tools, and best practices to deliver robust, scalable, and maintainable software solutions.\n\nEssential Skills and Experience:\n\nDemonstrated expertise in software design patterns and coding best practices\nAI Assisted Development – tools like GitHub Copilot to write, review, debug code\nPrompt Engineering\nExperience in SaaS-based full stack development, with proficiency in Java and modern JavaScript frameworks.\nHands-on experience with Spring (or similar backend frameworks).\nExperience working with frontend frameworks such as Angular or React.\nProven experience designing and implementing infrastructure-as-code on AWS, including services such as CloudFormation, CDK, load balancers, EC2, S3, Lambda, and container-based runtime environments.\nSolid understanding of CI/CD principles and experience with tools such as GitHub, CircleCI, CodePipeline, or Bamboo.\nStrong problem-solving and system design capabilities.\nAbility to mentor, coach, and effectively share knowledge within the team.\nProven track record of proactive contribution across the Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC).\n\nDesirable Skills and Experience:\n\nPrevious experience with monolithic to microservices App migration\nExperience with NoSQL/Document/Vector databases\nPerformance optimizations with data caching and related designs\nHave worked in Data pipelines/ETL\nApplication monitoring with CloudWatch, New Relic\nRAG Pipeline Design\n\nQualifications:\n\nBachelor of Computer Science degree or equivalent academic qualification','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Infomedia','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=17f926f34f121904','scraped','3 days ago'),(2640,NULL,'job','Optimisation Manager','','Macquarie Park NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'At Metcash, you’re part of something bigger. We’ve got the heart of a small business with the strength and support of a big business. When you join Metcash, your work makes a real difference to independent businesses and local communities, empowering you to:\n\nGrow your career with tailored development programs\nMake your mark in a high-performing, values-led team\nThrive your way with flexible work options\n\nAbout the Opportunity\n\nAt Metcash, we’re transforming how IT operates—making it simpler, smarter, and more customer-focused. We’re looking for an IT Optimisation Manager who can improve processes, drive change, and partner with stakeholders to deliver real impact.\n\nIn this role, you’ll work closely with IT leaders to identify opportunities to standardise and simplify processes, embed change, and uplift capability. You’ll also act as a trusted advisor, coaching leaders through change initiatives while leading key optimisation projects end-to-end.\n\nIn this Role, You Will:\n\nPartner with IT stakeholders and offshore teams to identify and implement process improvements across IT demand, contracts, time sheeting, and controls, including driving AI-led productivity initiatives\nLead IT tools rationalisation and optimisation projects end-to-end, acting as Project Manager to deliver standardisation and efficiency outcomes\nCoach leaders and project teams on change management practices, ensuring successful adoption and maintaining the IT Change Heat Map for visibility and alignment\nCollaborate with Change & Communications teams and support PI Planning to deliver a consistent, customer-centric IT experience\n\nYou’ll bring:\n\nStrong experience in IT environments, with a focus on projects, process improvement, and transformation\nProven ability to lead change initiatives in complex environments\nSolid understanding of change management frameworks (Prosci, AMPG or similar preferred)\nConfidence to coach, influence, and engage stakeholders at all levels\nExceptional communication and storytelling skills, with the ability to simplify complex ideas\nA proactive mindset with strong planning, organisation, and problem-solving skills\nExperience in learning, capability uplift, and stakeholder engagement\n\nWhat’s on Offer\n\n️ Extra Leave: 5th week of annual leave, 2 well-being days, 1 volunteer day\nCareer Growth: Endless learning and development opportunities\nParental Leave: 12 weeks of gender-neutral paid leave for primary carers\nInclusive Culture: Bronze Employer for LGBTQ Inclusion\n ️ Neutral Pay Gap: Gender pay gap under 5% (WGEA 2024–2025)\nMental Health: Gold accreditation by Mental Health Australia\nFlexibility: Flex Ready and Family Friendly Workplace accredited\n\nAbout Us\n\nMetcash is Australia’s leading wholesale distribution company, with $19.5 billion in sales (FY25) and a proud spot in the ASX Top 125. We believe in the power of independent, family-owned businesses to shape vibrant communities. Through our food, liquor, and hardware pillars, we help retailers become the ‘Best Store in Their Town’ by providing merchandising, operational and marketing support.\nWe’re committed to diversity, inclusion, and sustainability — and we welcome applicants from all backgrounds, including First Nations. If you need support during the application process, just let us know. Your privacy and dignity are always respected.\n\nJoin us and be part of something bigger!\n\n#INFLA\n\n#LI-SS1','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Metcash','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=aa94d8ff8618de42','scraped','2 days ago'),(2641,NULL,'job','Client Care Counsellor','Part-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About us:\n\nSpectrum.Life is a whole-of-health digital partner delivering clinically backed digital health, mental health and wellbeing solutions internationally to over 7.2 million insurance members, 3,000 corporate clients, and 650,000 university students. Established in 2018, we employ over 450 people and our vision is simple: to change and save as many lives as possible.\n\nWe are not a traditional EAP. We are a clinically led digital health partner building something genuinely different for the Australian market — integrating AI-assisted triage, innovative technology, and a multidisciplinary clinical team united by one mission.\n\nRole Brief:\n\nWhy Spectrum.Life\n\n- Clinical depth at scale.\nYou will work within a stepped care model designed to PHN standards, backed by a clinical governance framework that takes quality seriously. Your clinical decisions matter and are supported.\n\n- Industry-leading tools.\nSpectrum.Life integrates AI-assisted triage, digital outcome measurement, and a best-in-class telehealth platform. You will be working at the frontier of what clinically governed digital mental health looks like in practice.\n\n- Real flexibility.\nRemote, part-time through to full-time, with a schedule that can flex to your life. We trust our clinicians to work independently and we build our model around that trust.\n\n- Supervision and CPD included.\nIndividual clinical supervision is provided in-house, alongside access to professional development pathways that support your growth — clinically and professionally.\n\n- Meaningful work.\nEvery contact matters. Our outcomes data shows it. When you work at Spectrum.Life, you are part of a service that measurably changes lives.\n\nThe Role\nThis is a front-line clinical role within our Band 2 stepped care pathway. As a Client Care Counsellor, you will carry two core responsibilities from the moment a client makes contact:\n\nTriage — rapid, structured clinical assessment to determine the right care pathway at first contact.\nSingle Session Therapy (SST) — purposeful, evidence-based brief intervention where one well-structured session is complete and sufficient.\n\nYou will take calls on demand across a 24/7 service, delivering support to clients when they need it — including evenings, weekends, and public holidays on a rostered basis. A typical shift involves up to 8 consultations, combining on-demand triage contacts and pre-scheduled SST sessions.\n\nYou will work fully remotely from anywhere in Australia, supporting individuals experiencing mild to moderate mental health difficulties including anxiety, depression, work-related stress, and adjustment challenges. You will work within a NICE-aligned, clinically governed model with real infrastructure, real supervision, and technology that works with you.\n\nThis is not a role for practitioners who need multiple sessions to orient before acting clinically. Every contact requires immediate clinical judgement.\n\n24/7\nOn-demand service\nCalls come in when clients need them, across all days and hours Up to 8\nConsultations per day\nScheduled and on-demand contacts across your shift 1–6\nSessions per client\nBrief, purposeful intervention. One session can be enough.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\nTake calls on demand as part of a 24/7 rostered service — responding to clients when they make contact, not when it is convenient. Your shift may include evenings, weekends, or public holiday cover on a rotating roster.\nTriage incoming contacts through structured clinical assessment — determining risk level, presenting need, and the right care pathway at first contact. Triage is a clinical act, not an administrative one.\nDeliver up to 8 consultations per day across your shift, combining on-demand triage contacts and pre-scheduled Single Session Therapy sessions.\nDeliver Single Session Therapy and brief structured counselling (1–6 sessions) via phone, video, and live chat using evidence-based approaches including CBT, Behavioural Activation, Problem-Solving Therapy, and Person-Centred brief models.\nConduct structured mental health assessments, clinical formulations (5-P model), and risk assessments at every contact — including suicidality, self-harm, domestic violence, and safeguarding.\nUse validated outcome measures (CORE-10, PHQ-9, GAD-7, K10, ORS, SRS, WSAS) as active clinical tools to guide treatment planning, stepped care routing, and progress review.\nMake evidence-based stepped care decisions — stepping clients up, across, or down as clinically indicated, with documented rationale.\nMaintain accurate, timely clinical case notes that document reasoning, risk, and clinical decisions promptly after each contact.\nWork confidently within AI-integrated digital platforms, maintaining full clinical accountability for all decisions — including those that follow AI-assisted triage.\nConnect clients with relevant community supports and referral pathways as a clinical decision, not an afterthought.\nEngage actively with clinical supervision, CPD, and team governance processes.\n\nRequirements:\n\nAQF Level 7 minimum — Bachelor of Counselling, Graduate Diploma, accredited Bachelor or qualifying Master of Social Work, or equivalent.\nCurrent full membership with ACA (Level 2+), PACFA (Registered Counsellor or Clinical Member), or AASW (full member) — active, not provisional or lapsed.\nMinimum 2 years post-qualification clinical mental health experience (direct client-facing; pre-qualification placements excluded).\nDemonstrated competence with brief structured therapeutic models and documented, regular structured risk assessment practice.\nComfortable working across a 24/7 rostered service — including availability for evening, weekend, and public holiday shifts.\nConfident delivering via telehealth modalities — phone, video, and live chat.\nDigitally confident — comfortable with digital case management, PROMs tools, and AI-assisted platforms.\nAccurate, timely clinical documentation completed promptly after each contact.\nActive CPD plan and regular clinical supervision engagement.\nWorking knowledge of mandatory reporting obligations, Privacy Act 1988, and Australian Privacy Principles in a digital health context.\nCultural safety awareness — knowledge of the SEWB framework and culturally safe practice for First Nations peoples and CALD communities.\n\nDesirable:\n\nEAP, PHN-funded, or primary care mental health experience.\nFormal SST training (Talmon / Hoyt / Young model) or supervised SST practice.\nSolution-Focused Brief Therapy (SFBT) competency.\niCBT or guided self-help delivery experience.\nPrior experience with AI-integrated clinical platforms.\nDual PACFA / AASW registration.\nSecond language relevant to Australian CALD communities.\nExperience with children, young people, or workplace mental health.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Spectrum Life','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=274951ee5063e3db','scraped','3 days ago'),(2642,NULL,'job','Manager, Sales Engineering','Full-time','Remote',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'SailPoint is the leading, AI-driven security platform providing the autonomous governance that best solves the needs for the modern enterprise. SailPoint makes it possible to automate and streamline the identity journey. We marry technical expertise with business acumen to deliver identity security that will drive business forward.\n\nWe are proud of our team and the culture we have built which has led to our employees voting us “best places to work” – 15 years in a row.\n\nThe role:\n\nSailPoint is seeking a Solution Engineering Manager to support our A/NZ solution engineering team. You will play a critical role in growing SailPoint’s business by building and leading a high performing team of Solution Engineers. Our Solution Engineers play a vital role in demonstrating and communicating the value of SailPoint’s products and thought leadership to our prospective customers in the Identity Governance market.\n\nWhat you will do:\n\nHire, coach, and drive an outstanding Solution Engineering team to deliver against assigned goals\n\nManage individual and team performance ensuring that we are taking the necessary actions to maintain high levels of performance\n\nDemonstrate analytical and problem-solving skills, and strong management consulting skills to influence thinking or gain acceptance of multiple customer constituencies\n\nWork to improve the SailPoint sales methodology and processes effectively, including development of product presentations and demonstrations tailored to our partners requirements and tuned to suit the level and nature of the audience\n\nAssess gaps in evolving training needs and then create and implement programs to improve sales, product and technology skills of the Sales Engineering team\n\nWork with Regional Sales directors on account planning, strategy, and sales call activity\n\nProvide timely and insightful input back to other corporate functions, particularly field sales, product management and marketing\n\nManage relationships with product teams & decision makers both internally and externally\n\nWhat we are looking for:\n\nPrevious experience, 5+ years as a sales engineering manager and 5+ years as a sales engineer\n\nExcellent communication skills including experience speaking to a technical and business audiences\n\nThe ideal candidate will already have a good understanding of the solutions, market dynamics and best practices in the Identity Security market\n\nPath to Success:\n\nWithin 30 Days:\n\nOnboarded and met all team members and sales leaders the territory supports.\n\nWithin 60 Days:\n\nFamiliar with business and top opportunities and established cadences with peers, sales, and team members.\n\nWithin 90 Days:\n\nComplete product training and into rhythm with team members, peers, and leadership.\n\nWithin 1-Year:\n\nContinue in full partnership with sales leaders and trust of your team while achieving budget for the sales territories supported.\n\nEducation:\n\nPreferred, not required: Bachelor’s in Computer Science or global equivalent experience\n\nSailPoint is an equal opportunity employer and we welcome all qualified candidates to apply to join our team. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, protected veteran status, or any other category protected by applicable law.\n\nAlternative methods of applying for employment are available to individuals unable to submit an application through this site because of a disability. Contact applicationassistance@sailpoint.com or mail to 11120 Four Points Dr, Suite 100, Austin, TX 78726, to discuss reasonable accommodations. NOTE: Any unsolicited resumes sent by candidates or agencies to this email will not be considered for current openings at SailPoint.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'SailPoint','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=956bf03e96b8b316','scraped','2 days ago'),(2643,NULL,'job','2026 Datacom Australia - Graduate Cloud Associate','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Kick‑start your cloud career and help shape the future of Tech!\nAs a Graduate Cloud Associate, you’ll work alongside experienced Cloud and DevOps professionals to design, build and optimise cloud environments for real customers. You’ll gain hands‑on experience across AWS, Azure, automation tools and modern platforms — all while learning best practices that set you up for a long-term career in cloud engineering.\n\nThis role is perfect for curious problem solvers who love technology, enjoy learning new tools, and want to make a real impact from day one.\n\nOur Why\n\nDatacom works with organisations and communities across Australia and New Zealand to make a difference in people’s lives and help organisations use the power of tech to innovate and grow.\n\nWhat you\'ll be doing\n\nAs part of our cloud team, you’ll:\n\nSupport customers to build, migrate and optimise cloud environments using AWS and/or Azure.\nHelp resolve technical incidents and service requests, investigating issues and learning how to troubleshoot cloud-based systems.\nLearn and apply Infrastructure as Code (IaC) practices to automate and standardise deployments.\nAssist with cloud migrations, automation and DevOps workflows, including CI/CD pipelines.\nContribute to the creation and maintenance of coding, implementation and design standards.\nParticipate in planning and delivery of work packages, tracking progress and celebrating wins.\nCreate and maintain documentation such as solution designs, test plans and support guides.\nGet hands-on with automation, orchestration and modern toolchains that power scalable systems.\nCollaborate with teammates, mentors and customers to continuously learn and improve.\nWhat we’re looking for\n\nWe’re not expecting you to know everything — we’re looking for potential, curiosity and a willingness to learn.\n\nYou’ll thrive in this role if you have:\n\nA degree or relevent qualification in IT, Computer Science, Engineering or a related field.\nExposure to cloud platforms such as AWS or Microsoft Azure through study, labs, projects or internships.\nA basic understanding of scripting or coding (e.g. PowerShell, Python, or similar).\nFamiliarity with concepts like DevOps, CI/CD, containers or automation — even at a foundational level.\nInterest in Infrastructure as Code tools such as Terraform, Ansible or GitHub.\nCuriosity about AI tools and prompt engineering, and how they can enhance productivity.\nStrong problem‑solving skills and a proactive mindset.\nGood communication skills and the ability to learn collaboratively.\n\nAbout our Early Careers Programme\n\nAs a graduate, you’ll be supported by our dedicated Early Careers Team throughout your first 12 months. We’ll guide you through onboarding, mentoring, events, workshops, and ongoing development opportunities—ensuring you’re set up for success while you settle into your new permanent role.\n\nWhy join us here at Datacom?\n\nDatacom is one of Australia and New Zealand’s largest suppliers of Information Technology professional services. We have managed to maintain a dynamic, agile, small business feel that is often diluted in larger organisations of our size. It\'s our people that give Datacom its unique culture and energy that you can feel from the moment you meet with us.\n\nWe care about our people and provide a range of perks such as social events, chill-out spaces, remote working, flexi-hours and professional development courses to name a few. You’ll have the opportunity to learn, develop your career, connect and bring your true self to work. You will be recognised and valued for your contributions and be able to do your work in a collegial, flat-structured environment.\n\n#LI-DNI\n\nRequirements\n\nAustralian Citizenship\nCurrently living in Sydney, Australia\nAvailable full time from May 2026','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Datacom','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a37ec2f30ea98fd0','scraped','3 days ago'),(2644,NULL,'job','Client Executive Lead','Full-time','Perth WA 6000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We power insights for better, safer workplaces…together.\n\nAre you ready to be Kin-at-i-can? As our Client Executive Lead, you’ll own a portfolio of Enterprise accounts, lead a high-performing team, and sit at the intersection of client strategy, product collaboration, and commercial growth. You’ll do it at a company that’s genuinely changing the way organisations manage workforce compliance, and you’ll have the tools, the trust, and the technology to do it well.\n\nIf you’re a senior client leader who loves building relationships, driving outcomes, and working in an environment where innovation is part of the everyday. Read on.\n\nAbout Kinatico\n\nKinatico is an ASX-listed Reg-Tech company with a product suite built on nearly two decades of trust. Our background screening platform, Kinatico CVCheck, has been in market since 2005 and today is serving over 10,000 organisations, has helped more than 1.6 million individuals meet regulatory requirements, and processes over 900,000 secure verifications every year. That kind of scale and longevity is rare in this space, and it gives our sales team something genuinely compelling to take to market. Alongside Kinatico CVCheck, our newest product Kinatico Compliance is a simple, secure and synchronised platform that gives organisations everything they need to manage their people’s compliance in one centralised place. From automated workflows and real-time credential tracking to proactive alerts and seamless HRIS integration, it’s designed to reduce admin burden and keep organisations audit-ready at every stage of the employee lifecycle. For a sales professional, this means you’re walking into conversations backed by a product with genuine market credibility, a strong reference base, and a clear growth story still being written.\n\nWe’re a team of curious, committed people who care about doing good work and making a real difference. We move quickly, think commercially, and back each other.\n\nOUR TEAM’S STRENGTH COMES FROM EVERYONE’S INDIVIDUALITY\n\nWhat you’ll bring:\n\nYou’re a commercially sharp, relationship-led senior professional who knows how to grow accounts, lead teams, and get things done. You’re just as comfortable in a strategic account planning session as you are on a call with a client who needs a trusted voice. You bring:\n\nSignificant experience in senior client management, account direction, or client partner roles, ideally within B2B software, SaaS, or technology-enabled services\nA proven track record of retaining and growing Enterprise accounts against revenue targets\nDemonstrated experience leading, coaching, and developing a high-performing team\nDeep knowledge of workforce compliance, HCM software, or adjacent HR technology solutions\nFamiliarity with structured sales methodologies (Miller Heiman or equivalent) and the discipline to apply them consistently\nA data-driven mindset, comfortable using Salesforce, reporting dashboards, and AI-assisted tools to make better decisions and manage your team more effectively\nGenuine curiosity about how technology (including AI) can improve client outcomes and team ways of working, without any expectation of being a technical expert\nDemonstrated experience working within or alongside compliance, workforce screening, background verification, or regulatory technology environments. You understand the stakes involved when organisations are making trust-critical decisions about their people, and you know how to speak the language of risk, obligation, and assurance with clients\nHuman resource, recruitment, or workplace safety experience is a bonus\n\nDELIVERING THE GOOD, STRIVING FOR THE GREAT\n\nAbout the role:\n\nThis is a senior commercial leadership role with real scope and real impact. You’ll manage a portfolio of Kinatico’s Enterprise clients, driving retention, growth, and satisfaction, while leading a team of Client Executives and owning the processes and rhythm that keep everything running smoothly.\n\nYou’ll also play a meaningful role in how Kinatico evolves. You’ll be the voice of the customer in product conversations, the bridge between clients and internal teams, and a champion for modern, technology-enabled ways of working. AI tools and intelligent insights will be part of how you work, not a stretch goal, just how things get done.\n\nWhat you’ll be doing:\n\nOwn and grow a portfolio of Enterprise accounts, driving retention, expansion, and outstanding client satisfaction\nBuild trusted, senior-level relationships across your clients’ organisations and act as a genuine strategic advisor\nLead, coach, and develop your team of Client Executives to achieve individual and collective performance goals\nEstablish and maintain team operating cadences (pipeline reviews, account planning, performance check-ins) so everyone knows where they stand and what’s next\nDefine and continuously improve the team’s account management processes, building playbooks and frameworks that scale best practice\nUse AI-assisted tools and CRM data to strengthen account strategies, improve forecasting, and move from instinct-led to insight-led decisions\nCollaborate with Product, Engineering, and Marketing teams to shape solutions that genuinely meet customer needs\nPresent and demonstrate Kinatico’s solutions, translating complex compliance capabilities into clear, compelling business value\nContribute to roadmap discussions and ensure the voice of your clients is heard in product prioritisation\nRepresent Kinatico at industry events and contribute to the organisation’s growth story\n\nARE YOU READY TO BE A KINATICAN?\n\nWhere our passion, talent, delivery and impact collide our purpose lies. Powering insights for better, safer workplaces, helping organisations to know their people, we are a global leader in Reg-Tech. Our technology helps organisations to know their people.\n\nFlexible and supportive work environment\nA culture of development and recognition, we want our people to thrive!\nAttend our Friday Funaticans in person and virtual events\nBright, spacious office in the Perth CBD\nWork for an ASX listed company and a leader in Reg-Tech\nJoin the company at an incredibly exciting time and enter a world of energy, enthusiasm and innovation\n\nResearch shows that while men apply to jobs when they meet an average of 60% of the criteria, women and other marginalised individuals tend to only apply when they check every box. If you think you have what it takes (a growth mindset) but don’t necessarily meet every single point on the job description, please still get in touch. We’d love to have a chat and see if you could be a great fit.\n\nApply Now!','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Kinatico','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=7d8099d1c309cf57','scraped','3 days ago'),(2645,NULL,'job','eCommerce Marketing & Content Specialist','Permanent','Inner West NSW',NULL,'',72500.00,'$70,000 - $75,000 a year','*eCommerce Marketing & Content Specialist *\n\n*Part-Time 20 - 25 hrs p/week | 2 positions to fill*\n\nUnboxed Talent is proud to be partnering with an amazing Australian entrepreneur. An owner operator of 2 fast-growing eCommerce brands. The success of both brands has been built, not just by running ads but by building brands that grow through the right content. Each brand has a clear identity, strong community, and serious growth potential.\n\nThe 2 brands are truly amazing: Beautiful personalised handmade bags and accessories and one of Australia\'s leading footcare brands.\n\nFast growth means it\'s now time to invest in 2 x eCommerce and Content Specialists to be a key factor in taking the business to its next level. The success of this business is a result of posting not just good, but great content. Not stuff where it\'s a hope for the best approach. They test, learn and scale what works. And it is working. If you are someone who loves turning ideas into content and content into revenue, keep reading.\n\n*What you\'ll be doing!*\n\n* Plan, launch, and optimise Meta ad campaigns (this is a core focus)\n* Create high-performing short-form content (Reels, ads, UGC-style)\n* Manage and grow social media / community across both brands\n* Write and execute EDM campaigns via Klaviyo\n* Continuously test hooks, creatives, and angles - this business moves fast!\n* Use AI tools to generate ideas and improve performance\n* Schedule and manage content through Planoly\n* Support Shopify operations and product launches\n* Work closely with the founder to execute and scale winning ideas\n\n*What You\'ll Bring*\n\n* Experience with Meta Ads - you understand testing, structure, and scaling\n* Strong content instincts - you know what makes people stop scrolling\n* Comfortable creating and editing video (CapCut, Canva, etc.)\n* Experience with EDMs (Klaviyo is a bonus)\n* A self-starter - confident taking ownership of projects and figuring things out!\n* Data-driven - you optimise based on results, not guesswork\n* Comfortable using AI tools (ChatGPT, Claude, etc.)\n\n*It\'s a bonus if you:*\n\n* Already use AI daily in your workflow\n* Have previously worked with eCommerce or product-based brands\n* Have created ads or content that has actually performed\n\n*Why This Role Is Different*\n\n* You’ll work directly with the founder, no layers, no slow approvals\n* Your ideas actually get tested and executed\n* You’ll work across two brands, not just one!\n* Ongoing support and training in Meta Ads\n* Fast-moving environment where you’ll grow quickly\n* Permanent part-time role (20-25 hrs/week)\n\n*IMPORTANT*\n\nThis is *not* a social media manager role.\n\nWe’re looking for someone who wants to test, learn, and improve constantly and cares about performance, not just posting.\n\n*Apply ... *Send your resume, including any links to content, ads or work you\'ve created to *helen@unboxedtalent.com.au*\n\nPay: $70,000.00 – $75,000.00 per year\n\nBenefits:\n* Employee discount\n* Employee mentoring program\n* Professional development assistance\n* Work from home\n\nWork Location: Hybrid remote in Inner West NSW','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Unboxed Talent','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6c5fbc939aac09c7','scraped','Just posted'),(2646,NULL,'job','Manager Talent Acquisition, Supply Chain','Full-time','Macquarie Park NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'CHEP helps move more goods to more people, in more places than any other organization on earth via our 347 million pallets, crates and containers. We employ approximately 13,000 people and operate in 60 countries. Through our pioneering and sustainable share-and-reuse business model, the world’s biggest brands trust us to help them transport their goods more efficiently, safely and with less environmental impact.\n\nWhat does that mean for you? You’ll join an international organization big enough to take you anywhere, and small enough to get you there sooner. You’ll help change how goods get to market and contribute to global sustainability. You’ll be empowered to bring your authentic self to work and be surrounded by diverse and driven professionals. And you can maximize your work-life balance and flexibility through our Hybrid Work Model .\n\nJob Description\n\nAt CHEP , we help move essential goods, reduce waste and make supply chains more resilient and sustainable. As part of Brambles , we operate at global scale — but it’s the decisions our people make every day that create real-world impact.\n\nWe’re now looking for a Manager, Talent Acquisition – Supply Chain to lead the end-to-end hiring strategy for our Supply Chain workforce across Australia.\n\nThis is a hands-on leadership role where you’ll shape how we attract, assess and hire talent across executive, professional and frontline roles — while building a future-ready, inclusive workforce that underpins business performance. As part of a global HR function, you will also have the opportunity to contribute to global best practice through HR programs of work\n\nYour impact in this role\n\nYou’ll be a trusted partner to Supply Chain and HR leaders, owning the Talent Acquisition strategy and translating workforce plans into scalable, high-quality hiring outcomes. This is an opportunity to build the function embedding automation and building best practice maturity for hiring across our network.\n\nWhat you\'ll expect:\n\nLead end-to-end Talent Acquisition, guiding a small team of talent professionals across the Supply Chain function, balancing strategic leadership with hands-on delivery.\n\nAct as a strategic advisor to senior leaders on talent risk, succession, internal mobility and workforce sustainability.\n\nEmbed DEI, EVP activation and workforce planning into hiring strategies to create sustainable pipelines.\n\nDrive operational excellence, governance and compliance across high-volume, professional and executive hiring.\n\nLeverage Workday ATS, AI-enabled tools and talent analytics to improve speed, quality and candidate experience, moving from manual to automated discipline across our sites.\n\nContributing to the AMETA TA Leadership Team, sharing insights and shaping regional and global TA capability.\n\nWhat you’ll bring\n\nProven experience leading Talent Acquisition in an operations frontline environment, ideally supply chain, logistics, manufacturing, industrial or similar.\n\nStrong capability translating business strategy into scalable, agile hiring models and influencing leader mindset within an established business to embed change.\n\nExperience leading recruitment transformation, including ATS optimisation, AI tools and automation, through demonstrated curiosity and root cause problem solving.\n\nA track record of EVP activation, campaign hiring and DEI-led approaches in competitive labour markets.\n\nConfidence operating as a trusted advisor to senior leaders in complex, fast-paced environments.\n\nDemonstrated ability to build engaged, resilient TA teams.\n\nWhy join CHEP / Brambles\n\nBe part of a global organisation with real-world purpose.\n\nWork in a culture grounded in trust, accountability and inclusion.\n\nAccess strong career development and internal mobility opportunities.\n\nShape strategic outcomes while staying close to delivery and impact.\n\nRemote Type\n\nHybrid Remote\n\nSkills to succeed in the role\n\nCoaching, Collaboration, Compliance and Adaptability, Data-Driven Insights, Disruptive Thinking, Diversity and Inclusion in Hiring, Employer Branding, Feedback, Inclusive Leadership, Leading Change, Leading Customer Centric Teams, Mentorship, Motivating Teams, Prioritization, Project Delivery, Recruitment Technology, Relationship Management, Self-Awareness, Talent Sourcing and Acquisition, Vendor Management\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer, and we are committed to developing a diverse workforce in which everyone is treated fairly, with respect, and has the opportunity to contribute to business success while realizing his or her potential. This means harnessing the unique skills and experience that each individual brings and we do not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because of race, color, sex, age, national origin, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity, status as a veteran, and basis of disability or any other federal, state, or local protected class.\n\nIndividuals fraudulently misrepresenting themselves as Brambles or CHEP representatives have scheduled interviews and offered fraudulent employment opportunities with the intent to commit identity theft or solicit money. Brambles and CHEP never conduct interviews via online chat or request money as a term of employment. If you have a question as to the legitimacy of an interview or job offer, please contact us at recruitment@brambles.com.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'CHEP','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b7bcd3f66aec3cf6','scraped','2 days ago'),(2647,NULL,'job','Senior Partner Business Manager','','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About Zscaler\n\nZscaler accelerates digital transformation to ensure our customers can be more agile, efficient, resilient, and secure. As an AI-forward enterprise, we are constantly pushing the envelope, leveraging the world\'s largest security data lake to power our cloud-native Zero Trust Exchange platform. This innovation protects our customers from cyberattacks and data loss by securely connecting users, devices, and applications in any location.\n\nHere, impact in your role matters more than title and trust is built on results. We say, impact over activity. We seek innovators who actively use AI to amplify their impact and who thrive in an environment where we leverage intelligent systems to stay ahead of evolving threats. We believe in transparency and value constructive, honest debate—we\'re focused on getting to the best ideas, faster. We build high-performing teams that can make an impact quickly and with high quality. To do this, we are building a culture of execution centered on customer obsession, collaboration, ownership, and accountability.\n\nWe value high-impact, high-accountability with a sense of urgency where you\'re enabled to do your best work and embrace your potential. If you\'re driven by purpose, thrive on solving complex challenges, and want to be part of the team that\'s helping to secure the AI age, we invite you to bring your talents to Zscaler and help shape the future of cybersecurity.\n\nRole\n\nWe are looking for a Senior Partner Business Manager to join our Global Partner Ecosystem department. This is a hybrid role based in Melbourne or Canberra (requiring 3 days a week in the office), reporting to the Senior Director, Partner Sales. Your core purpose is to build and scale high-performing partner relationships by aligning joint strategy, enablement, and go-to-market execution to drive mutual revenue growth. You will drive healthy partner engagement measured through pipeline, faster deal velocity, service creation, expanded market coverage, and improved customer outcomes.\n\nWhat you\'ll do (Role Expectations)\n\nDrive joint regional GTM sales execution in lockstep with Sales Directors\nDevelop and lead the regional partner strategy and long-term growth plan\nSpearhead partner activation through enablement, sales engagement, and pipeline development\nOwn partner performance management and maintain rigorous forecast governance\n\nWho You Are (Success Profile)\n\nYou act like an owner. Your passion for the mission fuels your bias for action. You operate with integrity because you genuinely care about the outcome. You adapt to what\'s needed, navigating seamlessly between high-level strategy and hands-on execution.\nYou operate with urgency. You understand that in a high-growth environment, speed and quality are not mutually exclusive. You have a relentless focus on execution and a bias for action, delivering high-impact results quickly to win for the customer and the team.\nYou think at scale. You connect your day-to-day work to the larger company mission and think globally. You build solutions, processes, and teams that are not just effective today but are built to last and support a high-growth, global organization.\nYou are resilient and adaptable. You view change as an opportunity and setbacks as temporary. You maintain composure and focus in high-pressure situations, guiding yourself and your team through complexity with a steady, positive hand.\nYou lead with integrity. You do the right thing, even when it\'s hard. You hold yourself and others to a high standard of accountability and build trust by matching your words with consistent, transparent action.\n\nWhat We\'re Looking for (Minimum Qualifications)\n\n10+ years in partner/channel sales, alliances, or regional partner management\nProven track record building joint GTM plans with regional sales leadership and executing co-sell motions such as account mapping and deal reviews\nExperience managing strategic partners—including GSIs, RSIs, VARs, distributors, MSSPs, and ISVs—across recruitment, activation, and performance management\nDeep expertise in network, cyber, and cloud security solutions\nWillingness to travel within the region as required to support partners and the sales team\n\nWhat Will Make You Stand Out (Preferred Qualifications)\n\nDirect experience within Public Sector and Education industry verticals\nProfessional background in partner services capability development\nStrong executive communication skills with a proven ability to engage and influence senior partner leadership\n\n#LI-Hybrid\n\n#LI-NL1\n\nAt Zscaler, we are committed to building a team that reflects the communities we serve and the customers we work with. We foster an inclusive environment that values all backgrounds and perspectives, emphasizing collaboration and belonging. Join us in our mission to make doing business seamless and secure.\n\nOur Benefits program is one of the most important ways we support our employees. Zscaler proudly offers comprehensive and inclusive benefits to meet the diverse needs of our employees and their families throughout their life stages, including:\n\nVarious health plans\nTime off plans for vacation and sick time\nParental leave options\nRetirement options\nEducation reimbursement\nIn-office perks, and more!\n\nLearn more about Zscaler\'s Future of Work strategy, hybrid working model, and benefits here.\n\nBy applying for this role, you adhere to applicable laws, regulations, and Zscaler policies, including those related to security and privacy standards and guidelines.\n\nZscaler is committed to providing equal employment opportunities to all individuals. We strive to create a workplace where employees are treated with respect and have the chance to succeed. All qualified applicants will be considered for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex (including pregnancy or related medical conditions), age, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, genetic information, disability status, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state, or local laws. See more information by clicking on the Know Your Rights: Workplace Discrimination is Illegal link.\n\nPay Transparency\n\nZscaler complies with all applicable federal, state, and local pay transparency rules.\n\nZscaler is committed to providing reasonable support (called accommodations or adjustments) in our recruiting processes for candidates who are differently abled, have long term conditions, mental health conditions or sincerely held religious beliefs, or who are neurodivergent or require pregnancy-related support.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Zscaler','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=25735af585adb06b','scraped','3 days ago'),(2648,NULL,'job','Neuroscience - AI Training - Adelaide, Australia','','Greater Adelaide SA',NULL,'',40.00,'$40 an hour','Neuroscience Specialist - AI Training\n\nAbout Prolific\n\nProlific is not just another player in the AI space – we are building the biggest pool of quality human data in the world.\n\nOver 35,000 AI developers, researchers, and organizations use Prolific to gather data from paid study participants with a wide variety of experiences, knowledge, and skills.\n\nThe role\n\nWe are seeking Neuroscience Experts to act as evaluators for a high-level AI verification project. AI models are now generating complex technical summaries, and we need specialists to ensure these outputs maintain scientific integrity and factual accuracy.\n\nWe need experts who can navigate dense scientific literature to judge the accuracy and structural integrity of AI-generated graphical abstracts. This is a flexible, ad hoc project paying $40+/h where your technical expertise directly influences how AI understands and summarizes complex research.\n\nWhat you\'ll bring\n\nSpecialized knowledge: Deep expertise in Neuroscience\n\nAdvanced Academic Credentials: you must hold a Master\'s or PhD in Neuroscience or a related field.\n\nAnalytical Skills: history with fact-checking tasks and strong attention to detail\n\nNice to have: Previous experience with AI-related training or evaluation tasks and a background in scientific publishing or peer review.\n\nWhat you\'ll be doing in the role\nScientific Review: review scientific papers alongside LLM-generated graphical abstracts.\nFact-Checking: identify issues and inaccuracies where the graphical abstract does not faithfully represent the source scientific paper.\nExpert Verification: use your domain knowledge to ensure that technical concepts are visually and textually summarized correctly.\nPlease note that to qualify for this study you will be required to pass a paid skills assessment with a sample paper and graphical abstract\nWhy Prolific is a great platform to join as a Participant\n\nJoining our platform as a Prolific participant will give you the chance to influence the AI models of the future using professional legal expertise. Once you pass our assessment, you can join Prolific in just 15 minutes, and start enjoying competitive pay rates, flexible hours, and the ability to work from home.\n\nWe\'ve built a unique platform that connects researchers and companies with a global pool of participants, enabling the collection of high-quality, ethically sourced human behavioural data and feedback. This data is the cornerstone of developing more accurate, nuanced, and aligned AI systems.\n\nWe believe that the next leap in AI capabilities won\'t come solely from scaling existing models, but from integrating diverse human perspectives and behaviours into AI development. By providing this crucial human data infrastructure, Prolific is positioning itself at the forefront of the next wave of AI innovation – one that reflects the breadth and the best of humanity.\n\nLinks to more information on Prolific\n\nWebsite\n\nYoutube\n\nPrivacy Statement\n\nBy submitting your application, you agree that Prolific may collect your personal data for recruiting and global organisation planning. Prolific\'s Candidate Privacy Notice explains what personal information Prolific may process, where Prolific may process your personal information, its purposes for processing your personal information, and the rights you can exercise over Prolific use of your personal personal information.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Prolific Academic Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=5db6cd002b6d342d','scraped','3 days ago'),(2649,NULL,'job','Senior Data Scientist (Brisbane)','Full-time','Brisbane QLD',NULL,'',11500.00,'$10,000 - $13,000 a month','Data#3 Limited is an Australian IT services and solutions company and headquartered in Brisbane, Queensland. The company provides a wide range of technology services including cloud solutions, cybersecurity, software licensing, hardware procurement, managed IT services, and consulting for government, education, and enterprise clients.\n\n*Senior Data Scientist -Job Description (Brisbane)*\n\nAcross companies like Suncorp Group, Queensland Rail, and government roles, the job is very similar.\n\n*Core responsibilities*\n\nTurn business problems into data solutions\n\nWork with stakeholders to define problems and translate them into data questions\n\nBuild models & advanced analytics\n\n*Machine learning, AI, predictive modelling*\n\nForecasting (e.g. customer behaviour, asset performance)\n\n*Data preparation*\n\nClean, merge, and transform large datasets from multiple sources\n\n*Communicate insights*\n\nDashboards, reports, presentations for non-technical teams\n\n*Lead & mentor*\n\nGuide junior data scientists and influence best practices\n\n*Deploy solutions*\n\nBuild and operationalise ML pipelines in real systems.\n\nPay: $10,000.00 – $13,000.00 per month\n\nBenefits:\n* Childcare assistance\n* Health insurance\n* Life insurance\n* Parental leave\n* Vision insurance\n\nWork Location: In person','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Data#3 Limited','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=796790c091bd487c','scraped','2 days ago'),(2650,NULL,'job','Salesforce Analyst','Full-time','Melbourne VIC 3000',NULL,'',130000.00,'$120,000 - $140,000 a year','Own the Salesforce roadmap and drive impactful platform enhancements\nLead system innovation supporting NDIS service delivery nationwide\nCollaborate with leaders to improve insights, efficiency, and client outcomes\n\nBuild and enhance a complex Salesforce ecosystem at Nextt - delivering scalable solutions that support NDIS services across Australia.\n\nPlay a hands-on role in developing and optimising Salesforce solutions that underpin NDIS service delivery\nOwn the technical design and delivery of Salesforce enhancements, from requirements through to build and deployment\nThe Salesforce Analyst is responsible for the technical design, configuration, and development of the Salesforce platform across Nextt and Lizard Centre.\nWe’re entering an exciting new chapter at Nextt with the implementation of a Salesforce ecosystem. To help us fully leverage this opportunity, We are seeking a hands-on Salesforce technical specialist with strong development capability, including experience with Apex and complex automation.\n\nThis role will take ownership of building and delivering enhancements directly, reducing reliance on external vendors for day-to-day development. You will leverage emerging AI capabilities within Salesforce (including Einstein and Copilot) to drive smarter automation and decision-making\n\nAbout Us\nAt Nextt, we’re passionate about delivering person-centred support. As a leading NDIS provider across QLD, NSW, VIC, and SA, we’re committed to supporting people to live their best lives – and we need talented, driven people to help us make it happen.\n\nThe Role\nThe Salesforce Analyst acts as the strategic Product Owner of the Salesforce platform across Nextt and Lizard Centre, accountable for ensuring the platform enables safe, compliant and efficient service delivery at scale. Reporting to the General Manager of Central Services, the role bridges business strategy, operational delivery and technology by translating complex service, funding and compliance requirements into effective Salesforce solutions.\n\nWe are seeking a technical analyst, one who is motivated by doing their own system configuration and fixes. We’d be expecting someone who can manage low to medium complexity development and configuration (including Apex, Flows, and data model design), supported by a Salesforce Admin, who’s skills they will develop. The business has a solid partnership with an external vendor who provide expert development and guidance when required.\n\nKey Responsibilities Include:\n\n3–5+ years’ experience in a Salesforce technical role (Administrator, Analyst, or Developer), with hands-on build experience\nSalesforce certification (Administrator or Platform Developer preferred)\nStrong experience across Salesforce configuration and development, including Flows, data model design, reporting, and Apex (triggers, classes, test coverage)\nAbility to troubleshoot and resolve complex issues across both configuration and code, with an understanding of Salesforce architecture and limits\nExperience delivering low to medium complexity enhancements across configuration and custom development\nExposure to multi-cloud Salesforce environments (e.g. Health Cloud, Service Cloud, Field Service, Marketing Cloud) and integrations with systems such as finance, payroll, or rostering\nAbility to gather requirements, map processes, and translate them into scalable technical solutions\nFamiliarity with Salesforce security, governance, and change management practices\nProactive mindset toward automation and continuous improvement, with interest or experience in AI capabilities (e.g. Einstein, Copilot)\nExperience in the NDIS, healthcare, or allied health sector (highly desirable)\n\nAbout You\nYou’re a proactive problem solver who thrives on turning complex requirements into simple, effective solutions. You bring strong hands-on Salesforce development experience, with the ability to design and build solutions independently\n\nReady to make a difference?\n\nApply now with your resume and a short cover letter. For a confidential chat, contact our Talent Acquisition Partner Christina – ckatopodis@nextt.com.au\n\nLet’s build a better future – together\nWorkplace diversity is highly valued at The Nextt Group, and we recognize a diverse workforce is beneficial for our employees and our clients. Here at The Nextt Group, we actively encourage and welcome candidates from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds, candidates with disability, members of the LGBTQIA+ community, and First Nations and Torres Strait Islander candidates.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Nextt Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=4eaf87f6549710e3','scraped','2 days ago'),(2651,NULL,'job','Simplified Chinese/Mandarin - Fluent Speakers - AI Training - Australia','Freelance','Brisbane QLD',NULL,'',30.00,'$30 an hour','Simplified Chinese/Mandarin - Fluent Speakers - AI Training - Australia\n\nAbout Prolific\n\nProlific is not just another player in the AI space – we are building the biggest pool of quality human data in the world.\n\nOver 35,000 AI developers, researchers, and organizations use Prolific to gather data from paid study participants with a wide variety of experiences, knowledge, and skills.\n\nThe role\n\nWe\'re looking for Advanced Simplified Chinese/Mandarin Speakers to help train and evaluate cutting-edge AI models. If you have the necessary experience, we\'ll send you a quick test to assess your skills and suitability for AI tasks. If successful, you\'ll be invited to join Prolific as a Domain Expert participant, where you\'ll get paid to train and evaluate powerful AI models.\n\nResearchers looking for your skills tend to pay $30/hr per AI task completed. You must be prepared to complete paid tasks that require one hour of uninterrupted work, though many are shorter.\n\nWhat you\'ll bring\nAdvanced language skills and verifiable experience as being fluent in Simplified Chinese/Mandarin.\nA willingness to take our skills verification test to assess your suitability for our Domain Expert participant pool\nStrong attention to detail and the ability to concentrate on complex tasks for up to one hour at a time\nA reliable and fast internet connection and access to a computer\nA willingness to self-declare your earnings, as our participants are self-employed\nA PayPal account to receive payment from our clients\nWhat you\'ll be doing in the role\nCompleting AI training tasks such as analyzing, editing, and writing in Simplified Chines/Mandarin\nJudging the performance of AI in performing Simplified Chinese/Mandarin prompts\nImproving cutting-edge AI models\nWhy Prolific is a great platform to join as a Participant\n\nJoining our platform as a Prolific participant will give you the chance to influence the AI models of the future using professional legal expertise. Once you pass our assessment, you can join Prolific in just 15 minutes, and start enjoying competitive pay rates, flexible hours, and the ability to work from home.\n\nWe\'ve built a unique platform that connects researchers and companies with a global pool of participants, enabling the collection of high-quality, ethically sourced human behavioural data and feedback. This data is the cornerstone of developing more accurate, nuanced, and aligned AI systems.\n\nWe believe that the next leap in AI capabilities won\'t come solely from scaling existing models, but from integrating diverse human perspectives and behaviours into AI development. By providing this crucial human data infrastructure, Prolific is positioning itself at the forefront of the next wave of AI innovation – one that reflects the breadth and the best of humanity.\n\nLinks to more information on Prolific\n\nWebsite\n\nYoutube\n\nPrivacy Statement\n\nBy submitting your application, you agree that Prolific may collect your personal data for recruiting and global organisation planning. Prolific\'s Candidate Privacy Notice explains what personal information Prolific may process, where Prolific may process your personal information, its purposes for processing your personal information, and the rights you can exercise over Prolific use of your personal personal information.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Prolific Academic Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ccf8418ebc97c472','scraped','3 days ago'),(2652,NULL,'job','Neuroscience - AI Training - Melbourne, Australia','','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',40.00,'$40 an hour','Neuroscience Specialist - AI Training\n\nAbout Prolific\n\nProlific is not just another player in the AI space – we are building the biggest pool of quality human data in the world.\n\nOver 35,000 AI developers, researchers, and organizations use Prolific to gather data from paid study participants with a wide variety of experiences, knowledge, and skills.\n\nThe role\n\nWe are seeking Neuroscience Experts to act as evaluators for a high-level AI verification project. AI models are now generating complex technical summaries, and we need specialists to ensure these outputs maintain scientific integrity and factual accuracy.\n\nWe need experts who can navigate dense scientific literature to judge the accuracy and structural integrity of AI-generated graphical abstracts. This is a flexible, ad hoc project paying $40+/h where your technical expertise directly influences how AI understands and summarizes complex research.\n\nWhat you\'ll bring\n\nSpecialized knowledge: Deep expertise in Neuroscience\n\nAdvanced Academic Credentials: you must hold a Master\'s or PhD in Neuroscience or a related field.\n\nAnalytical Skills: history with fact-checking tasks and strong attention to detail\n\nNice to have: Previous experience with AI-related training or evaluation tasks and a background in scientific publishing or peer review.\n\nWhat you\'ll be doing in the role\nScientific Review: review scientific papers alongside LLM-generated graphical abstracts.\nFact-Checking: identify issues and inaccuracies where the graphical abstract does not faithfully represent the source scientific paper.\nExpert Verification: use your domain knowledge to ensure that technical concepts are visually and textually summarized correctly.\nPlease note that to qualify for this study you will be required to pass a paid skills assessment with a sample paper and graphical abstract\nWhy Prolific is a great platform to join as a Participant\n\nJoining our platform as a Prolific participant will give you the chance to influence the AI models of the future using professional legal expertise. Once you pass our assessment, you can join Prolific in just 15 minutes, and start enjoying competitive pay rates, flexible hours, and the ability to work from home.\n\nWe\'ve built a unique platform that connects researchers and companies with a global pool of participants, enabling the collection of high-quality, ethically sourced human behavioural data and feedback. This data is the cornerstone of developing more accurate, nuanced, and aligned AI systems.\n\nWe believe that the next leap in AI capabilities won\'t come solely from scaling existing models, but from integrating diverse human perspectives and behaviours into AI development. By providing this crucial human data infrastructure, Prolific is positioning itself at the forefront of the next wave of AI innovation – one that reflects the breadth and the best of humanity.\n\nLinks to more information on Prolific\n\nWebsite\n\nYoutube\n\nPrivacy Statement\n\nBy submitting your application, you agree that Prolific may collect your personal data for recruiting and global organisation planning. Prolific\'s Candidate Privacy Notice explains what personal information Prolific may process, where Prolific may process your personal information, its purposes for processing your personal information, and the rights you can exercise over Prolific use of your personal personal information.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Prolific Academic Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d37233566bff9c52','scraped','3 days ago'),(2653,NULL,'job','eSafety - Digital Publishing Assistant, APS 4','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'At eSafety, we are pioneers in online safety regulation, leading global efforts to combat digital harms and foster safer, more positive online experiences for all Australians.\n\nOur mission is bold and far-reaching.\n\nFrom tackling cyberbullying and child sexual exploitation, to confronting emerging harms brought about by new innovations such as generative AI and immersive technologies, we oversee Australia’s online safety landscape.\n\nSitting within the Strategic Communications Branch, the Digital Content and Publishing team leads eSafety\'s digital content strategy and manages eSafety’s website as a vehicle for program delivery and user engagement. This includes co-creating webpages and resources and providing wider editorial services.\n\nWe have an exciting opportunity for a highly motivated Digital Publishing Assistant to learn from a team of experienced editors and publishers who produce unique, world-leading information that helps people navigate the complexities of the global digital environment.\n\nYou will be able to put your own document formatting and admin skills to good use, contributing to the end-to-end digital publishing process. You will have regular opportunities to be involved in ideation, development, website design and promotion of engaging content.\n\nThis is your chance to learn new skills while expanding your industry experience!\n\nTo be successful in this role you will have a careful eye for detail, be highly organised and enjoy collaborating. You’ll be able to proactively manage competing priorities and handle confidential information.\n\nThe following would also be highly regarded:\n\nExperience or training in digital publishing or a related field.\nExperience creating and amending Word documents, PDFs and web content.\n\nFull details of the position, and information about how you can apply, are provided in the candidate pack.\n\nTo be eligible for employment with eSafety, applicants must be Australian citizens.\n\nThis vacancy is available on a non-ongoing basis. This non-ongoing role may be offered for an initial period of up to 12 months with the possibility of extension or becoming ongoing. Suitable candidates may be placed in a merit pool from this selection process and the pool may be used to fill similar ongoing or non-ongoing roles. Applicants may have their application and assessment results shared with other Australian Public Service (APS) agencies looking to fill similar roles.\n\nTechnical assistance: For questions relating to the online lodgement of your application, please email hrassist@acma.gov.au before the closing date.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Australian Communications and Media Authority','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d187aabde52555c1','scraped','3 days ago'),(2654,NULL,'job','Workforce and Recruitment Support Officer','Permanent','Newcastle NSW',NULL,'',8454233.00,'$83,554.59 - $85,530.07 a year','Delivering trusted workforce and recruitment support across NSW Health Pathology\n\nEmployment Type: Permanent Full Time\nPosition Classification: Admin Off Lvl 6\nRemuneration: $83,554.59 - $85,530.07 per annum plus superannuation\nHours Per Week: 38\nRequisition ID: REQ658304\nLocation: Newcastle\nApplications Close: 07 May 2026 - 11:59pm\n\nNSW Health Pathology is seeking a motivated and experienced Workforce and Recruitment Support Officer to join our People and Culture team. This role plays a key part in delivering high quality, customer focused workforce and recruitment services in a complex and fast paced environment.\n\nYou will provide advisory and administrative support across a broad range of workforce operations, working closely with managers, stakeholders and external partners to ensure accurate, timely and compliant outcomes. The role supports key workforce systems and processes and contributes to continuous improvement initiatives across NSW Health Pathology.\n\nAbout you\n\nYou will have recent experience in a client focused workforce or recruitment environment. You will demonstrate:\n\nExperience supporting workforce or HRIS functions\n\nStrong communication and customer service skills\n\nSound judgement and attention to detail\n\nAbility to work collaboratively and adapt to changing priorities\n\nCapacity to interpret and apply industrial awards and policies\n\nWhat you\'ll be doing\n\nResponsible for a diverse range of workforce and recruitment functions, as well as the provision of support and advisory services to users of workforce operations functions including, but not limited to, StaffLink, ROB, PAT, SARA and ClinConnect\n\nLiaise and work effectively with internal/external stakeholders to facilitate a high quality, best practice, customer focused, value adding and comprehensive HR service\n\nWhat we can offer you\n\nFinancial Benefits - Generous salary packaging options and other fringe benefits\n\nWork-life balance - 9-day fortnight in addition to Annual Leave\n\nProfessional growth - Learning and development opportunities, including in-house training with RTO My Health Learning\n\nHealth & wellbeing - Fitness Passport gym discounts and Employee Assistance Program (EAP) for staff and families.\n\nHow to Apply\n\nIf you’re interested in joining Australia’s largest public pathology service? Apply now!\n\nYour application will require you to include a cover letter (maximum 2 pages), resume (maximum 5 pages) and responses to the selection criteria\n\nDescribe your experience supporting workforce or HRIS functions in a client‑focused team, including a time you adapted quickly to changing priorities using digital tools and sound judgement.\n\nTell us about a time you interpreted and applied an award, agreement or policy to resolve a workforce issue. How did you ensure your advice was compliant?\n\nInformation For Applicants\n\nNSW Health Pathology is an equal opportunity employer committed to an inclusive workplace. We value, and welcome all suitably qualified applicants regardless of age, background, disability, sexual orientation or gender identity.\n\nNSW Health Pathology is committed to providing accessibility and reasonable accommodations and ensuring our recruitment process is flexible, inclusive, and free from barriers, promoting equal opportunities for all to succeed. Please reach out if you need adjustments.\n\nNSW Health Pathology is committed to growing the Aboriginal workforce in public health. For Aboriginal candidates, support is available through the Stepping Up website\n\nYou must have valid working rights in Australia for the duration of the appointment to be eligible to apply.\n\nAll workers must meet NSW Health’s vaccination and screening requirements before starting employment. See PD2026_004 for more detail. The preferred candidate may be required to undergo a functional assessment prior to appointment.\n\nAn eligibility list may be created for similar vacancies in the future.\n\nWe encourage applicants to submit responses that reflect their own experiences and perspectives. Please note that applications that appear to be generated by AI tools or copied from external sources may not be considered.\n\nNeed more information?\n 1)\n 2)\nFor role related queries or questions contact Lydia McCann on Lydia.McCann@health.nsw.gov.au\n\nTo learn more about NSWHP please visit “Life at NSW Health Pathology” or connect with us on LinkedIn!','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'NSW Health','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c472d70a44e7a71e','scraped','3 days ago'),(2655,NULL,'job','Head of Customer Success APAC','','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Our Customer Success team is at the heart of Asana\'s mission to build the Agentic Enterprise, helping customers maximize value as they climb the \"context ladder\"—from individual task management to enterprise-wide intelligence. We are seeking a visionary and tenured leader to serve as the Head of Customer Success for APAC. Based in our Sydney office, you will lead a high-performing organization across one of our most complex regions and act as a primary architect for the \"CS Org of the Future\". You will drive the shift toward an AI-powered model where context-aware execution enables customers to move from \"doing\" work to \"guiding\" it.\n\nThis role is based in our Sydney office with an office-centric hybrid schedule. The standard in-office days are Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday. Most Asanas have the option to work from home on Mondays and Fridays. If you\'re interviewing for this role, your recruiter will share more about the in-office requirements.\n\nWhat you\'ll achieve\n\nDefine and execute a multi-year CS strategy for APAC that accounts for the unique cultural, linguistic, and market complexities across the territory.\nOwn the regional P&L for Customer Success, driving key performance indicators including Net Revenue Retention (NRR), Gross Revenue Retention (GRR), and customer advocacy.\nChampion the Agentic Enterprise mindset, consulting with C-suite executives on how to scale value through durable context and AI-led orchestration.\nLead and mentor a high-performing team of CS leaders and individual contributors, fostering a culture of excellence and a \"self-driving\" organizational mindset.\nForge deep cross-functional partnerships with regional Sales, Marketing, and Product leaders to align on account strategy and regional growth targets.\nInfluence the global product roadmap by surfacing deep market insights from the APAC region to ensure AI capabilities meet diverse market needs\n\nAbout you\n\nTenured Leadership: 5+ years of experience in Customer Success or client-facing leadership role within the SaaS industry, with a proven track record of managing large-scale regional organizations.\nRegional Expertise: Deep knowledge of the APAC market landscape and the ability to navigate diverse business cultures and regulatory environments.\nAI Visionary: Advanced understanding of \"Agentic AI\" and the ability to articulate how durable context and orchestration drive business value.\nSelf-Starter & Problem Solver: A proactive leader who thrives in ambiguity and is passionate about finding innovative solutions to complex organisational challenges.\nInfluential Partner: Exceptional ability to build consensus and influence stakeholders across global, matrixed organizations.\nChange Agent: Proactive problem solver who thrives in ambiguity and is passionate about building the future of how companies operate in an AI-centric world.\nEmerging Tech Curiosity: Demonstrates curiosity about AI tools and emerging technologies, with a willingness to learn and leverage them to enhance productivity, collaboration, or decision-making.\nDemonstrates curiosity about AI tools and emerging technologies, with a willingness to learn and leverage them to enhance productivity, collaboration, or decision-making\n\nAt Asana, we\'re committed to building teams that include a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills, as this is critical to helping us achieve our mission. If you\'re interested in this role and don\'t meet every listed requirement, we still encourage you to apply.\n\nWhat we\'ll offer\nOur comprehensive compensation package plays a big part in how we recognize you for the impact you have on our mission. We provide equitable and competitive benefits packages that support our employees worldwide, including:\n\nMental health, wellness, and fitness benefits.\nCareer coaching and support.\nInclusive family-building benefits.\nLong-term savings or retirement plans.\nIn-office culinary options tailored to dietary preferences.\n\nThese are just some of the benefits we offer, and benefits may vary based on role, country, and local regulations. If you\'re interviewing for this role, speak with your recruiter to learn more about the total compensation and benefits for this role.\n\n#LI-Hybrid\n\nAbout us\n\nAsana is a leading platform for human + AI collaboration. Millions of teams around the world rely on Asana to achieve their most important goals, faster. Asana has been named to Fortune\'s Best Workplaces for 7+ years and recognized by Fast Company, Forbes, and Gartner for excellence in workplace culture and innovation. We offer an exceptional office-centric culture while adopting the best elements of hybrid models to ensure that every one of our global team members can work together effortlessly. With 13+ offices all over the world, we are always looking for individuals who care about building technology that drives positive change in the world and a culture where everyone feels that they belong.\n\nJoin Asana\'s Talent Network to stay up to date on job opportunities and life at Asana.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Asana','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=39644c22845b57a7','scraped','3 days ago'),(2656,NULL,'job','Patient Navigator','Full-time','Australia',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About myTomorrows\n\nmyTomorrows is a global health tech company dedicated to breaking down barriers for patients seeking treatment options.\n\nWe strive to enable earlier and better treatment access by bridging the gap between those searching for possible options, and the companies who develop them. We work closely with patients, healthcare professionals, trial sites, patient advocacy groups, and BioPharma – connecting key stakeholders in the drug development ecosystem.\n\nWe’ve developed a cutting-edge AI-powered technology platform that simplifies and streamlines access to drugs in development. To support our users and clients, we have a range of industry-expert specialized teams ready to help. Our services include clinical trial patient recruitment, Expanded Access Program management and Real-World Data collection.\n\nWith a global footprint spanning 134 countries, to date we’ve supported over 17,000 patients, 3,000 physicians and 350 sites, earning the trust of 60+ BioPharma companies. In October 2025, we closed a €25M investment with Avego Healthcare Capital to fuel our global ambitions and scale the business.\n\nJoin us in shaping the future of treatment access - making tomorrow’s therapies accessible for people who need them today.\n\nThe opportunity: Patient Navigator\n\nThe Patient Navigator acts as the main point of contact for patients and their families, guiding them through clinical trials and expanded access options. The role focuses on empowering patients by explaining complex medical concepts, assisting in navigating treatment options, and facilitating pre-screening for and referral to clinical trials. This role does not provide medical advice but ensures patients have all the necessary information to make informed decisions about their treatment.\n\nWe are looking for a Remote Patient Navigator located in South Korea, Australia, or China (time zone UTC+9, +9.5 or +10) to join our team at myTomorrows. This role will report directly to our Patient Navigator Lead (Claire says, hi!).\n\nWhat you\'ll do in this role:\n\nCommunicate with patients and caregivers via phone and email as a response to requests for pre-approval treatment access.\n\nCapture medical data in our internal platform.\n\nSearch global trial databases using our AI tool to identify relevant pre-approval options for patients.\n\nPre-screen patients for specific clinical trials.\n\nEngage with patients to expand our Medical Community and create awareness about the myTomorrows platform.\n\nProactively identify trends and opportunities in our daily operations.\n\nAchieve and maintain high patient satisfaction\n\nContribute to improving our patient recruitment and pre-screening processes and strategies\n\nWhat you bring to the table:\n\nBachelor’s degree in life sciences, healthcare, or related fields, or higher\n\n3+ years of experience in patient navigation, clinical research, or healthcare communication roles.\n\nExperience with patient care in a clinical setting, as well as knowledge of clinical trials and expanded access, is preferred.\n\nKnowledge, Skills & Abilities:\n\nStrong communication and interpersonal skills.\n\nAbility to explain complex medical information in simple terms.\n\nExcellent verbal and written communication skills in English.\n\nFluency in one or more languages required (Korean, Mandarin and/or Cantonese ).\n\nProficiency in using CRM and healthcare databases.\n\nLiteracy in Microsoft Office and web-based media, and openness to technological innovation\n\nAbility to prioritize different commitments while maintaining high quality of work.\n\nProactivity and ability to work unsupervised.\n\nPatient-centric mindset, understanding and empathetic when working with patients.\n\nAttention to detail and ability to record information and clinical data accurately.\n\nAbility to build relationships of trust and manage confidential information and data appropriately\n\nA team player who thrives in a multicultural, diverse environment.\n\nCertifications:\n\nCertifications in Good Clinical Practice or healthcare-related fields (e.g., Certified Patient Navigator) are a plus.\n\nWhat success in the first 6 months looks like:\n\nHandling 100-125 moderately complex patient cases per month independently, only escalating highly specialized inquiries.\n\nTracking patient progress and documenting all communications within the case management system for internal reporting.\n\nCreating reports to be sent to patients with their options for pre-approval treatments.\n\nCurrently serving (or ready to) as the lead Patient Navigator on a client’s pre-screening and triaging program.\n\nProactively identifying trends and opportunities for improvement in our daily operations, participating in 1-2 active internal process change initiatives.\n\nEqual opportunities\n\nmyTomorrows is an Equal Opportunity Employer and, beyond upholding discrimination-free practices, we are committed to cultivating a workplace where difference and diversity are protected and celebrated. The best work comes from our best selves, and we go to great lengths in supporting our team members to be just that.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'myTomorrows','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=283c3477cf6e4641','scraped','3 days ago'),(2657,NULL,'job','Sales Engineer','Full-time','New South Wales',NULL,'',180000.00,'$144,000 - $216,000 a year','Mimecast started in email security — and we\'re still a recognised leader in it. But today we\'re much more than that. Through strategic acquisitions and organic development, Mimecast has built a connected Human Risk Management platform that spans email security, insider risk management, security awareness training, digital communications governance, and AI-powered threat intelligence. We protect over 42,000 organisations worldwide and we\'re focused on a problem the industry is only now catching up to: the human layer is the biggest attack surface in cybersecurity, and managing it requires more than point products. We\'re growing our ANZ team and looking for a Sales Engineer who can bring that full platform story to life for our customers and partners.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nReporting to the ANZ Sales Engineering Manager, you\'ll own the technical path to close across our midmarket and upper-SMB customers. This isn\'t a role where you sit behind a screen building lab environments all day — it\'s customer-facing from day one. You\'ll partner with Account Executives and Account Managers to run discovery, deliver demos, and position solutions that make sense for the customer\'s environment and budget. When it comes to the technical win, it\'s yours to drive.\n\nA meaningful part of this role involves our channel partners. You\'ll help enable partner SEs to position and demonstrate our solutions independently, run joint technical sessions, and act as a go-to technical resource for our partner community in ANZ.\n\nThe role is based in Sydney with hybrid working and potential for interstate travel. You\'ll be supported by an experienced SE leader who is invested in your development — this is a role where you\'ll grow, not just execute.\n\nWhat You\'ll Do\n\nOwn the technical conversation during the sales cycle — from initial discovery through to proof of value and technical close\n\nDeliver clear, compelling presentations and demonstrations to IT leaders, security teams, and business stakeholders\n\nPartner closely with AEs and AMs to build deal strategy, qualify opportunities, and align solutions to customer outcomes\n\nDevelop your technical discovery skills — going beyond a feature checklist to understand the customer\'s environment, pain points, and what success looks like for them\n\nSupport and enable channel partners through joint selling, technical enablement sessions, and partner-facing content\n\nManage proof of value engagements tied to defined success criteria\n\nSupport RFP, RFI, and tender responses with accuracy and commercial awareness\n\nHandle technical handovers to delivery and customer success teams to protect the customer experience\n\nContribute to field marketing activities including webinars, events, and thought leadership\n\nWhat You\'ll Bring\n\nCommunication and presence come first. You\'re confident presenting to a room of senior IT and security leaders. You can read the room, adjust your message, and hold attention without hiding behind slides. You write clearly and communicate complex ideas in plain language.\n\nCommercial instincts matter. You understand how deals work — not just the technical win, but what gets a deal across the line. You\'ve been exposed to structured sales methodologies (MEDDPICC, Sandler, Challenger, or similar) and you\'re comfortable qualifying, positioning value, and supporting your AE in building a compelling business case.\n\nChannel experience is a differentiator. You\'ve worked alongside channel partners — running joint demos, enabling partner SEs, or helping partners build their own technical capability around the solutions you represent. You understand that scaling through partners is how you multiply impact.\n\nTechnical depth is the foundation. You have hands-on experience across one or more cybersecurity domains — email security, insider risk and data loss prevention, security awareness training, endpoint protection, or identity and access management. You don\'t need to be an expert in all of them, but you need to be someone who rolls up their sleeves, learns fast, and can credibly speak to how security technologies work in practice.\n\nRequirements\n\n3+ years\' experience as a Sales Engineer or Solutions Engineer at a cybersecurity vendor\n\nDemonstrated experience supporting midmarket and/or SMB customer segments\n\nHands-on technical knowledge across relevant cybersecurity domains (email security, insider risk/DLP, security awareness, endpoint, identity)\n\nExperience working with and enabling channel partners\n\nStrong presentation, demonstration, and written communication skills\n\nBased in Sydney\n\nAustralian working rights\n\nNice to Have\n\nFamiliarity with the ANZ channel landscape and key security distributors/partners\n\nExperience with SaaS platforms and cloud-delivered security solutions\n\nRelevant industry certifications (vendor-specific, CompTIA Security+, CISSP, or equivalent)\n\nExposure to frameworks like the ASD Essential Eight or NIST CSF\n\nThe on-target earnings (OTE) range for this position is $144k $216k (OTE) plus benefits. This range represents the minimum and maximum new hire compensation for this role. The position may also be eligible for incentive plans and additional benefits, in accordance with company policy and local regulations. Our salary ranges are determined by role, level, and location with individual compensation also dependent on factors such as qualifications, experience, and skills. Final offers will reflect these considerations and may vary accordingly.\n\nBelonging at Mimecast\n\nCybersecurity is a community effort. That’s why we’re committed to building an inclusive, diverse community that celebrates and welcomes everyone – unless they’re a cybercriminal, of course.\n\nWe’re proud to be an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action Employer, and we’d encourage you to join us whatever your background. We particularly welcome applicants from traditionally underrepresented groups.\n\nWe consider everyone equally: your race, age, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity, ability, marital status, nationality, or any other protected characteristic won’t affect your application.\n\nDue to certain obligations to our customers, an offer of employment will be subject to your successful completion of applicable background checks, conducted in accordance with local law.\n\nIt is unlawful in Massachusetts to require or administer a lie detector test as a condition of employment or continued employment.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Mimecast','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2588b6b094d0226d','scraped','3 days ago'),(2658,NULL,'job','Product Sales Lead, Product and Sales Activation (Fixed-Term Contract)','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'At Google, we have a vision of empowerment and equitable opportunity for all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and commit to building reconciliation through Google’s technology, platforms and people and we welcome Indigenous applicants. Please see our Reconciliation Action Plan for more information.\n\nMinimum qualifications:\nBachelor\'s degree or equivalent practical experience.\n\n6 years of experience in product management, sales, marketing, management consulting, or project management in technology.\nExperience working with product management or sales teams, executive leadership, and cross-functional stakeholders.\nExperience developing business strategies or managing cross-functional initiatives.\n\nPreferred qualifications:\nMBA or Master\'s degree in Science.\nExperience influencing executive leaders through judgment and data.\nAbility to guide impact in a fast-paced environment.\nExcellent strategic thinking and problem-solving skills, with the ability to lead complex operational and strategic initiatives.\nExcellent communication skills in both practitioner and executive level contexts.\nAbout the job\n\nBusinesses of all shapes and sizes rely on Google’s unparalleled advertising solutions to help them grow in today\'s dynamic marketing environment. You bring a passion for sales, knowledge of online media, and commitment to maximize customer success. You act like an owner, move with velocity through change, finding innovative and strategic ways to consistently deliver extraordinary and incremental outcomes for both Google and your customers. You build trusted relationships with customers, uncovering their business needs and translating them into powerful solutions to achieve their most ambitious goals. You achieve as a team with sellers, shape the future of advertising in the AI-era, and make a real impact on the millions of companies and billions of users that trust Google with their most important goals.\n\nGoogle Customer Solutions (GCS) sales teams are trusted advisors and competitive sellers who maintain a relentless focus on customer success by bringing the best Google has to offer to small- and medium-sized businesses (SMBs), which are the backbone of our communities. As a member of our team, you’ll have the opportunity to work with company owners and make a real difference in their businesses by helping them grow. Together, we help shape the future of innovation for customers, partners, and sellers...and we have fun doing it.\n\nResponsibilities\nPartner with Sales teams, Google advertisers and agencies to increase adoption and usage of Google’s first-party data measurement solutions.\nWork with Sales teams based on a quarterly named client list via co-pitches, pre-pitch support. Collate information regarding common objections, successful strategies, product knowledge gaps, etc. and facilitate internal and external product trainings.\nDevelop an understanding of our advertisers measurement opportunities and issues in the privacy first world, in order to create activation strategy to drive current and future measurement products across APAC and help evolve the future strategy and Go-to-Market (GTM) approach.\nMonitor and report on key metrics. Work with team leads to ensure effective narratives are developed. Leverage those resources to equip promoters with product knowledge and expertise.\nCollaborate both cross-functionally and cross-regionally to develop opportunities to increase product adoption for key solutions.\nGoogle is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Google\'s EEO Policy and EEO is the Law. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know by completing our Accommodations for Applicants form.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Google','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=07bd768661d8dc97','scraped','3 days ago'),(2659,NULL,'job','E2E Architect','Full-time','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Accenture is a leading global professional services company that helps the world’s leading businesses, governments and other organizations build their digital core, optimize their operations, accelerate revenue growth and enhance citizen services—creating tangible value at speed and scale. We are a talent and innovation led company with 791,000 people serving clients in more than 120 countries. Technology is at the core of change today, and we are one of the world’s leaders in helping drive that change, with strong ecosystem relationships. We combine our strength in technology with unmatched industry experience, functional expertise and global delivery capability. We are uniquely able to deliver tangible outcomes because of our broad range of services, solutions and assets across Strategy & Consulting, Technology, Operations, Industry X and Accenture Song. These capabilities, together with our culture of shared success and commitment to creating 360° value, enable us to help our clients succeed and build trusted, lasting relationships. We measure our success by the 360° value we create for our clients, each other, our shareholders, partners and communities. Visit us at www.accenture.com.\n\nThe Accenture Microsoft Business Group (AMBG) is a strategic partnership between Accenture and Microsoft that combines the capabilities and expertise of both companies to help clients accelerate their digital transformation. The group offers end-to-end solutions across cloud, data, AI, security, and modern workplace, leveraging the power of Microsoft platforms such as Azure, Microsoft 365, Dynamics 365, and Power Platform. The group also provides industry-specific solutions and services tailored to the needs and challenges of different sectors and markets.\n\nAbout the role\n\nIgnite your passion for innovation! In this role, you will be a subject matter expert, collaborating with various teams to contribute to key decisions and provide solutions to challenges. You will engage with multiple teams and manage decisions that impact your immediate group and beyond.\n\nThe E2E Architect will be responsible for designing and managing the end-to end architecture of a system, ensuring that all components are integrated and functioning together seamlessly. This role involves understanding the business requirements, defining the architecture, and ensuring that the system can handle various workloads and failures. E2E Architects work closely with various stakeholders, including business, technology, and suppliers, to create a comprehensive and effective architecture that meets the needs of the organization.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nDesign end-to-end solution architectures aligned to business, technical, and non-functional requirements\n\nTranslate business and functional requirements into scalable, secure, and maintainable solution designs\n\nDefine system components, integration patterns, data flows, and technology standards\n\nCollaborate closely with business stakeholders, delivery teams, and technical specialists to ensure alignment\n\nEnsure solutions comply with security, performance, availability, and regulatory requirements\n\nProduce and maintain architecture artefacts including solution diagrams and design documentation\n\nReview and approve technical designs and implementation approaches\n\nSupport delivery teams during build, test, and deployment phases\n\nIdentify and manage architectural risks, dependencies, and trade-offs\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications\n\n8+ years’ experience in Solution Architecture or senior technical design roles\n\nMaster proficiency in Application Strategy.\n\nStrong experience designing complex application and integration solutions\n\nSolid understanding of cloud platforms, application architectures, and system integrations\n\nExperience working across Agile and hybrid delivery environments\n\nStrong stakeholder engagement and communication skills\n\nAdvance problem-solving skills\n\nProject Coordination skills will be well regarded.\n\nExperience producing clear and concise architecture documentation\n\nStrong analytical and problem-solving capabilities\n\nAbility to balance business needs, technical constraints, and delivery considerations\n\nBachelor\'s Degree in relevant field of studies.\n\nMandatory Requirements\n\nCandidate must be an Australian Citizen with Baseline Security Clearance\n\nAll our consulting professionals receive comprehensive training covering business acumen, technical and professional skills development. You’ll also have opportunities to hone your functional skills and expertise in an area of specialization. We offer a variety of formal and informal training programs at every level to help you acquire and build specialized skills faster. Learning takes place both on the job and through formal training conducted online, in the classroom, or in collaboration with teammates. The sheer variety of work we do, and the experience it offers, provide an unbeatable platform from which to build a career.\n\nAccenture Benefits\n\nTo view our Progressive Employee Benefits covering Health, Wellbeing, Progressive Leave Options, Sustainability click on the link below.\n\nProgressive Employee Benefits – Australia\n\nThis is an exceptional opportunity for an exceptional individual.\n\nEqual Employment Opportunity Statement for Australia\n\nAt Accenture, we recognise that our people are multi-dimensional, and we create a work environment where all people feel like they can bring their authentic selves to work, every day.\n\nOur unwavering commitment to inclusion and diversity unleashes innovation and creates a culture where everyone feels they have equal opportunity. Our range of progressive policies support flexibility in ‘where’, ‘when’ and ‘how’ our people work to ensure that Accenture is an organisation where you can strive for more, achieve great things and maintain the balance and wellbeing you need.\n\nWe encourage applications from all people, and we are committed to removing barriers to the recruitment process and employee lifecycle. All employment decisions shall be made without regard to age, disability status, ethnicity, gender, gender identity or expression, religion or sexual orientation and we do not tolerate discrimination. If you require adjustments to the recruitment process or have a preferred communication method, please email exectalent@accenture.com and cite the relevant Job Number, or contact us on +61 2 9005 5000.\n\nTo ensure our workplace is inclusive and diverse we are setting bold goals and taking comprehensive action. To achieve these goals, we collect information that allows us to track the effectiveness of our Inclusion and Diversity programs. Learn how Accenture protects your personal data and know your rights in relation to your personal data. Read more about our Privacy Statement.\n\n#LI_GM\n\n.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Accenture','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1d7b74b17c502179','scraped','3 days ago'),(2660,NULL,'job','E2E Architect (AU Citizen with Security Clearance)','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Accenture is a leading solutions and services company that helps the world’s leading enterprises reinvent by building their digital core and unleashing the power of AI to create value at speed across the enterprise, bringing together the talent of our approximately 786,000 people, our proprietary assets and platforms, and deep ecosystem relationships. Our strategy is to be the reinvention partner of choice for our clients and to be the most client-focused, AI-enabled, great place to work in the world. Through our Reinvention Services we bring together our capabilities across strategy, consulting, technology, operations, Song and Industry X with our deep industry expertise to create and deliver solutions and services for our clients. Our purpose is to deliver on the promise of technology and human ingenuity, and we measure our success by the 360° value we create for all our stakeholders.\n\nVisit us at www.accenture.com.\n\nThe Accenture Microsoft Business Group (AMBG) is a strategic partnership between Accenture and Microsoft that combines the capabilities and expertise of both companies to help clients accelerate their digital transformation. The group offers end-to-end solutions across cloud, data, AI, security, and modern workplace, leveraging the power of Microsoft platforms such as Azure, Microsoft 365, Dynamics 365, and Power Platform. The group also provides industry-specific solutions and services tailored to the needs and challenges of different sectors and markets.\n\nAbout the role\n\nIgnite your passion for innovation! In this role, you will be a subject matter expert, collaborating with various teams to contribute to key decisions and provide solutions to challenges. You will engage with multiple teams and manage decisions that impact your immediate group and beyond.\n\nThe E2E Architect will be responsible for designing and managing the end-to end architecture of a system, ensuring that all components are integrated and functioning together seamlessly. This role involves understanding the business requirements, defining the architecture, and ensuring that the system can handle various workloads and failures. E2E Architects work closely with various stakeholders, including business, technology, and suppliers, to create a comprehensive and effective architecture that meets the needs of the organization.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nDesign end-to-end solution architectures aligned to business, technical, and non-functional requirements\n\nTranslate business and functional requirements into scalable, secure, and maintainable solution designs\n\nDefine system components, integration patterns, data flows, and technology standards\n\nCollaborate closely with business stakeholders, delivery teams, and technical specialists to ensure alignment\n\nEnsure solutions comply with security, performance, availability, and regulatory requirements\n\nProduce and maintain architecture artefacts including solution diagrams and design documentation\n\nReview and approve technical designs and implementation approaches\n\nSupport delivery teams during build, test, and deployment phases\n\nIdentify and manage architectural risks, dependencies, and trade-offs\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications\n\n8+ years’ experience in Solution Architecture or senior technical design roles\n\nMaster proficiency in Application Strategy.\n\nStrong experience designing complex application and integration solutions\n\nSolid understanding of cloud platforms, application architectures, and system integrations\n\nExperience working across Agile and hybrid delivery environments\n\nStrong stakeholder engagement and communication skills\n\nAdvance problem-solving skills\n\nProject Coordination skills will be well regarded.\n\nExperience producing clear and concise architecture documentation\n\nStrong analytical and problem-solving capabilities\n\nAbility to balance business needs, technical constraints, and delivery considerations\n\nBachelor\'s Degree in relevant field of studies.\n\nMandatory Requirements\n\nCandidate must be an Australian Citizen with Baseline Security Clearance\n\nAll our consulting professionals receive comprehensive training covering business acumen, technical and professional skills development. You’ll also have opportunities to hone your functional skills and expertise in an area of specialization. We offer a variety of formal and informal training programs at every level to help you acquire and build specialized skills faster. Learning takes place both on the job and through formal training conducted online, in the classroom, or in collaboration with teammates. The sheer variety of work we do, and the experience it offers, provide an unbeatable platform from which to build a career.\n\nAccenture Benefits\n\nTo view our Progressive Employee Benefits covering Health, Wellbeing, Progressive Leave Options, Sustainability click on the link below.\n\nProgressive Employee Benefits – Australia\n\nThis is an exceptional opportunity for an exceptional individual.\n\nEqual Employment Opportunity Statement for Australia\n\nAt Accenture, we recognise that our people are multi-dimensional, and we create a work environment where all people feel like they can bring their authentic selves to work, every day.\n\nOur unwavering commitment to inclusion and diversity unleashes innovation and creates a culture where everyone feels they have equal opportunity. Our range of progressive policies support flexibility in ‘where’, ‘when’ and ‘how’ our people work to ensure that Accenture is an organisation where you can strive for more, achieve great things and maintain the balance and wellbeing you need.\n\nWe encourage applications from all people, and we are committed to removing barriers to the recruitment process and employee lifecycle. All employment decisions shall be made without regard to age, disability status, ethnicity, gender, gender identity or expression, religion or sexual orientation and we do not tolerate discrimination. If you require adjustments to the recruitment process or have a preferred communication method, please email exectalent@accenture.com and cite the relevant Job Number, or contact us on +61 2 9005 5000.\n\nTo ensure our workplace is inclusive and diverse we are setting bold goals and taking comprehensive action. To achieve these goals, we collect information that allows us to track the effectiveness of our Inclusion and Diversity programs. Learn how Accenture protects your personal data and know your rights in relation to your personal data. Read more about our Privacy Statement.\n\n#LI_GM\n\n.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Accenture','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=fe2881d7496f913e','scraped','3 days ago'),(2661,NULL,'job','EL1 - Assistant Director, Business Architect (IT Front Door & Architecture)','Part-time','Canberra ACT',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Contact Officer:\n\n Bryce Undy on Bryce.Undy2@infrastructure.gov.au or\n\n (02) 6136 7295\n\n Closing Date:\n\n 11.59pm AEST, Sunday 17 May 2026\n\nWe actively seek to reflect the diversity of the Australian community in our workforce. We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with disability and/or who are neurodivergent, people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds and members of the LGBTQIA+ community, including people of all genders and gender identities. We uphold gender equality as a core organisational value. If you’re interested in the role but feel uncertain, we still encourage you to apply if you feel your passions, transferable skills and valuable experience align with this position.\n\nThe opportunity we have available\n\nOrganised within the Chief Operating Officer Group within the department, Information Technology & Data Division’s (ITDD) purpose is to connect people, data, and technology, empowering the department to excel. ITDD is responsible for the consolidated provision and support of stable and secure IT Systems, applications and services to all department users across all States and Territories, including Indian Ocean Territories and Norfolk Island, as well as supporting seven Ministerial offices, and coordination with portfolio entities. ITDD provides the digital collaboration and communications tools necessary to connect a geographically dispersed workforce and to optimise hybrid working arrangements. We manage industry and public facing digital systems, deliver desktop services, oversee cyber security, and provide data, AI, and information management advice to over 2,400 staff, supporting over 30 office locations across Australia.\n\nThe IT Front Door and Architecture section is a critical bridge between departmental business areas and technology delivery. It supports business areas to shape and clarify IT-related demand so proposals are evidence‑based, aligned to strategy, and ready to progress through governance and delivery with reduced rework. The EL1 - Assistant Director, Business Architect operates as a senior specialist, working across stakeholders to ensure new IT investments align with strategic goals, architectural standards and enterprise direction.\n\nThis role is also designed as a development pathway into Enterprise Architecture, with progressive exposure to enterprise artefacts, governance and architecture practices over time.\n\nWhat will you do?\n\nIn this role you will:\n\nShape demand into decision‑ready proposals: translate business demand into clear, actionable IT requirements; improve the quality and completeness of intake; and help prioritise initiatives based on strategic alignment, capability needs and value considerations.\nFacilitate stakeholder alignment: build strong working relationships across business and IT; translate between business needs and technology considerations; and negotiate practical trade‑offs to resolve conflicting requirements.\nProvide investment assurance and uplift investment readiness: support triage and analysis of new initiatives and technology requests; strengthen business proposals to reduce misalignment and redundancy; and contribute to business case development for IT components (including NPP costings), identifying dependencies, risks and constraints early.\nMaintain business architecture artefacts: develop and maintain a Business Capability Model and related artefacts to identify capability gaps, overlaps and opportunities for transformation; and ensure technology investment aligns to business priorities and objectives.\nArchitecture integration deliverables (Front Door Architecture): produce “architecture‑ready” handover packs for shaped initiatives (problem statement, outcomes, assumptions, constraints, dependencies, key risks and options considered) and support architecture/design assurance activities by ensuring decisions and rationale are captured and traceable.\nPromote user‑centred and accessible outcomes: identify end‑user needs and apply best practice approaches (user research, human‑centred design and service design), ensuring proposals consider whole‑of‑government expectations including digital accessibility where relevant.\n\nWho are we looking for?\n\nThe successful candidate for this position will be able to demonstrate their capability against the Executive level 1 Work level standards.\n\nTo be successful in this role, you will need to demonstrate your ability to:\n\nShape ambiguous demand into structured advice: translate unclear requests into clear problem statements, requirements, options and recommendations suitable for decision‑making.\nEngage and influence stakeholders: build effective working relationships, facilitate discussions, and negotiate outcomes across diverse business and ICT stakeholders.\nDeliver investment assurance: support triage and analysis of initiatives with IT components; strengthen proposals to reduce misalignment and redundant effort; and identify risks, dependencies and constraints early.\nApply business architecture practices: develop and maintain capability models and use them to identify gaps, overlaps and alignment to business priorities.\nCommunicate clearly in executive-ready formats: prepare complex briefs, papers and correspondence that are well‑structured, evidence‑based and easy to consume.\nBring an Enterprise Architecture growth mindset: demonstrate an understanding of Enterprise Architecture concepts and a willingness to develop deeper architecture capability over time as part of a structured progression pathway.\n\nCultural capability requirement\n\nThe department believes every role contributes to cultural safety and that building staff cultural capability helps us deliver better policies, programs and services for First Nations people and the broader Australian community. Candidates will be required to demonstrate their willingness to develop their cultural capability as part of the assessment process. In making it a requirement across all roles in our department, we are taking a practical step in delivering our commitments under the Our Stories on Country Agreement and the Diversity, Equity and Inclusion Strategy 2025–28.\n\nAs an EL1 you will be expected to:\n\nLead the integration of cultural considerations into work area outcomes.\nBuild trusted relationships with Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander stakeholders.\nChampion cultural capability within teams and challenges culturally unsafe practices.\n\nRecruitAbility minimum requirements\n\nThe Department of Infrastructure, Transport, Regional Development, Communications, Sport and the Arts is committed to supporting the employment and career development of people with disability. Our participation in APS RecruitAbility means we will progress an applicant with disability to a further stage in the recruitment process, where they opt into RecruitAbility and meet the minimum requirements for the vacancy.\n\nYou will be asked to indicate if you wish to opt into RecruitAbility in the application form. You must tick the \'opt in\' box to participate in RecruitAbility. Simply declaring that you have a disability will not automatically include you.\n\nWe provide reasonable adjustments such as access, equipment or other practical support at relevant stages of the recruitment process. Please advise in the application form or the contact officer if you need any adjustments made.\n\nThe minimum requirements for this role include:\n\nDemonstrated experience translating business demand into clear, actionable requirements and advice suitable for decision‑making.\nDemonstrated stakeholder engagement and influence skills, including facilitating and negotiating outcomes across business and IT stakeholders.\nDemonstrated experience contributing to investment assurance activities (e.g., triage, options, risk/dependency identification, and/or business case support including NPP costings).\nDemonstrated capability in business architecture and/or business analysis practices, including capability modelling (or demonstrated equivalent experience).\n\nMore information can be found at RecruitAbility scheme: A guide for applicants | Australian Public Service Commission.\n\nWhat else can we offer?\n\nWe offer flexible work arrangements (including hybrid work options), access to learning and development opportunities, and support for professional growth and mobility across the Department and the broader APS. We encourage ongoing development aligned to role needs, including opportunities to build deeper architecture capability over time.\n\nEligibility requirements\n\nEmployment with the Department of Infrastructure, Transport, Regional Development, Communications, Sport and the Arts is subject to conditions prescribed within the Public Service Act 1999 including:\n\nCitizenship: candidates must be an Australian citizen at the time of submitting your application.\nHealth Assessment: The preferred candidate may be required to undergo a medical examination conducted by the department’s preferred medical provider.\nSecurity Clearance: The successful candidate must be able to obtain and/or maintain a security clearance at Baseline Level. You must be willing to disclose all relevant and required information. You must have lived in Australia, or have a checkable background, for at least the preceding five years for Baseline Vetting clearances. More information on the security clearance vetting process is available on the Australian Government Security Vetting Agency (AGSVA) website.\nPolice check: The successful candidate must satisfactory complete an Australian Federal Police criminal history check.\nIntegrity and Performance check: The successful candidate must satisfy the requirements in an Integrity and Performance check which is completed by your most recent employer.\n\nTimeline and assessment\n\nA selection panel will be established to assess your suitability against the advertised role.\n\nIf a merit pool is established it will be valid for 18 months from date it first appeared in the APS Gazette.\n\nApplications open: 01 May 2026\n\nApplications close: 17 May 2026\n\nApplication shortlisting: 22 May 2026\n\nFurther assessments: 29 May 2026\n\nSelection report finalised: 12 June 2026\n\nOffers and announcements: 19 June 2026\n\nThe above is indicative only, please reach out to the contact person if you have any questions on the recruitment process or timeframes.\n\nYour application will be assessed against the requirements of the job and the Work level standards. Once the entire applicant pool has been assessed, the panel will create a shortlist of applicants. If your application is shortlisted, you may be asked to undertake further assessment, this may include work sample testing, interviews, and reference checks.\n\nHow to apply\n\nApplications for this opportunity close at 11.59pm AEST, Sunday 17 May 2026.\n\nIn applying for this position, you are not required to address individual selection criteria. Rather, you should provide in a PDF document a statement of no more than 3 pages outlining your background, capabilities and experiences, and how these align with the advertised role.\n\nYou should also provide a tailored CV in PDF, no more than 10 pages. The capabilities and behaviours required to be successful for this role are identified in the ‘Who are we looking for’ section.\n\nYour application should be received through the department’s online recruitment system. Applications via Indeed will not be accepted.\n\nIf you experience any issues with the system please contact the recruitment team on 02 6136 8989 or via email at recruitment@infrastructure.gov.au to discuss an alternative way to submit your application.\n\nPlease advise the contact officer if you require adjustments during the recruitment process. We recognise and value diversity as our strength and promote a culture of inclusion to enhance our work performance and the wellbeing of our employees. We are committed to systems that are accessible, inclusive and safe for all. If you need any further information about accessibility and inclusion at our department, please contact DiversityandInclusion@infrastructure.gov.au.\n\nWork with us. Apply now!','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Australian Department of Infrastructure and Regional Development','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8aae40b0ae4966ae','scraped','3 days ago'),(2662,NULL,'job','Solution Designer (AU Citizen with Security Clearance)','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Accenture is a leading global professional services company that helps the world’s leading businesses, governments and other organizations build their digital core, optimize their operations, accelerate revenue growth and enhance citizen services—creating tangible value at speed and scale. We are a talent and innovation led company with 791,000 people serving clients in more than 120 countries. Technology is at the core of change today, and we are one of the world’s leaders in helping drive that change, with strong ecosystem relationships. We combine our strength in technology with unmatched industry experience, functional expertise and global delivery capability. We are uniquely able to deliver tangible outcomes because of our broad range of services, solutions and assets across Strategy & Consulting, Technology, Operations, Industry X and Accenture Song. These capabilities, together with our culture of shared success and commitment to creating 360° value, enable us to help our clients succeed and build trusted, lasting relationships. We measure our success by the 360° value we create for our clients, each other, our shareholders, partners and communities. Visit us at www.accenture.com.\n\nThe Accenture Microsoft Business Group (AMBG) is a strategic partnership between Accenture and Microsoft that combines the capabilities and expertise of both companies to help clients accelerate their digital transformation. The group offers end-to-end solutions across cloud, data, AI, security, and modern workplace, leveraging the power of Microsoft platforms such as Azure, Microsoft 365, Dynamics 365, and Power Platform. The group also provides industry-specific solutions and services tailored to the needs and challenges of different sectors and markets.\n\nAbout the role\n\nIgnite your passion for innovation! In this role, you will be a subject matter expert, collaborating with various teams to contribute to key decisions and provide solutions to challenges. You will engage with multiple teams and manage decisions that impact your immediate group and beyond. Your expertise in Solution Planning Costing & Pricing will be invaluable as you work towards creating effective solutions. We invite you to join us in this exciting journey where your contributions will make a significant difference!\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nDevelop detailed solution designs aligned to approved architecture and business requirements\n\nTranslate high level architecture into detailed technical designs and specifications\n\nDefine application components, integrations, data flows, and configuration details\n\nCollaborate closely with solution architects, developers, and business analysts to ensure design clarity\n\nEnsure designs align with non-functional requirements including security, performance, and scalability\n\nProduce and maintain solution design documentation and diagrams\n\nSupport development teams during build and test phases by clarifying design intent\n\nParticipate in design reviews and address technical risks and issues\n\nEnsure traceability between requirements, design, and implementation\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications\n\n5+ years’ experience in Solution Design, technical design, or senior engineering roles\n\nStrong experience producing detailed technical and solution design documentation\n\nSolid understanding of application development, integrations, and system design\n\nExperience working within defined architecture standards and frameworks\n\nFamiliarity with cloud platforms and modern application architectures\n\nExperience supporting Agile or hybrid delivery environments\n\nStrong analytical, problem-solving, and documentation skills\n\nExperience supporting Agile or hybrid delivery environments\n\nGood communication skills both written and verbal\n\nGood stakeholder engagement skills\n\nAbility to collaborate effectively with both technical and non-technical stakeholders\n\nBachelor\'s Degree in relevant field of studies.\n\nBonus Points if you have\n\nExpert proficiency in Requirements Analysis.\n\nExpert proficiency in Solution Architecture.\n\nExpert proficiency in Solution Planning Costing & Pricing.\n\nAdvanced problem solving\n\nBeginner process improvement\n\nMandatory Requirements\n\nCandidate must be an Australian Citizen with Baseline Security Clearance\n\nAll our consulting professionals receive comprehensive training covering business acumen, technical and professional skills development. You’ll also have opportunities to hone your functional skills and expertise in an area of specialization. We offer a variety of formal and informal training programs at every level to help you acquire and build specialized skills faster. Learning takes place both on the job and through formal training conducted online, in the classroom, or in collaboration with teammates. The sheer variety of work we do, and the experience it offers, provide an unbeatable platform from which to build a career.\n\nAccenture Benefits\n\nTo view our Progressive Employee Benefits covering Health, Wellbeing, Progressive Leave Options, Sustainability click on the link below.\n\nProgressive Employee Benefits – Australia\n\nThis is an exceptional opportunity for an exceptional individual.\n\nEqual Employment Opportunity Statement for Australia\n\nAt Accenture, we recognise that our people are multi-dimensional, and we create a work environment where all people feel like they can bring their authentic selves to work, every day.\n\nOur unwavering commitment to inclusion and diversity unleashes innovation and creates a culture where everyone feels they have equal opportunity. Our range of progressive policies support flexibility in ‘where’, ‘when’ and ‘how’ our people work to ensure that Accenture is an organisation where you can strive for more, achieve great things and maintain the balance and wellbeing you need.\n\nWe encourage applications from all people, and we are committed to removing barriers to the recruitment process and employee lifecycle. All employment decisions shall be made without regard to age, disability status, ethnicity, gender, gender identity or expression, religion or sexual orientation and we do not tolerate discrimination. If you require adjustments to the recruitment process or have a preferred communication method, please email exectalent@accenture.com and cite the relevant Job Number, or contact us on +61 2 9005 5000.\n\nTo ensure our workplace is inclusive and diverse we are setting bold goals and taking comprehensive action. To achieve these goals, we collect information that allows us to track the effectiveness of our Inclusion and Diversity programs. Learn how Accenture protects your personal data and know your rights in relation to your personal data. Read more about our Privacy Statement.\n\n#LI_GM\n\n.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Accenture','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6b02067bb0469184','scraped','3 days ago'),(2663,NULL,'job','OSHC Coordinator | St Elizabeth\'s','Part-time','Wanneroo WA 6065',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nPartnering with parents and school communities, at Junior Adventures Group (JAG) our goal is to help today\'s children navigate their tomorrow by supporting children\'s development through play in fun, engaging environments. We live and breathe our company values every day by being considerate, passionate, courageous, and making a difference.\n\nJob Description\n\nJoin us at St Elizabeth\'s, Wanneroo OSHClub, as an OSHClub Coordinator and lead a team of passionate Educators while making a real impact on the lives of children! This permanent, part-time role offers 33 hours per week, including 4 non-contact admin hours.\n\nYou’ll work across split shifts, Monday to Friday: 6:30-8:30am (Rise then Shine) 3:00-6:00pm (Stay and Play) 7:00am - 6:00pm (School Holiday Program)\n\nWhy JAG?\n\nCoordinator Loyalty Program – Enjoy $1,250 in retention bonuses during your first year as a thank-you for your commitment.\n\nEmployee Referral Rewards – Earn up to $1,000 cash for each successful referral—share the opportunity and get rewarded.\n\nGenerous childcare savings – Access 50% off childcare fees in addition to government subsidies\n\nExtra earning power – We’re approved for the ECEC Grant, giving you an additional boost.\n\nAccelerated career growth – Gain access to ongoing professional development, tailored leadership training, and dedicated mentorship to help you excel and advance confidently.\n\nGuaranteed interview – When you apply, we’ll fast-track you straight to an interview—no waiting, no wondering.\n\nAbout the role\n\nAs an OSHClub Coordinator, you’ll be leading a team of passionate Educators and overseeing an engaging before- and after-school program for children aged 5-12 years. This role is all about leadership:\n\nYou’ll create and lead a dynamic, child-centered program, filled with exciting activities like STEM, sports, cooking, arts and crafts—all designed to inspire and engage.\n\nYou’ll take full ownership of your team’s roster, manage day-to-day operations, ensure compliance, and handle admin tasks—all while fostering an environment of teamwork and growth.\n\nWith mentorship from regional managers and support from a dedicated office team, you’ll have everything you need to develop your leadership skills and make a real impact.\n\nQualifications\n\nWho we are looking for?\n\nIf you have a passion for supporting children, we’d love to hear from you! Here’s what we’re looking for:\n\n✔️ A natural leader who enjoys guiding a team and helping others grow.\n✔️ Strong communication skills—you’ll be leading by example!\n✔️ A team player who inspires others and encourages growth.\n✔️ You have (or are willing to obtain) a National Police Check and Working with Children Check.\n✔️ Australian work rights.\n✔️ A relevant qualification (or working towards it) as per ACECQA.\n\n✔ National Child Safety Training completion prior to onboarding\n\nAdditional Information\n\nNext Steps?\n\n We do things a bit differently here at JAG. After submitting your application, you’ll be invited to complete a quick 10-15 min chat-based interview. It’s part of our innovative and cutting-edge process to find the best people to work with us at JAG. It also gives you a chance to showcase your superior talents that aren’t easily captured on paper. Once you complete, we can move you through to the next stage. Since it’s such a valuable tool for career development, we will send you an overview of the results for your own benefit.\n\n Click ‘Apply’ and start your AI-powered chat today!\n\n#junioradventuresgroup\n\nAt Junior Adventures Group, child safety and child safeguarding principles are our top priorities. Our recruitment process includes thorough background checks and screenings to ensure the wellbeing of all children in our care.\n\nWe welcome individuals from all backgrounds, abilities, and identities, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Junior Adventures Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ddbd0607682c0549','scraped','4 days ago'),(2664,NULL,'job','QA Engineer (SQL, Python & Pyspark)','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nFor a winning team that is evolving. Forward with Cuscal.\n\nAt Cuscal, you’ll find a strong, successful company that’s reimagining the future. And our team is right there at the heart of it all. Here, you’ll deliver or support interesting, ground-breaking projects that have real impact - on Australia’s financial services sector and the millions of customers it serves. You’ll innovate alongside skilled, smart, connected teams. And you’ll build an impressive, fulfilling career that continues to grow. As the largest independent payment solution providers, we’ve set the standard for over 50 years. Now, we’re preparing to pioneer the next 50.\n\nJob Description\n\nWhat is this role about?\n\nThe Quality Assurance Automation Engineer is responsible for ensuring the reliability, security, and efficiency of our systems and applications by:\n\n• Overseeing the entire quality assurance process, from planning and strategizing to executing and maintaining test protocols.\n\n• Identifying and mitigating potential risks but also ensuring that all software products comply with regulatory standards and industry best practices.\n\n• By implementing testing methodologies and automated solutions.\n\n• Fostering a culture of quality and continuous improvement within the development team. This involves mentoring, collaborating with cross-functional teams, and driving the adoption of advanced testing techniques and tools.\n\n• Agile methodologies and test automation.\n\n• Understanding of financial processes allows them to design and execute tests.\n\n• Delivering reliable, high-quality financial services and products to its customers.\n\nQualifications\n\nWhat can you bring?\n\n5+ years of experience in quality assurance and automation testing, with a strong emphasis on software development lifecycle (SDLC) processes and methodologies.\nExperience with Python, SQL and Pyspark.\nExperience with Git (Bitbucket, Github etc.) and CI/CD tools and pipelines (e.g. Bamboo, Github Actions etc.).\nExperience using AI tools\n\nAlthough not required, any experience in the following would be considered highly desirable:\n\nKnowledge of PCI/DSS compliance standards\nKnowledge of AS2805 / ISO8353 standards\nPayment industry knowledge\nDatabricks\nSAP BODs\n\nAdditional Information\n\nWhy Cuscal?\nWe are in the rapidly evolving world of payments, and we are committed to providing a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. We support our colleagues with flexible work arrangements through our hybrid model whilst also offering a wide range of educational, financial, lifestyle, health & wellbeing benefits.\n\nNext Step\nIf you think this role is the right fit for you, we invite you to apply. Let’s explore who you are and what drives you. We’d love to share our vision for the future of payments sector. Please note candidate screening and interviews may be conducted prior to the closing date of the job advert.\n\nCuscal does not accept unsolicited resumes from recruitment agencies and search firms. Please do not email or send unsolicited resumes to any Cuscal employee, location or address.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Cuscal','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=01c028ae159c80a9','scraped','4 days ago'),(2665,NULL,'job','Senior Software Engineer, AI-Assisted Full Stack Development','Full-time','Brisbane QLD',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Forwood Safety is on a mission to make every shift safer and every workplace fatality-free. We build enterprise SaaS solutions that help organisations identify, manage and eliminate critical risks before serious incidents occur. Our engineering team embraces modern, AI-assisted development workflows to deliver high-quality software faster without compromising safety, security, or reliability.\n\nAs a Senior Software Engineer, you will help design, build, and maintain high-impact front-end and back-end systems while using AI co-pilot tooling as a core part of your daily workflow. You will own end-to-end feature delivery across our React/Remix + TypeScript front end and NestJS/AWS microservices back end, while helping shape how AI is used across the engineering team to improve velocity, quality, and consistency.\n\nThis is a 100% remote role based in Australia, working closely with teams in AU time zones.\n\nMain Responsibilities:\n\nDesign, build, and ship high-impact features across React/Remix front-end applications and NestJS/Node.js back-end services.\nDevelop and maintain secure, scalable REST and GraphQL APIs and microservices deployed on AWS.\nOwn features end-to-end, from design and implementation through to production release and ongoing optimisation.\nUse AI co-pilot tools (e.g. Cursor, GitHub Copilot, Windsurf) for code generation, refactoring, test creation, and documentation.\nDevelop and share effective prompt patterns and AI best practices to improve team productivity and code quality.\nValidate and secure AI-assisted code through testing, reviews, and static analysis.\nWrite and maintain unit, integration, and end-to-end tests (Jest, React Testing Library, Playwright/Cypress).\nContribute to CI/CD pipelines with automated quality gates, security scanning, and rollback strategies.\nMentor engineers on strong engineering fundamentals and effective AI-driven development workflows.\nStay current with emerging AI tools and identify opportunities to improve delivery through AI-enabled solutions.\n\nRequirements:\n\n5–7+ years of professional software engineering experience, with strong full-stack capability.\nAdvanced experience with React, TypeScript, and modern frameworks such as Remix or Vite.\nStrong back-end experience with Node.js/NestJS and microservice architectures.\nHands-on, daily use of AI co-pilot tools (Cursor, GitHub Copilot, Windsurf or similar). Proven ability to validate, test, and secure AI-assisted code.\nSolid experience with AWS (ECS, Lambda, RDS, S3, IAM, CloudWatch).\nExperience building and maintaining CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions, Bitbucket Pipelines).\nA production mindset with a strong focus on maintainability, security, and scalability.\nExcellent communication skills and a genuine interest in mentoring others.\nBased in Australia and able to collaborate effectively across AU time zones.\n\nIf you’re excited to combine solid engineering practices with AI-assisted workflows, and to use that capability to help prevent workplace fatalities, we’d love to hear from you.\n\nThis role is 100% remote but must be based in Australia.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Forwood Safety','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=18f89614f67a9a9a','scraped','4 days ago'),(2666,NULL,'job','Operations Coordinator','Permanent','Brookvale NSW 2100',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Systems‑savvy. Solutions‑focused. Obsessed with using technology to support teams to work better.\n\nIf that sounds like you, this could be your next move.\n\nDue to continued growth across our Recruitment, HR Consulting and Learning and Development teams, Allan Hall HR is looking for a proactive and highly organised Operations Coordinator to join our Operations Team. This is a hands‑on role where you’ll help improve efficiency, support our teams, and enhance both employee and client experience across the business.\n\nThis role is open to early‑career candidates, as well as those with more experience who enjoy being close to the detail and making things run smoothly. In this role, you will be trusted to take ownership, spot opportunities for improvement, and help shape how we work.\n\nWhat You’ll Be Doing\n\nWorking closely with senior team members, you will support the smooth running of the business as well as future business success and innovation. Your role will include:\n\nProviding day‑to‑day support across business systems including JobAdder, HubSpot, WorkflowMax, Employment Hero, Aircall and Xero.\nTroubleshooting system and process issues and working with our external IT provider to resolve technical matters.\nSupporting office operations, including meeting rooms, technology and facilities.\nRecording, documenting and maintaining business systems, processes and workflows.\nManaging data cleansing and coordinating reporting and insights across out teams.\nIdentifying inefficiencies and recommending automations and improvements to systems, processes and tools.\nResearching new technologies and best‑practice approaches to support business performance and improvement.\nCoordinating onboarding and offboarding across tools and systems.\n\nYou will be supported and trained - curiosity, willingness to learn and attention to detail matter more than knowing everything on day one.\n\nWhat You’ll Bring\n\nYou’ll thrive in this role if you’re organised, curious and enjoy working behind the scenes to make teams more effective. You’ll bring:\n\nPrevious experience in an office, admin, operations or professional services environment with a strong interest in systems and business support.\nConfidence across systems and applications, in particular all Microsoft 365 tools.\nExperience or aptitude with AI enabled tools (eg, HubSpot, Copilot / ChatGPT, JobAdder, Power BI).\nA high level of attention to detail and a natural ability to spot issues and improvement opportunities.\nA solutions‑focused, proactive and positive approach.\nThe ability to juggle multiple tasks and priorities.\nA collaborative, team-first approach and clear communication skills.\nFull Australian working rights (sponsorship is not available for this role).\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\nAllan Hall HR is a people‑first, established HR consulting firm based on Sydney’s Northern Beaches. We partner with a broad and growing client base to deliver practical, commercially focused and tailored people solutions, underpinned by a strong reputation and a highly collaborative team culture.\n\nWhat you can expect:\n\nA newly created role with genuine scope to add value, create efficiencies and automations and shape to how the business operates.\nTraining, support and mentoring from experienced leaders.\nOpportunities to develop your skills in operations, systems and continuous improvement.\nA collaborative, professional environment where initiative and ideas are encouraged.\n\nLet’s Talk\n\nIf you’re looking for a role where you can make a meaningful operational impact and grow your career in a supportive, high‑performing team, we’d love to hear from you.\n\nApply now with your resume and a brief cover note outlining your interest in the role\n\nCompany Overview\n\nPlease visit our company website for more information','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Allan Hall Human Resources','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ba2025e68037c84e','scraped','4 days ago'),(2667,NULL,'job','SaaS Sales Closer (High Commission | Remote)','Contract','Remote',NULL,'',155000.00,'$110,000 - $200,000 a year','Amaya AI is a fast-growing SaaS Product that helps businesses better understand and optimise their sales and customer conversations using AI-driven insights.\n\nWe are currently expanding our remote sales team and are hiring *Sales Closers* to handle qualified meetings and convert them into paying customers.\n\nThis is a *fully remote, commission-based role* suited to individuals who are confident communicating with others, experienced in sales conversations (or eager to develop this skill), and motivated by performance. The role involves running sales calls with business owners, understanding their needs, presenting the product, handling objections, and closing deals.\n\nWe’re looking for people who are consistent, coachable, and enjoy working in a structured, fast-moving environment where performance and results are clearly measured.\n\n*Key Responsibilities*\n\n* Run sales calls with qualified leads (booked meetings provided or self-generated depending on structure)\n* Speak with business owners and decision-makers\n* Understand customer needs and present Amaya AI effectively\n* Handle objections and guide prospects through the decision-making process\n* Close deals and convert opportunities into customers\n* Maintain accurate notes and update CRM / tracking systems\n\n*Requirements*\n\n* Strong communication and persuasion skills\n* Confidence running sales conversations with decision-makers\n* Ability to handle objections professionally\n* Self-motivated and able to work independently\n* Consistent work ethic and willingness to learn\n* Previous sales experience (B2B, closing, SDR, or call-based roles) is beneficial but not required\n\n*Role Expectations*\n\n* Attend and run sales calls consistently\n* Follow up on leads when required\n* Maintain organised pipeline and notes\n* Focus on closing qualified opportunities\n* Maintain high standards of communication and professionalism\n\n*Compensation*\n\n* Commission-based role\n* Earn per deal closed (approx. *25% commission*)\n* Uncapped earning potential based on performance\n\n*This Role May Not Be Suitable If You:*\n\n* Prefer a fixed salary or hourly structure\n* Are not comfortable running sales calls\n* Struggle with rejection or objection handling\n* Require constant supervision or structure\n\n*What We Offer*\n\n* Fully remote work environment\n* Flexible schedule\n* Opportunity to work in a fast-growing SaaS environment\n* High earning potential based on performance\n* Clear progression opportunities within the sales team\n\n*Application Process*\n\nShortlisted candidates will be contacted and asked to complete a short screening task, including a brief voice note to assess communication and sales ability.\n\nOnly candidates who complete this step will be considered.\n\n*Additional Information*\n\nStart Date: Immediate\n\nJob Type: Contract\nContract length: 800 months\n\nPay: $110,000.00 – $200,000.00 per year\n\nWork Location: Remote','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amaya AI','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ea9cc34197319463','scraped','4 days ago'),(2668,NULL,'job','Talent Acquisition & HR Specialist – Remote','Permanent','Canberra ACT 2600',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Talent Acquisition & HR Specialist — Remote\n\nFull-time | 100% Remote | Play a key role for a $3.3B Global AutoTech Unicorn | 3-4 days per week (up to 30 hours)\n\nAbout Cars24 Australia\n\nCars24 is one of the world\'s largest AutoTech companies — and in Australia, we\'ve built the country\'s largest online pre-loved car dealership. We\'re changing how Australians buy cars: fully online, transparent, and backed by a world-first 30-day money-back guarantee.\n\nBehind that experience is a fast-scaling team across sales, operations, customer experience and refurbishment — and we\'re growing fast.\n\nThis role sits inside that growth story. You\'ll work remotely, directly under the Cars24 Australia People & Culture Head, supporting hiring and HR admin across the entire Australia business.\n\nWhy This Role\n\nThis is not a typical recruiter role. You won\'t be one of dozens working in a large agency or shared services team. You\'ll be working directly with the Australia HR lead, senior hiring managers, and executives across both Australia and India — getting real visibility into how a high-growth global business builds its teams.\n\nIf you\'re sharp, fast, and genuinely enjoy speaking to people, this role offers something most remote recruitment roles don\'t: direct exposure to a global business, a clear pathway into broader HR and People functions, and the kind of ownership that accelerates a career 100x.\n\nWhat You\'ll Do\n\nTalent Acquisition & Candidate Experience\n\nManage end-to-end recruitment across multiple role types — sales, operations, customer experience, refurbishment, tech and corporate\nConduct structured phone screenings with Australian candidates — speed and quality both matter\nRepresent Cars24 Australia as a compelling, high-performance place to work\nCoordinate interview scheduling with hiring managers and ensure a smooth, professional candidate journey throughout\n\nStakeholder Management\n\nLiaise with hiring managers across Australia and India to understand role requirements and gather timely feedback\nDrive next steps confidently — progression, rejection, offer coordination\nMaintain clear and proactive communication with all parties at every stage\n\nRecruitment Operations\n\nPost roles across SEEK, LinkedIn and Employment Hero ATS\nKeep candidate pipelines organised and data accurate at all times\nIssue employment contracts, support onboarding coordination and assist with offboarding and employment changes\nMaintain accurate records across HR systems\n\nHR Exposure & Growth\n\nSupport broader People & Culture operations including onboarding documentation and HR administration\nLearn directly from experienced HR leaders and gain exposure to Australian employment frameworks\nGrow into broader HR, Talent Lead or People Operations responsibilities over time\n\n✅ What You Bring\n\n2-3+ years of experience in talent acquisition, recruitment coordination or HR\nExceptional spoken and written English — this is an Australian-facing role and non-negotiable\nExperience working with international teams or in fully English-speaking professional environments\nHands-on experience with ATS platforms — Employment Hero or Workable strongly preferred\nConfidence using AI tools including Claude, ChatGPT or Gemini as part of your daily workflow\nStrong organisational skills and the ability to manage multiple open roles simultaneously\nHigh ownership mindset — you follow through, close loops, and don\'t let candidates sit in limbo\nDegree or qualification in Human Resources, Business Administration or a related field\n\nWhat Makes This Different\n\nDirect exposure to the Australia business of a $3.3B global AutoTech unicorn\nWork closely with founders, executives and senior leaders across two countries\nReal ownership — not just coordination, but genuine impact on candidate experience and hiring outcomes\nClear pathway into HR, Talent Lead or broader People Operations roles\nFully remote and flexible — built for someone who works well independently\n\nThe Kind of Person Who Will Thrive Here\n\nYou enjoy speaking to people and you\'re good at it. You move quickly and take pride in a strong candidate experience. You want more than task management — you want career exposure, global context, and the opportunity to grow fast inside a business that\'s scaling.\n\nApply Now\n\nIf you\'re looking for a remote role with real responsibility, global exposure and a genuine pathway forward — we\'d like to hear from you.\n\nCompany Overview\n\nAt Cars24, our mission is simple: to make buying and selling cars easy, transparent and fully online. We exist to remove the friction, uncertainty and inefficiency that have traditionally defined the car industry. We value ownership, speed and customer obsession. We back data over opinion, action over perfection, and we hold ourselves accountable to high standards. Our culture is fast-paced and performance-driven, but grounded in trust and collaboration. We encourage people to think like builders, challenge assumptions and improve the system, not just operate within it. At our core, we are here to simplify one of life’s bigger purchases and give customers more control and confidence at every step of the journey.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Cars24','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a5401d6f8b5b2ef2','scraped','4 days ago'),(2669,NULL,'job','Graphic Designer','Permanent','Belconnen ACT 2617',NULL,'',57500.00,'$55,000 - $60,000 a year','Graphic Designer\n\n*Koala Ink Pty Ltd*\n*Westfield Belconnen, Canberra ACT*\n*Full-time | $60,000 package including super | Weekend roster required*\n\nAbout Koala Ink\n\nKoala Ink is a new retail print and personalisation shop opening at *Shop 161, Level 3, Westfield Belconnen*.\n\nWe combine *on-the-spot design*, *personalised products*, and *modern digital printing technology* to create customised items for customers in-store and online. Customers will be able to request artwork, upload files, and order personalised products through our website, as well as visit the shop for live design support.\n\nWe are looking for a reliable, creative and hands-on person to join us as a *Graphic Designer / Online Orders & UV Print Production team member*.\n\nAbout the role\n\nThis is a *multi-role position* suited to someone who enjoys design, customer interaction, online order handling, and learning print production.\n\nYou will create print-ready artwork, assist customers in-store, respond to online artwork requests, and participate in UV print production using modern equipment, including a *Roland VersaOBJECT MO-240 UV printer*.\n\nTraining will be provided for UV print production, machine care, maintenance routines and shop workflows.\n\nKey responsibilitiesDesign and customer artwork\n\nYou will:\n\n* Create print-ready artwork quickly and accurately for personalised products\n* Work directly with customers in-store, including live edits while customers are present\n* Handle artwork requests received through website submissions, phone enquiries, chat/email and uploads\n* Prepare files correctly for production, including sizing, templates, resolution, formats and naming conventions\n\nOnline orders and fulfilment\n\nYou will:\n\n* Monitor and respond to online order and artwork requests\n* Convert customer briefs into artwork drafts efficiently\n* Request clarification from customers where required\n* Support order tracking, packing, handover, shipping preparation and basic customer updates\n\nUV print production\n\nYou will:\n\n* Assist with UV print production using equipment such as the Roland MO-240\n* Help with print setup, basic checks, safe handling and quality control\n* Follow procedures carefully when working with high-value machinery\n* Report any issues promptly\n\nEquipment care and shop presentation\n\nYou will:\n\n* Complete daily cleaning and basic maintenance tasks as required\n* Keep the production area, workstation and shop tidy and organised\n* Follow maintenance checklists and basic operating procedures\n* Assist with general shop duties, file organisation, material handling and basic housekeeping\n\nMarketing and social media\n\nYou should be comfortable occasionally appearing in simple company marketing content such as short clips, product showcases or behind-the-scenes videos. This is not an influencer role, but you should be comfortable being on camera from time to time.\n\nWhat we are looking for\n\nThe ideal candidate will have:\n\n* Strong skills in *Adobe Illustrator and Photoshop*\n* Ability to create print-ready artwork quickly and accurately\n* Confidence using AI creative tools to assist with concepts and artwork preparation\n* Good communication skills with customers, both in person and online\n* Ability to work under pressure when customers are waiting\n* Basic computer/admin skills, including Word and Excel\n* A reliable, punctual and careful approach to work\n* A responsible attitude when working with expensive machinery\n\nHighly regarded but not essential\n\nExperience in any of the following would be an advantage:\n\n* Digital printing or print production\n* Roland, Mimaki or similar printing equipment\n* E-commerce order handling\n* Customer service or retail work\n* Personalised products, signage, gifts or custom printing\n\nWhat we offer\n\n* Full-time role in a new retail print business\n* Training on UV print production and Roland MO-240 workflows\n* Exposure to both retail and online custom order systems\n* A creative, fast-moving shop environment in a major shopping centre\n* Opportunity to grow with the business as the product range expands\n\nImportant details\n\n*Location:* Shop 161, Level 3, Westfield Belconnen, Canberra ACT\n*Employment type:* Full-time\n*Salary:* $60,000 package including super\n*Roster:* Weekend work will be required as part of shopping centre trading hours\n\nHow to apply\n\nPlease apply with your resume and, where available, examples of your design work or portfolio.\n\nWe are looking for someone who is creative, reliable, hands-on, and willing to learn both the design and production side of a modern personalised printing business.\n\nPay: $55,000.00 – $60,000.00 per year\n\nWork Location: In person','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Kola Ink Pty Ltd','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=109576abcba80fb6','scraped','4 days ago'),(2670,NULL,'job','Donor Engagement & Marketing Strategist','Permanent','Blackburn North VIC 3130',NULL,'',115000.00,'$100,000 - $130,000 a year','*Donor Engagement & Marketing Strategist*\n\n*Part-time, minimum 3 days per week, with flexibility to increaseMelbourne / hybridHeartburst Pty Ltd*\n\nHeartburst helps nonprofits, faith-aligned organisations and purpose-driven teams build better digital systems for engagement, fundraising and growth.\n\nWe work across CRM, websites, donor journeys, automation, reporting, integrations and digital experience. Our clients are doing meaningful work, but their systems, communications and donor journeys are not always keeping up with the mission.\n\nWe are looking for a *Donor Engagement & Marketing Strategist* to help turn strategy into practical action for clients, while also supporting Heartburst’s own marketing.\n\nThis is not a traditional marketing manager role. It is a hands-on strategic role for someone who can think clearly, write well, use AI intelligently, engage with clients, and produce practical work.\n\n*The role*\n\nYou will help clients improve how they engage supporters, donors, customers and communities.\n\nThis may include donor journey planning, campaign ideas, email content, marketing coordination, CRM-enabled engagement, workshops, case studies, newsletter content, campaign briefs and implementation planning.\n\nYou do not need to be a deep technical specialist in every tool. Google Ad Grants, advanced paid ads, deep CRM configuration and analytics setup can be supported by specialists. However, you need enough understanding to brief specialists well, work with technical teams and help clients make sensible decisions.\n\nAI-assisted work is important to how we operate. We expect you to use AI tools confidently for research, ideation, drafting, repurposing, workshop preparation and campaign development — while still applying human judgement, accuracy, tone and commercial sense.\n\n*What you will do*\n\nYou will support and sometimes lead work such as:\n\n* Donor journey workshops, mapping and implementation planning\n* Practical marketing and donor engagement strategy\n* Campaign planning for nonprofits, ministries, schools and purpose-led organisations\n* Email journey planning, copywriting and nurture content\n* Persona, segmentation and messaging work\n* CRM-enabled engagement planning, including tags, segments, automations, forms and reporting requirements\n* Content briefs for landing pages, website updates and campaign assets\n* Coordination with designers, developers, CRM specialists and external contractors\n* Client meeting preparation, notes, follow-up actions and progress updates\n* Campaign review and practical optimisation recommendations\n\nYou will also help keep Heartburst’s own marketing moving, including newsletters, case studies, award submissions, speaking applications, LinkedIn / website content, offer promotion and repurposing content from webinars, talks and proposals.\n\n*What we are looking for*\n\nYou are likely to have *4–7+ years of experience* in marketing, digital, fundraising communications, donor engagement, content strategy or a related field.\n\nYou may have worked in an agency, nonprofit, ministry, school, consultancy, digital team or purpose-led organisation.\n\nYou should be able to:\n\n* Think strategically, but still enjoy getting on the tools\n* Write clearly and persuasively\n* Turn messy client conversations into clear actions\n* Prepare workshops, campaign plans and client-ready documents\n* Use AI tools fluently without outsourcing your judgement\n* Understand donor/supporter journeys and how communication builds trust over time\n* Work with email marketing, CRM, website and campaign tools at a practical level\n* Brief technical specialists clearly when deeper expertise is required\n* Keep client work moving without needing constant supervision\n* Communicate confidently with senior clients while staying practical and grounded\n\n*What would make you stand out*\n\n* Experience with nonprofits, charities, churches, schools, membership organisations or purpose-led organisations\n* Experience with donor journeys, supporter engagement or fundraising communications\n* Experience writing email journeys, appeals, newsletters or nurture campaigns\n* Familiarity with platforms such as Mailchimp, Campaign Monitor, HubSpot, Virtuous, Salesforce, Blackbaud, Raisely, Brevo, WordPress or similar\n* Experience coordinating Google Ad Grants or paid campaigns, even if not as a deep technical specialist\n* Strong attention to detail without getting stuck in perfectionism\n* Comfort working in a small team where priorities can shift quickly\n\n*What this role is not*\n\nThis is not a pure social media role, a traditional fundraising role, a back-office administration role, a senior marketing manager role, or a specialist Google Ads / CRM technician role.\n\nIt is a role for someone who can help nonprofits clarify their message, engage supporters, improve donor journeys and turn strategy into practical marketing activity.\n\n*Why Heartburst*\n\nHeartburst is building a strong position in nonprofit CRM, donor engagement systems, digital experience and automation.\n\nWe are growing our work with organisations that need more than a website or a campaign. They need connected systems that help them engage supporters, improve retention, reduce friction and scale their impact.\n\nYou will join a small, capable team where your work will directly shape client outcomes and Heartburst’s own growth.\n\n*Hours and remuneration*\n\nThis is a *part-time role of at least 3 days per week*, with some flexibility around exact days and the potential to increase as client demand grows.\n\nIndicative full-time equivalent remuneration is *$100,000–$130,000 + super*, pro rata based on agreed days, depending on experience and capability.\n\n*How to apply*\n\nPlease send us:\n\n* Your CV or LinkedIn profile\n* A short note outlining why this role interests you\n* 2–3 examples of relevant work, such as campaign content, donor communications, strategy documents, email journeys, case studies, workshop outputs or marketing plans\n\nWe are less interested in polished corporate language and more interested in clear thinking, strong writing and practical evidence that you can help move meaningful work forward.\n\nJob Types: Part-time, Permanent\n\nPay: $100,000.00 – $130,000.00 per year\n\nExpected hours: 24 per week\n\n\n\nAbility to commute/relocate:\n* Blackburn North VIC 3130: Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Required)\n\nApplication Question(s):\n* Which of the following best describes your experience level?\n\nMostly coordination / administration\nHands-on marketing execution\nHands-on strategy and execution\nMarketing management / team leadership\nSpecialist technical marketing role\n* Which of the following have you personally produced? Select all that apply.\n\nOptions:\n\nEmail campaigns or nurture sequences\nCampaign plans\nMarketing strategy documents\nDonor/supporter communications\nCase studies or website articles\nWorkshop materials\nClient-ready reports or recommendations\nSocial media content only\nNone of the above\n* How confident are you using AI tools such as ChatGPT, Claude or similar in your work?\n\nOptions:\n\nI use AI regularly and confidently as part of my workflow\nI use AI occasionally\nI have experimented with AI but do not use it much\nI do not currently use AI tools\n* Are you comfortable working directly with clients or senior stakeholders?\n\nOptions:\n\nYes, I regularly lead or contribute to client/stakeholder meetings\nYes, I have some experience\nI prefer mostly internal execution work\nNo\n* What is your expected full-time equivalent salary, excluding super?\n\nExperience:\n* Digital marketing: 3 years (Required)\n\nWork Authorisation:\n* Australia (Required)\n\nWork Location: Hybrid remote in Blackburn North VIC 3130','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Heartburst','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=431b670f2289a682','scraped','4 days ago'),(2671,NULL,'job','Marketing & Design Associate','Part-time','Brunswick VIC 3056',NULL,'',29.50,'$25 - $34 an hour','We’re on a mission to build an ecosystem of products & education for Framer (no-code website design tool). We’re a fast-moving startup, with 10,000+ global customers, 35,000+ community of designers & epic clients such as Framer & Lovable (the world’s fastest growing startup).\n\n*Learn more about us:* https://insertframe.io/about\n\nContractor, 2 days/wk to start. The hope is that we continue working together on a long term basis & this role becomes full-time.\n\n*What you\'ll actually do*\n\nYou take direction and turn it into work that ships. That could look like:\n\n* Designing social posts, thumbnails, and website graphics/updates\n* Writing first drafts of emails, blogs, and captions\n* Scheduling and managing our social content across channels\n* Keeping our docs, showcase and content engine running\n* Supporting our Head of Operations & Marketing on whatever\'s in front of us that week\n\n*No two weeks look the same - Intentional.*\n\n*Why work at Insert Frame?*\n\n* Be at the forefront of the design industry\n* A great team passionate about what we do\n* Our trust. We want you to take ownership of your work!\n* Learning & growth with Framer & no-code tools\n* Work directly with the leadership team\n* Work remotely or from our uber-cool Brunswick office\n\n*What you need*\n\n* Figma skills - not portfolio-perfect, but you know your way around\n* A background in tech or startups\n* Strong communication skills\n* Human skills (we love & use AI, but people matter most in this role)\n* You\'ve run socials for yourself, a small business, or a side project\n* You can take an early-stage idea and run with it until it\'s done\n* You\'re comfortable with ambiguity and know how to find clarity fast\n\n*Show us what you’ve got (30‑second video)*\n\nAlong with your application, we’d love a *30-second video*. It can be:\n\n* A quick intro about who you are and what you’re into, *or*\n* A short piece of content you’ve created that you’re proud of\n\nThis doesn’t need to be fancy or highly produced, your phone camera, Loom, whatever works. We just want to get a feel for your personality and how you think about content.\n\nSend your video (or a link to it) to *georgia@insertframe.io* & *ryan@insertframe.io* with the subject line: `Insert Frame Application Video`\n\n*Bonus points*\n\n* You use Framer or are genuinely curious about it\n* You have a side hustle (the weirder the better)\n* You\'ve worked in a fast-moving startup before\n* You\'re Melbourne-based or want to be in the room\n* Being super competitive at Mario Kart\n\n*If this sounds like the role for you, apply now! *Got a question? Reach out to georgia@insertframe.io / ryan@insertframe.io\n\nJob Types: Part-time, Contract\n\nPay: $25.00 – $34.00 per hour\n\nBenefits:\n* Work from home\n\nWork Location: Hybrid remote in Brunswick VIC 3056','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Insert Frame','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ddfee4fc701cd382','scraped','4 days ago'),(2672,NULL,'job','Enterprise Account Executive - Sydney','','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Founded in 2017, Obsidian Security was created to close a critical gap: securing the SaaS applications where modern business happens—platforms like Microsoft 365, Salesforce, and hundreds more.\n\nBacked by top investors including Greylock, Norwest Venture Partners, and IVP, we\'ve built a complete SaaS security platform to reduce risk, detect and respond to threats, and prevent breaches at the source. Our team includes leaders who helped define the categories of endpoint and identity security at CrowdStrike, Okta, Cylance, and Carbon Black.\n\nNow, we\'re transforming how SaaS is secured—in the era of agentic AI.\n\nToday, Obsidian is trusted by global enterprises like Snowflake, T-Mobile, and Pure Storage. We protect more than 200 organizations across North America, Europe, the Middle East, Southeast Asia, Australia, and New Zealand—including many of the world\'s largest Fortune 1000 and Global 2000 companies.\n\nWith strong global momentum, a growing partner ecosystem including SentinelOne, Databricks, and Google Cloud, and a major fundraise on the horizon, we\'re scaling quickly toward long-term growth and IPO readiness. Join us as we define the future of SaaS security!\n\nAbout the Team:\n\nWe\'re looking for a hardworking, focused and driven Enterprise Account Executive to channel energy, passion and initiative into new logo acquisition. You\'ll be responsible for developing and executing against a comprehensive account/territory plan whilst working collaboratively with our internal and external resources.\n\nAbout the Role:\n\nProactively, identify, qualify and close sales pipeline across your territory and accounts\nClose business to meet and exceed monthly, quarterly and annual business targets\nDemonstrate an extensive understanding of the Obsidian Security offering and our value to our customers\nAlign with our partners and alliances to optimize opportunities\nPartner with internal resources across Sales Engineering, Customer Success and Professional Services\nDemonstrate accurate pipeline forecasting and management\nActively participate in our sales enablement training\n\nAbout You:\n\n10+ years of enterprise sales experience\nWorking knowledge of sales concepts, methods and techniques\nExperience evangelizing new technology into F1000 accounts.\nAble to maintain and manage existing client relationships and accounts.\nAble to utilize existing client and/or C-Level relationships, as well as build new relationships across IT Security as well as other lines of business.\nSelf Starter that creates and maintains a sales pipeline by capturing accurate and complete information in selected CRM databases including activity, closing, project forecast, close ratios and market intelligence.\nStrong ability to understand a customer\'s business issues and needs and be able to articulate and map back value to a solution.\nStrong prospecting skills, deal qualification, and POV management skills, leading to acquisition of new business.\nTeam player with the ability to collaborate well with internal stakeholders or partners to drive opportunities to closure.\nNeed to maintain and keep up with market trends, competitor analysis, and market conditions which may impact customers.\nAble to learn quickly and ramp to be able to effectively articulate and differentiate the value of our product to prospective clients.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Obsidian Security','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9c842ccdbcd5489c','scraped','4 days ago'),(2673,NULL,'job','Trade Compliance Officer (AU)','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Work with cutting edge AI technology, making the world a safer and more secure place. DroneShield (ASX:DRO) offers an opportunity to solve some of world’s most challenging technical problems in the rapidly growing counter-drone sector.\n\nOur customers operate in some of the most challenging and high-stakes environments in the world, including military organisations, government agencies, airports, critical infrastructure operators, and law enforcement. Protecting airspace in these settings requires technology that performs under pressure and teams that understand what’s at stake. At DroneShield, employees work at the leading edge of counter-drone innovation, helping to address real-world security challenges as drone threats continue to evolve globally.\n\nWith one of the largest listed defence company market capitalisations in Australia, now part of the ASX200 index, DroneShield is experiencing a period of hypergrowth. Revenue has surged from A$57 million in 2024 to over A$190 million in 2025, representing growth of more than 400% year-on-year, with record profitability and cashflow. The total addressable global market for counter-drone is assessed at approximately $100 billion, and is currently at the nascent stage with much of the growth still to come, with DroneShield well positioned as a global market leader, and the only public listed pure-play business in this sector.\n\nThe company has grown from 11 employees in 2017 to over 450 staff globally today, and is on track to reach around 550 by the end of 2026. This expansion includes investment of over A$50 million annually in R&D, a global pipeline exceeding A$2.5 billion, and continuous scaling of production capacity to meet accelerating demand.\n\nThe role is based at DroneShield’s central Sydney headquarters. Overseas on-the-ground presence includes Virginia (USA), Netherlands, Denmark, Mexico and Dubai, as well as distributors in over 70 countries worldwide.\n\nAbout the role\n\nThe Trade Compliance Officer will be responsible for assisting a comprehensive global trade compliance program ensuring adherence to Australian and international export controls regulations. This role requires expertise in trade regulations and export controls related to goods for both munition and dual-use lists, with a particular focus on Australian regulations.\n\nResponsibilities, Duties and Expectations\n\nSupport the global trade compliance framework, ensuring alignment between Australian trade and export control requirements and the organisation’s global compliance standards\nAssist the global trade compliance team with ensuring all import and export activities comply with Australian regulations, while supporting compliance with international export control regimes, including U.S. (ITAR/EAR) and European regulations\nAct as a regional point of contact for Australia, providing guidance and support to global stakeholders on Australian export controls and regulatory requirements\nMonitor, interpret and communicate changes in Australian export control and customs regulations to the global trade compliance team, supporting export assessments and implementation activities\nAssist with export control classifications for goods, technology and software, ensuring classifications are communicated and consistent across global systems and jurisdictions\nSupport the preparation, drafting and submission of export/import permits under the Australian regulatory framework, in coordination with global licensing requirements\nMaintain accurate record‑keeping and export registers, ensuring documentation meets both Australian and International regulatory requirements\nContribute to global trade compliance initiatives, including process improvement, internal controls, training, and audit readiness activities\n\nQualifications, Experience and Skills\n\nEducation: Bachelor’s or Master degree in Law, International Business, Supply Chain Management, Logistics Management or proven equivalent field experience\nMinimum 1–2 years’ experience in trade compliance, export controls, customs brokerage or a related regulatory role\nExperience supporting or working within a multi-jurisdictional or global trade compliance environment;\nDefence or aerospace industry experience strongly preferred\nDemonstrable knowledge of Australian export control and customs regulations, with awareness of major international export control regimes\n\nNote for recruitment agencies: We do not accept unsolicited candidates from external recruiters unless specifically instructed.\n\n#669','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'DroneShield Limited','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=df35984db0afe971','scraped','4 days ago'),(2674,NULL,'job','Banking Technical Consultant','','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'About Us:\n\nInnovation is and will always be the core of SAP Fioneer, and it is the promise of why we were spun out of SAP: agility, innovation, and delivery.\n\nSAP Fioneer builds on a heritage of outstanding technology and a deep understanding of corporate and consumer demands. At the heart of it all it is simple: We bring financial services to the next level with innovative software solutions and platforms.\n\nWe are helping companies in the financial services industry to achieve speed, scalability, and cost-efficiency through digital business innovation, cloud technology, and solutions that cover banking and insurance processes end-to-end.\n\nA global company, with rapid growth, innovative people, and a lean organization makes SAP Fioneer a place where you accelerate your future!\n\nThe SAP Fioneer Banking Technical Consultant will play a leading role in the SAP Technical team within the Banking Business Unit. Many of our customers are installing or upgrading to the latest version of our software platform. There is a large demand for people who can help us work with our clients in converting their software to the latest version of the platform and at the same time identify and realise value adding business opportunities together with our clients.\n\nYou will be responsible for both sales and delivery of SAP Fioneer banking related projects. This includes sales and pre-sales activities of opportunity identification, pre-sales presentation and proposal writing and submission. You will be responsible for the quality of client interaction including thought leadership and guidance on industry best practice, while also playing a key role in the delivery and implementation of the required technical solution. You will follow project standards within established timeframes and at defined quality levels, and ensure projects are completed according to schedule and client specifications. This position is client-facing and requires travel to the client site as the project warrants.\n\nYou will work as a trusted technical advisor to our banking clients on their transformation journeys. On this path, you get the chance to play high visibility roles with hands-on experience with Fioneer banking product portfolio.\n\nYou will provide the following technical advisory roles and services as part of SAP Fioneer Banking implementations:\n\nWork closely with bank\'s Solution Architects, Product Owners, and Scrum Masters in defining the scope of work to be delivered\nProviding SAP Fioneer Banking technical expertise to internal and external stakeholders\nProviding thought leadership on platform conversion options and methods towards the latest releases of our software (TRBK on S/4 Hana)\nProviding thought leadership on legacy system migration to SAP Banking platform\nParticipate in development and implementation of the SAP Fioneer team strategy.\nTraining and mentorship of junior resources.\nMaintain, enhance, and broaden knowledge and skills of SAP Fioneer Banking applications, industry technology best practices and developments.\nInteract with clients to provide them insights and possibilities within the Technology domain to help shape and craft their transformation journeys, with specific focus on the SAP Fioneer technical capabilities and integration patterns\nUse subject matter knowledge to advise the client on the most suitable options, including when to make use of standard capabilities or when customisation is required\nFunctional knowledge in some of SAP Banking Modules like Deposit Management / Loans Management / Master Contract management is mandatory.\nConsulting knowledge and experience in evaluating customer requirements, and propose Solution / Architecture approaches.\nProficiency in ABAP Technologies - ABAP Workbench, ABAP Data Dictionary, Report Programming, Data Migration, Screen Programming, SmartForms, Adobe forms, Authorizations, ALE/IDOC, Workflow, Web Dynpro ABAP, OO ABAP, Enhancements & Modifications.\nRecording of requirements from the specialist department, e.g. via workshops or coordination meetings, and creation of solution concepts as a basis for the implementation of software\nCreate the necessary design and build artefacts\nProvide SAP Fioneer Design Authority for the approved scope of work\nProduce SAP Fioneer Technical architecture and design documents\nProduce SAP Fioneer Software configuration design documents\nProduce SAP Fioneer Software integration and interface design documentation\nCollaborate in integrating SAP Fioneer solutions into channels and downstream systems\n\nRequirements\n\nBachelor or master’s degree in finance, computer science, technology, or engineering\n8+ years of consulting experience in at least 3 of the SAP Core banking domains like Deposits, Loans, Master Contracts, Collateral Management & Payments\nExperience with modern SAP technologies such as API management, REST/OData, and event‑driven architecture.\nSolid technology architecture knowledge and understanding, ideally in software or cloud solutions\nProven industry relevant track record of in-depth knowledge of SAP Fioneer technical platform capabilities and functional capabilities, implementations, associated standards, practices and regulations\nClient facing service experience required. Engagement across stakeholders and ability to run information gathering and sharing sessions\nMaintain a strong understanding of emerging AI trends and apply AI‑driven techniques to enhance analysis, automation, and delivery efficiency within SAP Fioneer Banking implementations.\n\nTechnical Skills:\n\nSolid SAP Fioneer Banking Technical project experience, including implementation, platform upgrade, legacy migrations and data migration\nA working knowledge of domestic and international banking domains\nSolid Business Writing Skills (business cases, proposals)\nSolid Presentation and Facilitation Skills\nEagerness to learn and to take responsibility\nYou demonstrate ownership and accountability in everything you do\n\nSoft Skills:\n\nStrong analytical and problem-solving skills.\nGood communication and teamwork abilities.\nWillingness to learn and adapt to new technologies and processes.\nAbility to work independently and handle multiple priorities.\n\nBenefits\n\nYou will have the opportunity to collaborate with some of the brightest minds in the industry on an incredibly ambitious project to shape the ever-evolving financial sector. This is an environment where you can have it all - the agility, enthusiasm and dynamism of a start-up, combined with the established expertise, solid market presence and extensive customer network of a more established organisation.\n\nAt SAP Fioneer, you will benefit from a flexible work environment that encourages creativity and encourages you to think outside the box, bring new ideas to the table, and challenge the status quo. You will become part of a diverse and global team that we are proud of and are constantly growing and reinventing. As an employee, you will have the chance to chart your own career path and take advantage of competitive compensation packages and progression opportunities based on merit.\n\nWe offer pension plans and life insurance for financial security. Our health and wellbeing benefits include private medical insurance, wellness cover, and an employee assistance program.\n\nSAP FIONEER DIVERSITY COMMITMENT\n\n SAP Fioneer believes in the power of innovation that each employee brings and would like to leverage the qualities and appreciate the unique competencies that each diverse person brings to the company.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'SAP Fioneer','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=35312b9725f540f6','scraped','4 days ago'),(2675,NULL,'job','Sales Appointment Setter (Remote, Commission-Based)','Contract','Remote',NULL,'',155000.00,'$110,000 - $200,000 a year','Amaya AI is a fast-growing SaaS startup that helps businesses better understand and optimise their sales and customer conversations using AI-driven insights.\n\nWe are currently expanding our remote sales team and are hiring *Appointment Setters* to support outbound outreach by booking qualified meetings with business owners and decision-makers.\n\nThis is a *fully remote, commission-based role* suited to individuals who are confident communicating with others, comfortable with outreach, and motivated by performance. The role involves starting conversations with business owners, identifying potential interest, and booking meetings for our sales team to follow up.\n\nWe’re looking for people who are consistent, coachable, and enjoy working in a structured, fast-moving environment where performance and results are clearly measured.\n\n*Key Responsibilities*\n\n* Conduct outbound outreach to businesses (primarily cold calling)\n* Speak with decision-makers (e.g. owners, managers)\n* Introduce the product and start conversations\n* Identify potential interest and qualify leads\n* Book meetings for the sales team\n* Maintain accurate notes and update lead tracking systems\n\n*Requirements*\n\n* Strong verbal communication skills\n* Comfortable speaking with new people daily\n* Ability to handle rejection professionally\n* Self-motivated and able to work independently\n* Consistent work ethic and willingness to learn\n\n_Previous sales, call centre, or outreach experience is beneficial but not required._\n\n*Role Expectations*\n\n* High daily outreach activity (calls and follow-ups)\n* Consistent pipeline updates and organisation\n* Focus on booking qualified meetings\n\n*Compensation*\n\n* Commission-based role\n* Earn per deal closed from meetings you book (approx. *15% commission*)\n* Uncapped earning potential based on performance\n\n*This Role May Not Be Suitable If You:*\n\n* Prefer a fixed salary or hourly structure\n* Are not comfortable with outbound outreach\n* Require constant supervision or direction\n\n*What We Offer*\n\n* Fully remote work environment\n* Flexible schedule\n* Opportunity to develop sales skills in a growing SaaS company\n* Potential progression into a closing role\n\n*Application Process*\n\nShortlisted candidates will be contacted and asked to complete a short screening task, including a brief voice note simulating a sales call.\n\nOnly candidates who complete this step will be considered.\n\n*Additional Information*\n\n* Start Date: Immediate\n\nJob Type: Contract\n\nPay: $110,000.00 – $200,000.00 per year\n\nWork Location: Remote','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Amaya AI','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=cb037c64ecf90af7','scraped','4 days ago'),(2676,NULL,'job','Computer Vision Engineer (AU)','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Work with cutting edge AI technology, making the world a safer and more secure place. DroneShield (ASX:DRO) offers an opportunity to solve some of world’s most challenging technical problems in the rapidly growing counter-drone sector.\n\nOur customers operate in some of the most challenging and high-stakes environments in the world, including military organisations, government agencies, airports, critical infrastructure operators, and law enforcement. Protecting airspace in these settings requires technology that performs under pressure and teams that understand what’s at stake. At DroneShield, employees work at the leading edge of counter-drone innovation, helping to address real-world security challenges as drone threats continue to evolve globally.\n\nWith one of the largest listed defence company market capitalisations in Australia, now part of the ASX200 index, DroneShield is experiencing a period of hypergrowth. Revenue has surged from A$57 million in 2024 to over A$217 million in 2025, representing growth of more than 400% year-on-year, with record profitability and cashflow. The total addressable global market for counter-drone is assessed at approximately $100 billion, and is currently at the nascent stage with much of the growth still to come, with DroneShield well positioned as a global market leader, and the only public listed pure-play business in this sector.\n\nThe company has grown from 11 employees in 2017 to over 450 staff globally today, and is on track to reach around 550 by the end of 2026. This expansion includes investment of over A$50 million annually in R&D, a global pipeline exceeding A$2.5 billion, and continuous scaling of production capacity to meet accelerating demand.\n\nThe role is based at DroneShield’s central Sydney headquarters. Overseas on-the-ground presence includes Virginia (USA), Netherlands, Denmark, Mexico and Dubai, as well as distributors in over 70 countries worldwide.\n\nAbout the role\n\nIn this role, you will be at the forefront of advancing our computer vision capabilities by integrating cameras and algorithms to build our next-generation AI-powered detection, identification, and tracking optical systems.\n\nYou’ll collaborate closely with system engineers, machine learning engineers, and product teams to ensure our product is performant, reliable, and optimised for real-world defence applications. This position offers the opportunity to work on unique, mission-critical challenges where your contributions directly impact global security outcomes.\n\nResponsibilities, Duties and Expectations\n\nDesign, implement, benchmark, and optimise computer vision algorithms to enhance detection, classification, and tracking capabilities\nDevelop and adapt software interfaces to support the integration of new camera models and configurations\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to define technical requirements and ensure seamless integration of computer vision solutions\n\nQualifications, Experience and Skills\n\nBachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or equivalent practical experience\nMore than 3 years of experience in software engineering\nProficiency in C++ development, including multi-threading, unit testing, benchmarking, and profiling\nExperience programming in Python is required, and familiarity with Golang is preferred\nExperience with computer vision libraries (e.g. OpenCV) or integrating AI models (e.g. ONNX, TensorRT)\nExperience integrating cameras or similar sensors (e.g., LiDAR, thermal cameras)\nExperience with edge computing or embedded systems for real-time applications (e.g. NVIDIA GPUs, CUDA, GStreamer)\nExperience with AI/ML engineering is preferred\nExperience with version control systems (e.g., Git) and workflow automation tools (e.g. GitLab CI, ClearML)\nPrevious ‘start-up’ or ‘scale-up’ experience is preferred\nStrong problem-solving skills, attention to data quality, and effective cross-team communication\nAn abundance of ambition and motivation to grow the company and compete with the big players in the industry\n\nNote for recruitment agencies: We do not accept unsolicited candidates from external recruiters unless specifically instructed.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'DroneShield Limited','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=606008c8b56ad8a5','scraped','4 days ago'),(2677,NULL,'job','Senior Python Software Engineer (Backend Workflows Team) - open to remote across ANZ','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Job Description\n\nJoin the team redefining how the world experiences design.\n\nHey, g\'day, mabuhay, kia ora,你好, hallo, vítejte!\n\nThanks for stopping by. We know job hunting can be a little time consuming and you\'re probably keen to find out what\'s on offer, so we\'ll get straight to the point.\n\nWhere and how you can work\n\nOur flagship campus is in Sydney. We also have a campus in Melbourne and co-working spaces in Brisbane, Perth and Adelaide. But you have choice in where and how you work. That means if you want to do your thing in the office (if you\'re near one), at home or a bit of both, it\'s up to you.\n\nWhat you’d be doing in this role\n\nAs Canva scales change continues to be part of our DNA. But we like to think that\'s all part of the fun. So this will give you the flavour of the type of things you\'ll be working on when you start, but this will likely evolve.\n\nAt the moment, this role is focused on:\n\nShaping the Python language ecosystem with a strong product and platform mindset, defining clear development patterns and documentation in partnership with Infra and Product teams to support Canva’s broader AI strategy.\nArchitecting, building and delivering high-impact solutions that uplift the Python developer experience at Canva, ensuring high standards of engineering excellence.\nAdvocating for Python engineering best practices across the organization, influencing teams and aligning development patterns to Canva’s long-term strategy.\nDeveloping internal observability tooling and metrics that give the team actionable insights, enabling informed, targeted decisions on where to invest in the Python ecosystem.\nDriving org-wide ecosystem migrations and tooling transformations, owning design, rollout, telemetry, communication, and long-term maintenance strategies.\nShaping and executing the long-term vision for IDE developer tooling, ensuring our tools evolve to meet the needs of Python engineers and industry trends.\n\nYou\'re probably a match if\n\nYou have expert-level Python experience, with familiarity in modern development ecosystems and tools such as Bazel being a plus.\nYou have demonstrated leadership and ownership of complex, high-impact engineering initiatives, with a strong sense of accountability for outcomes.\nYou have a deep commitment to engineering excellence and systems architecture, with the ability to design for scale, reliability, and strong non-functional foundations.\nYou have extensive experience with containerization, Terraform, and GitOps, and a solid understanding of how to build and operate production-grade infrastructure.\nYou have a background in integrating ML applications into platform or backend systems, with an understanding of AI/ML toolchains and their operational requirements.\nYou can translate customer and developer needs into impactful technical solutions, applying a product mindset to improve developer experience at scale.\n\nAbout The Group\n\nWe are part of Developer Workflows, shaping the end-to-end engineering experience to build, test, deploy, and operate software at Canva. We bring together developer advocacy, product thinking, and deep technical expertise. The Backend Workflows team focuses on empowering backend engineers by removing friction from the software development lifecycle and delivering intuitive, scalable workflows. We collaborate across platform and product teams to compose seamless backend experiences that support Canva’s rapid growth. Together, we create the foundations that enable every engineer to do the best work of their lives - and directly contribute to Canva’s long-term vision and success.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nWe’re on a mission to elevate Python into a first-class experience across Canva, unlocking the full potential of our ML/AI and backend engineering teams. As a Senior Python Software Engineer in Backend Workflows, you will lead the design and delivery of workflows, tooling, and best practices that make Python development fast, reliable, and frictionless. Your work will shape how engineers write, test, build, and operate Python code everyday at scale - directly empowering teams who are building the AI-powered capabilities that define Canva’s future. We work closely with ML, backend, and platform engineers to deeply understand their challenges and craft solutions that accelerate their impact. This is a highly influential role where your contributions will have broad, long-lasting impact on Canva’s engineering velocity and AI strategy.\n\nWhat\'s in it for you?\n\nAchieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you\'ll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a stack of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.\n\nHere\'s a taste of what\'s on offer:\n\nEquity packages - we want our success to be yours too\nInclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers\nAn annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more\nFlexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally\n\nCheck out lifeatcanva.com for more info.\n\nOther stuff to know\n\nWe see AI as a powerful amplifier of creativity and technology at Canva. We’re evolving how we assess AI skills in our Technology hiring experience - you’ll tackle interactive, real-time challenges that reflect the kind of work we do. In some interviews, you may also be asked to solve a problem using an AI tool to show how you approach challenges with tech by your side. Your recruitment partner will walk you through what to expect. We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture.\n\nWhen you apply, please tell us the pronouns you use and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process. We celebrate all types of skills and backgrounds at Canva, so even if you don’t feel like your skills quite match what’s listed above - we still want to hear from you!\n\nPlease note that interviews are conducted virtually.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Canva','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=062650955dceb20b','scraped','4 days ago'),(2678,NULL,'job','Product/Service Designer (AI Experience & Commerce) - Contract','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nAt NCS Australia, we believe in doing technology services better. Our commitment to quality, focus on people, and willingness to challenge traditional thinking set us apart. Our team brings this belief to life by partnering with our clients and communities to make tomorrow together.\n\nWe are committed to creating an environment that prioritises innovation, collaboration, and purposeful work. Our diverse team is empowered to make a meaningful impact with curiosity, creativity and resilience to shape better outcomes. Join us and accept the challenge of creating a better tomorrow.\n\nPlease note we would look at either a contract or permanent person for this position\n\nJob Description\n\nWe are looking for a forward-thinking Product / Service Designer to help define the future of how customers interact with products in an AI-driven world. This role is focused on designing \"future-state\" experiences where AI agents—not just humans—act as the primary interface for discovery, comparison, and transactions.\n\nYou will bridge the gap between traditional user-centric design and the emerging field of machine-readable commerce, ensuring our product constructs are optimized for both human clarity and agentic efficiency.\n\nThe Role\n\nAs a Product / Service Designer, you will lead the research and design efforts to determine how AI agents discover and transact within our ecosystem. You will be responsible for translating complex technical possibilities into seamless service journeys and product information architectures.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nFuture-State Design: Design end-to-end product experiences specifically optimized for AI agent interactions and automated commerce.\nJourney Mapping: Develop key user journeys that illustrate how agents assist in product discovery and facilitate secure transactions.\nAgentic Research: Conduct deep-dive research into how AI agents (LLMs, personal assistants, etc.) search, compare, and execute purchases in the telco and technology sectors.\nProduct Architecture: Design agent-optimized product constructs, ensuring that product information is structured for maximum machine discoverability.\nStrategic Balancing: Balance the needs of the human end-user with the technical requirements of the AI agents representing them.\n\nQualifications\n\nTechnical Requirements & Skills\n\nWe are looking for a designer who is comfortable working in \"the grey\" of emerging technology and can apply rigorous design thinking to unstructured problems.\n\nService Design & IA: Proven proficiency in service design methodology and complex product information architecture.\nAdvanced Research: Strong user research capabilities, with a track record of gathering insights in emerging tech domains.\nAI Ecosystem Knowledge: Familiarity with Generative Engine Optimization (GEO) and the mechanics of how AI platforms consume and surface data.\nStrategic Translation: The ability to turn abstract research findings into concrete design requirements for technical teams.\n\nAdditional Information\n\nWhy join us:\n\nNCS Australia is where you can feel at home, nurturing your talents and skills as we make tomorrow together, one day at a time. Our benefits include paid parental leave, initiatives focused on your well-being and discounted health insurance. You will also enjoy discounts on various products and services and be regularly recognised and rewarded for high performance. We are committed to your career development through our Capability Fingerprint, industry and partner training programs, special interest groups, and an AI-driven learning platform. No matter where you are in your career, we offer meaningful work and opportunities for growth.\n\nNCS Australia is an equal-opportunity employer, and we take pride in our commitment to valuing and supporting our people and the communities we serve.We are dedicated to attracting, retaining and developing our people regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability and age. Applications are encouraged from all sectors of the community and we strongly encourage applications from the Veterans, Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander community.\n\nAt NCS Australia, we are committed to supporting adjustments throughout the recruitment and selection process, as well as during employment. We actively support and encourage people with disability to apply.\n\nAgencies:\n\nWe’ve got this. We request that you do not contact NCS employees outside of the Talent Acquisition team. NCS exclusively accepts resumes from agencies on our preferred supplier panel through the NCS Agency Portal. Agencies that submit resumes must have a valid fee agreement and be assigned to the particular requisition by the Talent Acquisition team. Any resumes that are submitted outside of this process will become the sole property of NCS. If a candidate is hired outside of this process, no fee or payment will be given.\n\nWork rights and background checks:\n\nTo be eligible for a position with us, applicants will need to have valid work rights for Australia and be willing to undergo a comprehensive background checking process, including probity and police checks','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'NCS Australia','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=890f82eba8a4db1c','scraped','4 days ago'),(2679,NULL,'job','Senior Digital Media Specialist','','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Please note that we will never request payment or bank account information at any stage of the recruitment process. As we continue to grow our teams, we urge you to be cautious of fraudulent job postings or recruitment activities that misuse our company name and information. Please protect your personal information during any recruitment process. While Monks may contact potential candidates via LinkedIn, all applications must be submitted through our official website (monks.com/careers).\n\nRole Summary\n\nThe Senior Digital Media Specialist is a strategic and leadership-focused professional responsible for managing key client accounts, leading media delivery projects, and driving business growth within the APAC region. They serve as a primary client contact for our key accounts, overseeing the delivery of integrated services, fostering strong relationships with budget holders and internal leads, and leading internal and external teams.The role involves strategic promotion of the media business, proactive leadership, a strong understanding of media investment strategies and continuous improvement initiatives.The Senior Digital Media Specialist acts as a bridge between clients and internal teams, ensuring high-quality execution, financial accountability, and alignment with overall business and media strategies.\n\nRole Responsibilities\nClient Management & Relationships: Develop and maintain strong external relationships with clients\' operational and senior stakeholders. Lead client meetings, ensuring delivery of value, capturing feedback, and identifying new business opportunities.\nMedia Delivery & Oversight: Lead the planning, execution, and monitoring of media campaigns and services, ensuring alignment with client expectations and contractual SLAs. Oversee delivery teams, providing guidance and quality assurance.\nProduct & Service Knowledge: Maintain advanced knowledge of media products (from a technical and strategic lense), services, and platforms. Lead discussions internally and externally about media offerings, ensuring proper delivery and optimizations.\nBusiness Development & Sales Support: Identify revenue opportunities, support pitching efforts, and assist in scoping and contracting processes with a thorough understanding of legal and commercial frameworks.\nStrategy Promotion & Leadership: Promote APAC media and business strategies within the team and across client portfolios. Support the adoption of strategic initiatives to enhance client outcomes and operational efficiency.\nFinancial & Resource Management: Manage budgeting, billing, invoicing, and forecasts. Provide feedback on resource allocation, onboarding of new team members, and project profitability.\nPartnerships & Industry Insights: Engage in vendor and technology partner feedback forums, keep certifications current, and surface new business opportunities. Share industry insights and case studies to foster continuous learning.\nTeam & People Development: Mentor and guide team members, participate in growth conversations, and foster a positive, collaborative team culture. Lead performance reviews and support team motivation.\nResearch & Industry Knowledge: Dedicate time to ongoing research, share learnings internally and with clients, and incorporate insights into strategic planning.\nExperience:\nMedia Experience: 5+ years of experience in media account management, client servicing, or campaign delivery, with progressively increasing responsibility.\nStrategic Thinking: Ability to promote and implement media strategies aligned with business goals\nClient Management: Strong relationship-building skills with experience managing key accounts and engaging senior stakeholders.\nMedia Expertise: Deep understanding of media products, platforms, and services, including digital, managed media, advisory solutions, and R&A offerings.\nLeadership Skills: Proven ability to collaborate as a leader within small teams or create initiatives and inspire teams.\nProject & Delivery Management: Demonstrated ability to oversee complex projects, ensure timeliness, quality, and contractual adherence.\nEducational Background: Bachelor\'s degree or higher in marketing, media, communications, business, or related fields.\nAnalytical & Market Insight Skills: Strong research skills, industry awareness, and an ability to leverage insights for strategic advantage.\nFinancial Acumen: Proficient in managing budgets, billing, invoicing, forecasts, and resource allocation.\n\n#LI-CX1\n\nAbout Monks\n\nMonks is the global, digital-first, data-driven, unitary operating brand of S4 Capital plc. With a legacy of innovation and specialized expertise, Monks combines an extraordinary range of global Marketing and Technology Services to redefine how brands interact with the world. Through Monks.Flow, its flagship AI ecosystem for marketing orchestration, Monks transforms marketing into a growth engine, collapsing timelines and connecting brands to culture in real time. By deploying bespoke intelligent agents across disciplines and delivering culturally relevant, high-impact creative and digital solutions, Monks solves key critical business challenges across the entire brand enterprise to help brands sustain long-term impact.\n\nMonks was named a Contender in The Forrester Wave™: Global Marketing Services, ranks among Cannes Lions\' Top 10 Creative Companies (2022-25) and remains the only partner featured in AdExchanger\'s Programmatic Power Players list every year (2020-24). Named Adweek\'s first AI Agency of the Year (2023) and The One Show\'s inaugural AI Pioneer Organization, Monks was also awarded Business Intelligence Group\'s 2025 Excellence in Artificial Intelligence Award in both the Organizational and AI Product categories. As a trusted partner to cutting-edge innovators in tech, Monks earned titles such as Optimizely Experimentation Partner of the Year (2025), runner-up for the Adobe Firefly Partner Award (2024), and Workato\'s AI Visionary Customer Impact Award (2024). Additionally, Monks achieved a record-breaking number of FWAs and continues to hold the most of any partner.\n\nWe are an equal-opportunity employer committed to building a respectful and empowering work environment for all people to freely express themselves amongst colleagues who embrace diversity in all respects. Including fresh voices and unique points of view in all aspects of our business not only creates an environment where we can all grow and thrive but also increases our potential to produce work that better represents—and resonates with—the world around us.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Monks','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2e0c6d39fe99f76a','scraped','4 days ago'),(2680,NULL,'job','Senior Manager, Member Strategy','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2010',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nSupporting millions of Aussies since 1988 with low fees and competitive long-term performance. Profits back to members, not shareholders\n\nClosing date: Wednesday 13th May 2026.\n\nPlease note Rest does not accept speculative resumes from recruitment agencies\n\nRest will review applications prior to the closing date and may close the role earlier\n\nJob Description\n\nEstablished in 1988, Rest is one of Australia’s largest profit-to-member superannuation funds.\n\nWe support more than two million members, with around $100 billion of funds under management and are recognised as a responsible investment leader*. We believe when members understand and engage with their super, they’re more likely to get a better retirement outcome.\n\nEverything we do at Rest is underpinned by our values and behaviours, we want to Be Daring, Keep it Simple, Take Action and Have Grit. To put it simply we want our people to thrive and love the work they do.\n\nThe Senior Manager, Member Strategy is responsible for shaping Rest’s member and employer acquisition and retention strategies in alignment with the group strategy. It is a key connecting role between the group strategy and Member teams, hence with a direct reporting line to the GM, Member Value and a dotted line to the GM Strategy. The role brings together external market insights, Voice of Customer (VOC) analysis and portfolio analytics to ensure the delivery of Rest’s strategy is meaningfully shaped by the member voice and focused on the strongest value creation for members. The role also provides strategic guidance to the Member division leadership team on specific focus areas and initiatives.\n\nKey Accountabilities/Responsibilities\n\nDevelop the member and employer acquisition, growth and retention plans ensuring alignment with Rest’s purpose and group strategy, and Member divisional operational requirements.\nMonitor and analyse external market trends, competitor activity, regulatory developments and demographic shifts to proactively shape member and employer strategy and planning.\nTranslate enterprise strategy and market insights into clear, actionable strategic plans that support long-term member value.\nDesign and refine strategies to drive member acquisition, employer channel growth and improved member engagement across Rest’s diverse membership segments.\nDesign and deliver customer segmentation strategy, driving alignment to segment priorities and opportunities across the enterprise.\nEstablish data‑led retention strategies, identifying key drivers of member attrition and developing interventions to improve loyalty and tenure.\nPartner with Strategy, Finance and relevant Member teams to develop business cases to support strategic recommendations.\nPartner with Experience Design and Journeys teams to ensure member strategies translate into coherent, high-impact experiences across all channels.\nProvide strategic advice to the GM Member Value, CMO, GM Strategy and leadership teams on member and employer value, growth opportunities and risk considerations.\nSupport enterprise prioritisation by advocating for the member voice across forums, governance bodies, and planning processes.\nContribute to preparation of strategy papers, Board/Committee materials and executive updates to ensure consistency, quality, and alignment.\nContribute to an engaged, high-performing team environment that promotes collaboration, accountability, and continuous learning.\n\nQualifications\n\nRelevant Business, Commerce or Finance degree.\n\nRequired experience, understanding or credentials including:\n\nFinancial Services Expertise: demonstrable experience within superannuation or financial services, with a deep understanding of member, product and regulatory environments.\nCore Strategic Capability and Skills: Demonstrable consulting experience with a focus in problem solving, strategy development and ability to support strategic thinking, ideally with experience in Customer Strategy, Go to Market Strategy and Growth.\nStrategic and Commercial Acumen: Proven ability to apply commercial judgment to shape strategic direction, make critical decisions and deliver outcomes to defined timeframes.\nFinancial Acumen: Proven ability to model and demonstrate financial outcomes of strategic recommendations.\nInnovation and Problem Solving: With applied experience in HCD and customer-led strategy to bring creativity and complex problem-solving skills, and the ability to design and deliver innovative solutions that enhance member experience.\nAI and Digital Mindset: Passion for leveraging data, analytics, and emerging technologies to uncover insights, measure performance, and inform continuous improvement.\nCollaborative Leadership: Strong influencing skills with the ability to lead through others, fostering alignment and collaboration across diverse functions and teams. Demonstrated ability to manage senior stakeholders.\nAttention to Detail and Perspective: Balances strategic vision with operational precision, ensuring initiatives are both high-impact and well-executed.\nEffective Communication: Exceptional written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to translate complex insights and strategies into clear, compelling narratives.\nResilience and Prioritisation: Skilled in managing multiple priorities in complex, fast-paced environments while maintaining focus on strategic outcomes and member value.\n\nAdditional Information\n\nOur benefits have been designed so you can tailor your experience with us and include:\n\nPersonal and professional development opportunities\nHybrid working\nPurchase leave scheme and gender neutral 16 weeks paid parental leave\nSuper Contribution Continuation for 12 Months of parental leave\nLinkedin Learning\nIncome Protection Insurance\nRest Excellence awards (peer recognition awards based on Rest’s values and behaviours)\nRest Stops - meeting free breaks\n\nIf you share our values, believe you can help make a difference for our members and want to be part of a leading superannuation fund with a Super culture, please click Apply Now.\n\nRest is committed to creating a flexible work environment and culture that embraces diversity, equity, and inclusion - where people feel welcome, safe to be themselves and inspired to do their best.\n\nWe value the different backgrounds, lived experiences and abilities our diverse team brings. We welcome and encourage applications from candidates of all ages, cultural backgrounds, faiths, gender identities, sexual orientations and thinking styles. This includes people with disability, neurodiverse individuals, Aboriginal & Torres Strait Islander peoples and those with disrupted work history due to career or other breaks.\n\nPlease note only people with the right to work in Australia will be considered.\n\n*Funds under management as at 31 July 2025. Rest is recognised as a Responsible Investment Leader by the Responsible Investment Association Australia (RIAA) in its Responsible Investment Benchmark Report 2022.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Rest','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c6648e881df97cf2','scraped','4 days ago'),(2681,NULL,'job','Delivery Lead (Agentic Commerce Initiative) - Contract or Permanent','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nAt NCS Australia, we believe in doing technology services better. Our commitment to quality, focus on people, and willingness to challenge traditional thinking set us apart. Our team brings this belief to life by partnering with our clients and communities to make tomorrow together.\n\nWe are committed to creating an environment that prioritises innovation, collaboration, and purposeful work. Our diverse team is empowered to make a meaningful impact with curiosity, creativity and resilience to shape better outcomes. Join us and accept the challenge of creating a better tomorrow.\n\nPlease note we would look at either a contract or permanent person for this position\n\nJob Description\n\nWe are looking for a highly organized and strategic Delivery Lead to drive the execution of our Agentic Commerce initiative. This is a high-visibility role responsible for managing a complex, multi-workstream program that sits at the cutting edge of AI and digital commerce.\n\nYou will be the operational heartbeat of the program, ensuring that internal product teams, technical workstreams, and global partners are aligned and delivering against our strategic roadmap.\n\nThe Role\n\nAs the Delivery Lead, you will establish the governance and execution framework required to move the Agentic Commerce initiative from vision to reality. You will manage the intersection of product optimization, technical visibility enhancements, and a major strategic partnership.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nProgram Execution: Lead the end-to-end delivery of the Agentic Commerce initiative, ensuring all workstreams are tracking toward key milestones.\nGovernance Framework: Design and implement robust internal and external governance structures to manage decision-making and accountability.\nStakeholder & Partner Management: Act as the primary operational interface for our Google partnership and internal product leadership.\nDependency Management: Identify and resolve cross-functional dependencies across technical, product, and data workstreams.\nTracking & Reporting: Establish recurring governance cycles and program tracking to ensure transparent reporting on progress and risks.\n\nQualifications\n\nTechnical Requirements & Experience\n\nWe are seeking a delivery professional who thrives in high-scale, fast-paced environments where the technology is rapidly evolving.\n\nProject/Program Leadership: Proven experience managing complex, multi-workstream initiatives with a track record of successful delivery.\nStrategic Governance: Strong capability in designing governance frameworks and managing high-level stakeholder relationships.\nPartnership Management: Experience managing external global partnerships and complex vendor relationships.\nAgile & Tech Savvy: Deep familiarity with agile methodologies and a solid understanding of AI/product technology delivery.\nCommunication: Exceptional ability to translate technical milestones into executive-level progress reports.\n\nAdditional Information\n\nWhy join us:\n\nNCS Australia is where you can feel at home, nurturing your talents and skills as we make tomorrow together, one day at a time. Our benefits include paid parental leave, initiatives focused on your well-being and discounted health insurance. You will also enjoy discounts on various products and services and be regularly recognised and rewarded for high performance. We are committed to your career development through our Capability Fingerprint, industry and partner training programs, special interest groups, and an AI-driven learning platform. No matter where you are in your career, we offer meaningful work and opportunities for growth.\n\nNCS Australia is an equal-opportunity employer, and we take pride in our commitment to valuing and supporting our people and the communities we serve.We are dedicated to attracting, retaining and developing our people regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability and age. Applications are encouraged from all sectors of the community and we strongly encourage applications from the Veterans, Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander community.\n\nAt NCS Australia, we are committed to supporting adjustments throughout the recruitment and selection process, as well as during employment. We actively support and encourage people with disability to apply.\n\nAgencies:\n\nWe’ve got this. We request that you do not contact NCS employees outside of the Talent Acquisition team. NCS exclusively accepts resumes from agencies on our preferred supplier panel through the NCS Agency Portal. Agencies that submit resumes must have a valid fee agreement and be assigned to the particular requisition by the Talent Acquisition team. Any resumes that are submitted outside of this process will become the sole property of NCS. If a candidate is hired outside of this process, no fee or payment will be given.\n\nWork rights and background checks:\n\nTo be eligible for a position with us, applicants will need to have valid work rights for Australia and be willing to undergo a comprehensive background checking process, including probity and police checks','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'NCS Australia','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=245911deb488690b','scraped','4 days ago'),(2682,NULL,'job','AI Program Lead','','Perth WA 6000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Country/Region: AU\nState: WA\nCity: Perth\nJob ID: 16217\nAI Program Lead\nAbout Us\n\nFortescue is both a proud West Australian company and a global green solutions business. We are recognised for our culture, innovation and industry-leading development of infrastructure, mining assets and green energy initiatives.\n\nOur Opportunity\n\nWork Location: Perth Office - Fortescue\'s Perth office is located on the traditional lands of the Whadjuk people.\n\nRoster: Monday to Friday\n\nAs the AI Program Lead, you will play a central role in coordinating and governing Fortescue’s AI program. This role is responsible for driving program-level discipline across a portfolio of AI domains and products, ensuring the pipeline is captured, prioritised, tracked and reported effectively for senior leaders and the Board. You will bring a strong PMO and program management capability, enabling quality execution, clear governance, and transparency of progress, risks and decisions across the program.\n\nKey to the role is supporting the Product owners on valuation and value attribution. You will work closely with product teams, Finance Business Partners, FP&A and business stakeholders to ensure value cases are robust, assumptions are sound, Fortescue value standards are consistently applied, and commitments are tracked through to realised outcomes. This role will help embed a disciplined, credible approach to measuring and reporting value from AI investments.\n\nThe AI Program Lead will work across product teams, domain leaders, finance, strategy and technology stakeholders to support the successful delivery of AI-enabled products aligned to Fortescue’s business priorities.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nManage program governance rhythms, including stage gate and investment review processes in our Steering Committee meetings, documenting actions and follow-up. Ensure program and governance standards are consistently applied across the AI portfolio\nMaintain a high-quality view of the AI portfolio, including status, risks, dependencies, decisions, milestones and delivery confidence\nPrepare high-quality reporting for directors, executive leaders and the Board, including updates on pipeline health, delivery progress, risks, value and key decisions required\nPartner with product teams to support the development of robust business cases for AI initiatives using Fortescue value standards and frameworks, ensuring benefits are measured consistently and credibly\nWork closely with Finance Business Partners, FP&A and relevant business stakeholders to validate assumptions, inputs, baselines and calculation methods\nTrack value commitments and delivery performance against approved expectations, highlighting variances and required interventions\nEnsure value attribution is transparent, evidence-based and aligned with finance governance requirements\nIdentify cross-program risks, issues and interdependencies, and work with stakeholders to manage them proactively.\n\nQualifications and Experience\n\nBachelor’s degree in Business, Finance, Engineering, Technology or a related field\nSignificant experience in program management, PMO, strategy, finance business partnering, or a similar role in a complex environment\nProven experience coordinating portfolios or large cross-functional programs with strong governance and executive reporting requirements\nStrong capability in business case development, valuation, benefits management or value tracking\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills, including experience preparing materials for senior executives and boards\nDemonstrated ability to manage multiple stakeholders, drive follow-through, and improve quality and discipline across a program\nFamiliarity with AI, digital, technology or software delivery programs will be highly regarded\nHighly organised and detail-oriented, with strong ownership and accountability for outcomes\nStrong commercial and financial acumen, able to navigate ambiguity and bring clarity to complex problems\nCollaborative and influential, with strong stakeholder management skills and the confidence to challenge assumptions constructively.\n\nOur Commitment\n\nFortescue is deeply committed to providing a safe culture that builds respect, fosters inclusiveness, and values diversity. We celebrate individual strengths and team members from all backgrounds are encouraged to bring their whole selves to work. Our global workforce drives and promotes an inclusive culture, both within our organisation and throughout the communities we interact with across the world. Diverse backgrounds include First Nations Peoples, people with differing abilities, LGBTIQ+ community, gender, neurodiverse, cultural diversity, all age groups, and those with an intersectional or multiple diverse characteristics. We encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply.\n\nhttps://fortescue.com/careers\n\nInternal Candidates / Current Contractors please apply via Success Factors Careers Portal. For further information on how to apply please visit the Fortescue Hub.\n\nFortescue reserves the right to close applications early should a suitable pool of candidates be identified. Fortescue will never contact you to ask for payment of any kind, whether directly or through a third party.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Fortescue','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=6ebed30cadc4b870','scraped','4 days ago'),(2683,NULL,'job','Data Scientist (AI Visibility & Commerce Analytics) - Contract','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nAt NCS Australia, we believe in doing technology services better. Our commitment to quality, focus on people, and willingness to challenge traditional thinking set us apart. Our team brings this belief to life by partnering with our clients and communities to make tomorrow together.\n\nWe are committed to creating an environment that prioritises innovation, collaboration, and purposeful work. Our diverse team is empowered to make a meaningful impact with curiosity, creativity and resilience to shape better outcomes. Join us and accept the challenge of creating a better tomorrow.\n\nPlease note we would look at either a contract or permanent person for this position\n\nJob Description\n\nWe are seeking a Data Scientist to join our team in Sydney. This is a pioneering role focused on defining how we measure success in the \"Agentic Web.\" You will be responsible for building the measurement framework that tracks how AI agents discover our products, how they rank them, and how effectively they convert those discoveries into commerce.\n\nAs the bridge between raw data and AI strategy, you will provide the insights necessary to optimize our presence across the global AI ecosystem.\n\nThe Role\n\nYour mission is to move beyond traditional web analytics into the world of Generative Engine Optimization (GEO). You will establish the baselines, metrics, and tools required to understand how LLMs and AI agents perceive our product suite.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nFramework Design: Establish a comprehensive measurement framework for agent visibility and commerce performance.\nMetric Definition: Define and track core metrics for \"agent discoverability\"—understanding how and why an AI agent selects a specific product.\nTooling & Integration: Integrate advanced measurement tools and data platforms to capture non-traditional traffic and agent interactions.\nPerformance Baselining: Establish current performance baselines and build the infrastructure for ongoing monitoring of AI platform rankings.\nImpact Analysis: Conduct deep-dive analyses on how technical optimizations (such as LLMs.txt, Schema updates, and crawler configurations) impact product discovery.\n\nQualifications\n\nTechnical Requirements\n\nWe are looking for a data scientist who is comfortable with high-ambiguity environments and possesses a deep curiosity about AI behavior.\n\nAnalytics Expertise: Strong experience in designing analytics and metrics frameworks from the ground up.\nVisibility Tracking: Proven proficiency with SEO/GEO analytics, web visibility tracking, and data integration platforms.\nAI Knowledge: A solid understanding of LLM behavior, AI platform mechanics, and how product ranking algorithms function in a generative context.\nData Engineering: Experience setting up data collection pipelines for emerging technology domains.\n\nAdditional Information\n\nWhy join us:\n\nNCS Australia is where you can feel at home, nurturing your talents and skills as we make tomorrow together, one day at a time. Our benefits include paid parental leave, initiatives focused on your well-being and discounted health insurance. You will also enjoy discounts on various products and services and be regularly recognised and rewarded for high performance. We are committed to your career development through our Capability Fingerprint, industry and partner training programs, special interest groups, and an AI-driven learning platform. No matter where you are in your career, we offer meaningful work and opportunities for growth.\n\nNCS Australia is an equal-opportunity employer, and we take pride in our commitment to valuing and supporting our people and the communities we serve.We are dedicated to attracting, retaining and developing our people regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability and age. Applications are encouraged from all sectors of the community and we strongly encourage applications from the Veterans, Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander community.\n\nAt NCS Australia, we are committed to supporting adjustments throughout the recruitment and selection process, as well as during employment. We actively support and encourage people with disability to apply.\n\nAgencies:\n\nWe’ve got this. We request that you do not contact NCS employees outside of the Talent Acquisition team. NCS exclusively accepts resumes from agencies on our preferred supplier panel through the NCS Agency Portal. Agencies that submit resumes must have a valid fee agreement and be assigned to the particular requisition by the Talent Acquisition team. Any resumes that are submitted outside of this process will become the sole property of NCS. If a candidate is hired outside of this process, no fee or payment will be given.\n\nWork rights and background checks:\n\nTo be eligible for a position with us, applicants will need to have valid work rights for Australia and be willing to undergo a comprehensive background checking process, including probity and police checks','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'NCS Australia','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=d8ce73e41241666b','scraped','4 days ago'),(2684,NULL,'job','Senior Software Engineer - Full Stack, with a FE focus','Permanent','Sydney NSW 2000',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Title: Senior Software Engineering Consultant\n\nPosition: Permanent Full Time\n\nLocation: This is a hybrid role based in Sydney with a blend of working from home & on-site with clients. You must have a current visa and full working rights in Australia.\n\nAbout the role:\n\nAs a DiUS consultant, you will be partnering with clients to develop and deliver custom software products and digital solutions; getting the most out of their technology landscape, and leaving them in a better place. This hands-on role is more than just systems and coding - it’s also about asking the right questions, understanding the needs, thinking outside the box to creatively develop solutions, driving best practice, developing strong client relationships and collaborating on the bigger picture.\n\nThroughout your time with DiUS, you will work on different business projects in a range of digital web, data and mobile capabilities, while increasingly factoring in AI powered engineering practices.\n\nThis will accelerate your growth as each client will have different technologies, tools & frameworks, as well as different business challenges, solutions, and stakeholders. We work on problems our clients aren’t able to solve themselves.\n\nAbout DiUS:\n\nDiUS is an Australian B2B technology services company with an excellent reputation as a trusted consulting partner. We’re a go-to company for helping organisations of all sizes tackle hard engineering problems, their delivery practices, modernise applications, and design, build and deliver a new product to market.\n\nWe have a powerful ability to figure out the best path forward for each of our clients by drawing upon our broad range of deep and specialist capabilities: software engineering, experience design, data and analytics, machine learning and AI.\n\nAbout You:\n\nYou will have a dynamic background as a full stack software engineer, proficient in both back end and front end development, with lots of breadth across each. You enjoy variety and have spent time learning different tech stacks in your previous roles, adapting to different environments.\n\nExperienced across the entire SDLC, you can effectively design customised solutions, deploy to cloud platforms and work with Infrastructure as Code, with a focus on building secure, scalable, and high-performing systems.\n\nWhether your experience is from consulting, or working across multiple projects, you have a natural leadership style that builds trust with the people you work with. You have experience leading projects and small teams end to end, and you are flexible and adaptable, navigating the grey areas comfortably as you step into, and sometimes lead, different projects - you may be designing a new system and platform features this month, and then building agents next month.\n\nMain Tech Skills Needed:\n\nFull-stack software engineer with 10+ years of experience in various back end and front end tech languages such as: Java, Node, NestJS, C#/ .net, Python, JavaScript, Typescript, React, Next.js, Angular, Vue\n\nStrong experience in React & Next.js is required\n\nPurposeful design and implementation of software solutions (yes, from scratch)\n\nCommercial experience deploying code into the cloud (AWS, Azure, GCP) & IaC tools\n\nSolid level of proficiency in modern architectural practices\n\nExperience in AI assisted engineering across the software development lifecycle\n\nExperience in using LLMs, RAG and agentic frameworks to deliver AI solutions\n\nMain Consulting Skills Needed:\n\nAble to openly collaborate and listen; understand and refine requirements, & iterate on delivery outcomes\n\nAble to problem solve; identify purposeful solutions, factoring in how to integrate into a wider solution/system\n\nAble to navigate ambiguity; land on your feet and find the way forward\n\nAdaptable to different paces and environments; from the complexity of a large enterprise or influencing in a fast-paced start-up\n\nExcellent communication skills\n\nAble to efficiently self manage and coordinate / prioritise tasks and workload\n\nCurious with a growth mindset, always seeking to learn and investing in own development\n\nPassionate about spreading change through thought leadership, mentoring, meetups, writing blogs or staying active on GitHub.\n\nA change champion who can influence and drive transformation\n\nWant to know more about this role, or think you\'ve got what it takes? Apply now!\n\nNote to Recruitment Agencies: we got this - no need to reach out please!','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'DiUS','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=905e01a4932bcae0','scraped','4 days ago'),(2685,NULL,'job','Senior API Engineer - Contract','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nAt NCS Australia, we believe in doing technology services better. Our commitment to quality, focus on people, and willingness to challenge traditional thinking set us apart. Our team brings this belief to life by partnering with our clients and communities to make tomorrow together.\n\nWe are committed to creating an environment that prioritises innovation, collaboration, and purposeful work. Our diverse team is empowered to make a meaningful impact with curiosity, creativity and resilience to shape better outcomes. Join us and accept the challenge of creating a better tomorrow.\n\nPlease note we would look at either a contract or permanent person for this position\n\nJob Description\n\nWe are looking for a Senior API Engineer to join our team in Sydney. This is a high-impact role focused on building the bridge between our core products and the next generation of AI agents. You will be responsible for developing the API infrastructure that enables AI agents to discover, interact with, and execute transactions across our product suite.\n\nThis role sits at the intersection of product innovation and cutting-edge tech, working in close collaboration with our Google partnership and internal product teams to ensure our ecosystem is AI-ready.\n\nThe Role\n\nAs a Senior API Engineer, your primary mission is to ensure our API infrastructure is robust, scalable, and optimized for Unified Customer Platform (UCP) integration. You will play a lead role in assessing API readiness and building the feeds necessary for AI agent discoverability.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nInfrastructure & Integration: Build and maintain high-performance API infrastructure and microservices to enable seamless AI agent access.\nStrategic Assessment: Evaluate current API readiness for UCP integration and contribute to the technical roadmap for the remainder of the year.\nAI Readiness: Implement product feeds and ensure APIs support complex transaction capabilities and agent discoverability.\nAutomation Innovation: Design and build automated solutions for AI discoverability, such as periodic scraping and publishing of LLMs.txt files to guide Large Language Models.\nStakeholder Collaboration: Work closely with the Tech Lead on UCP design and maintain a strong technical relationship with our Google partners.\n\nQualifications\n\nTechnical Requirements\n\nWe are looking for an engineer who thrives in complex, high-scale environments and has a deep understanding of how APIs power modern ecosystems.\n\nAPI Expertise: Extensive experience in API builds, microservices architecture, and API gateway patterns.\nCloud Infrastructure: Strong hands-on experience with GCP (Google Cloud Platform) services.\nIntegration Experience: Proven track record of working with Google partnership integrations or similar large-scale third-party ecosystems.\nAI Familiarity: A solid understanding of how AI agents and LLMs consume data (experience with LLMs.txt or similar machine-readable documentation is a plus).\n\nAdditional Information\n\nWhy join us:\n\nNCS Australia is where you can feel at home, nurturing your talents and skills as we make tomorrow together, one day at a time. Our benefits include paid parental leave, initiatives focused on your well-being and discounted health insurance. You will also enjoy discounts on various products and services and be regularly recognised and rewarded for high performance. We are committed to your career development through our Capability Fingerprint, industry and partner training programs, special interest groups, and an AI-driven learning platform. No matter where you are in your career, we offer meaningful work and opportunities for growth.\n\nNCS Australia is an equal-opportunity employer, and we take pride in our commitment to valuing and supporting our people and the communities we serve.We are dedicated to attracting, retaining and developing our people regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability and age. Applications are encouraged from all sectors of the community and we strongly encourage applications from the Veterans, Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander community.\n\nAt NCS Australia, we are committed to supporting adjustments throughout the recruitment and selection process, as well as during employment. We actively support and encourage people with disability to apply.\n\nAgencies:\n\nWe’ve got this. We request that you do not contact NCS employees outside of the Talent Acquisition team. NCS exclusively accepts resumes from agencies on our preferred supplier panel through the NCS Agency Portal. Agencies that submit resumes must have a valid fee agreement and be assigned to the particular requisition by the Talent Acquisition team. Any resumes that are submitted outside of this process will become the sole property of NCS. If a candidate is hired outside of this process, no fee or payment will be given.\n\nWork rights and background checks:\n\nTo be eligible for a position with us, applicants will need to have valid work rights for Australia and be willing to undergo a comprehensive background checking process, including probity and police checks','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'NCS Australia','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c388156b51efb0dd','scraped','4 days ago'),(2686,NULL,'job','Customer Care Engineer (Technical Support Engineer)','','Australia',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Forward Networks is transforming how the world\'s most complex networks are managed and secured. Founded in 2013 by four Stanford Ph.D.s, we built the industry\'s first network digital twin, a mathematically precise model of the production network that gives IT teams unmatched visibility, verification, and agility across every major cloud and vendor environment.\n\nOur customers include global leaders such as Goldman Sachs, PayPal, S&P Global, IBM, and Dell, as well as fast-growing enterprises and government agencies. According to IDC, Forward Networks customers realize an average of $14.2 million in annual benefits through improved efficiency and security.\n\nBacked by world-class investors including Andreessen Horowitz, Goldman Sachs, MSD Partners, and Threshold Ventures, Forward Networks offers a people-centric, innovative culture where brilliant minds are shaping the future of network reliability, security, and AI-ready operations.\n\nForward Networks is looking for a Customer Care Engineer (Technical Support Engineer), Australia\n\nDo you want to create a category and help build a special company?\n\nJoin a company that has been in the market 6+ years and has some of the top Federal agencies and F500/Global 2000 already buying and referenceable.\n\nWe are building a special team and hope you consider us if you want to have the experience of changing the networking world as we know it.\n\nWhat you\'ll do:\n\nAs a Customer Care Engineer (Technical Support Engineer) for our Support team, you will be responsible for providing world class post-sales customer support and technical leadership to our client base.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nProviding triage, prioritizing, and resolving technical issues for our top customers.\n\nIdentifying s/w bugs, recreate customer issues, and test/verify versions with s/w fix.\n\nWorking with Forward Engineering teams to resolve customer issues.\n\nEscalating unresolved issues in a timely manner and maintaining direct communications with all stakeholders.\n\nRequirements:\n\n3+ years of technical customer support experience.\n\nExperience working at a technical support center assisting a variety of customers.\n\nAbility to cover NAM EST time zones\n\nParticipate in after hours on-call rotation\n\nExperience:\n\nStrong understanding of fundamentals in Networking, Cloud or Security\n\nStrong written and interpersonal communications skills\n\nExcellent analytical & problem-solving skills, combined with the ability to provide quick resolution to problems\n\nExperience supporting a multi-vendor network (e.g. A10, Arista, Cisco, F5, Fortinet, Juniper, Palo Alto Networks, AWS, GCP etc.)\n\nProven ability to work cross-functionally within a team-oriented environment.\n\nHighly Desired:\n\n B.S. Computer Science or equivalent educational experience.\n\nPython scripting experience\n\nKubernetes experience\n\nLinux fundamentals\n\nAPI debugging\n\nCloud networking (AWS, Azure, GCP)','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Forward Networks','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=3c86b261f38a33af','scraped','4 days ago'),(2687,NULL,'job','AI Creative Strategist','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Stake is looking for an AI Creative Strategist to join us at our brand new Sydney CBD location within a hybrid working model!\n\nWe\'re an Australian investing platform that helps ambitious people confidently grow their wealth. By offering seamless, immersive access to the share markets, we\'ve empowered a new wave of investors. Stake has grown fast from a fintech startup into a robust financial services company. Today we have 750,000+ customers and more than A$5 billion under administration.\n\nAt Stake, we break barriers in everything we do. Just like our customers, we\'re driven by ambition. Our desire for continuous growth is what creates the collaborative and high-performance environment we work in. Though we\'re spread around the world, we\'re a unified team moving towards a shared vision: to unleash the investor in everyone.\n\nJoin us as we continue to reshape the financial industry, inspiring investor confidence and celebrating our wins along the way\n\nAbout this role\n\nAs the AI Creative Strategist, you will be responsible for the end-to-end creative production and output that powers our ability to efficiently acquire users through paid social. Reporting to the Growth Lead, you will own a high-output creative production engine that drives strategy, execution, and optimisation across social-first acquisition channels, with a focus on scaling creative volume and performance. You will combine performance marketing, creative strategy, and production to build a system designed for speed, scale, and iteration. This role shifts acquisition from channel management to creative systems, where success is driven by the volume, quality, and velocity of ad creative. You will be a key driver in achieving growth targets, working cross-functionally to translate insights into assets, and assets into measurable acquisition outcomes.\n\nThis is a unique opportunity where you\'re able to utilise the most disruptive technology in performance marketing and will be given the reigns to create your vision for a world class production engine.\n\nKey deliverables\n\nCreative-Led Acquisition Strategy and Planning Develop and execute acquisition strategies that prioritise creative output as the primary growth lever. Define clear targets, KPIs, and budgets across channels, with a focus on scaling creative volume, speed, and efficiency.\nCreative System Development Build and implement a modular creative framework. Structure ads into repeatable components (e.g. hooks, messaging, product, calls to action) and enable systematic production, testing, and iteration at scale.\nCampaign Development and Execution Lead the development and execution of data-driven campaigns. Ensure effective targeting, messaging, and creative output across all channels, with a focus on continuous production and rapid iteration rather than one-off campaigns.\nTesting and Experimentation Establish a rigorous testing framework for creative. Run high-frequency experiments, analyse performance, and iterate on promising concepts. Drive a culture of continuous experimentation and learning.\nAI-Driven Creative Optimisation Leverage AI tools to enhance creative production, including generating visuals, voiceovers, and variations. Use AI to accelerate workflows, improve performance, and scale iteration.\nCross-Functional Collaboration Work closely with Product, Analytics, Design, and Marketing teams to align acquisition efforts with product roadmap, user experience, and broader marketing initiatives.\n\nAbout you\n\nGenerally, Creative Strategists at Stake have a strong track record in acquisition or performance marketing, with 4+ years of relevant experience. They have a deep understanding of paid channels and a proven ability to drive measurable growth outcomes. They combine analytical thinking with creative judgment, and are comfortable working across strategy and execution. They are proactive, results-oriented, and thrive in fast-paced environments where testing and iteration are core to success. Experience working with creative production, UGC, or AI tools is highly regarded.\n\nAt Stake, we\'re more interested in your attitude than your resume. If you believe this is a role you want to jump into, please apply and let us know why in your cover letter!\n\nBenefits of working at Stake\n\nYou\'ll have the opportunity to work with autonomy while learning from some of the best talent in the industry, playing a meaningful role in building a company that has loads of positive momentum and excitement around it. Having said that, we also have perks.\n\nPlease see on our Careers website (https://hellostake.com/au/careers) the list of benefits under our Grow with Stake program. They include:\n\nCareer relevant development and training with professional development allowance\nUp to 16 weeks of paid parental leave\nChildcare allowance\nSonder - healthcare, safety support and EAP for you and your immediate family\nAdditional leave types (Swap days, Bear Days, TOIL, Compassionate, Sorry Business)\nDiscretionary performance bonus and talent referral bonus\nEmployee Share Options scheme for senior leaders\nStake products: SMSF 30% discount on yearly membership fee, $295 AUD annual trading credit and Stake Black account\nRecognition awards and team celebrations\n\nStake is an equal opportunity employer that values diversity. We\'re proactive about providing an inclusive work environment and do not discriminate based on race, religion, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, age or disability status. We\'re also endorsed by WORK180 as a great employer for women.\n\nIt all comes together to explain why Stake placed 1st in the 2024 AFR BOSS Best Places to Work list for the Banking, Superannuation & Financial Services category, across all of Australia and New Zealand.\n\nSo what happens next?\n\nOnce we\'ve received your application, we\'ll give it the attention it deserves and you\'ll hear from us either way. We\'re committed to responding to every applicant. If we think you\'d be a good addition to our team, we\'ll give you a call and from there, you\'ll cruise through our recruitment process.\n\nTo all recruitment agencies: Stake does not accept agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias or directly to Stake employees. Stake is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Stake','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=b619404b0e7b728a','scraped','4 days ago'),(2688,NULL,'job','Advisor Business Controls','','Brisbane QLD',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'You will primarily support the business with incident and issue management, test and monitor the effectiveness of controls, compliance with obligations and risk appetite, as well as provide risk insights by identifying new / emerging risks and regulatory change, to support the consistent delivery of meaningful value to our customers. Where risk events or compliance breaches occur, you will drive, track and monitor remediation and treatment of risks outside of appetite to fulfill our commitment to our customers and communities.\n\nYou will support the consistent implementation of change by ensuring that Great Southern Bank’s frameworks, policies, supporting standards, processes and procedures are applied, with a focus on embedding divisional senior leader accountability for risk management.\n\nYou’ll make an impact by:\n\nAct as a trust business partner to help manage incidents and issues\nAssisting the team in coordinating risk and control identification\nSupporting risk assessments and managing risk acceptances\nWorking with the Senior Advisors and stakeholders to set key risk indicators (KRIs), thresholds and triggers\nPerform and Review control design and operating effectiveness\nDocumenting and providing assurance that reasonable steps are being taken to meet accountabilities\nLeveraging AI tools to improve processes and efficiency\n\nDo things differently with us\n\nTo succeed in this role, you will have:\n\nMinimum 1-3 years in financial services with a sound understanding of operational risk and compliance in the financial services industry\nDemonstrated Experience in Financial Services Operations, Risk or Business Controls function\nExperience in data analysis using SQL and Data Bricks is highly desirable\nExperience in AI Risk and usage of AI tools is desirable\nControls testing and assurance activities highly desirable\nDegree in management, business, finance or related discipline (desirable)\nKnowledge of relevant Finance industry standards, acts, codes and legislation (e.g., APRA, Consumer Credit Code, Credit Union Code of Practice, Privacy Act, Trade Practices Act, FSRA) (essential)\n\nWhy Great Southern Bank?\n\nWhatever your role with us, you’ll be part of a force for good. We’re owned by our customers right here in Australia, so our success benefits everyday people and families. Working at Great Southern Bank, you’ll also enjoy a range of fantastic benefits, some examples include:\n\nHelping you unlock a brighter future by investing in your development and wellbeing, offering you study leave, a day for you and professional wellbeing coaching.\nBenefits that support you and your wellbeing so that you can thrive at work and at home, today and tomorrow. Enjoy access to our wellbeing centre and the flexibility to work from home two days a week.\nHelping you to achieve your financial goals and positively impact your family and community. We offer discounts on a wide range of Great Southern Bank products and services such as savings and transaction accounts, insurance, home loans and more!\n\nImagine working for a bank that truly helps people. You can.\n\nQuestions? Please contact our Talent Acquisition team at careers@gsb.com.au\n\nAt Great Southern Bank, we’re building a workplace where everyone belongs. We value diverse backgrounds, cultures, abilities and experiences - including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, veterans, people with disability, and the LGBTQ+ community - because it makes us stronger for our people, customers and communities. Through flexible working, collaboration and fair, inclusive decision-making, we empower our people to do their best every day.\n\nWe move with purpose, are curious about what’s next, remain focused on what matters most, and are always ready to find smarter ways to help our customers and communities thrive. Our people bring energy and initiative to a fast-changing environment, making thoughtful decisions that balance doing good for our customers with driving sustainable success for our business. If you enjoy working in a place where priorities evolve, ideas are valued, and every action contributes to something bigger, you’ll feel right at home here at Great Southern Bank.\n\n#LI-Hybrid','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Great Southern Bank','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=3a58f62d5e975ee6','scraped','4 days ago'),(2689,NULL,'job','Senior Medical Officer','Permanent','Newman WA 6753',NULL,'',332500.00,'$310,000 - $355,000 a year','AI Job Summary\nHave Vocational Registration or Fellowship of the Royal Australian College of General Practitioners.\nRelevant experience delivering health care to Aboriginal communities as a senior team member, with ability to lead GPs.\nKnowledge of the Medicare billing framework and willingness to appropriately maximize Medicare billing.\nSign up or log in to analyse my fit\nRole Type\nOn-site • Permanent • Full-time • Executive\nPay Rate\n310000 AUD – 355000 AUD (Annum)\nDescription\n\nAbout the Opportunity\n\nAre you passionate about making an impact while working in a dynamic and supportive team?\n\nJoin Puntukurnu Aboriginal Medical Services (PAMS) as a Senior Medical Officer\n\nAs a member of a multidisciplinary team, the Senior Medical Officer provides high quality, client focused and culturally appropriate primary health care services to the Aboriginal people of Newman and remote communities of Jigalong, Punmu, Parnngurr and Kunawarritji.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\n·Lead clinical governance, quality improvement, and accreditation (AGPAL) activities\n·Deliver high-quality, culturally appropriate GP services in a multidisciplinary team\n·Drive improved health outcomes through prevention, chronic disease management, and health promotion\n·Provide strategic clinical advice and support organisational planning and service delivery\n·Supervise and mentor clinical staff, supporting workforce development and capability\n·Ensure best practice in documentation, Medicare billing, reporting, and KPI performance\n\nAbout You\n\nTo be considered for this position, you must have:\n\n·Uphold and contribute to the organisation’s mission, values, and objectives\n·Comply with all policies, procedures, and relevant legislation\n·Foster teamwork, open communication, and a positive workplace culture\n·Participate in professional development, training, and Employee Development Days\n·Support continuous quality improvement and quality management systems\n·Adhere to Work Health & Safety requirements, including identifying and managing risks.\n\nThe position involves working with a multicultural organisation where the majority of staff, clients and stakeholders identify as Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander. Candidates must be able to demonstrate an understanding of the issues affecting Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people and their ability to communicate sensitively and effectively with Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people.\n\nAs per section 51 of the Equal Opportunity Act 1984 (WA) PAMS actively seeks to increase the diversity of our workforce to better meet the differing needs of our clients and stakeholders and to improve equal opportunity outcomes for our employees. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people are strongly encouraged to apply.\n\nPlease note: In addition to the above skills and experience, relevant licences and eligibility criteria apply (as per the Job Description).\n\nApplicants for this position must be legally entitled to work in Australia and will be required to provide evidence of this entitlement. Acceptable evidence includes an Australian or New Zealand passport, birth certificate, or foreign passport with relevant visa.\n\nRemuneration & Benefits\n\nAttractive base salary of $310,000 – $355,000 per annum (excluding superannuation)\n5 weeks’ annual leave plus 17.5% leave loading\n11% superannuation\nSalary packaging up to $15,900 plus entertainment benefits\nPower subsidy allowance and PAMS-provided accommodation\nTwo return flights per year\nEmployee Assistance Program (EAP)\nRetention incentives in line with PAMS Employee Remuneration Policy\n\nAbout the Organisation\n\nWith an administrative hub based in Newman, in the Pilbara region of Western Australia, The Puntukurnu Aboriginal Medical Service (PAMS) provides holistic primary health care to the individuals and families within the remote communities of Jigalong, Parnngurr, Punmu and Kunawarritji.\n\nPAMS aims to improve the standard of health of the Martu people and all Aboriginal people living in the East Pilbara region of Western Australia through the provision of community based, comprehensive primary health care services. We exist to promote the health and well-being of individual community members and to relieve sickness and the suffering of the indigenous community as a whole. We are passionate about providing the highest standard of patient care whilst incorporating a holistic approach toward diagnosis and management of illness.\n\nApplication Process\n\nWe require you to submit:\n\nA current comprehensive CV including the contact details of two current referees and;\nA cover letter no more than 2 pages that clearly outlines the skills and experience you have gained to make you suitable for this position.\n\nScreening and assessment will commence immediately.\n\nFor further information including, please contact the People and Culture Team on 08 9177 8307 or pamshr@puntukurnu.com.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'PAMS - Puntukurnu Aboriginal Medical Service','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9d64838a3abc2cc2','scraped','4 days ago'),(2690,NULL,'job','Product Manager - Hybrid','Permanent','Australia',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Work options: Hybrid\n\nWe are passionate about people making their own decisions about where and when they work. Our aim is to facilitate hybrid working (mix of in the office and from home) where possible to support our people to be effective, empowered, and productive to achieve both their career and personal goals. Because we recognise that working flexibly means different things to different people, flexible working exists in many forms.\n\nWho are we?\n\nHumanforceʼs vision is to make work easier and life better for frontline and flexible workforces.\n\nHumanforce provides the market leading, best-in-one human capital management (HCM) suite for frontline and flexible workforces - without compromise. Our employee centered, intelligent and compliant HCM suite is highly integrated and composable, and consists of Workforce Management (WFM), HR, Talent, Payroll, and Wellbeing.\n\nHumanforce has built strong foundations since its founding in 2002. We help over 2300 customers and almost 1 million employees under management in 30+ countries, across a wide range of industries, including aged, child and health care; education; hospitality; retail; local government and more. Today, we have offices across Australia, New Zealand, United Kingdom, North America and the Philippines.\n\nCustomers choose Humanforce because we enable them to deliver an exceptional employee experience, build a compelling employee value proposition, and connect the flow of the worlds talent with the growth, productivity and efficiency objectives of frontline and flexible workforces.\n\nAI at Humanforce\n\nAt Humanforce, we\'re not experimenting at the edges of AI — we\'re redesigning the core of how we operate. We see AI as a fundamental shift, not an incremental improvement, and we\'re deliberately moving toward becoming an AI-native organisation.\n\nThat means rethinking how work gets done end-to-end: how we build our products, make decisions, serve customers, and scale impact. We\'re not layering AI onto old ways of working — we\'re redefining and reimagining our processes, tools, and team structures to take full advantage of what AI makes possible.\n\nWho you are\n\nYou are a commercially and customer-minded product manager with domain expertise in HRIS or HR technology. You understand how HR practitioners and people teams actually work - not just in theory, but in practice and you bring that insight directly into how you define, prioritise, and ship product.\n\nYou thrive in a delivery-focused environment where you own your roadmap, make decisions with incomplete information, and move quickly. You\'re comfortable working deeply embedded within an engineering team, know how to build trust fast, and communicate clearly with both technical and non-technical stakeholders.\n\nYou\'ll drive product thinking, own near-term priorities including a critical position management capability, and contribute to the development of AI-powered HRIS features that are shaping the future of how HR teams operate.\n\nWhat you will do\nOwn the product roadmap for your area of the HRM Tribe, driving discovery, prioritisation, and delivery of near-term capabilities — including key upcoming strategic projects; Humanforce\'s position management feature and the LMS product\nLead the development of HR agentic workflows: work with engineering to design, define, and ship AI-powered automation within the HRIS product that meaningfully improves how HR practitioners operate\nTranslate customer pain points into well-defined product requirements — writing clear PRDs, acceptance criteria, and specifications that engineering can act on without ambiguity\nBe embedded in delivery: run sprint planning, backlog refinement, sprint reviews, and retrospectives as an active and accountable member of the engineering team\nBuild and maintain strong customer feedback loops — conducting discovery interviews, synthesising insights, and ensuring real customer needs shape every product decision\nPartner closely with cross-functional stakeholders including engineering leads, design, sales, implementation, and customer success to align on priorities and communicate trade-offs\nRepresent your product area to internal leadership: provide clear visibility on roadmap progress, risks, and outcomes on a regular cadence\n What you’ll need\n2 - 4 years of product management experience in a B2B SaaS environment, with a track record of owning features end-to-end from discovery through to launch\nStrong HRIS or HR system experience, either as a PM who has built HR products, or as a practitioner or implementer with deep knowledge of how these systems work (position management, org hierarchies, leave accruals, and similar concepts)\nGenuine customer acumen; you regularly talk to customers yourself, can distinguish between what people say they want and what they actually need, and let that insight drive product direction\nCollaborative working style with the ability to operate effectively across multi-site engineering teams in Brisbane, Melbourne, and Sydney.\nClear, direct communicator who can make confident decisions, explain trade-offs to both technical and non-technical audiences, and deliver difficult messages constructively.\nComfort with ambiguity and pace, you can operate with a high degree of autonomy in a fast-moving, high-growth environment without needing a perfectly defined brief.\nDemonstrated use of AI tools in your day-to-day work, or strong and genuine eagerness to adopt and apply them, including in the context of building AI-enabled products.\nSome ‘nice to haves’\nExperience with payroll systems or workforce management products\nHands-on familiarity with AI tools such as Claude, Cursor, or similar, and experience incorporating them into product workflows or building AI-adjacent features\nBackground in a PE-backed or high-growth technology business where pace, autonomy, and adaptability are table stakes\nOur values\nWe are bold\nWe are all in\nWe are customer obsessed\nWe do what we say\nWe are good humans\nOur approach to flexibility\n\nWe are passionate about people making their own decisions about where and when they work. Our hybrid model of minimum two days a week of in office moments supports flexibility tailored to individual and team needs, empowering people to achieve their career and personal goals.\n\nBenefits\nA truly flexible workplace through our Flex@HF approach\nThe opportunity to be part of a fast-growing global tech company\nA focus on learning and development through Humanforce HR\nA generous talent referral program – know great people, be rewarded\n12 weeks paid parental leave for primary careers, 4 weeks for secondary\n4 extra days leave to focus on your wellbeing\nContemporary and practical Employee Assistance Program\nA cool reward and recognition program – shout to your colleagues and earn points to spend\nAccess to our own financial wellbeing platform Thrive – including earned wage access, tools to budget and save, perks and cashback across 100s of Australian retailers\nFun, collaborative culture with passionate people\nA workplace where you can genuinely improve the world of work!\n\nWe are a diverse and dispersed organisation and are actively looking to grow our team with individuals from all diverse backgrounds. We encourage applicants from all backgrounds, cultures, ages, genders, neurodiversity, religions, sexual orientations, and experiences to apply.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Humanforce','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=cf6800e6b7839ed2','scraped','4 days ago'),(2691,NULL,'job','Head of Data & Intelligence, Enterprise','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Create your best future and join Westpac as Head of Data & Intelligence\n\nWhat’s the Role:\n\nAs Head of Data & Intelligence, this role is accountable for lifting the division’s data and analytics maturity through modern data foundations, reusable data products, and embedded decision intelligence. It leads the use of advanced analytics, AI and the Westpac Intelligence Layer to deliver trusted, scalable insight, improve decision‑making, and drive productivity across the business. The role owns divisional data and analytics prioritisation, value realisation and governance, while building sustainable capability and ensuring AI and analytics are delivered safely, responsibly and in line with enterprise standards\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nDesign and deliver a modern, scalable data ecosystem that embeds analytics, decision intelligence and AI into customer and business journeys.\nAccelerate insight‑to‑action by integrating data‑driven decisioning into day‑to‑day business and operational processes.\nDrive measurable improvements in customer outcomes, including engagement, personalisation and NPS, while supporting sustainable revenue growth through data‑led decisions.\nEnsure all data, analytics and AI initiatives deliver quantifiable value and clearly defined ROI.\nEstablish and maintain trusted, explainable and compliant data, analytics and automation solutions that operate within risk appetite.\nEnable the safe and confident adoption of advanced analytics and AI at scale through strong governance and Responsible AI practices.\nBuild an AI‑enabled, data‑led division with decision‑making embedded into operating rhythms, supported by the Westpac Intelligence Layer and agentic capabilities.\nAlign workforce capability and operating model with the Strategic Workforce Plan to ensure long‑term sustainability.\n\nWhat do I need?\n\nSenior leadership experience delivering large‑scale data, analytics, AI or technology‑enabled transformation with measurable business outcomes.\nExperience across Enterprise functions including (Finance, Risk, etc) to drive reuseability and work with the heads across each vertical domains under Enterprise Functions.\nProven end‑to‑end delivery of data, analytics and AI initiatives driving revenue growth, productivity uplift, cost reduction and improved customer outcomes.\nStrong commercial acumen, with the ability to prioritise data and AI investments based on ROI and business impact.\nExecutive‑level influence, shaping strategic decisions, funding priorities and enterprise direction.\nDemonstrated operating‑model and change leadership, embedding analytics and decision intelligence into business decision‑making and operating rhythms.\nStrong technical judgement across modern data ecosystems, data products and reusable platform foundations.\nPractical experience scaling AI (ML and GenAI) and advanced analytics into production with governance, monitoring and value tracking.\nProven capability to build sustainable data and AI capability, including workforce strategy, talent pipelines, succession planning and operating effectively in regulated environments.\n\nWhy join us?\n\nWe’re obsessed with becoming our customers\' #1 banking partner for life and we’re looking for people who are passionate about helping us achieve that goal. In return, we’re committed to making Westpac the best place to work in the country. Here are just a few of the ways we’re already doing that:\n\nSpecial offers on banking products and discounts from top brands, including generous employee only mortgage rates!\nFlexible work arrangements to help you achieve a greater work/life balance, and a variety of leave options including Culture, Lifestyle and Wellbeing leave.\nTailored learning and development opportunities to help your grow your career within the bank.\nLots of opportunities to ‘give back’ to the Community by getting involved in our many volunteering initiatives.\n\nCreate your future today\n\nTo get started, simply click on the APPLY or APPLY NOW button\n\nWe’re all about creating a supportive and inclusive community. We welcome everyone no matter your age, gender, background, or abilities. We also provide additional support to welcome our veterans, Indigenous Australians and neurodiverse community.\n\nIf you need any adjustments during the recruitment process, you can find out more information and additional contact details by visiting the \"People with Disability and/or needing Accessibility Requirements\" page on our website .\n\nWe’re all about helping our people grow and succeed. Whether you’re a current employee, trainee, or intern, we’re committed to your career development Check out our FAQs and internal support resources here.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Westpac Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=0d32c3c3bcf0b181','scraped','4 days ago'),(2692,NULL,'job','Principal Security Architect','Permanent','Brisbane QLD',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Who We Are\n\n iSelect and Compare the Market are trusted, well-known brands dedicated to helping millions of Australians compare and buy personal finance and household products such as insurance, energy, and loans. Together, we provide a seamless, customer-focused experience that makes it easier for Australians to find the right products to suit their needs.\n\nWhat You’ll Be Doing\n\n The Security Architect designs and governs secure‑by‑design architectures, aligning security strategy with business objectives, risk appetite, and regulatory requirements across cloud, infrastructure, applications, data, and identity.\n\nDefine and maintain enterprise security architecture principles, patterns, standards, and reference architectures\nLead security design for new platforms, services, and major initiatives\nConduct security architecture reviews, threat modelling, and risk assessments\nEnsure alignment to Zero Trust, defence‑in‑depth, and least‑privilege principles\nDefine SOC strategy, operating model, service design, policies, SOPs, playbooks, and reporting\nAct as a trusted security advisor to architects and engineering teams\nEmbed security‑by‑design and DevSecOps practices across delivery\nDrive continuous improvement, automation, and innovation including AI/ML adoption\n\n What’s In It For You\n\n At Compare the Market and iSelect, we’re all about helping people make smart choices – and joining us might just be yours. We offer an environment where your ideas are heard, your contributions are valued, and your growth genuinely matters. Collaboration is part of our DNA, and you’ll be joining a supportive, forward-thinking team where you can do meaningful work (and be recognised for it!)\n\nWe’re guided by three shared values that shape how we work, how we treat each other, and how we show up for our customers - Drive, Noble Intent and All Together.\n\nPlus, we offer a range of great perks to help you thrive both in and out of work:\n\nVibrant and social community who have annual celebrations, family fun days and regular events\nEnjoy flexible work arrangements, including the option of one day working from home each week or a 9-day fortnight\nEnjoy additional leave days - ‘ME’ leave and ‘Volunteer Day’ leave\nOption to purchase additional leave\nReturn To Work bonus for returning parents\nQuarterly Award and Recognition program\n\nWhat Sets You Apart\n\n10+ years’ in cybersecurity with architecture or senior engineering experience.\nStrong knowledge of cloud, IAM, application, data, and infrastructure security knowledge across modern enterprise environments.\nExperience applying security frameworks (e.g. NIST, SABSA, TOGAF).\nStrong stakeholder engagement and communication skills\nHas defined and embedded organisation‑wide security architecture standards across delivery teams and platforms, ensuring consistent adoption aligned to risk appetite, regulatory requirements, and industry best practice.\nHas driven the early integration of security into solution design, resulting in a demonstrable reduction in late‑stage security issues, architectural rework, and delivery risk.\nExperience providing trusted, pragmatic security advice to senior technical and business stakeholders, evidenced by positive stakeholder feedback and effective enablement of delivery outcomes.\nHas led and evidenced measurable improvements in organisational security maturity through architectural governance, metrics, and continuous improvement initiatives.\n\nAt Compare the Market and iSelect we’re proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer and we embrace diversity.\n\nThis role is available to candidates with unlimited Australian working rights only. Sponsorship is not available.\n\nCompare the Market and iSelect are committed to protecting your privacy. All applications and personal information are kept confidential and securely stored in line with Australian privacy laws, used only for recruitment purposes, and not shared with third parties outside the Auto and General Holdings Group without your consent.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'iSelect','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=87f23f48b4c58167','scraped','4 days ago'),(2693,NULL,'job','Administration Officer - Anatomical Pathology','Permanent','New Lambton NSW',NULL,'',7603722.50,'$75,176.80 - $76,897.65 a year','Employment Type: Permanent Full Time\nPosition Classification: Administration Officer Level 4\nRemuneration: $75,176.80 - $76,897.65 per annum plus superannuation\nHours Per Week: 38\nRequisition ID: REQ655759\nLocation: John Hunter Hospital\nApplications Close:12 May 2026 - 11:59pm\n\nAbout the opportunity\n\nNSW Health Pathology is currently seeking a skilled Administration Officer to join the Anatomical Pathology Department at John Hunter Hospital in Newcastle. Operating in a busy and dynamic environment, the Anatomical Pathology Laboratory at John Hunter Hospital conducts tests for surgical patients across Newcastle and the Hunter Valley region.\n\nIf you\'re driven and thrive in a team environment, we encourage you to submit your application today!\n\nNestled on the beautiful, sun-drenched eastern coastline of New South Wales, just over two hours north of Sydney, Newcastle is a vibrant city bursting with things to do. Spectacular beaches and coastal scenery, with ocean baths and some of the country’s best surfing spots, are only just the start. Then there’s a dedication to coffee to attract envious glances from Melbourne.\n\nWhat you\'ll be doing\n\nThe Administration Officer provides effective administrative and office support services for the Anatomical Pathology Department, whilst ensuring all tasks undertaken are managed in a timely manner.\n\nWhat we can offer you\n\nFinancial Benefits - Generous salary packaging options and other fringe benefits\n\nWork-life balance - Up to 12 additional days off per year in addition to Annual Leave (for full-time employees)\n\nProfessional growth - Learning and development opportunities, including in-house training with RTO My Health Learning\n\nHealth & wellbeing - Fitness Passport gym discounts and Employee Assistance Program (EAP) for staff and families.\n\nInterested in joining Australia’s largest public pathology service? Apply now by addressing the following questions:\n\nProven computer literacy and strong keyboard skills with speed and accuracy, including use of digital transcription equipment.\nProven experience working in a high workload and pressure area with successful track records to provide best performance as well as knowledge of clinical and corporate applications and work practices, and their relationship to other health care processes.\nDemonstrated ability and initiative to work both as part of a team and independently, supporting your team members and management, with sound knowledge of administrative procedures in health setting.\nDemonstrated strong customer focus and commitment to providing exceptional services to all clients (internal and external to the organistion).\nExcellent interpersonal and communication skills including strong written and verbal English and be capable of professionally liaising and working with stakeholders across all levels of the organisation using different modes of communication in a technical and business context.\nDemonstrated knowledge of anatomical terms and awareness of the diagnostic role of anatomical pathology.\n\nInformation For Applicants\n\nNSW Health Pathology is an equal opportunity employer committed to an inclusive workplace. We value, and welcome all suitably qualified applicants regardless of age, background, disability, sexual orientation or gender identity.\n\nNSW Health Pathology is committed to providing accessibility and reasonable accommodations and ensuring our recruitment process is flexible, inclusive, and free from barriers, promoting equal opportunities for all to succeed. Please reach out if you need adjustments.\n\nNSW Health Pathology is committed to growing the Aboriginal workforce in public health. For Aboriginal candidates, support is available through the Stepping Up website\n\nYou must have valid working rights in Australia for the duration of the appointment to be eligible to apply.\n\nAll workers must meet NSW Health’s vaccination and screening requirements before starting employment. See PD2026_004 for more detail. The preferred candidate may be required to undergo a functional assessment prior to appointment.\n\nAn eligibility list may be created for similar vacancies in the future.\n\nWe encourage applicants to submit responses that reflect their own experiences and perspectives. Please note that applications that appear to be generated by AI tools or copied from external sources may not be considered.\n\nThis position requires a Working with Children Check (WWCC) issued by the Office of the Children’s Guardian.\n\nNeed more information?\n\n 1)\n 2)\n 3) For role related queries or questions contact Patricia Lusby on Patricia.Lusby@health.nsw.gov.au\n\nTo learn more about NSWHP please visit “Life at NSW Health Pathology” or connect with us on LinkedIn!','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'NSW Health','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=bacc86f0de91a4d7','scraped','4 days ago'),(2694,NULL,'job','Lead Business Analyst','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Create your best future and join Westpac as a Lead Business Analyst.\n\nThis role will play a crucial part of the UNITE team. UNITE is our business-led, tech-enabled transformation, and a key priority for the Group. UNITE is about delivering \'one best way\' to make our processes, systems and tech simpler so we can deliver a better experience for our customers and make things easier for our people.\n\nLocation: Sydney-based role only\nOn-site Requirement: 3 days in the office per week\nWhy On-site? This is a highly collaborative position involving regular face-to-face workshops and close team interaction, making in-office presence essential.\n\nWhat’s the role?\n\nAs a Lead Business Analyst, you will partner closely with stakeholders to understand, analyse, and clearly define requirements for changes to business products, processes, policies, data, and systems, ensuring alignment to Westpac’s strategic objectives and business needs.\n\nIn this people leader role you’ll lead, coach and motivate delivery teams thorough complex migrations. You will also drive and champion the effective use of AI across the BA community.\n\nAdditionally, you will manage requirements through the full delivery lifecycle, providing clear recommendations that support effective business solutions and deliver measurable value. You will ensure consistency and quality across deliverables that contribute across multiple streams of work.\n\nWhat do I need?\n\nProven experience as a Lead Business Analyst, including leading and coordinating work across a BA team\nPrevious people management experience\nExperience delivering data migration initiatives within large, complex organisations, ideally in banking or financial services\nStrong stakeholder management skills, with the ability to balance competing needs while staying within agreed scope\nHighly collaborative, able to work effectively across teams and initiatives to ensure alignment and clarity of outcomes\nDemonstrated analytical and logical thinking, with the ability to plan ahead and solve complex problems with practical solutions\nStrong understanding of project management disciplines, technology, and business systems, enabling delivery of high‑quality, value‑driven outcomes\nAbility to coach and develop team members on adopting industry best practices related to Business Analyst work\n\nWhy join us?\n\nWe’re obsessed with becoming our customers\' #1 banking partner for life and we’re looking for people who are passionate about helping us achieve that goal. In return, we’re committed to making Westpac the best place to work in the country. Here are just a few of the ways we’re already doing that:\n\nSpecial offers on banking products and discounts from top brands, including generous employee-only mortgage rates!\nFlexible work arrangements to help you achieve a greater work/life balance, and a variety of leave options including Culture, Lifestyle and Wellbeing leave.\nTailored learning and development opportunities to help your grow your career within the bank.\nLots of opportunities to ‘give back’ to the Community by getting involved in our many volunteering initiatives.\n\nCreate your future today\n\nTo get started, simply click on the APPLY or APPLY NOW button | #UNITEProgram\n\nWe’re all about creating a supportive and inclusive community. We welcome everyone no matter your age, gender, background, or abilities. We also provide additional support to welcome our veterans, Indigenous Australians and neurodiverse community.\nIf you need any adjustments during the recruitment process, you can find more information and contact details on our FAQs and how to contact us page , under the ‘Diversity, sustainability and flexibility’ section.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Westpac','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=dba0587a0870f757','scraped','4 days ago'),(2695,NULL,'job','Assistant Advisor, Talent Acquisition','Permanent','Chatswood NSW',NULL,'',8355458.00,'From $83,554.58 a year','Assistant Advisor – Administrative Officer Level 6\n\nPermanent Full Time\nHybrid flexibility for work-life balance | Chatswood or Charlestown\nSalary commencing from $83,554.58 + 12% Super + 17.5% annual leave loading\nUp to 12 extra days off per year + 4 weeks annual leave\nIncrease your take home pay with salary packaging, meal allowance, fitness passport and more\nJoin the team enriching health in millions of ways every day through digital innovation\n\nApplications Close: 11:59pm, 6 May 2026\n\nAbout Us – eHealth NSW\n\nAt eHealth NSW, we’re leading the digital transformation of Australia’s largest health system. As NSW Health’s digital centre of excellence, we design, build and support world-class ICT solutions that improve patient care across the state.\n\nGuided by a Cloud First Strategy, we’re harnessing digital technology to better patient care and deliver scalable, quality, patient-centred, digital healthcare. With your skills and experience, you can help enrich the lives of millions while developing your career within Australia’s largest health organisation—alongside passionate tech professionals, health partners and industry leaders building solutions that truly make a difference.\n\nAbout the Opportunity\n\nAs an Assistant Advisor in our Talent Acquisition team at eHealth NSW, you will help make a real difference in healthcare through ensuring eHealth NSW can attract, hire and support the skilled people who design and deliver digital health services. By providing efficient recruitment support, maintaining accurate systems, contributing to recruitment projects, and ensuring a smooth experience for candidates and hiring managers, the role helps build a high‑performing workforce that supports better patient care across NSW\n\nIn this role, you will:\n\nDeliver a range of administrative recruitment services aligned to best practice and NSW Health policies to support high-quality attraction, selection and assessment activities.\nCoordinate and support recruitment projects by monitoring milestones, reporting on progress and contributing to team-wide priorities.\nMaintain and improve office systems, records and processes to ensure data accuracy, compliance and accessibility.\nManage your own workload and day‑to‑day priorities while supporting team objectives within a high‑volume environment.\n\nAbout You\n\nWe are looking for someone who:\n\nHas experience delivering recruitment or HR administration services within a fast‑paced environment.\nDemonstrates strong organisational skills, with the ability to balance competing priorities and deliver consistent, high‑quality work.\nCommunicates effectively with stakeholders and provides excellent customer service to candidates and hiring managers.\nUses technology confidently, including HRIS, records management systems and Microsoft Office tools.\nWorks collaboratively within a team to deliver shared goals and contribute to a constructive workplace culture.\n\nNeed more information?\n\nPosition description\nFind out how we hire at eHealth NSW\nCheck out our diversity and inclusion commitment\nLearn more about us at eHealth NSW\n\nWorking at eHealth\n\nOur people are at the heart of who we are. We support our people with great benefits so they can enrich health in millions of ways every day:\n\nFlexible work options\nProfessional growth and career development\nAllocated day off per month\nSalary packaging\nVarious health and wellbeing programs to support our team\n\nHow to apply\n\nShare with us your cover letter and most up to date resume (up to 5 pages), highlighting your relevant skills and experience.\n\nWe recognise that AI tools are increasingly being used to assist with resumes and applications. While we accept their use, we’re eager to see your personality and get to know the person behind the application!\n\nFor further discussions around the role or recruitment process, including adjustments, please contact Amy Korompay on Amy.Korompay@health.nsw.gov.au and quote REQ650224.\n\nWe will review all applications after the closing date. If your application is successful, you may be invited to take part in additional assessments as part of the recruitment process.\n\nAdditional information\n\nThis recruitment may be used to create a Talent Pool for similar future roles (ongoing or temporary) that may arise over the next 18 months.\nTo be eligible for this role you must have current Australian work rights (Australian citizen, permanent resident, New Zealand citizen with a current passport, or hold a valid visa with permission to work in Australia).\nIf you currently reside outside NSW, please confirm in your application your willingness to relocate if successful.\n\n.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'NSW Health','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=cd244c4aec222507','scraped','4 days ago'),(2696,NULL,'job','Sr. Account Executive - Federal Government','','Canberra ACT 2600',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'OPENTEXT - THE INFORMATION COMPANY\nOpenText is a global leader in information management, where innovation, creativity, and collaboration are the key components of our corporate culture. As a member of our team, you will have the opportunity to partner with the most highly regarded companies in the world, tackle complex issues, and contribute to projects that shape the future of digital transformation.\n\nAI-First. Future-Driven. Human-Centered.\nAt OpenText, AI is at the heart of everything we do—powering innovation, transforming work, and empowering digital knowledge workers. We\'re hiring talent that AI can\'t replace to help us shape the future of information management. Join us.\n\nPURPOSEAt OpenText, we are the Information Company, dedicated to creating software solutions and delivering services that redefine the future of digital. Join our winning team and lead the way in Enterprise Information Management (EIM). Our mission is to enable the digital transformation of our customers with sophisticated, secure, high-value, and cost-effective solutions—whether onsite, via mobile devices, private cloud, or in the cloud. Our EIM platform includes comprehensive and integrated product suites such as Content Suite, Process Suite, Experience Suite, Discovery Suite, Information Exchange Suite, and AI/Analytics.We celebrate diversity in all its forms—ethnicity, gender, language, age, sexual orientation, religion, socio-economic status, physical and mental ability, thinking styles, experience, and education. This diversity fuels innovation and business success, making us more creative, flexible, and competitive.Our Senior Account Executive for the Federal Government will focus on a select number of Key and Strategic Accounts, representing OpenText at the highest levels. Our customers are driving their applications to the cloud, and you will bring recent experience in transforming traditional Enterprise Software businesses to the cloud.\n\nSTRENGTHSYou are a self-motivated individual who makes things happen. You listen carefully to understand your customers and peers, challenge effectively, and make quick, logical decisions that drive positive outcomes. You are not afraid to fail and learn quickly from setbacks. You excel at managing large, complex deals and orchestrating successful outcomes with customers, partners, and internal teams. Your persistence, inner composure, and self-assurance empower you to navigate complex problems and situations. You thrive on new challenges and are determined to succeed. You build deep, meaningful relationships with senior executives in the organizations you engage with.\n\nORGANISATIONAL ALIGNMENTDuring our first ANZ Leadership Team Meeting, we envisioned a future where OT solutions in the Cloud drive customer success through innovation, partnerships, and business solutions. To achieve this vision, we focus on: 1.High Performance Culture•We measure six distinct elements to support a high-performance culture: Customer Satisfaction, Employee Satisfaction, Quota Attainment, Innovative Ideas, Employee Retention, and Local Regional Awards.2.One Team•As the Senior Account Executive for the Federal Government, you will lead the Federal Government operation for OpenText’s content services. You will work with and demonstrate leadership across various business areas, including Solution Consulting, Professional Services, Partner Managers, Customer Renewals, Maintenance, HR, Finance, and Revenue Recognition. You will excel as a matrix leader, inspiring those around you to achieve their best.3.Individual Responsibility for Collective Success•OpenText’s Federal Government operation may be small in staff numbers, but our customer base and opportunities are impressive. Maximizing your effectiveness and that of your team is critical. You will focus on your role and quota targets while coaching your teams to deliver outstanding customer outcomes. This role goes beyond selling; you will effectively lead the OpenText content services operation in the ACT.\n\nWHAT IT TAKES: •A track record of at least 5+ years of selling Software Solutions in government or significant experience in consulting to or in government.•Experience with cloud-based, on-premises, or hybrid solutions.•Ability to identify, develop, and navigate large government businesses.•Strong knowledge of the customer buying process.•Demonstrated strong sales methodologies and the use of tools to achieve and exceed targets.•Intellectual curiosity, the ability to grasp new products and solutions quickly, and a spirit of innovation.•Completed post-secondary education and a passion for continuous learning.\n\nOpenText\'s efforts to build an inclusive work environment go beyond simply complying with applicable laws. Our Employment Equity and Diversity Policy provides direction on maintaining a working environment that is inclusive of everyone, regardless of culture, national origin, race, color, gender, gender identification, sexual orientation, family status, age, veteran status, disability, religion, or other basis protected by applicable laws.\nIf you need assistance and/or a reasonable accommodation due to a disability during the application or recruiting process, please contact us athr@opentext.com. Our proactive approach fosters collaboration, innovation, and personal growth, enriching OpenText\'s vibrant workplace.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'OpenText','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9a9309ab3285b33b','scraped','4 days ago'),(2697,NULL,'job','Senior Business Development Manager (Unit 42)','Full-time','Sydney NSW 2060',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'North Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Sales Ref ID: JR-016970\n\nOur Mission\n\nAt Palo Alto Networks®, we’re united by a shared mission—to protect our digital way of life. We thrive at the intersection of innovation and impact, solving real-world problems with cutting-edge technology and bold thinking. Here, everyone has a voice, and every idea counts. If you’re ready to do the most meaningful work of your career alongside people who are just as passionate as you are, you’re in the right place.\n\nWho We Are\n\nIn order to be the cybersecurity partner of choice, we must trailblaze the path and shape the future of our industry. This is something our employees work at each day and is defined by our values: Disruption, Collaboration, Execution, Integrity, and Inclusion. We weave AI into the fabric of everything we do and use it to augment the impact every individual can have. If you are passionate about solving real-world problems and ideating beside the best and the brightest, we invite you to join us!\n\nWe believe collaboration thrives in person. That’s why most of our teams work from the office full time, with flexibility when it’s needed. This model supports real-time problem-solving, stronger relationships, and the kind of precision that drives great outcomes.\n\nJob Summary\n\nYour Career\n\nOur Unit 42 organization is one that’s dynamic, high energy and highly collaborative. If you have an inner entrepreneurial spirit, comfortable working in fast-paced environments and yearn for hands-on impact then this organization is the right one for you.\n\nYou will centre your role on relationship management to achieve measurable results in increased revenue, market share, and depth within each sales segment. Your success in this role will span the creation and execution of unique business plans in your region in partnership with other Palo Alto Networks Core sales organizations and channels. Your responsibilities will include finding and generating new customers, growing existing accounts and partnerships. You develop new accounts and/or expand existing accounts within an established geographic territory, industry, product segment or channel.\n\nYour Impact\n\nDirectly drives revenue impact by exceeding bookings goals of assigned partners and new initiatives\n\nIdentify, create, and implement a comprehensive account strategy to develop new business and drive expansion growth with enterprise customers across your territory, including channel partner\n\nScope, negotiate and close enterprise contracts to exceed all bookings and revenue targets\n\nEstablish access and create positive business relationships with key executives and senior-level decision-makers\n your knowledge of the cybersecurity industry, market landscape, technology, product, and processes to educate prospective and current customers on the business value of Unit 42’s offering and services\n\nCollaborate cross-functionally with key internal stakeholders (Field Sales, Marketing, Sales Operations, Product Management, Engineering, Pre/Post Sales, and Finance) to drive product adoption in target accounts\n\nDevelop relationships with select partners in your region to leverage their account presence and drive new growth and further penetration of Expanse’s solutions in the market\n\nMaintain accurate and up-to-date account intelligence in SFDC, including regular forecasting of business opportunities to Sales and executive leadership\n\nQualifications\n\nYour Experience\n\nExperience in Business Development and Sales roles within the cybersecurity industry\n\nTrack record exceeding your sales quota as a Major / Large Account Manager, Regional Sales Manager / Services Sales Manager/Channel Sales or Enterprise seller focused on F1000 accounts in high growth companies\n\nAt least 4 years of experience selling Enterprise Security solutions and services - SOC security-based products/services (such as Incident Response, Breach Management, Malware/Exploit Prevention, Anti-Virus, White Listing, SIEM, and other techniques) or SAS, Behavior Analytic or Logging tools - preferably Subscription or SaaS solutions as a direct contributor - Solutions related to Security Operations / SIEM / SOAR or adjacent solutions focused on Data / ML and automation preferred\n\nDeep understanding of channel partners and a channel-centric go to market approach in your region\n\nKnowledgeable in MEDDIC and Complex Solution Sales methodology and proven ability to sell complex enterprise software solutions to large and sophisticated enterprises at 6-figure transaction sizes and greater\n\nIn-depth knowledge of how specific industries might leverage security solutions and able to succinctly translate complex technical benefits to solve high leverage business problems - you can effectively articulate and present well in front of technical and executive-level stakeholders\n\nYou have a demonstrated passion for this space and you are excited about the prospect of scaling a new, emerging technology and accustomed to working in a fast-paced environment\n\nOur Commitment\n\nWe’re trailblazers that dream big, take risks, and challenge cybersecurity’s status quo. It’s simple: we can’t accomplish our mission without diverse teams innovating, together.\n\nWe are committed to providing reasonable accommodations for all qualified individuals with a disability. If you require assistance or accommodation due to a disability or special need, please contact us at accommodations@paloaltonetworks.com.\n\nPalo Alto Networks is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity in our workplace, and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or other legally protected characteristics.\n\nAll your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.\n\nIs role eligible for Immigration Sponsorship? No. Please note that we will not sponsor applicants for work visas for this position.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Palo Alto Networks','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=c8c7b9fee9ca4f3b','scraped','4 days ago'),(2698,NULL,'job','Senior Engineer','Full-time','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Create your best future and join Westpac as a Senior Engineer, where you’ll help deliver UNITE, our business led, technology enabled simplification program shaping how we serve customers and grow the bank.\n\nWhat’s the role?\n\nYou’ll join our Chief Technology Office as a Senior Engineer, building and supporting the technology that powers how our customers bank every day. This is a full time permanent role based in Sydney or Warrane on Gadigal Country, with a hybrid way of working that balances time in the office and at home.\n\nYou’ll design, build and improve customer servicing and origination solutions across online and staff facing channels. You won’t be handed a finished design. You’ll collaborate closely with architects, delivery leads, product owners and platform teams to shape solutions end to end.\n\nThis role suits engineers who enjoy working across technologies, owning outcomes in production environments and using modern tools including AI to accelerate delivery. From design and development through to support and optimisation, you’ll play a key role in delivering reliable, scalable solutions that create real value for customers.\n\nWhat do I need?\n\n• Strong core engineering skills with proficiency in at least two of Java or Kotlin using Spring Boot, TypeScript or JavaScript using React, or SQL, including hands on experience designing and building RESTful APIs using contract first approaches\n• Solid software engineering fundamentals applied in practice, including object oriented design, domain driven design, test driven development and infrastructure as code, alongside strong SQL and data modelling skills across MSSQL, Oracle and Postgres, with an understanding of batch and streaming data flows\n• Experience using AI tools to accelerate real engineering work, including code generation, automated code review, test scaffolding and prompt engineering as part of everyday delivery\n• A strong focus on developer experience and automation, with practical experience across DevOps and CI CD practices and modern engineering toolchains such as VS Code, IntelliJ, GitHub, Bitbucket, GitHub Actions, Jenkins or Bamboo\n• Proven ability to build and operate reliable systems at scale, communicate complex technical ideas clearly, and work across teams with a mindset of collective ownership\n\nWhy join us?\n\nWe’re obsessed with becoming our customers #1 banking partner for life and we’re looking for people who are passionate about helping us achieve that goal. In return we’re committed to making Westpac the best place to work in the country. Here are just a few of the ways we’re already doing that:\n\n• Special offers on banking products and discounts from top brands, including generous employee only mortgage rates\n• Flexible work arrangements to help you achieve a greater work life balance, and a variety of leave options including Culture, Lifestyle and Wellbeing leave\n• Tailored learning and development opportunities to help your grow your career within the bank\n• Lots of opportunities to give back to the Community by getting involved in our many volunteering initiatives\n\nCreate your future today\n\nTo get started, simply click on the APPLY or APPLY NOW button\n\nWe’re all about creating a supportive and inclusive community. We welcome everyone no matter your age, gender, background, or abilities. We also provide additional support to welcome our veterans, Indigenous Australians and neurodiverse community.\nIf you need any adjustments during the recruitment process, you can find more information and contact details on our FAQs and how to contact us page , under the ‘Diversity, sustainability and flexibility’ section.\n\n#UNITEprogram','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Westpac Group','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=a9094b2a1d6c7a34','scraped','4 days ago'),(2699,NULL,'job','Innovation & Commercial Analyst','Permanent','Brisbane QLD',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Make a real difference in veterans\' and their families\' lives through growth & transformation.\n\n29th April, 2026\n\nRSL Queensland is a dynamic, not-for-profit organisation delivering innovative programs and initiatives that support veterans and their families. A deeply engaged workforce with a culture where people feel connected, supported and genuinely proud to be part of the organisation.\n\nOur Growth & Transformation team drives new revenue opportunities and leads organisational transformation to ensure RSL Queensland remains sustainable, relevant and impactful. With an entrepreneurial mindset, we identify, validate and commercialise new opportunities that support our long‑term strategic goals.\n\nThe Innovation & Commercial Analyst will utilise research, financial modelling, AI‑enabled analysis, and turn complex data into clear, evidence‑based recommendations. The role will work across the full Innovation Lifecycle – from early discovery through to pilot evaluation – ensuring every opportunity is commercially viable, strategically aligned and decision‑ready.\nThis role reports to the Head of Innovation & Growth and as part of the Innovation & Growth team, key responsibilities include:\n\nUse AI‑enabled research platforms to accelerate discovery and generate strategic insights.\nDeliver sharp market research and competitor analysis.\nRun primary research to validate ideas fast.\nTurn complex data into clear, actionable insights.\nSupport initiatives across the full Innovation Lifecycle.\nBuild financial models and stress‑test assumptions.\nDevelop business cases with strong commercial logic.\nAnalyse costs, risks and benefits for new opportunities.\nKeep governance, documentation and stage‑gates tight.\nContribute to government and institutional tender work.\n About you:\n\nYou’re analytical, curious and commercially minded, with confidence navigating ambiguity.\nYou love solving complex problems, exploring new markets and using data to drive decisions.\nYou bring experience in commercial analysis, market research and business case development.\nYou have strong financial modelling skills and capability in Excel and PowerPoint.\nYou communicate clearly, collaborate well and present insights confidently to senior stakeholders.\n2+ years’ experience in commercial analysis, market research, business case development or tender support.\nTertiary qualification in Business, Economics, Finance, Analytics or related field.\nFor a complete outline of role accountabilities and essential qualifications and experience, refer to our position description. If this is an opportunity that speaks to you, we’d love to hear from you.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'RSL Queensland','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=54aadb6601d3299f','scraped','4 days ago'),(2700,NULL,'job','Payroll Officer','Casual','Sydney NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Overview\n\nThroughout our worldwide network of experts, clients and communities, we are renowned for our leadership in fire protection engineering – a legacy of responsibility we have proudly upheld since 1939. Today, our expertise extends broadly across closely related security and risk-based fields – from accessibility consulting and risk analysis to process safety, forensic investigations, security risk consulting, emergency management, digital innovation and more.\n\nOur engineers and consultants collaborate to solve complex safety and security challenges, ensuring our clients can protect what matters most. For over 80 years, we have helped mitigate risks that threaten lives, property and reputations. Through technology, expertise and industry-leading research, we remain dedicated to our purpose of making our world safe, secure and resilient.\n\nWhy you should grow your career at Jensen Hughes\n\nYou will work with market-leading clients and have the backing of a leading international firm.\nYou\'ll have support from the leadership team and given flexibility to work where and when you want.\nFlexible working arrangements and Casual Friday.\nRegular monthly social activities and other celebratory occasions.\nFive weeks annual leave and Company paid parental leave.\nCareer development and ongoing internal and external learning opportunities.\nPerks, benefits and reward platform - Perkbox.\nGreat company culture and benefits.\n\nJob Overview\n\nWe are looking for a Payroll Administrator to support our growing business across Australia. The purpose of this role is act as a partner to the business and provide support to help with operational growth. We are looking for someone to support the payroll and finance teams to enable a positive environment with all our colleagues.\n\nIn this role, you will work across a range of different activities:\n\nConducting payroll onboarding of new starters.\nSupporting the payroll team with queries.\nSupport end-to-end processing of fortnightly employee payroll data accurately and to deadline, using MYOB Acumatica.\nProcess, maintain and reconcile payroll records.\nSupport payroll reporting for management and team as required.\nSupport the creation of documented payroll processes.\nSupport with monthly payroll & superannuation reconciliation.\nProvide support to the finance team as required including but not limited to reconciliations and accounts payable integration activities\nProvide any additional ad hoc support directed by the Finance Manager\n\nRequirements And Qualifications\n\nMust be an Australian Citizen/Permanent Resident.\nExperience in Payroll processes within Australia.\nFamiliar with MYOB Acumatica or MYOB Advanced is essential.\nIntermediate skills in Excel\nFamiliar with Microsoft Word and Microsoft O365\nSomeone who loves collaborating with all stakeholders.\n\nJensen Hughes is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Qualified candidates will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability or protected veteran status.\n\nAt Jensen Hughes, we embrace innovation and understand that people are increasingly using artificial intelligence (AI) tools like ChatGPT and other generative platforms to learn, prepare and communicate. We have provided some guidelines regarding the responsible use of AI in the recruitment process. Please click here to review.\n\nThe security of your personal data is important to us. Jensen Hughes has implemented reasonable physical, technical, and administrative security standards to protect personal data from loss, misuse, alteration, or destruction. We protect your personal data against unauthorized access, use, or disclosure, using security technologies and procedures, such as encryption and limited access. Only authorized individuals may access your personal data for the purpose for which it was collected, and these individuals receive training about the importance of protecting personal data. Jensen Hughes is committed to compliance with all relevant data privacy laws in all areas where we do business, including, but not limited to, the GDPR and the CCPA. Additionally, our service providers are contractually bound to maintain the confidentiality of personal data and may not use the information for any unauthorized purpose.\n\n*Policy on use of 3rd party recruiting agency for direct placements\n\nJensen Hughes will occasionally augment a recruiting search through agencies for certain positions when business conditions warrant. Jensen Hughes will not accept resumes, inquiries or proposals from recruiting agencies as an acceptable method to consider a candidate. 3rd party recruiting agencies must sign a standard Jensen Hughes agreement after being evaluated and accepted by a Human Resources or Talent Acquisition manager, or member of the talent acquisition team. Hiring managers and employees of Jensen Hughes are not authorized to accept resumes, engage in fee-based searches through recruiting firms or sign a search agreement. Please note this policy does not apply to \"staffing firms\" or firms that are involved with hiring temporary staff. Any recruiting agency interested in being considered may contact our recruiting team at jensenhughesrecruiting.com.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Jensen Hughes','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=88c87c1c40fd115e','scraped','4 days ago'),(2701,NULL,'job','Developer - Government API\'s','','Melbourne VIC',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'We’re a leading business management solution with a core purpose: helping more businesses in Australia and New Zealand start, survive and succeed.\n\nAt MYOB, we believe what’s good for one business is good for all business—and for all of us. Whether you support them, work for them, or dream of building your own, when businesses run smoothly, everybody feels it. Owners, employees, customers, suppliers—even families. That’s why we’re here: to give every person in business the tools they need to focus on what really matters and do Big Things—whatever big looks like for them.\n\nAnd for you? Joining MYOB means being part of that impact. It means using your skills to help businesses thrive, shaping the future of work, and growing alongside the people and communities we support. Because while we’re the business of software, we’re really in the business of people. And that makes MYOB Everyone’s Business.\n\nWe\'re MYOB\n\nWe’re MYOB, a business management platform designed to unleash the potential of businesses across Australia and New Zealand! As the #originalstartup, our roots are in finance and accounting software, but today we are so much more. We help our Aussie and Kiwi customers unleash their full potential, giving them the tools to Start, Survive and Succeed: all in the one place.\n\nWe’re always on the hunt for those who bring a different perspective, diversity of thought and the drive to make our culture even better. Take your career to a new dimension at MYOB.\n\nOur Tech team are true heroes. They’ve taken our legacy success and transformed it into an extraordinary SaaS platform to support SME and Enterprise businesses in ways they never knew they needed. By joining the Tech team, you’ll be an integral part of building our all-in-one business management platform.\n\nAbout the role\n\nAs a full stack developer in Government API(GAPI) you will help design, build and maintain the APIs and services that enable MYOB products to integrate with government agencies such as the Australian Taxation Office (ATO) and New Zealand Inland Revenue (IRD). These APIs provide lodgement gateways for tax forms, Single Touch Payroll (STP), NZ Payday filing and business number lookup services, and must meet strict security, reliability and compliance standards. You\'ll join a highly dedicated team, committed to providing seamless and creative solutions that uphold the highest quality.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nDesign, build and maintain secure, compliant backend services and APIs within the GAPI domain, incorporating AU/NZ regulatory changes (ATO, IRD, STP/Payday).\nWrite clean, well‑tested code (unit, integration and contract tests) to protect critical API flows and minimise regressions.\nCollaborate with internal product teams and platform services to support GAPI integration, troubleshoot issues, and drive successful adoption.\nContribute to platform modernisation and migrations (e.g. .NET upgrades), working closely with developers and platform teams.\nSupport operational excellence through documentation, incident response, root‑cause analysis, CI/CD adherence, and auditable, compliant change delivery.\n\nSkills & Experience\n\nExperience developing and maintaining backend services and APIs (e.g. .NET), including REST/JSON and external system integrations.\nProficient in C# with hands-on experience in cloud environments and tooling (AWS/Azure).\nProven experience with database technologies such as MySQL, PostgreSQL and DynamoDB.\nFamiliar with Git, DevOps practices, CI/CD pipelines and Agile delivery methodologies.\nProven focus on test‑driven development, automated testing, observability and building reliable, production‑critical APIs.\nExcellent problem‑solving and communication skills, comfortable collaborating across teams, with exposure to AI tools such as GitHub Copilot and Cursor.\n\nOur Culture & Benefits\n\nOur values have stood the test of time. If you want to work and collaborate where opinions are valued, and your ideas can make a difference, come to a place where Your Work Matters.\n\nDo your best work in a flexible work environment, right down to financial assistance to set up your home office…it’s called Flexperience, and it’s designed by you and your team!\nOur partnership with Smiling Mind helps support the wellbeing of our team members and customers\nDrive your own learning via conferences, in-house training, LinkedIn Learning, study assistance and a strong focus on leaders creating a learning environment\nA multitude of leave options including up to an additional four weeks of purchased leave, generous parental leave, domestic violence leave, transgender leave, volunteer leave, study leave, plus more!\nCommunities built around ‘Wellness’, ‘Belonging’ and the ‘Planet’ where you can make a meaningful contribution\nAccess to best-in-class discounts and vouchers from leading retailers, and a lot more.\n\nMYOB are an equal opportunity employer and champion diversity. We are proud to be a Circle Back Initiative Employer and we commit to respond to every applicant. We’d love to hear from you regarding this role, or if it’s not the right time, join our talent community so that we can reach out regarding future roles.\n\nOur Culture & Benefits\nAt MYOB our values are at the heart of everything we do. If you want to work and collaborate where opinions are valued, and your ideas can make a difference, come to a place where Your Work Matters.\n\\uD83C\\uDFA5 See what it\'s like to work at MYOB and what we\'re all about.\n\n\\uD83D\\uDFE3Enjoy a flexible, hybrid workplace that brings balance to how you work, all of our centrally located offices come together for a number of in-person celebrations and social events\n\\uD83D\\uDFE3Set up your home office with a little financial help from us, and take advantage of great corporate discounts and vouchers from top retailers\n\\uD83D\\uDFE3Benefit from our partnership with Sonder, which supports the wellbeing of our team members\n\\uD83D\\uDFE3Unlock your potential via in-house training and programs, LinkedIn Learning, conferences and study assistance\n\\uD83D\\uDFE3Access to a variety of leave options available to support your wellbeing, including up to an additional four weeks of purchased leave, generous parental leave, domestic violence leave, transgender leave, community leave, study leave, and more\n\\uD83D\\uDFE3Join our communities, built around ‘Wellness’, ‘Belonging’ and the ‘Planet’ where you can make a meaningful contribution\n\nAt MYOB, we’re all about embracing difference and backing people to be their true selves. We’re proud to be an equal opportunity employer and big believers that the best hires don’t just fit our culture — they add to it. That means bringing your unique contributions, lived experiences, and fresh perspective to the table.\n\nLove the sound of MYOB and this role but don’t tick every single box in this ad? Apply anyway! Studies show that women and underrepresented groups often hold back if they don’t meet every requirement — but we want to hear from you.\n\nWe’re proud to be a Circle Back Initiative Employer and we commit to responding to every applicant.\n\nWe may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'MYOB','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8552f2e170defd57','scraped','4 days ago'),(2702,NULL,'job','OSHC Educator | Leschenault (Qualified & Unqualified)','Part-time','Leschenault WA 6233',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'Company Description\n\nPartnering with parents and school communities, at Junior Adventures Group (JAG) our goal is to help today\'s children navigate their tomorrow by supporting children\'s development through play in fun, engaging environments. We live and breathe our company values every day by being considerate, passionate, courageous, and making a difference.\n\nJob Description\n\nOur OSHC service Leschenault OSHClub is looking for a dedicated Qualified & Unqualified Educator to join our team in delivering fun and engaging programs for primary school children. This permanent part-time role guarantees a minimum of 12 hours per week, with opportunities for extra hours during the school holidays.\n\nWhy JAG?\n\nEmployee Referral Rewards – Earn up to $1,000 cash for each successful referral—share the opportunity and get rewarded.\n\nGenerous childcare savings – Access 50% off childcare fees in addition to government subsidies\n\nExtra earning power – We’re approved for the ECEC Grant, giving you an additional boost.\n\nAccelerated career growth – Gain access to ongoing professional development, tailored leadership training, and dedicated mentorship to help you excel and advance confidently.\n\nGuaranteed interview – When you apply, we’ll fast-track you straight to an interview—no waiting, no wondering.\n\nAbout the Role\n\nWorking alongside a supportive team, you’ll help create a welcoming and enriching environment for children aged 5-12 years old. Your role will include:\n\nFacilitating exciting, child-led activities, including STEM, sports, cooking, arts & crafts – whatever you and the kids love!\n\nBuilding strong relationships with children, families, and the school community\n\nCollaborating with a team of skilled Educators to ensure a safe, fun, and engaging program\n\nYou\'ll work split shifts Monday – Friday across the services opening hours of:\n\nMorning: 6:30am – 8:45am (Rise then Shine Program)\nAfternoon: 2:45pm – 6:00pm (Stay and Play Program)\nSchool Holidays: 6:00am – 6:00pm (Holiday HQ Program)\n\nQualifications\n\nWho We’re Looking For\n\nNo formal experience? No problem! We’ll provide all the training you need. We’re looking for someone who:\n✔️ Enjoys working with children and making a positive impact\n✔️ Communicates clearly and confidently\n✔️ Works well in a team and aspires to grow into a leadership role\n✔️ Holds (or is willing to obtain) a National Police Check and a Working with Children check\n\n✔️National Child Safety Training completion prior to onboarding\n\n✔️ Has Australian work rights\n\nIf you’re looking for a rewarding role where you can have fun while making a difference, we’d love to hear from you. Apply today and start your journey with Junior Adventures Group!\n\nAdditional Information\n\nNext Steps?\n We do things a bit differently here at JAG. After submitting your application, you’ll be invited to complete a quick 10-15 min chat-based interview. It’s part of our innovative and cutting-edge process to find the best people to work with us at JAG. It also gives you a chance to showcase your superior talents that aren’t easily captured on paper. Once you complete, we can move you through to the next stage. Since it’s such a valuable tool for career development, we will send you an overview of the results for your own benefit.\n\n Click ‘Apply’ and start your AI-powered chat today!\n\nAt Junior Adventures Group, child safety and child safeguarding principles are our top priorities. Our recruitment process includes thorough background checks and screenings to ensure the wellbeing of all children in our care.\n\nWe welcome individuals from all backgrounds, abilities, and identities, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people.','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'OSH Club','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=ebe2a4ff7bd2be7f','scraped','4 days ago'),(2703,NULL,'job','Senior Technical Support Engineer, Observe by Snowflake','','Barangaroo NSW',NULL,'',0.00,NULL,'At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn\'t just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nObserve by Snowflake is an AI-powered observability platform built on the Snowflake AI Data Cloud and engineered for scale. We ingest and store logs, metrics, traces, and events on an open, scalable data lakehouse, using open formats like Apache Iceberg, at dramatically lower cost. A dynamic Context Graph and chat-based AI SRE provide rich context and automated workflows so teams can move from detection to root cause of production issue and resolution 10x faster.\n\nLeading engineering teams at companies like Capital One, Topgolf, and Dialpad rely on Observe to troubleshoot hundreds of terabytes of telemetry daily while maintaining reliability at enterprise scale. As part of Snowflake, Observe combines startup-style ownership and velocity with the global reach, operational excellence, and ecosystem of one of the world’s leading data platforms.\n\nAs a Senior Technical Support Engineer, you will be a trusted advisor and technical resource for our customers in the APAC region. This is a hands-on role for someone who thrives in dynamic environments, loves troubleshooting complex technical issues, and is passionate about delivering exceptional support experiences.\n\nYou’ll be responsible for resolving high-impact technical issues, driving customer success, and collaborating closely with product, engineering, and customer success teams. This is an opportunity to shape how support is delivered and to contribute to the evolution of our platform and processes.\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES\n\nDeliver expert-level technical support to customers through phone, email, and chat.\n\nTroubleshoot and resolve complex technical issues involving our observability platform, integrations, and customer environments.\n\nPartner with engineering teams responsible for performance to become the subject matter expert on performance issues related to components like dashboards, monitors, and datasets. Lead initiatives to improve performance and educate engineering, technical support, and sales engineering teams on best practices.\n\nHelp to design and build AI skills that increase technical support engineering productivity, quality and speed.\n\nOwn and manage high-priority escalations, coordinating with engineering and product teams to drive resolution.\n\nCreate and maintain high-quality technical documentation, including knowledge base articles and runbooks.\n\nAct as a technical liaison between customers and internal teams, translating customer feedback into actionable product insights.\n\nParticipate in the on-call rotation to support urgent customer issues outside normal hours.\n\nProactively contribute to process improvement, tooling, and support automation initiatives.\n\nMentor junior support engineers and help level up the broader team through knowledge sharing.\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\nTechnical Expertise\n\nBachelor\'s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related technical field.\n\n5+ years in a technical support or customer-facing engineering role, ideally in a SaaS, DevOps, or observability-focused environment.\n\nDeep familiarity with operating systems (Linux, Unix, macOS, and Windows) and modern networking concepts.\n\nProficient in scripting languages such as Python or Bash.\n\nExperience with cloud platforms like AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud Platform.\n\nWorking knowledge of Kubernetes; particularly in troubleshooting, scaling, and deployment contexts.\n\nStrong diagnostic and debugging skills across complex distributed systems.\n\nSOFT SKILLS\n\nExceptional problem-solving skills and a methodical, customer-first approach to issue resolution.\n\nClear, concise communicator able to translate complex technical topics for non-technical audiences.\n\nCalm under pressure, with the ability to multitask and prioritize in high-stakes situations.\n\nCollaborative mindset, with a track record of building strong working relationships across functions.\n\nDemonstrated leadership potential, including the ability and drive to lead a team, mentor colleagues, and autonomously manage initiatives.\n\nBONUS POINTS\n\nExperience with observability/monitoring tools such as Prometheus, Grafana, Jaeger, Loki, or similar platforms.\n\nProficiency with OpenTelemetry (OTEL), configuring and troubleshooting for distributed tracing, metrics, and logging.\n\nExperience using Terraform to deploy infrastructure preferably in combination with CI/CD tools such as Github Actions or Jenkins.\n\nHands-on experience with Kubernetes clusters, including Helm, CNI, CSI, kubectl, and k9s.\n\nExposure to modern data storage and retrieval systems including SQL, NoSQL, and data warehousing technologies.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com','2026-05-07 01:37:32','open',0,'Snowflake','https://au.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=582e3090f9bb0324','scraped','4 days ago'),(2704,NULL,'job','Software Development Engineer in Test','Full Time/Permanent','Lahore',NULL,'3 Years',375000.00,'Rs. 300,000 - 450,000','The Division: Jonas Premier Construction - a division of Constellation Software Inc. ᅡᆲ ̄ツ﾿ ̄テᄁ is the market-leading cloud-based integrated construction management solution, for mid-sized General Contractors, Design Builders and Land Developers. Constellation companies are leading developers of technology solutions for vertical markets in North America, Europe, and Australia. Jonas Software is the valued technology partner of over 8000 customers worldwide in 15 countries. Jonas is headquartered in Canada and operates offices in the United States, the United Kingdom, and the Caribbean. The Position: We are looking to hire a Software Development Engineer in Test (SDET) , with a strong background in Test Automation (using Selenium, C# & NUnit), as well as in Manual Testing , to work as part of the JPC R&D team to help ensure high quality and timely delivery of releases. Working out of the Contour Software Lahore office, the successful hire will collaborate with team members in the same office and those in Markham, Canada. Qualifications & Skills: University degree in Computer Science or a related discipline 3-7 years of formal QA/Test Automation experience, working on customer-facing enterprise-level software solutions Strong background in Test Automation using Selenium, Visual Studio/C# & NUnit Extensive background in Test Documentation and Manual Testing Ability to create Test Automation frameworks Excellent command of English (written and verbal) Experience working with Azure DevOps or Jenkins for creating pipelines Experience with Microsoft SQL Server and/or Oracle with the ability to write complex SQL statements. Strong familiarity with software lifecycle and quality assurance concepts, testing, approaches, and planning Strong ability to understand business processes and logic Ability to perform comfortably in a fast-paced, deadline-oriented agile work environment Familiarity with the Construction Industry will be a plus Responsibilities (not limited to the following): Collaborate with testers, developers to create detailed, comprehensive, and well-structured test plans and test cases Grow, Maintain and Enhance existing Test Automation Framework and Test Scripts to increase/extend automation coverage Execute tests manually when required Review requirements specifications and technical design documents to provide timely and meaningful feedback Estimate, prioritize, plan, and coordinate testing activities Design, develop and execute automation scripts on different releases/versions Create concise, easily understandable defect reports Coordinate/participate in meetings with the on-shore team on day to day basis and provide active feedback Perform any other responsibilities assigned by the on-shore Managers Exciting Benefits we offer: Market-leading Salary Medical Coverage ᅡᆲ ̄ツ﾿ ̄テᄁ Self & Dependents Parents Medical Coverage Provident Fund Employee Performance-based bonuses Home Internet Subsidy Conveyance Allowance Profit Sharing Plan [Tenured Employees Only] Life Benefit Child Care Facility Company Provided Lunch/Dinner Professional Development Budget Recreational area for in-house games Sporadic On-shore training opportunities Friendly work environment Leave Encashment','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Contour Software','https://www.rozee.pk/contour-software-software-development-engineer-in-test-jobs-1490930.php','scraped','May 08, 2024'),(2705,NULL,'job','Network Engineer','Full Time/Permanent','Karachi',NULL,'3 Years',425000.00,'Rs. 400,000 - 450,000','SUMMARY Constellation Software&#39;s rapidly growing Perseus Operating Group (CSI) has an outstanding opportunity for an experienced Network Engineer to help support the day-to-day operations, network security and design, and fielding of incidents as they come in, while adapting security standards and governance to the real-world challenges of a large-scale, multi-location, multi-business and multi-cultural environment. The Position The Network Engineer is responsible for ensuring network connectivity and security. This position will provide on-going technical service in network support, circuit support, routing support, security monitoring, routing and switching, VLAN support and infrastructure design for the Perseus Operating Group business needs. JOB DUTIES &amp; RESPONSIBILITIES Network Maintenance: Create and maintain operational procedures and systems documentation for processes, networks, systems, and software. Install and maintain network devices including firewalls, switches, wireless access points, SD-WAN, routers, circuits, gateways, etc. Install server hardware and server-related peripheral devices. Install and use network and server analysis and performance tools to improve overall reliability and throughput. Participate in the design and review of new network environments and patching of these environments. Evaluate, recommend, and implement new products to extend the reliability, responsiveness, and effective use of the network environment. Security: Assist in overall management of the firewalls, switches, circuits, and routing of the corporate wide area network. Ensure high availability and performance of security and network environment. Strong demonstrated knowledge on perimeter security like IDS/IPS, firewalls, web proxies, etc. Extensive experience with VPN/IPSEC tunnels, both site-to-site and client-based. Support: Responsible for resolving any technical issues the business units may encounter in their normal course of business as a result of Constellation&#39;s WAN and LAN environments. Troubleshoot and resolve hardware and software problems. Provide third-tier network support for the various businesses. Daily recording and submitting of accurate timecards. Adjust work schedule to accommodate business needs. Other duties and projects as required by the company. REQUIRED EXPERIENCE B.S. degree in IT / CS / EE or equivalent with 3 years working experience maintaining a wide area network Strong knowledge of network engineering. Possess basic project management skills Excellent English communication skills are essential. Must be able to give and receive correct information, explain difficult information in layman&#39;s terms and maintain a customer service attitude to all levels of users. Experience working in Active Directory, including security groups and overall AD structure knowledge Packet Capturing OSI Model Understanding Experience Configuring Network Infrastructure Hardware (Switches, Routers, Load Balancers) Experience Deploying and Configuring Network Security Appliances (Firewalls, IPS&#39;s, Application Layer Gateways) Solid understanding of networking technologies and protocols (IP, TCP, UDP, VLANS, OSPF, BGP, Static Routing, DNS) Strong demonstrated knowledge on perimeter security like IDS/IPS, Firewalls, Web Proxies, etc. Extensive experience with VPN/IPSEC tunnels, both site-to-site and client-based Experience supporting and troubleshooting routing issues, security rules, NAT, PAT, QOS, SSL decryption, URL filtering, threat detection, intrusion detection Experience supporting and troubleshooting Wireless networks Experience supporting and troubleshooting VOIP Experience supporting and troubleshooting QOS Experience supporting and troubleshooting VLANing, Spanning Tree, Guard Root, Trunking Experienced with hardware builds, rack-mounting configuration and deployment PREFERRED EXPERIENCE 3+ years engineering experience or equivalent industry knowledge Experience supporting and troubleshooting Palo Alto Networks Experience administrating, supporting and maintaining Solarwinds Palo Alto, CCNA, Aruba, ClearPass, Dell certifications desirable Experience supporting and troubleshooting IP networking including firewalls, IP routing, IPSEC VPNs, MPLS, SDWAN and Wireless Experience supporting and troubleshooting some or all of the following: Palo Alto, Cisco, Dell, Client/Aruba switch hardware, Aruba Wireless, ClearPass Supporting and implementing a Wide Area Network with over 90+ locations Azure, AWS, Google, or other cloud experience Scripting skills (BASH, Python, Powershell) a plus ADDITIONAL QUALIFICATIONS Ability to work 8:00am-5:00pm ET time zone Perform 24x7 advanced tier troubleshooting, including off-hour maintenance activities, problem resolution, and on-call troubleshooting efforts during data network outages Must be able to sit at a computer workstation for extended time periods and fully utilize the PC monitor, keyboard, mouse, and required programs. Able to present ideas in business-friendly and user-friendly language Possess strong interpersonal and communication skills Capable of writing documentation Possess a keen attention to detail Strong customer service orientation Proven analytical and problem-solving abilities Highly self-motivated and directed Ability to effectively prioritize and execute tasks in a high-pressure environment Experience working in a process-oriented, collaborative environment Exciting Benefits we offer: Market-leading Salary Medical Coverage &ndash; Self &amp; Dependents Parents Medical Coverage Provident Fund Employee Performance-based bonuses Home Internet Subsidy Conveyance Allowance Profit Sharing Plan [Tenured Employees Only] Life Benefit Child Care Facility Company Provided Lunch/Dinner Professional Development Budget Recreational area for in-house games Sporadic On-shore training opportunities Friendly work environment Leave Encashment','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Contour Software','https://www.rozee.pk/contour-software-network-engineer-jobs-1542168.php','scraped','Oct 29, 2024'),(2706,NULL,'job','DevOps Engineer','Full Time/Permanent','Karachi',NULL,'3 Years',175000.00,'Rs. 150,000 - 200,000','Job Role: We are looking for additional help on our technical team to monitor and maintain internal and customer systems. Additionally, interaction with our internal staff solving user issues on a daily basis may be a significant part of this position. The role also calls for someone who can be available on a weekend day to install security updates once or twice a month. This will generally be a full time position working UK (GMT/BST) hours with the exception of weekend day that would be traded (i.e. one or two weeks of a month they might work Saturday and have Friday off or something similar). They will also be responsible for assisting in installing security updates in Docker container images and other maintenance tasks. Required Skills and Experience: Proven experience in infrastructure engineering with a strong emphasis on Linux and AWS Cloud. Solid understanding of DevOps principles and practices, including experience with CI/CD tools (e.g., Jenkins, GitLab CI). Proficiency in scripting languages (e.g., Python, Bash) for automation tasks. Strong troubleshooting skills and the ability to resolve complex technical issues. Excellent documentation skills with a keen attention to detail. Experience with monitoring and logging tools (e.g., Prometheus, Grafana, ELK stack). Familiarity with networking concepts and security best practices. Strong customer service orientation and the ability to support end users effectively. Ability to work independently as well as part of a team. Proactive mindset and propose innovative solutions when necessary Familiarity with Microsoft Windows Server, Windows 10/11, Active Directory management Desirable Qualifications: Relevant certifications (e.g., AWS Certified Solutions Architect, Certified Kubernetes Administrator) are advantageous. Experience with containerisation and orchestration tools (e.g., Docker, Kubernetes). Knowledge of infrastructure as code (IaC) tools (e.g., Terraform, Ansible). Knowledge of Google Workspace administration Knowledge of Azure AD / Entra and Microsoft 365 environments. Exciting Benefits we offer: Market-leading Salary Medical Coverage – Self & Dependents Parents Medical Coverage Provident Fund Employee Performance-based bonuses Home Internet Subsidy Conveyance Allowance Profit Sharing Plan [Tenured Employees Only] Life Benefit Child Care Facility Company Provided Lunch/Dinner Professional Development Budget Recreational area for in-house games Sporadic On-shore training opportunities Friendly work environment Leave Encashment','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Contour Software','https://www.rozee.pk/contour-software-devops-engineer-jobs-1542112.php','scraped','Oct 29, 2024'),(2707,NULL,'job','Azure Software Engineer (Dynamics 365)','Full Time/Permanent','Multiple Cities',NULL,'5 Years',350000.00,'Rs. 300,000 - 400,000','The Division Dot.cy - We are a global leading provider of world-class software solutions, built on the powerful ecosystem of Microsoft Dynamics 365. Since our foundation in 1999, we have served more than 200 clients in their digital transformation, improving their processes, products, and customer experiences. The Position: We are looking for Azure Software Engineer who will participate in the development of our product dot.Hospitality ( www.dothospitality.com ). This position will entail working together with the rest of the development team of dot.Hospitality which is distributed in Cyprus, Greece, and UAE. The chosen individual will work out of the Contour Software Karachi/Lahore/Islamabad resource center office, as an extension of the division-based R&D department. Roles and Responsibilities: Develop Azure resources using Azure SDK\'s, .NET and C#. Design and develop CI/CD components using Azure DevOps Pipelines. Drive the effort to establish C# code libraries using the latest .Net, Microsoft and Web technologies effectively. Provide front-end development capabilities using known JavaScript Frameworks. Extend Dynamics 365/CRM platform using MS Dynamics SDK and .Net Framework. Follow Microsoft development standards and best practices. Integrate Dynamics 365 Customer Engagement with other systems and applications. Design and develop robust, scalable, high performing, high-volume production applications with users across the globe. Recommend innovative solutions that will support improved business processes. Perform unit testing, integration testing prior to deploying into production. Required Skills: 5+ years in Azure, C#, .NET, and Dynamics 365 (ideally in combination)Dynamics 365 (cloud and online) on a strong, confident level. Technical knowledge of deployments using Azure DevOps Pipelines. Knowledge of JavaScript Frameworks for front end development. Ability to troubleshoot, test, repair, and service technical equipment Ability to work independently, planning the workflow accurately. Ability to work flexible shifts and to adapt to changing work schedules. Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills. Good English knowledge, written and oral. Exciting Benefits we offer: Market-leading Salary Medical Coverage – Self & Dependents Parents Medical Coverage Provident Fund Employee Performance-based bonuses Home Internet Subsidy Conveyance Allowance Profit Sharing Plan [Tenured Employees Only] Life Benefit Child Care Facility Company Provided Lunch/Dinner Professional Development Budget Recreational area for in-house games Sporadic On-shore training opportunities Friendly work environment Leave Encashment','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Contour Software','https://www.rozee.pk/contour-software-azure-software-engineer-dynamics-365-jobs-1534848.php','scraped','Oct 06, 2024'),(2708,NULL,'job','Software Quality Assurance Engineer','Full Time/Permanent','Lahore',NULL,'Fresh',300000.00,'PKR 300,000','Infotech is seeking a dedicated Software Quality Assurance Engineer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate is a sharp and quick learner with a strong foundation in software QA methodologies, tools, and processes. This role requires a deep understanding of quality assurance principles, hands-on experience writing complex SQL queries and test scripts, and familiarity with key frameworks such as CMMI. The candidate will play a pivotal part in ensuring the quality and reliability of our software products by executing thorough testing, including load, stress, and security testing. A strong grasp of TCP/IP protocol stack, web technologies, and secure API testing is essential to excel in this position. Experience with test automation tools and test management platforms like JIRA is highly valued. Excellent verbal and written communication skills, together with sharp analytical abilities and keen observational skills, are crucial to successfully identify issues and improve product quality. This position does not involve managing a team but offers an excellent opportunity for professional growth within a highly skilled QA environment. Responsibilities Develop, execute, and maintain complex test scripts and SQL queries to validate software functionality and performance. Apply comprehensive knowledge of software QA methodologies, industry best practices, and company standards to enhance testing processes. Use test management tools such as JIRA or Quality Center to document test cases, manage defects, and track testing progress efficiently. Perform manual and automated testing, utilizing tools such as JMeter, QTP, Silk Test, and Selenium to ensure software stability under various conditions. Conduct load, stress, and security testing to assess application resilience, identify bottlenecks, and detect potential vulnerabilities. Evaluate web and web technologies in-depth, understanding the TCP/IP protocol stack to troubleshoot and analyze software behavior effectively. Test secure APIs rigorously to ensure data integrity and security compliance across integrations. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand product requirements and translate them into detailed test plans and test cases. Apply knowledge of CMMI framework to align testing practices with organizational quality goals and continuous improvement initiatives. Analyze testing outcomes critically and document findings across all software releases, providing actionable feedback to development teams. Employ keen observation and analytical skills to detect subtle defects and inconsistencies, ensuring comprehensive coverage and high-quality deliverables. Stay current with emerging QA trends, tools, and technologies to continuously improve testing effectiveness and efficiency. Participate actively in review meetings and contribute to improving the QA strategy, ensuring that all quality standards are consistently met. Leverage prior experience with stock market trading systems where applicable to understand domain-specific requirements and risks. Communicate clearly and professionally in verbal and written forms, facilitating smooth information flow throughout the project lifecycle.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Infotech','https://www.rozee.pk/infotech-software-quality-assurance-engineer-jobs-1833578','scraped','Mar 30, 2026'),(2709,NULL,'job','Senior Software Engineer','First Shift (Day)','Lahore',NULL,'2 Years',0.00,NULL,'Conrad Labs is a dynamic software technology company with offices in Lahore, Karachi, and Austin, Texas. Our team is composed of passionate professionals dedicated to solving complex problems through cutting-edge technologies. We focus on creating innovative products that deliver tangible real-world benefits, with significant expertise in cloud infrastructure management, healthcare solutions, and AI/ML-driven training and education platforms. Key Responsibilities - Design, develop, and maintain scalable software solutions aligned with company goals. - Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define, design, and ship new features. - Troubleshoot, debug, and optimize existing applications to improve performance and reliability. - Participate in code reviews and contribute to continuous improvement of development processes. - Stay updated with emerging technologies and integrate them into projects where applicable. - Ensure software quality through comprehensive testing and documentation. Required Qualifications - Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field. - Proven experience in software development with proficiency in relevant programming languages and frameworks. - Strong understanding of cloud infrastructure and services. - Experience working with AI/ML technologies or healthcare-related software is a plus. - Ability to work effectively in a collaborative team environment. - Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail. Preferred Qualifications and Benefits - Advanced degree or certifications in software development, cloud computing, or AI/ML. - Prior experience in a fast-paced startup or technology-driven environment. - Opportunities for professional growth and skill development. - Collaborative culture that encourages innovation and creativity. - Competitive compensation and benefits package. Join Conrad Labs to be part of a forward-thinking team that values innovation and impact, working on projects that shape the future of technology across multiple industries.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Naseeb Enterprise Inc','https://www.rozee.pk/senior-software-engineer-lahore-jobs-1838042','scraped','Apr 10, 2026'),(2710,NULL,'job','Senior Cloud Engineer','Full Time/Permanent','Multiple Cities',NULL,'5 Years',215000.00,'Rs. 180,000 - 250,000','THE DIVISION: Constellation1 , a division of Perseus (an operating group of Constellation Software Inc.) is the leading provider of truly integrated technology, media and data solutions to real estate franchisors, brokerages, agents and MLS organizations and associations. We\'re clear about what we want to do: Innovate in real estate. Not in pursuit of some larger business strategy, but in pursuit of making this industry – our industry – better. We don\'t just sell technology. We work closely with clients and partners to identify problems, develop solutions and uncover opportunities. THE POSITION: A Senior Cloud Engineer is responsible for helping to architect, design, and implement key features and components in our AWS mission-critical platform by building micro-services and designing serverless applications in AWS to support our real estate data business. From a technical perspective, this role requires working with many of the major AWS offerings including services, such as Lambda, Step Functions, Kinesis, Dynamo, Redshift, Scaling EC2 and CloudWatc h as examples. An understanding of Serverless design patterns and how and when to implement auto-scaling to ensure optimal throughput is essential. Aside from the architecture and design, a Sr. Cloud Engineer must be an AWS cloud evangelist who loves teaching, mentoring and growing the talent around him/her. A team leader who enjoys making the team around him or her better. Leads by example. Lastly, at times this role will require someone to lead a project and small team for the sake of building or enhancing a particular product or feature. This means working on a new project from initiation, design, architecture, planning, estimating, tracking and helping others on the team see the vision and develop in unison as a cohesive team that delivers incremental customer usable features on-time. JOB RESPONSIBILITIES: Help oversee architecture of real estate data pipeline. Develop pipeline components that are scalable, reliable and efficient. Continual oversight of the overall architecture ensuring the overall system doesn\'t erode or become overly complex as time passes and features are added. Perform Project and Team lead duties as needed for new core features. Code reviews, mentoring and coaching teammates to understand and implement AWS best practices in line with an &quot;AWS Well-Architected Framework” . Provide feedback and constructive critiques resulting in optimum performance and system design . Continual tracking of component and overall system performance by applying and automating application and performance best practice testing, monitoring and reporting. P rovide input and recommendations on managing costs within our AWS infrastructure at micro and macro levels. JOB QUALIFICATIONS We are seeking a Sr. Cloud Engineer that has familiarity with AWS Serverless architectures and has 4+ years of systems engineering/administration experience with Elastic Search. Candidate must have experience which demonstrates an understanding software design as it relates to Elasticsearch or OpenSearch deployments, indexing and querying. Estimated 50/50 split between general AWS and Elastic Search development. 5+ years of professional coding experience with 3+ years in cloud services. Experience in major AWS event-driven, compute and database solutions, including but not limited to: Lambda, OpenSearch, Step Functions, SQS, Dynamo, Aurora and/or RDS (candidates with experience in both NoSQL and relational are preferred) C#/.Net Framework experience preferred. Understanding of developing microservices in AWS. Understanding of CI/CD principles. 4+ years of experience with Elastic Stack cluster architecture, design and deployment. 2+ years of working with and understanding software design as it relates to Elasticsearch deployments or distributed computing / system architecture. Reporting and alerting tools such as Grafana, Kibana, Cloudwatch, Quicksight etc. Exciting Benefits we offer: Market-leading Salary Medical Coverage – Self & Dependents Parents Medical Coverage Provident Fund Employee Performance-based bonuses Home Internet Subsidy Conveyance Allowance Profit Sharing Plan [Tenured Employees Only] Life Benefit Child Care Facility Company Provided Lunch/Dinner Professional Development Budget Recreational area for in-house games Sporadic On-shore training opportunities Friendly work environment Leave Encashment','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Contour Software','https://www.rozee.pk/contour-software-senior-cloud-engineer-jobs-1542272.php','scraped','Oct 29, 2024'),(2711,NULL,'job','Software Quality Assurance Engineer','Full Time/Permanent','Lahore',NULL,'5 Years',55000.00,'PKR 55,000','Bytepeach is seeking an experienced Software Quality Assurance (SQA) Engineer with a minimum of five years of experience to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate excels in test automation and agile testing methodologies, ensuring the delivery of high-quality software products. This role involves hands-on testing activities and close collaboration with the development team to identify defects early and improve software performance. Although this position does not involve managing a team, the SQA Engineer will take ownership of the quality assurance processes and contribute to enhancing testing strategies. Responsibilities Develop and execute automated test scripts to validate software functionality and performance according to specifications. Design and implement testing frameworks that support agile development practices and continuous integration pipelines. Collaborate closely with developers, product managers, and other stakeholders to understand requirements and provide timely feedback on product quality. Identify, document, and track software defects and work with development teams to ensure timely resolution. Participate actively in sprint planning, daily stand-ups, and retrospectives to align testing efforts with project goals. Analyze test results, generate detailed test reports, and recommend improvements for software quality and testing processes. Maintain and update existing automation scripts to accommodate new features and changing requirements. Ensure adherence to organizational quality standards and advocate for best practices in testing and quality assurance. Contribute to continuous process improvement initiatives by sharing insights gained from testing activities. Support the evaluation and adoption of new testing tools and technologies to enhance test coverage and efficiency.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Bytepeach','https://www.rozee.pk/bytepeach-software-quality-assurance-engineer-lahore-jobs-1841920','scraped','Apr 19, 2026'),(2712,NULL,'job','Senior Java Software Engineer','First Shift (Day)','All Cities',NULL,'2 Years',0.00,NULL,'We are seeking a skilled web application developer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will be responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining high-quality web applications while collaborating closely with team members throughout the entire software development lifecycle. This role requires a detail-oriented professional who can contribute to project planning, execute effective unit testing, and ensure timely delivery of solutions that meet business requirements. Key Responsibilities - Develop and maintain robust web applications that align with project specifications and user needs. - Create and execute comprehensive unit tests to ensure code quality and functionality. - Collaborate with the team leader to accurately estimate project timelines and deliverables. - Actively participate in all phases of the software development lifecycle, including requirements gathering, architecture design, coding, testing, and deployment. - Work closely with cross-functional teams to troubleshoot and resolve software defects and performance issues. - Continuously improve application performance and user experience through iterative development and feedback incorporation. Required Qualifications - Proven experience in web application development with a strong understanding of front-end and back-end technologies. - Proficiency in writing effective unit tests to validate code functionality. - Ability to work collaboratively within a team environment and communicate effectively with stakeholders. - Solid understanding of the software development lifecycle and agile methodologies. - Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail. - Experience in estimating project timelines and managing deliverables alongside team leaders. Preferred Qualifications and Benefits - Familiarity with modern web frameworks and tools that enhance development efficiency. - Experience with deployment processes and continuous integration/continuous deployment (CI/CD) pipelines. - Opportunities for professional growth and skill development within a supportive team environment. - Competitive compensation and benefits package tailored to attract and retain top talent. This position offers the chance to contribute to meaningful projects in a collaborative setting, where innovation and quality are highly valued. If you are passionate about web development and eager to take on new challenges, we encourage you to apply.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Naseeb Enterprise Inc','https://www.rozee.pk/senior-java-software-engineer-jobs-1835426','scraped','Apr 03, 2026'),(2713,NULL,'job','Software Engineer Internal Systems','First Shift (Day)','All Cities',NULL,'2 Years',0.00,NULL,'BAJO Digital Ventures is partnering with a US-based venture capital fund-of-funds to recruit a talented professional to join their team. This firm manages a diverse portfolio that includes multiple fund families and co-investment vehicles, primarily focused on early-stage technology investments. The team, consisting of approximately 20 members, operates with a technology-first approach, developing proprietary internal systems that enhance the sourcing, analysis, and management of investments. This role offers a unique opportunity to work in a dynamic environment that blends venture capital expertise with innovative technology solutions. Key Responsibilities - Support the investment team in sourcing and evaluating early-stage technology fund opportunities and co-investments. - Conduct thorough due diligence, including market research, financial analysis, and competitive landscape assessments. - Assist in the development and maintenance of proprietary tools and systems to improve investment processes. - Collaborate closely with portfolio companies and fund managers to monitor performance and provide ongoing support. - Prepare detailed investment memos, presentations, and reports for internal and external stakeholders. - Track industry trends and emerging technologies to inform investment strategies. - Participate in meetings with fund managers, entrepreneurs, and other key stakeholders to gather insights and build relationships. Required Qualifications - Bachelor’s degree in Finance, Business, Economics, or a related field. - Strong analytical skills with experience in financial modeling and data analysis. - Familiarity with venture capital, private equity, or investment management is essential. - Proficiency in using technology tools and platforms to support investment activities. - Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to present complex information clearly. - Detail-oriented with strong organizational skills and the ability to manage multiple tasks simultaneously. - Demonstrated ability to work effectively both independently and as part of a collaborative team. Preferred Qualifications and Benefits - Advanced degree such as an MBA or relevant certifications (e.g., CFA) is a plus. - Prior experience working within a venture capital fund-of-funds or in early-stage technology investing. - Exposure to building or working with proprietary investment systems or software. - Opportunity to work in a forward-thinking, technology-driven environment that values innovation. - Collaborative culture with a small, focused team dedicated to leveraging technology for competitive advantage. - Potential for professional growth and development within a fast-paced venture capital setting. This position is ideal for candidates passionate about venture capital and technology, eager to contribute to a firm that combines deep industry knowledge with cutting-edge technological tools to drive investment success.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Naseeb Enterprise Inc','https://www.rozee.pk/software-engineer-internal-systems-jobs-1831840','scraped','Mar 26, 2026'),(2714,NULL,'job','Software Engineer','Full Time/Permanent','Karachi',NULL,'2 Years',1000000.00,'PKR 1,000,000','Samad Enterprises is seeking a skilled Software Engineer with a minimum of two years of professional experience to join our dynamic development team. The ideal candidate possesses a strong understanding of the Software Development Life Cycle and Agile Methodologies, and demonstrates expertise in Code Review, Unit Testing, and Continuous Integration. This role involves collaborating within a team environment and requires excellent problem-solving skills, attention to detail, and the ability to deliver high-quality software solutions. The Software Engineer will work closely with cross-functional teams to design, develop, test, and maintain software applications that meet business needs. Additionally, the position involves managing a team of five professionals, fostering collaboration, and ensuring that project goals are met efficiently. Responsibilities Develop, test, and maintain software applications following the Software Development Life Cycle and Agile practices. Participate in daily stand-ups, sprint planning, and retrospectives to ensure continuous improvement and delivery. Perform thorough code reviews to maintain code quality and adherence to company standards. Write and execute unit tests to identify and fix defects early in the development process. Implement Continuous Integration pipelines to automate build, test, and deployment processes. Collaborate with team members to analyze requirements, design solutions, and troubleshoot issues. Lead and guide a team of five software professionals, providing technical direction and support. Ensure that all software development activities meet project timelines and quality expectations. Document software designs, coding standards, and test plans for reference and compliance purposes. Communicate progress and challenges effectively with stakeholders and adapt to evolving project requirements.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Samad Enterprises','https://www.rozee.pk/samad-enterprises-software-engineer-karachi-jobs-1831758','scraped','Mar 25, 2026'),(2715,NULL,'job','Dynamics 365 Customer Engagement Engineer','Full Time/Permanent','Lahore',NULL,'5 Years',400000.00,'Rs. 350,000 - 450,000','The Division Dot.cy - We are a global leading provider of world-class software solutions, built on the powerful ecosystem of Microsoft Dynamics 365. Since our foundation in 1999, we have served more than 200 clients in their digital transformation, improving their processes, products, and customer experiences. The Position We are looking for Dynamics 365 Customer Engagement Engineer who will participate in the development of our two products, dot.Ticketing ( www.dotticketing.com ) or dot.Hospitality ( www.dothospitality.com ). This position will entail working together with the rest of the development team of dot.Ticketing and dot.Hospitality which is distributed in Cyprus, Greece, and UAE. We will select which resource will work on which product depending on the interview results. Each resource will work on only 1 product. The chosen individual will work out of the Contour Software Karachi/Lahore/Islamabad resource center office, as an extension of the division-based R&D department. Roles and Responsibilities: Extend Dynamics 365 Customer Engagement platform using MS Dynamics SDK and .NET Framework. Use satellite products from the Dynamics 365 family to provide solutions to clients. Design and develop robust, scalable, high performing, high-volume production applications with users across the globe. Provide front-end Dynamics 365 development capabilities using known JavaScript Frameworks. Follow Microsoft development standards and best practices. Integrate Dynamics 365 with other systems and applications. Perform unit testing prior to deploying solution on test environment for quality assurance. Experience with MAUI and/or Xamarin technologies will be considered as an additional advantage. Required Skills: 5+ year experience on related stack. Software development skills with 5+ years of experience using .NET framework and Dynamics 365 CE. Technical proficiency in development of web services. Hands on object-oriented development experience in a Microsoft stack development environment primarily using C# in Visual Studio. Working experience in HTML5, CSS3, jQuery and with known JavaScript frameworks like AngularJS will be considered as an advantage. Understanding of UI, cross-browser compatibility, general web functions and standards. Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills. Good English knowledge, written and oral. Exciting Benefits we offer: Market-leading Salary Medical Coverage – Self & Dependents Parents Medical Coverage Provident Fund Employee Performance-based bonuses Home Internet Subsidy Conveyance Allowance Profit Sharing Plan [Tenured Employees Only] Life Benefit Child Care Facility Company Provided Lunch/Dinner Professional Development Budget Recreational area for in-house games Sporadic On-shore training opportunities Friendly work environment Leave Encashment','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Contour Software','https://www.rozee.pk/contour-software-dynamics-365-customer-engagement-engineer-jobs-1542088.php','scraped','Oct 29, 2024'),(2716,NULL,'job','Software Engineer .NETAngular','First Shift (Day)','All Cities',NULL,'2 Years',0.00,NULL,'We empower financial institutions to become leaders in digital transformation. As a globally recognized professional team, we collaborate with top-tier clients on innovative and exciting projects, fostering an environment where continuous learning and growth are part of the daily experience. Every contribution, whether through code, ideas, or teamwork, is valued and celebrated. We seek candidates who align with our core values, possess the necessary skills, and are passionate about shaping the digital future of finance alongside us. Key Responsibilities - Collaborate with cross-functional teams to design, develop, and implement cutting-edge digital solutions for financial institutions. - Write clean, efficient, and maintainable code while adhering to best practices and coding standards. - Participate actively in code reviews, providing constructive feedback and ensuring high-quality deliverables. - Troubleshoot, debug, and resolve technical issues in a timely manner. - Engage in continuous learning to stay updated with emerging technologies and industry trends. - Contribute to the overall improvement of development processes and team collaboration. - Communicate effectively with clients and internal stakeholders to understand requirements and deliver solutions that meet business objectives. Required Qualifications - Proven experience in software development within the financial services sector or a related industry. - Strong proficiency in relevant programming languages and frameworks. - Solid understanding of software development lifecycle, agile methodologies, and version control systems. - Excellent problem-solving skills and attention to detail. - Ability to work collaboratively in a diverse, global team environment. - Strong communication skills, both verbal and written. - Passion for innovation and continuous improvement in technology and processes. Preferred Qualifications and Benefits - Experience working with cloud platforms and modern DevOps practices. - Familiarity with digital banking platforms, fintech solutions, or blockchain technologies. - Opportunities for professional development and career growth within a global organization. - Exposure to cutting-edge projects that drive the future of digital finance. - A supportive and inclusive workplace culture that celebrates success and encourages learning. Join us to be part of a dynamic team where your skills and passion will contribute to transforming the financial industry through technology. Together, we build the digital future of finance.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Naseeb Enterprise Inc','https://www.rozee.pk/software-engineer-netangular-jobs-1831388','scraped','Mar 25, 2026'),(2717,NULL,'job','Senior Elastic Search Engineer','Full Time/Permanent','Multiple Cities',NULL,'7 Years',250000.00,'Rs. 200,000 - 300,000','THE POSITION: A Senior Elastic Search Engineer is responsible for helping to architect, design, and implement key features and components in our AWS mission-critical platform by building micro-services and designing serverless applications in AWS to support our real estate data business. From a technical perspective, this role requires working with many of the major AWS offerings including services, such as Lambda, Step Functions, Kinesis, Dynamo, Redshift, Scaling EC2 and CloudWatc h as examples. An understanding of Serverless design patterns and how and when to implement auto-scaling to ensure optimal throughput is essential. Aside from the architecture and design, a Sr. Cloud Engineer must be an AWS cloud evangelist who loves teaching, mentoring and growing the talent around him/her. A team leader who enjoys making the team around him or her better. Leads by example. Lastly, at times this role will require someone to lead a project and small team for the sake of building or enhancing a particular product or feature. This means working on a new project from initiation, design, architecture, planning, estimating, tracking and helping others on the team see the vision and develop in unison as a cohesive team that delivers incremental customer usable features on-time. JOB RESPONSIBILITIES: Help oversee architecture of real estate data pipeline. Develop pipeline components that are scalable, reliable and efficient. Continual oversight of the overall architecture ensuring the overall system doesn\'t erode or become overly complex as time passes and features are added. Perform Project and Team lead duties as needed for new core features. Code reviews, mentoring and coaching teammates to understand and implement AWS best practices in line with an &quot;AWS Well-Architected Framework” . Provide feedback and constructive critiques resulting in optimum performance and system design . Continual tracking of component and overall system performance by applying and automating application and performance best practice testing, monitoring and reporting. P rovide input and recommendations on managing costs within our AWS infrastructure at micro and macro levels. JOB QUALIFICATIONS We are seeking a Sr. Cloud Engineer that has familiarity with AWS Serverless architectures and has 4+ years of systems engineering/administration experience with Elastic Search. Candidate must have experience which demonstrates an understanding software design as it relates to Elasticsearch or OpenSearch deployments, indexing and querying. Estimated 50/50 split between general AWS and Elastic Search development. 5+ years of professional coding experience with 3+ years in cloud services. Experience in major AWS event-driven, compute and database solutions, including but not limited to: Lambda, OpenSearch, Step Functions, SQS, Dynamo, Aurora and/or RDS (candidates with experience in both NoSQL and relational are preferred) C#/.Net Framework experience preferred. Understanding of developing microservices in AWS. Understanding of CI/CD principles. 4+ years of experience with Elastic Stack cluster architecture, design and deployment. 2+ years of working with and understanding software design as it relates to Elasticsearch deployments or distributed computing / system architecture. Reporting and alerting tools such as Grafana, Kibana, Cloudwatch, Quicksight etc. Exciting Benefits we offer: Market-leading Salary Medical Coverage – Self & Dependents Parents Medical Coverage Provident Fund Employee Performance-based bonuses Home Internet Subsidy Conveyance Allowance Profit Sharing Plan [Tenured Employees Only] Life Benefit Child Care Facility Company Provided Lunch/Dinner Professional Development Budget Recreational area for in-house games Sporadic On-shore training opportunities Friendly work environment Leave Encashment Exciting Benefits we offer: Market-leading Salary Medical Coverage – Self & Dependents Parents Medical Coverage Provident Fund Employee Performance-based bonuses Home Internet Subsidy Conveyance Allowance Profit Sharing Plan [Tenured Employees Only] Life Benefit Child Care Facility Company Provided Lunch/Dinner Professional Development Budget Recreational area for in-house games Sporadic On-shore training opportunities Friendly work environment Leave Encashment','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Contour Software','https://www.rozee.pk/contour-software-senior-elastic-search-engineer-jobs-1427941.php','scraped','Oct 27, 2023'),(2718,NULL,'job','Senior Software Engineer I - iOS','First Shift (Day)','All Cities',NULL,'2 Years',0.00,NULL,'Careem is a leading technology platform dedicated to building the Everything App for the greater Middle East, making everyday tasks such as transportation, food and grocery delivery, and payment management seamless and accessible. Since its inception in 2012, Careem has empowered over 2.5 million Captains (drivers) to earn a livelihood, simplified the lives of more than 70 million customers, and fostered a thriving ecosystem for the region’s top talent and entrepreneurs. Operating across 70+ cities in 10 countries—from Morocco to Pakistan—Careem is committed to solving complex regional challenges at scale while delivering exceptional experiences to Customers, Captains, and Merchants. Joining Careem means working with cutting-edge technology alongside a diverse and talented team spread across multiple geographies. Applicants will be considered for various roles within the company, ensuring alignment with their career goals and personal preferences. As a full-time team member, you will have the opportunity to make a meaningful impact in the region while advancing your professional growth. Key Responsibilities - Collaborate with cross-functional teams to design, develop, and implement innovative solutions that enhance user experience and operational efficiency. - Analyze complex problems and provide scalable, high-quality technical solutions that meet business requirements. - Participate actively in code reviews, testing, and debugging to maintain high standards of software quality. - Contribute to the continuous improvement of development processes and best practices within the team. - Engage with stakeholders to gather requirements, provide updates, and ensure alignment throughout the project lifecycle. - Mentor junior team members and foster a collaborative and inclusive work environment. Required Qualifications - Proven experience in software development with strong proficiency in relevant programming languages and frameworks. - Solid understanding of software engineering principles, data structures, algorithms, and design patterns. - Experience working in agile environments and familiarity with continuous integration and deployment practices. - Ability to analyze and solve complex technical problems efficiently. - Strong communication skills and the ability to work effectively in a multicultural, cross-functional team. - Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience. Preferred Qualifications and Benefits - Experience working in fast-paced, high-growth technology companies or startups is highly desirable. - Knowledge of the Middle Eastern market and regional challenges is a plus. - Exposure to cloud platforms, microservices architecture, and scalable system design will be advantageous. - Opportunity to work with a diverse and talented team across multiple countries. - Access to continuous learning and development programs to support career growth. - Chance to contribute to impactful projects that improve millions of lives in the region. Careem offers a dynamic and inclusive work environment where innovation and collaboration are encouraged. By joining the team, you will be part of a mission-driven organization focused on simplifying and improving everyday life across the Middle East.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Naseeb Enterprise Inc','https://www.rozee.pk/senior-software-engineer-i-ios-jobs-1834292','scraped','Mar 31, 2026'),(2719,NULL,'job','Java Software Engineer','First Shift (Day)','Multan',NULL,'2 Years',0.00,NULL,'Systems Limited is seeking experienced Senior Developers with strong expertise in Java and AWS to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidates will have between 5 to 10 years of hands-on experience in delivering high-quality software solutions. They should possess deep knowledge of their domain and demonstrate the ability to meet project requirements effectively while maintaining best practices in software development. Key Responsibilities - Design, develop, and maintain scalable Java-based applications leveraging AWS cloud services. - Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define, design, and ship new features. - Ensure the performance, quality, and responsiveness of applications. - Identify and correct bottlenecks and fix bugs to improve application performance. - Participate in code reviews, provide constructive feedback, and mentor junior developers. - Stay updated with emerging technologies and apply them to improve development processes. - Work closely with product owners and stakeholders to understand requirements and translate them into technical solutions. - Maintain documentation related to system design, architecture, and code changes. Required Qualifications - 5 to 10 years of professional experience in Java development with a strong grasp of object-oriented programming concepts. - Proven experience working with AWS services such as EC2, S3, Lambda, RDS, and CloudFormation. - Solid understanding of microservices architecture and RESTful API design. - Experience with containerization technologies like Docker and orchestration tools such as Kubernetes is highly desirable. - Proficient in database management and writing optimized SQL queries. - Familiarity with CI/CD pipelines and automation tools to streamline deployment processes. - Strong problem-solving skills and ability to work independently or as part of a team. - Excellent communication skills to effectively collaborate with technical and non-technical stakeholders. Preferred Qualifications and Benefits - Experience with Agile methodologies and working in Scrum teams. - Knowledge of front-end technologies such as Angular, React, or Vue.js is a plus. - Exposure to monitoring and logging tools like CloudWatch, ELK stack, or Prometheus. - Opportunity to work on cutting-edge cloud technologies and large-scale enterprise projects. - Supportive work environment encouraging continuous learning and professional growth. - Competitive compensation package aligned with industry standards. Candidates who meet the above criteria and are passionate about delivering robust and scalable software solutions are encouraged to apply. Join Systems Limited to be part of a forward-thinking organization that values innovation, quality, and teamwork.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Naseeb Enterprise Inc','https://www.rozee.pk/java-software-engineer-multan-jobs-1841706','scraped','Apr 17, 2026'),(2720,NULL,'job','Remote Software Engineer (Rust)','First Shift (Day)','All Cities',NULL,'2 Years',0.00,NULL,'We are seeking a motivated professional to contribute to the development of large language model (LLM) evaluation and training datasets aimed at enhancing LLM capabilities in solving realistic software engineering challenges. This role involves creating verifiable software engineering tasks derived from public repository histories using a synthetic approach combined with human-in-the-loop validation. The project focuses on expanding dataset coverage across various programming languages, difficulty levels, and task types to ensure comprehensive training and evaluation. Key Responsibilities - Design and develop verifiable software engineering tasks based on public code repositories. - Implement synthetic data generation methods integrated with human-in-the-loop processes to ensure task quality and accuracy. - Expand dataset diversity by incorporating multiple programming languages and varying levels of task complexity. - Collaborate with cross-functional teams to refine dataset requirements and improve evaluation metrics. - Analyze and validate dataset outputs to maintain high standards of reliability and relevance for LLM training. - Document methodologies and contribute to continuous improvement of dataset creation workflows. Required Qualifications - Strong background in software engineering with hands-on experience in multiple programming languages. - Familiarity with version control systems and public code repositories such as GitHub. - Experience in dataset creation, data annotation, or synthetic data generation techniques. - Understanding of machine learning concepts, particularly related to natural language processing or LLMs. - Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment and communicate technical information effectively. - Detail-oriented mindset with a focus on data quality and verifiability. Preferred Qualifications and Benefits - Experience working with human-in-the-loop systems or crowdsourcing platforms for data validation. - Knowledge of software engineering education or assessment methodologies. - Prior involvement in research or projects related to LLM training or evaluation. - Opportunities for professional growth within an innovative AI research environment. - Exposure to cutting-edge developments in AI and software engineering intersection. This position offers the chance to contribute to pioneering work at the intersection of artificial intelligence and software engineering, helping to build datasets that enable LLMs to better understand and solve real-world coding problems.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Naseeb Enterprise Inc','https://www.rozee.pk/remote-software-engineer-rust-jobs-1834854','scraped','Apr 02, 2026'),(2721,NULL,'job','Associate Software Engineer (C)','First Shift (Day)','All Cities',NULL,'2 Years',0.00,NULL,'We are seeking an Associate Software Engineer with expertise in C++ to join our dynamic development team. This position is ideal for fresh graduates or professionals in the early stages of their careers who possess a strong passion for programming and problem-solving. The role involves contributing to software development projects within the Exploration & Production (E&P) industry, working collaboratively in an agile environment that follows Microsoft coding standards. Key Responsibilities - Develop and maintain software applications tailored for the E&P sector. - Collaborate effectively within an agile team to design, code, test, and deploy software solutions. - Adhere to Microsoft coding standards and best practices to ensure high-quality and maintainable code. - Participate in code reviews and contribute to continuous improvement of development processes. - Troubleshoot and resolve software defects and issues in a timely manner. - Document software designs, processes, and updates clearly for team reference. Required Qualifications - Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field. - Proficiency in C++ programming language with a solid understanding of object-oriented principles. - Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with attention to detail. - Familiarity with agile software development methodologies. - Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment and communicate effectively. - Basic understanding of software development lifecycle and version control systems. Preferred Qualifications and Benefits - Internship or project experience related to software development in the E&P or similar industries. - Knowledge of Microsoft coding standards and development tools. - Exposure to additional programming languages or frameworks is a plus. - Opportunity to grow professionally within a supportive and innovative team. - Gain hands-on experience working on real-world applications impacting the energy sector. This role offers a valuable opportunity for early-career professionals to develop their technical skills and contribute meaningfully to software solutions in a specialized industry. Candidates who are eager to learn and grow in a collaborative setting will find this position rewarding.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Naseeb Enterprise Inc','https://www.rozee.pk/associate-software-engineer-c-jobs-1834336','scraped','Mar 31, 2026'),(2722,NULL,'job','Software Quality Assurance Engineer','First Shift (Day)','All Cities',NULL,'2 Years',0.00,NULL,'ICIL Technologies is a forward-thinking company at the forefront of automation and artificial intelligence, dedicated to transforming how businesses function in today’s digital landscape. With a strong emphasis on innovation and client-centric solutions, ICIL focuses on simplifying complex business processes while delivering significant strategic advantages. Central to its product suite is BOTeye, a cutting-edge platform that integrates Robotic Process Automation (RPA), Agentic Automation, and AI capabilities. This platform empowers organizations to automate not only routine, rule-based tasks but also sophisticated decision-making processes, advancing beyond conventional automation methods. Key Responsibilities - Develop, implement, and maintain automation solutions using BOTeye and related technologies to enhance operational efficiency. - Collaborate with cross-functional teams to analyze business processes and identify automation opportunities. - Design and execute test cases to ensure the quality and reliability of automation workflows. - Troubleshoot and resolve issues related to automation tools and processes in a timely manner. - Document automation processes, configurations, and updates to maintain clear records for future reference. - Stay updated with the latest trends and advancements in RPA, AI, and automation technologies to continuously improve solutions. - Provide training and support to end-users and stakeholders to facilitate smooth adoption of automation tools. Required Qualifications - Proven experience in Robotic Process Automation (RPA) development and deployment, preferably with hands-on expertise in BOTeye or similar platforms. - Strong understanding of automation frameworks, scripting languages, and workflow design. - Ability to analyze complex business processes and translate them into effective automation solutions. - Excellent problem-solving skills with a detail-oriented approach to troubleshooting automation issues. - Effective communication skills to work collaboratively with technical and non-technical teams. - Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, or a related field. Preferred Qualifications and Benefits - Experience with AI-driven automation and agentic automation technologies is highly desirable. - Familiarity with software testing methodologies and quality assurance practices. - Exposure to cloud platforms and integration of automation solutions within cloud environments. - Opportunity to work in a dynamic, innovation-driven environment focused on cutting-edge automation technologies. - Access to continuous learning and professional development programs to enhance technical skills. - Collaborative culture that values creativity, initiative, and client-focused solutions. This role offers a unique chance to contribute to the evolution of automation technology within a company that values innovation and strategic impact. Candidates passionate about leveraging AI and automation to solve complex business challenges will find this position rewarding and growth-oriented.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Naseeb Enterprise Inc','https://www.rozee.pk/software-quality-assurance-engineer-jobs-1837824','scraped','Apr 09, 2026'),(2723,NULL,'job','Software Engineer III - PHP','First Shift (Day)','Lahore',NULL,'2 Years',0.00,NULL,'TCP is seeking motivated professionals to join our team and contribute to delivering innovative workforce management solutions. With over 30 years of experience, TCP provides flexible, mobile timekeeping and employee management technology trusted by tens of thousands of customers across public and private sectors. Our solutions support complex timekeeping, scheduling, and leave management needs, backed by personalized service. As we continue to grow, we invite you to be part of a forward-thinking company dedicated to helping organizations engage their people effectively. Please note that TCP is committed to diversity and inclusion; however, we are unable to sponsor visas for this position. Key Responsibilities - Develop, implement, and maintain workforce management software solutions that meet client requirements. - Collaborate with cross-functional teams including sales, support, and product development to ensure seamless delivery of services. - Provide technical expertise and support during the sales process, including product demonstrations and responding to client inquiries. - Troubleshoot and resolve software issues, ensuring timely and effective solutions to maintain customer satisfaction. - Participate in continuous improvement initiatives to enhance product functionality and user experience. - Document technical specifications, processes, and procedures to support internal knowledge sharing and client training. - Stay current with industry trends and emerging technologies to contribute innovative ideas and maintain competitive advantage. Required Qualifications - Proven experience in software development or technical roles within workforce management or related industries. - Strong understanding of timekeeping, employee scheduling, and leave management systems. - Proficiency in relevant programming languages and software development tools. - Excellent problem-solving skills with the ability to troubleshoot complex technical issues. - Effective communication skills to interact with clients and internal teams. - Ability to work independently and collaboratively in a fast-paced environment. - Commitment to delivering high-quality solutions and exceptional customer service. Preferred Qualifications and Benefits - Experience working with cloud-based workforce management platforms. - Familiarity with integration of third-party systems and APIs. - Knowledge of compliance and labor laws related to timekeeping and employee management. - TCP offers a dynamic work environment with opportunities for professional growth. - Access to cutting-edge technology and resources to support your career development. - A culture that values diversity, inclusion, and teamwork. Join TCP and contribute to shaping the future of workforce management technology. We look forward to welcoming talented individuals who are passionate about making a difference in how organizations manage their most valuable asset—their people.','2026-05-07 01:37:34','open',0,'Naseeb Enterprise Inc','https://www.rozee.pk/software-engineer-iii-php-lahore-jobs-1834610','scraped','Apr 01, 2026');
